de2c49e3-6abd-4352-82d5-1654b5f7bdae Preheat the oven to 450°.
de2c49e3-6abd-4352-82d5-1654b5f7bdae In a large bowl rub down the lamb with olive oil, salt, coriander cumin, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, and pepper until all sides of the leg of lamb are covered.
de2c49e3-6abd-4352-82d5-1654b5f7bdae Next, place the leg of lamb in a Reynolds Kitchens® 10lb Roaster pan, place it on a sheet pan, and bake in the oven for 30 minutes.
de2c49e3-6abd-4352-82d5-1654b5f7bdae After 30 minutes of cooking on 450° turn down the heat to 350° and finish cooking the lamb for 30 minutes or until it has an internal temperature of 145°. Remove the lamb from the oven and let the meat rest for 10 to 15 minutes.
de2c49e3-6abd-4352-82d5-1654b5f7bdae Slice the leg of lamb before serving.
c6ff9a3f-f5b6-4c33-8282-e756bc3a453f Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.
c6ff9a3f-f5b6-4c33-8282-e756bc3a453f In a microwave safe bowl, add the butter, sugar, cocoa powder, and salt. Microwave in 20 second increments, stirring after each time, until butter is completely melted. Set aside for 5 minutes to cool slightly. Mix will be very grainy.
c6ff9a3f-f5b6-4c33-8282-e756bc3a453f After the mixture has cooled, stir in the vanilla extract. Next, add the egg and beat until it is fully incorporated. Add the flour and mix until just combined, careful not to over mix.
c6ff9a3f-f5b6-4c33-8282-e756bc3a453f Pour the brownie batter into Reynolds Kitchens® 9x13 Dessert Pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
1bb576a0-4e2f-4fe7-8f12-c69f980f1905 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside of a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
1bb576a0-4e2f-4fe7-8f12-c69f980f1905 PLACE onions evenly in liner. Place beef on top of onions. SPRINKLE beef with garlic powder and onion powder, if desired. MIX barbecue sauce, steak sauce and Worcestershire sauce; pour evenly over beef. Place lid on slow cooker.
1bb576a0-4e2f-4fe7-8f12-c69f980f1905 COOK on LOW for 8 to 10 hours or HIGH for 4 to 5 hours until beef is tender.
1bb576a0-4e2f-4fe7-8f12-c69f980f1905 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. PLACE roast on cooking board and shred with 2 forks, or slice thinly and chop, if you prefer. Stir in additional barbecue sauce, if desired. Serve shredded beef on buns. Add sliced red onion, Cole slaw, dill pickles and carrot sticks, if desired.
1bb576a0-4e2f-4fe7-8f12-c69f980f1905 REMOVE all food and juices from lined-slow cooker. COOL slow cooker completely. Do not lift or transport liner with food or liquids inside. Remove empty liner and toss.
3a5a0f70-c443-4481-850b-c616df2e741d RINSE chicken under cold water; pat dry.
3a5a0f70-c443-4481-850b-c616df2e741d COMBINE Italian salad dressing, lemon juice, honey, Worcestershire sauce and paprika in a plastic zipper bag. Reserve 1/2 cup marinade for basting chicken during grilling. Add chicken. Close the bag and turn to coat chicken. Marinate 1 hour, turning chicken once. Remove chicken from marinade and discard marinade.
3a5a0f70-c443-4481-850b-c616df2e741d PREHEAT grill to medium. Tear off a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil long enough to cover grill grate. Make drainage holes in sheet foil with a large grilling fork.
3a5a0f70-c443-4481-850b-c616df2e741d PLACE aluminum foil sheet with holes on grill rack; immediately place chicken on aluminum foil.
3a5a0f70-c443-4481-850b-c616df2e741d GRILL chicken 5 minutes; turn. Continue grilling and turning every 5 minutes until chicken is tender and reaches 180°F, about 30 minutes. Brush with reserved marinade during last 5 minutes grilling time.
25cb9a98-aa7e-4a2f-a64c-50a22bdb574a PREHEAT oven to 425°F.
25cb9a98-aa7e-4a2f-a64c-50a22bdb574a LINE a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil.
25cb9a98-aa7e-4a2f-a64c-50a22bdb574a PREPARE stuffing mix following package directions. Stir in apple and cranberries. Spread stuffing evenly in aluminum foil-lined pan.
25cb9a98-aa7e-4a2f-a64c-50a22bdb574a PLACE chops on top of stuffing; sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
25cb9a98-aa7e-4a2f-a64c-50a22bdb574a MIX brown sugar and butter; brush onto chops.
25cb9a98-aa7e-4a2f-a64c-50a22bdb574a BAKE 20 to 22 minutes or until chops are done.
b4a34c82-3932-40dc-98de-b0e23e1eba02 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
b4a34c82-3932-40dc-98de-b0e23e1eba02 PLACE chicken in slow cooker liner. Place onions and bell peppers on top of chicken.
b4a34c82-3932-40dc-98de-b0e23e1eba02 MIX salsa, fajita seasoning mix and cayenne pepper in a medium bowl. Pour over chicken. Place lid on slow cooker.
b4a34c82-3932-40dc-98de-b0e23e1eba02 COOK on LOW for 6 to 7 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours until chicken is done.
b4a34c82-3932-40dc-98de-b0e23e1eba02 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Gently stir chicken and sauce with a plastic or wooden slotted spoon. Spoon 1/2 cup of chicken mixture into center of each tortilla; add desired toppings and fold tortilla over filling. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
0e6c67f8-6375-4847-bb3f-d0ec4ba7cc5a PREHEAT oven to 450°F. Line 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
0e6c67f8-6375-4847-bb3f-d0ec4ba7cc5a COMBINE black beans, corn, tomatoes and onion; season to taste. Add ½ cup chipotle marinade. Spoon into aluminum foil-lined pan
0e6c67f8-6375-4847-bb3f-d0ec4ba7cc5a PLACE chicken breasts on top of vegetables; season to taste. Spoon remaining ¼ cup chipotle marinade on chicken breasts. Cover pan with a sheet of aluminum foil; crimp to seal edges.
0e6c67f8-6375-4847-bb3f-d0ec4ba7cc5a BAKE 22 to 26 minutes or until chicken registers 170°F. on thermometer. Top with Southwest Dressing and garnish as desired.
0e6c67f8-6375-4847-bb3f-d0ec4ba7cc5a THE REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: To serve as a salad, spoon black bean salsa over salad greens, top with diagonally sliced chicken strips, Southwest Dressing and garnishes.
387d6dd7-1500-4c2e-bf99-8d076008d1df Sprinkle the cutting board with a little flour and roll out the dough into a pizza crust.
387d6dd7-1500-4c2e-bf99-8d076008d1df Oil the top of the dough and make sure the oil covers the entire surface.
387d6dd7-1500-4c2e-bf99-8d076008d1df Get the grill ready for direct grilling with an internal temperature of 375–425 degrees F.
387d6dd7-1500-4c2e-bf99-8d076008d1df Place a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil down on the grill, non-stick side up. Place the pizza crust on the foil, oiled side down. Oil the unoiled top of the pizza and wait.
387d6dd7-1500-4c2e-bf99-8d076008d1df When the crust starts to bubble, peek at the bottom to check for browning. Once it browns on the bottom, remove the pizza crust from the grill and place it on a cutting board, browned side up.
387d6dd7-1500-4c2e-bf99-8d076008d1df Apply all toppings and place back on the grill, oiled side down.
387d6dd7-1500-4c2e-bf99-8d076008d1df Close the lid for a few minutes, checking after 3-4 minutes to see if the bottom has browned and then every 60 seconds after that until the bottom is browned.
387d6dd7-1500-4c2e-bf99-8d076008d1df Once the bottom browns, the toppings should be warm and the cheese melted, so remove from the heat, slice and serve.
7761755b-0dd2-45dc-b470-922e5aa12ce2 Mix 1 teaspoon of Gum-Tex powder with 4 tablespoons of boiling water (added 1 tbsp. at a time) and your choice of food coloring. We recommend a combination of liquid food coloring and liquid pearl sheen for the brightest colors. TIP: You can quadruple the batter for a larger batch. You’ll need approximately 12 – 16 individual batches to fully cover a 16-pound turkey. Mix Gum-Tex powder, boiling water and food coloring thoroughly with a rubber or silicone spatula. Mix until you get a paste-like consistency, approximately three – five minutes.
7761755b-0dd2-45dc-b470-922e5aa12ce2 Once mixed to a paste-like consistency, spread out on foil-lined baking sheet. Spread the mixture out into a thin layer as best as you can along the foil-lined sheet. Bake in a pre-heated oven at 275°F for about 30 minutes, or until the mixture is completely dried out and hard.
7761755b-0dd2-45dc-b470-922e5aa12ce2 Once the mixture has dried and cooled, break up into pieces and place into a clean coffee grinder or food processer. Pulse until pieces are grinded. Place a sieve over a bowl and pour the mixture into the sieve. Shake the sieve to separate the smaller pieces from the larger pieces. Place larger pieces back into the grinder. Repeat until you have enough to completely cover your turkey. You’ll need approximately 12 – 16 individually baked batches to fully cover a 16-pound turkey.
7761755b-0dd2-45dc-b470-922e5aa12ce2 Preheat oven to 325°F. Line roasting pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil.
7761755b-0dd2-45dc-b470-922e5aa12ce2 Remove neck and giblets from turkey; rinse turkey and pat dry. Place turkey in foil-lined roasting pan. If stuffing is desired, loosely stuff turkey.
7761755b-0dd2-45dc-b470-922e5aa12ce2 Brush turkey with oil and insert meat thermometer into thickest part of thigh, not touching bone. Sprinkle the glitter on top of the turkey, covering it completely.
7761755b-0dd2-45dc-b470-922e5aa12ce2 Make a foil tent by placing a sheet of foil over turkey, leaving 1 inch between top of turkey and foil tent for heat circulation. Crimp foil onto long sides of pan.
7761755b-0dd2-45dc-b470-922e5aa12ce2 Roast turkey until meat thermometer inserted in thickest part of the thigh not touching the bone reads a temperature of 165°F. For approximate roasting times see chart below. For stuffed turkey, add 30 minutes to roasting time.
7761755b-0dd2-45dc-b470-922e5aa12ce2 To brown turkey, remove foil tent after 1 hour of roasting. For easy slicing, cover turkey with foil and let stand 15 minutes.
702297a4-4573-4c26-9090-7f4b8904b48b Preheat oven at 325°F.
702297a4-4573-4c26-9090-7f4b8904b48b Place ranch-flavored corn chips in a food processor and process until fully crushed. You can also add to a zip top bag and roll with a rolling pin until chips are completely crushed.
702297a4-4573-4c26-9090-7f4b8904b48b Brush oil or butter on turkey and coat with the crushed chips.
702297a4-4573-4c26-9090-7f4b8904b48b Tear off a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil 2 1/2 times longer than turkey. Place turkey lengthwise in center of foil sheet.
702297a4-4573-4c26-9090-7f4b8904b48b Close foil loosely by overlapping the ends. Turn up short sides of foil to hold in juices. Do not seal airtight. Place foil wrapped turkey in roasting pan at least 2 inches deep. Insert meat thermometer through foil into thickest part of inner thigh, not touching bone.
702297a4-4573-4c26-9090-7f4b8904b48b Roast turkey until meat thermometer reads 180°F. For approximate roasting times, see chart above. For stuffed turkey, add 30 minutes to roasting time. To brown turkey, open and turn back foil 30 minutes before roasting is finished. For easy slicing, cover turkey with foil and let stand 15 minutes.
c8fe733b-10c8-4162-8991-a9fb90d47a39 OPEN Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
c8fe733b-10c8-4162-8991-a9fb90d47a39 MIX brown sugar, paprika, seasoned salt, pepper and onion powder; rub mixture into ribs. Cut ribs into 4-rib sections. Place ribs in slow cooker liner. Pour 1/2 cup barbecue sauce over ribs. Place lid on slow cooker.
c8fe733b-10c8-4162-8991-a9fb90d47a39 COOK on LOW for 5 to 6 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours. Remove ribs using tongs or large spatula. Using ladle or large plastic spoon, remove and discard juices. Place ribs back into slow cooker liner; pour remaining barbecue sauce over ribs. Cook additional hour or until sauce is heated.
c8fe733b-10c8-4162-8991-a9fb90d47a39 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve ribs directly from slow cooker liner. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
59943384-ba45-4446-a326-8829a9344e9d PREHEAT the oven to 425°
59943384-ba45-4446-a326-8829a9344e9d SEASON the inside of the chicken cavity with salt and pepper and stuff the lemon wedges in side. Tie together the chicken legs with butchers twine to stop the lemon edges from falling out.
59943384-ba45-4446-a326-8829a9344e9d In a large bowl rub down the roasting chicken with olive oil, garlic, thyme, oregano, zest of 1 lemon, salt and pepper until all sides of the chicken are covered.
59943384-ba45-4446-a326-8829a9344e9d Next, place the chicken in a Reynolds Kitchens® 10lb Roaster pan, place it on a sheet pan, and bake in the oven for 30 minutes.
59943384-ba45-4446-a326-8829a9344e9d After 30 minutes of cooking on 425° turn down the heat to 350° and finish cooking the chicken for 60 minutes or until it is cooked throughout.
59943384-ba45-4446-a326-8829a9344e9d SLICE the chicken before serving.
fb82be69-6deb-4ba2-ba79-76fed99d3cec PREHEAT the oven to 325°.
fb82be69-6deb-4ba2-ba79-76fed99d3cec PLACE the ham in a Reynolds Kitchens® 10lb Roaster Pan, and place it on a sheet pan, and press each clove into the ham 1 inch apart from each other covering all sides of the ham.
fb82be69-6deb-4ba2-ba79-76fed99d3cec Next, in a small sized saucepot add the pineapple juice, brown sugar, and honey and whisk until combined. Place the saucepot on a burner on high heat for 12 to 15 minutes or until the liquid is reduced by half.
fb82be69-6deb-4ba2-ba79-76fed99d3cec Once the pineapple glaze is done cooking, whisk in the butter and baste the ham on all sides reserving some to baste throughout the cooking process as well as serving alongside once the ham is finished.
fb82be69-6deb-4ba2-ba79-76fed99d3cec PLACE ham in the bakeware pan on the sheet pan in the oven and cook for 90 minutes, while continuing to baste with the pineapple glaze through out the cooking process.
fb82be69-6deb-4ba2-ba79-76fed99d3cec Once finished, let the ham rest for 10 minutes and slice before serving.
908df677-f365-457a-9586-a51ab0aaf9f5 PREHEAT the oven to 375°
908df677-f365-457a-9586-a51ab0aaf9f5 In a large bowl whisk together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt and set aside. Once combined add in the shredded carrots and toss until the carrots are coated. Set the bowl aside.
908df677-f365-457a-9586-a51ab0aaf9f5 In a separate large bowl whisk together the eggs and yogurt, followed by whisking in the sugars and vegetable oil. Once combined fold the mixture into the large flour bowl until just combined.
908df677-f365-457a-9586-a51ab0aaf9f5 Next, pour the carrot cake batter into a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Dessert Pan and bake in the oven for 40 minutes. After cooking for 40 minutes on 375° turn the heat down to 325° and bake for 15 minutes. Once it is done cooking remove the pan from the oven and completely cool on a rack.
908df677-f365-457a-9586-a51ab0aaf9f5 Butter Cream Frosting: In a standing mixer with the paddle attachment, whip the butter until it becomes light and fluffy. Next, add in the powdered sugar and whip until the butter and sugar are completely combined. Next, add in the vanilla and milk and mix until combined.
908df677-f365-457a-9586-a51ab0aaf9f5 Ice the carrot cake with the buttercream and serve.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Preheat the oven to 350° F.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Cream the butter and sugars together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed or using a hand blender on high speed for 5-7 minutes or until light and fluffy.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Pour in the vanilla and add the eggs and mix on medium speed until completely mixed in.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Mix together the flour, cocoa powder, salt, ¼ teaspoon of cayenne pepper, baking soda, and baking powder together in a bowl until combined.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Add the dry ingredients to the stand mixer on low speed and mix until just combined.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Place a 3-tablespoon scoop of the cookie dough onto a cookie sheet tray lined with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® and repeat until all of the dough has been used.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Place the cookies into the oven on the middle rack for 8 minutes.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Remove the cookies and then place as many mini marshmallows that will fit over the top of each cookie gently pressing down to make them stick.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Return the cookies to the oven and bake for an additional 2 minutes.
27f21965-d425-4add-8d2f-c2d1e96ec7b1 Cool the cookies completely on a rack to room temperature and garnish more cayenne pepper and a candy cane.
40d21102-b366-4183-aace-404d7e0186e1 Cream the butter and sugars together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed or using a hand blender on high speed for 5-7 minutes or until light and fluffy.
40d21102-b366-4183-aace-404d7e0186e1 Add in the vanilla on low speed and then add in the flour and mix just until combined.
40d21102-b366-4183-aace-404d7e0186e1 Fold in the chocolate chips and sprinkles using a rubber spatula.
40d21102-b366-4183-aace-404d7e0186e1 Place a 3-tablespoon scoop of the cookie dough into your hands and roll it into a ball.
40d21102-b366-4183-aace-404d7e0186e1 Dip each cookie dough ball using 2 spoons into a bowl of melted chocolate and move around until coated.
40d21102-b366-4183-aace-404d7e0186e1 Place the cookies on a cookie sheet tray lined with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® and repeat until all of the dough has been used.
40d21102-b366-4183-aace-404d7e0186e1 Immediately garnish the tops of each chocolate dough ball with popping candy and cool to room temperature.
d1237472-5ffc-4ce6-a92d-f5d1d9ba3621 PREHEAT oven to 350 degrees. Line a 13x9-inch pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil and set aside.
d1237472-5ffc-4ce6-a92d-f5d1d9ba3621 PULL each cheeseburger apart separating the buns, beef patties, lettuce and pickles. Chop the buns into 1/2 x 1/2-inch pieces and set aside. Chop each beef patty into 6 pieces and set aside. Cover the lettuce and pickles and refrigerate, along with the special sauce until serving.
d1237472-5ffc-4ce6-a92d-f5d1d9ba3621 MELT the butter in a large skillet. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring often for 2 to 3 minutes. Add pickles and cut beef patties and continue cooking for 1 to 2 minutes. Add the stock and continue cooking until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and set aside.
d1237472-5ffc-4ce6-a92d-f5d1d9ba3621 PLACE cut buns into prepared pan. Drizzle the beaten egg on top and toss to coat. Pour the stock mixture on top. Using a spatula, stir mixture to fully coat the bread.
d1237472-5ffc-4ce6-a92d-f5d1d9ba3621 COVER with foil and bake for 25 minutes. Remove foil and bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until top is crisp. Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes.
d1237472-5ffc-4ce6-a92d-f5d1d9ba3621 DRIZZLE with special sauce and garnish with lettuce and pickles before serving.
fd4ee1b2-59db-44b5-a2ed-de9d9f86db1d PREHEAT oven to 350 degrees. Line a 13x9-inch pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and set aside.
fd4ee1b2-59db-44b5-a2ed-de9d9f86db1d PULL each crunchy tortilla wrapped taco apart, separating the ground beef and nacho cheese, tortilla shells, and lettuce tomatoes and sour cream.
fd4ee1b2-59db-44b5-a2ed-de9d9f86db1d PLACE ground beef and nacho cheese into bottom of prepared pan. Cut tortilla shells into 2-inch triangles. Combine with corn tortilla chips and place on top of ground beef mixture. Pour taco sauce on top.
fd4ee1b2-59db-44b5-a2ed-de9d9f86db1d COVER with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil and bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes. Garnish with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes and sour cream before serving.
3a57ab80-fd99-4aab-8304-eeaf7bb9d94e Preheat oven to 350°F.
3a57ab80-fd99-4aab-8304-eeaf7bb9d94e Place the Cheetos® FLAMIN' HOT® in a food processor and process until fully crushed. You can also add to a zip top bag and roll with a rolling pin until sticks are completely crushed.
3a57ab80-fd99-4aab-8304-eeaf7bb9d94e Brush oil or butter on turkey and coat with the crushed chips.
3a57ab80-fd99-4aab-8304-eeaf7bb9d94e Add 1 Tbsp of flour to the Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag and place in a large roasting pan that is at least 2 inches deep.
3a57ab80-fd99-4aab-8304-eeaf7bb9d94e Carefully slide turkey into the oven bag, making sure the opening of the bag is facing the end of the roasting pan, and not facing up. The bag should be inside the pan, not hanging over the edges of the pan. Close oven bag with the included nylon tie, and cut six 1/2 inch slits in the top of the bag.
3a57ab80-fd99-4aab-8304-eeaf7bb9d94e Cook turkey till it reaches 165°F in several places. Remove from oven and let stand in oven bag for 15 minutes or until cool enough to handle.
3a57ab80-fd99-4aab-8304-eeaf7bb9d94e Cut open the top of the bag. Carefully lift turkey from bag and place in a large baking dish or pan with at least 2” sides. Return turkey to oven for 15 to 20 minutes to crisp the coating.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 CREAM together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 WHISK together the egg whites and shredded coconut in a separate bowl.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 ADD in the coconut extract and then the egg whites and shredded coconut mixture in 3 batches into the butter-sugar mixture.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 MIX the flour, baking powder and salt together in a bowl and add into the creamed butter-sugar mixture while alternating with the coconut milk but beginning and ending with the dry ingredients. Be sure to stop and scrape the sides of the bowl often.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 DISTRIBUTE the cake batter evenly into 3 Reynolds Kitchens® Cake Pans.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 BAKE the cake in the oven on 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and firm in the center.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 COOL the cake pans on a cooling rack for 10 to 15 minutes.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 WHIP the butter and cream cheese in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment until light and fluffy.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 ADD in the coconut extract and powdered sugar until completely mixed in.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 TOSS together 1 1/2 cups of the shredded coconut and 4 to 6 drops of green food coloring in a slider bag until the coconut becomes green
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 FROST the cooled coconut cake in layers with a small amount of frosting. After each layer has been frosted sprinkle on ½ cup of shredded coconut and press into the frosting before adding on the next layer of cake.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 FROST the entire outside and top of the cake and use the remaining shredded white coconut to coat the outside of the cake.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 FINISH the top of the layered coconut cake by sprinkling on the green coconut shreds, but take care to not get any of the shreds around the outside.
40f29704-e792-4fc2-8ab5-633dafc5f154 GARNISH the top of the cake with assorted Easter egg candy and chocolate.
aa0dd060-17fd-4a3a-baa5-5fb8e7bfc8ec To Brine: In a large brining vessel, mix equal parts Mountain Dew® and water. For every liter of liquid added, add ¼ cup of kosher salt. Completely immerse turkey in brine and allow to sit overnight refrigerated.
aa0dd060-17fd-4a3a-baa5-5fb8e7bfc8ec Preheat oven to 350°F.
aa0dd060-17fd-4a3a-baa5-5fb8e7bfc8ec Place a Reynolds Kitchens® Turkey Oven Bag into a large roasting pan that is at least two inches deep. Sprinkle one tablespoon of flour into the bag, and shake to distribute.
aa0dd060-17fd-4a3a-baa5-5fb8e7bfc8ec Remove the neck and giblets from the turkey. Then rinse, and pat dry. If you like to stuff your turkey, place stuffing into cavity. Brush the turkey with oil or melted butter and season as desired.
aa0dd060-17fd-4a3a-baa5-5fb8e7bfc8ec Place turkey in the Turkey Oven Bag and close the bag with the nylon tie included within the Oven Bag box (It’s usually folded inside the cooking chart.)
aa0dd060-17fd-4a3a-baa5-5fb8e7bfc8ec Make 6 half-inch slits in the top of the bag, to allow steam to escape as the turkey cooks. Tuck corners of the bag in the pan and trim or fold down the end of the bag to make sure it doesn’t touch the oven or heating elements when it’s cooking.
aa0dd060-17fd-4a3a-baa5-5fb8e7bfc8ec Insert turkey thermometer through one of the cut slits in the top of the bag, into the thickest part of the turkey thigh. Turkey is done cooking when it reaches an internal temperature of 165°F.
aa0dd060-17fd-4a3a-baa5-5fb8e7bfc8ec Remove from oven and let turkey stand in the bag for 15 minutes. Cut the bag open with cooking shears or a paring knife.
aa0dd060-17fd-4a3a-baa5-5fb8e7bfc8ec To remove the turkey from the bag, insert serving forks in the neck and chest cavity of the turkey. Then simply lift your Oven Bag Turkey and transfer to a serving dish for dinner. Use the juices to make flavorful gravy to pair with the moist turkey.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Preheat the oven to 350° F.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Cream the butter and sugars together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed or using a hand blender on high speed for 5-7 minutes or until light and fluffy.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Pour in the vanilla and add the eggs and mix on medium speed until completely mixed in.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Mix together the baking soda, baking powder, flour and mashed ½ cup of potato chips together in a bowl until combined.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Add the dry ingredients to the stand mixer on low speed and mix until just combined.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Place a 3-tablespoon scoop of the cookie dough into your hands and flatten it out using your hand.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Put 1 teaspoon each of jelly and peanut butter into the center of the flattened cookie dough and bring up all the sides to keep the jelly and peanut butter stuffed inside and roll into a ball.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Place the cookies on a cookie sheet tray lined with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® and repeat until all of the dough has been used.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Bake at 350°F for 12 mins.
531eb517-aa19-40eb-ae30-d6db1ece8399 Garnish the top of each cookie with left over mashed potato chips and cool completely on a rack before serving.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Preheat the oven to 350° F.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Cream the butter and sugars together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed or using a hand blender on high speed for 5-7 minutes or until light and fluffy.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Pour in the vanilla and add the eggs and mix on medium speed until completely mixed in.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Mix together the crushed graham crackers, flour, baking soda, and baking powder together in a bowl until combined.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Add the dry ingredients to the stand mixer on low speed and mix until just combined.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Place a 3-tablespoon scoop of the cookie dough into your hands and roll it into a ball.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Place the cookies on a cookie sheet tray lined with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® and repeat until all of the dough has been used.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Bake at 350°F for 8 minutes.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Remove the cookies and then place a large marshmallow onto the top of each cookie gently pressing down to make them stick.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Return the cookies to the oven and bake for an additional 2 minutes.
d999949e-2dab-4d4d-ad24-540f1ceaa617 Finish by pressing a chocolate kiss down on the center of the marshmallow, garnish with a piece of bacon and drizzle with caramel.
df1eb972-3287-41ee-91e9-af545c3d80cd PREHEAT oven to 350°F. LINE 13x9x2-inch baking dish with Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with the non-stick (dull) side facing up towards the food and the shiny side facing the dish; set aside.
df1eb972-3287-41ee-91e9-af545c3d80cd ARRANGE apples evenly in dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar; set aside.
df1eb972-3287-41ee-91e9-af545c3d80cd MIX flour, oats, brown sugar, walnuts and salt in a medium bowl. Cut in butter until well blended. SPRINKLE flour mixture over apples.
df1eb972-3287-41ee-91e9-af545c3d80cd BAKE 40 to 45 minutes, until apples are soft and topping is lightly browned. SERVE warm with ice cream.
56538df3-5c73-47e4-b210-c1ba448bdd3b Preheat oven to 350° and line a 2 quart baking dish with Reynolds Wrap ® Aluminum Foil for easy cleanup and removal.
56538df3-5c73-47e4-b210-c1ba448bdd3b For pudding, cream together sugar and butter. Mix in egg, then add Granny Smith apples.
56538df3-5c73-47e4-b210-c1ba448bdd3b Mix in dry ingredients and pour batter into prepared baking dish.
56538df3-5c73-47e4-b210-c1ba448bdd3b Bake for about 40 minutes, or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
56538df3-5c73-47e4-b210-c1ba448bdd3b Combine butter, sugar and cream in saucepan and cook on low for 10 minutes. Do not boil.
56538df3-5c73-47e4-b210-c1ba448bdd3b Remove sauce from heat and stir in vanilla and nutmeg.
56538df3-5c73-47e4-b210-c1ba448bdd3b Pour sauce over cut pudding squares and enjoy!
e91adaa7-701f-4c03-b599-01cba40ea692 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line cookie sheet with parchment paper.
e91adaa7-701f-4c03-b599-01cba40ea692 Spray oven-safe, metal cookie cutters with non-stick cooking spray, then place on the cookie sheet.
e91adaa7-701f-4c03-b599-01cba40ea692 Fill each cookie cutter with peppermint candies. Break candies into pieces to fill in smaller areas.
e91adaa7-701f-4c03-b599-01cba40ea692 Bake in oven at 350 degrees F for 3–9 minutes until candies melt into cookie cutter shape.
e91adaa7-701f-4c03-b599-01cba40ea692 Remove from oven and let candy harden. Then stretch cookie cutter to remove candy “ornament”.
1e864df0-c8db-4994-90dd-a32b69fe789f Coat an unheated large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Preheat over medium heat. Brown chicken, half at a time, in hot skillet.
1e864df0-c8db-4994-90dd-a32b69fe789f In a 3-1/2- or 4-quart slow cooker, combine frozen artichoke hearts, garlic, and onion.
1e864df0-c8db-4994-90dd-a32b69fe789f In a small bowl, combine broth, rosemary, lemon peel, and pepper. Pour over vegetables in slow cooker. Add browned chicken; spoon some of the garlic mixture over chicken.
1e864df0-c8db-4994-90dd-a32b69fe789f Cover and cook on low-heat setting for 6 to 7 hours or on high-heat setting for 3 to 3-1/2 hours.
1e864df0-c8db-4994-90dd-a32b69fe789f Transfer chicken and artichokes to a serving platter, reserving cooking liquid. Cover chicken and artichokes with foil to keep warm. If using low-heat setting, turn to high-heat setting.
1e864df0-c8db-4994-90dd-a32b69fe789f In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and the cold water. Stir into liquid in slow cooker. Cover and cook about 15 minutes more or until slightly thickened. Spoon sauce over chicken and artichokes. If desired, serve with lemon wedges.
954237d4-d855-47dd-ac0d-ba172eed6110 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high. Cut Alaska salmon fillets crosswise into 1/2 inch strips. Squeeze lime juice over salmon. Combine salmon strips, fajita seasoning and flour; set aside. Combine peppers, onion, beans and salsa.
954237d4-d855-47dd-ac0d-ba172eed6110 CENTER one-fourth of pepper mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Aluminum Foil. Top with salmon strips.
954237d4-d855-47dd-ac0d-ba172eed6110 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
954237d4-d855-47dd-ac0d-ba172eed6110 BAKE 25 to 30 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven or GRILL 9 to 11 minutes in covered grill. Serve with tortillas, additional salsa and cheese.
18e9c70c-7782-4d6d-9b2e-8c130775b731 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. SHAKE flour in Reynolds Oven Bag; place in 13x9-inch baking pan. Add 1/2 cup salsa to bag. Squeeze bag to blend in flour.
18e9c70c-7782-4d6d-9b2e-8c130775b731 COMBINE ground beef with 1/2 cup salsa and other ingredients until well blended. Place in bag, shaping into a 9 x 4-inch loaf.
18e9c70c-7782-4d6d-9b2e-8c130775b731 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
18e9c70c-7782-4d6d-9b2e-8c130775b731 BAKE 1 hour or until firm when top is pressed and meat thermometer reads 165°F. Carefully open bag and spoon remaining salsa on top. Let stand 10 minutes; slice and serve.
abe82d1c-93e2-4388-b513-133d68078cf3 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high. Combine rice, tomatoes, green pepper, celery, onion, Creole seasoning, brown sugar and oregano. Stir in shrimp.
abe82d1c-93e2-4388-b513-133d68078cf3 CENTER one-fourth of mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food.
abe82d1c-93e2-4388-b513-133d68078cf3 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
abe82d1c-93e2-4388-b513-133d68078cf3 BAKE 14 to 16 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven
abe82d1c-93e2-4388-b513-133d68078cf3 OR GRILL 8 to 10 minutes in covered grill.
7ed772f5-482d-4ce6-a4c9-36dd865fe30d Heat oven to 350°F. In large bowl, beat sugar and butter with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and egg; beat well. Add flour and baking powder; stir well.
7ed772f5-482d-4ce6-a4c9-36dd865fe30d Divide dough into equal parts. On lightly floured surface, shape each part into inch roll; place on cookie sheets lined with parchment paper. Using handle of wooden spoon or finger, make depression about 1/2 inch wide and 1/4 inch deep lengthwise down center of each roll. Fill each roll with tablespoons jelly.
7ed772f5-482d-4ce6-a4c9-36dd865fe30d Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool slightly. Cut each baked roll diagonally into cookies. Cool on cooling racks.
0b965e1c-7ac0-429e-88b0-0205bbc7f521 LINE a 5 - 6 quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim. Set aside.
0b965e1c-7ac0-429e-88b0-0205bbc7f521
0b965e1c-7ac0-429e-88b0-0205bbc7f521 BROWN ground beef, bell pepper and onion in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until beef is no longer pink. Drain well. Spoon beef mixture into the lined-slow cooker. Add beans, seasoning mix, tomato sauce, diced tomatoes and green chilies to beef mixture; STIR gently with wooden or plastic spoon.
0b965e1c-7ac0-429e-88b0-0205bbc7f521
0b965e1c-7ac0-429e-88b0-0205bbc7f521 COVER and cook 6 to 7 hours on LOW OR 3 to 3 1/2 hours on HIGH, until hot and bubbly throughout.
0b965e1c-7ac0-429e-88b0-0205bbc7f521
0b965e1c-7ac0-429e-88b0-0205bbc7f521 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Stir gently using a wooden or plastic utensil. Serve food directly from lined slow cooker. Top with cheese and sour cream, if desired. Remove all food and cool slow cooker completely before lifting liner from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.
0b965e1c-7ac0-429e-88b0-0205bbc7f521
7510ec5c-b756-457b-86f8-acb2bfbe81b8 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil.
7510ec5c-b756-457b-86f8-acb2bfbe81b8 COMBINE vegetable oil, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in a large bowl. Stir thoroughly to combine. Add eggs and continue stirring until fully incorporated.
7510ec5c-b756-457b-86f8-acb2bfbe81b8 ADD flour, cocoa powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Continue stirring the mixture until just combined, being careful not to over mix. Transfer batter to foil-lined pan.
7510ec5c-b756-457b-86f8-acb2bfbe81b8 BAKE 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies have set and the edges are firm. Let brownies cool in pan for 20 minutes, then use ends of foil to lift brownies from pan and transfer to a wire rack to cool completely before cutting.
dba942d3-618c-4174-ac9e-520808560c2d PREHEAT oven to 350 degrees. Line a 13x9-inch pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and set aside.
dba942d3-618c-4174-ac9e-520808560c2d Melt the butter in a large skillet. Add onion and garlic and cook over medium-high heat, stirring often for 2 to 3 minutes. Add celery, corn and pimento peppers and continue cooking for 1 to 2 minutes. Add the stock and continue cooking until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in chicken.
dba942d3-618c-4174-ac9e-520808560c2d PLACE biscuits into prepared pan. Drizzle the beaten egg on top and toss to coat. Pour the stock/chicken mixture on top. Using a spatula, stir mixture to fully coat the biscuits.
dba942d3-618c-4174-ac9e-520808560c2d COVER with foil and bake for 25 minutes. Remove foil and bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until top is crisp. Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes before serving.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 PREHEAT oven to 350° F.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 LINE an 8.5 x 4.5 x 2.75 inch loaf pan with a Reynolds® Non Stick Pan Lining Paper.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 MIX the sugar with the butter to make a paste, set aside.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 SLICE the apples very thin.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 For the curst, COMBINE the butter with the flour. Mix in the almonds, the pecans, and egg with the salt.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 For the bread pudding, MIX the almond milk, the yogurt, the vanilla, the maple syrup and the egg. Incorporate the bread. Cut into pieces and combine all.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 SPREAD a small amount of the paste to cover the bottom of the loaf pan and arrange the apple slices on top, use alternating layers of apples with the paste. Press down and compress the apples.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 SPREAD the crust over the apple layer pressing down.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 SPREAD the bread pudding mixture on top.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 BAKE at 350 degrees for 55 minutes to 1 hour and 5 minutes or until top is golden brown.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 MIX heavy cream, honey and orange zest together and pour on top of finished loaf.
585e81fe-e6b2-4420-8589-93cea158e555 Optional, DUST with powdered sugar on the top for extra sweetness.
f62594b2-e1d2-47d6-87ea-5607bf03c9bd PREHEAT oven to 375°F.
f62594b2-e1d2-47d6-87ea-5607bf03c9bd LINE a 13x9x2-inch baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper with parchment paper side toward food. Crimp Pan Lining Paper around rim of pan; set aside.
f62594b2-e1d2-47d6-87ea-5607bf03c9bd PLACE apple slices in a large bowl. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
f62594b2-e1d2-47d6-87ea-5607bf03c9bd COMBINE sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; sprinkle mixture over apples; mix well. Pour into lined dish; spread in an even layer. Dot with butter.
f62594b2-e1d2-47d6-87ea-5607bf03c9bd FOR TOPPING Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix in butter until crumbly. Stir in milk until mixture is a soft dough. Place teaspoonfuls of dough over hot apples, covering top surface.
f62594b2-e1d2-47d6-87ea-5607bf03c9bd BAKE 30 minutes. Using a plastic spoon, stir apples.
f62594b2-e1d2-47d6-87ea-5607bf03c9bd CONTINUE BAKING 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.
3f89c6eb-de48-4fd7-aa81-879049a42574 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. SHAKE flour in Reynolds® Oven Bag; place in 13x9-inch baking pan.
3f89c6eb-de48-4fd7-aa81-879049a42574 BRUSH both sides of chicken with dressing. Add chicken to bag in single layer, tucking thinner portions of each breast under so chicken is even thickness and leaving a little space between each. Sprinkle paprika and Parmesan cheese evenly over each breast.
3f89c6eb-de48-4fd7-aa81-879049a42574 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
3f89c6eb-de48-4fd7-aa81-879049a42574 MIX ingredients for Tomato Relish in small bowl. To serve, spoon Tomato Relish over Caesar Chicken and top with chopped parsley.
3f89c6eb-de48-4fd7-aa81-879049a42574 BAKE 30 to 40 minutes or until meat thermometer reaches 170°F. Let stand for 10 minutes.
86d55855-10c9-45a2-8c64-85c7290fc680 PREHEAT grill to medium-high. PLACE each pizza crust on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil; set aside.
86d55855-10c9-45a2-8c64-85c7290fc680 HEAT olive oil in a small skillet over medium heat. Add garlic and onion; cook, stirring frequently, until onion is softened.
86d55855-10c9-45a2-8c64-85c7290fc680 BRUSH pizza crust with olive oil mixture; arrange the onion, tomatoes, artichoke hearts, mushrooms and basil on crust. Sprinkle with cheese.
86d55855-10c9-45a2-8c64-85c7290fc680 GRILL pizza on foil sheets in covered grill for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese is melted.
42bd62d5-7da1-440f-a58b-f87ed894eed7 Wash and dry apples. Insert a popsicle stick into end of each apple.
42bd62d5-7da1-440f-a58b-f87ed894eed7 Line a large tray with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Sprinkle parchment paper with brown sugar.
42bd62d5-7da1-440f-a58b-f87ed894eed7 Combine caramel candies, milk, vanilla extracct and allspice in a medium size microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on high for 2 minutes. Stir ingredients until evenly mixed.
42bd62d5-7da1-440f-a58b-f87ed894eed7 Dip and roll apples in caramel mixture to coat. Roll apple in topping, if desired.
42bd62d5-7da1-440f-a58b-f87ed894eed7 Stand apple on brown sugar-sprinkled parchment paper. Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
7b71e57f-7b81-4e9d-9059-ddc68c2b444c PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
7b71e57f-7b81-4e9d-9059-ddc68c2b444c COMBINE rice, red pepper, onions, coconut, pineapple, brown sugar and lime juice. Center one-fourth of rice mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Rub jerk seasoning over chicken; place on top of ingredients on foil sheet.
7b71e57f-7b81-4e9d-9059-ddc68c2b444c BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
7b71e57f-7b81-4e9d-9059-ddc68c2b444c BAKE 18 to 22 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven
7b71e57f-7b81-4e9d-9059-ddc68c2b444c OR GRILL 16 to 20 minutes in covered grill.
9b7639cd-10c7-4545-8d8d-4b5e7224c292 Preheat oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high
9b7639cd-10c7-4545-8d8d-4b5e7224c292 Center one chicken breast half on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Spoon spaghetti sauce over the chicken. Top with zucchini. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
9b7639cd-10c7-4545-8d8d-4b5e7224c292 Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make 2 packets.
9b7639cd-10c7-4545-8d8d-4b5e7224c292 Bake 18 to 22 minutes on a cookie sheet in the oven or Grill 12 to 14 minutes in covered grill. Springle with Mozzarella cheese before serving.
0bbe7d8e-892e-4790-a32a-541af30a94f3 PREHEAT grill to medium-high OR oven to 450°F.
0bbe7d8e-892e-4790-a32a-541af30a94f3 CENTER onion slices and one chicken breast half on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Brush each chicken breast half with 1/4 teaspoon olive oil. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon basil,1/4 teaspoon seasoned salt and lemon pepper, and 1/8 teaspoon paprika.
0bbe7d8e-892e-4790-a32a-541af30a94f3 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
0bbe7d8e-892e-4790-a32a-541af30a94f3 GRILL 12 to 14 minutes in covered grill OR
0bbe7d8e-892e-4790-a32a-541af30a94f3 BAKE 18 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet in oven.
da0c7431-53fa-4eb8-93cd-dfea2de74408 PREHEAT grill to medium-high. Place a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food on a cookie sheet to transport pizza to and from the grill.
da0c7431-53fa-4eb8-93cd-dfea2de74408 ROLL or pat pizza dough into a rectangle on the foil-lined cookie sheet. Combine olive oil and garlic. Brush over pizza dough.
da0c7431-53fa-4eb8-93cd-dfea2de74408 SLIDE foil sheet with pizza dough onto grill.
da0c7431-53fa-4eb8-93cd-dfea2de74408 GRILL pizza dough 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned. Slide foil sheet with pizza crust back onto cookie sheet to add toppings. (You will need to remove the crust from the grill while adding toppings to prevent the crust from continuing to brown.) Using a spatula, turn crust over.
da0c7431-53fa-4eb8-93cd-dfea2de74408 SPREAD sauce evenly over crust. Sprinkle with 2 cups cheese. Spread pepperoni slices and bell pepper strips evenly. Add any other toppings of your choice.
da0c7431-53fa-4eb8-93cd-dfea2de74408 GRILL 3 to 4 minutes or until crust is golden brown and cheese is melted. Slide foil sheet with pizza back onto cookie sheet to remove from the grill.
3a996784-d7e6-4c0b-9eb6-421110d2d79b PREHEAT grill to medium-high. Place a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side towards food on a cookie sheet to transport pizza to and from the grill.
3a996784-d7e6-4c0b-9eb6-421110d2d79b CENTER Italian bread crust, bottom side up, on foil sheet. Combine olive oil and garlic. Brush over pizza crust.
3a996784-d7e6-4c0b-9eb6-421110d2d79b SLIDE foil sheet with pizza dough onto grill.
3a996784-d7e6-4c0b-9eb6-421110d2d79b GRILL pizza crust 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned. Slide foil sheet with pizza crusts back on cookie sheet to add toppings. (You will need to remove the crusts from the grill while adding toppings to prevent the crust from continuing to brown.) Using a spatula, turn crust over.
3a996784-d7e6-4c0b-9eb6-421110d2d79b SPREAD up foil sides. Spread sauce evenly over crust. Arrange vegetables over sauce. Slide foil sheet with pizza from cookie sheet back onto the grill.
3a996784-d7e6-4c0b-9eb6-421110d2d79b GRILL to minutes in covered grill or until cheese is melted. Slide foil sheet with pizza back onto cookie sheet to remove from the grill.
467869f6-c21a-4747-a4fc-8a91aadf7f6d Preheat oven to 375°
467869f6-c21a-4747-a4fc-8a91aadf7f6d In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter, peanut butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the egg, applesauce, vanilla, nutmeg, and honey
467869f6-c21a-4747-a4fc-8a91aadf7f6d In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients and gradually stir in the creamed mixture
467869f6-c21a-4747-a4fc-8a91aadf7f6d Drop batter by rounded spoonfuls, onto a cookie sheet lined with parchment paper. Space at least 2 inches apart
467869f6-c21a-4747-a4fc-8a91aadf7f6d Bake for 8-10 minutes
467869f6-c21a-4747-a4fc-8a91aadf7f6d Allow cookies to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool, cookies will be soft
67994528-04e9-4ba6-b51f-aa01ff071ac4 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
67994528-04e9-4ba6-b51f-aa01ff071ac4 PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
67994528-04e9-4ba6-b51f-aa01ff071ac4 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes, using 3 eggs and amount of oil specified. Replace 1/2 cup of the water with Irish cream liqueur. Spoon batter into baking cups.
67994528-04e9-4ba6-b51f-aa01ff071ac4 BAKE following package directions. Cool.
67994528-04e9-4ba6-b51f-aa01ff071ac4 Tip: To make cake a non-alcoholic version, try substituting flavored coffee creamer for the Irish cream liqueur.
67994528-04e9-4ba6-b51f-aa01ff071ac4 MAKE frosting: 1.Combine butter, cream cheese, salt; beat until light and fluffy. 2.Add confectioners' sugar slowly, beating on low speed. 3.Beat in irish cream liqueur one tablespoon at a time until desired consistancy is reached.
67994528-04e9-4ba6-b51f-aa01ff071ac4 FILL a pastry bag, fitted with a plain 1/2 inch round tip, with frosting. Fill a second pastry bag, fitted with a star decorating tip, with vanilla frosting.
67994528-04e9-4ba6-b51f-aa01ff071ac4 PIPE concentric circles of Irish Cream Frosting onto each cupcake to form a peak. Pipe a dot of vanilla frosting on the side.
67994528-04e9-4ba6-b51f-aa01ff071ac4 GRATE semi sweet chocolate on top of each cupcake.
e2bd87d9-6f81-430a-b075-81c9f0431c43 PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper with parchment side toward food. Crimp Pan Lining Paper around rim of pan; set aside.
e2bd87d9-6f81-430a-b075-81c9f0431c43 COMBINE ground beef, pasta sauce and 2 teaspoons Italian seasoning in a bowl; set aside.
e2bd87d9-6f81-430a-b075-81c9f0431c43 COMBINE ricotta cheese, egg, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasoning in another bowl; set aside.
e2bd87d9-6f81-430a-b075-81c9f0431c43 PLACE 1 cup of sauce mixture evenly in the bottom of lined pan.
e2bd87d9-6f81-430a-b075-81c9f0431c43 ARRANGE noodles in a single layer on top of sauce in lined pan. Spread noodles with 1/3 of ricotta cheese mixture, 1/3 of mozzarella cheese and 1/3 of remaining sauce mixture. Repeat 2 more times to make 3 total layers. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
e2bd87d9-6f81-430a-b075-81c9f0431c43 BAKE 40 to 45 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and cheese is golden brown. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
cf9beedc-7a3a-4f36-a19c-ffae39002ddd BEAT together powdered sugar, peanut butter, melted chocolate, butter and milk with an electric mixer on low speed until blended. Add additional powered sugar is mixture is too soft to shape.
cf9beedc-7a3a-4f36-a19c-ffae39002ddd SHAPE mixture into a log; roll log in parchment paper, twisting ends to secure. Refrigerate about 1 hour until firm and chilled.
cf9beedc-7a3a-4f36-a19c-ffae39002ddd UNWRAP log. SLICE into 1-inch pieces. SHAPE pieces into balls.
cf9beedc-7a3a-4f36-a19c-ffae39002ddd DIP balls in melted chocolate or sprinkles. Wrap in candies in Reynolds® Parchment Paper or place on parchment lined container for storage.
667d5c78-1c9e-437a-ad80-6aefa969f840 PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper or Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
667d5c78-1c9e-437a-ad80-6aefa969f840 SEPARATE dough into triangles on parchment paper. Sprinkle each triangle with barbecue seasoning. Place cheese on wide end of triangle, leaving 1/4-inch of dough around cheese.
667d5c78-1c9e-437a-ad80-6aefa969f840 ROLL UP each hot dog, starting with the wide end of triangle, rolling toward the point.
667d5c78-1c9e-437a-ad80-6aefa969f840 BAKE to minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately.
8d21b726-0e5d-4045-9310-a8ff6df3dafc PREHEAT oven to 325°F. Place Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans.
8d21b726-0e5d-4045-9310-a8ff6df3dafc MIX graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and sugar in a small bowl. Spoon and press a heaping tablespoon into each baking cup; set aside.
8d21b726-0e5d-4045-9310-a8ff6df3dafc BEAT cream cheese on medium speed for 2 minutes till smooth. Add eggs, sugar and vanilla extract; continue beating on medium speed for 2 minutes smooth and well blended. SPOON about 3 tablespoons mixture into each baking cup; they should be about ½ full.
8d21b726-0e5d-4045-9310-a8ff6df3dafc BAKE 25 to 30 minutes until set. Cool completely on wire rack.
8d21b726-0e5d-4045-9310-a8ff6df3dafc While cupcakes are baking, HEAT drained pineapple, brown sugar and butter in a medium sauce pan over high heat, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes or until it boils. Once the mixture boils, reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; set aside and cool.
8d21b726-0e5d-4045-9310-a8ff6df3dafc Chill cupcakes until ready to serve. To serve, top each cupcake with 2 tablespoons pineapple topping and whipped topping.
d05b894e-e4d4-48ee-b551-ede0ccf5de59 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
d05b894e-e4d4-48ee-b551-ede0ccf5de59 PLACE onion slices evenly in foil-lined pan. Top onions with chicken, peppers and pasta sauce.
d05b894e-e4d4-48ee-b551-ede0ccf5de59 BAKE 20 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese and pepperoni.
d05b894e-e4d4-48ee-b551-ede0ccf5de59 CONTINUE BAKING 20 to 25 minutes longer or until chicken reaches 170°F and juices run clear.
13283a75-3ff9-4664-a348-59eca9579cad PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
13283a75-3ff9-4664-a348-59eca9579cad PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
13283a75-3ff9-4664-a348-59eca9579cad PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes, adding 3 tablespoons instant coffee before mixing. Spoon batter into baking cups.
13283a75-3ff9-4664-a348-59eca9579cad BAKE following package directions. Cool.
13283a75-3ff9-4664-a348-59eca9579cad TINT frosting green.
13283a75-3ff9-4664-a348-59eca9579cad SPREAD frosting onto cupcakes.
13283a75-3ff9-4664-a348-59eca9579cad SPRINKLE cupcakes with sugar crystals.
13283a75-3ff9-4664-a348-59eca9579cad MAKE playing cards: 1. Roll-out white, black and red fondant. 2. For cards, cut white fondant into rectangles about 1-inch X 2-inches. 3. Cut heart, diamond, club and spade shapes using a tiny cutter or a knife with a sharp tip. Cut letters or numbers for the cards. 4. Moisten the backs of the fondant shapes and adhere to the cards. 5. Place 1 or 2 cards on each cupcake.
e8a3fbb9-88b7-4f28-86ba-a876805b90c4 PREHEAT grill to medium-high. Make drainage holes in a sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with a large fork; set aside.
e8a3fbb9-88b7-4f28-86ba-a876805b90c4 COMBINE butter and garlic. Baste mushroom caps with mixture. Place foil on grill grate with non-stick (dull) side facing up. Immediately place mushrooms on foil.
e8a3fbb9-88b7-4f28-86ba-a876805b90c4 GRILL uncovered 6 to 8 minutes, turning once, until mushrooms are browned and tender. Place 1 slice of cheese on each mushroom during the last minute of grilling.
e8a3fbb9-88b7-4f28-86ba-a876805b90c4 COMBINE sour cream, vinegar, mustard, sugar and pepper in small microwave-safe bowl to make sauce. Microwave on HIGH power 30 seconds or until warm. Serve sauce over burgers in buns. Add lettuce and tomato, if desired.
c7694daa-8b52-4f93-bf44-05cdc36d1312 PREHEAT oven to 325°F.
c7694daa-8b52-4f93-bf44-05cdc36d1312 SHAKE flour in Reynolds Oven Bag; place in 13x9-inch baking pan. Add water to bag. Squeeze bag to blend water and flour.
c7694daa-8b52-4f93-bf44-05cdc36d1312 COMBINE garlic salt, onion powder, ground mustard, pepper and paprika. Sprinkle and rub over all sides of pork. Add pork to bag.
c7694daa-8b52-4f93-bf44-05cdc36d1312 CLOSE bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
c7694daa-8b52-4f93-bf44-05cdc36d1312 BAKE 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender enough to shred. Remove any bones and visible fat. With 2 forks, shred meat. Skim fat from juices; pour enough over meat to moisten. Spoon into buns and drizzle with barbecue sauce.
fa34d47b-860b-4322-b830-4db004538422 PREHEAT oven to 450°F. For easy cleanup, line a 13x9x2-inch pan with Reynolds Wrap Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
fa34d47b-860b-4322-b830-4db004538422 PLACE chicken in foil-lined pan. Combine garlic, olive oil, lemon juice and Italian seasoning. Brush chicken with half of olive oil mixture. Arrange vegetables around chicken. Drizzle vegetables with remaining olive oil mixture. Sprinkle seasoned salt and pepper over chicken and vegetables.
fa34d47b-860b-4322-b830-4db004538422 MAKE a foil tent by placing a sheet of foil over chicken, leaving space between top of chicken and foil tent for heat circulation. Crimp foil to rim of pan.
fa34d47b-860b-4322-b830-4db004538422 BAKE 45 minutes. Remove foil cover.
fa34d47b-860b-4322-b830-4db004538422 CONTINUE BAKING 15 minutes or until meat thermometer reads 180°F.
fa34d47b-860b-4322-b830-4db004538422 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIPS: To line pan, flip pan upside down. Press a sheet of foil around pan. Remove foil. Flip pan upright and drop foil inside. Crimp edges to rim of pan. To reduce fat and calories, remove skin from chicken before eating.
d7dbcfbc-1732-47bf-9ae1-a23fba8d4333 COMBINE flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl; set aside.
d7dbcfbc-1732-47bf-9ae1-a23fba8d4333 BEAT butter and sugar with electric mixer until fluffy, about 3 minutes. Beat in egg yolks and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture and combine.
d7dbcfbc-1732-47bf-9ae1-a23fba8d4333 WRAP dough in parchment paper and place in plastic Hefty® Slider Bag; refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.
d7dbcfbc-1732-47bf-9ae1-a23fba8d4333 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Parchment Paper; set aside.
d7dbcfbc-1732-47bf-9ae1-a23fba8d4333 ROLL out dough 1/8-inch thick between 2 sheets of parchment paper. CUT dough with 2 inch cookie cutters. PLACE dough on parchment-lined cookie sheets.
d7dbcfbc-1732-47bf-9ae1-a23fba8d4333 BAKE 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned on edges. Slide parchment paper with cookies onto cooling rack; cool.
d7dbcfbc-1732-47bf-9ae1-a23fba8d4333 DECORATE as desired. Store in airtight containers for up to 5 days.
4142bb0f-8347-481f-9d3a-34955a634cd9 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
4142bb0f-8347-481f-9d3a-34955a634cd9 SHAKE flour in Reynolds Oven Bag; place in 13x9-inch baking pan.
4142bb0f-8347-481f-9d3a-34955a634cd9 MIX seasonings. Add 1 tablespoon to bag; squeeze to blend with flour.
4142bb0f-8347-481f-9d3a-34955a634cd9 BRUSH chicken with melted butter. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of seasoning mixture in cavity. Sprinkle and rub remaining seasoning mixture all over chicken. Add to bag.
4142bb0f-8347-481f-9d3a-34955a634cd9 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
4142bb0f-8347-481f-9d3a-34955a634cd9 BAKE 1 1/4 - 1 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer inserted in thickest part of thigh not touching bone reads 180°F. Let stand 10 minutes; slice and serve.
010800ff-c05e-45a8-9093-8b4f28bec43f PREHEAT oven to 400°F.
010800ff-c05e-45a8-9093-8b4f28bec43f MIX olive oil, tarragon, garlic, lemon peel, seasoned salt and pepper in a small bowl; set aside.
010800ff-c05e-45a8-9093-8b4f28bec43f TEAR off four 15-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap Pan Lining Paper. With the parchment side toward the inside, fold each sheet in half and crease it in the center. Unfold.
010800ff-c05e-45a8-9093-8b4f28bec43f ARRANGE 1/4 of asparagus evenly on one-half of each sheet near crease on the parchment side of the Pan Lining Paper. Place salmon fillet on top of asparagus. Spread each fillet with 1/4 of olive oil mixture. Top each fillet with a lemon slice.
010800ff-c05e-45a8-9093-8b4f28bec43f FOLD over other half of sheet to enclose ingredients. Starting at top corner, make small overlapping folds down entire length of packet to seal edges together. Twist the last fold several times to make a tight seal. Repeat to make 4 packets. Place packets on a large cookie sheet.
010800ff-c05e-45a8-9093-8b4f28bec43f BAKE 18 to 20 minutes. Place packets on dinner plates. Carefully cut an "X" in top of each packet to allow steam to escape. Serve immediately.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b PLACE Reynolds Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b CUT a marshmallow in half crosswise with scissors. Then cut a 1/4-inch slice from one side to make a muzzle piece. Repeat with remaining marshmallows to cut enough muzzle pieces for all cupcakes.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b ATTACH the marshmallow muzzles on the lower half of each cupcake with some chocolate frosting.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b PLACE some pink sugar crystals in a small bowl.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b CUT the mini marshmallows in half crosswise and press into pink sugar to adhere to the cut sides for the ears.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b ATTACH two marshmallow ears, pink sides up on the top edge of each cupcake with some of the chocolate frosting.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b SPOON the rest of the chocolate frosting into a pastry bag fitted with a small star tip. Pipe the fur, starting around the outer edge of cupcake to cover the cupcake and marshmallows as well.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b PIPE white dots of tube frosting for the eyes. Press mini green candies into the white frosting for center of eyes.
8e8dce84-ec32-4aec-9ecd-8bc501ba583b ADD a pink jellybean nose and a mini red candy for the tongue on each cupcake.
aa7d7b25-4901-456b-a4af-8ad0cf239483 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
aa7d7b25-4901-456b-a4af-8ad0cf239483 PLACE one-fourth of shrimp on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Combine carrots, zucchini, onion, spaghetti sauce and red pepper flakes; spoon over shrimp.
aa7d7b25-4901-456b-a4af-8ad0cf239483 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
aa7d7b25-4901-456b-a4af-8ad0cf239483 BAKE 14 to 18 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven
aa7d7b25-4901-456b-a4af-8ad0cf239483 OR GRILL 8 to 10 minutes in covered grill. Serve over pasta; sprinkle with cheese.
3595a153-6fed-4a8e-8ace-49b8a3b2286b OPEN Reynolds Slow Cooker Liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
3595a153-6fed-4a8e-8ace-49b8a3b2286b BROWN ground beef, bell pepper and onion in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until beef is no longer pink. Drain well.
3595a153-6fed-4a8e-8ace-49b8a3b2286b PLACE beef mixture into slow cooker liner. Combine remaining ingredients in a medium bowl. Pour over beef mixture; gently stir with wooden or plastic spoon to combine. Place lid on slow cooker.
3595a153-6fed-4a8e-8ace-49b8a3b2286b COOK on LOW for 6 to 7 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 3 1/2 hours until heated through.
3595a153-6fed-4a8e-8ace-49b8a3b2286b CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker liner. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
72a05d62-f15e-498a-97ed-718d05a3d2d4 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
72a05d62-f15e-498a-97ed-718d05a3d2d4 BROWN ground beef and onion in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until beef is no longer pink. Stir in seasoning to evenly coat meat and onions. Stir in pasta sauce. Set aside.
72a05d62-f15e-498a-97ed-718d05a3d2d4 MIX 1 cup mozzarella cheese, the ricotta and Parmesan in a medium bowl. Spoon 2 cups of the meat sauce into the lined-slow cooker; top with 2 cups uncooked ziti pasta. Drop half of the cheese mixture, by rounded tablespoons, over pasta; carefully spread over pasta using back of spoon. Layer with 2 cups meat sauce, the remaining pasta and the remaining cheese mixture. Top with the remaining meat sauce, completely covering all the pasta and cheese mixture. Place lid on slow cooker.
72a05d62-f15e-498a-97ed-718d05a3d2d4 COOK on LOW for 4 to 5 hours or until noodles are tender.
72a05d62-f15e-498a-97ed-718d05a3d2d4 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Sprinkle food with the remaining 1 cup mozzarella cheese; let stand 10 minutes until melted. Serve food directly from lined-slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
a27850d5-5b99-4f53-8c25-a29fd7ebb3a6 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
a27850d5-5b99-4f53-8c25-a29fd7ebb3a6 PLACE Reynolds Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
a27850d5-5b99-4f53-8c25-a29fd7ebb3a6 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups
a27850d5-5b99-4f53-8c25-a29fd7ebb3a6 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
a27850d5-5b99-4f53-8c25-a29fd7ebb3a6 DIVIDE fondant into two pieces; 2/3 will be used for the snowmen, 1/3 will be tinted and used for the hat and scarf.
a27850d5-5b99-4f53-8c25-a29fd7ebb3a6 MAKE Snowmen 1.Roll white fondant into balls 12 balls (2 per snowman), six, to be used for the heads, should be about 2-inches in diameter, six, for the bodies, should be slightly bigger. 2.Stack the heads onto the bodies using a toothpick. 3.Tint 1/3 of rolled fondant with food coloring by placing it in a plastic bag and following package directions. 4.Roll pink fondant about 1/4-inch thick. MAKE scarf 1.Use a pizza cutter to cut six (6) strips of fondant (5 to 6 ½ inches each), that are long enough to wrap around the neck of the snowman. 2.If desired, press small pieces of white fondant into the ends of the scarf. 3.Cut three (3), 1/2-inch slits on each side of the scarf to make fringe. 4.Place the scarf around the snowman's neck. Use small dots of frosting (toothpicks work well) and press to keep it in place.
a27850d5-5b99-4f53-8c25-a29fd7ebb3a6 MAKE hat 1.Cut 6 small triangle pieces using the size of chocolate kiss candy as a guide. 2.Wrap fondant around chocolate kiss candies with seam on back. Use small dots of frosting to seal fondant to chocolate kiss. 3.Cut 2-inch strips for hat band. Coat strip with a thin layer of frosting to hold sprinkles. Press sprinkles into each fondant hat band. 4.Wrap sprinkle covered band around hat; attach with dots of frosting. 5.If desired, cut strips of fondant to make a tassel for the hat. Coat tassel lightly with frosting, press sprinkles into tassel, and attach to hat with frosting.
a27850d5-5b99-4f53-8c25-a29fd7ebb3a6 DECORATE snowman 1.Use nonpareils and small red candies for eyes and nose; press into fondant. Cut mouth from pink fondant with a pizza cutter; use a small dot of frosting (toothpicks work well) to attach to face. 2.Place fondant-covered candy hat on snowman's head, using dots of frosting to hold it in place. 3.Cut mouth from pink fondant with a pizza cutter; use a small dot of frosting (toothpicks work well) to attach to face. 4.Insert toothpick into bottom of snowman. Center snowman on top of frosted cupcake
10049d59-45d9-4268-969f-10949a266265 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or preheat grill to medium-high.
10049d59-45d9-4268-969f-10949a266265 CENTER one-fourth of corn on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Top with shrimp and salsa. Drizzle with lime juice and oil.
10049d59-45d9-4268-969f-10949a266265 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
10049d59-45d9-4268-969f-10949a266265 BAKE 14 to 18 minutes on cookie sheet in oven
10049d59-45d9-4268-969f-10949a266265 OR GRILL 12 to 16 minutes in covered grill.
10049d59-45d9-4268-969f-10949a266265 SERVE with Chili Rice. To prepare rice while packets are cooking, combine chicken bouillon granules, chili powder and brown rice; cook following package directions.
ff8331ea-d2e6-4aa7-a18c-21d3961147f6 COMBINE Lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, seafood seasoning, lemon pepper, basil and garlic. Gradually add oil, stirring mixture until thickened. Reserve half of marinade for basting. Add shrimp to remaining marinade; stir to coat evenly. Cover shrimp and refrigerate 30 minutes. Drain shrimp; discard marinade.
ff8331ea-d2e6-4aa7-a18c-21d3961147f6 HEAT grill to medium-high (400° to 450°F). Cut slits in a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-stick Aluminum Foil. Place on grill rack with non-stick side toward food. Arrange shrimp on top
ff8331ea-d2e6-4aa7-a18c-21d3961147f6 GRILL uncovered 4 to 6 minutes, turning and basting once with reserved marinade, until shrimp are firm and pink.
ff8331ea-d2e6-4aa7-a18c-21d3961147f6 REMOVE shrimp from aluminum foil sheet; allow remaining juices to cool before handling foil.
1be4e097-1806-4606-b0f4-0684355560ec PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
1be4e097-1806-4606-b0f4-0684355560ec PLACE Reynolds Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
1be4e097-1806-4606-b0f4-0684355560ec PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
1be4e097-1806-4606-b0f4-0684355560ec BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
1be4e097-1806-4606-b0f4-0684355560ec TINT frosting pink with food coloring. Spoon frosting into a pastry bag fitted with a large leaf tip.
1be4e097-1806-4606-b0f4-0684355560ec PIPE frosting from center to outer edge to look like petals.
1be4e097-1806-4606-b0f4-0684355560ec FILL the center with 1 to 2 teaspoons of mini green candies.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d PREHEAT oven to 350°F. <br />COOKIES:
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d LINE cookie sheets with Reynolds Parchment Paper; set aside. No need to add extra grease or spray your cookie sheets.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d KNEAD flour into sugar cookie dough until well blended.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d ROLL out half of cookie dough at a time to 1/4-inch thickness between lightly floured sheets of Parchment Paper. Using circles, flower or butterfly cookie cutters, cut out cookies; place on parchment-lined cookie sheets.<br /> DECORATING SUGAR COOKIES:
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d BEAT powdered sugar, meringue powder, water and extract in a large bowl, with an electric mixer, on high speed until smooth and thick, about 1 minute.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d DIVIDE icing into 6 small bowls. Stir food coloring in remaining frosting to make purple, blue, orange, yellow, pink and green icing. Cover icing tightly when not in use, icing dries quickly.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d PIPE outlines of cookies with contrasting colors of icing using a decorating bag with tip. Or, place icing in plastic zipper bags. Snip off one corner with scissors and use to pipe icing.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d FOR SUGARED OUTLINES, sprinkle heavily with sugar crystals while icing is wet. Lightly shake off excess crystals. TIP: Sprinkle over Parchment Paper to catch excess for reuse.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d TO ICE INSIDE OUTLINES, add a little water to thin icing, if necessary. Spoon a small amount of icing onto outlined cookies. Using a brush, small spatula or your finger, spread icing up to outline to fill in spaces.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d FOR BUTTERFLY, while icing is still wet, pipe dots around edge of wings. Inside upper part of wings, pipe 3 dots in a line. Drag a toothpick down through the center of the dots to make the heart-shaped designs. Pipe 1 dot in the bottom part of the wing. Drag a toothpick up to make the upside down heart design. For the body of the butterfly, pipe a line of brown frosting in the center and immediately arrange 4 candy-coated chocolate candies on the icing.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d FOR FLOWERS, pipe a small amount of icing in center. While wet, add a contrasting color candy-coated chocolate candy. Pipe 2 small lines of green icing at angles between petals to form leaves.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d FOR SMILEY FACE, use brown frosting to pipe a smile. Pipe 2 dots of frosting for eyes. Add 2 candy-coated chocolate candies for the eyes.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIPS: - Cover icing at all times. Icing can dry out quickly. - Let icing dry before adding a different color of icing. If icing is still wet, colors will blend.
ce3c0731-70ce-42a1-b9a1-278dff127f1d BAKE 7 to 12 minutes, depending on the size of the cookies or until the edges begin to brown. Let stand one minute on cookie sheets. Slide Parchment Paper with cookies onto a wire racks to cool completely.
b71a438e-0ae5-40a9-ac73-1787db810629 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
b71a438e-0ae5-40a9-ac73-1787db810629 PLACE Reynolds Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
b71a438e-0ae5-40a9-ac73-1787db810629 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon cake batter into baking cups.
b71a438e-0ae5-40a9-ac73-1787db810629 BEAT cream cheese, egg, chopped dried cherries and sugar in bowl, with electric mixer. Stir in a few drops red food coloring, if desired. Drop by tablespoonfuls into cupcake batter
b71a438e-0ae5-40a9-ac73-1787db810629 BAKE 20 to 22 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean; cool.
b71a438e-0ae5-40a9-ac73-1787db810629 MAKE flowers: 1.Shape the pink fondant into 1-inch balls. Flatten slightly. 2.Place the flower stamp on top of the pink fondant and flatten to make stamp imprint. 3.Brush the center of the flower stamps lightly with corn syrup. Sprinkle with yellow sprinkles; set aside. 4.Flatten the green fondant and cut into 1/2-inch leaf shapes and a stem if desired. Set aside.
b71a438e-0ae5-40a9-ac73-1787db810629 SPREAD the top of each cupcake with frosting.and make smooth.
b71a438e-0ae5-40a9-ac73-1787db810629 PLACE a flower, leaves and stem on each cupcake.
07cb8996-87ca-4440-8743-6f933b054486 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place Reynolds Baking Cups in muffin pans or on a cookie sheet; set aside.
07cb8996-87ca-4440-8743-6f933b054486 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes adding mashed strawberries before mixing. Spoon batter into baking cups.
07cb8996-87ca-4440-8743-6f933b054486 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes. Cool.
07cb8996-87ca-4440-8743-6f933b054486 MIX frosting and banana extract in a medium bowl until well blended. Frost cupcakes. Top with strawberry and banana slices before serving, if desired.
746a28e5-92a2-4598-a1e7-98488568bd8c PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
746a28e5-92a2-4598-a1e7-98488568bd8c PLACE Reynolds Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
746a28e5-92a2-4598-a1e7-98488568bd8c PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups
746a28e5-92a2-4598-a1e7-98488568bd8c BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
746a28e5-92a2-4598-a1e7-98488568bd8c TINT about 1/4 cup frosting green. Tint remaining frosting yellow.
746a28e5-92a2-4598-a1e7-98488568bd8c SPREAD yellow frosting on cupcakes.
746a28e5-92a2-4598-a1e7-98488568bd8c PIPE a large green leaf near center of each cupcake.
746a28e5-92a2-4598-a1e7-98488568bd8c PLACE sugar daisies next to the leaves.
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a LINE cookie sheets with Reynolds Parchment Paper; set aside. No need to add extra grease or spray your cookie sheets.
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a KNEAD flour into sugar cookie dough until well blended.
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a ROLL out half of cookie dough at a time to 1/4-inch thickness between lightly floured sheets of Parchment Paper. Using circles, ice cream cone or footprint cookie cutters, cut out cookies; place on parchment-lined cookie sheets.<br />DECORATING SUGAR COOKIES:
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a BEAT powdered sugar, meringue powder, water and extract in a large bowl, with an electric mixer, on high speed until smooth and thick, about 1 minute.
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a DIVIDE icing into 8 small bowls. Reserve one bowl as white frosting. Stir food coloring in remaining frosting to make purple, blue, orange, yellow, pink, green and brown icing. Cover icing tightly when not in use, icing dries quickly. PIPE outlines of cookies with matching or contrasting colors of icing using a decorating bag with tip. Or, place icing in plastic zipper bags. Snip off one corner with scissors and use to pipe icing. <br />TO ICE INSIDE OUTLINES:
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a Add a little water to thin icing, if necessary. Spoon a small amount of icing onto outlined cookies. Using a brush, small spatula or your finger, spread icing up to outline to fill in spaces. <br />FOR FLIP FLOPS:
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a Pipe dots of purple icing on unfrosted cookies to make nail polish on toes. Use green icing to pipe lines to form top of flip flop. While icing is wet, add a large candy coated candy with 6 small candies around it to make a flower decoration on top of the flip flop. <br />FOR ICE CREAM CONES:
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a Pipe brown icing onto unfrosted cookies to draw crisscross lines to make the cone. For the ice cream follow directions above for outlining and icing the cookies with pink outlines and icing. While frosting is still wet, sprinkle with multi-colored sprinkles and top with a small red candy-coated chocolate. FOR SUN, pipe orange icing in center. With a small star decorating tip, pipe yellow icing in sun rays around orange center. <br />FOR WATERMELON SLICES:
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a Follow directions above for outlining and icing half circle cookies with red, white and green icing in semi-circles, letting icing dry between colors. While red icing is still wet, sprinkle with chocolate jimmies. <br />FOR BEACH BALLS:
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a Divide circle cookies in fourths following directions above for outlining and icing the cookies with red, blue, yellow and green icing, letting icing dry between colors. Pipe white lines between colors to segment the colors. Add a small brown candy-coated chocolate candy in the center of cookie where the colors meet.
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIPS: Cover icing at all times. Icing can dry out quickly. - Let icing dry before adding a different color of icing. If icing is still wet, colors will blend.
acb7e5ce-bbda-46f5-8e7a-ed2511ff1c5a BAKE 7 to 12 minutes, depending on the size of the cookies or until the edges begin to brown. Let stand one minute on cookie sheets. Slide Parchment Paper with cookies onto a wire racks to cool completely.
f932475a-f326-41a3-96ad-192092f24b1e <span>Fill your small pitcher with the sparkling water. Add Tbsp lemon juice to give the beverage a little extra kick. In individual glasses, place a slice of lemon, a few sprigs of thyme and some ice cubes. Pour drink into each glass, cover with a Reynolds® Baking Cup, add a straw and enjoy! </span>
d79333d1-c044-4beb-983e-ea3272e4ad73 PREHEAT oven to 450°F. Line a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil; set aside.
d79333d1-c044-4beb-983e-ea3272e4ad73 COMBINE sweet and sour sauce, garlic salt and red pepper flakes in a large bowl. Add meatballs, bell pepper and pineapple. Stir to coat evenly. ARRANGE in even layer in foil-lined pan.
d79333d1-c044-4beb-983e-ea3272e4ad73 BAKE 25 minutes or until meatballs are hot; stirring once during baking. Spoon sauce of meatballs. Serve warm.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 SOAK wooden skewers in water for 30 minutes.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 PREHEAT grill to medium-high.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 FOLD sheet of Reynolds Wrap Foil in half; set aside.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 THREAD fruit chunks onto skewers, alternating so there are about 2 pieces each fruit on each skewer.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 COMBINE sugar, melted butter and lime juice in small bowl.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 BRUSH on all sides of fruit.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 PLACE skewers on grill.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 SLIDE folded sheet of Reynolds Wrap Foil under the exposed end of the skewers.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 GRILL for about 8 minutes in covered grill, turning once, until lightly browned and slightly softened.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 DRIZZLE remaining butter mixture on fruit.
d8ace224-6fec-4afe-bb96-6898e3b16b39 SPRINKLE with chopped mint.
34c9cdab-a3b1-4f97-b16b-49bf23b60eab BAKE light colored cupcakes (yellow, lemon, or white) in Reynolds® Yellow Pastel Baking Cups in yellow pastel in order to get the most authentic looking tennis ball.
34c9cdab-a3b1-4f97-b16b-49bf23b60eab LINE your counter with Reynolds® Cut-Rite® Wax Paper so clean-up will be simple.
