34c9cdab-a3b1-4f97-b16b-49bf23b60eab SPREAD the top of each cupcake with white frosting and, while the frosting is still moist, dip the frosted cupcake in nonpareils to cover entire top. If areas are not covered, sprinkle more nonpareils over the top and press gently to cover completely. Reynolds Kitchens Tip: To make an even surface, dip a small knife or spreader into a bowl of warm water and gently shake off the excess before smoothing over frosting.
34c9cdab-a3b1-4f97-b16b-49bf23b60eab PIPE markings onto the tennis ball using a #3 tip. It may be easiest to accomplish if you think of it as a rounded hill shape.
34c9cdab-a3b1-4f97-b16b-49bf23b60eab A DIFFERENT TAKE To make the tennis balls look at home on the tennis court, bake in Reynolds bright green Party baking cups!
be1c3f1c-12fc-473a-a561-8e760153ff8e PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food.
be1c3f1c-12fc-473a-a561-8e760153ff8e PLACE salmon, skin side down, in foil-lined pan.
be1c3f1c-12fc-473a-a561-8e760153ff8e MIX remaining ingredients together in a medium bowl until well blended. Spread over salmon.
be1c3f1c-12fc-473a-a561-8e760153ff8e BAKE 16 to 18 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
be1c3f1c-12fc-473a-a561-8e760153ff8e REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: Roasted sesame seeds can be found in the International grocery section of the store where you shop.
e8da5bde-fab3-4706-bd23-ddb713589f28 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high. Combine teriyaki sauce, sesame oil, ginger and garlic powder in large bowl. Cut steak lengthwise in half and then crosswise into 1/8" thick strips. Add beef; stir to coat with sauce.
e8da5bde-fab3-4706-bd23-ddb713589f28 CENTER one-fourth of vegetables on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Arrange beef in an even layer over vegetables.
e8da5bde-fab3-4706-bd23-ddb713589f28 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
e8da5bde-fab3-4706-bd23-ddb713589f28 BAKE 18 to 20 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven
e8da5bde-fab3-4706-bd23-ddb713589f28 OR GRILL 8 to 10 minutes in covered grill. Serve over rice.
4781812d-e701-4abd-8acc-190cfd476fee PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
4781812d-e701-4abd-8acc-190cfd476fee PLACE Reynolds Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
4781812d-e701-4abd-8acc-190cfd476fee PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
4781812d-e701-4abd-8acc-190cfd476fee BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
4781812d-e701-4abd-8acc-190cfd476fee TINT frosting blue. Place inside of zipper bag. Cut large corner off bag and pipe each cupcake with frosting.
4781812d-e701-4abd-8acc-190cfd476fee MAKE chocolate morsel drizzles 1.Place chocolate chips in a microwave-safe container. Microwave on HIGH for 45 seconds to 1 minute, stirring every 15 seconds until the chocolate is melted. 2.Put chocolate chips into a second zipper bag. Cut off a very small corner. 3.Squeeze bag in a back-and-forth motion over the cupcakes.
4781812d-e701-4abd-8acc-190cfd476fee REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: EASY CLEANUP Use Reynolds® Cut-Rite® Wax Paper to catch excess sprinkles, chopped nuts and coconut. Cleanup is simple and there are no sticky messy countertops when you are done.
e3fe8a16-d2d9-4999-99a4-162202f79ea9 PREHEAT oven to 450°F. Combine turkey, Alfredo sauce, mushrooms, peas and carrots, Parmesan cheese and milk.
e3fe8a16-d2d9-4999-99a4-162202f79ea9 CENTER one-fourth of turkey mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
e3fe8a16-d2d9-4999-99a4-162202f79ea9 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
e3fe8a16-d2d9-4999-99a4-162202f79ea9 BAKE 15 to 18 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven. Stir turkey mixture; spoon over spaghetti. Sprinkle with croutons, if desired.
e3fe8a16-d2d9-4999-99a4-162202f79ea9 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: Packets can be frozen up to 4 weeks. Bake frozen packets on a cookie sheet in preheated 450°F oven 25 to 30 minutes.
bc96e99c-1ac5-4f73-8b75-4edad27045e9 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
bc96e99c-1ac5-4f73-8b75-4edad27045e9 PLACE Reynolds Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
bc96e99c-1ac5-4f73-8b75-4edad27045e9 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
bc96e99c-1ac5-4f73-8b75-4edad27045e9 BAKE following package directions (18 to 22 minutes). Cool.
bc96e99c-1ac5-4f73-8b75-4edad27045e9 TINT frosting pink. Spread the top of each cupcake with tinted frosting.
bc96e99c-1ac5-4f73-8b75-4edad27045e9 SPOON the tinted frosting into a pastry bag fitted with a small star tip.
bc96e99c-1ac5-4f73-8b75-4edad27045e9 PIPE a decorative edge around the edge of each cupcake and fill in with some more frosting.
bc96e99c-1ac5-4f73-8b75-4edad27045e9 ADD a 4 to 6 raspberries in the center of each cupcake.
32e3ded7-1dd0-4c89-8cf2-f4884f9a12b7 PREHEAT grill to mediumhigh or oven to °F. Cut steak lengthwise in half and then crosswise into /inch thick strips. Combine steak strips, peppers with onions, black beans and fajita marinade. CENTER half of steak mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
32e3ded7-1dd0-4c89-8cf2-f4884f9a12b7 BAKE to minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR GRILL to minutes in covered grill. Serve with tortillas; sprinkle with cheese before serving.
a1ce1316-38d1-4829-b9b4-2bf01fcfc33d PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper with parchment side toward food. Crimp Pan Lining Paper around rim of pan; set aside.
a1ce1316-38d1-4829-b9b4-2bf01fcfc33d COMBINE ground beef, pasta sauce and 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Stir pasta into meat sauce; spread half of mixture evenly in pan. Top with half of mozzarella cheese.
a1ce1316-38d1-4829-b9b4-2bf01fcfc33d COMBINE ricotta cheese, egg, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasoning; spread over mozzarella cheese in pan. Spread remaining pasta mixture over ricotta cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
a1ce1316-38d1-4829-b9b4-2bf01fcfc33d COVER with Reynolds Wrap Pan Lining Paper with parchment side toward food.
a1ce1316-38d1-4829-b9b4-2bf01fcfc33d BAKE 45 minutes. Remove cover and CONTINUE BAKING 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
9c009fba-4281-47d5-b5e0-bc1e9ca43e23 Preheat oven to 375° F and line a baking sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper
9c009fba-4281-47d5-b5e0-bc1e9ca43e23 Sift the flour and sea salt in a bowl, set aside
9c009fba-4281-47d5-b5e0-bc1e9ca43e23 In a mixer, mix together the unsalted butter, brown and granulated sugar, baking soda mixture, egg (one at a time), and vanilla until fully blended
9c009fba-4281-47d5-b5e0-bc1e9ca43e23 Slowly add the flour mixture until all the dry and wet ingredients are incorporated (but do not over-mix)
9c009fba-4281-47d5-b5e0-bc1e9ca43e23 Fold in chocolate chunks into cookie dough with spatula (do not over-work)
9c009fba-4281-47d5-b5e0-bc1e9ca43e23 Use a medium-sized ice cream scooper to scoop out evenly-sized balls of dough and place on the lined baking sheet, about 2 inches apart
9c009fba-4281-47d5-b5e0-bc1e9ca43e23 Bake for 8 – 10 minutes, remove from oven and allow to cool on the sheet for an additional 2 minutes
9c009fba-4281-47d5-b5e0-bc1e9ca43e23 Carefully slide parchment paper onto a cooling to cool completely and store in an air-tight container
27600063-fcb1-4540-867d-712f0e9ecdd1 Arrange ribs in a single layer in a shallow roasting pan. Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat for 20 minutes, turning frequently or until browned. Drain well.
27600063-fcb1-4540-867d-712f0e9ecdd1 Meanwhile, place disposable oven bag in a 3-quart rectangular baking dish according to package directions, shaking at least a tablespoon of flour in the bag. Cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag. Combine apples, sauerkraut, cabbage, onion, broth, brown sugar, caraway seed, salt, nutmeg, pepper, and cloves; place in bag. Season ribs with additional salt and pepper, if desired. Place ribs on top of sauerkraut mixture in bag, pushing ribs down into the mixture; close bag.
27600063-fcb1-4540-867d-712f0e9ecdd1 Bake in a 325 degree F oven for 1 to 1-1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove from oven. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.
c7e8c2ac-6c53-4498-84dd-9c1f9f9403b5 PREHEAT oven to 350F.
c7e8c2ac-6c53-4498-84dd-9c1f9f9403b5 Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food.
c7e8c2ac-6c53-4498-84dd-9c1f9f9403b5 COMBINE ground beef, pasta sauce and 2 teaspoons Italian seasoning. Stir pasta into meat sauce; spread half of mixture evenly in pan. Top with half of Mozzarella cheese.
c7e8c2ac-6c53-4498-84dd-9c1f9f9403b5 COMBINE ricotta cheese, egg, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasoning; spread over Mozzarella cheese in pan. Spread remaining pasta mixture over ricotta cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
c7e8c2ac-6c53-4498-84dd-9c1f9f9403b5 COVER with Reynolds® Wrap Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Bake 45 minutes. Remove foil cover and continue baking 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
ee487517-44ad-4d65-a7d9-760d4f3f95bd PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
ee487517-44ad-4d65-a7d9-760d4f3f95bd SHAKE flour in Reynolds Oven Bag; place in 13x9x2-inch baking pan with opening towards wide side of pan.
ee487517-44ad-4d65-a7d9-760d4f3f95bd ADD potatoes to oven bag. Drizzle with olive oil, garlic and spices. Turn bag to coat ingredients; arrange evenly in bag.
ee487517-44ad-4d65-a7d9-760d4f3f95bd CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
ee487517-44ad-4d65-a7d9-760d4f3f95bd BAKE to minutes or until potatoes are done.
7b5773f0-e772-4853-ad64-8b875ff6e1b4 PREHEAT oven to 375°F.Place Reynolds Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch baking dish with opening towards wide side of pan; set aside.
7b5773f0-e772-4853-ad64-8b875ff6e1b4 WHISK together olive oil and flour in a bowl until blended. Add rosemary, thyme, salt and pepper; whisk until well blended.
7b5773f0-e772-4853-ad64-8b875ff6e1b4 PLACE vegetables in oven bag. Pour olive oil mixture over vegetables.
7b5773f0-e772-4853-ad64-8b875ff6e1b4 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie. Turn bag gently to coat vegetables; arrange in an even layer. Cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag; tuck ends of bag in dish.
7b5773f0-e772-4853-ad64-8b875ff6e1b4 BAKE 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Spoon vegetables into a serving dish. If desired, top with extra olive oil and toasted pumpkin seeds.
7b5773f0-e772-4853-ad64-8b875ff6e1b4 REYNOLDS KITCHEN TIPS: -Toasted walnuts can be substituted for the pumpkin seeds. -If baby beets are not available, substitute 3 medium beets, quartered.
eb1bfb53-995f-4891-a891-a7f41672903b OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
eb1bfb53-995f-4891-a891-a7f41672903b COMBINE all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended. Place stuffing mixture into slow cooker liner. Place lid on slow cooker.
eb1bfb53-995f-4891-a891-a7f41672903b COOK on LOW for 3 1/2 to 4 hours or on HIGH for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
eb1bfb53-995f-4891-a891-a7f41672903b CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
eb1bfb53-995f-4891-a891-a7f41672903b REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: Remove lid of slow cooker 15 minutes prior to serving for a drier top.
8829104a-fa9e-481c-b881-f510f579a89d In large bowl, beat brown sugar and / cup butter with electric mixer on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, until light and fluffy. Beat in vanilla, maple flavor, whole egg and egg yolk until well blended. On low speed, beat in flour, baking soda and salt. Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate at least hour for easier handling.
8829104a-fa9e-481c-b881-f510f579a89d Heat oven to °F. Line cookie sheets with parchment paper. Arrange pecan pieces in groups of on cookie sheets to resemble head and legs of turtle. In small bowl, beat egg white with fork or wire whisk. Shape dough into inch balls. Dip bottoms in beaten egg white; press lightly onto pecans (tips of pecans should show).
8829104a-fa9e-481c-b881-f510f579a89d Bake to minutes or until edges are light golden brown. Immediately remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks. Cool completely, about minutes.
8829104a-fa9e-481c-b881-f510f579a89d Meanwhile, in quart saucepan, heat chocolate chips, milk and tablespoon butter over low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in powdered sugar. If necessary, add additional powdered sugar until frosting is spreadable. Frost cooled cookies. Let frosting set before storing in tightly covered container.
b0ee2aad-5f51-44c5-8635-45b8d32a16f0 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line 2 cookie sheets with Reynolds Parchment Paper; set aside. Thaw pastry sheets at room temperature 20 minutes before unfolding.
b0ee2aad-5f51-44c5-8635-45b8d32a16f0 COMBINE spinach, Swiss cheese, onion, cottage cheese, bread crumbs, 2 eggs, salt and nutmeg. On lightly floured sheet of parchment paper, unfold each pastry sheet and roll out into a 12–inch square. Cut each sheet into sixteen 3-inch squares.
b0ee2aad-5f51-44c5-8635-45b8d32a16f0 PLACE 1 teaspoon spinach mixture in center of each square. Beat together remaining egg with water. Brush 2 edges of each square with egg mixture. Fold squares in half to form triangles. Press edges together with a fork. Place filled triangles on parchment-lined cookie sheets; brush with egg mixture. Reynolds Kitchens Tip: To freeze, place a sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-StickFoil over each cookie sheet of unbaked Spinach Bites. To seal packets, fold edges of bottom foil sheet and top foil sheet together. Place cookie sheets with packets in freezer. When frozen, remove cookie sheets from freezer and stack packets in flat layers in the freezer. To bake, preheat oven to 400°F. Return frozen foil packets to cookie sheets, remove top sheet of foil. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
b0ee2aad-5f51-44c5-8635-45b8d32a16f0 BAKE to minutes or until golden brown and puffed.
7768ad73-49e2-48fa-b67f-7550106fdc9e In a medium saucepan combine whipping cream, the 1 tablespoon ancho chile pepper, cinnamon, cayenne pepper, and salt. Bring to boiling. Remove from heat; cover saucepan and let mixture stand for 2 hours.
7768ad73-49e2-48fa-b67f-7550106fdc9e Reheat cream mixture over medium heat just until boiling. Add chocolate pieces. Let stand for 5 minutes. Stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is perfectly smooth.
7768ad73-49e2-48fa-b67f-7550106fdc9e Pour chocolate mixture into a parchment-lined 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Chill for 2 to 4 hours or until set.
7768ad73-49e2-48fa-b67f-7550106fdc9e Using a 1-inch scoop or a measuring tablespoon, scoop chocolate mixture into balls (about 30 balls). Quickly roll balls between palms of your hands to smooth the surface. Place on parchment paper. If necessary, chill for 5 to 10 minutes to set up.
7768ad73-49e2-48fa-b67f-7550106fdc9e In a small bowl combine cocoa powder and the 1-1/2 teaspoons ancho chile pepper. Roll balls in cocoa mixture to coat well. Place balls on a parchment-lined baking sheet and chill until serving time, up to 2 hours. If chilled longer than 30 minutes, let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving. Makes about 30.
00500338-83f8-443e-b3d6-32a6fd7540d7 In large bowl, mix all base ingredients except flour with spoon until well blended. Stir in flour until dough forms. If necessary, cover dough with plastic wrap, and refrigerate hour for easier handling.
00500338-83f8-443e-b3d6-32a6fd7540d7 Heat oven to °F. On wellfloured surface, roll out half of dough at a time into xinch rectangle. With pastry wheel or knife, cut into inch squares. Place / inch apart on cookie sheets lined with parchment paper.
00500338-83f8-443e-b3d6-32a6fd7540d7 Bake to minutes or until set. Immediately remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks. Cool completely, about minutes.
00500338-83f8-443e-b3d6-32a6fd7540d7 In quart saucepan, heat caramels, tablespoons whipping cream and tablespoons butter over low heat, stirring frequently, until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in / cup powdered sugar and the chopped pecans (add additional whipping cream a few drops at a time if needed for desired spreading consistency). Spread teaspoon warm filling on each cookie square.
00500338-83f8-443e-b3d6-32a6fd7540d7 In quart saucepan, heat chocolate chips, tablespoon whipping cream and teaspoons butter over low heat, stirring frequently, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth. REMOVE FROM HEAT. Stir in tablespoons powdered sugar and teaspoon vanilla. Spread glaze evenly over caramel filling on each cookie. Top each with pecan half.
5194758f-eb22-41a1-9ae3-ed200b9328ed PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
5194758f-eb22-41a1-9ae3-ed200b9328ed LINE cookie sheets with Reynolds Parchment Paper; set aside. No need to add extra grease or spray your cookie sheets. KNEAD flour into sugar cookie dough until well blended. ROLL out half of cookie dough at a time to 1/4-inch thickness between lightly floured sheets of Parchment Paper. Using Valentine cookie cutters, cut out cookies; place on parchment-lined cookie sheets.
5194758f-eb22-41a1-9ae3-ed200b9328ed BEAT powdered sugar, meringue powder, water and extract in a large bowl, with an electric mixer, on high speed until smooth and thick, about 1 minute.
5194758f-eb22-41a1-9ae3-ed200b9328ed DIVIDE icing into 3 small bowls. Leave one bowl of icing white. Stir food coloring in remaining 2 bowls to make pink and red icing of desired color. Cover icing tightly when not in use, icing dries quickly.
5194758f-eb22-41a1-9ae3-ed200b9328ed PIPE outlines of cookies with contrasting colors of icing using a decorating bag with tip. Or, place icing in plastic zipper bags. Snip off one corner with scissors and use to pipe icing.
5194758f-eb22-41a1-9ae3-ed200b9328ed FOR SUGARED OUTLINES, sprinkle heavily with sugar crystals or nonpareils while icing is wet. Lightly shake off excess crystals.
5194758f-eb22-41a1-9ae3-ed200b9328ed TO ICE INSIDE OUTLINES, add a little water to thin icing, if necessary. Spoon a small amount of icing onto outlined cookies. Using a brush, small spatula or your finger, spread icing up to outline to fill in spaces.
5194758f-eb22-41a1-9ae3-ed200b9328ed FOR OTHER DECORATIONS, use same techniques for piping dots, drizzles or to write messages.
5194758f-eb22-41a1-9ae3-ed200b9328ed BAKE 7 to 12 minutes, depending on the size of the cookies or until the edges begin to brown. Let stand one minute on cookie sheets. Slide Parchment Paper with cookies onto a wire racks to cool completely.
125fd7a5-72c2-47ba-b3c0-ac3f088f9382 PREHEAT grill to medium-high heat. Place sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil on counter; set aside. Open Mann's Vegetable Medley; set aside.
125fd7a5-72c2-47ba-b3c0-ac3f088f9382 COMBINE olive oil, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper together in a large bowl. Add vegetables; toss to coat evenly. Center vegetables on foil sheet. Add ice cubes.
125fd7a5-72c2-47ba-b3c0-ac3f088f9382 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal making one large packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
125fd7a5-72c2-47ba-b3c0-ac3f088f9382 GRILL covered 10 to 12 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with balsamic vinegar just before serving.
07c00b74-2481-4bab-bea4-118f79e3bc9c In a small bowl, combine tomato, onion, jalapeno, cilantro, lime juice, and salt to taste. Set aside.
07c00b74-2481-4bab-bea4-118f79e3bc9c Heat a grill to high. Coat the flesh side of the avocados with the oil, and season with salt and pepper.
07c00b74-2481-4bab-bea4-118f79e3bc9c Lay a piece of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil on half the grill. Place the avocados, cut side down, on the foil. Cook for 3-4 minutes until nicely browned, moving around if needed to cook evenly.
07c00b74-2481-4bab-bea4-118f79e3bc9c Place avocados on serving platter, and fill the centers with pico de gallo. Dollop some yogurt or sour cream on top of each one. Sprinkle with more salt, and serve with lime wedges and sprigs of cilantro and lime zest.
e136db32-3725-4d14-b985-fa702b613681 PREHEAT grill to 400°F. Cut peaches in half. Discard pits and set aside. Combine brown sugar, honey and cinnamon. Spoon brown sugar mixture into each of the peach cavities.
e136db32-3725-4d14-b985-fa702b613681 USE a fork to poke drainage holes into 8 sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil. Fully wrap each peach in sheet of foil.
e136db32-3725-4d14-b985-fa702b613681 GRILL 5 minutes in covered grill over direct heat. Turn peaches and grill additional 5 minutes or until peaches are tender.
e136db32-3725-4d14-b985-fa702b613681 REMOVE from foil and serve immediately with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
aa531dd0-3c39-441f-bdcb-ba2cefda2e24 PREHEAT oven to 325°F.
aa531dd0-3c39-441f-bdcb-ba2cefda2e24 SHAKE flour in a Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag; place in 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
aa531dd0-3c39-441f-bdcb-ba2cefda2e24 ADD water and soup mix to oven bag. Squeeze oven bag to blend in flour. Add roast to oven bag. Turn oven bag to coat roast with sauce. Place potatoes, onion and carrots in oven bag around roast.
aa531dd0-3c39-441f-bdcb-ba2cefda2e24 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
aa531dd0-3c39-441f-bdcb-ba2cefda2e24 BAKE until roast is tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
aa531dd0-3c39-441f-bdcb-ba2cefda2e24 SPRINKLE with parsley before serving, if desired.
abd5f39a-a9b0-4be9-8f79-3e1ffe499f66 POUR drippings from turkey into a large glass measuring cup.
abd5f39a-a9b0-4be9-8f79-3e1ffe499f66 SPOON off fat from drippings, reserving 3 to 4 tablespoons (discard remaining fat). Set aside remaining drippings.
abd5f39a-a9b0-4be9-8f79-3e1ffe499f66 PLACE reserved fat in medium saucepan. Stir in flour, salt and poultry seasoning.
abd5f39a-a9b0-4be9-8f79-3e1ffe499f66 COOK over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until smooth and bubbly, about 1 minute. If necessary, add water to reserved turkey drippings to measure 2 1/2 cups.
abd5f39a-a9b0-4be9-8f79-3e1ffe499f66 Gradually STIR drippings into flour mixture.
abd5f39a-a9b0-4be9-8f79-3e1ffe499f66 HEAT mixture to boiling, stirring frequently. Boil until thickened, 5 to 7 minutes.
75fe57fa-06da-4fec-a02d-17365eb5a770 Preheat oven to 375°F. Remove neck and giblets from turkey. Rinse, and pat dry.
75fe57fa-06da-4fec-a02d-17365eb5a770 Tear off a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil 2-1/2 times longer than turkey. Place turkey lengthwise in center of aluminum foil sheet to cook.
75fe57fa-06da-4fec-a02d-17365eb5a770 Brush with oil, then fully coat turkey in powdered cheese mixture.
75fe57fa-06da-4fec-a02d-17365eb5a770 Close foil loosely by overlapping the ends. Turn up short sides of aluminum foil to hold in juices. Do not seal airtight. Place foil wrapped turkey in roasting pan at least 2 inches deep. Insert meat thermometer through foil into thickest part of inner thigh, not touching bone.
75fe57fa-06da-4fec-a02d-17365eb5a770 Roast turkey until meat thermometer reads 165°F. Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes. See cooking chart for estimated cooking times.
75fe57fa-06da-4fec-a02d-17365eb5a770 Remove and discard foil. Transfer to a serving dish and add prepared boxed macaroni and cheese for garnish.
789e8b3a-939e-43ca-b773-9a1ac744a381 Preheat oven to 350°F. Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, allspice cloves and salt.
789e8b3a-939e-43ca-b773-9a1ac744a381 Place a Reynolds Kitchens® Turkey Oven Bag into a large roasting pan that is at least two inches deep. Sprinkle one tablespoon of flour into the bag, and shake to distribute.
789e8b3a-939e-43ca-b773-9a1ac744a381 Remove the neck and giblets from the turkey. Rinse, and pat dry. If you like to stuff your turkey, place stuffing into cavity.
789e8b3a-939e-43ca-b773-9a1ac744a381 Brush the turkey with olive oil then rub the pumpkin spice rub all over the turkey.
789e8b3a-939e-43ca-b773-9a1ac744a381 Place turkey in the Turkey Oven Bag and close the bag with the nylon tie included within the Oven Bag box (It’s usually folded inside the cooking chart.)
789e8b3a-939e-43ca-b773-9a1ac744a381 Make 6 half-inch slits in the top of the bag, to allow steam to escape as the turkey cooks. Tuck corners of the bag in the pan and trim or fold down the end of the bag to make sure it doesn’t touch the oven or heating elements when it’s cooking.
789e8b3a-939e-43ca-b773-9a1ac744a381 Insert turkey thermometer through one of the cut slits in the top of the bag, into the thickest part of the turkey thigh. Turkey is done cooking when it reaches an internal temperature of 165°F. See cooking chart for approximate cooking times.
789e8b3a-939e-43ca-b773-9a1ac744a381 Remove from oven and let turkey stand in the bag for 15 minutes. Cut the bag open with cooking shears or a paring knife.
789e8b3a-939e-43ca-b773-9a1ac744a381 Remove the turkey from the bag by inserting serving forks in the neck and chest cavity of the turkey. Then simply lift your Oven Bag Turkey and transfer to a serving dish for dinner. Add desired garnish.
066a5ad3-7a96-4610-9dad-df8d92b7221d PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
066a5ad3-7a96-4610-9dad-df8d92b7221d SHAKE flour in Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag; place in roasting pan at least 2 inches deep. Spray inside of bag with nonstick spray to reduce sticking, if desired.
066a5ad3-7a96-4610-9dad-df8d92b7221d ADD vegetables to oven bag. Remove neck and giblets from turkey. Rinse turkey; pat dry. Lightly stuff with your favorite stuffing recipe, if desired. Brush turkey with oil. Place turkey in bag on top of vegetables.
066a5ad3-7a96-4610-9dad-df8d92b7221d CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2–inch slits in top. Insert meat thermometer through bag into thickest part of inner thigh, not touching bone. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
066a5ad3-7a96-4610-9dad-df8d92b7221d BAKE until meat thermometer reads 180°F, 2 to 2 1/2 hours for a 12 to 16 lb. turkey, 2 1/2 to 3 hours for a 16 to 20 lb. turkey, and 3 to 3 1/2 hours for a 20 to 24 lb. turkey. Add 1/2 hour for stuffed turkey. For easy slicing, let stand in oven bag 15 minutes. If turkey sticks to bag, gently loosen bag from turkey before opening oven bag.
066a5ad3-7a96-4610-9dad-df8d92b7221d REYNOLDS KITCHEN TIP: Estimate 1 pound per person for generous servings with leftovers.
40354b7d-83b0-4866-a3f3-2c4d5f860adb Preheat grill on high heat.
40354b7d-83b0-4866-a3f3-2c4d5f860adb Tear a square of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil and brush with olive oil. Roll pizza dough onto foil and top with pizza sauce, mozzarella, goat cheese, red peppers and salami.
40354b7d-83b0-4866-a3f3-2c4d5f860adb Pick up the edges of the Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil and place directly on grill. Close grill and allow to cook for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese is melted and edges begin to char.
40354b7d-83b0-4866-a3f3-2c4d5f860adb Remove from grill and transfer to a cutting board. Drizzle with honey and red pepper flakes before serving.
7c186290-5533-4fc9-bb4e-d979a42324d8 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food.
7c186290-5533-4fc9-bb4e-d979a42324d8 PLACE tilapia in foil-lined pan.
7c186290-5533-4fc9-bb4e-d979a42324d8 MIX lime juice, olive oil, seafood seasoning, garlic, salt and red pepper flakes in a medium bowl until well blended. Pour over fish.
7c186290-5533-4fc9-bb4e-d979a42324d8 BAKE 18 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Serve 1/2 fillet in each tortilla with lettuce, salsa and avocado.
6ff7d5a2-c9ce-447f-bf18-4bf8ae260192 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
6ff7d5a2-c9ce-447f-bf18-4bf8ae260192 In a large pot of boiling water, cook the pasta according to the package directions until al dente. drain well.
6ff7d5a2-c9ce-447f-bf18-4bf8ae260192 Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat the oil over medium-low heat. Add the onions and cook until soft, about 4-5 minutes. Stir in the garlic and cook for 30 seconds. Stir in the beef and cook until browned; season with salt and pepper. Stir in the tomato paste, then add the tomatoes with their juices and mustard. Let the mixture bubble gently until it has slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.
6ff7d5a2-c9ce-447f-bf18-4bf8ae260192 Toss the meat mixture with the pasta and spread it into Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan. Top with the cheddar and bake until the cheese is melted, about 10 minutes. Sprinkle the lettuce and chopped pickles over the top and serve. You can also add fresh chopped tomatoes and green onions over the top.
707fc7c5-f38d-4aac-9aad-5a2db2b04898 Line a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
707fc7c5-f38d-4aac-9aad-5a2db2b04898 Place chicken in slow cooker. Top with 1 can of enchilada sauce.
707fc7c5-f38d-4aac-9aad-5a2db2b04898 Cover the slow cooker and cook on low for 4–6 hours.
707fc7c5-f38d-4aac-9aad-5a2db2b04898 Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Remove the chicken and place on a cutting board. Use two forks to shred, or use your stand mixer to help speed up the process. Place the chicken in the mixer and turn the mixer to low for about 30 seconds. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
707fc7c5-f38d-4aac-9aad-5a2db2b04898 Line a cookie sheet with the Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil, facing the dull side up. Line the foil with tortilla chips and top with the chicken, black beans and shredded cheese. Bake for about 10 minutes, until the cheese is all melted. Remove nachos from oven and top with sliced olives, salsa, avocados, banana peppers and any other fixings of your choosing!
46736844-329a-4a89-8087-03ba83ba947c Place popcorn in a large bowl.
46736844-329a-4a89-8087-03ba83ba947c Make it sweet: Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium-low heat. Add brown sugar and cook, stirring constantly for 30 seconds. Pour over popcorn and toss. Drizzle on melted chocolate and toss again. Sift powdered sugar on top and toss again. Serve immediately.
46736844-329a-4a89-8087-03ba83ba947c Make it spicy: Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium-low heat. Stir in lime juice. Pour over popcorn and toss. Combine salt, red pepper flakes and chili powder. Sprinkle on popcorn and toss. Serve immediately.
46736844-329a-4a89-8087-03ba83ba947c Make it savory: Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium-low heat. Add garlic and cook for 2 minutes. Pour over popcorn and toss. Combine Italian seasoning, salt and paprika. Sprinkle on popcorn and toss. Sprinkle cheese on top and toss again. Serve immediately.
d95ec49b-3775-44cf-b063-1ac3b9b25d4a Thread a strawberry, pineapple and cake on a skewer, repeating two more times per skewer. Heat the honey and lime juice in the microwave for 30-seconds and brush on each skewer.
d95ec49b-3775-44cf-b063-1ac3b9b25d4a Line Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil on the grill, dull side facing the food and punch holes all over to allow the juices to drip through. Cook on low, turning the skewers to evenly brown all of the sides.
d95ec49b-3775-44cf-b063-1ac3b9b25d4a Once they are browned, remove them from the grill. Melt the chocolate chips in the microwave, for 45-seconds, and drizzle the melted chocolate on the fruit skewers.
d95ec49b-3775-44cf-b063-1ac3b9b25d4a Serve and enjoy!
13892479-cd89-40ef-ad16-e53aa903a5bf Wash and dry all the vegetables. Cut into desired portions.
13892479-cd89-40ef-ad16-e53aa903a5bf Line a vegetable grilling tray with the foil and create incisions into the holes on the tray so that heat passes through.
13892479-cd89-40ef-ad16-e53aa903a5bf Season the vegetables with your favorite seasoning, as well as salt and pepper. If your seasoning is salty, skip the salt.
13892479-cd89-40ef-ad16-e53aa903a5bf Spray the veggies with avocado oil and grill on your preheated grill for anywhere from 5 to 10 minutes, depending on how big you cut the veggies and the type of veggies you use. Remember to turn the veggies over halfway through so the other side cooks as well.
13892479-cd89-40ef-ad16-e53aa903a5bf Once the veggies have cooked through, transfer them to a platter lined with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil for easy cleanup.
13892479-cd89-40ef-ad16-e53aa903a5bf Serve and enjoy!
a48b3ae9-405b-4abd-b0bc-c2fc4ff41dce Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.
a48b3ae9-405b-4abd-b0bc-c2fc4ff41dce Peel, core, and roughly chop your apples into bitesize pieces. In a large bowl, combine apples, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg, as well as 1/2 cup water. Mix to combine.
a48b3ae9-405b-4abd-b0bc-c2fc4ff41dce Place flour in Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag. Close the bag with your hands and give it a good shake to distribute the flour throughout the bag. Place the Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag in your ovensafe baking dish and then add your apple mixture to the bag. Add the remaining 1/2 cup of water.
a48b3ae9-405b-4abd-b0bc-c2fc4ff41dce Use the provided oven bag ties and close the bag. Then cut small slits in the top of the oven bag to provide some ventilation while cooking. Tuck the area of the bag where the opening and tab closure is under the rest of the bag, and place in the oven for 45 minutes.
a48b3ae9-405b-4abd-b0bc-c2fc4ff41dce When you remove your apples from the oven, give them a touch (be sure you are wearing oven mitts!). If they still seem somewhat firm, put them back in the oven. If they give easily, then they are ready! Carefully cut a large slit in the bag (watch out for the steam!) and give the apple mixture a good stir. Let it cool for 10 minutes.
a48b3ae9-405b-4abd-b0bc-c2fc4ff41dce Once it has cooled down a bit, transfer the mixture to a food processor, or to a large bowl if you have a hand held blender. Using either tool, blend the ingredients until you have achieved your desired consistency. Sprinkle each serving with a little extra cinnamon, if so desired. Enjoy!
7594f828-03b0-4d7c-abd0-a8ee48d8a035 Preheat the grill to 500° F.
7594f828-03b0-4d7c-abd0-a8ee48d8a035 Prepare all topping ingredients (if using).
7594f828-03b0-4d7c-abd0-a8ee48d8a035 Cut an 18-inch piece of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil. Place the foil dull-side up and roll out the pizza dough to 1/2-inch thick (or thinner if desired) directly on the foil. Brush both sides of the dough with olive oil.
7594f828-03b0-4d7c-abd0-a8ee48d8a035 Transfer the foil to the preheated grill and cook 4–5 minutes or until the dough begins to bubble and is lightly browned on the bottom.
7594f828-03b0-4d7c-abd0-a8ee48d8a035 Using tongs, flip the dough over and add pizza sauce, toppings and cheese. Reduce the heat to medium-high, about 400° F.
7594f828-03b0-4d7c-abd0-a8ee48d8a035 Close the lid of the grill and cook for an additional 4 minutes or until cheese has melted and dough is cooked through.
7594f828-03b0-4d7c-abd0-a8ee48d8a035 Cool 5 minutes before cutting.
f99eb504-f7e6-434f-89b0-3284df3593a2 Preheat oven to Hi-Broil. Place chilies on a foil-lined baking sheet and broil until skin is blackened, 10–12 minutes, checking often.
f99eb504-f7e6-434f-89b0-3284df3593a2 Wrap foil around chilies and let sit 10 minutes.
f99eb504-f7e6-434f-89b0-3284df3593a2 Scrape off loose skin and discard most of the seeds. Chop finely.
f99eb504-f7e6-434f-89b0-3284df3593a2 Mix together chicken, corn, sour cream, oregano and salt.
f99eb504-f7e6-434f-89b0-3284df3593a2 Place a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner inside a 5–61⁄2 quart slow cooker bowl as directed on package.
f99eb504-f7e6-434f-89b0-3284df3593a2 Using half of each ingredient, layer beans, scallions, sour cream mixture, jalapeños, salsa, tomatoes and cheese.
f99eb504-f7e6-434f-89b0-3284df3593a2 Repeat, ending with cheese.
f99eb504-f7e6-434f-89b0-3284df3593a2 Cover slow cooker and cook on Low for 3–31⁄2 hours. Use Warm setting to serve.
f99eb504-f7e6-434f-89b0-3284df3593a2 Serve with tortilla chips and sliced raw vegetables for dipping.
58b2e86a-2980-4d57-af3f-8c75d2257ed4 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
58b2e86a-2980-4d57-af3f-8c75d2257ed4 PRESS pizza dough into 10-inch round on parchment-lined cookie sheet. Prick dough with fork.
58b2e86a-2980-4d57-af3f-8c75d2257ed4 BAKE 14 to 17 minutes or until golden brown. Cool. Slide pizza crust onto 12-inch round serving platter.
58b2e86a-2980-4d57-af3f-8c75d2257ed4 COMBINE softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings in small bowl; mix well. Spread cream cheese mixture over pizza crust. Top with chopped vegetables. Sprinkle with matchstick carrots. Chill 1 hour before serving
f5ea3e78-9f0f-4205-b049-c2112c064670 Preheat oven to 350°F.
f5ea3e78-9f0f-4205-b049-c2112c064670 Line a muffin pan with Reynolds® StayBrite®Baking Cups and set aside. Soften the apples by folding the apples, sugar and lemon juice in a large bowl and set aside.
f5ea3e78-9f0f-4205-b049-c2112c064670 In another large bowl combine flour, dark brown sugar, ground cinnamon, ground nutmeg baking powder, baking soda. Pour in melted butter and mix with a fork or your fingers until a crumbly flour mixture is formed.
f5ea3e78-9f0f-4205-b049-c2112c064670 In a medium bowl, mix together eggs, buttermilk and vanilla to create buttermilk mixture. Once incorporated, add buttermilk mixture to flour mixture and fold in macerated apples.
f5ea3e78-9f0f-4205-b049-c2112c064670 Use an ice cream scooper to scoop mixture into the baking cups.
22b82bf5-f2b3-40e4-9b96-781a39f38b14 Preheat grill to medium-high heat.
22b82bf5-f2b3-40e4-9b96-781a39f38b14 Whisk together ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar, molasses, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, garlic powder, onion powder, pepper and 1/4 cup water. Reserve 1/3 cup and set aside.
22b82bf5-f2b3-40e4-9b96-781a39f38b14 Combine ketchup mixture and chicken in a gallon-size slider bag or large bowl; marinate for at least 1 hour to overnight, turning the bag occasionally. Drain the chicken from the marinade.
22b82bf5-f2b3-40e4-9b96-781a39f38b14 Make drainage holes in a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with a grilling fork. Place foil sheet on grill grate with non-stick (dull) side facing up. Immediately place chicken on foil.
22b82bf5-f2b3-40e4-9b96-781a39f38b14 Add chicken to grill and cook, flipping once and basting with reserved 1/3 cup marinade until cooked through, about 10 to 12 minutes on each side.
22b82bf5-f2b3-40e4-9b96-781a39f38b14 Serve immediately, garnished with parsley, if desired.
9bfa105b-eac4-4472-8d0e-10c067847cd0 Preheat the grill to high heat.
9bfa105b-eac4-4472-8d0e-10c067847cd0 Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large pot on medium-high heat and add the onions and brown, about 6 to 8 minutes.
9bfa105b-eac4-4472-8d0e-10c067847cd0 Add in the grits and 6 cups of water and stir over medium-low heat until the grits have absorbed the water and are cooked through, about 20 to 25 minutes.
9bfa105b-eac4-4472-8d0e-10c067847cd0 Whisk the cheese into the grits and season with salt and pepper. Keep warm.
9bfa105b-eac4-4472-8d0e-10c067847cd0 Line a hot grill with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
9bfa105b-eac4-4472-8d0e-10c067847cd0 Combine the shrimp, paprika, cumin and remaining 3 tablespoons of olive oil in a bowl and mix.
9bfa105b-eac4-4472-8d0e-10c067847cd0 Place the shrimp right onto the foil on the grill and cook for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until browned and cooked throughout.
9bfa105b-eac4-4472-8d0e-10c067847cd0 Pour the BBQ sauce on top of the shrimp and mix.
9bfa105b-eac4-4472-8d0e-10c067847cd0 Serve the BBQ shrimp with the cheesy grits.
181e79bb-a744-464e-b73a-20203b3cf737 Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.
181e79bb-a744-464e-b73a-20203b3cf737 Place the boneless chicken breasts in a foil-lined baking dish. Sprinkle herbs, salt and pepper generously over the top of the breasts and roast until cooked through and tender, approximately 20-25 minutes.
181e79bb-a744-464e-b73a-20203b3cf737 While the chicken roasts, in a saucepan with a lid, melt butter over medium high heat then add carrots, onion and celery and sauté until tender – approximately 5 minutes. Add rice and sauté for two more minutes stirring often. Add bay leaf, pour in chicken stock and bring to a boil. Cover with lid and reduce heat to a simmer, cooking rice until tender (approximately 12 minutes.) When rice is tender, add peas and stir. Cover and allow to sit for a few minutes in order for the peas to heat through. Remove and discard bay leaf.
181e79bb-a744-464e-b73a-20203b3cf737 Remove chicken from the oven and place on a cutting board. Pour juices from roasted chicken into the pot of rice and vegetable. Cut chicken breasts into bite-sized chunks, then stir into rice.
181e79bb-a744-464e-b73a-20203b3cf737 Add salt and pepper to taste if desired. Serve immediately
181e79bb-a744-464e-b73a-20203b3cf737 Store leftovers in Reynolds Heat and Eat containers
a5b84f4c-7786-4448-97bb-631060a04977 Heat a grill to about 375 degrees F.
a5b84f4c-7786-4448-97bb-631060a04977 Add potato pieces to a large pot of water and bring to a boil. Simmer for 10 minutes, just to jump-start the cooking process.
a5b84f4c-7786-4448-97bb-631060a04977 Arrange roughly 12x18-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil on a clean work surface.
a5b84f4c-7786-4448-97bb-631060a04977 Divide the shrimp, slightly cooked potatoes, kielbasa and corn atop the four pieces of foil, piling in the center. Add one tablespoon of butter to each pile. Drizzle each with 1 tablespoon olive oil, sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and sprinkle each generously with creole seasoning. Squeeze a lemon onto each pile, and add the lemon to the shrimp, potato and corn mixture. Sprinkle with black pepper.
a5b84f4c-7786-4448-97bb-631060a04977 Wrap each piece of foil into a tightly sealed pouch. Place on the grill. Cover. Allow to cook and steam for 15 to 18 minutes until the shrimp and potatoes are cooked through.
a5b84f4c-7786-4448-97bb-631060a04977 Serve by carefully unwrapping the foil and serving with slices of bread and hot sauce.
6d597f52-5d11-4205-9441-e531ec1db611 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Place Reynolds® Baking Cups in a muffin pan; set aside.
6d597f52-5d11-4205-9441-e531ec1db611 COMBINE topping ingredients until crumbly; set aside.
6d597f52-5d11-4205-9441-e531ec1db611 MAKE muffins: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
6d597f52-5d11-4205-9441-e531ec1db611 BEAT together yogurt, egg, oil and milk in small bowl. Add to flour mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Gently stir in apples and raisins.
6d597f52-5d11-4205-9441-e531ec1db611 SPOON batter into baking cups, filling even with top of baking cups. Sprinkle topping over each muffin.
6d597f52-5d11-4205-9441-e531ec1db611 BAKE 23 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan.
6ffc7810-3861-4545-bdce-af5fa0845bda PREHEAT oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit
6ffc7810-3861-4545-bdce-af5fa0845bda CRACK eggs into bowl, and mix with milk, green onion and cheese
6ffc7810-3861-4545-bdce-af5fa0845bda LINE cupcake tin with Reynolds® Stay Brite Baking Cups. Wrap slice of bacon around the inside of the baking cup.
6ffc7810-3861-4545-bdce-af5fa0845bda FILL bacon-lined baking cup 1/3 full with egg mixture.
6ffc7810-3861-4545-bdce-af5fa0845bda BAKE until cooked all the way through, about 20 – 25 minutes
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 Pre-heat oven to 400°, clean Salmon and pat dry
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 Use a round biscuit or cookie cutter to cut out round pieces of salmon and set aside
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 Use <a href="/products/parchment-paper/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Reynolds® Parchment Paper</span></a> to create a heart shaped parchment pouch (en papillote) like I did when making <a href="/kitchen-tips/tip-technique-items/ginger-shrimp-and-broccoli-en-papillote/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Ginger Shrimp & Broccoli</span></a>
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 Place 2-3 round salmon pieces on the right side of your parchment pouch, drizzle each piece with extra virgin olive oil, lemon juice, sea salt and black pepper – fold other side over to cover the salmon and fold over to close
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 Bake for 15-17 minutes
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 LET’S MAKE THE BEARNAISE SAUCE – over medium heat melt 1 tbsp. unsalted butter in medium sauce pan, once butter is melted add shallots and allow to cook for 1 minute, then add white wine and white vinegar allow to cook for 5 minutes then set aside to cool about 5 minutes
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 In medium bowl add yolks and cooled shallots, wine and vinegar and use hand mixer to begin mixing on low for 30 seconds, begin to slowly pour the melted butter into the bowl and continue to use hand mixer on low in intervals until all butter is incorporated
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 Once butter is incorporated, add lemon juice, sea salt and tarragon, then mix on medium speed for 2-3 minutes or until sauce is creamy and has thickened
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 LET’S MAKE THE GRITS – over high heat bring water to a boil, once boiling add grits and turn heat down to medium and allow to cook uncovered whisking periodically until water has evaporated, slowly add milk and continue to whisk, add butter and sea salt
ef753eda-fa34-400c-8e7d-1478ffda5950 Plate as follows: grits, salmon & béarnaise sauce
e47b19c5-0049-4911-9440-210a6a5d83f8 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
e47b19c5-0049-4911-9440-210a6a5d83f8 CENTER one pork chop on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Arrange vegetables beside each pork chop. Sprinkle pork chops and vegetables with garlic salt. Combine barbecue sauce, celery and onions; spoon over pork chops.
e47b19c5-0049-4911-9440-210a6a5d83f8 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
e47b19c5-0049-4911-9440-210a6a5d83f8 *THE REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: Substitute any combination of the following vegetables to equal 2 cups: frozen whole kernel corn, whole green beans and baby peas.
e47b19c5-0049-4911-9440-210a6a5d83f8 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR
e47b19c5-0049-4911-9440-210a6a5d83f8 GRILL 14 to 16 minutes in covered grill. Serve with rice, if desired.
67e50a65-1e17-4c01-9b2a-a43e4000eacd PREHEAT oven to 450°F. MIX melted butter, soy sauce, rice vinegar and brown sugar in a small bowl; set aside.
67e50a65-1e17-4c01-9b2a-a43e4000eacd MIX remaining ingredients in a large bowl. PLACE half the veggie mix in center of sheet of foil. SPOON half the butter mixture over veggies.
67e50a65-1e17-4c01-9b2a-a43e4000eacd BRING up sides of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil over veggies; fold down two times. DOUBLE FOLD both ends of foil to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. REPEAT to make second packet. PLACE packets on baking sheet with 1-inch sides.
67e50a65-1e17-4c01-9b2a-a43e4000eacd BAKE 15 to 20 minutes or until veggies are desired crispness. OPEN packets carefully by cutting along top folds with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape. STIR to coat evenly.
d7ffd47f-0863-4e0c-9823-3d62b9d45dab PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
d7ffd47f-0863-4e0c-9823-3d62b9d45dab COMBINE ground beef, pasta sauce and 2 teaspoons Italian seasoning. Stir pasta into meat sauce; spread half of mixture evenly in parchment-lined pan. Top with half of Mozzarella cheese.
d7ffd47f-0863-4e0c-9823-3d62b9d45dab COMBINE ricotta cheese, egg, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasoning; spread over Mozzarella cheese in pan. Spread remaining pasta mixture over ricotta cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
d7ffd47f-0863-4e0c-9823-3d62b9d45dab BAKE to minutes or until hot and cheese is golden brown. Let stand minutes before serving.
893371e2-005a-4faa-bd8d-27b83cf322ce PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 9x5-inch loaf pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, extending paper up sides of pan; set aside.
893371e2-005a-4faa-bd8d-27b83cf322ce COMBINE flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt on a sheet of parchment paper; set aside. In a large bowl combine bananas, eggs, oil, milk and vanilla extract. Add dry ingredients to banana mixture; stir just until moistened. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips; pour into parchment lined-pan.
893371e2-005a-4faa-bd8d-27b83cf322ce BAKE to minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool minutes in pan. Use edges of parchment to lift bread from pan onto a wire rack. Pull back edges of parchment. Cool completely.
5a014b60-7951-4735-87ec-efdfa444b266 PREHEAT oven to 325°F. SHAKE flour and pepper in Reynolds™ Oven Bag, Large Size; place in 13x9-inch baking pan. Add broth to bag. Squeeze bag to blend in flour.
5a014b60-7951-4735-87ec-efdfa444b266 PLACE onions in single layer in bottom of bag. Add roast to bag. Sprinkle soup mix over meat; press into all sides of meat.
5a014b60-7951-4735-87ec-efdfa444b266 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
5a014b60-7951-4735-87ec-efdfa444b266 BAKE 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until meat thermometer reaches desired doneness, 145F for medium and 160F for well done. Let sit 10 minutes. Slice meat thinly across the grain. Pile slices into sandwich rolls; top with some of the onions. Top with cheese is desired. Spoon juices into small individual bowls for dipping.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Scrape seeds from vanilla bean into a small food processor. Add sugar, anise seeds, and lemon peel; cover and pulse several times to combine.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 In a large mixing bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Add sugar mixture and lemon juice.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Beat until fluffy, scraping bowl occasionally. Beat in flour and salt until combined.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Divide dough in half. Cover and chill 1 hour or until dough is easy to handle.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Preheat oven to 275 degrees F.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 On a lightly floured surface, roll half the dough at a time to 1/2 inch thick. Using a 2- to 2-1/2-inch fluted round cookie cutter, cut out dough.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Sprinkle cookies with cinnamon sugar.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Place cutouts on Reynolds® Parchment Paper lined cookie sheet.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 In a medium bowl, combine 2 cups powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons milk, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Beat together with an electric mixer on medium speed until combined.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Add more milk, if necessary, to make a spoonable glaze.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Bake in the preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until edges are firm to the touch.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Cool on cookie sheet 2 minutes. Transfer cookies to a wire rack; let cool.
0c3f4065-47da-44b6-bdc4-3f572f9d1229 Spoon Lemon Glaze evenly over cookies. Let cookies stand until glaze is set.
121db797-6360-4926-8b1f-8ffe9fe6bef2 In a large bowl, combine blackberries, blueberries, sugar, 1/4 cup flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
121db797-6360-4926-8b1f-8ffe9fe6bef2 Preheat the oven to 375, and let the berry mixture sit while the oven preheats.
121db797-6360-4926-8b1f-8ffe9fe6bef2 Once the oven is ready, pour the berry mixture into an 8” x 8” Reynolds® Bakeware pan (disposable, non-stick...just perfect!). Cover the top of the bakeware pan tightly with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Place in the oven for 30 minutes.
121db797-6360-4926-8b1f-8ffe9fe6bef2 While the berry mixture cooks, prepare the topping.
121db797-6360-4926-8b1f-8ffe9fe6bef2 In a food processor, combine graham crackers, 1/3 cup flour, brown sugar, shredded coconut and butter.
121db797-6360-4926-8b1f-8ffe9fe6bef2 Pulse mixture until well combined.
121db797-6360-4926-8b1f-8ffe9fe6bef2 After 30 minutes in the oven, remove the foil cover from the pan. Sprinkle the topping evenly over the fruit mixture.
121db797-6360-4926-8b1f-8ffe9fe6bef2 Cook for an additional 15 minutes with the foil lid removed.
121db797-6360-4926-8b1f-8ffe9fe6bef2 Optional: set the oven to broil for the last minute of cooking for a browned top. Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.
4afa9c3e-e42c-4da5-8057-4fae37f355e3 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
4afa9c3e-e42c-4da5-8057-4fae37f355e3 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups
4afa9c3e-e42c-4da5-8057-4fae37f355e3 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
4afa9c3e-e42c-4da5-8057-4fae37f355e3 PLACE the black sugar in a medium bowl.
4afa9c3e-e42c-4da5-8057-4fae37f355e3 SPREAD the top of each cupcake with the dark chocolate frosting.
4afa9c3e-e42c-4da5-8057-4fae37f355e3 LIGHTLY PRESS each frosted cupcake into the black sugar to coat.
4afa9c3e-e42c-4da5-8057-4fae37f355e3 SPOON the vanilla frosting into a zipper bag. Snip a very small corner, (1/16 inch) from the bag.
4afa9c3e-e42c-4da5-8057-4fae37f355e3 PIPE swirly designs on top of each cupcake, making sure to anchor the frosting in the sugar.
1a6a644e-748c-43fd-b9fb-ad36071848d7 COMBINE olive oil, salt, and 1/2 teaspoon black pepper in a small bowl. Center half of the mushrooms and onion on a sheet (12x18 inches) of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Drizzle with half of the olive oil mixture. Bring up foil sides. Double-fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
1a6a644e-748c-43fd-b9fb-ad36071848d7 LINE a baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Mix the beef, Worcestershire sauce, and 1/2 teaspoon black pepper in a large bowl until combined. Shape beef mixture into eight thin, 4-inch diameter patties on the prepared baking sheet. Place 1 tablespoon of the blue cheese onto the center of each of four of the patties. Top with the remaining four patties; pinch edges to seal.
1a6a644e-748c-43fd-b9fb-ad36071848d7 TRANSFER burgers on the foil and foil packets to the rack of an uncovered grill directly over medium-high heat and grill for 10 minutes or until burgers are done (160°F) and vegetables are tender. Toast cut sides of hamburger buns during the last minute of grilling.
1a6a644e-748c-43fd-b9fb-ad36071848d7 OPEN packets carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape; then open top of foil packet.
1a6a644e-748c-43fd-b9fb-ad36071848d7 SERVE burgers on buns with grilled vegetables and lettuce and/or tomato slices, if desired.
e83c9078-2f17-4c48-928f-5b491b081997 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place Reynolds® Foil Baking Cups in muffin pans or on a cookie sheet; set aside.
e83c9078-2f17-4c48-928f-5b491b081997 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes, adding 2 tablespoons bourbon to batter. Spoon batter into baking cups.
e83c9078-2f17-4c48-928f-5b491b081997 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes. Cool.
e83c9078-2f17-4c48-928f-5b491b081997 MIX remaining bourbon, butter, milk and vanilla extract until blended. Gradually add powdered sugar until blended. Stir in walnuts. Frost cupcakes.
c0398ed4-9f50-4076-8bcf-837864d6f6ac PREHEAT grill to medium high OR oven to 450°F. CENTER sausages on sheet of Reynolds Wrap Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Top with tablespoons onions and peppers. BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to form one large foil packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
c0398ed4-9f50-4076-8bcf-837864d6f6ac GRILL 20 minutes in covered grill OR BAKE 25 to 30 minutes on cookie sheet in oven. Serve on buns.
4a252241-9fbc-44b1-bf58-1b7ca1a29cc8 PREHEAT oven to 425°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food.
4a252241-9fbc-44b1-bf58-1b7ca1a29cc8 MIX broccoli, soup, stuffing mix, 1/2 cup cheese and water together in a large bowl until well blended. Spread evenly in foil-lined pan.
4a252241-9fbc-44b1-bf58-1b7ca1a29cc8 TOP with chicken. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
4a252241-9fbc-44b1-bf58-1b7ca1a29cc8 BAKE to minutes or until chicken reaches °F and juices run clear. Top with remaining / cup cheese. Cover with a sheet of nonstick foil; let stand until cheese melts.
8591b55d-f2a6-4d51-be13-f3de974f5cdc Heat oven to 325F and place rack in center.
8591b55d-f2a6-4d51-be13-f3de974f5cdc Line two baking sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. On a floured work surface, using a floured rolling pin, roll out dough to about 1/8 inch thick, occasionally running a spatula under dough to keep from sticking to work surface.
8591b55d-f2a6-4d51-be13-f3de974f5cdc Using 1-1/4-, 1-3/4-, 2-1/2- and 3-inch star cookie cutters, cut out ten 1-1/4-inch and 20 of each of the other sizes; transfer to prepared sheets.
8591b55d-f2a6-4d51-be13-f3de974f5cdc Bake, one sheet at a time, until just golden around edges, 8 to 10 minutes.
8591b55d-f2a6-4d51-be13-f3de974f5cdc Transfer sheets to a wire rack and let cool completely. Transfer icing to a decorating bag fitted with a small plain. Secure end of bag with a rubber band, squeezing out air. (When not using, place, tip side down, in a tall glass with a damp paper towel in bottom so icing doesn't harden in tip.)
8591b55d-f2a6-4d51-be13-f3de974f5cdc Working with one cookie at a time, pipe icing around rim of each star and sprinkle with sanding sugar. Let stand until set, about 30 minutes.
8591b55d-f2a6-4d51-be13-f3de974f5cdc For each tree, using a dab of icing to adhere, stack 2 large, 2 medium, 2 small and 1 tiny star; top with a gumdrop.
818a8637-5093-449f-a207-3995d1994b64 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
818a8637-5093-449f-a207-3995d1994b64 CUT the grilled chicken into ½ inch chunks and toss them in a large bowl along with the buffalo wing sauce until every piece of chicken is coated.
818a8637-5093-449f-a207-3995d1994b64 PLACE the buffalo chicken into a Reynolds® 12x9 Bakeware casserole dish.
818a8637-5093-449f-a207-3995d1994b64 EVENLY SPREAD on the provolone cheese on top of the buffalo chicken.
818a8637-5093-449f-a207-3995d1994b64 BAKE the chicken for 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
818a8637-5093-449f-a207-3995d1994b64 SERVE the buffalo chicken alongside some celery and carrot sticks, blue cheese and ranch dressing, and mini hamburger buns.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups (Dots) in muffin pans; set aside.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 BAKE following package directions (18 to 22 minutes). Cool.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 SPREAD thin layer of frosting on each cupcake; set aside.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 DIVIDE remaining frosting evenly into two bowls. Leave one bowl white, tint the other bowl black.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 ROLL OUT pink fondant for bunny heads. Cut round shapes the same size as top of cupcake. Place fondant circles on top of cupcakes.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 MAKE AND ASSEMBLE bunny face
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Roll pink fondant into one oval shaped ball about 1/8" wide x 1/4" long.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Use paintbrush to brush one side lightly with water and attach to center of cupcake. This will be the nose.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Roll white fondant into two thin stips about 1/2" square. Place these teeth on the head, about 1/4" below nose.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Roll pink fondant into two egg-shaped balls that will form the cheeks.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Use a wooden toothpick or skewer to make the small indentions that give the cheeks dimension.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Brush back-sides lightly with water and attach at 45 degree angles just below the nose and on top of the upper part of the teeth.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 For ears, roll out pink fondant and cut into slightly rounded, ear-shaped triangles. Bend their tops slightly forward to give them shape. Let dry.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Brush water lightly on back of the bottom edge of ears to attach.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Prepare piping bags with white and black frosting. If using a zipper bag, be sure to snip just a tiny corner off the bag so that the lines are delicate.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Use white frosting to pipe two small circles for eyes and three straight lines on each side of the nose for whiskers.
3bf135d8-52fa-44e7-a052-2b8419c1a423 Pipe black icing onto centers of eyes and eyebrows.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 PLACE 24 Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups (Dots) in muffin pans; set aside.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 MAKE AND ASSEMBLE the butterfly wings 1.Line 2 cookie sheets with Reynolds® Cut-Rite® Wax Paper. 2.Pipe lines of the butterfly wings with melted chocolate. 3.While the chocolate is still wet, sprinkle the tops with pink sugar. Continue to make 48 wings. 4.Place the cookie sheets in the refrigerator until set, about 5 minutes.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 TINT frosting green. Spread the top of each cupcake with tinted frosting.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 TINT coconut green with food coloring. Top each cupcake with green coconut.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 ADD some of the flower sprinkles to coconut.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 PEEL the chocolate wings from the wax paper.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 PLACE 2 wings in the center of each cupcake.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 SPOON chocolate frosting into a zipperbag. Snip a small corner from the bag and pipe the body in between the chocolate wings.
1413b688-2e9c-4866-926e-6db727bbc9c6 INSERT 2 licorice pieces as antennae on each cupcake.
10bb40f6-a10d-40c8-aa67-bbd0ec929b75 In a medium mixing bowl, combine the flour, salt and sugar. Use hands to cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs and no pieces are larger than a pea. Stir in the cold buttermilk until mixture starts to clump together. Use hands to form the dough into a tight ball, pat it into a disk about 1 1/2-inch thick and wrap tightly in plastic wrap. Chill for a least an hour and up to a day.
10bb40f6-a10d-40c8-aa67-bbd0ec929b75 Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. On a floured surface, roll piecrust into a large circle. Press dough into a pie pan. Line the crust with a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and fill the foil with pie weights or dried rice/beans. Make sure to get the weights into the corners of the pie and press into the bottom and sides. Chill the crust for 15 minutes and then bake for 15 minutes. Remove pie crust from the oven and remove the weights and foil. Reduce the oven to 350 degrees F and let the crust cool while you make the filling.
10bb40f6-a10d-40c8-aa67-bbd0ec929b75 Beat egg whites in a stand mixer with whisk attachment until soft peaks form. Set aside. Using the whisk attachment, cream butter and sugar. Add yolks to butter-sugar mixture and combine well. Add the flour, lemon juice, nutmeg and salt to the mixture. Slowly add in buttermilk and mix for 1 minute. Buttermilk will curdle slightly but will smooth out upon baking.
10bb40f6-a10d-40c8-aa67-bbd0ec929b75 Gently fold the egg whites into the buttermilk mixture. Pour mixture into the crust. Smooth with spatula and bake for 45–50 minutes or until golden and set in the middle. Cool thoroughly on a rack before serving.
e2f614a9-327a-456e-aa1f-f3a5d6a219c8 PREHEAT oven to 450°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil; set aside.
e2f614a9-327a-456e-aa1f-f3a5d6a219c8 MIX olive oil, 1/2 teaspoon parsley, seasoned salt and pepper in a large bowl. Add vegetables, stir to coat evenly. Spread in even layer in foil-lined pan.
e2f614a9-327a-456e-aa1f-f3a5d6a219c8 BAKE 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in same bowl, toss fish with Cajun seasoning and remaining parsley. Remove pan from oven. Place fish on top of vegetables and return to oven.
e2f614a9-327a-456e-aa1f-f3a5d6a219c8 BAKE 15 minutes longer or until fish is opaque in center.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 PREHEAT oven to 350ºF. Line cupcake pan with Reynolds® Baking Cups.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 COMBINE butter, white sugar and brown sugar in a large mixing bowl. MIX until mixture is smooth. BEAT in egg. ADD pureed apple and stir until well mixed.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 COMBINE flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a separate bowl. Gradually incorporate into the apple mixture. POUR batter into prepared pans or baking cups.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 BAKE for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown on top and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Let cool completely before frosting.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 Meanwhile, HEAT sugar over medium high-heat in the bottom of a heavy 2-3 quart saucepan. When the sugar starts to melt, WHISK the sugar continuously. STOP when sugar has melted.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 HEAT the sugar until it reaches a deep amber color. Make sure not to burn the caramel. You want the caramel to reach 350ºF. (Use a thermometer if you have one.)
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 As soon as the sugar reaches the dark amber color, carefully ADD the butter. WHISK until butter is melted.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 REMOVE the pan from the heat and carefully pour in the heavy cream. WHISK until cream is incorporated and caramel is smooth.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 WHISK in the fleur de sel or Maldon sea salt flakes.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 Let the caramel sauce COOL for about 10 minutes in the pan. POUR the caramel into a large mason jar and cool to room temperature. (Note: Makes about 2 cups of caramel so you'll have leftovers!)
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 For the frosting, BEAT butter on medium-high speed until light in color and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 Reduce speed to low, ADD powdered sugar and salt, and mix until incorporated.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 TURN OFF the mixer, and then ADD the salted caramel sauce. BEAT frosting on low to combine, and then increase to medium-high and beat until airy and thoroughly mixed, about 2 minutes.
afce1409-d34e-49b0-9098-9e2815078340 Once the cupcakes are cooled, SPREAD or PIPE the frosting onto each cupcake. For an extra special touch you can decorate with gold sprinkles.
4406f9e5-0bb0-4884-9d7b-b2038ebbef03 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, extending paper up sides of pan; set aside.
4406f9e5-0bb0-4884-9d7b-b2038ebbef03 Prepare brownie mix according to package directions. Pour half of batter into pan. Cover with half of caramel topping, chocolate chunks and almonds. Pour in the remaining brownie batter.
4406f9e5-0bb0-4884-9d7b-b2038ebbef03 Drop remaining caramel by rounded teaspoons onto brownie batter. Swirl with a knife. Top with remaining chocolate chunks and almonds.
4406f9e5-0bb0-4884-9d7b-b2038ebbef03 Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until edges are set. Remove and let tray cool completely in pan. Use edges of parchment to lift brownies from pan onto a cutting board. Pull back edges of parchment for easy cutting. Cut into bars.
ba6a6f95-49e6-4bc7-97d0-7a926925a320 BAKE 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. COOL 10 minutes in pan on cooling rack.
ba6a6f95-49e6-4bc7-97d0-7a926925a320 USE ends of parchment paper to lift loaf from pan. Continue cooling on wire rack.
ba6a6f95-49e6-4bc7-97d0-7a926925a320 WRAP cooled loaf or cut slices in Reynolds Wrap® Duty Aluminum Foil and refrigerate to store.
8c667dea-6620-47a0-ad88-cbcd410a5b23 COMBINE olive oil, salt, and 1/2 teaspoon black pepper in a small bowl. Center half of the mushrooms and onion on a sheet (12x18 inches) of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Drizzle with half of the olive oil mixture. Bring up foil sides. Double-fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
8c667dea-6620-47a0-ad88-cbcd410a5b23 LINE a baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Mix the beef, Worcestershire sauce, and 1/2 teaspoon black pepper in a large bowl until combined. Shape beef mixture into eight thin, 4-inch diameter patties on the prepared baking sheet. Place 1 tablespoon of the shredded cheese onto the center of each of four of the patties. Top with the remaining four patties; pinch edges to seal.
8c667dea-6620-47a0-ad88-cbcd410a5b23 TRANSFER burgers on the foil and foil packets to the rack of an uncovered grill directly over medium-high heat and grill for 10 minutes or until burgers are done (160°F) and vegetables are tender. Toast cut sides of hamburger buns during the last minute of grilling.
8c667dea-6620-47a0-ad88-cbcd410a5b23 OPEN packets carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape; then open top of foil packet.
8c667dea-6620-47a0-ad88-cbcd410a5b23 SERVE burgers on buns with grilled vegetables and lettuce and/or tomato slices, if desired.
a15e9177-e908-4bc7-bb7a-b4b305598259 Turn broiler on high
a15e9177-e908-4bc7-bb7a-b4b305598259 Rinse shrimp, peel and remove tails
a15e9177-e908-4bc7-bb7a-b4b305598259 Add shrimp to a bowl and add extra virgin olive oil, melted butter, lemon juice, crushed garlic, spring/green onions, sea salt and ground black pepper, fold until incorporated
a15e9177-e908-4bc7-bb7a-b4b305598259 Line a baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and add shrimp to pan (including all butter, seasoning and onions), make sure shrimp are spread out and not on top of each other
a15e9177-e908-4bc7-bb7a-b4b305598259 Broil for 6 minutes
a15e9177-e908-4bc7-bb7a-b4b305598259 Remove from broiler and sprinkle cheese all over shrimp, place back in broiler for 1-2 minutes or until cheese is melted
34a7e1da-d5f1-4e08-878a-191236a45530 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, creasing folds into corners to fit pan extending paper up sides of pan; set aside.
34a7e1da-d5f1-4e08-878a-191236a45530 COMBINE flour, baking powder and salt on a sheet of parchment paper; set aside.
34a7e1da-d5f1-4e08-878a-191236a45530 BEAT together brown sugar and butter in a large bowl on medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, milk, vanilla and almond extracts; beat well. Beat in flour mixture until well blended. Stir in 1/2 cup almonds, cherries and white chocolate chips.
34a7e1da-d5f1-4e08-878a-191236a45530 SPREAD dough evenly in parchment-lined pan. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup almonds on top.
34a7e1da-d5f1-4e08-878a-191236a45530 BAKE 25 to 27 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack. Use edges of parchment to lift brownies from pan onto a cutting board. Pull back edges of parchment for easy cutting. Cut into bars.
6ca6b8e7-04f4-40e0-a559-063006722123 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
6ca6b8e7-04f4-40e0-a559-063006722123 PLACE Reynolds Baking® Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
6ca6b8e7-04f4-40e0-a559-063006722123 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
6ca6b8e7-04f4-40e0-a559-063006722123 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
6ca6b8e7-04f4-40e0-a559-063006722123 MAKE CANDY TWIGS 1. Melt candy melts in microwave in medium bowl, about 1 minute. Transfer to resealable bag and seal. Snip small corner (1/8 inch) of bag. 2. Line two cookie sheets with waxed paper. Using melted candy, pipe wavy lines about 2 to 3 inches long, adding several smaller lines to each as branches. Transfer cookie sheets to fridge and chill about 5 minutes.
6ca6b8e7-04f4-40e0-a559-063006722123 MAKE CANDY FLOWERS 1. Sprinkle work surface with white decorating sugar. Press two white spice drops together. Roll out spice drops in white sugar (for white flowers) and pink sugar (for pink flowers), coating with more sugar to prevent stickiness. 2. Cut-out flower shapes with small cookie cutter. Poke in center of each cut-out with a chopstick to look like a flower. 3. Repeat steps 1 and 2 using red spice drops and red sugar.
6ca6b8e7-04f4-40e0-a559-063006722123 TINT frosting pink. Spread on cupcakes.
6ca6b8e7-04f4-40e0-a559-063006722123 ARRANGE candy twigs and candy flowers on top of cupcake. PIPE the centers of the flowers with pink and chocolate decorating frosting.
5c4a170f-49eb-4b8e-9e62-ef3f46441354 PREHEAT oven to 375°F. LINE a 13x9x2-inch baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper with parchment paper side toward food. Crimp Pan Lining Paper around rim of pan; set aside.
5c4a170f-49eb-4b8e-9e62-ef3f46441354 COMBINE cream of chicken soup, poultry seasoning and pepper in a large bowl. Stir in chicken and vegetables. Spread evenly in lined pan. Cover with a sheet of Pan Lining Paper with parchment paper side down toward food.
5c4a170f-49eb-4b8e-9e62-ef3f46441354 BAKE 35 to 40 minutes or until mixture is bubbling around the edges. Top with biscuits. Return pan to oven.
5c4a170f-49eb-4b8e-9e62-ef3f46441354 CONTINUE BAKING uncovered 15 to 18 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
2d65097e-6283-4d9d-8931-7cf58a87d380 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Tear off four 15-inch sheets of Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Fold each sheet in half and crease it in the center. Unfold.
2d65097e-6283-4d9d-8931-7cf58a87d380 COMBINE teriyaki sauce, peanut butter, red pepper flakes and ginger in small bowl until well blended. Stir in chicken.
2d65097e-6283-4d9d-8931-7cf58a87d380 DIVIDE chicken evenly on one-half of each sheet near crease. Arrange snow peas and carrots on top of chicken in an even layer.
2d65097e-6283-4d9d-8931-7cf58a87d380 FOLD over other half of sheet to enclose ingredients. Starting at top corner, make small overlapping folds down entire length of packet to seal edges together. Twist the last fold several times to make a tight seal. Repeat to make 4 packets. Place parchment packets on large cookie sheet.
2d65097e-6283-4d9d-8931-7cf58a87d380 BAKE to minutes. Place parchment packets on dinner plates. Carefully cut an X in top of each packet to allow steam to escape. Serve with pasta and garnish with green onions, if desired.
d60bc09a-55cc-4c55-95ef-088a3a08428c PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
d60bc09a-55cc-4c55-95ef-088a3a08428c PLACE 24 Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups (Black Damask) in muffin pans; set aside.
d60bc09a-55cc-4c55-95ef-088a3a08428c PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes, adding 3 tablespoons instant coffee before mixing. Spoon batter into baking cups.
d60bc09a-55cc-4c55-95ef-088a3a08428c BAKE following package directions. Cool.
d60bc09a-55cc-4c55-95ef-088a3a08428c TINT frosting black. Pipe frosting onto cupcakes using decorating tip #1M.
d60bc09a-55cc-4c55-95ef-088a3a08428c ADD about 15 white pearls to each cupcake. These can be purchased (candy) or made from fondant.
1cfee3fe-7d06-4256-816a-f874bee5eeeb PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
1cfee3fe-7d06-4256-816a-f874bee5eeeb Prepare cake mix following package directions, adding 2 tablespoons instant coffee before mixing.
1cfee3fe-7d06-4256-816a-f874bee5eeeb Spoon cake batter into parchment paper-lined baking pan.
1cfee3fe-7d06-4256-816a-f874bee5eeeb BAKE 29 to 34 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Invert cake onto a platter; remove parchment paper.
1cfee3fe-7d06-4256-816a-f874bee5eeeb DISSOLVE remaining instant coffee in hot water. Stir frosting into coffee mixture until smooth. Frost cake. Microwave chocolate chips and oil on HIGH power in a small microwave-safe dish, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring once, until chocolate is melted. Drizzle melted chocolate over frosted cake. Let stand until chocolate sets. Cut into 12 squares. Garnish with fresh raspberries, if desired.
9134c4c5-c259-4c6c-be25-96b4c69c2cf4 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
9134c4c5-c259-4c6c-be25-96b4c69c2cf4 PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups (Pink Damask) in muffin pans; set aside.
9134c4c5-c259-4c6c-be25-96b4c69c2cf4 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon cake batter into baking cups.
9134c4c5-c259-4c6c-be25-96b4c69c2cf4 BEAT cream cheese, egg, chopped dried cherries and sugar in bowl, with electric mixer. Stir in a few drops red food coloring, if desired. Drop by tablespoonfuls into cupcake batter.
9134c4c5-c259-4c6c-be25-96b4c69c2cf4 BAKE 20 to 22 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean; cool.
9134c4c5-c259-4c6c-be25-96b4c69c2cf4 STIR cherry extract and maraschino juice into frosting.
9134c4c5-c259-4c6c-be25-96b4c69c2cf4 PIPE or spread frosting onto cupcakes.
9134c4c5-c259-4c6c-be25-96b4c69c2cf4 TOP with maraschino cherry.
f50eaf73-66af-436b-a6f6-d37bc5411f46 PREHEAT oven to 300° F. Line 2 cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. MIX butter, brown sugar and vanilla using an electric mixer. Gradually blend in flour and corn starch. Add chocolate chips.
f50eaf73-66af-436b-a6f6-d37bc5411f46 FORM dough into 1-inch balls and place on parchment-lined cookie sheets. Pour sugar on a small plate; dip bottom of drinking glass in sugar and gently press down on each cookie to flatten.
f50eaf73-66af-436b-a6f6-d37bc5411f46 BAKE 25 to 30 minutes, or until bottoms begin to brown.
f50eaf73-66af-436b-a6f6-d37bc5411f46 COOL 5 minutes. Slide parchment with cookies onto a wire rack to cool completely. Lightly sprinkle additional sugar on top of cookies while cooling, if desired.
f50eaf73-66af-436b-a6f6-d37bc5411f46 RECIPE NOTE: For European-style shortbread, turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, about 2 minutes. Pat into a 1/3-inch thick rectangle, measuring 11 x 8 inches. Cut dough unto 2 x 1-inch strips. Place strips 1 inch apart on parchment-lined cookie sheets. Prick with a fork and bake as above.
e6bf8c1e-233b-4c19-a564-e6fba1bd20dc PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line 2 cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
e6bf8c1e-233b-4c19-a564-e6fba1bd20dc BEAT cake mix, oil, water, eggs and vanilla extract together in a large bowl, with an electric mixer, until well blended.
e6bf8c1e-233b-4c19-a564-e6fba1bd20dc STIR in white chocolate chips, nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by heaping tablespoons onto parchment-lined cookie sheets.
e6bf8c1e-233b-4c19-a564-e6fba1bd20dc BAKE 10 to 12 minutes or until set. Slide parchment with cookies onto a wire rack to cool .Cool cookies completely before removing with spatula.
e6bf8c1e-233b-4c19-a564-e6fba1bd20dc REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: Drizzle with melted white chocolate chips for a more professional look.
5f63f44f-f360-4883-abe1-e28ab0d64a9a Heat oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9-inch pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Let cookie dough stand at room temperature 10 minutes to soften.
5f63f44f-f360-4883-abe1-e28ab0d64a9a Finely chop 1 cup of the pretzels; place in large bowl. Add cookie dough and shortening. Beat with electric mixer on low speed until well mixed. Press dough evenly in pan. Bake 14 to 18 minutes or until crust is light golden brown. Remove from oven; cool 10 minutes.
