5f63f44f-f360-4883-abe1-e28ab0d64a9a Meanwhile, in 2 quart heavy saucepan, heat sweetened condensed milk over medium heat 5 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly until hot and mixture is thin. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and chocolate hazelnut spread until well blended. Spread over baked crust. Sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup coarsely chopped pretzels. Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until edges are golden brown. Cool completely, about 1 1/2 hours. Drizzle with caramel syrup. Cut into 6 rows by 4 rows. Store covered.
4d7ff7c8-17dc-4ab2-950e-fb9dd1c466f9 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
4d7ff7c8-17dc-4ab2-950e-fb9dd1c466f9 ADD the butter and chocolate chips to a medium sized metal bowl and put it over a pot of simmering water to create a double boiler. Continually stir with a rubber spatula.
4d7ff7c8-17dc-4ab2-950e-fb9dd1c466f9 WHISK together in a separate large bowl the eggs, brown sugar, sugar, flour, cocoa powder, vanilla and baking powder.
4d7ff7c8-17dc-4ab2-950e-fb9dd1c466f9 COOL the chocolate at room temperature for 10 minutes and then fold it into the eggs and sugar mixture until completely combined.
4d7ff7c8-17dc-4ab2-950e-fb9dd1c466f9 POUR the batter into a Reynolds® Bakeware 8x8 Pan and bake in the oven on 350° for 35 minutes or until the brownies begin to pull away from the outside of the pan.
4d7ff7c8-17dc-4ab2-950e-fb9dd1c466f9 COOL before serving.
472e815e-a8f6-4b3b-8420-270750da655f PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
472e815e-a8f6-4b3b-8420-270750da655f SHAKE flour in Reynolds™ Oven Bag, Large Size; place in 13x9-inch baking pan. Add water to oven bag. Squeeze bag to blend in flour.
472e815e-a8f6-4b3b-8420-270750da655f ADD beef to bag, fat side up. Sprinkle allspice, salt and pepper over meat. Place vegetables around beef.
472e815e-a8f6-4b3b-8420-270750da655f CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
472e815e-a8f6-4b3b-8420-270750da655f BAKE 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until fork-tender. Let stand 10 minutes. Remove and toss top leaf from cabbage. Slice beef and serve with vegetables and meat juices.
54396a92-d8a5-428d-b2eb-613ff234e0f4 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
54396a92-d8a5-428d-b2eb-613ff234e0f4 SHAKE cornstarch in Reynolds® Oven Bag; place in 13x9-inch baking pan. DRY shrimp very well on paper towels. Add to bag; shake to coat with cornstarch. Spread in even layer in bottom of bag. Sprinkle peas evenly over shrimp.
54396a92-d8a5-428d-b2eb-613ff234e0f4 WHISK together coconut milk, curry powder, coriander, salt and pepper; pour over shrimp and peas; top with tomatoes.
54396a92-d8a5-428d-b2eb-613ff234e0f4 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan
54396a92-d8a5-428d-b2eb-613ff234e0f4 BAKE to minutes or until liquid is bubbly and all shrimp are pink. Stir in mango. Spoon shrimp and sauce over rice.
4f9041a3-9112-4def-9ec2-b3588681be9e PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, extending paper up sides of pan; set aside.
4f9041a3-9112-4def-9ec2-b3588681be9e BEAT cake mix, milk, cream cheese, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl on low speed of an electric mixer 30 seconds. Then beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spread batter evenly in parchment-lined pan.
4f9041a3-9112-4def-9ec2-b3588681be9e BAKE to minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely. Invert onto a platter; remove parchment paper. Frost cake. Decorate with sprinkles.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 FOR BASE COOKIE DOUGH: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside. Cream butter and sugar in large bowl, on medium speed of mixer, for about 3 minutes. Gradually add flour to butter and sugar mixture. Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 inch jelly roll pan with Reynolds Parchment Paper.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 STIR oats, raisins, cinnamon and MILKY WAY Bars into Base Cookie Dough until blended. Spread the batter evenly in parchment-lined pan.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 BAKE 15 to 20 minutes. Cool completely.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 SPREAD cream cheese frosting over cookie. Use fork tines to create a wavy line in the icing. Use parchment to lift cookies onto cutting board. Pull back parchment; cut into 1 1/2 x 2-inch rectangles. Decorate top with holiday M&M'S Brand Chocolate Candies.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place Reynolds Mini Foil Baking Cups in mini cupcake pans or on a cookie sheet.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 STIR cocoa powder, 18 melted chocolates and flaked coconut into Base Cookie Dough. Spoon walnut size nuggets into baking cups.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 PRESS a DOVE Brand Dark Chocolate on top of each cookie while they are still warm. Cool completely.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line 2 cookie sheets with Reynolds Parchment Paper; set aside.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 STIR SNICKERS Bars into Base Cookie Dough. Drop rounded teaspoons of cookie dough onto parchment-lined cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 BAKE 12 to 15 minutes. Cool completely.
766398f3-38ec-477b-9298-6b69a895c337 MARS BRIGHT IDEAS TIP: Bake smart. Make three different kinds of cookies from the same dough: Oatmeal Raisin Cookies, Dark Chocolate Coconut Cups and Peanut Butter Drops. Number of Servings: Oatmeal Raisin cookies makes 4 dozen cookies; Dark Chocolate Coconut Cups makes 4 dozen cookies; Peanut Butter Cookies Makes 3 dozen cookies.
9343b4d3-c95d-46f1-a2d8-1da1089df56c PREHEAT oven to 450°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food; set aside.
9343b4d3-c95d-46f1-a2d8-1da1089df56c COMBINE mayonnaise, cheese, water and onion in a shallow dish. Spread crushed chips onto sheet of Reynolds Cut-Rite Wax Paper; set aside.
9343b4d3-c95d-46f1-a2d8-1da1089df56c DIP fillets in mayonnaise mixture to lightly coat both sides; coat with crushed corn chips. Remove foil-lined pan from oven. Place fillets 1 inch apart in foil-lined pan.
9343b4d3-c95d-46f1-a2d8-1da1089df56c BAKE 13 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Serve immediately.
9343b4d3-c95d-46f1-a2d8-1da1089df56c REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: To line pans for easy cleanup, turn the pan upside down and press Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil (dull side down) around it. Remove foil, flip pan over and drop foil inside. Crimp the edges over the rim of the pan and you are ready to cook.
686d81d0-8740-47df-90f6-a313cbf4a808 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
686d81d0-8740-47df-90f6-a313cbf4a808 UNFOLD pastry on parchment paper. Brush pastry with olive oil. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; cut into 3 strips along fold marks. Cut each strip into 6 rectangles. Place on parchment-lined cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
686d81d0-8740-47df-90f6-a313cbf4a808 BAKE 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool. Split pastries into 2 layers; set aside.
686d81d0-8740-47df-90f6-a313cbf4a808 MIX remaining ingredients in large bowl until well blended. Divide crab mixture evenly over pastry bottoms. Top with remaining pastry layers. Serve immediately or refrigerate.
4629b5c5-837c-4bfd-9dd1-4b119ff514eb PREHEAT oven to 400°F. For easy cleanup, line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Parchment Paper. Wash chicken; pat dry.
4629b5c5-837c-4bfd-9dd1-4b119ff514eb COMBINE eggs and milk in bowl. Combine Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, Italian seasoning and pepper on a sheet of wax paper. Dip chicken pieces one at a time in egg mixture, roll in crumb mixture, turning to coat evenly. Place in Reynolds® Parchment Paper-lined pan.
4629b5c5-837c-4bfd-9dd1-4b119ff514eb BAKE 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear or meat thermometer reads 170° for breasts, 180° for other pieces.
86024d14-0f5c-404f-8b7e-0a47db3548f6 PREHEAT oven to 300° F. Line 2 cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. MIX butter, brown sugar and vanilla using an electric mixer. Gradually blend in flour and corn starch. Add chocolate chips.
86024d14-0f5c-404f-8b7e-0a47db3548f6 FORM dough into 1-inch balls and place on parchment-lined cookie sheets. Pour sugar on a small plate; dip bottom of drinking glass in sugar and gently press down on each cookie to flatten.
86024d14-0f5c-404f-8b7e-0a47db3548f6 BAKE 25 to 30 minutes, or until bottoms begin to brown.
86024d14-0f5c-404f-8b7e-0a47db3548f6 COOL 5 minutes. Slide parchment with cookies onto a wire rack to cool completely. Lightly sprinkle additional sugar on top of cookies while cooling, if desired.
86024d14-0f5c-404f-8b7e-0a47db3548f6 RECIPE NOTE: For European-style shortbread, turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, about 2 minutes. Pat into a 1/3-inch thick rectangle, measuring 11 x 8 inches. Cut dough unto 2 x 1-inch strips. Place strips 1 inch apart on parchment-lined cookie sheets. Prick with a fork and bake as above.
886ced74-5dbc-4de8-9c98-cb55b2fc11ec PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
886ced74-5dbc-4de8-9c98-cb55b2fc11ec PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups (Black Damask) in muffin pans; set aside.
886ced74-5dbc-4de8-9c98-cb55b2fc11ec PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
886ced74-5dbc-4de8-9c98-cb55b2fc11ec BAKE following package directions (19 to 22 minutes). Cool.
886ced74-5dbc-4de8-9c98-cb55b2fc11ec PIPE frosting onto each cupcake.
886ced74-5dbc-4de8-9c98-cb55b2fc11ec SELECT small roses free of pesticides.
886ced74-5dbc-4de8-9c98-cb55b2fc11ec BEAT egg whites lightly. Use a small paint brush to paint the flower petals with the egg white.
886ced74-5dbc-4de8-9c98-cb55b2fc11ec DIP the flowers gently into sugar crystals. Let dry.
886ced74-5dbc-4de8-9c98-cb55b2fc11ec PLACE flowers gently on top of frosted cupcakes.
f85f3ac9-ea48-4ae7-8b1d-592078843bba PREHEAT oven to 400F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch pan.
f85f3ac9-ea48-4ae7-8b1d-592078843bba ADD flour, cumin, garlic powder, salt and pepper to oven bag; gently squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Add quinoa and vegetables; turn bag several times to mix ingredients. Arrange ingredients in even layer in bag. Fold down bag opening two times to hold bag open; set aside.
f85f3ac9-ea48-4ae7-8b1d-592078843bba MICROWAVE vegetable stock in a medium microwave-safe bowl for about 4 minutes on high power until stock is very hot. Carefully pour or ladle stock over vegetables. Carefully unfold bag opening.
f85f3ac9-ea48-4ae7-8b1d-592078843bba CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top of bag near tie. Tuck ends of bag in pan
f85f3ac9-ea48-4ae7-8b1d-592078843bba BAKE 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender and quinoa is soft and translucent. Let stand 5 minutes. Carefully cut top of bag open; stir. Top with fresh herbs and pine nuts, if desired. Season with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups (Dots) in muffin pans; set aside.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae SPREAD the top of each cupcake with chocolate frosting.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae TINT 1/2 cup of the vanilla frosting pink with the red food coloring and the other 1/2 cup of the vanilla frosting green.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae SPOON each color into a separate zipper bags.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae SNIP a very small corner, (1/16 inch) from the bag.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae PIPE random dots of frosting on top of each cupcake.
47da5f10-f19e-4927-8cba-5e8c0d9822ae PLACE a red or green candy on top of each of the dots of frosting.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 PREHEAT oven to 400°F
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 COMBINE flour, cumin and chili powder in a small bowl.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 HEAT the chicken broth, either in the microwave or on the stove, until very hot.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 PLACE a Reynolds® Large Oven Bag in a 13x9 inch pan. Fold down the bag opening to help hold the bag open.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 ADD chicken to the bag and sprinkle with salt, pepper, and seasonings.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 ADD beans, red peppers, jalapeño pepper, and rice to the bag as well.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 Carefully POUR the broth into the bag.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 CLOSE the bag with a nylon tie and cut six slits in the top of the bag. Secure the ends of the bag by tucking them in the pan.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 WRAP tortillas in foil.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 BAKE chicken in the oven for 30 minutes, or until the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F. Let stand 5 minutes.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 PLACE tortillas in oven during the last 10 minutes of cooking.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 SPOON chicken mixture into the middle of the warmed tortillas. Add your favorite toppings, if desired.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 FOLD the tortilla side closest to you over the filling, then fold in the sides of the tortilla toward the center and continue rolling tightly.
c91ecd5b-9104-49ee-965c-a6a23cda54b9 SERVE topped with more salsa and sour cream, if desired.
54596c99-ffc8-450b-9779-def7c3e86bc2 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 2-quart rectangular baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper, parchment side up. No need to grease dish.
54596c99-ffc8-450b-9779-def7c3e86bc2 COMBINE the undrained tomatoes, salsa, and chili powder in a medium saucepan. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally and mashing with the back of a spoon.
54596c99-ffc8-450b-9779-def7c3e86bc2 STACK tortillas; wrap tightly in Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
54596c99-ffc8-450b-9779-def7c3e86bc2 BAKE tortillas about 10 minutes or until warm.
54596c99-ffc8-450b-9779-def7c3e86bc2 HEAT oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add squash, onion, and garlic; cook and stir for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat. Stir in half of the tomato mixture, the black beans, chicken, and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
54596c99-ffc8-450b-9779-def7c3e86bc2 DIVIDE the black bean mixture among the warm tortillas; roll up the tortillas. Arrange the rolled tortillas, seam sides down, in the prepared baking dish. Spoon the remaining tomato mixture over the tortillas. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
54596c99-ffc8-450b-9779-def7c3e86bc2 BAKE, uncovered, about 20 minutes or until heated through.
b481f3af-f2dd-4e5d-82a6-87b0514db0d8 LINE a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper: set aside. No need to add extra grease or spray your cookie sheet.
b481f3af-f2dd-4e5d-82a6-87b0514db0d8 COMBINE flour, baking powder and salt on a sheet of parchment paper; set aside. Beat sugar and butter until fluffy in large bowl, with an electric mixer. Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended. Gradually beat flour mixture into butter mixture until smooth. Divide dough in half; shape into 2 flat disks. Wrap dough in Parchment Paper; refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm enough to roll.
b481f3af-f2dd-4e5d-82a6-87b0514db0d8 TO BAKE, preheat oven to 375°F. Roll out dough 1/8-inch thick between 2 lightly floured sheets of parchment paper. Cut dough with a 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter. Place cookies 1-inch apart on parchment-lined cookie sheet.
b481f3af-f2dd-4e5d-82a6-87b0514db0d8 BAKE 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are just beginning to brown on edges. Cool.
846130cc-c501-485b-9912-2276e5d56ca4 PREHEAT grill to medium or preheat oven to 450°F. For each s'more, top one graham cracker square with one candy bar half, one marshmallow and another graham cracker square. Repeat with remaining graham crackers, candy and marshmallows.
846130cc-c501-485b-9912-2276e5d56ca4 CENTER s'mores individually on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
846130cc-c501-485b-9912-2276e5d56ca4 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
846130cc-c501-485b-9912-2276e5d56ca4 GRILL 4 to 5 minutes in covered grill
846130cc-c501-485b-9912-2276e5d56ca4 OR BAKE 4 to 5 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven.
684bd50f-29f6-4c92-aa5d-c8174de3cb26 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Add flour to a Reynolds® Large Oven Bag. Shake. Place bag in 2-quart rectangular baking dish at least 2 inches deep.
684bd50f-29f6-4c92-aa5d-c8174de3cb26 PLACE spinach in bag; sprinkle with onion. Top with fish. Stir together the butter, garlic, salt, and black pepper. Brush over fish. Arrange lemon slices over fish. Close bag with tie (found inside package). Cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag to allow steam to escape. Tuck ends of bag in dish.
684bd50f-29f6-4c92-aa5d-c8174de3cb26 PLACE dish in oven, allowing room for bag to expand during cooking without touching heating elements, wall, or racks. Bag should not hang over dish.
684bd50f-29f6-4c92-aa5d-c8174de3cb26 BAKE 20 minutes.
684bd50f-29f6-4c92-aa5d-c8174de3cb26 CUT open top of oven bag carefully. Remember: Always support bag with the dish.
684bd50f-29f6-4c92-aa5d-c8174de3cb26 SERVE fish with spinach and lemon, and spoon any juices over the top. Sprinkle with crushed red pepper, if desired.
fda80047-50e8-4166-a16b-fb05d2c0a67b PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
fda80047-50e8-4166-a16b-fb05d2c0a67b CENTER onion slices on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Top with pork chops; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine cream of mushroom soup and soy sauce; spoon over pork chops. Top with green pepper slices.
fda80047-50e8-4166-a16b-fb05d2c0a67b BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
fda80047-50e8-4166-a16b-fb05d2c0a67b BAKE 16 to 18 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven or GRILL 10 to 12 minutes in covered grill. Serve over rice.
d224483e-d77b-4faa-b2f7-80a3241f3df6 OPEN Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner and place it inside a 3- to 4-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
d224483e-d77b-4faa-b2f7-80a3241f3df6 COMBINE chili, corn, Velveeta and tomatoes in large bowl. Layer 1/3 of the chili mixture into slow cooker liner, top with 1/2 of the chips. Repeat layers, and top with remaining chili mixture. Place lid on slow cooker.
d224483e-d77b-4faa-b2f7-80a3241f3df6 COOK on HIGH for 2 hours or until Velveeta is melted and edges are bubbling. Set slow cooker control to WARM setting.
d224483e-d77b-4faa-b2f7-80a3241f3df6 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food from slow cooker using a wooden or plastic spoon. Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream, if desired. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
d224483e-d77b-4faa-b2f7-80a3241f3df6 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIPS: For a less spicy flavor, use mild diced tomatoes and green chilies. If desired, top with additional crushed tortilla chips just before serving.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 PRE-HEAT the oven to 375 degrees
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 LINE a 13x9 baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 BROWN the ground turkey in 1 tablespoon of olive oil.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 ADD the remaining olive oil, crushed red pepper, salt, garlic, and tomatoes.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 HEAT to a gently simmer, this should take no more than 5 minutes.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 TASTE and adjust seasoning if needed.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 LADLE sauce into the lined baking dish, just enough to cover the bottom.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 LINE with 4 lasagna noodles.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 TOP noodles with half of the ricotta.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 10. ADD another layer of sauce and 4 more lasagna noodles.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 11. SPREAD on the remaining ricotta and half of the mozzarella slices.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 12. TOP with the last 4 lasagna noodles.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 13. SPREAD on the remaining sauce and top with the mozzarella.
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 COVER the lasagna loosely with foil
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 BAKE covered for 30 – 40 minutes until the cheese is thoroughly melted
bd8d1367-a9e4-4bd3-9ec8-469fe7c3ca76 CAREFULLY remove the foil cover and bake an additional 5 minutes
178b7463-f044-43d1-a336-793274032419 For the crust, PREHEAT oven to 350°F. LINE bottom of 8-inch spring form pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
178b7463-f044-43d1-a336-793274032419 PROCESS TWIX Cookie Bars with graham cracker crumbs in food processor until finely ground. Blend in butter and sugar. Press mixture around bottom and slightly up the sides parchment-lined pan.
178b7463-f044-43d1-a336-793274032419 BAKE 7 to 10 minutes or until fragrant.
178b7463-f044-43d1-a336-793274032419 For filling: BEAT cream cheese with sugar until smooth, about 3 minutes. Meantime, melt dark chocolate with milk in microwave until smooth, about 30 seconds. Add to cream cheese mixture.
178b7463-f044-43d1-a336-793274032419 ADD eggs, one at time, beating well after each addition. Stir in espresso powder and vanilla extract. Pour mixture over crust.
178b7463-f044-43d1-a336-793274032419 BAKE approximately 30 minutes, reduce heat to 300°F and continue baking until center is almost set, about 20-30 minutes.
178b7463-f044-43d1-a336-793274032419 COOL completely before removing the ring. Refrigerate 4 hours or until chilled. For topping:
178b7463-f044-43d1-a336-793274032419 SPOON whipped topping into a resealable plastic bag with a 1/2-inch corner snipped off. Pipe rosettes around edge of cake. Using a hand grater, grate DOVE Brand Milk Chocolate, sprinkling the gratings over whipped topping and cake.
672180f1-2ffa-4e00-b3ac-014946a90ed6 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
672180f1-2ffa-4e00-b3ac-014946a90ed6 PLACE Reynolds Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
672180f1-2ffa-4e00-b3ac-014946a90ed6 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
672180f1-2ffa-4e00-b3ac-014946a90ed6 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool. Life-like trees use 1/4 can of green icing each and make beautiful centerpieces, The simpler version is a better choice for consumption.
672180f1-2ffa-4e00-b3ac-014946a90ed6 SPREAD one container of white frosting onto 16 cupcakes; set aside.
672180f1-2ffa-4e00-b3ac-014946a90ed6 MAKE four (4) centerpiece trees 1.Using the green decorating icing with a leaf tip, start 1/2-inch from the point of the cone and work your way down the cone making leaves with frosting as you go. Leaving the tip undecorated will allow you to transfer the decorated cone to the top of the cupcake without touching the icing. 2.Holding onto the undecorated tip of the tree, place one decorated ice cream cone onto center of each of four cupcakes. 3.Finish decorating the top of the cone with frosting and sprinkles. 4.Use a small star cookie cutter to cut a star out of chewing gum or rolled fondant. Place star on top of tree. MAKE twenty (20) trees better suited for eating 1.Use scissors to cut ice cream cones to about 2" tall. 2.Tint second container of frosting green. 3.Use a spatula or knife to spread a thin layer of icing on cones - again, leaving the tip uncovered for clean transfer to the cupcake. 4.Place decorated cones on frosted cupcakes. 5.Follow decorating/placing directions above. Want to add an extra-tasty surprise? Consider one of the following ideas: 1.Before spreading green frosting on ice cream cones, use a knife or spreader to put Nutella® Hazelnut Spread or melted chocolate chips inside. If chocolate chips, refrigerate until chocolate is solid and then decorate. 2.Place candy, chocolate kiss, or other surprise in the center of the cupcake before you add the ice cream cone...to be revealed when taken off the cupcake
672180f1-2ffa-4e00-b3ac-014946a90ed6 REYNOLDS KITCHEN TIP: Using a skewer to hold the ice cream cone can make it easier to frost and decorate. Insert the bottom of the skewer into a styrofoam square. To evenly frost and add sprinkles, hold onto the tip of the cone and rotate.
629f17ff-4853-42c9-9194-1965c365100b PLACE Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
629f17ff-4853-42c9-9194-1965c365100b ADD flour, Mexican seasoning, olive oil, lime juice, cilantro and garlic in Reynolds® Oven Bag; gently squeeze bag to mix ingredients.
629f17ff-4853-42c9-9194-1965c365100b ADD fish to oven bag; turn bag several times to coat fish with marinade ingredients. Arrange fish into an even layer. Close oven bag with nylon tie. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
629f17ff-4853-42c9-9194-1965c365100b PREHEAT oven to 400F. Cut six 1"-inch slits in top of bag. Tuck ends of bag in pan. Make Crema Sauce:
629f17ff-4853-42c9-9194-1965c365100b MIX sour cream, lime juice and salt in a small bowl.
629f17ff-4853-42c9-9194-1965c365100b BAKE 15 minutes or until fish flakes. Carefully cut bag open and remove fish with slotted spoon to platter. For Each Taco,
629f17ff-4853-42c9-9194-1965c365100b HEAT two tortillas according to package directions. Stack tacos; spoon fish in center. Top with cabbage and drizzle with Crema sauce. Add toppers.
a670b56d-df02-4605-8b7d-6c1ae3034a73 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups (Black Damask) in muffin pans or on a cookie sheet; set aside.
a670b56d-df02-4605-8b7d-6c1ae3034a73 PLACE semisweet chocolate and butter in a microwave-safe bowl. Using 50% power and stirring once, microwave 1 ½ to 2 minutes or until melted. Stir to blend.
a670b56d-df02-4605-8b7d-6c1ae3034a73 BEAT eggs with electric mixer in medium bowl until light yellow, about 30 seconds to 1 minute. Add sugar, cocoa powder and vanilla extract. Beat until blended, about 1 minute.
a670b56d-df02-4605-8b7d-6c1ae3034a73 ADD melted chocolate and butter to egg mixture. Beat until blended, about 30 seconds. Spoon batter into baking cups, filling about 2/3 full.
a670b56d-df02-4605-8b7d-6c1ae3034a73 BAKE 15 to 18 minutes or just until set. Cool in pan 5 minutes. Tops may crack and sink slightly in center. Makes 12 cupcakes.
a670b56d-df02-4605-8b7d-6c1ae3034a73 PIPE whipped cream on top of cupcakes.
a670b56d-df02-4605-8b7d-6c1ae3034a73 TOP with sliced strawberries
083c72ef-e220-47a6-988e-163bbc0d5796 LINE two 9-inch round cake pans with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Spread onefourth of ice cream in each pan. Drizzle with chocolate syrup; sprinkle each with 1/2 cup cookie crumbs. Spread with remaining ice cream. Top with remaining crumbs.
083c72ef-e220-47a6-988e-163bbc0d5796 COVER with foil; freeze until firm.
083c72ef-e220-47a6-988e-163bbc0d5796 LINE large tray with foil. Using edges of foil, lift ice cream layers from pans; uncover. Place one layer upside down on tray; peel off foil. Remove foil from second layer.
083c72ef-e220-47a6-988e-163bbc0d5796 FOLLOW pattern to cut ears and bow tie. Arrange on tray to form bunny. Frost with whipped topping; decorate with coconut, colored sprinkles, jelly beans and licorice. For bunny ears, tint coconut with a few drops of red food coloring diluted with 1/2 teaspoon of water. To freeze until serving time, cover loosely with foil.
8c1eab88-bc03-4b42-b450-d3b435eed6ea PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Tear off four 15-inch sheets of Reynolds Parchment Paper. FOLD each sheet in half and crease it in the center. Cut each into a heart shape; unfold.
8c1eab88-bc03-4b42-b450-d3b435eed6ea DIVIDE broccoli and shrimp evenly on one-half of each sheet near crease.
8c1eab88-bc03-4b42-b450-d3b435eed6ea MIX garlic, sesame oil, ginger and soy sauce. Spoon ¼ the mixture evenly over broccoli and shrimp on each sheet.
8c1eab88-bc03-4b42-b450-d3b435eed6ea FOLD over other half of each sheet to enclose ingredients. Starting at top, make small overlapping folds down entire length of parchment to secure edges together. Twist last fold several times to make a tight seal. Place parchment packets on a large baking sheet with 1-inch sides.
8c1eab88-bc03-4b42-b450-d3b435eed6ea BAKE 13 to 15 minutes or until shrimp is done.
8c1eab88-bc03-4b42-b450-d3b435eed6ea PLACE parchment packets on dinner plates. Carefully cut an “X” in the top of each packet; open carefully, allowing steam to escape. Serve immediately.
572a4ee4-6877-4294-bb18-ef887d7cafe2 In a large mixing bowl beat the butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed 30 seconds or until softened. Add about half of the flour and all of the sugar, molasses, egg, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, and cloves. Beat until thoroughly combined, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally. Beat or stir in the remaining flour.
572a4ee4-6877-4294-bb18-ef887d7cafe2 Divide the dough in half. Cover and chill about 3 hours or until the dough is easy to handle. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, then set it aside. On a lightly floured surface, roll each half of the dough to a 1/8-inch thickness.
572a4ee4-6877-4294-bb18-ef887d7cafe2 Using 3- to 4-inch people-shaped cookie cutters, cut the dough into shapes. Place 1-inch apart on the prepared cookie sheet.
572a4ee4-6877-4294-bb18-ef887d7cafe2 Bake in a 375 degree F oven for 5 to 6 minutes or until the edges are firm. Cool the cookies on the cookie sheet for 1 minute. Transfer the cookies to a wire rack. Cool.
572a4ee4-6877-4294-bb18-ef887d7cafe2 In a heavy small saucepan heat and stir the vanilla coating and 1 tablespoon shortening over low heat until melted. In another saucepan heat and stir the chocolate pieces and the remaining 1 tablespoon shortening over low heat until melted.
572a4ee4-6877-4294-bb18-ef887d7cafe2 Dip the hands, feet, and tops of the heads of the cookies in either the vanilla or chocolate mixture. Place on a wire rack until set. If desired, dip cookies again in the contrasting mixture; place on a wire rack until set. In a small mixing bowl combine the sifted powdered sugar, the vanilla, and enough milk to make a frosting of drizzling or spreading consistency. Use the icing to pipe details onto cookies.
7c2d0a61-64ab-45d3-9e94-10115eb80343 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place Reynolds® Baked for You StayBrite Baking Cups in muffin pans or on a cookie sheet; set aside.
7c2d0a61-64ab-45d3-9e94-10115eb80343 PLACE cake mix, eggs, milk, oil and 2 teaspoons banana extract in a large mixing bowl.
7c2d0a61-64ab-45d3-9e94-10115eb80343 BEAT with electric mixer on low speed 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
7c2d0a61-64ab-45d3-9e94-10115eb80343 STIR in mashed bananas.
7c2d0a61-64ab-45d3-9e94-10115eb80343 SPOON batter into baking cups, filling about 2/3 full.
7c2d0a61-64ab-45d3-9e94-10115eb80343 BAKE 20 to 22 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean . Cool.
7c2d0a61-64ab-45d3-9e94-10115eb80343 STIR 1 teaspoon banana extract into chocolate frosting until well blended. Frost cupcakes. Top with banana shaped candies, if desired.
7c2d0a61-64ab-45d3-9e94-10115eb80343 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: For extra banana flavor, add ¼ teaspoon banana extract at a time to frosting until desired flavor is reached.
29875dd3-7654-4635-a13c-516bea2ad505 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Tear off four 15-inch sheets of Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Fold each sheet in half and crease it in the center. Unfold.
29875dd3-7654-4635-a13c-516bea2ad505 MIX together olive oil, 1 1/2 teaspoons Greek seasoning and seasoned salt; set aside.
29875dd3-7654-4635-a13c-516bea2ad505 COMBINE feta cheese, olives, garlic and remaining Greek seasoning. To create a pocket, make a long, deep horizontal cut in one side of each chicken breast being careful not to cut all the way through. Stuff 1/4 of cheese mixture into each chicken breast half. Drizzle with 1/4 of olive oil mixture.
29875dd3-7654-4635-a13c-516bea2ad505 FOLD over other half of sheet to enclose ingredients. Starting at top corner, make small overlapping folds down entire length of packet to seal edges together. Twist the last fold several times to make a tight seal. Repeat to make 4 packets. Place parchment packets on large cookie sheet.
29875dd3-7654-4635-a13c-516bea2ad505 BAKE to minutes. Meanwhile, combine tomatoes, onions and basil; refrigerate until ready to serve. Place parchment packets on dinner plates. Carefully cut an X in top of each packet to allow steam to escape. Top with tomato relish. Serve immediately.
e0c8d8b8-eb38-4715-a57e-a02945f4c8c1 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
e0c8d8b8-eb38-4715-a57e-a02945f4c8c1 PLACE all unwrapped DOVE Brand Miniatures in the parchment-lined pan. Place in the oven for 2 minutes, just to soften; set aside.
e0c8d8b8-eb38-4715-a57e-a02945f4c8c1 MIX cereal, mini marshmallows and M&M'S Brand Peanut Chocolate Candies for the Holidays in a large bowl.
e0c8d8b8-eb38-4715-a57e-a02945f4c8c1 MELT butter and regular-size marshmallows in a large pan, over medium heat. Pour marshmallow mixture over cereal mixture, mixing to coat well.
e0c8d8b8-eb38-4715-a57e-a02945f4c8c1 SPREAD marshmallow and cereal mixture evenly on top of the DOVE Brand Miniatures. Then, sprinkle plain M&M'S Brand Chocolate Candies for the Holidays on top, pressing slightly.
e0c8d8b8-eb38-4715-a57e-a02945f4c8c1 REFRIGERATE until set, about 30 minutes. Use parchment to lift treat onto cutting board. Pull back parchment; cut into 1 1/4-inch squares.
e0c8d8b8-eb38-4715-a57e-a02945f4c8c1 FILL clear plastic bags with 3 to 4 squares and tie with ribbon.
e0c8d8b8-eb38-4715-a57e-a02945f4c8c1 MARS BRIGHT IDEAS TIP: These treats make perfect gifts for all of your child's friends. When your child sees someone special during the day, they can reach into their backpack and give a pouch of holiday wishes! Refrigeration time is 30 minutes, decoration time is 10 minutes.
37985216-b94a-4534-a1ca-170ac8fd54de PREHEAT grill to medium-high or preheat oven to 450°F. Combine beans, rice, cheese, salsa, onion and cilantro; set aside. Microwave tortillas 15 to 20 seconds until soft.
37985216-b94a-4534-a1ca-170ac8fd54de CENTER one tortilla on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Spoon one–fourth of bean mixture in center of each tortilla. Wrap filling in each tortilla burrito-style. Center burrito on foil sheet seam-side down.
37985216-b94a-4534-a1ca-170ac8fd54de BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
37985216-b94a-4534-a1ca-170ac8fd54de GRILL 12 to 16 minutes in covered grill, turning once half way through grilling
37985216-b94a-4534-a1ca-170ac8fd54de OR BAKE 18 to 20 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven.
4476843e-8ab1-4e7f-8b05-37c35da42ea1 PREPARE fajita seasoning mix following package directions and pour over steak. Cover with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil and marinate steak 1 to 2 hours.
4476843e-8ab1-4e7f-8b05-37c35da42ea1 MAKE a grill pan by shaping two layers of foil over the outside of 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Remove foil and crimp the edges to form a tight rim, making a pan with one-inch sides. Place on cookie sheet.
4476843e-8ab1-4e7f-8b05-37c35da42ea1 PREHEAT grill to high. Remove steak from marinade; discard marinade. Add peppers, onion and oil to foil pan. Slide foil pan from cookie sheet onto grill and place steak beside pan on grill.
4476843e-8ab1-4e7f-8b05-37c35da42ea1 GRILL 8 to 10 minutes on high in covered grill. Stir vegetables and turn steak after 5 minutes. Slide foil pan from grill onto cookie sheet. Slice grilled steak into thin strips.
4476843e-8ab1-4e7f-8b05-37c35da42ea1 WRAP tortillas in foil; add to grill to heat while slicing steak. Serve beef, peppers and onions wrapped in warm tortillas with salsa.
9c6a65d5-2312-469c-acec-e5b03b024c92 SOAK skewers in water for at lease 30 minutes.
9c6a65d5-2312-469c-acec-e5b03b024c92 MIX steak sauce, honey and thyme leaves in a small bowl; set aside.
9c6a65d5-2312-469c-acec-e5b03b024c92 THREAD cubes of beef, peppers and onions in alternating arrangement on skewers for each kabob. Brush kabobs with steak sauce.
9c6a65d5-2312-469c-acec-e5b03b024c92 HEAT gill to medium-high.
9c6a65d5-2312-469c-acec-e5b03b024c92 PLACE sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with holes (see Tip) on grill grate with non-stick (dull) side towards food.
9c6a65d5-2312-469c-acec-e5b03b024c92 GRILL 7 minutes; turn kabobs. Brush kabobs with steak sauce. Continue grilling 7 minutes, until beef is done. Discard any remaining honey mixture.
dd18dcfb-b17d-4bcc-8301-3e5e550c7e54 RINSE chicken thighs under cold water; pat dry.
dd18dcfb-b17d-4bcc-8301-3e5e550c7e54 COMBINE Kikkoman Low Sodium Soy Sauce, hot pepper sauce, garlic, onion powder, thyme and red pepper in a plastic zipper bag. Add chicken thighs. Close the bag and turn to coat chicken. Marinate at least 30 minutes.
dd18dcfb-b17d-4bcc-8301-3e5e550c7e54 PREHEAT grill to medium. Make drainage holes in sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with a large grilling fork.
dd18dcfb-b17d-4bcc-8301-3e5e550c7e54 PLACE oil sheet with holes on grill rack with non-stick (dull) side towards food; immediately place chicken on foil.
dd18dcfb-b17d-4bcc-8301-3e5e550c7e54 GRILL chicken minutes; turn. Continue grilling and turning every minutes until chicken is tender and reaches °F, about minutes. Makes servings.
859d6946-0fa5-4f5a-9ce2-caba19088579 PREHEAT grill to medium-high.
859d6946-0fa5-4f5a-9ce2-caba19088579 PLACE 1/2 of vegetables in center of one sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil; repeat with remaining vegetables on 2nd sheet of foil. Combine garlic, oil, lemon juice, basil, seasoned salt and thyme in small bowl; drizzle over vegetables.
859d6946-0fa5-4f5a-9ce2-caba19088579 BRING up sides of foil over vegetables; fold down two times. DOUBLE FOLD both ends of foil to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. REPEAT to make two packets. PLACE packets on baking sheet with 1-inch sides.
859d6946-0fa5-4f5a-9ce2-caba19088579 SLIDE packets off of baking sheet onto preheated grill.
859d6946-0fa5-4f5a-9ce2-caba19088579 GRILL 10 to 12 minutes on medium-high in covered grill.
859d6946-0fa5-4f5a-9ce2-caba19088579 SLIDE packets off of grill onto baking sheet. OPEN packets carefully by cutting beside top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape. TRANSFER grilled vegetables to plates, and sprinkle with grated cheese, if desired.
dde7926a-f26e-4cc9-8eb8-1e8318ca7397 Mix the olive oil, 4 teaspoons garam masala, garlic, salt, and black pepper in a small bowl until combined. Tear four sheets (12x18 inches each) of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Center one chicken breast half on a sheet of foil; sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon garam masala on both sides.
dde7926a-f26e-4cc9-8eb8-1e8318ca7397 Place the squash and onion slices on top of the chicken. Drizzle evenly with one-fourth of the olive oil mixture. Bring up foil sides. Double-fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
dde7926a-f26e-4cc9-8eb8-1e8318ca7397 GRILL over medium-high heat in covered grill 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and an instant-read thermometer inserted into chicken registers 165°F.
dde7926a-f26e-4cc9-8eb8-1e8318ca7397 OPEN packets carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape.; then open top of foil packet. To serve, top with yogurt and sprinkle with cilantro, if desired.
f2ced3c6-4477-4622-84c0-1ac6d2471ed4 Preheat grill to medium high. Tear off a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick foil long enough to cover the entire grill grates. Make draining holes in the sheet of foil with a large grilling fork; set aside.
f2ced3c6-4477-4622-84c0-1ac6d2471ed4 Combine ingredients for Curry Rub, Coconut Lime sauce and Honey Barbecue Sauce in separate bowls; set aside. Sprinle remaining curry rub over chicken. Brush onion slices with vegetable oil.
f2ced3c6-4477-4622-84c0-1ac6d2471ed4 Place foil sheet with holes on grill rack with non-stick (dull) side towards food; immediately place chicken, onion slices and pineapple slices on foil.
f2ced3c6-4477-4622-84c0-1ac6d2471ed4 Grill chicken, onion and pineapple 3 to 5 minutes. Brush chicken and onion slices with Honey Barbecue Sauce; grill 5 minutes longer. Remove pineapple and onion slices from foil sheet. Turn chicken and brush with barbecue sauce. Continue grilling 3 to 5 minues until chicken is tender and juices run clearo or meat thermometer reads 170°f.
f2ced3c6-4477-4622-84c0-1ac6d2471ed4 Place onion and pineapple slices on top of the chicken. Drizzle with Coconut Lime Sauce. Grill 2 to 3 minutes until sauce is heated.
152941b6-2d57-4171-ae5f-92c8103c72cd PREHEAT grill to medium.
152941b6-2d57-4171-ae5f-92c8103c72cd COMBINE brown sugar, minced garlic, seasoned salt, paprika and black pepper in a small bowl; set aside. SLICE pork tenderloin into 1-inch medallions; set in a large baking dish. Generously rub each side of the pork slices with seasoning rub. Set aside.
152941b6-2d57-4171-ae5f-92c8103c72cd TEAR off 6 sheets (12x18 –inches each) of Reynolds® Wrap Aluminum Foil and set on a flat surface. Lay 2-3 pork medallions in the middle of one sheet of foil. Add one-sixth of the potatoes, zucchini, sweet peppers, and onions on top of pork. Drizzle vegetables with a small amount of olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
152941b6-2d57-4171-ae5f-92c8103c72cd Bring up foil sides. Double-fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make six packets.
152941b6-2d57-4171-ae5f-92c8103c72cd Grill over medium to high heat. When grill is hot, ADD packets directly to the grill, meat-side down. Lower lid and cook for 10-15 minutes.
152941b6-2d57-4171-ae5f-92c8103c72cd TURN the packets over to cook vegetable-side down, with lid closed, for another 15 minutes.
152941b6-2d57-4171-ae5f-92c8103c72cd AFTER 20-25 minutes total cooking time, check for doneness by removing one packet onto a plate and. OPEN packet carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape; then open top of foil packet.
152941b6-2d57-4171-ae5f-92c8103c72cd If additional time is needed, place packet back on the grill and continue cooking for another 5 minutes.
152941b6-2d57-4171-ae5f-92c8103c72cd SERVE: simply open packets and serve each individual portion on a plate.
ebd97f63-3042-48b6-821f-7279695b8c7c PREHEAT grill to medium-high.
ebd97f63-3042-48b6-821f-7279695b8c7c CENTER one pork chop on each sheet of REYNOLDS WRAP® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with vegetables. Combine teriyaki sauce and pineapple; spoon evenly over top.
ebd97f63-3042-48b6-821f-7279695b8c7c BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
ebd97f63-3042-48b6-821f-7279695b8c7c GRILL to minutes in covered grill. Serve over rice.
21116730-eec1-40e6-bc7a-0f076fd341b7 PREHEAT grill to medium-high heat. Tear off a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil long enough to cover entire grill grate. Make drainage holes in the non-stick foil with a grilling fork; set aside.
21116730-eec1-40e6-bc7a-0f076fd341b7 COMBINE barbecue sauce and teriyaki sauce; set aside. Combine ground beef, red onion, garlic salt, pepper and 1/2 cup barbecue sauce mixture in large bowl until well blended. Shape beef mixture into 8 burgers, 4 inches round and 1/2-inch thick.
21116730-eec1-40e6-bc7a-0f076fd341b7 PLACE foil sheet with holes on grill grate with non-stick (dull) side facing up. Immediately place burgers and pineapple slices on foil.
21116730-eec1-40e6-bc7a-0f076fd341b7 GRILL burgers and pineapple uncovered 5 minutes; turn. Brush burgers with remaining barbecue sauce; grill 5 minutes.
21116730-eec1-40e6-bc7a-0f076fd341b7 Remove pineapple slices from foil. Turn burgers; brush with barbecue sauce. Grill 3 minutes longer or until burgers are done.
21116730-eec1-40e6-bc7a-0f076fd341b7 Lightly toast hamburger buns on grill. Top burgers with 1 slice cheese before removing from grill. Place burgers on buns; top with grilled pineapple slices. Serve on onion rolls with additional barbecue sauce and lettuce, if desired.
f92852b1-8554-454f-80a1-fa5aaed1679e PREHEAT oven to 450°F or preheat grill to medium-high. Cut steak lengthwise in half and then crosswise into 1/8" thick strips. Sprinkle beef with garlic powder and pepper. Combine beef, potatoes, red pepper, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
f92852b1-8554-454f-80a1-fa5aaed1679e CENTER one-fourth of mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
f92852b1-8554-454f-80a1-fa5aaed1679e BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
f92852b1-8554-454f-80a1-fa5aaed1679e BAKE 25 to 30 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR
f92852b1-8554-454f-80a1-fa5aaed1679e GRILL 15 to 18 minutes in covered grill.
a45bc53c-0445-4e01-83b7-8e7b0ebb181f PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high. Cut steak into 1/2–inch cubes.
a45bc53c-0445-4e01-83b7-8e7b0ebb181f CENTER half of beef, potatoes and carrots in an even layer on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with Non-stick (dull) side toward food. Spoon gravy over beef mixture; sprinkle with onion salt and pepper.
a45bc53c-0445-4e01-83b7-8e7b0ebb181f BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
a45bc53c-0445-4e01-83b7-8e7b0ebb181f BAKE 30 to 35 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR
a45bc53c-0445-4e01-83b7-8e7b0ebb181f GRILL 14 to 16 minutes in covered grill. Stir before serving.
1a1c8a19-d8d0-458a-bc71-44bdc36d9a18 PREHEAT oven to 425°F.
1a1c8a19-d8d0-458a-bc71-44bdc36d9a18 LINE a 13x9x2-inch pan with Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Place chicken pieces in pan. Brush with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
1a1c8a19-d8d0-458a-bc71-44bdc36d9a18 COMBINE basil, rosemary and garlic salt in medium bowl; sprinkle 1/2 of the herb mixture over the chicken.
1a1c8a19-d8d0-458a-bc71-44bdc36d9a18 ADD remaining olive oil, potatoes, carrots and onion to bowl with the herb mixture; stir to coat. Arrange vegetables in an even layer around chicken. Cover dish with sheet of foil; fold back one corner of cover for heat circulation.
1a1c8a19-d8d0-458a-bc71-44bdc36d9a18 BAKE 45 to 50 minutes or until vegetables are done and meat thermometer reads 170°F for white meat and 180°F for dark meat. Carefully remove cover and serve.
66362fce-2956-4bd2-91bf-4ce9c7be3826 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
66362fce-2956-4bd2-91bf-4ce9c7be3826 SHAKE flour in Reynolds® Oven Bag, Turkey Size; place in large roasting pan at least 2 inches deep. Spray inside of bag with nonstick cooking spray, if desired to reduce sticking with large turkeys.
66362fce-2956-4bd2-91bf-4ce9c7be3826 ADD vegetables to oven bag. Remove neck and giblets from turkey. Rinse turkey, pat dry and brush with oil. COMBINE seasonings in a small bowl; sprinkle and rub evenly over turkey.
66362fce-2956-4bd2-91bf-4ce9c7be3826 PLACE turkey in oven bag on top of vegetables.
66362fce-2956-4bd2-91bf-4ce9c7be3826 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six ½-inch slits in top. Insert meat thermometer through slit in bag into thickest part of inner thigh no touching the bone. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
66362fce-2956-4bd2-91bf-4ce9c7be3826 BAKE according to times below or until meat thermometer reads 180°F.
66362fce-2956-4bd2-91bf-4ce9c7be3826 Let Stand in oven bag 15 minutes. Cut open top of bag. Use two carving forks, inserting one in each end, to lift turkey from bag.
8385f296-73df-4d46-9edb-209d3dca54bb Cut the salmon into 2-inch chunks. Fold the lemon coins in half and thread the salmon and lemon onto the soaked skewers, alternating between the salmon and lemon. Place the salmon skewers in a shallow dish and set aside.
8385f296-73df-4d46-9edb-209d3dca54bb In a large bowl, whisk together the mustard, vinegar, honey, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, salt and pepper to taste. Pour marinade over the skewers, turning to coat, and marinate for 15 to 30 minutes.
8385f296-73df-4d46-9edb-209d3dca54bb While the skewers are marinating, prepare your grill. Cut a large piece of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and firmly fit it over the grill grate. Preheat the grill to medium heat. For a charcoal grill, place 4 to 5 hickory wood chunks on top of hot coals and close the grill cover to let the smoke accumulate. For a gas grill, place wood chunks in a smoker box or in a large piece of foil; fold up side to make a packet. Poke holes with a fork and place on the grill. Close the cover to let smoke accumulate.
8385f296-73df-4d46-9edb-209d3dca54bb Open the grill and lightly oil the foil.
8385f296-73df-4d46-9edb-209d3dca54bb Cook the salmon skewers for 4 to 5 minutes per side, until fish is opaque in color. Plate the salmon skewers and sprinkle with parsley. Serve hot.
8016f25f-6a69-4f60-b05f-267888d7cf16 PREHEAT oven to 350oF. Line muffin pans with Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups.
8016f25f-6a69-4f60-b05f-267888d7cf16 SIFT together the flour, white chocolate, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a medium bowl; set aside.
8016f25f-6a69-4f60-b05f-267888d7cf16 CREAM the butter and sugar in a large bowl on high speed until light and fluffy. Set mixer to low speed. Add the eggs, buttermilk and peppermint and vanilla extracts. Mix until incorporated. Slowly add in the flour mixture until combined.
8016f25f-6a69-4f60-b05f-267888d7cf16 SPOON batter into baking cups, filling about 2/3 full (about 3 tablespoons of batter).
8016f25f-6a69-4f60-b05f-267888d7cf16 BAKE for 19 to 22 minutes, until the tops are brown and a toothpick comes out clean. Cool in the pan for 15 minutes. Remove to a baking rack and cool completely.
8016f25f-6a69-4f60-b05f-267888d7cf16 FROST cupcakes with vanilla frosting.
8016f25f-6a69-4f60-b05f-267888d7cf16 SPRINKLE or dip frosted cupcakes with crushed hard peppermint candies.
df491bb0-2133-44d8-a439-e827f6cf3d51 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
df491bb0-2133-44d8-a439-e827f6cf3d51 SPREAD half of each tortilla with 2 tablespoons pizza sauce. Sprinkle half of cheese over sauce. Arrange 6 pepperoni slices on top of each tortilla. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
df491bb0-2133-44d8-a439-e827f6cf3d51 Fold tortillas in half enclosing filling; place on parchment paper-lined cookie sheet.
df491bb0-2133-44d8-a439-e827f6cf3d51 BAKE 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted and tortillas are golden brown.
6e46e462-59ed-4a8c-9c7d-a3e20a8fb45e PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line a large baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil; sprinkle with cornmeal. Set aside.
6e46e462-59ed-4a8c-9c7d-a3e20a8fb45e BROWN sausage in large skillet on medium-high heat. Drain and set aside.
6e46e462-59ed-4a8c-9c7d-a3e20a8fb45e UNROLL pizza dough onto prepared baking sheet. Carefully stretch or roll dough into a 13x10-inch rectangle. Arrange sausage on dough to within 1/2 inch of the edges. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of the mozzarella. Layer spinach on cheese. Top with the remaining 1/2 cup mozzarella and the Parmesan. Starting from a long side, roll up dough to make a 13-inch-long loaf. Pinch seam and ends to seal.
6e46e462-59ed-4a8c-9c7d-a3e20a8fb45e PLACE loaf, seam side down, on the prepared baking sheet. Brush with egg. Using a sharp knife, cut four 2-inch slits in top for steam to escape.
6e46e462-59ed-4a8c-9c7d-a3e20a8fb45e BAKE 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. If necessary, cover the last 5 minutes of baking to prevent overbrowning. Remove from oven and slice into rounds to serve with pizza sauce.
868ea6df-58f0-4a69-9a5f-01faa380ed09 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. For easy cleanup, line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Combine honey, mustard, butter, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; set aside.
868ea6df-58f0-4a69-9a5f-01faa380ed09 PLACE salmon in center of parchment-lined pan. Arrange asparagus around salmon. Sprinkle with walnuts; drizzle with reserved sauce
868ea6df-58f0-4a69-9a5f-01faa380ed09 BAKE to minutes or until salmon flakes when tested with a fork.
552509a9-3214-4577-9197-693237893b3b PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
552509a9-3214-4577-9197-693237893b3b SHAKE flour in Reynolds® Oven Bag, Large Size; place in 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Shake flour to center of bag.
552509a9-3214-4577-9197-693237893b3b COMBINE mayonnaise, mustard, honey and red pepper. Spread about 3 tablespoons of the mixture on top of salmon fillets. Add to bag. Sprinkle with parsley.
552509a9-3214-4577-9197-693237893b3b CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan
552509a9-3214-4577-9197-693237893b3b BAKE 20 to 25 minutes or until salmon is opaque and flakes easily with fork. Remove skin if desired; Stir sauce in bag and serve with salmon.
92632acc-cc91-4d66-842c-8676b52a890b LINE an 8x8-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper with parchment paper side toward food, extending paper up sides of pan, set aside.
92632acc-cc91-4d66-842c-8676b52a890b PREPARE brownie mix following package directions; stir in nuts and coconut. Spread batter evenly in parchment-lined pan
92632acc-cc91-4d66-842c-8676b52a890b BAKE following brownie package directions. Cool completely.
92632acc-cc91-4d66-842c-8676b52a890b SPREAD chocolate frosting over cooled brownie. Squeeze softened vanilla frosting in 6 to 8 lines crosswise over chocolate frosting, spacing lines 1 inch apart. Using a wooden pick, draw lines through frosting alternating direction to create a marbled pattern. Cut into bars.
1246b586-f1c1-436f-87b8-7b26f515b7f0 To make graham cracker crust, combine graham cracker crumbs with sugar and butter. Mix until crumbs are completely coated.
1246b586-f1c1-436f-87b8-7b26f515b7f0 Press crumbs into Reynolds StayBrite® Baking Cups. This can be made done easily by pressing the crumbs with the bottom of a juice glass.
1246b586-f1c1-436f-87b8-7b26f515b7f0 Bake crusts at 375° for 5 minutes.
1246b586-f1c1-436f-87b8-7b26f515b7f0 Spoon 2 tablespoons of cherry pie filling onto cooled crusts.
1246b586-f1c1-436f-87b8-7b26f515b7f0 In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until smooth. Fold in whipped topping and spoon 2 tablespoons of this mixture on top of the cherry pie filling.
1246b586-f1c1-436f-87b8-7b26f515b7f0 Top individual desserts with fresh blueberries and chill in the refrigerator until ready
9dc51b2c-327f-46f4-abfe-500ed8abe371 PREHEAT grill to medium-high or oven to 450°F.
9dc51b2c-327f-46f4-abfe-500ed8abe371 CENTER one chicken breast half on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Sprinkle with Italian seasoning. Arrange tortellini around chicken. Spoon tomatoes and olives over tortellini.
9dc51b2c-327f-46f4-abfe-500ed8abe371 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
9dc51b2c-327f-46f4-abfe-500ed8abe371 BAKE 20 to 25 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR
9dc51b2c-327f-46f4-abfe-500ed8abe371 GRILL 14 to 18 minutes in covered grill.
b19e5dc5-9d1b-4c6e-b853-7c80e3b3f611 PREHEAT oven to 420°F. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
b19e5dc5-9d1b-4c6e-b853-7c80e3b3f611 MIX all ingredients together in a large bowl until soft dough forms.
b19e5dc5-9d1b-4c6e-b853-7c80e3b3f611 DROP dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto parchment-lined cookie sheet. Flatten dough slightly with the back of a spoon.
b19e5dc5-9d1b-4c6e-b853-7c80e3b3f611 BAKE to minutes or until golden brown.
8fd9b3d7-37c9-40b8-a74e-232a44e45a5f PREHEAT the oven to 350°
8fd9b3d7-37c9-40b8-a74e-232a44e45a5f COOK the onions on medium heat in olive olive oil for 4 to 6 minutes or until slightly brown.
8fd9b3d7-37c9-40b8-a74e-232a44e45a5f ADD in the taco seasoning and pinto beans and stir.
8fd9b3d7-37c9-40b8-a74e-232a44e45a5f LAYER the Reynolds® 8x8 Bakeware pan as followed: refried beans and cooked onions, ½ of the jack cheese, chopped chicken, cheddar cheese, chorizo, and the rest of the jack cheese.
8fd9b3d7-37c9-40b8-a74e-232a44e45a5f PLACE the pan in the oven and bake for 25 minutes.
8fd9b3d7-37c9-40b8-a74e-232a44e45a5f FINISH the dip with diced tomatoes and green onions.
6553adc1-cba0-46f6-b1b4-eed569893253 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
6553adc1-cba0-46f6-b1b4-eed569893253 PLACE 24 Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
6553adc1-cba0-46f6-b1b4-eed569893253 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups
6553adc1-cba0-46f6-b1b4-eed569893253 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
6553adc1-cba0-46f6-b1b4-eed569893253 TINT frosting green. Spread the top of each cupcake with tinted frosting.
6553adc1-cba0-46f6-b1b4-eed569893253 CUT the marshmallows crosswise into thin slices with a pair of scissors. (You will get about 5 petals per marshmallow.)
6553adc1-cba0-46f6-b1b4-eed569893253 FLATTEN green candies adding some sugar to prevent sticking and cut into small leaf shapes.
6553adc1-cba0-46f6-b1b4-eed569893253 ARRANGE about 7 marshmallow slices as the petals on top of the cupcakes.
6553adc1-cba0-46f6-b1b4-eed569893253 PLACE a yellow candy in the center of the petals and the green candies as the leaves.
330e289e-9d7e-4ade-9a12-7e0e2ea4900e PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high. Spray four 12x18-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil with nonstick cooking spray, set aside. Combine the couscous, green onion, coriander, paprika, hot pepper sauce, sliced almonds, and currants in a large bowl. Stir in half of the chicken broth.
330e289e-9d7e-4ade-9a12-7e0e2ea4900e CENTER one-fourth of the mixture on each sheet of aluminum foil. Top with Alaska seafood fillet, butter and lemon slices.
330e289e-9d7e-4ade-9a12-7e0e2ea4900e BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and one end of packet. Through open end, add one-fourth of remaining broth. Double fold remaining end to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
330e289e-9d7e-4ade-9a12-7e0e2ea4900e BAKE 20 to 25 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR
330e289e-9d7e-4ade-9a12-7e0e2ea4900e GRILL 8 to 10 minutes in covered grill. Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
a7893fa1-eb9b-495b-8a07-b1523ee1f9b2 PREHEAT grill to medium-high or oven to 450°F.
a7893fa1-eb9b-495b-8a07-b1523ee1f9b2 CENTER one-fourth chicken breast strips and vegetables on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. MIX lemon peel, basil, garlic salt and pepper in a small bowl. Sprinkle evenly over chicken and vegetables. TOP each with 1 tablespoon butter. Mix lemon juice and water; spoon two tablespoons mixture over on each packet.
a7893fa1-eb9b-495b-8a07-b1523ee1f9b2 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets
a7893fa1-eb9b-495b-8a07-b1523ee1f9b2 GRILL 10 to 12 minutes in covered grill OR
a7893fa1-eb9b-495b-8a07-b1523ee1f9b2 BAKE 22 to 25 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven. Serve over hot cooked pasta; squeeze fresh lemon juice over chicken and vegetables, if desired.
edeb9721-d5ee-4cd2-ab3f-8f390e26ab34 PREHEAT oven to 400°F.
edeb9721-d5ee-4cd2-ab3f-8f390e26ab34 TEAR off four 15-inch sheets of Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Fold each sheet in half and crease it in the center. Unfold.
edeb9721-d5ee-4cd2-ab3f-8f390e26ab34 MIX lemon peel, olive oil, pepper and seasoned salt in a small bowl until well blended; set aside.
edeb9721-d5ee-4cd2-ab3f-8f390e26ab34 PLACE 1 fish fillet on one-half of each sheet near crease. Spread 1/4 of seasoning mixture over each fillet. Top with strips of bell pepper.
edeb9721-d5ee-4cd2-ab3f-8f390e26ab34 FOLD over other half of sheet to enclose ingredients. Starting at top corner, make small overlapping folds down entire length of packet to seal edges together. Twist the last fold several times to make a tight seal. Repeat to make 4 packets. Place parchment packets on a large cookie sheet.
edeb9721-d5ee-4cd2-ab3f-8f390e26ab34 BAKE to minutes. Place parchment packets on dinner plates. Carefully cut an X in top of each packet to allow steam to escape. Serve immediately.
890a4863-44ba-410c-9ac9-70920f30fd14 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
890a4863-44ba-410c-9ac9-70920f30fd14 LINE an 8x8x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, extending paper up sides of pan; set aside.
890a4863-44ba-410c-9ac9-70920f30fd14 COMBINE graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar until well blended. Press into parchment-lined pan. Bake 10 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
890a4863-44ba-410c-9ac9-70920f30fd14 COMBINE cream cheese and powdered sugar with an electric mixer until well blended. Add pudding mix, milk and lemon peel; beat 2 minutes or until well blended.
890a4863-44ba-410c-9ac9-70920f30fd14 LAYER raspberries evenly on top of baked crust. Pour pudding mixture over raspberries; spread gently to cover berries. Garnish with reserved raspberries. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving. Use edges of parchment to lift bars from pan onto a cutting board. Pull back edges of parchment for easy cutting. Cut into 9 squares.
523647d4-abde-462a-ba5a-9b565795f37e PREHEAT grill to medium-high OR oven to 450°F.
523647d4-abde-462a-ba5a-9b565795f37e MIX lemon peel, olive oil, rosemary, seasoned salt and pepper in small bowl until well blended; set aside.
523647d4-abde-462a-ba5a-9b565795f37e CENTER one chicken breast half on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper. Spread about 2 teaspoons seasoning mixture over each chicken breast. Arrange peas, squash and red pepper around chicken. Repeat for all chicken breasts.
523647d4-abde-462a-ba5a-9b565795f37e BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
523647d4-abde-462a-ba5a-9b565795f37e GRILL 12 to 14 minutes in covered grill
523647d4-abde-462a-ba5a-9b565795f37e OR BAKE 18 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet in oven.
fdcfc937-7e5b-4bf7-b7d4-e30dbb9e41e0 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
fdcfc937-7e5b-4bf7-b7d4-e30dbb9e41e0 SHAKE flour in Reynolds® Oven Bag, Large Size; place in 13x9x2-inch baking pan with opening towards wide side of pan.
fdcfc937-7e5b-4bf7-b7d4-e30dbb9e41e0 ADD potatoes to oven bag. Drizzle with olive oil; sprinkle with spices. Turn bag to coat potatoes; arrange evenly in bag.
fdcfc937-7e5b-4bf7-b7d4-e30dbb9e41e0 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
fdcfc937-7e5b-4bf7-b7d4-e30dbb9e41e0 BAKE to minutes or until potatoes are done. Carefully open bag; sprinkle potatoes with cheese, bacon and onions. Let stand minutes or until cheese melts. Serve with sour cream, if desired.
035a92e9-863c-463b-b3bb-6ad861d3d27a PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
035a92e9-863c-463b-b3bb-6ad861d3d27a PLACE Reynolds<span>®</span> Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
035a92e9-863c-463b-b3bb-6ad861d3d27a PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
035a92e9-863c-463b-b3bb-6ad861d3d27a BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
035a92e9-863c-463b-b3bb-6ad861d3d27a MAKE LOLLIPOP 1. Divide each fondant color into quarters. Keep pieces covered while not working with them to prevent drying. 2. Roll a quarter of each color into a rope about 1/4 inch thick. 3. Press the two color fondants together and roll out to 1/4 inch thickness, twisting slightly to create swirl. 4. Roll up the rope into a flat spiral, about 2 1/2 inches wide. Snip the end and pinch to seal. 5. Break a wheat stick into a 2 1/2 inch length. Press the cut end against side of spiral as lollipop stick 6. Repeat with remaining fondant to make 24 lollipops.
035a92e9-863c-463b-b3bb-6ad861d3d27a TINT frosting yellow. Spread on top of cupcakes
035a92e9-863c-463b-b3bb-6ad861d3d27a ADD fondant lollipop and 3 different colored spic drops
5d0b1991-3c24-410a-adce-f5afc69a44d6 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place Reynolds<span>®</span> Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
5d0b1991-3c24-410a-adce-f5afc69a44d6 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon cake batter into baking cups.
5d0b1991-3c24-410a-adce-f5afc69a44d6 BAKE 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.
5d0b1991-3c24-410a-adce-f5afc69a44d6 FROST cupcakes with chocolate frosting.
5d0b1991-3c24-410a-adce-f5afc69a44d6 DIP baked cookies in melted white chocolate or frosting. Sprinkle with colored sprinkles while wet. Let set until is firm or frosting set.
5d0b1991-3c24-410a-adce-f5afc69a44d6 WRITE Valentine messages on cookies with decorating gel or melted chocolate.
5d0b1991-3c24-410a-adce-f5afc69a44d6 INSERT decorated cookies in frosting on top of cupcakes.
2a21fcf9-7f6d-4314-a5fc-c656c2f9115a PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
2a21fcf9-7f6d-4314-a5fc-c656c2f9115a CENTER one-fourth of pork slices, broccoli, carrots, water chestnuts, red pepper and onions on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Combine soy sauce, sesame oil and ginger; spoon over pork and vegetables.
2a21fcf9-7f6d-4314-a5fc-c656c2f9115a BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
2a21fcf9-7f6d-4314-a5fc-c656c2f9115a BAKE 18 to 22 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven
2a21fcf9-7f6d-4314-a5fc-c656c2f9115a OR GRILL 14 to 16 minutes in covered grill. Serve with rice and soy sauce.
1bc58e9f-8b5b-49d0-bc18-f227ca1c435f PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line an 8x8x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, extending paper up sides of pan; set aside.
1bc58e9f-8b5b-49d0-bc18-f227ca1c435f COMBINE brown sugar, maple syrup and butter; pour mixture in parchment-lined pan. Sprinkle evenly with pecans. Layer apple slices over pecans; place cinnamon rolls on top of apples.
1bc58e9f-8b5b-49d0-bc18-f227ca1c435f REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: Substitute 1/2 cup sweetened dried cranberries for the apple, if desired.
1bc58e9f-8b5b-49d0-bc18-f227ca1c435f BAKE to minutes or until rolls are golden brown. Let stand minutes. Invert onto platter. Remove parchment paper. Serve warm
4e32d04d-5bd7-4cea-8f07-ccdc222a9323 LINE an 8x8-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, extending paper up sides of pan set aside.
4e32d04d-5bd7-4cea-8f07-ccdc222a9323 PREPARE brownie mix following package directions; stir in nuts and coconut. Spread batter evenly in parchment-lined pan.
4e32d04d-5bd7-4cea-8f07-ccdc222a9323 BAKE following brownie package directions. Cool completely.
4e32d04d-5bd7-4cea-8f07-ccdc222a9323 SPREAD chocolate frosting over cooled brownie. Squeeze softened vanilla frosting in 6 to 8 lines crosswise over chocolate frosting, spacing lines 1 inch apart. Using a wooden pick, draw lines through frosting alternating direction to create a marbled pattern. Cut into bars.
bc96895b-376e-41a4-9174-174a9caf6612 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
bc96895b-376e-41a4-9174-174a9caf6612 PLACE pizza crusts on parchment paper. In a small skillet, over medium heat cook garlic and onion in olive oil 3 to 4 minutes.
bc96895b-376e-41a4-9174-174a9caf6612 BRUSH pizza crusts with olive oil mixture. Top with tomatoes and olives. Sprinkle with cheese. Arrange onion on pizza
bc96895b-376e-41a4-9174-174a9caf6612 BAKE to minutes or until cheese is melted and pizzas are crispy. Garnish with basil.
df1a50e9-ff07-49f3-b647-a3377bd8be10 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
df1a50e9-ff07-49f3-b647-a3377bd8be10 PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
df1a50e9-ff07-49f3-b647-a3377bd8be10 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups
df1a50e9-ff07-49f3-b647-a3377bd8be10 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
df1a50e9-ff07-49f3-b647-a3377bd8be10 SPREAD the top of each cupcake with white frosting.
df1a50e9-ff07-49f3-b647-a3377bd8be10 ROLL the edge of the cupcakes in green sugar to coat.
df1a50e9-ff07-49f3-b647-a3377bd8be10 MAKE AND ASSEMBLE the olives 1.Use green fondant or tint white fondant with green food coloring and shape into 24 one-inch ovals. 2.Insert a red jelly bean at one short end of each oval to make the stuffed olives. 3.Insert one toothpick through each olive until olives are almost centered on toothpicks. 4.Insert one end of skewer with olive on each cupcake
3a6c9e1f-f566-4cb6-aba6-8696c4c23354 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
3a6c9e1f-f566-4cb6-aba6-8696c4c23354 PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
3a6c9e1f-f566-4cb6-aba6-8696c4c23354 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
3a6c9e1f-f566-4cb6-aba6-8696c4c23354 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
3a6c9e1f-f566-4cb6-aba6-8696c4c23354 SPREAD the top of each cupcake with white frosting.
3a6c9e1f-f566-4cb6-aba6-8696c4c23354 FOR HATS sprinkle top third and halfway down one side of each cupcake with red sugar crystals.
3a6c9e1f-f566-4cb6-aba6-8696c4c23354 FOR BEARD and HAT BRIM & TASSEL cut miniature marshmallows in half with scissors. Arrange marshmallows, cut-sides-down on edge of red sugar for hat brim and end of sugar on side for tassel. Place overlapping marshmallow slices around bottom of cupcake for beard.
3a6c9e1f-f566-4cb6-aba6-8696c4c23354 FOR FACE place mini candies on frosting for eyes and nose.
c8ad9632-9673-4904-816f-e0a2228e4463 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
c8ad9632-9673-4904-816f-e0a2228e4463 CENTER one pork chop on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil; sprinkle with chili powder and garlic salt. Top with pinto beans, corn and tomatoes.
c8ad9632-9673-4904-816f-e0a2228e4463 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
c8ad9632-9673-4904-816f-e0a2228e4463 BAKE 16 to 18 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR
c8ad9632-9673-4904-816f-e0a2228e4463 GRILL 9 to 11 minutes in covered grill.
c8ad9632-9673-4904-816f-e0a2228e4463 SERVING SUGGESTION: Serve with tortilla chips, if desired.
291ace79-5c40-43a7-b137-0891c2b6f5a1 LINE a large micro-wave safe plate with Reynolds Parchment Paper.
291ace79-5c40-43a7-b137-0891c2b6f5a1 WASH and dry apples. Remove core if desired. CUT apples into very thin slices, 1/8-inch or thinner. Place slices between two sheets of paper towel; pat slices dry with paper towel.
291ace79-5c40-43a7-b137-0891c2b6f5a1 ARRANGE apples slices in a single layer on parchment-lined plate.
291ace79-5c40-43a7-b137-0891c2b6f5a1 MICROWAVE on high power for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, until chip edges start to curl.
291ace79-5c40-43a7-b137-0891c2b6f5a1 COOL on plate for 2 to 3 minutes. Sprinkle with brown sugar and ground cinnamon, if desired. Eat immediately.
33a3b875-b409-48a6-b5d7-2a52df893a16 PREHEAT the oven to 375°.
33a3b875-b409-48a6-b5d7-2a52df893a16 MIX together the ground beef, peppers, onions, egg, soaked French bread, hot sauce to taste, and salt and pepper to taste.
33a3b875-b409-48a6-b5d7-2a52df893a16 DIVIDE the ground meat mixture into 3 Reynolds® Bakeware Non-Stick Mini-Loaf Pans with Parchment Lining and bake them in the oven on 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until the tops become brown and the meatloaf is firm to the touch.
33a3b875-b409-48a6-b5d7-2a52df893a16 EASILY REMOVE the meatloaves from the pans and sprinkle the cheese on top of each meatloaf and top them off with your favorite salsa.
33a3b875-b409-48a6-b5d7-2a52df893a16 SERVE hot.
99ee39ee-edaf-476c-bb54-2d914b6a9ee7 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place 24 Reynolds® Foil Baking Cups in muffin pans or on a cookie sheet; set aside.
99ee39ee-edaf-476c-bb54-2d914b6a9ee7 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes, adding 2 teaspoons peppermint extract to batter. Spoon batter into baking cups.
99ee39ee-edaf-476c-bb54-2d914b6a9ee7 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes. Cool.
99ee39ee-edaf-476c-bb54-2d914b6a9ee7 MIX frosting and remaining peppermint extract in a medium bowl until well blended. Tint with food coloring to desired shade of green. Frost cupcakes. Top with jelly beans or mini chocolate chips.
bbb2a031-63be-481d-ab84-847a218b6175 Cut the cod into 4 equal pieces, rinse and pat dry.
bbb2a031-63be-481d-ab84-847a218b6175 In a small saucepan, combine the water and sugar and bring to a boil. Stir in the miso and mirin or sake. Place the pan back over medium-high heat and stir until the sugar has dissolved. Remove from the heat and cool.
bbb2a031-63be-481d-ab84-847a218b6175 Place the cod in a ceramic dish and coat with the miso glaze. Marinate the fish overnight or for at least four hours.
bbb2a031-63be-481d-ab84-847a218b6175 Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F. Line a sheet pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Wipe off the excess marinade from the fish (but do not rinse with water) and place skin-side down on the foil-lined pan.
bbb2a031-63be-481d-ab84-847a218b6175 Drizzle the asparagus spears and sliced mushrooms with olive oil and season with kosher salt and black pepper. Toss to coat. Scatter the vegetables around the fish fillets.
bbb2a031-63be-481d-ab84-847a218b6175 Broil the fish and vegetables for 10 to 15 minutes depending on the thickness of the cod, or until the fish has cooked through but is still flaky and the vegetables are fork tender.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 PLACE 24 Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 SPREAD frosting onto cupcakes making sure to save 1/4 cup for decorations; set aside.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 Frost the top third of one vanilla wafer and place on top of cupcake.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 Place mini vanilla wafers in the top corners of the cupcake under the vanilla wafer that is going to be the monkey face. These will serve as ears and prop up the face to give it more dimension.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 Make eyes by placing 2 mini candy-coated chocolate candies on frosted part of vanilla wafer.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 Use black decorator icing to make a dot in center of candies for pupils of eyes and two dots in the center of the vanilla wafer for the nose.
ecfd7467-b758-4831-85d9-9d171bb50b66 Use red decorator icing to draw a mouth
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 PLACE 24 Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 ROLL out the pink fondant to 1/8th-inch thickness.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 CUT 48 3/4-inch circles for the ears and 24 2-inch ovals for the face. Keep the cut-out pieces covered with plastic wrap to prevent drying.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 CUT 12 of the mini chocolate candies in half to make the noses.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 SPOON 1/2 cup of the chocolate frosting into a zipper bag. Spread the top of each cupcake with the remaining chocolate frosting and make a smooth mound.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 PRESS the small fondant circles onto one side of each of the small cookies. Insert the cookies on either side of the cupcake for the ears.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 PRESS the large fondant oval on the lower front of the cupcakes for the mouth.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 ADD the candies for the eyes and the nose to each cupcake using a dot of frosting to secure.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 SNIP a small corner from the zipper bag with the chocolate frosting and pipe a few dots of frosting at the top of each cupcake as fur.
d017e91a-516b-46b8-b7d5-35731a3e7f14 PIPE a mouth on each cupcake with the black decorating frosting.
6505f3ac-3e9a-4280-8d94-141ebdcab917 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium–high.
6505f3ac-3e9a-4280-8d94-141ebdcab917 CENTER one chicken breast half one each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Combine cumin, cinnamon, salt and pepper; sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon mixture all over chicken. Combine tomatoes with remaining spice mixture; spoon beside chicken. Arrange zucchini strips over chicken and tomatoes.
6505f3ac-3e9a-4280-8d94-141ebdcab917 Bring up aluminum foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal foil packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two aluminum foil packets
6505f3ac-3e9a-4280-8d94-141ebdcab917 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven or GRILL 14 to 16 minutes in covered grill, until meat thermometer inserted in thickest part of chicken breast reads at least 165°F. SERVING SUGGESTION: Sprinkle with chopped fresh cilantro, if desired. Serve with hot cooked couscous or rice.
44fbc899-c9d4-4759-addc-f787515a3c6a CUT bananas crosswise in half. Insert wooden sticks in each half; set aside.
44fbc899-c9d4-4759-addc-f787515a3c6a MICROWAVE chocolate chips and peanut butter in a medium microwave-safe bowl on HIGH power, 1 to 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds until chocolate is melted.
44fbc899-c9d4-4759-addc-f787515a3c6a LINE countertop with an 18-inch sheet of Reynolds® Cut-Rite® Wax Paper. Pour melted chocolate on one end of the wax paper and nuts on the opposite end.
44fbc899-c9d4-4759-addc-f787515a3c6a ROLL banana pop in the melted chocolate to coat evenly; immediately roll in chopped nuts. Place banana pops on a tray lined with wax paper.
44fbc899-c9d4-4759-addc-f787515a3c6a PLACE in the freezer for 2 hours.
44fbc899-c9d4-4759-addc-f787515a3c6a WRAP each banana in Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Store in freezer.
4cf1ae64-a10c-4265-9b6f-6f093dc1f186 Heat oven to 350°F. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. In large bowl, break up cookie dough. Sprinkle vanilla and rum extract over dough; mix well. Stir toasted almonds into dough.
4cf1ae64-a10c-4265-9b6f-6f093dc1f186 Divide dough into 4 equal portions; shape each into 8x1-inch log. On cookie sheet, place logs 3 inches apart; flatten each log until about 1 1/2 inches wide.
4cf1ae64-a10c-4265-9b6f-6f093dc1f186 Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 200°F.
4cf1ae64-a10c-4265-9b6f-6f093dc1f186 With serrated knife, carefully cut each log into 10 (3/4-inch) slices. On same cookie sheet, place slices, cut side down.
4cf1ae64-a10c-4265-9b6f-6f093dc1f186 Return to oven; bake 1 hour. Remove cookies from cookie sheet to cooling rack. Cool completely, about 20 minutes. Meanwhile, in small microwavable bowl, place chocolate chips. Microwave on High 1 minute. Stir; microwave 1 minute longer, stirring every 15 seconds.
4cf1ae64-a10c-4265-9b6f-6f093dc1f186 Line cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Dip 1/4 of each cookie into melted chocolate; place on cookie sheet. Refrigerate until chocolate is set, about 10 minutes.
9c350d46-72e4-4348-a4b5-29858bd50262 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
9c350d46-72e4-4348-a4b5-29858bd50262 PREPARE pastry. Roll out half of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a sheet of lightly floured Reynolds Parchment Paper. Place in 9-inch deepdish pie plate; set aside.
9c350d46-72e4-4348-a4b5-29858bd50262 COMBINE apples, sugar, flour and cinnamon in large mixing bowl; mix to coat apples thoroughly. Spoon mixture evenly into pie crust; dot with butter.
