9c350d46-72e4-4348-a4b5-29858bd50262 ROLL remaining pastry for top crust to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured sheet or Reynolds<span>®</span> Parchment Paper. Place on top of pie. Trim off excess pastry along edges. Fold edges under and crimp. Cut design in center to allow steam to escape. Brush pastry lightly with milk; sprinkle with sugar.
9c350d46-72e4-4348-a4b5-29858bd50262 BAKE 45 to 50 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Serve warm.
9c350d46-72e4-4348-a4b5-29858bd50262 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: To prevent pie crusts from over-browning, make a foil pie ring. Fold a 12-inch foil square into quarters. With scissors, cut out center; round off edges, leaving a 2-inch-wide ring. Unfold ring; place over pie. Remove foil ring after baking pie 20 minutes.
f8d825aa-7677-4052-9137-5f191f9bf677 Whisk together eggs, orange juice, milk, 3 tablespoons pecans, brown sugar, orange zest, cinnamon and nutmeg.
f8d825aa-7677-4052-9137-5f191f9bf677 Pour half of the mixture into a 13x9x2-inch dish. Place the bread in a single layer on top of the egg batter. Pour the remaining batter over the top of the bread. Cover with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes.
f8d825aa-7677-4052-9137-5f191f9bf677 Fry bread in a skillet over medium-high heat until golden on each side.
f8d825aa-7677-4052-9137-5f191f9bf677 Serve with remaining pecans and maple syrup.
52e91424-3e3d-433b-b511-076230acac9e PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Fold each sheet of Reynolds Parchment Paper in half; then open on counter.
52e91424-3e3d-433b-b511-076230acac9e PLACE 1 cup spinach leaves beside center crease on each sheet of parchment paper. MIX minced garlic, salt, ground mustard and pepper; sprinkle and rub on both sides of each chicken breast half. Place chicken breast on spinach leaves.
52e91424-3e3d-433b-b511-076230acac9e TOP each chicken breast with 2 orange slices and ¼ of scallions. MIX olive oil, vinegar, and orange juice: spoon evenly over chicken.
52e91424-3e3d-433b-b511-076230acac9e FOLD other half of parchment paper over ingredients. Starting at top corner crease, crimp and twist edges of parchment sheets together to seal packet. Repeat to make four packets. Arrange packets in a single layer on large (21x17x1-inch) baking pan so that packets don’t hang over rim and touch oven racks or walls.
52e91424-3e3d-433b-b511-076230acac9e BAKE 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken reaches 170°F on a meat thermometer.
52e91424-3e3d-433b-b511-076230acac9e To serve, slide packet onto serving plate using oven mitts. OPEN packet carefully by cutting top with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape.
6b488644-6c6e-436f-8220-1a1bc0c64e3e PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
6b488644-6c6e-436f-8220-1a1bc0c64e3e SHAKE flour in Reynolds® Oven Bag, Large Size; place in 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
6b488644-6c6e-436f-8220-1a1bc0c64e3e LOOSEN skin of chicken over breast area by slipping your fingers or a knife under the skin. Place basil leaves and 4 orange slices under the skin. Divide onion slices and remaining orange slices between cavity of chicken and bottom of oven bag. Tuck the wings under the chicken and tie legs together, if desired. Brush chicken with vegetable oil; sprinkle with pepper. Place chicken in oven bag on top of onion and orange slices.
6b488644-6c6e-436f-8220-1a1bc0c64e3e CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
6b488644-6c6e-436f-8220-1a1bc0c64e3e BAKE 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until chicken is tender and meat thermometer reads at least 165°F in several places not touching the bone.
0557e993-f895-438e-ae90-b5c13defd521 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place Reynolds® Foil Baking Cups in muffin pans or on a cookie sheet; set aside.
0557e993-f895-438e-ae90-b5c13defd521 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes adding 1 teaspoon orange extract and vanilla extract to batter. Spoon batter into baking cups.
0557e993-f895-438e-ae90-b5c13defd521 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes. Cool.
0557e993-f895-438e-ae90-b5c13defd521 MIX frosting and remaining orange extract in a medium bowl until well blended. Frost cupcakes. Top with sprinkles.
72c7291c-39f6-497f-b3ce-79fff52aec44 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
72c7291c-39f6-497f-b3ce-79fff52aec44 SHAKE 1 tablespoon flour in Reynolds® Oven Bag, Large Size; place in 13x9x2–inch baking pan.
72c7291c-39f6-497f-b3ce-79fff52aec44 PLACE hens in oven bag. In small bowl, combine remaining flour, marmalade, soy sauce and ginger. Spoon sauce over hens in oven bag.
72c7291c-39f6-497f-b3ce-79fff52aec44 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in.
72c7291c-39f6-497f-b3ce-79fff52aec44 BAKE 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer inserted in thickest part of thigh not touching the bone reads 180°F. Let stand in oven bag 5 minutes. Serve with sauce, if desired.
8b94242d-00e9-42c0-a3d9-b64751b3094d PREHEAT grill to medium. Cut each rack of ribs into thirds. Center half of ribs in single layer on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
8b94242d-00e9-42c0-a3d9-b64751b3094d COMBINE all Seasoning Rub ingredients. Sprinkle and rub seasoning over ribs, turning to coat evenly.
8b94242d-00e9-42c0-a3d9-b64751b3094d BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and one end. Through open end, pour in 1/4 cup water. Double fold remaining end to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
8b94242d-00e9-42c0-a3d9-b64751b3094d GRILL 45 minutes to 1 hour on medium in covered grill. Remove steamed ribs carefully from foil. Place directly on grill. Combine peach preserves, lemon juice and soy sauce.
8b94242d-00e9-42c0-a3d9-b64751b3094d BRUSH ribs generously with glaze.
8b94242d-00e9-42c0-a3d9-b64751b3094d CONTINUE GRILLING 10 to 15 minutes on medium in uncovered grill, brushing with sauce and turning every 5 minutes to cook evenly.
66407af9-c0f1-44b3-ba77-44054b746e2d COMBINE all dry seasonings and ingredients in a bowl and mix.
66407af9-c0f1-44b3-ba77-44054b746e2d RUB the dry seasoning mixture on all sides of the pork ribs, cover with foil and place in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
66407af9-c0f1-44b3-ba77-44054b746e2d PREHEAT the oven to 300°.
66407af9-c0f1-44b3-ba77-44054b746e2d CUT the pork ribs in half so that there are 4 total ½ racks.
66407af9-c0f1-44b3-ba77-44054b746e2d PLACE the rubbed pork ribs into a Reynolds ® Bakeware roasting pan, cover with foil and cook in the oven for about 4 hours.
66407af9-c0f1-44b3-ba77-44054b746e2d POUR 1 ½ cups of BBQ sauce all over the ribs once they are done cooking and quickly sear on a hot grill (450° to 550°) for 3 minutes on each side.
66407af9-c0f1-44b3-ba77-44054b746e2d SERVE the ribs with the remaining ½ cup of BBQ sauce.
328f95da-6e4f-4ceb-a9d5-d443b34444aa Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. To prepare the artichokes, trim each stem to less than 2 inches in length. Slice off the tips of the artichoke and snip the thorny tips with some kitchen shears. Slice the artichoke in half lengthwise and then remove and discard the “choke” (white fibrous hairs and inner purple leaves) with a small knife.
328f95da-6e4f-4ceb-a9d5-d443b34444aa Lay out 8 squares of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Place 1 artichoke half in the center of each foil square. In a bowl, combine the olive oil, butter and lemon juice. Drizzle over the face-up artichoke halves, taking care to get the mixture in between the leaves. Flip the artichoke so it’s cut side down on the foil. Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet snugly around the artichoke. Roast on a baking sheet until the stems are fork-tender, about 40 minutes.
328f95da-6e4f-4ceb-a9d5-d443b34444aa As the artichokes roast, combine the mayonnaise, garlic, black pepper, chipotle powder and cheese; set aside.
328f95da-6e4f-4ceb-a9d5-d443b34444aa Open foil surrounding artichokes carefully by cutting along top with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape. Using tongs, flip the artichoke face up. Scoop the mayo mixture into the divot made by removing the “choke” and spread with a spoon to extend beyond the divot. Turn oven temperature to broil. Leaving the foil open, broil until the mayo mixture is browned, 4–5 minutes.
328f95da-6e4f-4ceb-a9d5-d443b34444aa To eat, remove the leaves from the outer part of the artichoke, dip in the mayo mixture and scrape the soft artichoke meat from the leaf with your teeth. Continue working your way through the artichoke until the leaves and dip disappear!
62219bda-f5d1-43b7-9075-edf437ba0d5f Preheat the oven to degrees. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Tear a third sheet the same size for later use.
62219bda-f5d1-43b7-9075-edf437ba0d5f In a large bowl, beat together butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar, salt and peanut butter. Blend in the eggs and vanilla.
62219bda-f5d1-43b7-9075-edf437ba0d5f In a separate bowl, combine the flour and baking soda. Then gradually stir the flour mixture into the batter until just combined. Mix in the chocolate chips.
62219bda-f5d1-43b7-9075-edf437ba0d5f Roll the dough balls by hand or use a small ice cream scoop, using roughly Tbsp of dough per cookie. Be sure to space them inches apart or more, with cookies per sheet. Flatten the cookies just a bit with a fork and make a crisscross pattern on top (if you like).
62219bda-f5d1-43b7-9075-edf437ba0d5f Bake the cookies for minutes in the oven, then allow them to cool for minutes directly on the cookie sheet prior to moving them to a wire rack. Once you have removed one set of cookies from the sheet, you can add your third sheet of parchment paper to the baking sheet and make your final set of cookies.
1c02cf26-0345-4f44-b524-be10506049ae Line a baking sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
1c02cf26-0345-4f44-b524-be10506049ae Spread out your popcorn evenly on the parchment paper. Then evenly top that with your pretzels, peanut butter cups and candies.
1c02cf26-0345-4f44-b524-be10506049ae Heat the peanut butter and chocolate chips with the canola oil in a microwave safe bowl on medium heat until melted. Check them every 30 seconds to prevent overheating.
1c02cf26-0345-4f44-b524-be10506049ae Use a fork to drizzle your melted chips all over your popcorn mix.
1c02cf26-0345-4f44-b524-be10506049ae Stick the entire pan in the fridge to cool for 15-20 minutes.
1c02cf26-0345-4f44-b524-be10506049ae Throw the mix into a Hefty® Slider bag for storage.
e47fe28d-8b1a-4f9b-b1bb-32c4fa8da6b1 PREHEAT broiler. Line a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil*. Set pan aside.
e47fe28d-8b1a-4f9b-b1bb-32c4fa8da6b1 Cut off and discard tips of chicken wings. Cut wings at joints to form 24 pieces. Put wing pieces into a large bowl; set aside.
e47fe28d-8b1a-4f9b-b1bb-32c4fa8da6b1 COMBINE the peanut butter, water, lime juice, soy sauce, honey, sesame oil, ginger, and garlic in a food processor or a blender. Cover and process or blend until smooth. Remove 1/3 cup of the sauce; add it to the chicken wings and stir to coat evenly. Add the cilantro to the remaining sauce in the food processor or blender and process or blend until combined. Set aside. Arrange chicken pieces in a single layer in prepared pan.
e47fe28d-8b1a-4f9b-b1bb-32c4fa8da6b1 BROIL wings 4 to 5 inches from the heat for 10 minutes. Turn wings. Broil about 10 minutes more or until tender and brown. Drain off fat.
e47fe28d-8b1a-4f9b-b1bb-32c4fa8da6b1 PLACE wings on a platter to serve, sprinkle with sesame seeds, and serve with the reserved peanut sauce.
043bca2c-6a09-4a33-95cc-5aa4b557a267 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line 2 cookie sheets with Reynolds<span>®</span> Parchment Paper; set aside.
043bca2c-6a09-4a33-95cc-5aa4b557a267 COMBINE 1 cup of butter, 1/2 cup of powdered sugar and 1/2 of teaspoon peppermint extract in large bowl. Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until creamy. Reduce speed to low; add flour and cornstarch. Beat until well mixed.
043bca2c-6a09-4a33-95cc-5aa4b557a267 COVER dough; refrigerate until firm (30 to 60 minutes).
043bca2c-6a09-4a33-95cc-5aa4b557a267 SHAPE rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on parchment-lined cookie sheets.
043bca2c-6a09-4a33-95cc-5aa4b557a267 BAKE 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Let stand 1 minute; slide parchment with cookies onto a wire rack to cool. Cool completely.
043bca2c-6a09-4a33-95cc-5aa4b557a267 FOR GLAZE, Combine 1-1/2 cups powdered sugar, 2 Tablespoons of butter, 1/4 teaspoon of peppermint extract and enough milk for desired glazing consistency in small bowl. Stir in food color, if desired. Drizzle glaze over cookies on parchment. Immediately sprinkle with crushed candy.
d8e6ae9e-774f-4690-8ba8-23509d1bb9ba PREHEAT oven to 425ºF. Shake flour in Reynolds Oven Bag, Large Size. Place in 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
d8e6ae9e-774f-4690-8ba8-23509d1bb9ba SEASON salmon with salt and pepper and spread pesto on top. Place in oven bag in a single layer; top with tomatoes and yellow pepper.
d8e6ae9e-774f-4690-8ba8-23509d1bb9ba CLOSE bag with nylon tie: cut six ½-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
d8e6ae9e-774f-4690-8ba8-23509d1bb9ba BAKE 15 to 20 minutes or until salmon flakes. Let stand 5 minutes. Carefully cut bag open to serve. Garnish with fresh basil and lemon twist, if desired.
d8e6ae9e-774f-4690-8ba8-23509d1bb9ba We tested with Buitoni® refrigerated pesto.
d8e6ae9e-774f-4690-8ba8-23509d1bb9ba Serve with Easy Mushroom & Onion Oven Risotto
4c757a7c-db4b-4b5d-a0c7-a6cc502c4a96 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Tear off four 15-inch sheets of Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Fold each sheet in half and crease it in the center. Unfold.
4c757a7c-db4b-4b5d-a0c7-a6cc502c4a96 PLACE 1 snapper fillet evenly one-half of each sheet near crease. Spread 1 teaspoon pesto onto each snapper fillet. Top each fillet with bell pepper rings and tomatoes.
4c757a7c-db4b-4b5d-a0c7-a6cc502c4a96 FOLD over other half of sheet to enclose ingredients. Starting at top corner, make small overlapping folds down entire length of packet to seal edges together. Twist the last fold several times to make a tight seal. Repeat to make 4 packets. Place parchment packets on large cookie sheet.
4c757a7c-db4b-4b5d-a0c7-a6cc502c4a96 BAKE to minutes. Place parchment packets on dinner plates. Carefully cut an X in top of each packet to allow steam to escape. Serve immediately.
fdc97266-3085-485b-a8f4-67414b23c381 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
fdc97266-3085-485b-a8f4-67414b23c381 PLACE Reynolds<span>®</span> Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
fdc97266-3085-485b-a8f4-67414b23c381 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups
fdc97266-3085-485b-a8f4-67414b23c381 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
fdc97266-3085-485b-a8f4-67414b23c381 TINT 1/4 cup of vanilla frosting bright pink. Spoon into freezer weight resealable bag and seal.
fdc97266-3085-485b-a8f4-67414b23c381 FROST cupcake with remaining white vanilla frosting.
fdc97266-3085-485b-a8f4-67414b23c381 SPRINKLE tops of cupcakes with pink decorating sugar.
fdc97266-3085-485b-a8f4-67414b23c381 CUT mini peanut butter cups in half. Press 4 peanut butter cup halves, cut side down, on top of cupcake.
fdc97266-3085-485b-a8f4-67414b23c381 SNIP small corner (1/8 inch) of bag with pink frosting. Pipe a swirl of frosting on top of each peanut butter cup to look like frosted cupcake.
a3bdcdaa-69e7-4611-a014-3ed9e5397020 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
a3bdcdaa-69e7-4611-a014-3ed9e5397020 PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
a3bdcdaa-69e7-4611-a014-3ed9e5397020 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups
a3bdcdaa-69e7-4611-a014-3ed9e5397020 BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
a3bdcdaa-69e7-4611-a014-3ed9e5397020 TINT frosting pink with red food coloring. Spread the top of each cupcake with tinted frosting.
a3bdcdaa-69e7-4611-a014-3ed9e5397020 SPRINKLE tops with pink sugar crystals.
a3bdcdaa-69e7-4611-a014-3ed9e5397020 ROLL out fondant. Cut into strips measuring 4 inches X 1/4 inch.
a3bdcdaa-69e7-4611-a014-3ed9e5397020 SHAPE fondant strips into ribbon shape. Place on cupcakes.
a3bdcdaa-69e7-4611-a014-3ed9e5397020 REYNOLDS KITCHEN TIP: MAKE COLORED SUGAR CRYSTALS Don't have colored sugar crystals? You can make your own! Place white granulated sugar on Cut-Rite Wax Paper. One drop at a time, add the food coloring and use your finger tips to work it through the sugar until the color is evenly distributed. One drop color will tint 1 or 2 tablespoons sugar a pastel shade. Too light, add more food coloring. Too dark, add more sugar.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d BAKE following package directions (17 to 23 minutes). Cool.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d MAKE AND ASSEMBLE the treasure chests: 1.Tint 1/4 cup each vanilla frosting yellow and red. Spoon each color into a separate zipper bag. 2.Snip a very small corner from each bag. Pipe 2 red lines on top (rounded side) of 24 of the chocolates as the bands of the chest. 3.Pipe a dollop of yellow frosting on the flat side of the remaining 24 chocolates and top with the yellow sprinkles to make the gold.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d MAKE AND ASSEMBLE the parrots: 1.Cut the wings and the tail feathers from the red fruit leather. 2.Make small slices in the green spice drop and insert the wings and the tail pieces of fruit leather to make the parrot. 3.Pipe a small dot of yellow frosting and attach the piece of banana candy as the beak. 4.Pipe the eyes with the black decorating frosting.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d SPREAD the tops of the cupcakes with the remaining vanilla frosting and make smooth.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d DIP the tops into the vanilla wafer crumbs to look like sand.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d PRESS the chocolates with the yellow frosting on top of the cupcakes. Add the other chocolates, flat side down to complete the treasure chests.
01b766be-d1a6-4270-a54c-86cf40c62f0d PIPE dots of yellow frosting on the treasure chests to secure the parrots on top. Pipe yellow feet on the parrots with the remaining yellow frosting.
fe63666a-3adb-4997-a629-2b4de54cd541 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
fe63666a-3adb-4997-a629-2b4de54cd541 COOK the onions in a large pot on high heat with olive oil until they become slightly brown.
fe63666a-3adb-4997-a629-2b4de54cd541 ADD in the can of diced tomatoes and juice once the onions are brown.
fe63666a-3adb-4997-a629-2b4de54cd541 BRING the tomatoes to a boil and whisk in the tomato paste.
fe63666a-3adb-4997-a629-2b4de54cd541 COOK the tomato sauce on medium heat until it becomes thick and add 1½ tablespoons of Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
fe63666a-3adb-4997-a629-2b4de54cd541 EVENLY SPREAD the cream cheese on the bottom of a Reynolds® 8x8 Bakeware pan.
fe63666a-3adb-4997-a629-2b4de54cd541 POUR the hot tomato sauce on top of the cream cheese followed up with the shredded mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
fe63666a-3adb-4997-a629-2b4de54cd541 SPRINKLE on the pepperoni and bake the pan in the oven for 25 minutes.
fe63666a-3adb-4997-a629-2b4de54cd541 SEREVE with sliced French bread.
2367e1c5-b477-444d-a836-2f3aa0ce3788 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
2367e1c5-b477-444d-a836-2f3aa0ce3788 PLACE Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups (Dots) in muffin pans; set aside.
2367e1c5-b477-444d-a836-2f3aa0ce3788 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups.
2367e1c5-b477-444d-a836-2f3aa0ce3788 BAKE following package directions (19 to 22 minutes). Cool.
2367e1c5-b477-444d-a836-2f3aa0ce3788 SPREAD the top of each cupcake with chocolate frosting.
2367e1c5-b477-444d-a836-2f3aa0ce3788 MAKE AND ASSEMBLE the purses: 1. Cut vanilla wafers in half & frost with vanilla frosting. 2. Dip the frosted wafers into bright pink sugar crystals. 3. Place on Reynolds Wax Paper to dry. 4. Once dry, use drops of frosting as glue to place mini candies on purses. Let set to dry. 5. For purse handles, pipe melted white chocolate onto Reynolds Wax Paper. 6. Place gold edible dragees onto the white chocolate; refrigerate to harden. 7. Use more melted white chocolate as glue to gently attach the handles to the purses. 8. For the clasp, add 2 gold edible dragees at the top of the purse with more melted white chocolate. INSERT half a preztel stick into the frosted cupcake slightly off center.
2367e1c5-b477-444d-a836-2f3aa0ce3788 PLACE the fully decorated purses carefully onto the cupcakes, leaning them onto the pretzels for support.
23a86fdb-38a6-47ff-b367-0a1b750d054f LINE a 15 1/2x10x1-inch baking pan or large tray with a sheet of Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
23a86fdb-38a6-47ff-b367-0a1b750d054f POP popcorn according to package directions; shake bag so that un-popped kernels fall to the bottom.
23a86fdb-38a6-47ff-b367-0a1b750d054f POUR popcorn, pretzels, almonds and dried cranberries into large bowl. Discard un-popped popcorn kernels.
23a86fdb-38a6-47ff-b367-0a1b750d054f MELT white morsels according to package directions. Stir in cinnamon; pour over popcorn and pretzels. Toss to evenly coat.
23a86fdb-38a6-47ff-b367-0a1b750d054f SPREAD evenly on parchment lined tray. Let set to harden, about 1 hour. Break apart large pieces. Store in airtight container.
7b03fdf7-944e-4bd8-aab3-336951ed4dc8 Preheat the grill to high heat.
7b03fdf7-944e-4bd8-aab3-336951ed4dc8 Line a hot grill with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil.
7b03fdf7-944e-4bd8-aab3-336951ed4dc8 Coat the chicken breasts with the oil and season on all sides with salt and pepper.
7b03fdf7-944e-4bd8-aab3-336951ed4dc8 Place the chicken breasts directly on the hot grill lined with foil and cook for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until grill marks have formed.
7b03fdf7-944e-4bd8-aab3-336951ed4dc8 Transfer the chicken in a slow cooker lined with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner and pour in water and BBQ sauce and cook on high heat for 3 hours or low heat for 5 hours.
7b03fdf7-944e-4bd8-aab3-336951ed4dc8 Pull the chicken apart using two forks until it is shredded and keep warm.
7b03fdf7-944e-4bd8-aab3-336951ed4dc8 Mix together the coleslaw mix, mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and salt and pepper until combined.
7b03fdf7-944e-4bd8-aab3-336951ed4dc8 Serve the pulled chicken on sweet rolls and top off with some creamy coleslaw.
0ae97efb-6a70-4f27-874c-1ba79b4a0655 COMBINE all dry seasonings and ingredients in a bowl and mix
0ae97efb-6a70-4f27-874c-1ba79b4a0655 RUB the dry seasoning mixture on all sides of the pork shoulder, cover with foil and place in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
0ae97efb-6a70-4f27-874c-1ba79b4a0655 PREHEAT oven to 300°
0ae97efb-6a70-4f27-874c-1ba79b4a0655 PLACE the rubbed pork shoulder into a Reynolds ® Bakeware roasting pan and cook in the oven for about 6 hours.
0ae97efb-6a70-4f27-874c-1ba79b4a0655 SHRED the pork using 2 forks until it is completely broken apart.
0ae97efb-6a70-4f27-874c-1ba79b4a0655 MIX in the BBQ sauce with the pulled pork and serve on mini buns
b0e3702c-78e9-4173-9e76-bcfc63a37e2d Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Combine the flour, oats, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a large mixing bowl. Melt the butter, let it cool, and pour into the mixing bowl with the dry ingredients. Stir until a soft dough forms. It should be just slightly crumbly. If the dough feels wet and heavy, add a little more flour.
b0e3702c-78e9-4173-9e76-bcfc63a37e2d Line the bottom and sides of a 9x13 inch baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Press 3/4 of the dough into the dish. Reserve the remaining 1/4 to use for topping. Bake for about 10 minutes or until the top is barely golden brown.
b0e3702c-78e9-4173-9e76-bcfc63a37e2d Combine the pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon, salt, ginger and cloves and mix until blended completely. When the crust is done, pour the filling mixture over the crust and continue to bake for 20 minutes.
b0e3702c-78e9-4173-9e76-bcfc63a37e2d Remove pan from oven and sprinkle the reserved dough over the filling. Bake for another 20 minutes. Let the bars cool.
b0e3702c-78e9-4173-9e76-bcfc63a37e2d For the caramel sauce, melt the 4 tablespoons of butter, 1/3 cup brown sugar and 1/3 cup cream together in a small saucepan. Set the temperature on medium heat and stir constantly until the caramel is smooth and barely bubbling. Pour over the bars. Cut and serve!
7188cb83-4eb6-415d-8ba0-b5d410ba4b63 <strong>PREHEAT</strong> oven to °F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Parchment Paper; set aside.
7188cb83-4eb6-415d-8ba0-b5d410ba4b63 <strong>COMBINE</strong> flour, baking powder, salt and spices in a medium bowl; set aside.
7188cb83-4eb6-415d-8ba0-b5d410ba4b63 <strong>BEAT</strong> butter and sugar together in a large bowl on medium speed, about minutes or until light and fluffy. Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla. Reduce speed to low. Gradually add flour mixture, beating after each addition until well blended. Stir in nuts and cranberries. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto parchmentlined cookie sheets.
7188cb83-4eb6-415d-8ba0-b5d410ba4b63 <strong>BAKE</strong> to minutes or until brown on edges. Slide parchment with cookies onto wire rack to cool.
7188cb83-4eb6-415d-8ba0-b5d410ba4b63 <strong>REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: </strong>
7188cb83-4eb6-415d-8ba0-b5d410ba4b63 Drizzle or frost cookies with cream cheese frosting, if desired.
623fc695-5c29-4c72-859e-3b1fb2d2125f PREHEAT oven to 400F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch pan. Spray inside of bag with cooking spray. Add flour and olive to oven bag; gently squeeze bag to mix ingredients.
623fc695-5c29-4c72-859e-3b1fb2d2125f REMOVE beet greens, leaving 2-inch stems and skin on beets. Wash beets; place in oven bag.
623fc695-5c29-4c72-859e-3b1fb2d2125f CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in bag near tie. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
623fc695-5c29-4c72-859e-3b1fb2d2125f BAKE 45 to 55 minutes or until beets are tender when pierced with a fork. Let stand 10 minutes. Carefully cut bag open and let beets cool slightly. When cool enough to handle, remove skin from beets.
623fc695-5c29-4c72-859e-3b1fb2d2125f CUT beets into -inch cubes; place in small bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
f85802c2-457f-4dbf-885d-4b57c8e171d1 Preheat oven to 475 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Spread the broccolini on the baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.
f85802c2-457f-4dbf-885d-4b57c8e171d1 Using tongs, gently toss the florets in the oil to combine. Cut the head of garlic in half, and place the exposed garlic in some of the drizzled olive oil. Turn the garlic-exposed side up on the baking sheet and sprinkle everything with red pepper flakes.
f85802c2-457f-4dbf-885d-4b57c8e171d1 Roast for 20-25 minutes until the broccolini is just slightly crispy.
f85802c2-457f-4dbf-885d-4b57c8e171d1 Remove the baking sheet from oven and squeeze juice from the the fresh lemon on top of the broccolini. Adjust seasoning and add grated Parmesan cheese. Transfer the broccolini to a serving platter with the halved garlic heads. Remove the aluminum foil from the baking sheet and discard for easy cleanup. Serve immediately.
4c5a9a74-a069-4df0-8cec-b0696a32b704 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Do not exceed 400°F. Add flour to a Reynolds® Large Oven Bag. Shake. Place bag in a roasting pan at least 2 inches deep.
4c5a9a74-a069-4df0-8cec-b0696a32b704 DRIZZLE eggplant with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
4c5a9a74-a069-4df0-8cec-b0696a32b704 PLACE eggplant and red onion in bag. Close bag with tie (found inside package). Cut six 1/2 -inch slits in top of bag to allow steam to escape. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
4c5a9a74-a069-4df0-8cec-b0696a32b704 PLACE pan in oven, allowing room for bag to expand during cooking without touching heating elements, wall, or racks. Bag should not hang over pan
4c5a9a74-a069-4df0-8cec-b0696a32b704 ROAST about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
4c5a9a74-a069-4df0-8cec-b0696a32b704 LINE a baking sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Place rolls on the prepared baking sheet with cut sides up. In a small bowl, mix feta and cream cheese together. Spread cheese mixture on cut sides of roll tops. Bake in the oven for the last 5 minutes of roasting.
4c5a9a74-a069-4df0-8cec-b0696a32b704 REMOVE rolls and eggplant from oven. To serve, carefully cut open top of oven bag. Remember: Always support bag with pan. Place eggplant and onion on roll bottoms. Top with red peppers and romaine. Close sandwiches with the cheese-topped halves.
0e33af7f-d8d9-4c45-8cc6-2505a65c3915 PREPARE Basil Oil: Combine basil, olive oil, chopped garlic and red pepper flakes in a large bowl; set aside.
0e33af7f-d8d9-4c45-8cc6-2505a65c3915 PREHEAT oven to 400F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in a 13x9x2-inch pan.
0e33af7f-d8d9-4c45-8cc6-2505a65c3915 PLACE tomatoes in oven bag and squeeze bag to crush tomatoes. Add eggplant, bell pepper, onion, oil, flour, Italian seasoning and salt. Turn bag several times to mix. Arrange ingredients in even layer.
0e33af7f-d8d9-4c45-8cc6-2505a65c3915 CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top of bag. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
0e33af7f-d8d9-4c45-8cc6-2505a65c3915 BAKE 20 to 25 minutes or until eggplant is tender. Carefully cut bag open. Spoon roasted vegetables into Basil Oil. Add the cooked pasta and cheeses; stir until mixed well. Serve immediately or at room temperature.
1797792d-6bd0-4ecc-8f9c-269ad8968659 PREHEAT oven to 400F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
1797792d-6bd0-4ecc-8f9c-269ad8968659 ADD flour and balsamic dressing to oven bag; gently squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Add mushrooms and onions; turn bag several times to coat vegetables with dressing.
1797792d-6bd0-4ecc-8f9c-269ad8968659 CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in neck of bag. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
1797792d-6bd0-4ecc-8f9c-269ad8968659 BAKE 10 minutes or until mushrooms are tender when pierced with a fork. COMBINE salad ingredients in a large bowl while mushrooms are baking.
1797792d-6bd0-4ecc-8f9c-269ad8968659 REMOVE mushrooms from oven and carefully cut open bag. Let cool slightly. Serve on plate with salad; drizzle additional balsamic vinaigrette dressing over mushrooms and salad, if desired.
b9f6808e-08a4-4326-91ee-13d11233f871 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. PLACE Reynolds® Oven Bags in 13x9x2-inch baking pan. SHAKE flour and paprika in bag.
b9f6808e-08a4-4326-91ee-13d11233f871 ADD potatoes, bell pepper and garlic to bag. Gently squeeze oven bag to blend ingredients and arrange in an even layer. Roll down open end of oven bag two or three times so that it stays open; set aside.
b9f6808e-08a4-4326-91ee-13d11233f871 HEAT oil in skillet on medium heat. Add onion and sausage, stirring until mixture starts to soften, about 5 minutes. Spoon evenly over ingredients in oven bag. Carefully pour chicken stock over ingredients in oven bag. Unroll open end of oven bag.
b9f6808e-08a4-4326-91ee-13d11233f871 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie (included in package); cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag. Tuck ends of oven bag in pan.
b9f6808e-08a4-4326-91ee-13d11233f871 BAKE for 45 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
b9f6808e-08a4-4326-91ee-13d11233f871 CAREFULLY cut the oven bag open. Spoon the salad into a serving dish.
b9f6808e-08a4-4326-91ee-13d11233f871 GARNISH with chopped basil (optional).
b9f6808e-08a4-4326-91ee-13d11233f871 SERVE warm or at room temperature.
0cb611ef-090d-46d8-829c-6c4e749c7713 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Lay a large sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil on a baking sheet. In the center of the foil, combine the sausage, onion, sauerkraut, oil, butter, pepper and caraway seeds; mix well. Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to make a packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Place the foil package in preheated oven and roast for 30 minutes.
0cb611ef-090d-46d8-829c-6c4e749c7713 Open packets carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape; then open top of foil packet. Stir in the green apples and reseal, adding another piece of foil to the top if necessary. Return to the oven for 10 more minutes. Remove from the oven, add salt to taste and serve.
3448be73-7344-416f-bf64-aaf1045ec1d4 Line a 9-inch pie pan with 1 pie crust. Crimp and flute the edges then transfer to refrigerator.
3448be73-7344-416f-bf64-aaf1045ec1d4 Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Line an 18x13x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
3448be73-7344-416f-bf64-aaf1045ec1d4 Place potatoes, onions, carrots, garlic and peppers in the prepared pan. Drizzle vegetables with oil, and then toss in the pan. Sprinkle vegetables with salt and pepper and then arrange in a single layer. Bake for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and reduce oven temperature to 375 degrees F.
3448be73-7344-416f-bf64-aaf1045ec1d4 Whisk together eggs, milk, cream and cheese.
3448be73-7344-416f-bf64-aaf1045ec1d4 Transfer vegetables to the prepared pie shell. Pour the egg mixture on top.
3448be73-7344-416f-bf64-aaf1045ec1d4 Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until eggs are fully cooked.
4a0ee688-afb3-421d-bc4c-d6aeca8f7fc2 PREHEAT oven to 425°F.
4a0ee688-afb3-421d-bc4c-d6aeca8f7fc2 LINE a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food; set aside.
4a0ee688-afb3-421d-bc4c-d6aeca8f7fc2 COMBINE rosemary, orange peel and garlic in a small bowl. Brush chicken with olive oil; sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper. Spread 1 teaspoon of rosemary mixture over each chicken breast half. Add honey to remaining rosemary mixture; set aside.
4a0ee688-afb3-421d-bc4c-d6aeca8f7fc2 BAKE 35 to 40 minutes or until meat thermometer reads 165°F. Brush with rosemary-honey mixture and continue baking 5 to 10 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear or meat thermometer reads 170°F.
fd5dab0e-4450-45c4-9b31-1b7551398288 PREHEAT the oven to 400°.
fd5dab0e-4450-45c4-9b31-1b7551398288 ADD 1 tablespoon of flour to a Reynolds® Oven Bag and shake. Place the bag in a 13x9x2 inch casserole dish.
fd5dab0e-4450-45c4-9b31-1b7551398288 PLACE the precooked white rice into the Reynolds® Oven Bag.
fd5dab0e-4450-45c4-9b31-1b7551398288 ADD the salmon on top of the pre cooked rice and evenly spread on the tomato wedges, olives, jalapeño slices, capers and lemons all over the top of the salmon and season with salt and pepper.
fd5dab0e-4450-45c4-9b31-1b7551398288 CLOSE the bag and seal it with the provided tie.
fd5dab0e-4450-45c4-9b31-1b7551398288 CUT 6 half inch slits in the top of the bag and tuck all of the ends into the pan and bake for 30-35 minutes on 400° or until the salmon flakes apart.
fd5dab0e-4450-45c4-9b31-1b7551398288 REMOVE the salmon, rice and toppings from the bag, drain any excess liquid from the bag, and place on a large plate to serve.
a849e534-3145-4eb3-97ae-68f3a99431f1 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium–high.
a849e534-3145-4eb3-97ae-68f3a99431f1 CENTER one–half of steak cubes on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food; sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon Sante Fe seasoning. Arrange zucchini, red pepper and corn on top of steak. Combine gravy, remaining seasoning and salt; drizzle over beef and vegetables.
a849e534-3145-4eb3-97ae-68f3a99431f1 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
a849e534-3145-4eb3-97ae-68f3a99431f1 BAKE 18 to 20 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR
a849e534-3145-4eb3-97ae-68f3a99431f1 GRILL 10 to 12 minutes in covered grill.
9a5518ba-fbc6-4a05-9084-37c56df33db5 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
9a5518ba-fbc6-4a05-9084-37c56df33db5 SLICE steak across the grain into thin strips. Center one-fourth of beef strips on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Top with snow peas. Combine teriyaki sauce, peanut butter and cornstarch; mix until smooth and well blended. Pour teriyaki mixture evenly over meat and vegetables.
9a5518ba-fbc6-4a05-9084-37c56df33db5 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
9a5518ba-fbc6-4a05-9084-37c56df33db5 BAKE 14 to 18 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven
9a5518ba-fbc6-4a05-9084-37c56df33db5 OR GRILL 10 to 14 minutes in covered grill.
9a5518ba-fbc6-4a05-9084-37c56df33db5 SERVE over angel hair pasta. Sprinkle each serving with tomatoes and green onions.
fe2aad2f-905e-4c1c-a474-983af17cba83 PREHEAT grill to medium heat. Mix together barbecue sauce, marmalade and pepper sauce until well blended; set aside.
fe2aad2f-905e-4c1c-a474-983af17cba83 CUT ribs into 2- or 4-rib sections. Center half of the ribs in single layer on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
fe2aad2f-905e-4c1c-a474-983af17cba83 BRING up long sides of foil. Double fold top and one end to seal. Pour 1/4 cup water (or 3 to 4 ice cubes) into foil packet through opening on side. Double fold remaining end, leaving room for heat circulation inside packet. Repeat with remaining ribs to make 2 packets.
fe2aad2f-905e-4c1c-a474-983af17cba83 GRILL covered 45 minutes or until ribs are cooked through. Remove from foil. Make drainage holes in a sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with a grilling fork. Place foil sheet on grill grate with non-stick (dull) side facing up. Immediately place ribs on foil. Brush ribs with barbecue sauce mixture.
fe2aad2f-905e-4c1c-a474-983af17cba83 CONTINUE GRILLING uncovered an additional 10 to 15 minutes; turning every 5 minutes and brushing with the remaining sauce.
80ae8a02-2159-4943-8d32-09a6ccb23aba PREHEAT oven to 375F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch pan. Spray inside of bag with cooking spray.
80ae8a02-2159-4943-8d32-09a6ccb23aba ADD cooking crme, artichokes, drained spinach, cheeses, mayonnaise, flour and garlic powder to oven bag. Gently squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Arrange ingredients in an even layer in bag.
80ae8a02-2159-4943-8d32-09a6ccb23aba CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan
80ae8a02-2159-4943-8d32-09a6ccb23aba BAKE 20 minutes or until mixture starts browning and is bubbly. Carefully cut bag open.
80ae8a02-2159-4943-8d32-09a6ccb23aba SPOON dip into serving dish; sprinkle with ground paprika, if desired. Serve warm with pita chips, tortilla chips or crackers.
11fdcc73-41c1-4a96-8167-ca788499166e PREHEAT oven to 450°F or preheat grill to medium-high. Sprinkle both sides of steak with garlic powder and pepper; cut in thin strips. Combine steak strips, mushrooms and teriyaki sauce.
11fdcc73-41c1-4a96-8167-ca788499166e CENTER one-fourth of steak mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Top with green onions.
11fdcc73-41c1-4a96-8167-ca788499166e BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets
11fdcc73-41c1-4a96-8167-ca788499166e BAKE 12 to 15 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR
11fdcc73-41c1-4a96-8167-ca788499166e GRILL 7 to 9 minutes in covered grill. SERVE over noodles.
3937231a-5c64-4cfc-a037-1ba2334b8194 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
3937231a-5c64-4cfc-a037-1ba2334b8194 BROWN meat slightly in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat; place into slow cooker liner. Add remaining ingredients; place lid on slow cooker.
3937231a-5c64-4cfc-a037-1ba2334b8194 COOK on LOW for 6 to 7 hours OR on HIGH for 4 to 5 hours.
3937231a-5c64-4cfc-a037-1ba2334b8194 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
ba98a114-80d2-4378-880d-23f929cefcc1 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
ba98a114-80d2-4378-880d-23f929cefcc1 PLACE pork in slow cooker liner. Mix salsa, peanut butter, ginger, soy sauce, sesame oil, cayenne pepper and garlic. Pour over pork. Place lid on slow cooker.
ba98a114-80d2-4378-880d-23f929cefcc1 COOK on LOW for 5 to 6 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours or until meat thermometer inserted in pork reaches 160°F.
ba98a114-80d2-4378-880d-23f929cefcc1 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Spoon rice onto serving platter. Remove pork from slow cooker using slotted spoon and place on top of rice. Gently stir sauce with plastic or wooden spoon; spoon sauce over pork. Sprinkle with cashews and green onions. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
6cdf3bc7-ef68-40ae-a426-3dec130d77f5 In a medium saucepan stir sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and butter into berries and simmer over medium heat until sugar is dissolved, well blended and juicy. Stir constantly to prevent burning.
6cdf3bc7-ef68-40ae-a426-3dec130d77f5 Combine remaining dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
6cdf3bc7-ef68-40ae-a426-3dec130d77f5 In microwave, melt 1/2-cup butter and stir into milk, then add beaten egg. Add to dry mixture and stir until crumbly.
6cdf3bc7-ef68-40ae-a426-3dec130d77f5 Line slow cooker with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner and pour berries into the liner.
6cdf3bc7-ef68-40ae-a426-3dec130d77f5 Sprinkle topping mixture over berries and cook on high for 2-3 hours.
6cdf3bc7-ef68-40ae-a426-3dec130d77f5 Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.
70c3cc37-72b9-4c17-b894-e71a7f23acc5 Trim fat from brisket. Cut the brisket, if necessary, to fit in a 3-1/2- to 4-quart crockery cooker.
70c3cc37-72b9-4c17-b894-e71a7f23acc5 Line slow cooker with the Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner.
70c3cc37-72b9-4c17-b894-e71a7f23acc5 Add water, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, and cumin or chili powder.
70c3cc37-72b9-4c17-b894-e71a7f23acc5 Cover and cook on low-heat setting for 10 to 12 hours or on high-heat setting for 4 to 5 hours. About 1 hour before serving, remove the meat from the cooker.
70c3cc37-72b9-4c17-b894-e71a7f23acc5 Discard cooking liquid. Using two forks to pull, shred meat and return it to the cooker. Stir in barbecue sauce. Cover and cook on the high-heat setting for 30 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
70c3cc37-72b9-4c17-b894-e71a7f23acc5 Serve atop split Kaiser rolls or hamburger buns with pickles and onion, if desired.
bd3a50cd-c929-4c72-9ad2-4690507dd27f OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
bd3a50cd-c929-4c72-9ad2-4690507dd27f PLACE all ingredients in the slow cooker liner; stir gently to mix.
bd3a50cd-c929-4c72-9ad2-4690507dd27f COOK on LOW for 7 to 8 hours OR on HIGH for 4 to 5 hours until done.
bd3a50cd-c929-4c72-9ad2-4690507dd27f CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
bd3a50cd-c929-4c72-9ad2-4690507dd27f REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: This recipe was developed for 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cookers, but it may be adjusted for smaller or larger cookers. Fill slow cooker at least 3/4 full for best results.
beefc15e-a470-4184-86bd-a4ae5cb7bfc1 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
beefc15e-a470-4184-86bd-a4ae5cb7bfc1 COAT roast in flour; brown on both sides in oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Place in the slow cooker liner. Top with onions, salt and pepper.
beefc15e-a470-4184-86bd-a4ae5cb7bfc1 COMBINE water, soy sauce, onion soup mix and ginger in a bowl. Pour over roast. Place lid on slow cooker.
beefc15e-a470-4184-86bd-a4ae5cb7bfc1 COOK on LOW for 8 to 9 hours OR on HIGH for 5 to 6 hours or until pot roast is tender.
beefc15e-a470-4184-86bd-a4ae5cb7bfc1 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker liner. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
2444a5e1-9d6e-4372-a3ad-ce877185caa9 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -qt slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
2444a5e1-9d6e-4372-a3ad-ce877185caa9 POUR the vegetable juice and water into the slow cooker liner. Add beef, vegetables, ketchup, bouillon and pepper; stir gently. Place lid on slow cooker.
2444a5e1-9d6e-4372-a3ad-ce877185caa9 COOK on LOW for 8 to 9 hours OR on HIGH for 4 to 5 hours until beef is tender.
2444a5e1-9d6e-4372-a3ad-ce877185caa9 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from lined-slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
a5e90b5b-6976-47fb-834d-5f6234f3828c OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
a5e90b5b-6976-47fb-834d-5f6234f3828c PLACE frozen vegetables and onion into slow cooker liner. Whisk together soup, chicken broth and spices in a large bowl until well blended. Add to slow cooker liner; place lid on slow cooker.
a5e90b5b-6976-47fb-834d-5f6234f3828c COOK on LOW for 4 to 5 hours OR on HIGH for 2 to 3 hours until vegetables are heated through.
a5e90b5b-6976-47fb-834d-5f6234f3828c CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Whisk together evaporated milk and flour in a medium bowl until well blended; add to slow cooker. Gently stir in cubed chicken. Place lid on slow cooker; cook 1 hour longer. Serve soup directly from slow cooker liner. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
7e8c6e03-b9dd-4f95-9e9f-c64bcc90a334 Line a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner. Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
7e8c6e03-b9dd-4f95-9e9f-c64bcc90a334 Place all ingredients, except bay leaf and cheese, in slow cooker liner. Stir gently using a wooden or plastic spoon to mix ingredients. Place bay leaves on top of ingredients. Place lid on slow cooker.
7e8c6e03-b9dd-4f95-9e9f-c64bcc90a334 Cover on low for 8 to 9 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.
7e8c6e03-b9dd-4f95-9e9f-c64bcc90a334 Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Remove bay leaves. Gently stir in cheese. Serve chowder directly from slow cooker liner. Sprinkle each serving with additional shredded cheese, if desired. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
a5843186-6b56-4534-a5d7-15d769063484 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
a5843186-6b56-4534-a5d7-15d769063484 PLACE chicken in slow cooker liner. Mix seasonings; sprinkle 1 teaspoon mixture into chicken cavity. Sprinkle remaining seasonings over chicken. Drizzle with lemon juice and butter. Place lid on slow cooker.
a5843186-6b56-4534-a5d7-15d769063484 COOK on LOW for 5 to 6 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours or until meat thermometer inserted into thickest part of chicken thigh not touching bone reads 180°F.
a5843186-6b56-4534-a5d7-15d769063484 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Place chicken on a platter to slice and serve. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
a5843186-6b56-4534-a5d7-15d769063484 REYNOLDS KITCHEN TIP:To reduce fat and calories, remove skin from chicken before eating.
be311d85-3ed6-413d-8240-542aed39bfe2 Line a slow cooker with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner. Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
be311d85-3ed6-413d-8240-542aed39bfe2 Whisk together soy sauce, garlic, brown sugar, sambal oelek, oyster sauce, ginger and sesame oil in the slow cooker. Add pork shoulder, then cover and cook on low heat for 7 to 8 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.
be311d85-3ed6-413d-8240-542aed39bfe2 Remove pork shoulder from the slow cooker and shred the meat before returning to the pot with the juices. Stir in broccoli, carrots, celery, snow peas and water chestnuts. Cover and cook on high heat for 15 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
be311d85-3ed6-413d-8240-542aed39bfe2 Cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.
be311d85-3ed6-413d-8240-542aed39bfe2 Serve pasta immediately, topped with pork mixture.
5c2447ed-6297-4818-9399-3f422121d96c OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
5c2447ed-6297-4818-9399-3f422121d96c COMBINE milk, soup, eggs, onion, cheese and macaroni in a large bowl until well blended. Sprinkle flour and pepper into cheese mixture; stir to combine. Pour into slow cooker liner. Place lid on slow cooker.
5c2447ed-6297-4818-9399-3f422121d96c COOK on LOW for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
5c2447ed-6297-4818-9399-3f422121d96c CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve food directly from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
5c2447ed-6297-4818-9399-3f422121d96c REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: To reduce fat and calories you may substitute reduced fat milk and reduced fat cheddar cheese.
3ea5c3eb-b4b4-428b-b008-c0f5eba4ba2e OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
3ea5c3eb-b4b4-428b-b008-c0f5eba4ba2e PLACE beef in the slow cooker liner. Combine mushroom soup, onion soup mix and brown gravy mix in a bowl until well blended. Stir in ginger ale. Add mushrooms to mixture; pour over beef. Place lid on slow cooker.
3ea5c3eb-b4b4-428b-b008-c0f5eba4ba2e COOK on LOW for 5 to 6 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours.
3ea5c3eb-b4b4-428b-b008-c0f5eba4ba2e CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food over noodles directly from slow cooker liner. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Add Reynolds® Slow Cooker liner to slow cooker
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Rinse brisket, pat dry and rub entire beef brisket with extra virgin olive oil
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Season brisket with sea salt, ground black pepper, granulated garlic, adobe all-purpose seasoning, paprika and dark/light brown sugar
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Place brisket in Reynolds® Slow Cooker liner in the slow cooker and add the beefy onion soup mix, beef broth, apple cider vinegar and A1 steak sauce
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Close the slow cooker with the lid and turn slow cooker on low heat, set timer for 9-12 hours and let it do its magic!
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Allow brisket to rest 8-10 minutes after removing from the slow cooker before slicing. (If you are serving the next day, allow brisket to cool completely then put in the refrigerator – to re-heat it the next day, slice and add extra virgin olive oil to skillet and cook for 2-4 minutes or until tender).<br />LET’S MAKE THE RED & GREEN PEPPERS WITH HONEY
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Add 2-4 tsp. olive oil to a skillet, cook red and green bell peppers over medium heat for 8-10 minutes or until tender, after bell peppers are tender, drizzle honey over them and allow to cook addition 2-4 minutes or until honey is caramelized.<br />LET’S MAKE THE OPEN FACED SANDWICH
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Turn oven to broil
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Split potato sandwich rolls in the middle (so you open the sandwich from the middle instead of the sides, spread unsalted butter on potato bread sandwich roll, pile brisket on, add bell peppers and add creamy Havarti cheese on top
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Broil for 1-2 minutes or until cheese is melted (watch it so it doesn’t burn)
e350de96-9692-4fea-8047-556e189ababe Add your favorite condiment (mayo, ketchup, mustard or like my daughter nothing at all) and ENJOY ENJOY ENJOY!!
04d7fd19-6f2c-481e-bd71-9c21b430b172 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
04d7fd19-6f2c-481e-bd71-9c21b430b172 PLACE all ingredients in the slow cooker liner; stir gently to mix. Place lid on slow cooker.
04d7fd19-6f2c-481e-bd71-9c21b430b172 COOK on LOW for 6 to 7 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours until hot and sauce thickens slightly.
04d7fd19-6f2c-481e-bd71-9c21b430b172 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker liner. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
52a9f230-91f2-498d-a288-a7d6deff8529 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
52a9f230-91f2-498d-a288-a7d6deff8529 PLACE chicken and carrots in the slow cooker liner. Pour white wine and chicken broth over chicken. Rub garlic over chicken. Sprinkle with rosemary, salt and pepper. Place lid on slow cooker.
52a9f230-91f2-498d-a288-a7d6deff8529 COOK on LOW for 5 to 6 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours or until meat thermometer inserted into thickest part of chicken thigh not touching bone reads 180°F.
52a9f230-91f2-498d-a288-a7d6deff8529 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Place chicken and vegetables on a platter to slice. Serve with rice, if desired. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
52a9f230-91f2-498d-a288-a7d6deff8529 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP:To reduce fat and calories, remove skin of chicken with a sharp knife or kitchen scissors before cooking.The slow cooker will keep your chicken moist and tender.
5ed200e9-2044-430a-9646-96547d07355d Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
5ed200e9-2044-430a-9646-96547d07355d Beat the butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds in a large mixing bowl. Add 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking soda, cream of tartar, and salt. Beat until combined, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally. Add the eggs one at a time, mixing until combined. Beat in the vanilla. Begin to add in as much of the flour as you can with the mixer. Using a wooden spoon, stir in any remaining flour and the pecans. Cover and chill about 1 hour or until the dough is easy to handle.
5ed200e9-2044-430a-9646-96547d07355d Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in a small bowl. Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls. Roll the balls in the sugar mixture to coat. Arrange 2 inches apart on the prepared cookie sheets. Flatten the dough balls slightly. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are firm and bottoms are very light brown.
5ed200e9-2044-430a-9646-96547d07355d While the cookies bake, beat the butter with an electric mixer on medium speed in a large mixing bowl until smooth. Add 2 cups powdered sugar, beating well. Mix in 1/4 cup milk, cinnamon, and vanilla. Gradually beat in the remaining powdered sugar. Beat in 2 to 4 teaspoons more milk until the frosting is of spreading consistency.
5ed200e9-2044-430a-9646-96547d07355d Let cool on the cookie sheets for 2 minutes. Slide the parchment paper with baked cookies on it to wire racks and let cool completely. Once cooled, slide the parchment paper onto a work surface.
5ed200e9-2044-430a-9646-96547d07355d Spread Cinnamon Buttercream Frosting onto the flat side of half of the cookies. Top with remaining cookies, flat sides down. Place unfilled cookies in an airtight container. Store at room temperature up to 3 days, or label and freeze for up to 3 months.
d135872c-6773-42c4-a4bf-faccad023c24 COMBINE dry rub ingredients in a small bowl; stir together. Sprinkle rub all over pork roast, patting it onto meat with your fingertips. Cover with foil and let pork cure at room temperature while you make the mop sauce.
d135872c-6773-42c4-a4bf-faccad023c24 MIX vinegar, mustard, water, salt and pepper in a large non-reactive bowl, add 1/2 cup water; whisk until salt dissolves.
d135872c-6773-42c4-a4bf-faccad023c24 SET UP grill for indirect grilling and PREHEAT grill to high. If using a gas grill, place all the wood chips or chunks in a smoker box or smoker pouch and run the grill on high until you see smoke, then reduce heat to medium-low. If using a charcoal grill, place a drip pan in the center, preheat the grill to medium-low, then toss 1 cup of the wood chips or chunks on the coals.
d135872c-6773-42c4-a4bf-faccad023c24 TO COOK, place pork roast, skin side up, if it has skin, in center of the grill grate over the drip pan and away from heat. Cover grill. Cook pork roast until darkly browned on the outside, about 3 hours. Cover loosely with Reynolds Wrap Foil; continue cooking for 1 to 2 hours longer, or until meat is very tender, 4 to 5 hours total. To test for doneness, use an instant-read meat thermometer: The internal temperature of the pork should be 195 degrees F. (Anything less and it will be impossible to pull the pork.) Every hour for the first 3 hours, swab the pork with some of the mop sauce, using a barbecue mop or basting brush. If using a charcoal grill, every hour youll need to add 12 fresh coals and 1/2 cup of wood chips or chunks to each side.
d135872c-6773-42c4-a4bf-faccad023c24 TRANSFER pork roast to a cutting board, cover it loosely with Reynolds Wrap Foil; let it rest 20 minutes. You can pull the meat into shreds with your fingers or two forks. You can also chop the pork with a knife or cleaver, or slice it across the grain (the practice of many South Carolina Pit Masters). Place shredded or sliced pork in an aluminum foil pan. If you are not quite ready to serve, cover pan tightly with Reynolds Wrap Foil; place it on a warmnot hotgrill or in a low (300 degrees F.) oven until heated through, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally with tongs.
d135872c-6773-42c4-a4bf-faccad023c24 BEFORE SERVING, if desired, brush hamburger buns with melted butter and lightlytoast them on the grill. Spread with mustard, if desired. Load each bun with pork. Top with pickle slices and serve immediately.
80df6e99-d5fa-4adc-a822-e675c4be6aea Let cookie dough stand at room temperature for 10 minutes to soften. Meanwhile, heat oven to 350°F. In large bowl, break up cookie dough; add marmalade and pecans. In small bowl, mix flour, 1/4 cup cocoa, coffee granules, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and red pepper; stir into dough mixture with wooden spoon until well blended.
80df6e99-d5fa-4adc-a822-e675c4be6aea Shape dough into 24 (about 1 1/2-inch) balls. On large cookie sheets lined with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, place balls 2 inches apart. Gently press 1 espresso bean into center of each cookie.
80df6e99-d5fa-4adc-a822-e675c4be6aea Bake 9 to 12 minutes or until tops are cracked and edges are set. Let stand on cookie sheet 1 minute; remove to cooling racks. Cool completely, about 30 minutes.
80df6e99-d5fa-4adc-a822-e675c4be6aea In small bowl, mix powdered sugar, milk and 1 tablespoon cocoa until smooth and well blended; drizzle over cookies. Let stand about 15 minutes until set.
de1d1e18-ca4e-4094-b739-4a49369bf270 Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.
de1d1e18-ca4e-4094-b739-4a49369bf270 Whisk together the harissa, honey and lemon in a bowl. Add chicken and mix until coated.
de1d1e18-ca4e-4094-b739-4a49369bf270 Skewer the chicken evenly between 8 wooden skewers and set aside.
de1d1e18-ca4e-4094-b739-4a49369bf270 Mix together the squash, zucchini, onion, mushrooms, olive oil, cumin and salt and pepper until completely combined.
de1d1e18-ca4e-4094-b739-4a49369bf270 Place a 1 1/2 to 2 feet long sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil on a table and place 1/4 of the vegetables in the center of the foil. Place 2 chicken skewers on top of the vegetables. Fold up the ends and then the outside of the foil to create a foil packet.
de1d1e18-ca4e-4094-b739-4a49369bf270 Repeat the process 3 more times and place the foil packets on a cookie sheet.
de1d1e18-ca4e-4094-b739-4a49369bf270 Bake in the oven at 425 degrees F for 20 minutes and then open the foil packets and cook for a further 15 minutes or until the chicken is lightly browned and cooked throughout.
75a5bf74-a171-4aca-8ed2-6af0af6b8adf Preheat the broiler to low heat.
75a5bf74-a171-4aca-8ed2-6af0af6b8adf Whisk together the chili garlic sauce, 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, 1 tablespoon of sesame oil, sugar and vinegar until combined.
75a5bf74-a171-4aca-8ed2-6af0af6b8adf Add the cut up salmon to the bowl and mix until coated.
75a5bf74-a171-4aca-8ed2-6af0af6b8adf Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and evenly spread out the salmon and cook under the broiler for 8 to 10 minutes or until browned and cooked throughout.
75a5bf74-a171-4aca-8ed2-6af0af6b8adf Pour the remaining 1 tablespoon of sesame oil into a large frying pan on high heat and add in the bell peppers, snow peas and carrot and stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes. Finish the vegetables by adding the remaining 1 tablespoon of soy sauce.
75a5bf74-a171-4aca-8ed2-6af0af6b8adf Divide the rice into 4 portions and serve the cooked salmon and vegetables evenly.
da74b17d-1765-4c99-8371-3bee6952b614 PREHEAT the oven to 400°
da74b17d-1765-4c99-8371-3bee6952b614 ADD 1 tablespoon of flour to a Reynolds® Oven Bag and shake. Place the bag in a 13x9x2 inch casserole dish.
da74b17d-1765-4c99-8371-3bee6952b614 MIX all of the ingredients in a large bowl and pour it into the Reynolds® Oven Bag.
da74b17d-1765-4c99-8371-3bee6952b614 CLOSE the bag and seal it with the provided tie.
da74b17d-1765-4c99-8371-3bee6952b614 CUT 6 half-inch slits in the top of the bag and tuck all of the ends into the pan.
da74b17d-1765-4c99-8371-3bee6952b614 BAKE for 30-35 minutes on 400° or until the meat has reached an internal temperature of 160 degrees F, or the meat is browned.
da74b17d-1765-4c99-8371-3bee6952b614 REMOVE the Spicy Szechuan Beef with Peppers from the bag once the cooking time has expired and drain any excess liquid from the bag.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 PREHEAT the oven to 300°.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 CREAM together the butter and sugar with the paddle attachment until it is white and fluffy.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 BEAT in 1 egg at a time.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 SCRAPE the bowl after the eggs have been beaten in and add in the lemon zest.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 MIX together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 WHISK together the milk and lemon juice.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 BEAT in ½ of the dry ingredients until combined and scrape the bowl once it is mixed in.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 BEAT in the milk and lemon juice until combined and stop and scrape the bowl again.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 FINISH beating in the remaining dry ingredients until combined and pour the batter into a Reynolds® Bakeware 8x8 pan and bake for 45 minutes on 300°.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 PLACE the cake on a cooling rack until completely cool before icing the cake with the butter cream.
0bff41e5-7f41-4ff0-95fd-1d72f2ec6b53 PLACE the fresh berries on the butter cream in the shape of a star.
a415b1c9-da60-4fa5-8ba8-de7bd062ebe4 Place a Reynolds® Oven Bag in 2-quart microwave-safe dish. Add sweet and sour sauce, melted butter, garlic, lemon juice, cornstarch and five spice seasoning to oven bag. Gently squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
a415b1c9-da60-4fa5-8ba8-de7bd062ebe4 Add drained vegetables and shrimp to bag. Gently turn bag to coat vegetables and shrimp. Close oven bag with nylon tie (included in package); cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag. Tuck ends of oven bag in dish.
a415b1c9-da60-4fa5-8ba8-de7bd062ebe4 Microwave on high for 8 to 10 minutes, until shrimp is pink and opaque and vegetables are hot. Let stand in bag for 2 to 3 minutes. Carefully open cut top of the oven bag with scissors. Stir ingredients and serve over hot cooked rice.
6b05638a-9c4c-44b3-b8b2-252b48e226c1 Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. In a medium bowl, stir together 1 cup sugar, 3 cups flour, and baking powder. Mix in salt and cinnamon, if desired. Use a fork or pastry cutter to blend in the butter and egg. Dough will be crumbly. Pat half of dough into the Reynolds® Bakeware pan.
6b05638a-9c4c-44b3-b8b2-252b48e226c1 In another bowl, stir together the sugar and cornstarch. Gently mix in the strawberries. Sprinkle the strawberry mixture evenly over the crust. Crumble remaining dough over the berry layer.
6b05638a-9c4c-44b3-b8b2-252b48e226c1 Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes, or until top is slightly brown. Cool completely before cutting into squares.
ac4a8cd9-9057-4c0f-ac47-933dfe6d8d0e TEAR sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil to fit your grill. Make several drainage holes using a grilling fork. Set aside.
ac4a8cd9-9057-4c0f-ac47-933dfe6d8d0e MIX together beef, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; shape each section of beef into a ball.
ac4a8cd9-9057-4c0f-ac47-933dfe6d8d0e MAKE an indention in center each ball with your thumb. Insert two cubes of cheddar cheese into indentions. Gently shape beef over cheese and flatten beef into a 4-inch patty making sure to completely enclose the cheese.
ac4a8cd9-9057-4c0f-ac47-933dfe6d8d0e PREHEAT your grill to medium-high.
ac4a8cd9-9057-4c0f-ac47-933dfe6d8d0e PLACE prepared sheet of foil on grill. PLACE burgers on foil.
ac4a8cd9-9057-4c0f-ac47-933dfe6d8d0e COOK in covered grill 5 minutes, turn burgers with a spatula. Continue cooking in covered grill until desired doneness.
ac4a8cd9-9057-4c0f-ac47-933dfe6d8d0e SPREAD a layer of herbed cream cheese on top halves of rolls.
ac4a8cd9-9057-4c0f-ac47-933dfe6d8d0e TOP burgers with lettuce, tomato, and onion, if desired.
f9732ade-870c-4422-9f12-547720d6e03b Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Cut the eggplants in half lengthwise, wrap each half in a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and arrange them on a baking sheet. Roast the eggplants until the centers are soft and tender, about 30 minutes. Unwrap the eggplants and scoop out the center pulp, leaving a 1/2-inch border around the edges of each eggplant. Roughly chop the reserved pulp and set it aside.
f9732ade-870c-4422-9f12-547720d6e03b Add the olive oil to a medium saucepan set over medium-low heat. Add the garlic and cook, stirring constantly for 1 minute, then add the couscous, allspice, bay leaves and cinnamon stick and cook, stirring constantly, for an additional 2 minutes.
f9732ade-870c-4422-9f12-547720d6e03b Add the chicken broth and 1/2 teaspoon salt then bring the mixture to a boil. Reduce the mixture to a simmer, cover the saucepan, and cook the couscous until it is tender and the liquid has absorbed, 10 to 12 minutes. Remove the bay leaves and cinnamon stick. Stir in the reserved eggplant, parsley and feta cheese, then divide the couscous mixture evenly among the eggplants.
f9732ade-870c-4422-9f12-547720d6e03b Arrange the stuffed eggplants on a foil-lined baking sheet and return them to the oven, uncovered, and bake until they are warmed throughout, about 5 minutes. Remove the eggplants from the oven, top them with pomegranate seeds and serve immediately.
8e8fd7f7-0c1b-463d-a280-e75797d69393 Line a 17x12-inch rimmed baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
8e8fd7f7-0c1b-463d-a280-e75797d69393 Combine turkey, bread crumbs, green onion, egg, ginger, garlic and sesame oil in a large bowl. Use your hands or a spoon to mix just until well combined.
8e8fd7f7-0c1b-463d-a280-e75797d69393 Roll into 1 1/4" to 1 1/2" meatballs and bake at 400 degrees F for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender and juices run clear or a meat thermometer reads 170 degrees F.
8e8fd7f7-0c1b-463d-a280-e75797d69393 Meanwhile simmer the sauce ingredients together in a small saucepan 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently until slightly thickened.
8e8fd7f7-0c1b-463d-a280-e75797d69393 Transfer warm meatballs to a mixing bowl, drizzle with warm sauce and toss to combine.
a7cfc3d8-15be-4f4d-94d7-489bed2f4474 PREHEAT grill to mediumhigh or oven to °F. CENTER one pork chop on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with vegetables. Combine teriyaki marinade & sauce and orange marmalade; spoon evenly over top. BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
a7cfc3d8-15be-4f4d-94d7-489bed2f4474 BAKE to minutes in covered grill OR GRILL to minutes on a cookie sheet in oven. Serve over rice.
d201e74f-3699-44d4-858a-8872fc27ab3c PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
d201e74f-3699-44d4-858a-8872fc27ab3c Combine next 6 ingredients and 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Shape mixture into 4 meat loaves, flattening slightly.
d201e74f-3699-44d4-858a-8872fc27ab3c CENTER one meat loaf on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Top with corn. Spoon remaining barbecue sauce over meat loaf and corn.
d201e74f-3699-44d4-858a-8872fc27ab3c BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
d201e74f-3699-44d4-858a-8872fc27ab3c BAKE 18 to 20 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven
d201e74f-3699-44d4-858a-8872fc27ab3c OR GRILL 12 to 14 minutes in covered grill.
f62b495b-91a6-44ed-b0a1-3c3366eddbe1 COMBINE cooked pasta, tomatoes, yellow bell pepper, artichoke hearts and basil in a large bowl.
f62b495b-91a6-44ed-b0a1-3c3366eddbe1 BLEND olive oil, vinegar, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Pour dressing mixture over pasta; toss to mix.
f62b495b-91a6-44ed-b0a1-3c3366eddbe1 COVER with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
f62b495b-91a6-44ed-b0a1-3c3366eddbe1 REFRIGERATE 2 hours or until serving time.
b1b3be37-0374-482c-acc1-43125483d9e1 PREHEAT the oven to 400°.
b1b3be37-0374-482c-acc1-43125483d9e1 ADD 1 tablespoon of flour to a Reynolds® Oven Bag and shake. Place the bag in a 13x9x2 inch casserole dish.
b1b3be37-0374-482c-acc1-43125483d9e1 PLACE the noodles, tomatoes, chicken, baby spinach, 10 basil leaves, and hot water into the Reynolds® Oven Bag and generously season with salt and pepper.
b1b3be37-0374-482c-acc1-43125483d9e1 CLOSE the bag and seal it with the provided tie.
b1b3be37-0374-482c-acc1-43125483d9e1 CUT 6 half inch slits in the top of the bag and tuck all of the ends into the pan and bake for 30-35 minutes on 400° or until the noodles reach al dente, or slightly crunchy.
b1b3be37-0374-482c-acc1-43125483d9e1 REMOVE the pasta from the bag and drain any remaining liquid.
b1b3be37-0374-482c-acc1-43125483d9e1 ADJUST the seasonings with salt and pepper and garnish with shredded mozzarella, buffalo mozzarella balls and 2 fresh-chopped basil leaves
adbec646-b9ea-4475-b012-abcd62ee1173 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F and place rack in the center of the oven. Line a 9x13 inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and set aside.
adbec646-b9ea-4475-b012-abcd62ee1173 Combine the flour, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl and set aside.
adbec646-b9ea-4475-b012-abcd62ee1173 Whip together the egg whites in the bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with a whisk attachment. Add the cream of tartar and whip until soft peaks form, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the egg whites to a separate bowl.
adbec646-b9ea-4475-b012-abcd62ee1173 Beat the egg yolks in the mixing bowl using a paddle attachment until thick and pale in color. Add the granulated sugar and beat on high for about 5 minutes, until very thick and ribbons fall when you lift the paddle attachment. Stir in the vanilla extract, almond extract and milk until smooth. Add the flour mixture and stir until just combined.
adbec646-b9ea-4475-b012-abcd62ee1173 Fold in the egg whites, in three increments, making sure to thoroughly incorporate the whites but try not to over-mix.
adbec646-b9ea-4475-b012-abcd62ee1173 Pour batter into prepared baking pan and bake for about 25 to 30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Remove from the oven and allow to cool completely on a wire rack.
adbec646-b9ea-4475-b012-abcd62ee1173 Whisk together the three milks in a medium bowl. Whisk in the rum and vanilla extract. Using a wooden skewer, poke holes all throughout the cooled cake. This will allow for the milk mixture to seep in. Pour the milk evenly over the cake. Cover with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and allow to chill in the fridge for about 3 hours or overnight.
adbec646-b9ea-4475-b012-abcd62ee1173 Whip together the heavy cream along with the powdered sugar, salt and vanilla extract until soft peaks form. Spread the whipped cream over the chilled cake. Decorate with sprinkles and cherries. Slice generously and enjoy!
f86a799a-6bf1-4e71-8040-37ddc5319e76 PREHEAT oven to 325°F. Line an 8x8x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Parchment Paper; set aside.
f86a799a-6bf1-4e71-8040-37ddc5319e76 MICROWAVE chocolate and butter in a large microwave-safe bowl, on high power for 1 to 1 ½ minutes, stirring every 30 seconds, until completely melted. STIR sugar into melted chocolate. STIR in flour, baking powder and salt until well blended. MIX in eggs and vanilla extract. SPREAD batter into parchment-lined 8x8x2-inch pan.
f86a799a-6bf1-4e71-8040-37ddc5319e76 BAKE 35 to 40 minutes until toothpick inserted 2 inches from edge is nearly clean with large crumbs sticking to it. COOL for 20 minutes on wire rack. Use edges of parchment to lift brownie cake from pan. Cool on wire rack. PLACE brownie cake on counter. Peel down parchment from sides of cake. INVERT cake plate on top of cake. Slide one hand under parchment and carefully FLIP brownie onto plate. Peel parchment form bottom of cake.
f86a799a-6bf1-4e71-8040-37ddc5319e76 Prepare Glaze: MICROWAVE dark chocolate pieces and butter in a small microwave safe bowl, on high power for 1 to 1 ½ minutes, stirring every 30 seconds, until chocolate is completely melted. Stir in corn syrup. Immediately spread glaze over cooled cake. Let stand about 30 to 40 minutes until glaze is set.
f86a799a-6bf1-4e71-8040-37ddc5319e76 Garnish by piping white icing around the edges and arranging chocolate covered strawberries on top of cake, if desired.
078d66a9-9ea7-402f-935a-f8df4b59c350 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high. Combine beans, tomatoes, and 1/2 teaspoon basil.
078d66a9-9ea7-402f-935a-f8df4b59c350 CENTER one-fourth of bean mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Top with halibut steak; drizzle with olive oil and lemon juice. Sprinkle halibut with remaining basil and lemon pepper. Top with lemon slices.
078d66a9-9ea7-402f-935a-f8df4b59c350 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
078d66a9-9ea7-402f-935a-f8df4b59c350 BAKE 16 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet in oven OR
078d66a9-9ea7-402f-935a-f8df4b59c350 GRILL 14 to 18 minutes in covered grill.
6f1afb86-8d38-4668-b030-b7ebe0887bc9 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
6f1afb86-8d38-4668-b030-b7ebe0887bc9 COOK the whipping cream in a medium sized pot on medium heat until it becomes thick like alfredo sauce (about 20 minutes).
6f1afb86-8d38-4668-b030-b7ebe0887bc9 WHISK the Parmesan cheese into the thickened cream until combined and keep warm.
6f1afb86-8d38-4668-b030-b7ebe0887bc9 PLACE the corn tortilla chips into a Reynolds® 12x9 Bakeware casserole dish and pour on the Parmesan cream.
6f1afb86-8d38-4668-b030-b7ebe0887bc9 EVENLY SPREAD on the shredded mozzarella cheese and chicken and bake for 20 minutes.
6f1afb86-8d38-4668-b030-b7ebe0887bc9 FINISH the nachos with sliced olives, diced tomatoes and sliced green onions.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a PREHEAT oven to 350ºF.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a CREAM the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy in a large mixing bowl, about 5 minutes. ADD the eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a SIFT together the dry ingredients.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a ADD the dry ingredients, alternating with the milk, in three equal parts. After each addition, beat until the ingredients are incorporated. Do NOT over beat.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a ADD the vanilla.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a SCRAPE the batter in the bowl to make sure the ingredients are well blended.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a ADD the sprinkles, and mix for 30 seconds.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a LINE a muffin tin with Reynolds® Foil Baking Cups.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a Carefully FILL baking cup, about 2/3 full.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a BAKE until the cupcakes are golden brown, about 20 – 25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cupcake comes out clean.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a REMOVE from the oven and let cool completely before frosting with your favorite buttercream frosting.
0cfa28f6-beee-4414-9c18-0b3fbe2c7d8a TOP with remaining sprinkles.
02dedcab-3605-4475-b879-2e1421841af1 LINE a deep sided 9 x 13 baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Set aside.
02dedcab-3605-4475-b879-2e1421841af1 PREHEAT oven to 400oF.
02dedcab-3605-4475-b879-2e1421841af1 MELT butter over medium heat in a heavy bottom sauce pan. Add flour. Stir to combine. Slowly add milk and whisk together until sauce thickens. Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg. Set aside.
02dedcab-3605-4475-b879-2e1421841af1 HEAT olive oil over medium heat in a large sauté pan. Add shallots cook until translucent. Add garlic and mushrooms. Season with salt and pepper. Cook until softened. Add spinach. Stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.
02dedcab-3605-4475-b879-2e1421841af1 ADD ricotta and egg into a small bowl while the vegetable mixture is cooking. Season with salt and pepper. Mix to combine. Set aside.
02dedcab-3605-4475-b879-2e1421841af1 PLACE a spoonful of béchamel sauce onto foil-lined dish. Top with three lasagna noodles. Spoon ricotta mixture, vegetable mixture, béchamel and a sprinkling of mozzarella. Continue for two additional layers, ending with layer of noodles, béchamel and mozzarella.
02dedcab-3605-4475-b879-2e1421841af1 COVER with additional aluminum foil. Bake for approximately 45 minutes. Uncover and continue cooking additional 10-15 minutes OR until top is golden.
02dedcab-3605-4475-b879-2e1421841af1 REST lasagna for minimum 15 minutes prior to slicing.
2808c842-4920-4fbf-96ff-279ffac28801 COMBINE all ingredients, except steaks, in a bowl and mix well.
2808c842-4920-4fbf-96ff-279ffac28801 RESERVE 1 cup of marinade and set aside.
2808c842-4920-4fbf-96ff-279ffac28801 PLACE steaks in a gallon resealable bag. Pour marinade over steaks and place in refrigerator to marinate for 24 to 48 hours.
2808c842-4920-4fbf-96ff-279ffac28801 PREHEAT grill. Place sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with holes (see Reynolds Kitchens Tip) on grill grate with non-stick (dull) side towards food.
2808c842-4920-4fbf-96ff-279ffac28801 GRILL steaks to desired doneness while basting with reserved marinade.
