2808c842-4920-4fbf-96ff-279ffac28801 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: To make drainage holes in the non-stick foil, lay a sheet of foil over the grate of a cold grill, broiler pan, or cooling rack. Make holes in the foil with a large grilling fork. Place the sheet of foil on a preheated grill.
58eeff28-0237-4260-92fa-fb2436f1dca7 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line 2 cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Set aside.
58eeff28-0237-4260-92fa-fb2436f1dca7 In a bowl stir together the cake mix, oil and egg until combined.
58eeff28-0237-4260-92fa-fb2436f1dca7 Drop dough by rounded tablespoon 3 inches apart on lined cookie sheets. Bake cookies for about 8-10 minutes. Remove from oven and let sit for 5 minutes. Carefully transfer the parchment paper onto a cooling rack. Let cookies cool completely.
58eeff28-0237-4260-92fa-fb2436f1dca7 In a saucepan, combine the chocolate chips, milk and butter. Cook over medium-low heat stirring constantly until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth. Cool to room temperature.
58eeff28-0237-4260-92fa-fb2436f1dca7 On the top of each cookie, frost the center portion with 1-1/2 tablespoon chocolate mixture (this will help hold the cone in place once each cone is placed on top of each cookie).
58eeff28-0237-4260-92fa-fb2436f1dca7 Frost cones leaving one inch at tip unfrosted. Holding frosted cone by tip, fill each with 1 tablespoon of chocolate candies. Center the filled cone on top of frosted cookie to form hat. Turn over and place each hat on baking sheet lined with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Repeat until all cookies and cones are used. Finish frosting the tops of the cones. Decorate with remaining chocolate candies, using chocolate mixture to adhere them.
baff9ae4-8856-4ae3-a432-03125e7dad9d In a food processor, blend onion, bell pepper, garlic and basil leaves until very fine.
baff9ae4-8856-4ae3-a432-03125e7dad9d In a separate bowl, combine the vegetable mixture with ground beef, eggs, breadcrumbs, salt, milk, ricotta cheese and Italian seasoning. Mix until thoroughly combined. Form the meat mixture into the shape of a loaf.
baff9ae4-8856-4ae3-a432-03125e7dad9d Line a 5-to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner. Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
baff9ae4-8856-4ae3-a432-03125e7dad9d Place meatloaf inside a lined slow cooker.
baff9ae4-8856-4ae3-a432-03125e7dad9d Place slices of mozzarella cheese on the meatloaf, so that none of the meat is visible.
baff9ae4-8856-4ae3-a432-03125e7dad9d Begin layering individual strands of fettuccine on top of the meatloaf, mimicking the look of a mummy. Adjust the position of the individual strands to cover the cheese.
baff9ae4-8856-4ae3-a432-03125e7dad9d Once satisfied with the look of your mummy meatloaf, turn on the slow cooker to low, place the lid on top, and set the timer for 5 hours. After 4 hours of cooking, spoon about half the jar of pasta sauce around the bottom of the mummy meatloaf.
baff9ae4-8856-4ae3-a432-03125e7dad9d Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Using plastic of wooden utensils, lift the mummy to a serving plate. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
baff9ae4-8856-4ae3-a432-03125e7dad9d Just before serving, add some olive eyes to your mummy
2f5ff941-fb39-41b2-8a34-39af0cfd02ce PREHEAT grill to medium-high heat. Make drainage holes in a sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with a grilling fork; set aside.
2f5ff941-fb39-41b2-8a34-39af0cfd02ce COMBINE ground beef, 1 cup salsa, 1/2 cup tortilla chips, 1/2 cup green onions, garlic salt and chili powder in large bowl until well blended. Shape beef mixture into 8 burgers, 4 inches in diameter and 1/2-inch thick.
2f5ff941-fb39-41b2-8a34-39af0cfd02ce PLACE foil sheet on grill grate with non-stick (dull) side facing up. Immediately place burgers on foil.
2f5ff941-fb39-41b2-8a34-39af0cfd02ce GRILL burgers uncovered, 5 minutes each side or until no longer pink in center. Grill or lightly toast hamburger buns. Top burgers with 1 slice cheese before removing from grill; let melt. Place burgers on buns. Top with remaining salsa, tortilla chips and green onions.
13159d0a-9d75-4160-bba2-1dba361717b4 HUSK the corn and preheat grill to medium-high.
13159d0a-9d75-4160-bba2-1dba361717b4 CENTER the four ears of corn on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Spread butter on the corn. Sprinkle with Kraft Grated Parmesan Cheese and spices. Top with ice cubes.
13159d0a-9d75-4160-bba2-1dba361717b4 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal making one large foil packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
13159d0a-9d75-4160-bba2-1dba361717b4 GRILL 15 to 20 minutes in covered grill. Add salt as desired.
98a2f32f-debe-4cde-8737-c9de513456a7 PREHEAT the oven to 350F. Place Reynolds® Bakeware Lasagna Pan on a baking sheet and set aside.
98a2f32f-debe-4cde-8737-c9de513456a7 COOK pasta according to package instructions for al dente. Remove, drain and rinse in cold water. Drain again and place in large mixing bowl.
98a2f32f-debe-4cde-8737-c9de513456a7 HEAT olive oil on medium high in large pot. Add ground beef, onions and garlic. Cook, stirring frequently, until the meat is no longer pink.
98a2f32f-debe-4cde-8737-c9de513456a7 ADD the pasta, tomato sauce, cream, mozzarella, Parmesan, and dried herbs to meat mixture; stir until mixed well.
98a2f32f-debe-4cde-8737-c9de513456a7 POUR pasta mixture into Bakeware. Sprinkle breadcrumbs over top.
98a2f32f-debe-4cde-8737-c9de513456a7 BAKE in oven for 35 to 40 minutes, until bubbling and crusty on top.
98a2f32f-debe-4cde-8737-c9de513456a7 REMOVE from oven and serve immediately.
89e9cdac-c9da-4636-b5ff-4c605caaabcd Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
89e9cdac-c9da-4636-b5ff-4c605caaabcd Heat a large cast-iron or sauté pan over medium heat. Add the olive oil, leek, onions and a pinch of salt. Cook until tender but not brown, about 5 minutes. Add mushrooms, garlic and thyme and cook, stirring occasionally, for 7 minutes until tender and slightly brown.
89e9cdac-c9da-4636-b5ff-4c605caaabcd Add the rice and cook until the kernels are well coated with the oil and mushrooms, about 2 minutes. Add wine, balsamic vinegar, broth and a pinch each of salt and pepper. Bring the liquid to a boil and then remove from heat. Transfer the mixture to a deep 9x13-inch baking dish. Wrap the top tightly with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Bake for 30 minutes until the rice is tender but al dente.
89e9cdac-c9da-4636-b5ff-4c605caaabcd Remove baking dish from oven and add the Parmesan and sage. Stir, adjust seasoning if necessary and serve immediately.
918288c6-6323-4d44-84ef-4f5f5e04a5c3 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
918288c6-6323-4d44-84ef-4f5f5e04a5c3 Bring a large pot of water to boil. Cook the shells according to the package instructions, making sure to cook them a bit al dente.
918288c6-6323-4d44-84ef-4f5f5e04a5c3 Gently fold together the ricotta, parmesan, parsley, salt, pepper, eggs, lemon zest and 1 cup of the mozzarella in a bowl.
918288c6-6323-4d44-84ef-4f5f5e04a5c3 Fill the cooked shells with 1 tablespoon of the ricotta mixture each.
918288c6-6323-4d44-84ef-4f5f5e04a5c3 Spoon a layer of the tomato sauce on the bottom of a 9-by-13-inch baking pan, about 2 1/2 cups. Placed the filled shells on top of the sauce; do not overcrowd.
918288c6-6323-4d44-84ef-4f5f5e04a5c3 Top the shells with the remaining 1 cup tomato sauce, sprinkle with the remaining 1 cup mozzarella.
918288c6-6323-4d44-84ef-4f5f5e04a5c3 Cover with foil and bake for 25 minutes; remove the foil and cook until the cheese is fully melted and browned on top, an additional 5 minutes.
918288c6-6323-4d44-84ef-4f5f5e04a5c3 Finish with chopped parsley and serve.
9ba56f6f-3ef2-417c-9d0e-dddb305bb037 Place flour tortilla in a Reynolds’ heat & eat container
9ba56f6f-3ef2-417c-9d0e-dddb305bb037 Layer with cooked scrambled eggs and a generous helping of leftover chili
9ba56f6f-3ef2-417c-9d0e-dddb305bb037 Top with your favorite shredded cheese and microwave on high for 1 minute or until the cheese is melted
a2d3bcab-0385-4b7f-bc9a-5d996e2b9dbc Wash the potatoes well and pat dry
a2d3bcab-0385-4b7f-bc9a-5d996e2b9dbc Cut the potatoes into wedges, leaving the skin on and place in a large bowl
a2d3bcab-0385-4b7f-bc9a-5d996e2b9dbc Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with kosher salt and toss to coat
a2d3bcab-0385-4b7f-bc9a-5d996e2b9dbc Place the wedges on a baking sheet and roast at 400 degrees for 15-20 minutes, turning once or twice until the potatoes are golden
a2d3bcab-0385-4b7f-bc9a-5d996e2b9dbc Place potatoes in a heat & eat container and top with a generous serving of leftover chili
a2d3bcab-0385-4b7f-bc9a-5d996e2b9dbc Microwave on high for 2 minutes or until the potatoes and chili are warmed through
a2d3bcab-0385-4b7f-bc9a-5d996e2b9dbc Garnish with feta cheese, sliced cherry tomatoes and cilantro
a97ba38d-7561-4a37-829c-2b716bca3f70 Cook pasta in a large pot of salted water to desired doneness. Drain pasta and reserve about 1 cup of the pasta water (DON’T FORGET).
a97ba38d-7561-4a37-829c-2b716bca3f70 In a large pot, melt 2 Tbsp butter over medium heat. Once hot, add spinach and stir until slightly wilted. The spinach wilts fast (about 1 minute).
a97ba38d-7561-4a37-829c-2b716bca3f70 Transfer wilted spinach to a colander and let it drain while preparing the rest of the recipe.
a97ba38d-7561-4a37-829c-2b716bca3f70 Add 4 Tbsp butter to the same now empty pot along with 4 oz cream cheese cut into pieces, 1 cup sour cream and 1 cup parmesan and stir until everything melts together and starts to bubble.
a97ba38d-7561-4a37-829c-2b716bca3f70 Stir in drained artichokes and cook an additional 1-2 min then add drained spinach, pressed garlic and jalapeños (if using). Cook until hot then toss in the cooked, drained pasta.
a97ba38d-7561-4a37-829c-2b716bca3f70 Stir in reserved pasta water if desired.
c33220e1-f0d9-4a00-9a0e-5bc6e234803e Preheat the oven to 350° and line a baking sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
c33220e1-f0d9-4a00-9a0e-5bc6e234803e In an electric mixing bowl mix the butter and sugar until combined, using a paddle attachment.
c33220e1-f0d9-4a00-9a0e-5bc6e234803e Mix in the vanilla, flour and salt. Turn the mixer on low and stir until mixture is no longer a powder but starts to come together like a dough.
c33220e1-f0d9-4a00-9a0e-5bc6e234803e On a floured surface, shape dough into a long log that is about 2″ in diameter. Wrap with parchment and chill for 25 minutes.
c33220e1-f0d9-4a00-9a0e-5bc6e234803e Remove the parchment paper and cut slices about ½” thick. If desired you can now use a cookie cutter to give any design or look to the slices. Don’t be afraid to use your fingers to push the dough into the crevices of the cutters.
c33220e1-f0d9-4a00-9a0e-5bc6e234803e Place the cookies on the parchment lined baking sheet and bake for 17 to 20 minutes, checking often toward the end. You do not want these cookies to brown. Remove from oven when the bottoms just start to brown.
c33220e1-f0d9-4a00-9a0e-5bc6e234803e When the cookies are cool, place 3 oz of the chocolate into a bowl and microwave for 30 seconds. Stir and continue to heat in 30-second increments until chocolate is melted. Stir in the remaining chocolate and continue to stir until chocolate is fully melted. The more you stir, the glossier your chocolate will be.
c33220e1-f0d9-4a00-9a0e-5bc6e234803e Cool chocolate to room temperature and then dip each cookie into chocolate halfway, and allow to cool and the chocolate to harden on the parchment paper before serving.
f1533a1f-b162-49d5-a0a2-306373641bef Heat oven to °F. Line large cookie sheets with parchment paper.
f1533a1f-b162-49d5-a0a2-306373641bef Let cookie dough stand at room temperature minutes to soften. In large bowl, break up cookie dough. Add frosting, oats and / teaspoon salt. Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Working with / of the dough; drop by tablespoonfuls to make cookies. Place inches apart on cookie sheets. (Cookies will spread.)
f1533a1f-b162-49d5-a0a2-306373641bef Bake cookie sheets at a time, to minutes or until golden brown, turning cookie sheets halfway through bake time. While cookies are baking, drop remaining tablespoonfuls of dough onto parchment paper to make additional cookies. Remove baked cookies and parchment paper to cooling rack. Cool completely, about minutes. Repeat with remaining dough and parchment paper.
f1533a1f-b162-49d5-a0a2-306373641bef Spread heaping teaspoon of the hazelnut spread onto bottom of cookies. Top with remaining cookies bottom side down; press lightly. Store in covered container.

02b32660-2377-46f4-ab66-120272cdedca BAKE 25 to 30 minutes on a cookie sheet or in a 13x9x2-inch dish OR GRILL 20 to 25 minutes in covered grill until sweet potatoes are tender.
2472b48a-eeb8-4231-9ebb-773d3c9affbe Preheat oven to 350°F. For meatballs, in a very large bowl, beat egg with a fork. Stir in bread crumbs, dried cranberries or raisins, onion, salt, and cloves or allspice. Add ground chicken or turkey; mix well. Shape into 60 meatballs.
2472b48a-eeb8-4231-9ebb-773d3c9affbe Lightly coat a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Place meatballs in pan.
2472b48a-eeb8-4231-9ebb-773d3c9affbe Bake for 15 to 18 minutes or until done (165°F).
2472b48a-eeb8-4231-9ebb-773d3c9affbe Meanwhile, place the disposable slow cooker liner inside a 3-1/2- to 4-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides; pull top of liner over rim of bowl. Stir together cranberry sauce and barbecue sauce; add to slow cooker. Add cooked meatballs, stirring gently to coat. Cover and cook on low-heat setting for 2 to 3 hours or on high-heat setting for 1 to 1-1/2 hours. (Meatballs may be kept warm on low-heat setting for up to 1 hour more.) Serve with toothpicks. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and discard. Makes 60 meatballs.
b9356aba-a55b-40d2-a4c2-b4b30e2028b4 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
b9356aba-a55b-40d2-a4c2-b4b30e2028b4 LINE a 13x9x2-inch baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper with parchment paper side toward food. Crimp Pan Lining Paper around rim of pan; set aside.
b9356aba-a55b-40d2-a4c2-b4b30e2028b4 PLACE butter and onion in large saucepan. Cook over medium heat until onion is tender. Add flour, salt and pepper; whisk until smooth. Blend in milk. Stirring constantly, heat until mixture is thickened and smooth.
b9356aba-a55b-40d2-a4c2-b4b30e2028b4 ADD cheese product and Cheddar cheese; stir until cheese is melted. Stir in cooked macaroni. Sprinkle with paprika.
b9356aba-a55b-40d2-a4c2-b4b30e2028b4 BAKE uncovered 40 to 45 minutes or until browned and bubbly. Garnish with tomato wedges and parsley.

c265c736-4bbd-4199-8af5-da6ebb82bcf8 SHAKE flour in Reynolds® Oven Bag; place in 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
c265c736-4bbd-4199-8af5-da6ebb82bcf8 ADD tomatoes and Creole seasoning to oven bag. Squeeze oven bag to blend in flour. Add beef, celery and green pepper to oven bag. Turn oven bag to coat beef with sauce. Arrange ingredients in an even layer in oven bag.
c265c736-4bbd-4199-8af5-da6ebb82bcf8 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
c265c736-4bbd-4199-8af5-da6ebb82bcf8 BAKE 1 1/4 to 1 3/4 hours or until meat thermometer reads 145°F. Thinly slice beef. Stir sauce; serve with rice, if desired.

a8b4ed99-2cf5-4867-91c4-317e74f8af93 Shape dough into balls. On cookie sheets lined with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, place balls inches apart. a8b4ed99-2cf5-4867-91c4-317e74f8af93 Bake to minutes or until edges are set. Cool minutes; remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks. Cool completely, about minutes.
df41e390-50f6-4a1e-8288-34f7398025a8 POUR enough water into the pot to be about ¾-inch deep.
df41e390-50f6-4a1e-8288-34f7398025a8 HEAT on medium-high until water comes to a gentle boil. Loosely cover the pot a sheet of standard gauge Reynolds Wrap Aluminum Foil to form a lid.
df41e390-50f6-4a1e-8288-34f7398025a8 MEANWHILE, make a foil bowl: TEAR a 7 to 8-inch sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Center non-stick foil over end of can, with the non-stick, dull, side toward the can; press the foil around can to form a “bowl” with about 1-inch sides. SCRUNCH the ends of the foil to make the rim of the bowl. Lift the foil bowl from the can and place it on the counter.
df41e390-50f6-4a1e-8288-34f7398025a8 SPRINKLE shredded cheddar cheese into foil bowl. CRACK the egg and place it in the foil bowl. Use slotted spatula to carefully SIT the bowl into the gently boiling water. Cover with foil lid.
df41e390-50f6-4a1e-8288-34f7398025a8 COOK 5 to 6 minutes until egg white is white and opaque; the yolk is firm and reaches 165°F. The yolk will be soft, add additional time if you prefer a firm yolk.
df41e390-50f6-4a1e-8288-34f7398025a8 CAREFULLY LIFT the foil bowl from the water using a slotted spatula. Let sit about 1 minute until foil is cool enough to handle.
df41e390-50f6-4a1e-8288-34f7398025a8 FOLD back the sides of the foil. Use spatula to gently slide egg onto plate.
da04a614-e392-4a06-b61d-1ed6f9f3bee7 Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
da04a614-e392-4a06-b61d-1ed6f9f3bee7 Peel and cut potatoes into strips about 1/4-inch thick. In a large bowl combine oil, thyme, garlic, and salt and pepper. Place potatoes in the bowl and toss, making sure to evenly coat.
da04a614-e392-4a06-b61d-1ed6f9f3bee7 Transfer potatoes to the baking sheet, making sure potatoes lie in a single layer across the foil. Cook for 15­–20 minutes until crispy. Remove tray from the oven and let cool for 10 minutes before serving.
1a73b163-4e6e-4234-acd3-1ecaf531f13c Preheat oven to 475 degrees F. Slice ends off of Brussels sprouts and remove outermost leaves. Slice thin with a knife or use a food processor fitted with a slicing blade. Toss sprouts and diced apples with olive oil and salt. Line a sheet pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil and roast sprouts and apples for 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
1a73b163-4e6e-4234-acd3-1ecaf531f13c In a skillet over medium heat, cook pancetta until crisp, about 5 minutes. Remove pancetta and leave 3 tablespoons of the grease. Add the onion and garlic and cook about 2 minutes. Add the radicchio, separating the quarters and stir until the leaves wilt. Add Brussels sprouts and pancetta, and toss to combine. Add vinegar and honey.
7506ceed-5769-4a7c-9154-3b1ebd180dbf PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
7506ceed-5769-4a7c-9154-3b1ebd180dbf CREAM together the butter and sugar in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed until light and fluffy.
7506ceed-5769-4a7c-9154-3b1ebd180dbf POUR in 1 egg at a time until completely mixed in on low speed.
7506ceed-5769-4a7c-9154-3b1ebd180dbf ADD in the vegetable oil, baking soda and vanilla extract and mix until combined on low speed.
7506ceed-5769-4a7c-9154-3b1ebd180dbf ADD the flour into the butter mixture on low speed until combined.
7506ceed-5769-4a7c-9154-3b1ebd180dbf FOLD the red and green colored chocolate candies into the batter with a spatula until mixed in.
7506ceed-5769-4a7c-9154-3b1ebd180dbf SPOON 1 tablespoon of the cookie dough onto a Reynolds® Bakeware Cookie Sheet Pan with Parchment Lining and repeat the process until the dough is gone. There should be 24 total cookies.
7506ceed-5769-4a7c-9154-3b1ebd180dbf BAKE the cookies at 350° for 14 to 16 minutes or until the edges are lightly browned.
7506ceed-5769-4a7c-9154-3b1ebd180dbf COOL to room temperature before serving.
26634308-2ce0-4e5b-a8ec-84d09870a83b PREHEAT oven to 400°F.
26634308-2ce0-4e5b-a8ec-84d09870a83b LINE a shallow baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick side toward food
26634308-2ce0-4e5b-a8ec-84d09870a83b PLACE vegetables in a large bowl. Add olive oil, seasoning or herbs, salt and pepper and toss to coat.
26634308-2ce0-4e5b-a8ec-84d09870a83b SPREAD vegetables in a single layer In the foil-lined pan. Sprinkle additional Italian seasonings or fresh herbs on top of the vegetables, if desired.
26634308-2ce0-4e5b-a8ec-84d09870a83b PLACE pan of vegetables into the oven on the top rack.
26634308-2ce0-4e5b-a8ec-84d09870a83b BAKE 15 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
26634308-2ce0-4e5b-a8ec-84d09870a83b SQUEEZE lemon over vegetables for even more flavor.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 PREHEAT the oven to 400°.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 ROLL the premade pie dough onto a clean surface dusted with flour until it expands by an additional 1/3 size.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 FORM the dough to a Reynolds® Bakeware Non-Stick Pie Pan and fold in the dough around the outside and flute.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 DOCK the dough using a fork and place a 1” foot sheet of Reynolds Wrap® down into the bottom of the dough and to cover it.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 BAKE in the oven at 400° for 6 minutes or until lightly browned and then cool to room temperature.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 WHIP 1 cup of heavy whipping cream in a standing mixer with the whisk attachment on high speed until stiff peaks are formed and then immediately cool.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 WHISK together the eggs and sugar over low heat until it reaches 160° and set aside.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 WHIP 1 cup of unsalted butter in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed until it is light and fluffy, about 6 minutes.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 POUR in the egg and sugar mixture along with the melted chocolate and whip on high speed for 5 minutes until it becomes fluffy.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 FOLD in the 1 cup of cooled whipped cream and transfer the batter to the pre-cooked pie dough and cool completely in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 FINISH the pie by adding on the 2 cups of sweet cream and optional chocolate shavings garnish.
929569e8-ab10-429b-86e9-c5a25197ecc1 REFRIGERATE before serving.

1dc333a0-1853-4a58-8d12-861c7408e6e9 Heat oven to °F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Shape dough into ( /inch) balls. Place balls inches apart on cookie sheets. 1dc333a0-1853-4a58-8d12-861c7408e6e9 Meanwhile, in quart saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Cool minute. 1dc333a0-1853-4a58-8d12-861c7408e6e9 When ready to assemble cookies, place filling slice on bottom of cookie; top with another cookie, bottom side down, and press together slightly. Repeat with remaining cookies.

4f6c1048-14da-4efc-bcf2-028ed40d4296 Add the potatoes to a pot of boiling water and cook for 5 minutes.
4f6c1048-14da-4efc-bcf2-028ed40d4296 Strain the potatoes and add them to a bowl with the onions and olive oil and toss to coat.

4f6c1048-14da-4efc-bcf2-028ed40d4296 Place the potatoes and onions on the foil on the grill and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until the potatoes and onions are browned and cooked.

bc1b8c05-1f75-4746-8b4d-02b49bf734ed Spread the potatoes out on a cookie sheet lined with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
bc1b8c05-1f75-4746-8b4d-02b49bf734ed Sprinkle the oil, honey, cinnamon, salt and pepper over the potatoes and cook for 30 minutes.
bc1b8c05-1f75-4746-8b4d-02b49bf734ed Once they are cooled scoop them onto a serving dish and devour!

c08bda6b-1de7-4b57-948a-de5dbfccbdd0 WHISK the buttermilk and baking soda in a separate bowl and add it to the butter sugar mixture.
c08bda6b-1de7-4b57-948a-de5dbfccbdd0 ADD in the cornmeal and flour and whisk until combine.

a6531f99-7e48-4082-af95-6eab12e4e713 Place the pork into a slow cooker lined with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner and pour in water and BBQ sauce and cook on high heat for 4 hours or low heat for 6 hours.

a6531f99-7e48-4082-af95-6eab12e4e713 Place a 1 1/2- to 2-feet-long sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil on a table and place the potato wedges in the center of the foil.
a6531f99-7e48-4082-af95-6eab12e4e713 Drizzle on the remaining 6 tablespoons of olive oil, season with salt and pepper, and then fold up the outside of the foil to create a foil packet.

a6531f99-7e48-4082-af95-6eab12e4e713 Serve the pulled pork over top of the potato wedges, cheese curds and diced pickles.

2eb25773-e18f-43d0-804c-0ded9bb437fd MIX together the flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon in a large bowl until combined and set aside.
2eb25773-e18f-43d0-804c-0ded9bb437fd WHISK together the vegetable oil, eggs and pumpkin puree until completely combined and pour it into the dry ingredients bowl and mix in completely.
2eb25773-e18f-43d0-804c-0ded9bb437fd POUR the batter evenly into 2 separate Reynolds® Bakeware Non-Stick Cake Pans with Parchment Lining.
2eb25773-e18f-43d0-804c-0ded9bb437fd BAKE at 350° for 30 minutes or until the top is lightly brown and the center is firm and

2eb25773-e18f-43d0-804c-0ded9bb437fd ADD in the powdered sugar and heavy cream and mix on low speed until incorporated and then mix on high speed for 2 minutes.
2eb25773-e18f-43d0-804c-0ded9bb437fd ICE the double layered cake on the sides and top until the cream cheese frosting is gone.
2eb25773-e18f-43d0-804c-0ded9bb437fd SERVE at room temperature.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 PREHEAT oven to 350°.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 PULSE together crushed pretzels, butter, and a 1/4 cup of sugar in a food processor until combined.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 PRESS the pretzel crust firmly into the bottom of a Reynolds® 1/4 Sheet Cake Bakeware Pan making sure to cover the bottom completely.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 BAKE the crust in the oven for 10 minutes and set aside to cool.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 BEAT the cream cheese until light and fluff on medium speed. Add the remaining sugar and continue mixing until combined.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 FOLD the whipped topping into the whipped cream cheese until combined.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 SPREAD the cream cheese and <span class="s1">whipped topping mixture</span>evenly over the cooled pretzel crust.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 STIR the gelatin into two cups of boiling water until completely dissolved.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 STIR the frozen raspberries into the gelatin and continuing stirring until the mixture becomes partially jelled.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 SPREAD the gelatin evenly over the cream cheese mixture.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 COVER and refrigerate until completely set.
10a73b34-70f4-403e-a4f1-72379b16b544 GARNISH with whipped cream and fresh raspberries before serving.
bac6fdc5-e9f5-4361-999c-75348d5edb0d Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Remove giblets and neck from inside turkey; discard. Rinse turkey and pat dry with paper towels. Sprinkle body cavity with salt and pepper.
bac6fdc5-e9f5-4361-999c-75348d5edb0d For herb-butter seasoning, in a small bowl, combine butter, herb, and garlic. Starting at the neck end of the turkey, loosen the skin by sliding your fingers underneath it, being careful not to tear it. Slide your hand as far as you can toward the other end of the turkey, separating the skin from the meat. Rub about two-thirds of the herb-butter seasoning over the entire breast.
bac6fdc5-e9f5-4361-999c-75348d5edb0d Spoon some stuffing loosely into the neck cavity. Pull neck skin to back and fasten with a skewer. Spoon more of the stuffing loosely into the body cavity. (If you pack stuffing too tightly, it will not get hot enough by the time the turkey is cooked.) If a band of skin crosses the tail, tuck the ends of the drumsticks under band. If there is no band, tie drumsticks to the tail using 100-percent-cotton string. Twist wing tips under back. Place any remaining stuffing in a casserole; cover and chill.
bac6fdc5-e9f5-4361-999c-75348d5edb0d Place turkey, breast side up, on a rack in a Reynolds® Bakeware heavy-duty turkey roaster pan. Insert a meat thermometer into the center of one of the inside thigh muscles. (The thermometer should not touch bone.)
bac6fdc5-e9f5-4361-999c-75348d5edb0d Rub remaining herb-butter seasoning over the entire turkey. Cover turkey loosely with foil. Roast for 20 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350 degrees F. Continue roasting for 2-1/2 hours. Cut the band of skin or string between the drumsticks so the thighs will cook evenly. Continue roasting for 1 to 1-1/2 hours more or until thermometer registers 180 degrees F to 185 degrees F and stuffing in turkey registers 165 degrees F. Bake casserole of stuffing alongside turkey the last 30 to 40 minutes of roasting. Uncover turkey the last 30 minutes of roasting.
bac6fdc5-e9f5-4361-999c-75348d5edb0d Remove turkey from oven. Cover with aluminum foil and let stand for 15 minutes before carving. To serve, remove stuffing from turkey and place in a serving bowl. Carve turkey and serve with stuffing. Makes 14 servings.
64e598b5-8629-4460-8874-4d5a0f0f5e4c Preheat oven to 375°F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Remove leaves from the cauliflower. Carefully trim stem ends, leaving core intact so florets are still attached. Cut 3/4- to 1-inch-thick slices crosswise through the core of each cauliflower head. Place the slices on the prepared baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.
64e598b5-8629-4460-8874-4d5a0f0f5e4c Bake 35 minutes, or until cauliflower is tender and golden brown.
64e598b5-8629-4460-8874-4d5a0f0f5e4c Top roasted cauliflower with Cilantro Cream. Garnish with cilantro, if desired.
89793646-c3fc-4afb-a764-41325e5ca67e PREHEAT oven to 400F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch pan. Add flour, rosemary, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Squeeze bag to blend seasonings.
89793646-c3fc-4afb-a764-41325e5ca67e ADD potatoes and olive oil to bag. Turn bag several times to coat potatoes with seasonings. Arrange potatoes in an even layer.
89793646-c3fc-4afb-a764-41325e5ca67e CLOSE bag with nylon tie; cut six -inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
89793646-c3fc-4afb-a764-41325e5ca67e BAKE 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork. Carefully cut bag open.
89793646-c3fc-4afb-a764-41325e5ca67e SPOON potatoes into bowl; mash lightly with a fork. Add sour cream, butter and green onions; mix lightly.
66209dd2-a7b6-42d1-8d2d-eb501edbe067 MIX olive oil, tarragon, garlic, lemon peel, seasoned salt and pepper in a small bowl; set aside.
66209dd2-a7b6-42d1-8d2d-eb501edbe067 TEAR off four 15-inch sheets of Reynolds Parchment Paper. Fold each sheet in half and crease it in the center. Unfold.
66209dd2-a7b6-42d1-8d2d-eb501edbe067 PLACE 1/4 of asparagus evenly on one-half of each sheet near crease. Place salmon fillet on top of asparagus. Spread each fillet with 1/4 of olive oil mixture. Top each fillet with a lemon slice.
66209dd2-a7b6-42d1-8d2d-eb501edbe067 FOLD over other half of sheet to enclose ingredients. Starting at top corner, make small overlapping folds down entire length of packet to seal edges together. Twist the last fold several times to make a tight seal. Repeat to make 4 packets. Place parchment packets on a large cookie sheet
66209dd2-a7b6-42d1-8d2d-eb501edbe067 BAKE 18 to 20 minutes. Place parchment packets on dinner plates. Carefully cut an X in top of each packet to allow steam to escape. Serve immediately.
66209dd2-a7b6-42d1-8d2d-eb501edbe067 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: To reduce fat and calories, remove skin of salmon with a sharp knife before cooking.
1dcfd193-0747-4662-b9ba-cf5bd1e577d5 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
1dcfd193-0747-4662-b9ba-cf5bd1e577d5 COOK bacon in a large skillet on medium heat until crispy; remove from skillet. Crumble bacon; set aside. Add onion to skillet; cook until transparent, 3 to 4 minutes.
1dcfd193-0747-4662-b9ba-cf5bd1e577d5 PLACE onion, beans and brown sugar in the slow cooker liner. Add crumbled bacon.
1dcfd193-0747-4662-b9ba-cf5bd1e577d5 MIX barbecue sauce, mustard and cornstarch in a small bowl; gently stir mixture into beans using a wooden or plastic spoon. Place lid on slow cooker.
1dcfd193-0747-4662-b9ba-cf5bd1e577d5 COOK on HIGH 2 to 3 hours OR on LOW 4 to 5 hours or until sauce is thickened and bubbly.
1dcfd193-0747-4662-b9ba-cf5bd1e577d5 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve beans directly from slow cooker liner. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
1dcfd193-0747-4662-b9ba-cf5bd1e577d5 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: To make Vegetarian Baked Beans, substitute vegetarian baked beans for pork and beans and omit the bacon.
a19504aa-dad3-4023-8a65-84d4c01af328 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
a19504aa-dad3-4023-8a65-84d4c01af328 PLACE potatoes in lined-slow cooker; sprinkle with garlic, salt and pepper. Pour water over potatoes. Place lid on slow cooker.
a19504aa-dad3-4023-8a65-84d4c01af328 COOK on LOW for 6 to 7 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours until potatoes are tender.
a19504aa-dad3-4023-8a65-84d4c01af328 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Gently mash potatoes into smaller pieces using a potato masher or back of a wooden or plastic spoon. Add milk and butter; stir gently. Serve warm potatoes directly from lined-slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
a19504aa-dad3-4023-8a65-84d4c01af328 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liners are great for reheating left over Smashed Potatoes. Place potatoes in a lined-slow cooker. Heat on HIGH for 1 to 2 hours until potatoes are hot.
69bc3692-e538-44b1-abe0-be5396ca9f11 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
69bc3692-e538-44b1-abe0-be5396ca9f11 PLACE sweet potatoes in slow cooker. Place apples in medium bowl. Pour orange juice over apples; stir to coat apples. Stir remaining ingredients, except Glazed Pecans, into orange juice. Pour apple mixture over sweet potatoes. Place lid on slow cooker.
69bc3692-e538-44b1-abe0-be5396ca9f11 COOK on LOW for 6 to 7 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours until sweet potatoes are tender.
69bc3692-e538-44b1-abe0-be5396ca9f11 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Remove sweet potatoes from slow cooker using a slotted plastic or wooden spoon. Leave lid off slow cooker continue cooking for 15 minutes to thicken sauce. Spoon thickened sauce over sweet potatoes. Sprinkle with Glazed Pecans, if desired.
69bc3692-e538-44b1-abe0-be5396ca9f11 GLAZED PECANS: Place 1/2 cup coarsely chopped pecans and 2 tablespoons sugar in medium sauce pan. Stir constantly over medium heat until sugar melts and coats pecans. Spread pecans on sheet of foil; cool completely.
ce2b39b0-657d-45ef-9876-2d489c182670 Quinoa: Add quinoa, water, salsa, bay leaf, cumin, salt, garlic powder, black beans and chicken to your slow cooker that has been lined with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner.
ce2b39b0-657d-45ef-9876-2d489c182670 Cover and cook on HIGH for hours or for hours on LOW.
ce2b39b0-657d-45ef-9876-2d489c182670 Dish quinoa into serving bowls and top with diced tomato and black beans.
ce2b39b0-657d-45ef-9876-2d489c182670 Remove all food and discard Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner.
ce2b39b0-657d-45ef-9876-2d489c182670 Tomatillo Salsa: Add all ingredients into a blender.
ce2b39b0-657d-45ef-9876-2d489c182670 Pulse several times and then blend until desired consistency.
ce2b39b0-657d-45ef-9876-2d489c182670 Season to taste with additional kosher salt, if necessary.
26108036-71b9-441a-b009-51302fda48b2 CORE the apples from the top, using a small melon baller or a paring knife. Remove the stem end and seeds, creating a cavity in the apple, but leave the bottom intact to hold in the filling.
26108036-71b9-441a-b009-51302fda48b2 PLACE 1/2 tablespoon whipped cream cheese in cavity of each apple. Top with 1/2 tablespoon apricot jam, 1/2 tablespoon brown sugar, and 1/2 tablespoon butter. The recipe can be prepared to this stage several hours ahead.
26108036-71b9-441a-b009-51302fda48b2 SET UP your grill for indirect grilling (rake the lit coals into two piles on opposite sides of the grill) and preheat to medium (about 350° F.) Place a foil drip pan in center under apples.
26108036-71b9-441a-b009-51302fda48b2 TEAR off six 3-inch pieces of Reynolds Wrap Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil to hold apples upright on the grill grate. Twist each piece into a doughnut shape about 2 inches in diameter.
26108036-71b9-441a-b009-51302fda48b2 ARRANGE apples on the Reynolds Wrap Foil doughnuts in the center of the grill over the drip pan. Make a smoker pouch with wood chips or toss half the wood chips on each mound of coals and cover the grill.
282a3bef-1e3f-4b7c-bba7-ad2e58350616 In large bowl, beat sugars, butter, water, vanilla and eggs with electric mixer on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, until blended. On low speed, beat in flour, baking soda and salt until well blended. Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate at least hours for easier handling.
282a3bef-1e3f-4b7c-bba7-ad2e58350616 Heat oven to °F. Using about tablespoon dough, press dough around each chocolate candy to cover completely. Place inches apart on cookie sheets lined with parchment paper. Top each with walnut half.
282a3bef-1e3f-4b7c-bba7-ad2e58350616 Bake to minutes or until light golden brown. Immediately remove from cookie sheets to cooling rack.
0aad3d5f-fcbc-4f6c-9dbd-4b6c8ddad6b8 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
0aad3d5f-fcbc-4f6c-9dbd-4b6c8ddad6b8 LINE a 13x9x2-inch baking dish with Reynolds Wrap Pan Lining Paper with parchment paper side toward food. Crimp Pan Lining Paper around rim of pan; set aside.
0aad3d5f-fcbc-4f6c-9dbd-4b6c8ddad6b8 COMBINE soup, sour cream and pepper in a large bowl; blend well. Add onions, red pepper, cheddar cheese, Swiss cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Stir in potatoes. Spoon mixture into lined pan in an even layer; sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
0aad3d5f-fcbc-4f6c-9dbd-4b6c8ddad6b8 BAKE uncovered 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until bubbling and golden brown.
3a433b1b-104f-4ff5-84a6-e1f59c40d218 Heat oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with parchment paper.
3a433b1b-104f-4ff5-84a6-e1f59c40d218 In large bowl, break up cookie dough. Stir or knead in remaining ingredients until well blended. On cookie sheets, drop dough by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart.
3a433b1b-104f-4ff5-84a6-e1f59c40d218 Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are golden brown. (Surface of cookies will look underbaked.) Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks.
eb563642-5e59-4f7d-adde-552cc8e0f835 PREHEAT oven to 450°F. Combine all ingredients; spoon onto foil in single layer.
eb563642-5e59-4f7d-adde-552cc8e0f835 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal making one large foil packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Place in 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
eb563642-5e59-4f7d-adde-552cc8e0f835 THE REYNOLDS KITCHEN TIP: For spicier flavor add 4 oz. chorizo sausage, casing removed and cut into 1/4-inch pieces, to potato ingredients before baking.
eb563642-5e59-4f7d-adde-552cc8e0f835 BAKE minutes.
3cfaeef2-6866-4dc2-b35d-6b93ac1a0a24 Preheat a gas or charcoal grill over high heat.
3cfaeef2-6866-4dc2-b35d-6b93ac1a0a24 Whisk together butter, Parmesan, basil and oregano; season with salt and pepper to taste.
3cfaeef2-6866-4dc2-b35d-6b93ac1a0a24 Center zucchini on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil. Spoon butter mixture over zucchini. Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
3cfaeef2-6866-4dc2-b35d-6b93ac1a0a24 Place foil packets on the grill and cook until just cooked through, about 15 to 20 minutes.
3cfaeef2-6866-4dc2-b35d-6b93ac1a0a24 Serve immediately, garnished with parsley, if desired.
5276c2bb-c461-4f36-b20b-2eb11ec07dc5 Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Place cherry tomatoes on the prepared baking sheet.
5276c2bb-c461-4f36-b20b-2eb11ec07dc5 Distribute sage and thyme amongst tomatoes, reserving about 1 tablespoon of each for garnishing. Drizzle generously with olive oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast for 30 minutes or until tomatoes blister.
5276c2bb-c461-4f36-b20b-2eb11ec07dc5 Remove tomatoes and place into a bowl, tossing all juices collected in the foil. Garnish with additional fresh thyme, sage and oregano. Season with salt and pepper to taste and serve.
ef12bdfe-3086-442f-8fc0-dba789d593d5 PREHEAT oven to 450°F OR grill to medium-high. Combine orange marmalade and salt. Add broccoli and carrots; toss to coat.
ef12bdfe-3086-442f-8fc0-dba789d593d5 CENTER vegetable mixture on sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
ef12bdfe-3086-442f-8fc0-dba789d593d5 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal making one large packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
ef12bdfe-3086-442f-8fc0-dba789d593d5 BAKE 15 to 20 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR
ef12bdfe-3086-442f-8fc0-dba789d593d5 GRILL 8 to 10 minutes in covered grill. Open packet, add oranges and stir. Sprinkle with cashews before serving.
2f4b372c-c0e1-440e-bc41-76ee796d3529 HEAT oven to 450ºF.
2f4b372c-c0e1-440e-bc41-76ee796d3529 PLACE tomatoes and garlic on center of sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil; drizzle with dressing. Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Place on rimmed baking sheet. Bake for 15 minutes.
2f4b372c-c0e1-440e-bc41-76ee796d3529 COOK pasta as directed on package, omitting salt.
2f4b372c-c0e1-440e-bc41-76ee796d3529 DRAIN pasta; place in serving bowl.
2f4b372c-c0e1-440e-bc41-76ee796d3529 OPEN packet carefully, allowing steam to escape, by cutting along top fold with sharp knife. Spoon vegetable mixture over pasta; top with cheese and basil.
a743507d-8d60-45b6-b35c-f4f419141159 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
a743507d-8d60-45b6-b35c-f4f419141159 CENTER vegetables on sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Sprinkle with Cajun seasoning; stir to blend. Top with margarine or butter.
a743507d-8d60-45b6-b35c-f4f419141159 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal making one large foil packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
a743507d-8d60-45b6-b35c-f4f419141159 BAKE 20 to 25 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR GRILL 12 to 14 minutes in covered grill.
188a6c12-70a2-4425-b3ad-33e9e3f78560 Heat oven to °F. Line large cookie sheets with parchment paper. Let cookie dough stand at room temperature for minutes to soften.
188a6c12-70a2-4425-b3ad-33e9e3f78560 In medium bowl, break up cookie dough. Add nuts, cherries, coconut and vanilla. Mix with wooden spoon or knead with hands until well blended. Shape rounded tablespoonfuls of dough into balls. Place inches apart on cookie sheets.
188a6c12-70a2-4425-b3ad-33e9e3f78560 Bake to minutes or until edges are light golden brown. Cool minutes. With back of teaspoon, make indentation in center of each cookie. Spoon teaspoon preserves in each indentation. Cool completely, about minutes. Store in covered container.
f438482e-b15f-45fb-853d-1fab8769ba0c PREHEAT oven to 425°F. Line two 8x8x2-inch baking pans with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. In large bowl, combine chicken, soup, vegetables and poultry seasoning; mix well. Spoon into baking pans.
f438482e-b15f-45fb-853d-1fab8769ba0c SOFTEN pie crusts following package directions. Using a small cookie cutter, make cut outs in pie crust or cut slits in top of crust to vent steam. Place one crust on top of each filling. Fold edges of pie crust under slightly to fit pan; flute, if desired.
f438482e-b15f-45fb-853d-1fab8769ba0c TO SERVE NOW , bake one casserole 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
f438482e-b15f-45fb-853d-1fab8769ba0c TO FREEZE, cover second casserole with a sheet of foil. Fold edges of bottom and top foil sheet together to make a packet; freeze. When frozen solid, remove baking pan from freezer.
f438482e-b15f-45fb-853d-1fab8769ba0c PREHEAT oven to 400°F. To bake, return frozen foil packet to original baking pan. Remove top foil sheet from casserole.
f438482e-b15f-45fb-853d-1fab8769ba0c BAKE 1 1/4 hours or until filling is hot.
bcf2876b-bbf5-46cc-9e2f-6859e906cb77 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
bcf2876b-bbf5-46cc-9e2f-6859e906cb77 COMBINE ground beef, pasta sauce and 2 teaspoons Italian seasoning. Stir pasta into meat sauce; spread half of mixture evenly in parchment-lined pan. Top with half of Mozzarella cheese.
bcf2876b-bbf5-46cc-9e2f-6859e906cb77 COMBINE ricotta cheese, egg, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasoning; spread over Mozzarella cheese in pan. Spread remaining pasta mixture over ricotta cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
bcf2876b-bbf5-46cc-9e2f-6859e906cb77 BAKE to minutes or until hot and cheese is golden brown. Let stand minutes before serving.
d0b921cd-3783-431a-89d4-eb20a01a8558 Cook pasta according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.
d0b921cd-3783-431a-89d4-eb20a01a8558 In a small bowl, whisk together cornstarch, soy sauce, hoisin sauce, rice wine vinegar, ginger, and water. Set aside.
d0b921cd-3783-431a-89d4-eb20a01a8558 In a large pan, heat a teaspoon of cooking oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken and stir fry until no longer pink, 5 - 8 minutes. Add cole slaw and snow peas; cook, stirring, until cole slaw wilts, just a minute or 2.
d0b921cd-3783-431a-89d4-eb20a01a8558 Add the cornstarch mixture to the pan, bring to a boil, and cook until thickened, about 2 minutes.
340f44ed-123b-4de8-9ea9-1b966d8a73d1 Preheat oven to 350F.
340f44ed-123b-4de8-9ea9-1b966d8a73d1 Cook pasta according to package instructions. Gently toss with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Set aside.
340f44ed-123b-4de8-9ea9-1b966d8a73d1 In a skillet over medium-high heat, cook ground turkey until no longer pink. Add taco seasoning and ¾ cup water. Bring to a simmer and let cook until most of the liquid has been absorbed. Stir in cream cheese and taco sauce until the cream cheese has completely melted.
340f44ed-123b-4de8-9ea9-1b966d8a73d1 Spread about ¼ cup of the salsa in the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish. Fill pasta shells one at a time with 2 - 3 tablespoons of the ground turkey mixture. Transfer to the baking dish. When all shells are done, top with remaining salsa and shredded cheddar.
340f44ed-123b-4de8-9ea9-1b966d8a73d1 Bake in preheated oven for about 15 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.
340f44ed-123b-4de8-9ea9-1b966d8a73d1 Top with chopped green onions and crumbled tortilla chips before serving.
6e8d1625-8cbe-45e7-ba16-e411ddbefa73 PREHEAT oven to 350 degrees. Melt the butter in a large skillet. Add onion, garlic, tomatoes, oregano and Greek seasoning.
6e8d1625-8cbe-45e7-ba16-e411ddbefa73 COOK over medium-high heat, stirring often for 2 to 3 minutes. Add gyro meat and continue cooking for 1 to 2 minutes. Add the stock and continue cooking until mixture comes to a boil. Stir in salt and pepper. Remove from heat and set aside.
6e8d1625-8cbe-45e7-ba16-e411ddbefa73 PLACE pita bread in a 13x9-inch Reynolds® Bakeware Pan. Drizzle the beaten egg on top and toss to coat. Pour the stock/gyro mixture on top. Using a spatula, stir mixture to fully coat the pita bread.
6e8d1625-8cbe-45e7-ba16-e411ddbefa73 BAKE for 30 minutes, then cover with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes.
6e8d1625-8cbe-45e7-ba16-e411ddbefa73 COMBINE all items for Tzatziki. Stir thoroughly to combine.
6e8d1625-8cbe-45e7-ba16-e411ddbefa73 SERVE Gyro Stuffing with Tzatziki sauce.
b72393e4-84ca-4641-b059-a05317e331a9 PREHEAT oven to 375 degrees. Melt the butter in a large saucepan. Add chorizo, onion and garlic. Cook 3 to 4 minutes, or until chorizo starts to brown. Add bell peppers, tomatoes, salt, paprika and saffron. Continue cooking 1 to 2 minutes.
b72393e4-84ca-4641-b059-a05317e331a9 STIR in stock. Continue cooking until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and set aside.
b72393e4-84ca-4641-b059-a05317e331a9 PLACE the rice evenly into a 13x9-inch Reynolds® Bakeware Pan. Add baguette pieces then drizzle the beaten egg on top. Gently toss to coat. Pour the stock/chorizo mixture on top. Using a spatula, gently spread the mixture over the bread.
b72393e4-84ca-4641-b059-a05317e331a9 BAKE for 30 minutes, then cover with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and bake and additional 25 to 30 minutes or until most of the liquid is evaporated.
b72393e4-84ca-4641-b059-a05317e331a9 REMOVE from oven and let cool 15 minutes before serving.
79e4b23c-e850-417d-aec8-85b2ee9969dd Preheat the oven to 325°.
79e4b23c-e850-417d-aec8-85b2ee9969dd Process together 16 chocolate sandwich cookies and melted butter until it is the consistency of bread crumbs.
79e4b23c-e850-417d-aec8-85b2ee9969dd Press the cookie crumb mixture to the bottom of a Reynolds® 13x9 Bakeware Pan to form a crust and bake for 10 minutes at 325°. Remove and set aside.
79e4b23c-e850-417d-aec8-85b2ee9969dd Whip the softened cream cheese and sugar together on high speed using a standing or hand mixer until it becomes light and fluffy, about 2 to 3 minutes.
79e4b23c-e850-417d-aec8-85b2ee9969dd Add in 1 egg at a time until completely combined and then add in 1 cup of sour cream and mix.
79e4b23c-e850-417d-aec8-85b2ee9969dd Roughly chop 16 chocolate sandwich cookies until it they are course and fold them into the cream cheese mixture.
79e4b23c-e850-417d-aec8-85b2ee9969dd Transfer the batter to the top of the pre-cooked crust and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until the outside edges are lightly browned and the middle is firm. Cool completely in the refrigerator.
79e4b23c-e850-417d-aec8-85b2ee9969dd Mix together in a medium size bowl ¾ cup sour cream, whipped cream and powdered sugar until combined and evenly spread it over top of the cooled cheese cake.
79e4b23c-e850-417d-aec8-85b2ee9969dd Chop the remaining 10 cookies until course and sprinkle them on top.
7ff009fe-5cd3-445b-85f2-d3a067a34ed3 Preheat the oven to 400°.
7ff009fe-5cd3-445b-85f2-d3a067a34ed3 Add tomatoes, onion, peppers, capers, olives, lemon juice, 3 tablespoons of olive oil and salt and pepper to a Reynolds® Lasagna Bakeware Pan and mix.
7ff009fe-5cd3-445b-85f2-d3a067a34ed3 Set the salmon fillets over top of the vegetables and glaze each piece of fish with olive oil and season them with salt and pepper.
7ff009fe-5cd3-445b-85f2-d3a067a34ed3 Bake at 400° for 35 to 50 minutes or until the salmon is lightly browned and cooked through out.
7ff009fe-5cd3-445b-85f2-d3a067a34ed3 Optional garnish with fresh cilantro leaves.
7ff009fe-5cd3-445b-85f2-d3a067a34ed3 Serve hot alongside white rice.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Cookies: Whisk together butter and sugar until light and fluffy, 30–40 seconds.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Cookies: Whisk in egg
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Cookies: Gently stir in next 4 ingredients, then oats. Refrigerate 1 hour, or up to 3 days.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Filling: Process all the ingredients in a food processor until smooth.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Remove dough from refrigerator for 10 minutes.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Preheat oven to 375˚.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Line 2 baking sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Scoop 2 tablespoons dough per cookie and gently round off.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Place onto parchment 2 inches apart. Flatten slightly.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Bake 6–7 minutes; cool 2 minutes on sheet, then transfer to wire rack to cool completely.
437631bd-5d30-4ca7-adcb-ecccf509b07a Use 11⁄2 tablespoons filling per sandwich.
27994840-d842-4492-98ff-1e537bc080bf PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
27994840-d842-4492-98ff-1e537bc080bf ADD the chocolate chips, butter and stout beer to a medium sized metal bowl and put it over a pot of simmering water to create a double boiler. Continually stir with a rubber spatula until smooth. Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
27994840-d842-4492-98ff-1e537bc080bf MIX together in a separate large bowl the eggs, brown sugar, sugar, flour, cocoa powder, vanilla and baking powder.
27994840-d842-4492-98ff-1e537bc080bf POUR the chocolate mixture into the eggs and sugar mixture and fold until combined.
27994840-d842-4492-98ff-1e537bc080bf POUR the batter into a Non-Stick Reynolds Wrap-lined pan. Top with infused pecans if desired.
27994840-d842-4492-98ff-1e537bc080bf BAKE in the oven on 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until the brownies begin to pull away from the outside of the pan.
27994840-d842-4492-98ff-1e537bc080bf COOL before serving.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line two muffin pans with Reynolds® Baking Cups.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 STIR together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl; set aside.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 COMBINE the red wine and milk. Set aside.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 BEAT butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds in a large mixing bowl. Gradually add sugar, about 1/4 cup at a time, beating on medium speed until well combined (3 to 4 minutes). Scrape the sides of the bowl; continue beating on medium speed for 2 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition (about 1 minute total). Beat in vanilla.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 ADD the flour mixture and wine/milk to the beaten mixture, alternating them and beating on low speed just until combined after each addition. Beat on high speed for 20 seconds more.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 TRANSFER batter to baking cups, then bake 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 Red Wine Frosting: COMBINE red wine and sugar in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil, then simmer and reduce by half. Remove from heat and set aside to cool.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 BEAT the butter and cream cheese with an electric mixer on high speed until light and fluffy.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 ADD in the powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons of the red wine reduction and mix on low speed until incorporated and then mix on high speed for 2 minutes.
225c51be-13fa-4012-af09-0adc13f66cb0 FROST Cupcakes before serving.
3fb9eb43-a4e5-42f1-b517-a2d742dbf892 PLACE the dark chocolate in a large bowl.
3fb9eb43-a4e5-42f1-b517-a2d742dbf892 HEAT the cream in a saucepan until it just about reaches a simmer
3fb9eb43-a4e5-42f1-b517-a2d742dbf892 POUR the cream over the melted chocolate. Add the vanilla extract and let set for 1 minute.
3fb9eb43-a4e5-42f1-b517-a2d742dbf892 STIR the cream and chocolate tougher until fully incorporated and smooth.
3fb9eb43-a4e5-42f1-b517-a2d742dbf892 Transfer to refrigerator until firm enough to roll into balls, about 1 hour. Stir the mixture occasionally while cooling.
3fb9eb43-a4e5-42f1-b517-a2d742dbf892 LINE a baking sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
3fb9eb43-a4e5-42f1-b517-a2d742dbf892 ROLL chocolate into 1-inch truffles. Transfer to parchment-lined baking sheet. Toss in one of the toppings below.
b4a1a61e-3d63-4677-aba8-36ed46782af7 Preheat oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
b4a1a61e-3d63-4677-aba8-36ed46782af7 In a large bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, and oil. With an electric mixer, beat on medium speed until smooth (dough will be stiff). Fold in 3 tablespoons sprinkles. Drop dough by rounded teaspoons onto the prepared cookie sheet.
b4a1a61e-3d63-4677-aba8-36ed46782af7 Bake for 7 to 8 minutes or until tops just start to brown. Cool on cookie sheets for 1 minute. Remove; cool completely on wire racks.
b4a1a61e-3d63-4677-aba8-36ed46782af7 Meanwhile, for buttercream frosting, beat butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sifted powdered sugar alternately with milk, beating well after each addition. Beat in additional milk, if necessary, to make a spreading consistency.
b4a1a61e-3d63-4677-aba8-36ed46782af7 Frost cookies with buttercream frosting and sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons sprinkles.
2491c2fc-bcd8-4819-8924-73af9ce13a57 Preheat oven to 300°F. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
2491c2fc-bcd8-4819-8924-73af9ce13a57 In a shallow baking pan, combine oats and walnuts. Bake about 20 minutes or until light brown, stirring occasionally; cool.
2491c2fc-bcd8-4819-8924-73af9ce13a57 Increase oven temperature to 350°F. In a medium bowl, combine egg, peanut butter, brown sugar, honey, vanilla, and salt. Stir in oat mixture, flaxseed meal, flour, and chocolate until combined.
2491c2fc-bcd8-4819-8924-73af9ce13a57 Using a medium cookie scoop, portion dough onto prepared cookie sheet (or measure 1 1/2-tablespoon portions). Using wet fingers, flatten dough balls to 1/2 inch.
2491c2fc-bcd8-4819-8924-73af9ce13a57 Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until firm around edges and light brown. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheets. Remove; cool completely on wire racks.
d9801823-b1fd-48e0-9a47-f93b18a652b7 COMBINE flour, cocoa powder, baking powder and salt in large bowl; set aside.
d9801823-b1fd-48e0-9a47-f93b18a652b7 BEAT butter and sugar with electric mixer until fluffy, about 3 minutes. Beat in egg yolks and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture and combine.
d9801823-b1fd-48e0-9a47-f93b18a652b7 WRAP dough in parchment paper and place in plastic zipper bag; refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.
d9801823-b1fd-48e0-9a47-f93b18a652b7 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
d9801823-b1fd-48e0-9a47-f93b18a652b7 ROLL out dough 1/8-inch thick between 2 lightly floured sheets of parchment paper. CUT dough with 2 inch cookie cutters. PLACE dough on parchment-lined cookie sheets.
d9801823-b1fd-48e0-9a47-f93b18a652b7 BAKE 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned on edges. Slide parchment paper with cookies onto cooling rack; cool.
d9801823-b1fd-48e0-9a47-f93b18a652b7 DECORATE as desired. Store in airtight containers for up to 5 days.
00d107b3-890c-4745-9a26-62337ec27e86 BEAT the cream cheese, butter and vanilla with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth. Add powdered sugar and continue mixing until combined.
00d107b3-890c-4745-9a26-62337ec27e86 ADD chocolate chips and toffee bits and mix until just combined.
00d107b3-890c-4745-9a26-62337ec27e86 TRANSFER to a bowl and serve with cookies.
458faed9-5897-4271-a668-2faf749e1cbc POUR cereal and pumpkin seeds onto a foil lined sheet pan.
458faed9-5897-4271-a668-2faf749e1cbc MIX powdered sugar, 1 tsp pumpkin pie spice, and 1 tsp cinnamon in a medium bowl and set aside.
458faed9-5897-4271-a668-2faf749e1cbc MELT the white chocolate chips, butter, sunflower butter using a double boiler or microwave (working in 20 second increments). When completely smooth add in the vanilla, 2 tsp pumpkin pie spice, and 1 tsp cinnamon. Stir until combined.
458faed9-5897-4271-a668-2faf749e1cbc DRIZZLE the white chocolate mixture over the cereal and pumpkin seeds. Toss gently using a wooden spoon or hands, coating evenly.
458faed9-5897-4271-a668-2faf749e1cbc POUR cereal into a Reynolds KITCHENS™ Oven Bag or food storage bag. Add powdered sugar mixture and shake gently, coating the cereal and pumpkin seeds evenly.
458faed9-5897-4271-a668-2faf749e1cbc ADD mellowcreme pumpkins and give another toss.
458faed9-5897-4271-a668-2faf749e1cbc PORTION into Reynolds KITCHENS™ Wax Paper Sandwich Bags.
4ed4873c-7ab8-4a4e-82f7-ea2c12483532 PREHEAT oven to 200°F.
4ed4873c-7ab8-4a4e-82f7-ea2c12483532 LINE a sheet pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil and cover with popcorn, pistachios, cashews, and cranberries.
4ed4873c-7ab8-4a4e-82f7-ea2c12483532 COMBINE butter, brown sugar, and honey in a medium saucepan. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and continue boiling for another 3 minutes.
4ed4873c-7ab8-4a4e-82f7-ea2c12483532 POUR the hot mixture over the ingredients on the sheet pan, quickly and carefully. Use a wooden spoon to toss lightly, coating the popcorn evenly.
4ed4873c-7ab8-4a4e-82f7-ea2c12483532 PLACE the sheet pan in the oven for 45 minutes. Toss the mixture lightly every 15 minutes.
4ed4873c-7ab8-4a4e-82f7-ea2c12483532 MELT the chocolate using a double boiler or microwave (working in 20 second increments).
4ed4873c-7ab8-4a4e-82f7-ea2c12483532 REMOVE sheet pan from the oven. Drizzle the melted chocolate over the popcorn mixture and let cool until chocolate hardens.
4ed4873c-7ab8-4a4e-82f7-ea2c12483532 BREAK apart and portion into Reynolds KITCHENS™ Wax Paper Sandwich Bags.
8191e219-9f9f-467c-8c45-b8fff66fa266 PLACE butter, sugar, cocoa powder, and salt in a large microwave safe bowl. Microwave in 20 second increments, stirring after each time, until butter is completely melted. Set aside for 5 minutes to cool slightly. Mix will be very grainy.
8191e219-9f9f-467c-8c45-b8fff66fa266 STIR in vanilla extract. Add eggs and beat until fully incorporated. Add the flour and mix until just combined, careful not to over mix.
8191e219-9f9f-467c-8c45-b8fff66fa266 LINE a 4 - 6 quart round slow cooker with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner. Spray with non-stick spray then pour the brownie batter into slow cooker.
8191e219-9f9f-467c-8c45-b8fff66fa266 COVER and cook on low-heat setting for 2 1/2 - 3 hours or until edges are set and center is still slightly gooey. Remove lid and let brownies cool in slow cooker completely before removing.
8191e219-9f9f-467c-8c45-b8fff66fa266 TRANSFER brownie to cutting board. Remove slow cooker liner then cut into 8 wedges, keeping the circular shape from the round slow cooker.
8191e219-9f9f-467c-8c45-b8fff66fa266 DECORATE by adding pretzel antlers, jellybean nose and white chocolate chip eyes. Use melted chocolate to affix decorations to brownies.
04b6db07-e59c-4414-9280-d0c9420bf1f6 Combine the oil, salt, pepper, thyme and garlic into a paste, then add and rub all over the roast meat. Set aside at room temperature for a time of 1 hour. 40 minutes into the hour, pre-heat the oven to 500 degrees F.
04b6db07-e59c-4414-9280-d0c9420bf1f6 On a baking sheet, place two sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil large enough to cover the roast. Place the meat on the foil sheets and transfer everything to the oven. Roast for 6 minutes per pound.
04b6db07-e59c-4414-9280-d0c9420bf1f6 Remove from the oven. Fold up the foil so it wraps the roast then return to the oven. Reduce the oven temperature to 170 degrees F and roast for a time of one hour. After an hour, check the internal oven temperature with an instant-read thermometer: 120-125 degrees F will yield a rare center, 130-140 degrees F will yield a medium-rare center, and 140-150 degrees F will yield a medium center.
04b6db07-e59c-4414-9280-d0c9420bf1f6 When the meat is finished, remove it from the oven and set it on a cutting board to rest. Transfer any drippings from the roast into a saucepan, then combine with the red wine and beef broth. Bring to a simmer over med-high heat and reduce by 1/4; reduce heat to medium-low and whisk in the cubes of butter one at a time until incorporated into the sauce. Add salt and pepper to taste and set the meat aside.
04b6db07-e59c-4414-9280-d0c9420bf1f6 Slice the meat into 1/2 inch thick slices and serve with the pan sauce poured on top.
514ec311-c043-4d18-93ef-464016b5dcd5 Heat oven to 350°F. In large bowl, combine quick bread mix, walnuts, butter and egg; mix well. Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls. Place 3 inches apart on cookie sheets lined with parchment paper. With glass dipped in sugar, press each to 1/8-inch thickness.
514ec311-c043-4d18-93ef-464016b5dcd5 Bake at 350°F for 7 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown around edges. Remove from cookie sheets.
348835d4-4124-4b97-a07f-b2bb43743e86 Place ribs on a sheet of Reynolds® Parchment Paper for easy cleanup.
348835d4-4124-4b97-a07f-b2bb43743e86 Generously sprinkle dry rub over the front and back of the ribs. Then use roughly 1 cup of spice rub to coat the ribs front and back (your hands will get dirty, but the mess is worth it!).
348835d4-4124-4b97-a07f-b2bb43743e86 Next, take a Reynolds® Turkey Oven Bag and sprinkle 1 tbsp. of flour inside, giving it a good shake to spread it around, per the box instructions.
348835d4-4124-4b97-a07f-b2bb43743e86 Then place the ribs inside the bag, secure it with the tie provided in the box, and tuck the top of the bag under the side of the ribs.
348835d4-4124-4b97-a07f-b2bb43743e86 Place the ribs back in the refrigerator to marinade if time permits.
348835d4-4124-4b97-a07f-b2bb43743e86 When you are ready to cook your ribs, preheat your oven to 350 degrees.
348835d4-4124-4b97-a07f-b2bb43743e86 Cut 6 slits along the top of the oven bag.
348835d4-4124-4b97-a07f-b2bb43743e86 Place the ribs on a baking sheet in the oven and let cook for 1 1/2 hours.
348835d4-4124-4b97-a07f-b2bb43743e86 After removing the ribs from the oven and letting them cool for a few minutes, carefully cut the bag open. Watch out for that steam! Apply the remaining 1/2-cup of barbecue sauce to the cooked ribs. Serve at once!
bbb75069-f749-47c4-a3a5-fdfe97ba993f PREHEAT oven to 425°F.For easy cleanup, line a 13x9x2-inch pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
bbb75069-f749-47c4-a3a5-fdfe97ba993f COMBINE olive oil, basil, rosemary and salt in a large bowl. Place pork tenderloin in foil-lined pan. Sprinkle and rub 2/3 of olive oil and herb mixture over pork, turning to coat evenly. Cut each garlic clove into 6 slices. Cut lemon peel crosswise into twelve 1–inch long strips. Cut 12 small slits in top of pork; place a garlic slice and a lemon peel strip in each slit.
bbb75069-f749-47c4-a3a5-fdfe97ba993f ADD potatoes and seasoned salt to bowl with remaining olive oil and herb mixture.Stir to coat potatoes. Arrange potatoes in an even layer around pork.
bbb75069-f749-47c4-a3a5-fdfe97ba993f BAKE 30 to 35 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 160°F. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
bbb75069-f749-47c4-a3a5-fdfe97ba993f REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIPS:To line pan, flip pan upside down. Press a sheet of foil around pan. Remove foil. Flip pan upright and drop foil inside. Crimp edges to rim of pan. Fresh herbs can be substituted for dried. Use 1 tablespoon fresh herbs for each teaspoon dried herbs.
886eb1ce-cbed-4df7-8f7d-e957a3a0afa4 In large bowl, beat sugar and shortening with electric mixer on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, until well blended. Beat in milk, vanilla and eggs. On low speed, beat in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt, scraping bowl occasionally, until dough forms. Stir in pecans, dates and 1/3 cup chopped cherries. If necessary, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate minutes for easier handling.
886eb1ce-cbed-4df7-8f7d-e957a3a0afa4 Heat oven to 375°F. Line cookie sheets with parchment paper. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into cereal; coat thoroughly. Shape into balls. Place inches apart on cookie sheets. Lightly press maraschino cherry quarter into top of each ball.
886eb1ce-cbed-4df7-8f7d-e957a3a0afa4 Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool minute; remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks.
aea1d4b3-0ff8-49d7-aa3a-c461558c6bf5 PREHEAT oven to 450°F.
aea1d4b3-0ff8-49d7-aa3a-c461558c6bf5 MIX couscous, seasoning packet, 3/4 cup water, mushrooms and almonds.
aea1d4b3-0ff8-49d7-aa3a-c461558c6bf5 CENTER one-fourth of couscous mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side facing up. Top with a salmon fillet. Sprinkle salmon with ginger; drizzle with sesame oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with chopped green onion and 3 mushroom slices.
aea1d4b3-0ff8-49d7-aa3a-c461558c6bf5 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and one end of packet. Through open end, add one-fourth of remaining water. Double fold remaining end to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets. Place packets on a cookie sheet.
aea1d4b3-0ff8-49d7-aa3a-c461558c6bf5 BAKE 20 to 25 minutes or until salmon is opaque in center.
7c2b9618-f194-4f19-b056-fc94cba40249 Heat oven to 350°F and place rack in center. Line baking sheets with Reynolds KITCHENS™ Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®.
7c2b9618-f194-4f19-b056-fc94cba40249 In a 2-quart saucepan combine chocolates and butter. Heat and stir over low heat until smooth. Remove from heat. Let cool for 10 minutes.
7c2b9618-f194-4f19-b056-fc94cba40249 In a small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Set aside.
7c2b9618-f194-4f19-b056-fc94cba40249 In a large mixing bowl combine sugars and eggs. Beat with an electric mixer on medium high speed for 2 to 3 minutes or until color lightens slightly. Beat in melted chocolate. Add flour mixture to chocolate mixture; heat until combined. Stir in pecans. Cover surface of cookie dough with plastic wrap. Let stand for 20 minutes (dough thickens as it stands).
7c2b9618-f194-4f19-b056-fc94cba40249 On your lined cookie sheets, drop dough by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart. Bake in the preheated oven about 9 minutes or just until tops are set. Let stand for 1 minute on cookie sheet and then transfer to a wire rack to let cool.
7c2b9618-f194-4f19-b056-fc94cba40249 FOR FILLING: In a large mixer bowl, sprinkle gelatin over color water and let stand until softened, about 5 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, combine sugar and water. Stir over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves. Using a pastry brush dipped in water, brush down sugar crystals on the sides of pan. Place a candy thermometer into mixture. Boil (do not stir) until syrup registers 238°F (soft-ball stage), about 10 minutes. Pour into gelatin. Using the whisk attachment, beat gelatin mixture on medium-low speed until slightly cooked, about 5 minutes. Increase speed to medium-high and beat to soft peaks, about 12 minutes. Tint with food coloring (if desired). Use immediately. Makes 4 cups.
7c2b9618-f194-4f19-b056-fc94cba40249 Spread 2 teaspoons of the filling on the bottoms of half of the cookies. Top with remaining cookies, bottom sides together. Roll edges of cookie sandwiches in additional sprinkles, if desired. Makes 60 cookies.
103fd75c-3f35-412a-bb0e-dcb883d2ca7f PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
103fd75c-3f35-412a-bb0e-dcb883d2ca7f CENTER one chicken breast half on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Spoon barbecue sauce over chicken. Top with vegetables. BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
103fd75c-3f35-412a-bb0e-dcb883d2ca7f BAKE 18 to 22 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR GRILL 12 to 15 minutes in covered grill.
a0dc31ca-6b17-40ea-bf11-76683b968b66 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high. Cut steak lengthwise in half and then crosswise into 1/8-inch thick strips. Sprinkle steak strips with salt and pepper; set aside.
a0dc31ca-6b17-40ea-bf11-76683b968b66 CENTER one-fourth of onions on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Top with steak strips and cheese.
a0dc31ca-6b17-40ea-bf11-76683b968b66 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
a0dc31ca-6b17-40ea-bf11-76683b968b66 COOK packets for 10-18 minutes or until meat reaches desired doneness. Serve on hoagie-style buns with ketchup or steak sauce.
0c56555f-1ee9-4249-97a0-f802bd361ae3 PREHEAT oven to 400°F.
0c56555f-1ee9-4249-97a0-f802bd361ae3 TEAR off four 15-inch sheets of Reynolds Parchment Paper. Fold each parchment sheet in half.
0c56555f-1ee9-4249-97a0-f802bd361ae3 UNFOLD each parchment sheet. Place 1/4 of shrimp on each sheet near fold. Mix olive oil, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Top shrimp with 1/4 of olive oil mixture and 2 lemon slices.
0c56555f-1ee9-4249-97a0-f802bd361ae3 FOLD over other half of each parchment sheet to enclose ingredients. To seal edges together, start at the top corner, making small overlapping folds down entire length of package. At the end of the package, twist the last fold several times to make a tight seal. Repeat to make 4 packages. Place parchment packages on a large cookie sheet.
0c56555f-1ee9-4249-97a0-f802bd361ae3 BAKE 13 to 15 minutes. While packages are baking, toss pasta with Parmesan cheese, sundried tomatoes, olive oil and parsley. Place cooked parchment packages on one side of dinner plates. Carefully cut an X in top of each package to allow steam to escape. Serve immediately with pasta on other half of plate.
7b84e18e-e5f5-4eac-9b2d-bf2fd530d02d PREHEAT Oven to 375°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil.
7b84e18e-e5f5-4eac-9b2d-bf2fd530d02d MOLD 4-6 foil block molds to hold and shape taco shells. Molds should be approx. 4” tall x 5”wide.
7b84e18e-e5f5-4eac-9b2d-bf2fd530d02d FLATTEN each biscuit dough piece into circular a disk about ¼-inch thick. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
7b84e18e-e5f5-4eac-9b2d-bf2fd530d02d DRAPE dough over foil molds and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until shells are golden. Cool for 10 minutes before removing shells from foil mold.
7b84e18e-e5f5-4eac-9b2d-bf2fd530d02d FILL with fresh fruit and favorite dessert toppings and serve immediately.
d643d129-280c-4022-8264-f123718f5b77 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line a baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil.
d643d129-280c-4022-8264-f123718f5b77 MOLD 4-6 foil block molds to hold and shape taco shells. Molds should be approximately 4” tall x 5” wide. Set aside.
d643d129-280c-4022-8264-f123718f5b77 COMBINE all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly to combine.
d643d129-280c-4022-8264-f123718f5b77 PLACE 1/4 cup of the zucchini mixture onto the foil, then use your hand to flatten into a disk.
d643d129-280c-4022-8264-f123718f5b77 BAKE 15 to 20 minutes or until shells are solid and pliable.
d643d129-280c-4022-8264-f123718f5b77 LINE a baking sheet with foil and place foil block molds on top. Drape shells over foil blocks. Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until shells are crisp. Cool for 10 minutes before removing shells from foil mold.
d643d129-280c-4022-8264-f123718f5b77 FILL with favorite taco fillings and serve immediately.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 COMBINE eggs, lemon, lemon juice and sugar in a large metal bowl and place over a pot of simmering water to create a double boiler.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 WHISK the mixture until it becomes thick to form a lemon curd (about 7 to 9 minutes). Be sure to hold the bowl with a thick towel to prevent burning your hand.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 REMOVE the bowl from the heat and whisk in the cold butter until it is combined.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 TRANSFER the lemon curd to a bowl and cover with foil and place in the refrigerator until it has completely cooled.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 PLACE the flour, sugar and butter into a food processor and pulse until the butter is the size of a small pea.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 ADD in the egg, vanilla and water and pulse until just combined.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 PLACE the dough onto a flour-dusted surface and roll out until the dough is 1/8 inches thick.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 TRANSFER the dough into Reynolds® Bakeware pie pan and form until it fits. Trim off any access dough and pierce the dough all over the bottom of the pan using a fork.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 PLACE a sheet of foil over the pie dough and press down until it has formed to the pie shell and bake in the oven on 350° for 25 minutes. Cool completely.
da356e63-3b42-4ea5-bea2-ce14dc4eba44 POUR the chilled lemon curd into the cooled pie crust and pour on the mixed berries and chill before serving.
dc1a1778-b94e-42e1-ad0a-5308b06e3f5e In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, light brown sugar, and granulated sugar. Stir well with a fork, breaking up the brown sugar if needed with your fingertips. Add the butter, and work it in with your fingers, until it looks clumpy, and is moist throughout. Add the oats and nuts, and work into the crumble. Chill until ready to use.
dc1a1778-b94e-42e1-ad0a-5308b06e3f5e Heat one side of a gas grill to medium low. Keeping one side off will moderate the heat. You don’t want the grill to be too hot.
dc1a1778-b94e-42e1-ad0a-5308b06e3f5e Tear off four 12” to 4” inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil and fold each in half. Roll the edges once or twice.
dc1a1778-b94e-42e1-ad0a-5308b06e3f5e Combine the fruit, lemon juice, and sugar in a medium bowl. Divide among the pieces of foil. Add 1 tsp butter to each one. Crimp the ends of the foil. If the fruit doesn’t look very juicy, add 1 tablespoon water to each packet, and close the top without crimping. Slide packets onto a baking sheet.
dc1a1778-b94e-42e1-ad0a-5308b06e3f5e Using tongs, slide the packets onto the hot side of the grill, and close the lid. If your grill has a temperature gauge, aim to keep it at 375°F-400°F. Cook for 10 minutes, then slide the packets back to the baking sheet. Open the top of each packet, and sprinkle on a scant ¼ cup of the topping. Slide back onto the grill, and continue cooking for 15-20 minutes, until fruit is bubbling and topping is golden brown.
f204af23-9086-4ad4-be7a-7e7b6f31dc04 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
f204af23-9086-4ad4-be7a-7e7b6f31dc04 COMBINE cherries, pickles, 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring frequently until mixture starts to thicken and bubble, about 5 minutes.
f204af23-9086-4ad4-be7a-7e7b6f31dc04 REMOVE from heat and transfer mixture to an 8x8-inch Reynolds® Bakeware Pan; set aside.
f204af23-9086-4ad4-be7a-7e7b6f31dc04 CUT biscuits into quarters, and then roll each into balls. Combine remaining 1 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
f204af23-9086-4ad4-be7a-7e7b6f31dc04 PLACE biscuit dough in butter, and then roll in cinnamon sugar. Place on top of cherry mixture. Repeat with remaining biscuits, fully covering cherries.
f204af23-9086-4ad4-be7a-7e7b6f31dc04 BAKE 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are lightly browned and mixture is bubbling. Cool for 1 hour before serving.
94bc43dd-22ad-4a1f-aa00-d83deeab8f9f MELT chocolate over stove or in microwave.
94bc43dd-22ad-4a1f-aa00-d83deeab8f9f BLOT pickles with paper towel.
94bc43dd-22ad-4a1f-aa00-d83deeab8f9f DIP in to melted chocolate and place on Reynolds KITCHENS® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®.
94bc43dd-22ad-4a1f-aa00-d83deeab8f9f TRANSFER to refrigerator until chocolate has set.
94bc43dd-22ad-4a1f-aa00-d83deeab8f9f PLACE dipped pickle on graham cracker square, top with marshmallow crème.
94bc43dd-22ad-4a1f-aa00-d83deeab8f9f ADD additional graham cracker to sandwich.
37fa95b9-a0f3-4826-8155-ee02382dbe0a PREHEAT oven to 350° F.
37fa95b9-a0f3-4826-8155-ee02382dbe0a PLACE six Reynolds® Foil Baking Cups on a sheet tray.
37fa95b9-a0f3-4826-8155-ee02382dbe0a MIX onion, Worcestershire sauce, oregano, tomato paste, chicken broth, salt and garlic until combined. ADD whisked egg to mixture and combine.
37fa95b9-a0f3-4826-8155-ee02382dbe0a ADD turkey breast and bread crumbs to the mixture and, using yours hands, work the meatloaf until all the ingredients are fully incorporated.
37fa95b9-a0f3-4826-8155-ee02382dbe0a BALL mixture into six even loaves and place in baking cups.
37fa95b9-a0f3-4826-8155-ee02382dbe0a BRUSH each meatloaf with desired amount of ketchup.
37fa95b9-a0f3-4826-8155-ee02382dbe0a COOK meatloaf cupcakes for 25 to 30 minutes until the internal temperature of the meatloaves reach 165° F.
