37fa95b9-a0f3-4826-8155-ee02382dbe0a SERVE warm.
a43ab8d7-5ffc-4f13-a574-9e6882f84f65 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line 2 cookie sheets with Reynolds KITCHENS® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® set aside.
a43ab8d7-5ffc-4f13-a574-9e6882f84f65 COMBINE flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl; set aside. Beat butter and sugar on medium speed of a mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, until blended. Gradually stir in the flour mixture.
a43ab8d7-5ffc-4f13-a574-9e6882f84f65 FOLD in pecans and 1 cup M&M'S Mint Chocolate Candies for the Holidays.
a43ab8d7-5ffc-4f13-a574-9e6882f84f65 DROP heaping teaspoons of dough onto parchment-lined cookie sheets. Place extra reserved M&M'S on top of each cookie before baking, press lightly.
a43ab8d7-5ffc-4f13-a574-9e6882f84f65 BAKE 12 to 15 minutes.
2aed6301-49a3-4b64-941c-23bad25eaf40 Place chopsticks on a flat surface and place 1 red potato between the chopsticks. Using a sharp knife, slice up the red potato into thin slices and be careful not to cut all the way through.
2aed6301-49a3-4b64-941c-23bad25eaf40 Once cut, carefully fan out the slices using your fingers to release steam. Spray the potato with water OR rinse it under cold water.
2aed6301-49a3-4b64-941c-23bad25eaf40 Tear off a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil, then place then sliced potato in the middle. Wrap up the potato to make a dome shape (or “steam chamber”). Repeat for the other potato.
2aed6301-49a3-4b64-941c-23bad25eaf40 Cook on the grill or in the oven for at least 50 minutes OR until the potato is fully cooked.
2aed6301-49a3-4b64-941c-23bad25eaf40 Peel back the foil and top with shredded cheese Place back on the grill for an additional 5 to 7 minutes to completely melt the cheese.
d50f93d6-529b-4ba7-a313-5acb31775145 Preheat the grill to high heat.
d50f93d6-529b-4ba7-a313-5acb31775145 Make foil packets. Tear off 2 18” sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
d50f93d6-529b-4ba7-a313-5acb31775145 In a medium bowl combine the zucchini, tomatoes, garlic, 2 teaspoons of the olive oil, 1/4 teaspoon salt and black pepper to taste.
d50f93d6-529b-4ba7-a313-5acb31775145 Place 10 clams on the center of each foil sheet. Divide the vegetables, then top with crushed red pepper flakes. Drizzle the remaining 1/2 teaspoon oil over each and 1/2 tablespoon wine over both.
d50f93d6-529b-4ba7-a313-5acb31775145 Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet over the food. Double fold the ends, leaving room for heat to circulate inside. Double fold the two short ends to seal the packet tight, so no steam escapes.
d50f93d6-529b-4ba7-a313-5acb31775145 Grill covered over high heat, until the clams open, 8 to 10 minutes. Use gloves or tongs to remove and carefully open.
9f259e49-08e6-48e3-bccf-e3c1124bf9c7 Whisk the grated garlic, salt, oil in a medium bowl. Add shrimp, toss to coat, and chill, uncovered, at least 30 minutes and up to 1 hour.
9f259e49-08e6-48e3-bccf-e3c1124bf9c7 Make foil packets. Tear off 4 16” sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
9f259e49-08e6-48e3-bccf-e3c1124bf9c7 Place 10 shrimp on the center of each foil sheet. Top each with remaining garlic slices, 1 tablespoon wine, lemon juice, pinch red pepper flakes and 1/2 tablespoon melted butter over each.
9f259e49-08e6-48e3-bccf-e3c1124bf9c7 Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet over the food. Double fold the ends, leaving room for heat to circulate inside. Double fold the two short ends to seal the packet.
9f259e49-08e6-48e3-bccf-e3c1124bf9c7 Grill over high heat, 8 minutes. Use gloves or tongs to remove and carefully open. Top with chopped parsley. Serve with lemon wedges.
ea8f1939-1820-429c-a784-988cd8a269a4 Heat gas or charcoal grill.
ea8f1939-1820-429c-a784-988cd8a269a4 In a saucepan set over medium heat, mix the shredded chicken with the bottle of BBQ sauce. Once the mixture gets warm, remove from heat.
ea8f1939-1820-429c-a784-988cd8a269a4 Tear 4-6 pieces of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil into 18” sections. With the non-stick side facing up, fold all 4 of the edges into the center, making walls to form small foil trays. The final size being approximately 8” x 6”.
ea8f1939-1820-429c-a784-988cd8a269a4 Fill each tray with a handful of tortilla chips. Sprinkle the chips evenly with half of the cheese.
ea8f1939-1820-429c-a784-988cd8a269a4 Add the BBQ chicken in small pieces, followed by the pineapple, red onion and jalapeño. Top with remaining cheese and place foil trays directly on the grill until the cheese is melted and the outer chips are starting to brown. About 5-10 minutes depending on the grill.
ea8f1939-1820-429c-a784-988cd8a269a4 Carefully remove nachos from the grill with a glove or metal spatula and top with avocado, cilantro and green onions.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Preheat oven to 325°F and place a rack in the center of the oven. Line a 9×5-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and set aside.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Whisk together flour, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl. Set aside.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Cream together softened butter and cream cheese in the bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment. Stop the mixer occasionally to scrape down the bowl and make sure that the butter and cream cheese are evenly mixed. Add the sugar to the butter and cream cheese mixture, and beat on medium speed until smooth and creamy, about 3 minutes.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Beat in one egg at a time, mixing for one minute after each addition. Stop the mixer and scrape down the sides of the bowl as necessary. Beat in vanilla extract.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Add dry ingredients all at once. Beat on low speed until dry ingredients are completely incorporated. Spoon batter into prepared pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, rotating once or twice during baking. Bake until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean or with just a few crumbs. Allow cake to cool in the pan for 15 minutes before inverting onto a wire rack to cool to room temperature. Wrap the cooled cake and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Slice the chilled pound cake into 8 thick slices.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Toss the strawberries together with the sugar in a small bowl. Allow to rest at room temperature for 20 minutes.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Whip the heavy cream with powdered sugar, salt and vanilla until soft peaks form. Set aside.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Grill the slices of pound cake over a warm, greased grill until golden brown grill marks appear on both sides of cake, flipping once.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Warm the strawberries on the grill by spooning strawberries among 8 Jumbo Reynolds® Aluminum Foil Baking Cups and warming alongside the pound cake.
92ee7826-3acd-41c7-8f38-63380e520b16 Serve warm pound cake slices with warmed strawberries and sweet cream.
bbdf2fb2-1e97-4c81-916c-dca2d7b34ad6 BRUSH chicken thighs with 2 tablespoons olive oil and transfer to a resealable plastic bag. Combine paprika, garam masala, cumin, cayenne pepper, garlic powder and salt in a small bowl. Reserve 1 teaspoon of spice mixture. Pour remaining spice mixture over the chicken thighs. Seal bag and shake until chicken is fully coated.
bbdf2fb2-1e97-4c81-916c-dca2d7b34ad6 PREHEAT grill to 425°F. Center seasoned chicken thighs evenly on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Bring up foil sides. Double-fold top and ends to seal, making one large packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
bbdf2fb2-1e97-4c81-916c-dca2d7b34ad6 GRILL 20 minutes in covered grill, or until chicken is tender and juices run clear or meat thermometer reads 165°F. Let chicken cool slightly, then shred chicken using two forks.
bbdf2fb2-1e97-4c81-916c-dca2d7b34ad6 CENTER each piece of naan bread evenly on an 8x8-inch sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Brush with remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil. Top each evenly with shredded chicken, onion, cherry tomatoes, garlic and mozzarella. Grill 10 minutes in covered grill over indirect heat.
bbdf2fb2-1e97-4c81-916c-dca2d7b34ad6 COMBINE yogurt, lemon juice and reserved spice mixture. Mix thoroughly to combine. Drizzle over top of each cooked pizza. Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve immediately.
092f1c55-5941-4d01-9ebb-e177d68e4f34 PREHEAT grill to 425°F. Pat shrimp dry with a paper towel and set aside. Whisk together egg and 1/2 cup coconut milk and set aside. Combine shredded coconut and panko breadcrumbs in a shallow bowl and set aside. Combine cornstarch, salt and pepper in a shallow bowl and set aside.
092f1c55-5941-4d01-9ebb-e177d68e4f34 PLACE 4 sheets Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side facing up onto your work surface.
092f1c55-5941-4d01-9ebb-e177d68e4f34 DIP shrimp into cornstarch mixture, then dip into egg mixture, then coat in the coconut/panko breadcrumb mixture. Repeat with all shrimp, placing an equal amount of coated shrimp on each piece of foil.
092f1c55-5941-4d01-9ebb-e177d68e4f34 BRING up foil sides and fold over to create a 2-inch rim. Repeat to make 4 open packets.
092f1c55-5941-4d01-9ebb-e177d68e4f34 GRILL 10 to 12 minutes in covered grill, or until coconut is golden and until shrimp is firm and pink.
092f1c55-5941-4d01-9ebb-e177d68e4f34 COMBINE lime juice and remaining 1/2 cup coconut milk. Drizzle over cooked shrimp just before serving.
f0b8db8e-d237-4c03-ba75-b9618b486b8d PREHEAT grill to 400°F. COMBINE potatoes, onion and garlic in a large bowl. Drizzle on oil and set aside. Combine curry powder, cumin, chili powder and turmeric. Pour spice mixture over potato mixture. Stir evenly to fully coat.
f0b8db8e-d237-4c03-ba75-b9618b486b8d CENTER potatoes evenly in a single layer on a 12x24-inch sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
f0b8db8e-d237-4c03-ba75-b9618b486b8d BRING up foil sides. Double-fold top and ends to seal, making one large foil packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
f0b8db8e-d237-4c03-ba75-b9618b486b8d GRILL 15 to 20 minutes in covered grill, or until potatoes are tender. Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve immediately.
53586298-953d-4ae4-8370-99f37fc9b9ad COMBINE 1/3 cup olive oil, lime juice, chili powder, brown sugar, cumin, paprika and garlic powder in a large resealable plastic bag. Mix thoroughly to combine. Add chicken tenders and fully coat. Transfer to refrigerator and marinate for 2 hours.
53586298-953d-4ae4-8370-99f37fc9b9ad PREHEAT grill to 425°F. Combine red pepper, yellow pepper, onion, jalapeño and corn in a large bowl. Drizzle with remaining olive oil and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
53586298-953d-4ae4-8370-99f37fc9b9ad CENTER one-fourth pepper mixture evenly on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Place two marinated chicken tenders on top pepper mixture.
53586298-953d-4ae4-8370-99f37fc9b9ad BRING up foil sides. Double-fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
53586298-953d-4ae4-8370-99f37fc9b9ad GRILL 15 to 20 minutes in covered grill, or until chicken is chicken is tender and juices run clear or meat thermometer reads 165°F.
f9760ede-a028-4367-b3f6-9282e2756016 COMBINE jackfruit, 1 cup of barbecue sauce and water in a large saucepan. Stir thoroughly to combine. Simmer over medium heat, covered, stirring occasionally, until liquid has reduced, about 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in remaining 1/2 cup of barbecue sauce. Using two forks, pull apart the jackfruit into shreds. Set aside.
f9760ede-a028-4367-b3f6-9282e2756016 PREHEAT grill to 400 °F. Place a 12-by-18-inch sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil on your work surface with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Spread corn chips on top, leaving a 2-inch border around the edge of the foil. Cover chips with shredded jackfruit, then top with cheese, black beans, tomatoes, sweet corn, red onion and jalapeños.
f9760ede-a028-4367-b3f6-9282e2756016 PLACE a second 12-by-18-inch sheet of foil on top with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Double fold the sides and each end to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Transfer to grill and cook over indirect heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
f9760ede-a028-4367-b3f6-9282e2756016 REMOVE from grill. Open packets carefully by cutting along top with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape, then open top of foil packet. Garnish with sour cream and cilantro before serving.
76057447-fa59-4ecb-814c-7acb6fe3ab67 Char both sides of the tortillas on a hot griddle or over the open flame. Keep warmed in the oven if eating right away. This will help the tortillas become more pliable and also improves the taste.
76057447-fa59-4ecb-814c-7acb6fe3ab67 Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add the bacon and cook until cooked through, about 4 to 5 minutes. Transfer with a slotted spoon to drain on a paper towel-lined plate.
76057447-fa59-4ecb-814c-7acb6fe3ab67 In a large bowl, whisk the eggs with salt. Mix in scallions and bell pepper.
76057447-fa59-4ecb-814c-7acb6fe3ab67 Discard the bacon grease leaving 1 teaspoon then add the eggs, let them set on the bottom then stir a few times to cook through, set aside.
76057447-fa59-4ecb-814c-7acb6fe3ab67 On a clean work surface, divide a generous 1/2 cup of the egg mixture onto the bottom third of the tortilla. Top each with a slice of bacon and 2 tablespoons cheese. Roll from the bottom, folding the left and right corners in toward the center and continue and roll into a tight cylinder. Set aside, seam-side down, and repeat with remaining tortillas and filling.
76057447-fa59-4ecb-814c-7acb6fe3ab67 If eating right away, heat a skillet over medium heat. When hot, spray the skillet with oil and add the burritos, seam-side down. Cook, covered, until the bottoms of the burritos are golden brown, about 2 minutes on each side. Serve with hot sauce or salsa, if desired.
76057447-fa59-4ecb-814c-7acb6fe3ab67 HOW TO FREEZE FOR MEAL PREP: (1) Place the foil on a work surface vertically, place the rolled burrito in the center bottom third, roll partially, folding the sides of the foil over the burritos, then roll it up. (2) Transfer to a freezer bag to prevent freezer burn. (3) Use a sharpie to label it with the name, date and cook time/temperature to reheat.
76057447-fa59-4ecb-814c-7acb6fe3ab67 HOW TO HEAT FROZEN BURRITOS: (1) To reheat, thawed overnight in the refrigerator: Transfer burrito to the refrigerator the night before. Bake in foil, in a preheated oven 425°F for 20 minutes, turning halfway. Unwrap foil and bake uncovered 5 minutes. Optional, you can also broil 2 to 3 minutes at the end to toast. (2) To reheat direct from freezer to oven: Bake in a preheated oven 425°F for 45 minutes turning halfway. Unwrap foil and bake uncovered 5 minutes. Optional, you can also broil 2 to 3 minutes at the end to toast. Let stand 2 minutes before eating. (3) To reheat direct from freezer to microwave: Remove the burrito from the foil and place on a microwave safe dish, cover with a paper towel and microwave 1 minute. Turn then cook an additional 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Let stand 2 minutes before eating. Optional, brown on a skillet 2 minutes on each side to toast, or broil 2 to 3 minutes. (4)To reheat in air fryer, thawed overnight in the refrigerator: Transfer burrito to the refrigerator the night before. Unwrap and discard foil, spritz with a little oil and air fry in a preheated air fryer 400°F for 8 to 9 minutes, turning halfway until heated through in the center.
02f35c41-f94c-4b65-be1b-9a286f72ee9a Preheat oven to 400°F.
02f35c41-f94c-4b65-be1b-9a286f72ee9a Slice each croissant in half. Spread the inside of the bottom half of the croissant with 1 ounce cream cheese. Top with one slice of swiss cheese, then 1/4 of the ham and top with another slice of swiss cheese. Repeat for all 4 sandwiches.
02f35c41-f94c-4b65-be1b-9a286f72ee9a Wrap each sandwich in Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and place on a baking sheet.
02f35c41-f94c-4b65-be1b-9a286f72ee9a Bake for 10 minutes until the cheese is melted and the ham is heated through.
02f35c41-f94c-4b65-be1b-9a286f72ee9a Serve dusted with powdered sugar and dipped in raspberry jam.
eb33f950-7cff-4927-a57e-76f7f4ab5682 Preheat oven to 425°F. Add baby potatoes to a large pot of boiling water and cook for about 10 minutes or until softened.
eb33f950-7cff-4927-a57e-76f7f4ab5682 Add corn to boiling water and cook for a few minutes until the color brightens. Remove from water and set aside.
eb33f950-7cff-4927-a57e-76f7f4ab5682 Cut corn into 2-inch-long pieces and cut sausage into thick slices.
eb33f950-7cff-4927-a57e-76f7f4ab5682 Remove shells from shrimp and devein.
eb33f950-7cff-4927-a57e-76f7f4ab5682 Add potatoes, corn, shrimp and sausage to a large bowl. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with seasoning. Toss well.
eb33f950-7cff-4927-a57e-76f7f4ab5682 Cut 16-inch-long sections of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil and place about 2 cups or so of the shrimp mixture onto a section of foil. Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet over the food. Double fold the end, leaving room for heat to circulate inside. Double fold the remaining sides so the pouch is sealed. Repeat process for the remaining material.
eb33f950-7cff-4927-a57e-76f7f4ab5682 Place on a baking sheet and bake at 425°F for about 10 minutes.
eb33f950-7cff-4927-a57e-76f7f4ab5682 Mince parsley. Melt butter with 1/2 tsp of the Cajun seasoning. Serve sprinkled with parsley and drizzled with butter.
86ca9381-ad39-454a-812f-dff22f9dc2d2 Preheat oven to 375°F.
86ca9381-ad39-454a-812f-dff22f9dc2d2 In a large mixing bowl beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add sugars, baking soda, and salt. Beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Beat in eggs and vanilla until combined. Beat in as much of the flour as you can with the mixer. Stir in any remaining flour. Stir in chocolate pieces and cherries.
86ca9381-ad39-454a-812f-dff22f9dc2d2 Drop dough by tablespoons 2 inches apart onto cookie sheets lined with Reynolds KITCHENS® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®. The gridlines make spacing easy!
86ca9381-ad39-454a-812f-dff22f9dc2d2 Bake for 9 minutes.
86ca9381-ad39-454a-812f-dff22f9dc2d2 Transfer to racks and allow to cool.
8f90f16c-a35e-4d40-ac9e-65fe0953e976 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Tear off four 15-inch sheets of Reynolds KITCHENS® Unbleached Parchment Paper. Fold each sheet in half and crease it in center. Unfold.
8f90f16c-a35e-4d40-ac9e-65fe0953e976 PLACE 1 catfish fillet on one-half of each sheet near crease. Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon Cajun seasoning evenly over each fillet.
8f90f16c-a35e-4d40-ac9e-65fe0953e976 COMBINE remaining ingredients and remaining Cajun seasoning; spoon mixture evenly around fillet in each packet.
8f90f16c-a35e-4d40-ac9e-65fe0953e976 FOLD over other half of sheet to enclose ingredients. Starting at top corner, make small overlapping folds down entire length of packet to seal edges together. Twist the last fold several times to make a tight seal. Repeat to make 4 packets. Place parchment packets on large cookie sheet.
8f90f16c-a35e-4d40-ac9e-65fe0953e976 BAKE to minutes. Place parchment packets on dinner plates. Carefully cut an X in top of each packet to allow steam to escape. Garnish with cilantro, if desired. Serve immediately.
8ba185ce-cc5a-49e8-ab7f-6800d95de1b9 Line a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds KITCHENS™ Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl; set aside.
8ba185ce-cc5a-49e8-ab7f-6800d95de1b9 Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high until shimmering. Sprinkle pork evenly with salt. Add pork to skillet; cook, turning occasionally, until browned on all sides, about 15 minutes.
8ba185ce-cc5a-49e8-ab7f-6800d95de1b9 While pork browns, stir together coconut milk, garlic, ginger, 1 tablespoon of the curry paste, and sugar in slow cooker until thoroughly combined. Add greens; toss to coat using tongs.
8ba185ce-cc5a-49e8-ab7f-6800d95de1b9 Nestle browned pork on top of collard greens mixture in slow cooker. Cover and cook on LOW until pork is tender, about 7 hours. Using tongs, remove pork from cooker. Let cool 15 minutes. Using 2 forks or your hands, remove bone and shred pork into large pieces. While pork cools, stir in lime juice and remaining 1 tablespoon curry paste into collard mixture.
8ba185ce-cc5a-49e8-ab7f-6800d95de1b9 Return shredded pork to slow cooker. Divide stew among 4 large bowls. Sprinkle evenly with chiles.
891bba47-b029-4d56-a750-8028b558f48d Line a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds KITCHENS™ Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
891bba47-b029-4d56-a750-8028b558f48d Stir together chicken broth, hominy, salsa, chiles, oregano and salt in slow cooker. Add chicken to stock mixture; submerge in liquid. Cover and cook on LOW until chicken is tender, about 7 hours. Using a slotted spoon, remove chicken from cooker. Let cool 10 minutes. Using 2 forks or your hands, remove bones and shred chicken into large pieces. Discard bones.
891bba47-b029-4d56-a750-8028b558f48d Return chicken to slow cooker. Divide soup among 4 large bowls. Top with tortilla strips, cilantro, avocado, radishes, and lime wedges.
90e5d57a-0664-47dc-979a-037a7074043a Store your brisket in the refrigerator until you are ready to start trimming. Cold briskets are much easier to work with. Flip your brisket over so the point end is underneath. Remove any silver skin or excess fat from the flat muscle. Trim down the large crescent moon-shaped fat section until it is a smooth transition between the point and the flat. Trim excessive or loose meat and fat from the point. Square the edges and ends of the flat. Flip the brisket over and trim the top fat cap to about 1/4 of an inch thickness across the surface of the brisket.
90e5d57a-0664-47dc-979a-037a7074043a In a mixing bowl or empty spice container, mix the salt, pepper and garlic. Shake over the brisket to evenly distribute the spices on all sides.
90e5d57a-0664-47dc-979a-037a7074043a Preheat your smoker to 225 degrees F using indirect heat and hardwood smoke. Place the brisket on the smoker with the point end facing your main heat source. This is a thicker part of the brisket and it can handle the additional heat. Close the lid and smoke until an internal thermometer reads 165 degrees F (usually takes around 8 hours).
90e5d57a-0664-47dc-979a-037a7074043a On a large work surface, roll out a big piece of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil and center your brisket in the middle. Wrap the brisket by folding edge over edge, creating a leak-proof seal all the way around. Return the wrapped brisket to the smoker, seam-side down so the weight from the brisket crimps the edges of the foil down tightly.
90e5d57a-0664-47dc-979a-037a7074043a Close the lid on the smoker and, maintaining 225 degrees F, continue cooking until the internal temperature of the brisket reaches 202 degrees F in the thickest part of the meat (takes anywhere from 5 to 8 hours).
90e5d57a-0664-47dc-979a-037a7074043a Remove the brisket to a large cutting board and allow to rest for 1 hour before slicing. Slice both the point and the flat against the grain with a sharp knife and serve immediately.
5d99c337-88ac-4b65-8132-836adbe41426 Prepare the crust: Add water to a large bowl. Stir in sugar, then sprinkle in yeast. Allow to rest 5 minutes until foamy. Whisk in salt and oil.
5d99c337-88ac-4b65-8132-836adbe41426 Using a wooden spoon, stir in flour. Flour a clean, flat surface and transfer dough to this space. Knead for 2-3 minutes until dough becomes elastic. Brush all over with oil, place in a medium bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and place in a warm place until doubled in size, about 45 minutes. Punch down, cover and allow to rise for another 30 minutes.
5d99c337-88ac-4b65-8132-836adbe41426 Roll dough out to into a large circle 1/4-inch thick.
5d99c337-88ac-4b65-8132-836adbe41426 Brush dough with olive oil and sprinkle with Italian seasoning. Place on a 16-inch piece of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and transfer to a preheated grill. Close the grill and cook for 5 minutes, flip over to cook on the other side for 5 minutes. If crust is browning too quickly, move it an area of the grill where it will not be directly over the flames.
5d99c337-88ac-4b65-8132-836adbe41426 Flip back over so the oiled side is up and drizzle half of the barbecue sauce on top. Top with mozzarella, chicken, garlic, onions and jalapeños. Cook another 10 minutes.
5d99c337-88ac-4b65-8132-836adbe41426 Top with remaining barbecue sauce, cotija cheese and cilantro. Cut into slices and serve.
ee3317b4-18b9-4179-8412-e081eeb9c521 Stir together your honey garlic sauce: honey, soy sauce, garlic and vinegar. Pour half of the sauce mixture into a large freezer bag with chicken thighs and marinate for 30–60 minutes, or overnight if desired. Refrigerate remaining sauce.
ee3317b4-18b9-4179-8412-e081eeb9c521 Preheat oven to 375 degrees F and line a rimmed baking sheet with a Reynolds Kitchens® Pop-Up Parchment Sheet.
ee3317b4-18b9-4179-8412-e081eeb9c521 Place chicken thighs on one side of the Reynolds Kitchens® Pop-Up Parchment Sheet. Stir together salt, pepper and garlic powder. Season chicken thighs with salt mixture, reserving some for the vegetables (you’ll use about 1/3–1/2).
ee3317b4-18b9-4179-8412-e081eeb9c521 Add potatoes and green beans to a medium bowl. Toss with oil and remaining salt mixture until well coated. Place vegetables on the other side of the Reynolds Kitchens® Pop-Up Parchment Sheet.
ee3317b4-18b9-4179-8412-e081eeb9c521 Bake for 30 minutes at 375 degrees F.
ee3317b4-18b9-4179-8412-e081eeb9c521 Meanwhile, pour remaining sauce mixture into a small saucepan and whisk in corn starch. Bring to a simmer over medium heat, cooking and whisking until thickened.
ee3317b4-18b9-4179-8412-e081eeb9c521 Remove sheet pan from oven and brush chicken with thickened sauce. Bake for 5 more minutes, until chicken reaches an internal temperature of at least 165 degrees F and vegetables are tender.
849e2d00-ace8-4e8f-a6e7-f534be760d6a Preheat the grill to high heat, covered. Place 4 large 10 x 18-inch pieces of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil on a flat surface. To bake in the oven, preheat oven to 425 degrees F and cook about 25 to 30 minutes.
849e2d00-ace8-4e8f-a6e7-f534be760d6a Place the vegetables in a medium bowl and mix well with olive oil, 3/4 teaspoon salt and black pepper. Divide vegetables between 4 pieces of foil and place in the center of each.
849e2d00-ace8-4e8f-a6e7-f534be760d6a In a medium bowl, combine ground turkey, oatmeal, 3 tablespoons barbecue sauce, onion, egg, 3/4 teaspoon salt and marjoram, mix well. Divide mixture into 4 equal portions. Shape each portion into a 4 x 2½-inch free-form loaf.
849e2d00-ace8-4e8f-a6e7-f534be760d6a Transfer to the Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil over the veggies. Brush the remaining 3 tablespoons of barbecue sauce over the top of the loaves.
849e2d00-ace8-4e8f-a6e7-f534be760d6a Bring up the long sides of the Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil, so the ends meet over the food. Double fold the ends, leaving room for heat to circulate inside. Double fold the two short ends to seal the packet tight, so no steam escapes.
849e2d00-ace8-4e8f-a6e7-f534be760d6a Grill covered on direct heat over the flames for 10 minutes. Move to indirect heat (away from the open flame) until the meatloaf is cooked through in the center, about 20 to 25 minutes.
849e2d00-ace8-4e8f-a6e7-f534be760d6a Use gloves or tongs to remove and carefully open. Serve with more (optional) barbecue sauce on top, if desired.
f4b7a1dc-f76a-49d7-8ec4-6337e7e996f1 Whisk together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.
f4b7a1dc-f76a-49d7-8ec4-6337e7e996f1 In a large bowl, beat butter, cream cheese and 1 1/4 cups sugar until smooth and creamy, 1–2 minutes.
f4b7a1dc-f76a-49d7-8ec4-6337e7e996f1 Mix in vanilla, lemon juice and lemon zest. Beat in egg.
f4b7a1dc-f76a-49d7-8ec4-6337e7e996f1 Slowly add flour mixture, mixing in a little at a time, until just combined.
f4b7a1dc-f76a-49d7-8ec4-6337e7e996f1 Wrap with Reynolds Kitchens® Quick Cut™ Plastic Wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour.
f4b7a1dc-f76a-49d7-8ec4-6337e7e996f1 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F and line a baking sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®.
f4b7a1dc-f76a-49d7-8ec4-6337e7e996f1 Scoop sugar cookie dough into balls and roll in sugar until coated all over.
f4b7a1dc-f76a-49d7-8ec4-6337e7e996f1 Bake cookies 10 minutes, until edges just start to brown.
f4b7a1dc-f76a-49d7-8ec4-6337e7e996f1 Let cookies cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes and move to a wire rack to finish cooling.
816cb6f6-1e07-456a-9929-2fb67b6ebb31 Preheat a grill to medium high. Lay out four 18-inch-long sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil on a work surface. Brush the foil with the olive oil (this will help the enchiladas get crisp on the bottom). Spread 1 tablespoon enchilada sauce in the center of each sheet.
816cb6f6-1e07-456a-9929-2fb67b6ebb31 Combine the chicken, 1 cup cheese, the refried beans, corn, oregano, 2 tablespoons enchilada sauce, a pinch of salt and a few grinds of pepper in a large bowl.
816cb6f6-1e07-456a-9929-2fb67b6ebb31 Stack the tortillas and wrap them in a damp paper towel. Microwave until warm and pliable, 15 to 30 seconds. Lay out the tortillas on a clean surface. Divide the chicken filling among the tortillas (about ¼ cup each) and roll up. Place 3 enchiladas seam-side down on each sheet of foil, arranging them on top of the sauce. Spoon 3 more tablespoons enchilada sauce over each trio of enchiladas, then sprinkle evenly with the remaining 1 cup cheese. Bring the two short ends of the foil together and fold twice to seal; fold in the sides to form a packet.
816cb6f6-1e07-456a-9929-2fb67b6ebb31 Grill the foil packets seam-side up until the cheese has melted and the enchiladas are warmed through and crisp on the bottom, about 7 minutes.
816cb6f6-1e07-456a-9929-2fb67b6ebb31 Meanwhile, heat the remaining enchilada sauce in a small saucepan or in the microwave. Carefully open the foil packets and top with the warm enchilada sauce, sour cream and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges.
d7a9145f-8408-4cd9-bd38-7b170f80e20e Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a 2-quart casserole dish with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil, dull side facing up. Set aside.
d7a9145f-8408-4cd9-bd38-7b170f80e20e Cook the pasta in a large pot according to the package directions; add the broccoli for the last 3 minutes of cooking. Drain in a colander; set aside.
d7a9145f-8408-4cd9-bd38-7b170f80e20e Melt 2 tablespoons butter in the pot over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic; sauté about 5 minutes, until onion is tender. Stir in flour, salt and black pepper. Add the milk all at once. Continue cooking while stirring constantly, until bubbly and slightly thickened. Add cheddar cheese and cream cheese; stir until melted. Stir cooked pasta and broccoli into cheese sauce. Spread evenly in the foil-lined casserole dish.
d7a9145f-8408-4cd9-bd38-7b170f80e20e Melt the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter. Stir melted butter and breadcrumbs in a small bowl until combined. Sprinkle evenly over pasta.
d7a9145f-8408-4cd9-bd38-7b170f80e20e Bake uncovered, about 25 minutes until bubbly and the center of the casserole reaches 165°F. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
d55d55de-d110-48e7-afcc-c641803986d8 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a large baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil, non-stick dull side facing food. In a separate bowl, combine chicken and soup with half of sour cream, cheese and cilantro.
d55d55de-d110-48e7-afcc-c641803986d8 Spoon 1/4 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up. Place, seam-sides down, in foil-lined pan. Top with salsa and remaining cheese. Cover with foil, non-stick dull side facing the food.
d55d55de-d110-48e7-afcc-c641803986d8 Bake for 15 minutes; remove foil. Continue baking 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Top with cilantro and sour cream.
7934f4a6-06cb-4c60-9966-a291fb73f410 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
7934f4a6-06cb-4c60-9966-a291fb73f410 CENTER one-fourth of onion slices and carrots on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil. Top with salmon. Sprinkle with ginger; drizzle with vinegar and oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
7934f4a6-06cb-4c60-9966-a291fb73f410 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
7934f4a6-06cb-4c60-9966-a291fb73f410 BAKE 16 to 20 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven or GRILL 14 to 18 minutes in a covered grill.
10eceae8-0758-492c-ac21-7b83b3d9815f LINE a 5 to 6 quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim.
10eceae8-0758-492c-ac21-7b83b3d9815f PLACE water and three-fourths of the vegetables in the lined-slow cooker. Reserve 1 tablespoon onion soup mix. Sprinkle remaining onion soup mix over vegetables; stir gently to coat evenly. Sprinkle and rub salt, pepper and thyme over the pot roast. Place pot roast on top of vegetables. Place remaining vegetables around pot roast; sprinkle vegetables with remaining onion soup mix.
10eceae8-0758-492c-ac21-7b83b3d9815f COVER and cook 8 to 9 hours on LOW OR 5 to 6 hours on HIGH, until pot roast is fork tender.
10eceae8-0758-492c-ac21-7b83b3d9815f CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from lined slow cooker using a wooden or plastic spoon. Remove all food and cool slow cooker completely before removing liner from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.
b4cdfae9-4219-4772-b2a7-a12a7d4f3c04 PREHEAT the oven to 400°.
b4cdfae9-4219-4772-b2a7-a12a7d4f3c04 COMBINE the peppers, onions, sliced flank steak, olive oil, chili powder, cumin and salt in a large bowl until is completely mixed together and set aside.
b4cdfae9-4219-4772-b2a7-a12a7d4f3c04 UNFOLD a Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag and open it up at the seal and add 1 tablespoon of flour. Close the bag and shake.
b4cdfae9-4219-4772-b2a7-a12a7d4f3c04 PLACE the bag into a 13 by 9 casserole dish and pour the fajita mixture into the bag.
b4cdfae9-4219-4772-b2a7-a12a7d4f3c04 CLOSE up the bag with the tie that’s provided and using a pair of scissors make 6 half inch slits in the top of the bag.
b4cdfae9-4219-4772-b2a7-a12a7d4f3c04 TUCK the extra plastic from the bag into the casserole dish.
b4cdfae9-4219-4772-b2a7-a12a7d4f3c04 BAKE in the oven on 400° for 40 minutes or until the meat is browned, cooked throughout andreaches an internal temperature of 165°.
b4cdfae9-4219-4772-b2a7-a12a7d4f3c04 CUT along the top of the bag and open it up once it’s finished cooking and drain any excess liquid from the bag.
1f964e35-2df6-401a-b6e8-ab5401b48940 PREHEAT oven to 400F. Add flour, Creole seasoning and thyme to Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag; shake to blend. Place bag in 13x9x2-inch pan.
1f964e35-2df6-401a-b6e8-ab5401b48940 ADD chicken, sausage, tomatoes, rice, bell pepper, and onion to oven bag; turn several times to coat ingredients with seasonings. Arrange ingredients in even layer in bag. Fold down bag opening two times to hold it open; set aside.
1f964e35-2df6-401a-b6e8-ab5401b48940 MICROWAVE broth in a medium microwave-safe bowl or measuring cup for about 2 minutes on high power until broth is very hot. Carefully pour or ladle both over ingredients in oven bag. Carefully unfold bag opening.
1f964e35-2df6-401a-b6e8-ab5401b48940 CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
1f964e35-2df6-401a-b6e8-ab5401b48940 BAKE 30 to 35 minutes, until chicken reads 170F on meat thermometer and rice is done. Let stand 5 minutes. Carefully cut top of bag open; stir with rubber scraper or spoon. Garnish servings with chopped green onions and add hot sauce, if desired.
1f964e35-2df6-401a-b6e8-ab5401b48940 TIP: To easily cut chicken thighs into cubes, open them and place flat on a cutting board to cut with knife.
1f964e35-2df6-401a-b6e8-ab5401b48940 OR use kitchen shears to cut into cubes.
d1e4e0f4-7620-4d5a-ad6b-4a33c58b132c Place an Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag in 2-quart oval dish (or similar-sized microwave safe dish).
d1e4e0f4-7620-4d5a-ad6b-4a33c58b132c Combine flour, soy sauce, wine, ginger, green onion and garlic cloves in bowl and stir to blend. Add asparagus to oven bag and arrange along sides of bag. Place tilapia fillets in center of asparagus.
d1e4e0f4-7620-4d5a-ad6b-4a33c58b132c Spoon sauce over tilapia fillets and asparagus. Close oven bag with nylon tie (included in package); cut 6 1/2-inch slits in top of bag. Tuck ends of oven bag in pan. Microwave on high for 6–7 minutes, turning dish halfway through if dish is too big to turn on the rotating carousel.
d1e4e0f4-7620-4d5a-ad6b-4a33c58b132c Carefully cut the oven bag open. Remove vegetables and fish using a spatula. Spoon excess sauce over fish, season with salt and pepper to taste, and serve with rice (made separately). Garnish with cilantro, if desired.
cbf0612c-bc72-4558-b2b8-5b397e59ef84 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium–high.
cbf0612c-bc72-4558-b2b8-5b397e59ef84 CENTER one tuna steak on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food; top with pineapple chunks. Combine teriyaki sauce, ginger and salt; spoon over tuna and pineapple. Arrange vegetables beside tuna.
cbf0612c-bc72-4558-b2b8-5b397e59ef84 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
cbf0612c-bc72-4558-b2b8-5b397e59ef84 BAKE 16 to 18 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven OR GRILL 8 to 10 minutes in covered grill.
5f9ec33e-20fa-4a8b-a763-bb61135cda71 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
5f9ec33e-20fa-4a8b-a763-bb61135cda71 CENTER one-fourth of pork slices, broccoli, carrots, water chestnuts, bell pepper and onions evenly on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
5f9ec33e-20fa-4a8b-a763-bb61135cda71 MIX sweet and sour sauce, stir fry sauce, sesame oil and ginger in a small bowl; spoon evenly over pork and vegetables.
5f9ec33e-20fa-4a8b-a763-bb61135cda71 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
5f9ec33e-20fa-4a8b-a763-bb61135cda71 If freezing, place packets in Hefty® Slider Bags. Label bags with permanent marker. Freeze till ready to thaw and cook.
5f9ec33e-20fa-4a8b-a763-bb61135cda71 PLACE frozen packets in refrigerator to thaw for 10 to 12 hours.
5f9ec33e-20fa-4a8b-a763-bb61135cda71 PLACE thawed packets on baking sheet to cook in oven or transport to grill.
5f9ec33e-20fa-4a8b-a763-bb61135cda71 BAKE 20 to 22 minutes in oven or GRILL 15 to 16 minutes in covered grill, till pork reaches 160°F and vegetables are crisp-tender. Serve with rice and more sauce, if desired.
210e634d-13c0-459b-8f0a-7fb969e61e05 PREHEAT grill to medium-high or oven to 450°F.
210e634d-13c0-459b-8f0a-7fb969e61e05 CENTER two chicken breast halves on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Spoon 1/4 the barbecue sauce over each piece of chicken. Top each piece of chicken with 1/4 of the vegetables.
210e634d-13c0-459b-8f0a-7fb969e61e05 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two packets.
210e634d-13c0-459b-8f0a-7fb969e61e05 GRILL 12 to 15 minutes in covered grill OR BAKE 18 to 22 minutes on a baking sheet in oven until chicken reaches 170°F on meat thermometer.
210e634d-13c0-459b-8f0a-7fb969e61e05 OPEN packets carefully, allowing steam to escape, by cutting along top fold with sharp knife.
7533331a-f324-4ff1-887e-459caac8780f PREHEAT oven to 450°F. Remove neck and giblets from turkey; rinse turkey and pat dry. If desired, loosely stuff turkey. Brush with oil.
7533331a-f324-4ff1-887e-459caac8780f TEAR off a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil 2 1/2 times longer than turkey. Place turkey lengthwise in center of aluminum foil sheet to cook.
7533331a-f324-4ff1-887e-459caac8780f CLOSE foil loosely by overlapping the ends. Turn up short sides of aluminum foil to hold in juices. Do not seal airtight. Place foil wrapped turkey in roasting pan at least 2 inches deep. Insert meat thermometer through foil into thickest part of inner thigh, not touching bone.
7533331a-f324-4ff1-887e-459caac8780f ROAST turkey until meat thermometer reads 180°F. For approximate roasting times, see chart above. For stuffed turkey, add 30 minutes to roasting time. To brown turkey, open and turn back foil 30 minutes before roasting is finished. For easy slicing, cover turkey with aluminum foil after removing and let stand 15 minutes.
30c91c76-1efa-49f3-bd84-68f9163affb3 PREHEAT oven to a temperature 325°F. Line roasting pan, at least 2 inches deep, with Reynolds Wrap® 18-inch Wide Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil; set aside.
30c91c76-1efa-49f3-bd84-68f9163affb3 REMOVE neck and giblets from turkey; rinse turkey and pat dry. Place turkey in foil–lined roasting pan. If stuffing is desired, loosely stuff turkey. Brush with oil. Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of thigh, not touching bone.
30c91c76-1efa-49f3-bd84-68f9163affb3 MAKE a foil tent by placing a sheet of foil over turkey, leaving 1 inch between top of turkey and foil tent for heat circulation. Crimp foil onto long sides of pan.
30c91c76-1efa-49f3-bd84-68f9163affb3 ROAST turkey until meat thermometer inserted in thickness part of the thigh not touching the bone reads a temperature of 180°F. For approximate roasting times see chart. For stuffed turkey, add 30 minutes to roasting time. To brown turkey, remove foil tent after 1 hour of roasting. For easy slicing, cover turkey with foil and let stand 15 minutes.
ff58e6db-a409-469f-bfe9-78da23621d91 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
ff58e6db-a409-469f-bfe9-78da23621d91 Shake flour inside the Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag and place in a large roasting pan that is at least 2 inches deep. You can opt to spray the inside of bag with nonstick cooking spray if you desire.
ff58e6db-a409-469f-bfe9-78da23621d91 Place onion wedges in the bottom of the bag.
ff58e6db-a409-469f-bfe9-78da23621d91 Remove neck and giblets from turkey, then rinse and pat your turkey dry. Brush with your 2 Tbs of oil or melted butter.
ff58e6db-a409-469f-bfe9-78da23621d91 In a small bowl, combine all seasonings and rub into the entire turkey.
ff58e6db-a409-469f-bfe9-78da23621d91 Carefully slide turkey into the oven bag, making sure the opening of the bag is facing the end of the roasting pan, and not facing up. The bag should be inside the pan, not hanging over the edges of the pan.
ff58e6db-a409-469f-bfe9-78da23621d91 Close oven bag with the included nylon tie, and cut six 1/2 inch slits in the top of the bag.
ff58e6db-a409-469f-bfe9-78da23621d91 Baking time varies depending on the size of your turkey. You can refer to the Oven Bag directions or use the reference above.
ff58e6db-a409-469f-bfe9-78da23621d91 When your turkey reaches an internal temperature of 180°F in thickest part of the thigh, not touching the bone, remove from oven and let stand in oven bag for another 15 minutes. Cut open the top of the bag and carefully remove turkey from the bag, and place onto a cutting board. Lifting works well by inserting one carving fork into each end of the turkey.
8299589f-141b-4661-aa05-ddb38e5e4783 PREHEAT grill to medium, indirect heat.
8299589f-141b-4661-aa05-ddb38e5e4783 MAKE a foil drip pan to place under turkey during indirect grilling. To make the foil drip pan, stack 2 sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil 6 inches longer and wider than the turkey. Fold in all edges 1 1/2–inches. Fold edges upright, forming 1 1/2–inch sides. Press corners against sides; set foil drip pan aside.
8299589f-141b-4661-aa05-ddb38e5e4783 REMOVE neck and giblets from turkey; rinse turkey and pat dry. Brush with oil. Do not stuff turkey. Stuffing may be wrapped in heavy strength foil and heated on the grill. Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of thigh, not touching bone. Place foil drip pan under grill grate. Brush grill grate with oil. Place turkey on grill grate above foil drip pan.
8299589f-141b-4661-aa05-ddb38e5e4783 GRILL turkey in covered grill over medium, indirect heat until meat thermometer reads 180°F. Approximate grilling times are 2-3 hours for 8-12 pound turkey; 3-4 hours for 12-16 pound turkey. Grilling is not recommended for turkey over 16 pounds. For easy slicing, remove turkey from grill, cover with foil and let stand minutes.
4ad88dc2-7c55-4986-8773-1f9cde603d1d PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
4ad88dc2-7c55-4986-8773-1f9cde603d1d SHAKE flour inside a Turkey Sized Reynolds® Oven Bag and place in a large roasting pan at least 2 inches deep. Spray inside of bag with nonstick spray to reduce sticking, if desired.
4ad88dc2-7c55-4986-8773-1f9cde603d1d ADD vegetables to oven bag. Remove neck and giblets from turkey. Rinse turkey; pat dry. Brush turkey with oil. Combine sage, thyme, rosemary and seasoned salt. Sprinkle and rub herb mixture over turkey, turning to coat evenly.
4ad88dc2-7c55-4986-8773-1f9cde603d1d PLACE turkey in oven bag on top of vegetables.
4ad88dc2-7c55-4986-8773-1f9cde603d1d CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Insert meat thermometer through slit in bag into thickest part of inner thigh. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
4ad88dc2-7c55-4986-8773-1f9cde603d1d BAKE 2 to 2 1/2 hours for a 12 to 16 lb. turkey, 2 1/2 to 3 hours for a 16 to 20 lb. turkey, and 3 to 3 1/2 hours for a 20 to 24 lb. turkey, or until meat thermometer reads 180°F. For easy slicing, let stand in oven bag 15 minutes before opening.
202bbd81-7444-4f5c-a655-a0021d366f99 PREHEAT oven to 325°F.
202bbd81-7444-4f5c-a655-a0021d366f99 LINE a large roasting pan, at least 2 inches deep, with Reynolds Wrap® 18-inch Wide Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Rinse turkey breast; pat dry. Place turkey breast in foil-lined pan. Brush turkey breast with vegetable oil.
202bbd81-7444-4f5c-a655-a0021d366f99 COMBINE parsley, sage, marjoram, thyme, rosemary and seasoned salt. Sprinkle and rub seasoning mixture over turkey breast, turning to coat evenly.
202bbd81-7444-4f5c-a655-a0021d366f99 MAKE a foil tent by placing a sheet of foil over turkey breast, leaving 1 inch between top of turkey breast and foil tent for heat circulation. Crimp foil onto long sides of pan.
202bbd81-7444-4f5c-a655-a0021d366f99 BAKE 1 hour; remove foil tent to brown turkey breast.
202bbd81-7444-4f5c-a655-a0021d366f99 CONTINUE BAKING uncovered 1 to 1 3/4 hours longer or until meat thermometer reads 170°F. For easy slicing, cover turkey breast with foil and let stand 15 minutes.
0ae139ca-b13f-4683-8998-d735e0f19522 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
0ae139ca-b13f-4683-8998-d735e0f19522 SHAKE 1 tablespoon flour in Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag, Turkey Size; place in large roasting pan at least 2 inches deep. Spray inside of bag with nonstick spray to reduce sticking, if desired. Set aside.
0ae139ca-b13f-4683-8998-d735e0f19522 MELT butter in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic and shallots. Cook, stirring occasionally until golden brown. Add remaining flour and continue cooking 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture is smooth; remove from heat. Pour into large bowl; add remaining ingredients. Cool mixture completely.
0ae139ca-b13f-4683-8998-d735e0f19522 RUB mixture over turkey, making sure to rub inside of cavity. Place turkey in oven bag.
0ae139ca-b13f-4683-8998-d735e0f19522 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Insert meat thermometer through slit in bag into thickest part of inner thigh. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
0ae139ca-b13f-4683-8998-d735e0f19522 BAKE to / hours or until meat thermometer reads °F. Remove from oven and let stand minutes. Slice turkey; spoon juices over turkey before serving.
105f9648-4a99-4e23-9dfe-efc5d1604372 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
105f9648-4a99-4e23-9dfe-efc5d1604372 SHAKE flour in a Reynolds Kitchens® Turkey Oven Bag; place in 13x9-inch baking pan. Add 1/2 cup broth to oven bag. Squeeze bag to blend in flour.
105f9648-4a99-4e23-9dfe-efc5d1604372 COMBINE stuffing mix, apple, celery, onion, cranberries, the remaining broth, and 2 tablespoons butter. In a small bowl, mix sage, thyme, seasoned salt, pepper and paprka; stir 2 teaspoons seasoning mixture into stuffing mixture.
105f9648-4a99-4e23-9dfe-efc5d1604372 CUT each tenderloin by making a horizontal cut along one long side, but NOT cutting all the way through, so that each is about 1/2 inch thick when opened. Open tenderloins and spoon half of stuffing mixture in center of each. Starting at one long edge, roll up. Add to bag, seam side down, leaving space between them in bag. Brush tenderloins with butter mixture; sprinkle with remaining seasoning mixture.
105f9648-4a99-4e23-9dfe-efc5d1604372 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
105f9648-4a99-4e23-9dfe-efc5d1604372 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: If tenderloins are too thin to cut in half, place each between 2 sheets of plastic wrap. Using a meat mallet or rolling pin, start at center and gently pound tenderloins until about 1/2-inch thick. OR place tenderloins in bag and spoon stuffing in center. Substitute pork tenderloins, 3/4 to 1 lb each, for the turkey tenderloins. Bake for 40 minutes, until pork meat thermometer reads 170F for turkey and 165°F for stuffing
105f9648-4a99-4e23-9dfe-efc5d1604372 BAKE 30 minutes, until meat thermometer reads 170°F for turkey and 165°F for stuffing. Let stand 10 minutes.
105f9648-4a99-4e23-9dfe-efc5d1604372 Cut in slices to serve. If desired, serve pan juices with turkey.
28eb11d5-7bbb-4600-ad06-8f27162e57a3 Preheat the oven to 350°F.
28eb11d5-7bbb-4600-ad06-8f27162e57a3 Roll the premade pie dough onto a clean surface dusted with flour until it expands by an additional 1/3 size.
28eb11d5-7bbb-4600-ad06-8f27162e57a3 Form the dough to a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Non-Stick Pie Pan and fold in the dough around the outside and flute.
28eb11d5-7bbb-4600-ad06-8f27162e57a3 Place the fluted dough into the freezer for 30 minutes
28eb11d5-7bbb-4600-ad06-8f27162e57a3 Whisk the eggs, corn syrup, brown sugar and melted butter in a large bowl until combined.
28eb11d5-7bbb-4600-ad06-8f27162e57a3 Fold in the chopped pecans and pour the mixture into the frozen fluted pie dough.
28eb11d5-7bbb-4600-ad06-8f27162e57a3 Arrange the pecan halves in a decorative fashion on top of pie filling.
28eb11d5-7bbb-4600-ad06-8f27162e57a3 Bake in the oven on 350° for 60 minutes or until the center is firm.
28eb11d5-7bbb-4600-ad06-8f27162e57a3 Cool to room temperature before serving.
3f164a41-9062-4bfd-b529-0c8156c71a60 PREHEAT oven to 325°F.
3f164a41-9062-4bfd-b529-0c8156c71a60 SHAKE flour in Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag; place in roasting pan at least 2 inches deep.
3f164a41-9062-4bfd-b529-0c8156c71a60 ADD the glaze mix of pineapple juice, brown sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon to oven bag. Squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Place pineapple slices in bag; arrange in an even layer around sides of bag. Lightly score surface of ham in a diamond pattern. Insert cloves, if desired. Place ham in bag in center of pineapple slices.
3f164a41-9062-4bfd-b529-0c8156c71a60 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2–inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
3f164a41-9062-4bfd-b529-0c8156c71a60 BAKE to / hours until meat thermometer reads °F. To serve, cut oven bag open and transfer ham to serving platter. Spoon glaze over ham.
4f7120f4-6f03-4560-b3fa-3ad23c45231d PREHEAT the oven to 400°F. LINE a 13x9x2-inch pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil; set aside.
4f7120f4-6f03-4560-b3fa-3ad23c45231d TRIM skin and excess fat from ham, leaving a thin layer of fat. Score surface of ham by lightly cutting diamond shapes into the thin layer of fat on the ham. PLACE the ham in the foil-lined pan with skin side up; set aside.
4f7120f4-6f03-4560-b3fa-3ad23c45231d COMBINE brown sugar, cornstarch, ground cinnamon and cayenne pepper in a large microwave safe bowl until thoroughly mixed. ADD marmalade, orange juice and lemon juice to the bowl. WHISK gently until mixture is thoroughly blended.
4f7120f4-6f03-4560-b3fa-3ad23c45231d COVER bowl and vent for steam to escape. MICROWAVE 4 minutes on high power. Remove and carefully whisk until smooth. Recover and continue heating on high power for 2 to 4 minutes, carefully whisking every 2 minutes until hot, bubbly and slightly thickened. Brush half the glaze over the ham. Reserve the remaining glaze to serve with ham.
4f7120f4-6f03-4560-b3fa-3ad23c45231d BAKE for 45 minutes in preheated oven, basting with the glaze every 15 minutes, until ham is golden browned.
4f7120f4-6f03-4560-b3fa-3ad23c45231d COVER ham with a fresh sheet of foil and let stand 15 minutes before slicing. SLICE ham and serve drizzled with warm glaze.
212c820c-3700-43b0-a93c-a3316e4a4e78 Preheat the oven to 325°F.
212c820c-3700-43b0-a93c-a3316e4a4e78 Whisk together the butter, thyme, sage, chives, garlic, lemon zest, orange zest, 1/2 tablespoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of ground pepper, and set aside.
212c820c-3700-43b0-a93c-a3316e4a4e78 Place the turkey in a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Roaster Pan. Season the outside and inside cavity with 1 tablespoon of salt and 1 teaspoon of ground pepper.
212c820c-3700-43b0-a93c-a3316e4a4e78 Stuff the inside turkey cavity with sliced lemons and oranges and tie the legs together with butcher’s twine.
212c820c-3700-43b0-a93c-a3316e4a4e78 Coat the turkey on all sides with the citrus-herb butter.
212c820c-3700-43b0-a93c-a3316e4a4e78 Bake in the oven for 3 ½ to 4 hours basting every 30 minutes.
212c820c-3700-43b0-a93c-a3316e4a4e78 Remove the turkey from the oven and let sit for 10 to 15 minutes before slicing.
5d1b5d52-1882-4dea-bb41-f97526c4c731 PREHEAT oven to 375°F.
5d1b5d52-1882-4dea-bb41-f97526c4c731 PLACE a 24-inch long piece Reynolds Kitchens® Unbleached Parchment Paper on to your work surface. Place the biscuit dough on top and sprinkle with flour. Using a rolling pin, roll the dough into an 18-inch by 8-inch rectangle.
5d1b5d52-1882-4dea-bb41-f97526c4c731 SPREAD preserves onto the prepared dough. Layer with salami, prosciutto and olives. Sprinkle with cheese.
5d1b5d52-1882-4dea-bb41-f97526c4c731 STARTING at the 18-inch side, roll up the dough and pinch edges together to seal. Cut into 12, 1 1/2-inch slices. Transfer to 8x8-inch Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Pan.
5d1b5d52-1882-4dea-bb41-f97526c4c731 BAKE 30 to 35 minutes or until rolls are golden. Cool on a wire rack for 15 minutes before serving.
51968d5e-76d2-4c13-8457-d957a050c7a8 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
51968d5e-76d2-4c13-8457-d957a050c7a8 CENTER potatoes evenly on sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Drizzle with oil. Sprinkle with garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper.
51968d5e-76d2-4c13-8457-d957a050c7a8 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal making one large foil packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
51968d5e-76d2-4c13-8457-d957a050c7a8 BAKE 30 to 35 minutes on cookie sheet in oven or GRILL 15 to 20 minutes in covered grill. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.
af686e26-dd39-4bae-9bfd-f218091f07f8 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with two long sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil, non-stick dull side facing up, overlapping them in opposing directions so you make a cross, with plenty of foil at each end to eventually fold over into the center. Set aside.
af686e26-dd39-4bae-9bfd-f218091f07f8 In a large mixing bowl, stir together cream, shallot and garlic. Add parsnips, sweet potato and turnip and carefully toss together until all the pieces are well coated. In another mixing bowl combine 1 cup of cheese, green onion and thyme and toss together.
af686e26-dd39-4bae-9bfd-f218091f07f8 To assemble, place a single layer of cream-coated root vegetable pieces onto the foil-lined baking sheet and season generously with salt and pepper. Sprinkle 1/4 of the cheese mixture over the surface. Repeat with another layer of vegetables, salt and pepper and cheese mixture and continue with this pattern until all the ingredients have been used (finishing with a layer of vegetables).
af686e26-dd39-4bae-9bfd-f218091f07f8 Bring each side of the excess foil hanging over the baking sheet together and seal tightly, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Bake gratin in the oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are fork tender. Open foil carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape; then open top of foil.
af686e26-dd39-4bae-9bfd-f218091f07f8 Uncover gratin and sprinkle remaining cheese over the top. Place gratin under a broiler and broil for 30 seconds to 1 minute or until cheese has melted and the top has browned slightly. Allow gratin to cool for about 10 minutes before cutting up and serving.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 PREHEAT the oven to 375° F.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 HEAT a medium sized pot on medium heat and add in 1 teaspoon of butter along with the diced yellow onion.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 COOK the onions until they become brown. Once brown, add in the remaining amount of butter and melt.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 ADD the flour to the pot and mix until it is combined to form a roux.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 POUR in the milk and bring it to a boil while occasionally whisking until it becomes very thick, similar to Alfredo sauce.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 WHISK in the Mozzarella cheese until it is melted and finish with salt and pepper.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 PLACE the sliced potatoes in a large bowl and pour on the thick cheese sauce and stir until combined.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 TRANSFER the potatoes and cream to a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Casserole pan.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 SPRINKLE on the breadcrumbs to cover the top of the potatoes.
4bccd25c-9c7d-4284-99dd-c42e519a60d9 BAKE the potatoes on 375° for 60 minutes or until golden brown on top and the potatoes are soft.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 PREHEAT the oven to 375° F.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 BOIL the cauliflower in a large pot of boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Strain and add to a large bowl.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 COOK the onions and garlic in a large pot on high heat with olive oil until golden brown.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 ADD the cream to the onion pot and cook until the cream begins to become thick, about 10 minutes.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 WHISK in 4 ounces each of cheddar and Monterey jack cheese to the cream until combined.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 ADD the cream to the bowl with the cauliflower and toss. Season with salt and pepper.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 POUR the cream cauliflower into a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Casserole Pan.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 SPRINKLE on the remaining cheese over the cauliflower.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 BAKE in the oven for 30 minutes on 375° or until the cheese and cauliflower and golden brown.
940d6bb5-c5ec-42b3-a566-7dcb433bd0a1 SERVE warm.
dd7fc301-53fe-479e-9a7d-265a5594c2b7 First, make the romesco sauce by adding 2 teaspoons of olive oil to a non-stick pan along with the peppers and almonds. Cook over medium heat for 4 minutes then add the garlic, tomatoes, paprika, cayenne and vinegar. Cook for 3–4 minutes then add a pinch of salt and pepper. Transfer to a food processor or blender and while machine is running, add the extra virgin olive oil. If the consistency is a bit loose, add 1–2 more tablespoons of oil. Check for seasoning, you may need more salt and vinegar.
dd7fc301-53fe-479e-9a7d-265a5594c2b7 For the cod, heat one half the grill to medium-high and the other half to low. Cut two 12-inch pieces of Reynolds Kitchens® Unbleached Parchment Paper, then fold over each piece and use a scissors to cut a half heart shape. Open the parchment paper and place the fish in the middle of one side of the heart. Season each cod filet with a shot of oil, a generous pinch of salt, and some pepper. Arrange the tomatoes, dill, lemon slices, asparagus, and olives around the fish. It’s nice to tuck some lemon slices under the fish. Securely close the parchment pouches by starting at the bottom of the heart and folding the paper over itself. This will create a tight seal and form the package.
dd7fc301-53fe-479e-9a7d-265a5594c2b7 Place both parchment pouches on the cool side of the grill, close the lid, and cook for 10–12 minutes, or until the fish flakes apart with a fork. After 10 minutes, you can cut the pouch open a bit to test the fish. If using an oven, bake on a sheet tray at 350 F for 12–14 minutes. Allow the fish to rest for 3 minutes after it comes off the grill, cut the parchment paper and transfer to a plate. Enjoy!
a68e2c6a-5305-45f6-aad8-a475f9146474 Place a Reynolds Kitchens® Small Slow Cooker Liner in a small slow cooker — about 2 1/2 to 4 quarts.
a68e2c6a-5305-45f6-aad8-a475f9146474 Add all ingredients and stir well to combine.
a68e2c6a-5305-45f6-aad8-a475f9146474 Put the lid on the slow cooker, and cook on low for 4–6 hours, depending on your slow cooker and your preferences.
a68e2c6a-5305-45f6-aad8-a475f9146474 Open the lid, stir and serve as desired.
a464f560-f887-4e87-8b8c-0124fb824c7c Stir together beef, pork, onion, egg, garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper and egg in a large bowl just until combined—don’t overmix.
a464f560-f887-4e87-8b8c-0124fb824c7c Preheat oven to 350 F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
a464f560-f887-4e87-8b8c-0124fb824c7c Shape meat into 1–1.5" balls and place 1" apart on baking sheet. (I get about 35 1.5" meatballs)
a464f560-f887-4e87-8b8c-0124fb824c7c Bake for 15–20 minutes, just until internal temperature reaches 160 F.
a464f560-f887-4e87-8b8c-0124fb824c7c Set aside to cool slightly. (*At this point, once cooled, you can freeze up to 3 months for a variety of uses).
a464f560-f887-4e87-8b8c-0124fb824c7c Place one Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner in a 2.5–4-quart slow cooker. Place meatballs in slow cooker.
a464f560-f887-4e87-8b8c-0124fb824c7c Stir together broth, half and half, corn starch, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, parsley, salt, thyme, pepper and nutmeg. Pour over meatballs in slow cooker.
a464f560-f887-4e87-8b8c-0124fb824c7c Cook on low until heated through and sauce has thickened—about 4–5 hours on low or 2 hours on high.
a464f560-f887-4e87-8b8c-0124fb824c7c Serve with sauce over mashed potatoes or egg noodles.
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a Move oven rack one level below center and preheat oven to 350 degrees.
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a In a small mixing bowl, stir together butter, garlic, thyme and season with a little salt and pepper.
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a Remove neck and giblets from turkey and remove any pin feathers left behind. Tuck wings under turkey. Season cavity of turkey with salt and pepper.
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a Using the back end of a wooden spoon, separate turkey breast skin from breast. Rub butter underneath skin, smooth over skin to spread butter out.
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a Season all over turkey with a fair amount of salt and pepper.
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a Add 1 tablespoon flour to the Reynolds Kitchens® Turkey Oven Bag and shake. Place oven bag in a roasting pan, add celery, onion and carrots to oven bag. Place turkey over vegetable layer in oven bag.
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a Close oven bag with the oven safe tie included. Cut 6 slits across top of the oven bag to allow steam to escape, then tuck ends of oven bag into the pan.
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a Cook unstuffed turkey according to size (thickest portion of thigh and breast should register 165 degrees in several places on an instant read thermometer):
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a 12–16-lb. turkey: 2–2 1/4 hours
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a 16–20-lb. turkey: 2 1/4–2 1/2 hours
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a 20–24-lb. turkey: 2 1/2–3 hours
16a15c3d-1480-4e6d-8a61-43ada27b5c9a Let turkey rest 20 minutes. Carefully cut top of oven bag open, transfer turkey to carving board and carve.
6034fd8d-116b-4731-948b-7ffc217826d1 Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Use Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil to cover one half of a large sheet pan. Fold up the edges to make a tray.
6034fd8d-116b-4731-948b-7ffc217826d1 Season chicken with salt, pepper and Italian seasoning. Drizzle a large pan with oil, brown the chicken on both sides, and set aside.
6034fd8d-116b-4731-948b-7ffc217826d1 Arrange chicken breasts in the foil tray. Stir together cranberry sauce, 1/2 cup broth (or water) and the onion soup mix. Spoon over the chicken breasts.
6034fd8d-116b-4731-948b-7ffc217826d1 Arrange stuffing, celery, and onions on the unused half of the sheet pan. In a medium bowl stir together broth, butter, salt and pepper. Pour over the stuffing and use spoons or your hands to toss well.
6034fd8d-116b-4731-948b-7ffc217826d1 Bake for 20–25 minutes until chicken is cooked through and stuffing is browned and crisp on the top. Top with dried cranberries and serve.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf In the bowl of your stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, mix the butter and cream cheese together for 2 minutes, until smooth and creamy.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Add in the egg, the yolk, vanilla, baking powder and salt and mix for 1 minute until smooth, scraping the sides of the bowl as necessary.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Turn the mixer to low and add in the flour, mixing until just combined.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Divide the dough in half, removing half from the mixing bowl.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Add in the cocoa powder to the remaining dough in the mixing bowl and mix until incorporated.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Form each dough into a squared off log, 2 inches tall and 6 inches long. Make sure both are the same size.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Place dough on a baking sheet and cover with cling wrap. Place dough into the refrigerator to chill for at least 1 hour.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Using a sharp knife, slice the dough into thirds, lengthwise. Then turn the dough one turn and cut into thirds again. You will have 9 strips. Repeat the process with the other dough. You will have 18 strips total.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Lay 1 piece of vanilla dough, one piece of chocolate, and another piece of vanilla on a flat surface next to each other. Top the 3 strips with alternating colors. Repeat this once more, so you have a square log. Press the dough strips together tightly, keeping the square shape. Repeat this with the remaining dough.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Refrigerate again for at least 30 minutes.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line a baking sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with Smart Grid®.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Remove the dough from the refrigerator and slice into 1/4-inch pieces.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Place the pieces on the prepared baking sheet.
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Bake for 9–10 minutes, or until set. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely
aac1c062-1baf-4866-9626-078526ac19cf Store airtight for up to 5 days. Freeze airtight for up to 30 days.
3fcf4ae9-befa-43d4-810c-c119a3100ae7 Place a heat-safe bowl over a saucepan of simmering water. Add the butter and the chopped chocolate. Stir until smooth (5–10 minutes).
3fcf4ae9-befa-43d4-810c-c119a3100ae7 Beat the eggs with the sugar in a stand mixer on medium speed. Beat in the vanilla. Scrape the sides if needed. Pour in the melted chocolate and beat until combined. Mix in the flour and baking powder. Turn off the mixer.
3fcf4ae9-befa-43d4-810c-c119a3100ae7 Stir in the chocolate chips.
3fcf4ae9-befa-43d4-810c-c119a3100ae7 Pour the batter into a large bowl and cover. Freeze for 1 hour.
3fcf4ae9-befa-43d4-810c-c119a3100ae7 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line your baking sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®. Scoop 2 tablespoons of batter into a ball (doesn’t have to be pretty) and place on the prepared baking sheets, about 2 inches apart (The Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® makes spacing super easy!)
3fcf4ae9-befa-43d4-810c-c119a3100ae7 Bake for 10 minutes, or until the cookies crack on top and appear dry on the edges.
3fcf4ae9-befa-43d4-810c-c119a3100ae7 Let cool on the cookie sheet for 10 minutes, then transfer to a cooling rack to cool completely.
3fcf4ae9-befa-43d4-810c-c119a3100ae7 If wanting to make the peppermint version, sprinkle cookies with crushed peppermint upon removing from the oven. Lightly and carefully press them into each cookie to adhere. Allow to cool as stated above.
6c96bee1-834a-4780-987d-b93bd311fc1e Place a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner in a 2.5–4-quart slow cooker.
6c96bee1-834a-4780-987d-b93bd311fc1e Add espresso, milk, pumpkin, maple syrup and pumpkin pie spice to slow cooker and whisk well.
6c96bee1-834a-4780-987d-b93bd311fc1e Cook on low for 2-3 hours until heated through.
6c96bee1-834a-4780-987d-b93bd311fc1e Top with whipped cream or milk foam and a dusting of pumpkin pie spice as desired to serve.
845ed1c6-ba00-448b-a085-28b87d4b7b06 If you’re not using pre-cooked chicken, just boil a chicken breast in salted water until cooked through (about 20 minutes).
845ed1c6-ba00-448b-a085-28b87d4b7b06 Shred the chicken with two forks. Transfer to a pan over medium heat and toss with salsa and spices. Cook until heated through and the salsa has been absorbed/cooked off. Set aside while you continue the prep. This chicken will keep in the fridge for up to four days. I like to make a double batch and have some delicious chicken for my salads later in the week.
845ed1c6-ba00-448b-a085-28b87d4b7b06 Prep all the ingredients needed. Shred the cheese, slice the peppers, green onions and dice the avocado and red onion, etc.
845ed1c6-ba00-448b-a085-28b87d4b7b06 Cover your baking sheet in Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil, then spread a thin layer of chips over the surface. Two chips is the maximum thickness—everyone wants toppings on their chips! Bake at 350 F for about 5 minutes to give the chips a toast and help them remain crispy. Set oven to 375 F after toasting.
845ed1c6-ba00-448b-a085-28b87d4b7b06 Spread the cheese over the chips and begin adding the toppings, like beans, chicken, corn and so on. Leave the “wetter” toppings, like the peppers and tomatoes, for last and always place the tomatoes halves cut side up. Toppings like avocados and sour cream will be added after baking just before serving.
845ed1c6-ba00-448b-a085-28b87d4b7b06 Bake at 375 F for about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbling.
845ed1c6-ba00-448b-a085-28b87d4b7b06 Add diced avocados, sour cream, and cilantro leaves just before serving. You can sprinkle some extra seasoning onto the sour cream dollops if desired.
40ed5dc5-e718-4aa8-ba71-f4d6c2abe3bb Preheat oven to 425 F. Cut the tomatoes in half lengthwise and toss with 2 tablespoons of olive oil, 1 teaspoon salt, and a couple cracks of pepper. Arrange cut side up on a sheet tray lined with Reynolds Kitchens® Pop Up Parchment Sheets and roast in the oven for 45 minutes. Turn the broiler on, and cook another 3–6 minutes, or until slightly charred around the edges.
40ed5dc5-e718-4aa8-ba71-f4d6c2abe3bb While the tomatoes are roasting, preheat a large pot over medium heat along with 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Add the onions, 1/4 teaspoon of kosher salt, and a couple cracks of fresh pepper. Cook for 8 minutes, stirring often. Add the garlic, thyme and pepper flakes and continue cooking until the onions are soft and translucent, about 4–5 minutes more. Add the roasted tomatoes, stock and basil leaves to the pot along with 2 teaspoons of salt and a couple cracks of pepper (remember, the stock is bland). Bring this mixture to a boil, and reduce to a simmer for 45 minutes with the lid on the pot.
40ed5dc5-e718-4aa8-ba71-f4d6c2abe3bb After 45 minutes, add 2 teaspoons of honey and check for seasoning—you will definitely need more salt.
40ed5dc5-e718-4aa8-ba71-f4d6c2abe3bb Use a hand/stick blender to puree the soup until it’s smooth. If you have to use a blender, be very careful and only fill the blender up halfway at a time, blend, dump and repeat. Return the soup back to the pot and check for seasoning. Serve soup with some chopped basil as garnish and a small drizzle of extra virgin olive oil if desired.
077f2a32-fa91-40c4-816b-fc43c259db6a In a large skillet over high heat, add hash browns. Drizzle with oil and season generously with salt and pepper. Cook for 6-10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until crispy. Set aside.
077f2a32-fa91-40c4-816b-fc43c259db6a In a medium bowl whisk together eggs, milk, and salt and pepper to taste. Add to a greased skillet and stir occasionally over medium heat for 6-8 minutes until mostly cooked. Stir in 1/2 cup cheese. Set eggs aside.
077f2a32-fa91-40c4-816b-fc43c259db6a Cook sausage in a large skillet over high heat, breaking up with a spoon or spatula, about 8-10 minutes until browned. Set aside.
077f2a32-fa91-40c4-816b-fc43c259db6a Cook bacon until crispy. Roughly chop and set aside.
077f2a32-fa91-40c4-816b-fc43c259db6a Microwave your tortillas for 20-30 seconds until warm and pliable. Assemble burritos by portioning out the hash browns, eggs, sausage, bacon, and cheese into the center of each tortilla. Roll the burritos tightly.
077f2a32-fa91-40c4-816b-fc43c259db6a Place each burrito in the center of a piece of foil. Fold the ends of the foil over the burrito, then roll tightly. Place in a Slider Bag, press out excess air, and seal the bag. Freeze until ready to use.
077f2a32-fa91-40c4-816b-fc43c259db6a When ready to use, bake burritos wrapped in the foil, in a preheated oven at 400 degrees for 12-15 minutes. Unwrap and garnish with any desired toppings and enjoy!
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 In the bowl of your stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, mix the butter and cream cheese together for 2 minutes, until smooth and creamy.
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 Add in the sugar and salt and mix for 1 minute, scraping the sides as necessary.
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 Turn mixer to low and add in the flour, mixing until just combined—don’t over-mix.
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 Place a large piece of Reynolds Kitchens® Quick Cut® Plastic Wrap onto your counter. Place the dough onto the plastic wrap and press it into a rectangle shape, approximately 1-inch thick. Wrap the dough tightly in the plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 6 hours, or overnight.
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 Preheat oven to 350 F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 Divide the dough into 4 equal pieces, working with one piece at a time, placing the dough you aren’t using back in the refrigerator.
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 On a lightly floured surface, roll out the dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Spread 1/4 cup of the preserves evenly onto the dough. Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the raisins and 1/4 cup walnuts evenly on top. Sprinkle about 1 1/2 teaspoons of cinnamon sugar all over the top. Roll the dough tightly from the long side into a log. Place the log seam side down onto your prepared baking sheet and repeat with the process with the remaining dough placing the logs 2 inches apart on the baking sheet.
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 Brush each log with milk and sprinkle with turbinado sugar.
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 Using a very sharp knife, cut the logs 3/4 through (not all the way) into 1-inch slices.
f13fa692-0d0e-4274-9499-c54166a54168 Bake for 45 minutes, or until golden. Allow to cool on the baking sheet for 30 minutes, and then transfer to a cutting board to slice all the way through.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a skillet over high heat. Coat the chicken with taco seasoning in a small bowl. Add the chicken to the skillet and sauté both sides until done. Remove from the skillet and set aside.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Add the remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil to a skillet over high heat. Add in the onions and peppers and cook until they are soft. Remove and set aside.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Combine the chicken and pepper mixture in one skillet.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Tear off three 16-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil (dull side facing up). Place on counter surface. Brush softened butter on one side of each tortilla. Center one tortilla on the full sheet.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Then build the quesadillas by laying grated cheese on the bottom tortilla, and then arranging the chicken and peppers mixture.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Top with a little more grated cheese and then top with a second tortilla. Repeat with the remaining tortillas and fillings.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Bring in the long side of each end of the foil, so the ends meet over half of the tortilla. Double fold the two short sides and seal the pocket.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Bake at 350 degrees F for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Remove from oven.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Cut each quesadilla into wedges as small as you’d like.
5dad38a9-038b-41df-878a-0bd4c20c1288 Serve with jalapeños, pico de gallo, sour cream and guacamole.
659a3ebf-aac4-49ae-9fd7-9f67079b95c9 LINE a 5 to 6 quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim. Set aside.
659a3ebf-aac4-49ae-9fd7-9f67079b95c9
659a3ebf-aac4-49ae-9fd7-9f67079b95c9 COOK sausage and onion for 8 to 10 minutes in a large skillet over medium-high heat, breaking up meat as it cooks. Drain well. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, oregano, and basil into sausage. Spoon 1/3 of the sausage mixture into the lined-slow cooker; arrange half of the noodles on top. Combine 2 cups of the mozzarella and the ricotta cheeses in a medium bowl. Spoon half of the cheeses evenly over the noodles. Repeat to add another layer. Top with remaining 1/3 sausage mixture.
659a3ebf-aac4-49ae-9fd7-9f67079b95c9 COVER and Cook 4 to 5 hours on LOW. Turn off slow cooker.
659a3ebf-aac4-49ae-9fd7-9f67079b95c9 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Mix the remaining cup of mozzarella and the Parmesan cheeses; sprinkle over the lasagna. Let stand 30 minutes until cheese melts and the lasagna sets up slightly. Serve lasagna directly from lined-slow cooker. Remove all food and cool slow cooker completely before removing liner from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.
f486836b-0e3f-40a5-a80c-40f17b1ac362 Line a 5-to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
f486836b-0e3f-40a5-a80c-40f17b1ac362 In a large skillet, cook ground turkey and onions in oil, until meat is browned. Drain off any excess fat.
f486836b-0e3f-40a5-a80c-40f17b1ac362 Spoon browned turkey mixture into the lined slow cooker.
