f486836b-0e3f-40a5-a80c-40f17b1ac362 Add garlic, taco seasoning, beans, tomatoes, milk and chicken broth to the slow cooker and gently stir with a rubber spatula to fully mix ingredients together.
f486836b-0e3f-40a5-a80c-40f17b1ac362 Cover and cook on low-heat setting for 7 to 8 hours or on high-heat setting for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
f486836b-0e3f-40a5-a80c-40f17b1ac362 Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker using a plastic, silicon or wooden spoon. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
f486836b-0e3f-40a5-a80c-40f17b1ac362 Top individual servings with cheddar cheese, tomato or sour cream as desired and serve.
1760620d-c9e9-4905-b2f3-6585320141e3 LINE your 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
1760620d-c9e9-4905-b2f3-6585320141e3 WHISK together eggs, milk, flour and baking powder in a large bowl. Add arugula, feta cheese, peppers, tomatoes, basil, garlic and pepper, if desired. Season with salt and pepper.
1760620d-c9e9-4905-b2f3-6585320141e3 POUR mixture into lined slow cooker.
1760620d-c9e9-4905-b2f3-6585320141e3 PLACE lid on slow cooker and cook on high for 3 to 4 hours or low for 5 to 6 hours. Quiche is done when center reaches 160°F, is set and edges are golden brown.
3203547d-2c53-4346-9780-b42b3e82c1b8 Heat 1 tablespoon of the vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium heat until shimmering. Add the mushrooms and 1/4 teaspoon salt, cover the skillet and cook until the mushrooms are softened, about 5 minutes. Uncover and continue to cook until the mushrooms are dry and browned, 5 to 10 additional minutes; transfer the mushrooms to a 6-quart slow cooker lined with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
3203547d-2c53-4346-9780-b42b3e82c1b8 Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons vegetable oil in the same skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add the onions, tomato paste, garlic, porcini and thyme, and cook until the onions are softened and lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes. Stir in the flour and cook for 1 minute. Slowly whisk in the broth, scraping up any browned bits and smoothing out any lumps. Transfer the mixture to the slow cooker.
3203547d-2c53-4346-9780-b42b3e82c1b8 Stir the wine, soy sauce and bay leaves into the slow cooker. Season the beef with salt and pepper and place in the slow cooker, nestling it in the liquid. Cover and cook on low until the beef is tender, 9 to 11 hours (or on high for 5 to 7 hours).
3203547d-2c53-4346-9780-b42b3e82c1b8 Once finished cooking, let the stew settle for 5 minutes, then remove fat from the surface using a large spoon and discard the bay leaves. In a small bowl, stir together 1 cup of the hot cooking liquid with the sour cream and Dijon, then stir the sour cream mixture into the slow cooker. Stir in the dill, season with salt and pepper, and serve.
d918a300-efd2-48b6-81c2-eb2734faf9a7 LINE a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
d918a300-efd2-48b6-81c2-eb2734faf9a7 ADD tomatoes, chicken, broth, green pepper, onion, celery, Cajun seasoning, garlic, black pepper, and cayenne pepper to prepared slow cooker. Stir gently with wooden spoon or rubber scraper to combine.
d918a300-efd2-48b6-81c2-eb2734faf9a7 COVER and cook on low for 6 hours.
d918a300-efd2-48b6-81c2-eb2734faf9a7 REMOVE lid and stir in shrimp gently with a wooden spoon or rubber scraper. Cover and cook about 3 minutes more, or until shrimp is opaque. Serve over cooked rice.
e256b711-49c3-4525-b29b-d6ed0a5d99d9 Preheat broiler. Line a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
e256b711-49c3-4525-b29b-d6ed0a5d99d9 Place the potatoes and onion in the prepared slow cooker. Top with the brisket, apple juice, thyme, salt and pepper.
e256b711-49c3-4525-b29b-d6ed0a5d99d9 Cook on low for 4 hours. Add the cabbage and apples to the slow cooker; cook on low for an additional 2 hours.
e256b711-49c3-4525-b29b-d6ed0a5d99d9 While the corned beef cooks, place rye bread on a baking sheet lined with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Spread bread with 2 tablespoons butter and broil 4 to 5 inches from heat 1 to 2 minutes or until toasted. Sprinkle with Gruyère cheese. Broil 1 to 2 minutes more or until cheese melts and browns.
e256b711-49c3-4525-b29b-d6ed0a5d99d9 Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Remove corned beef from slow cooker and thinly slice across the grain. Place on a large platter with the vegetables and apples, and drizzle with broth from the slow cooker to serve. Serve with rye bread cheese toasts. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
9759a096-8b51-4009-b9e4-c6cbf6b1fa12 OPEN Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner and place it inside a 5- or 6 1/2 -quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
9759a096-8b51-4009-b9e4-c6cbf6b1fa12 PLACE all ingredients in the lined-slow cooker; stir gently. Place lid on slow cooker.
9759a096-8b51-4009-b9e4-c6cbf6b1fa12 COOK on LOW for 7 to 8 hours OR on HIGH for 4 to 5 hours until done.
9759a096-8b51-4009-b9e4-c6cbf6b1fa12 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
6a696e97-7087-4918-aa6e-2aa7e1d11ee3 LINE a 5 to 6 quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim.
6a696e97-7087-4918-aa6e-2aa7e1d11ee3
6a696e97-7087-4918-aa6e-2aa7e1d11ee3 PLACE apples in the lined slow cooker; drizzle with lemon juice. Mix granulated sugar, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in a medium bowl. Sprinkle mixture over apples; stir gently with wooden or plastic spoon to coat apples. Drizzle with butter.
6a696e97-7087-4918-aa6e-2aa7e1d11ee3
6a696e97-7087-4918-aa6e-2aa7e1d11ee3 COVER and COOK 2 hours on LOW OR 1 hour on HIGH, until apples are done.
6a696e97-7087-4918-aa6e-2aa7e1d11ee3
6a696e97-7087-4918-aa6e-2aa7e1d11ee3 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Spoon warm apples over ice cream; serve with cookies, if desired. Remove all food and cool slow cooker completely before lifting liner from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.
6a696e97-7087-4918-aa6e-2aa7e1d11ee3
22417989-1b60-4061-915e-c923723e8269 Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.
22417989-1b60-4061-915e-c923723e8269 Melt the butter over medium-high heat in a 10–12-inch oven-safe skillet. Add the potatoes and cook 10 minutes. Add the peppers, onions and garlic. Continue cooking for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in black beans, cilantro, salt and pepper. Use a spatula to spread the mixture evenly throughout the pan. Sprinkle on cheese.
22417989-1b60-4061-915e-c923723e8269 Crack the eggs across the top of the potato mixture. Loosely cover with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
22417989-1b60-4061-915e-c923723e8269 Bake 10 minutes, remove the foil and bake an additional 5 to 8 minutes or until egg whites are fully cooked and yolk is still runny.
22417989-1b60-4061-915e-c923723e8269 Serve with fresh avocado slices and salsa.
a7454fc4-6366-41b1-acc0-36dec3336911 THAW fish if frozen. Rinse and pat dry with paper towels. Preheat grill to medium-high.
a7454fc4-6366-41b1-acc0-36dec3336911 TEAR off an 18x18-inch sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Place onion in the center of the sheet. Top with salmon. Drizzle with the olive oil and sprinkle with the salt and black pepper. Top with lemon slices. Bring up foil sides. Double-fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
a7454fc4-6366-41b1-acc0-36dec3336911 STACK flatbreads separately; wrap tightly in heavy duty aluminum foil.
a7454fc4-6366-41b1-acc0-36dec3336911 GRILL salmon packet over medium-high heat in covered grill 12 to 14 minutes or until fish begins to flake when tested with a fork and vegetables are tender.
a7454fc4-6366-41b1-acc0-36dec3336911 ADD the flatbread packet to the grill for the last 5 minutes of cooking to warm through, turning once. Remove all from grill.
a7454fc4-6366-41b1-acc0-36dec3336911 OPEN packets carefully by cutting along top folds with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape. Then open top (of) foil. Discard lemon slices. Use two forks to pull the salmon apart into chunks.
a7454fc4-6366-41b1-acc0-36dec3336911 ASSEMBLE sandwiches by topping pita with the salmon, onions, lettuce, and tomatoes. Fold in half to serve. In a small bowl, mix together the yogurt, basil, and dill. Serve over pita sandwiches.
d523520a-8898-4e48-8cc0-e5f33191235d Preheat grill to medium-high heat.
d523520a-8898-4e48-8cc0-e5f33191235d Brush corn with olive oil and individually wrap with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Place on the grill, turning frequently for 20 minutes. Allow to cool slightly before handling.
d523520a-8898-4e48-8cc0-e5f33191235d Cut corn off the cob and combine with black beans, jalapeño, cilantro and the juice of 1 lime. Season to taste with salt and pepper and set aside.
d523520a-8898-4e48-8cc0-e5f33191235d Slice avocados in half and remove the seeds but do not remove the skin yet. Squeeze the juice of the remaining lime over the avocados and lightly brush them with olive oil.
d523520a-8898-4e48-8cc0-e5f33191235d Grill flesh side down for 2 to 3 minutes and then remove. Quarter each avocado half and then carefully peel off the skin.
d523520a-8898-4e48-8cc0-e5f33191235d Wrap tortillas in foil and place on the grill while the avocados are cooking.
d523520a-8898-4e48-8cc0-e5f33191235d Build tacos by placing avocado slices on tortillas and then top with the corn and salsa.
d523520a-8898-4e48-8cc0-e5f33191235d Serve with your favorite hot sauce and additional lime wedges
fd718f9e-4f18-444f-bc55-48e96708bd39 HEAT grill to low, 325°-350°.
fd718f9e-4f18-444f-bc55-48e96708bd39 ASSEMBLE kabobs, alternating different vegetables and pineapple on wooden skewers.
fd718f9e-4f18-444f-bc55-48e96708bd39 COMBINE all ingredients for marinade in medium bowl and mix well.
fd718f9e-4f18-444f-bc55-48e96708bd39 BRUSH marinade onto fruit and veggie kabobs.
fd718f9e-4f18-444f-bc55-48e96708bd39 LINE grill with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
fd718f9e-4f18-444f-bc55-48e96708bd39 PLACE kabobs on grill on aluminum foil and grill for 10–15 minutes, or until veggies are desired doneness.
fd718f9e-4f18-444f-bc55-48e96708bd39 TRANSFER kabobs to plate to cool before serving.
a2866648-53cc-4bdf-a680-7bf99ffa4f46 Combine rice vinegar, sugar, and sesame oil in a small saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat to simmer for 2 minutes to allow the sugar to dissolve. Leave mixture to cool to room temperature.
a2866648-53cc-4bdf-a680-7bf99ffa4f46 Add cucumber, onion and chili pepper to a mixing bowl and pour over the cooled vinegar solution. Stir to mix everything together. Tightly cover bowl with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and place in fridge for 30 minutes.
a2866648-53cc-4bdf-a680-7bf99ffa4f46 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F and line a baking sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper. Place peanuts on baking sheet and season with a generous pinch of salt. Roast for 30 minutes, rotating the pan halfway through.
a2866648-53cc-4bdf-a680-7bf99ffa4f46 Remove the cucumber mixture from fridge and transfer to serving dish. Top with bean sprouts and roasted peanuts. Serve with lime wedges.
9f2d0529-6cb4-4550-a79b-9ae53738cab5 PREAHEAT the oven to 375°.
9f2d0529-6cb4-4550-a79b-9ae53738cab5 SPREAD 4 corn tortillas around a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Non-Stick 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan and evenly pour on 1/3 of the enchilada sauce on top of the tortillas.
9f2d0529-6cb4-4550-a79b-9ae53738cab5 ADD 1/3 of the black and pinto beans and ½ of the pulled rotisserie chicken all over the enchilada sauce.
9f2d0529-6cb4-4550-a79b-9ae53738cab5 SEASON everything with salt and pepper.
9f2d0529-6cb4-4550-a79b-9ae53738cab5 TOP the chicken and beans off with 1/3 of the shredded cheese.
9f2d0529-6cb4-4550-a79b-9ae53738cab5 REPEAT these steps 1 more time.
9f2d0529-6cb4-4550-a79b-9ae53738cab5 TOP off the casserole with the last 4 corn tortillas, 1/3 of enchilada sauce, 1/3 of the cheese and sliced jalapeños.
9f2d0529-6cb4-4550-a79b-9ae53738cab5 BAKE in the oven for 45 minutes.
9f2d0529-6cb4-4550-a79b-9ae53738cab5 GARNISH the baked enchiladas with lime slices, sliced avocado, sour cream and cilantro.
2befd1c3-fd33-4afc-a399-8b14dcb68a54 PREHEAT the oven to 350°
2befd1c3-fd33-4afc-a399-8b14dcb68a54 COAT the potatoes in olive oil and salt and bake in the oven for 60 minutes.
2befd1c3-fd33-4afc-a399-8b14dcb68a54 CUT the potatoes into small wedges and place in a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan.
2befd1c3-fd33-4afc-a399-8b14dcb68a54 SPREAD the butter chunks, chopped chicken, and cheddar cheese all over the potato wedges.
2befd1c3-fd33-4afc-a399-8b14dcb68a54 BAKE in the oven for 25 minutes.
2befd1c3-fd33-4afc-a399-8b14dcb68a54 FINISH the dish by spreading on the sour cream, chopped bacon and chives
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 PREHEAT the oven to 350°
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 COOK the chopped bacon in a large pot on medium-high heat until crispy.
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 REMOVE the bacon and add in the onions and cook until brown. Once they are browned add in the ground meat and cook until there is no more pink left.
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 ADD in the crushed tomatoes and chili powder and simmer on low heat.
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 WHISK in the tomato paste to thicken the sauce.
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 SEASON the sauce with salt and pepper and keep warm.
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 BOIL the macaroni noodles in a large pot of boiling water and cook until done.
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 STRAIN the noodles and add them to the tomato saucepot and toss.
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 POUR the noodles and sauce into a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan.
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 SPRINKLE on the shredded cheddar cheese and bake in the oven for 30 minutes or until the cheese is melted and starting to brown.
d9b94761-bda0-4ac5-8dc1-5b482910ff70 GARNISH with sliced green onions.
f11eca8b-381a-4e9d-94be-661b4501f4ec PREHEAT oven to 425°F. Line a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper.
f11eca8b-381a-4e9d-94be-661b4501f4ec MIX broccoli, soup, stuffing mix, 1/2 cup cheese and water together in a large bowl until well blended. Spread evenly in lined pan.
f11eca8b-381a-4e9d-94be-661b4501f4ec TOP with chicken. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
f11eca8b-381a-4e9d-94be-661b4501f4ec BAKE 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken reaches 170°F and juices run clear. Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.Cover with a sheet of foil; let stand until cheese melts.
fc10e780-0879-440c-973c-7447d8a64f79 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
fc10e780-0879-440c-973c-7447d8a64f79 COMBINE the rice, black beans, corn, diced tomatoes, green bell pepper, chopped chicken and enchilada sauce into a large bowl and mix.
fc10e780-0879-440c-973c-7447d8a64f79 POUR the mixture into a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan and spread it out using a rubber spatula.
fc10e780-0879-440c-973c-7447d8a64f79 SPRINKLE the shredded cheese all over the top.
fc10e780-0879-440c-973c-7447d8a64f79 BAKE at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the cheese has melted and is lightly browned.
c3a02355-4bd4-43c6-ac60-ca5269d09d8d PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
c3a02355-4bd4-43c6-ac60-ca5269d09d8d MELT the butter in a small saucepan and whisk in the flour until combined to form a roux. Set aside.
c3a02355-4bd4-43c6-ac60-ca5269d09d8d BOIL the milk in a large pot and whisk in the roux until it becomes very thick.
c3a02355-4bd4-43c6-ac60-ca5269d09d8d WHISK the cream cheese and shredded cheddar cheese into the thickened milk until completely combined.
c3a02355-4bd4-43c6-ac60-ca5269d09d8d SEASON the cheesy milk with salt and pepper and nutmeg.
c3a02355-4bd4-43c6-ac60-ca5269d09d8d BOIL the macaroni noodles in a large pot of boiling water and cook until done.
c3a02355-4bd4-43c6-ac60-ca5269d09d8d COMBINE the cheesy milk with the strained and cooked macaroni noodles, as well as the pulled rotisserie chicken and mix.
c3a02355-4bd4-43c6-ac60-ca5269d09d8d POUR the mixture into a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan and top off with the crushed cornflakes.
c3a02355-4bd4-43c6-ac60-ca5269d09d8d PLACE the pan in the oven and bake for 45 minutes.
b1c0c4fc-ffa9-4bb0-a5cb-5585ba70150b PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
b1c0c4fc-ffa9-4bb0-a5cb-5585ba70150b MELT the butter in a large pot over medium-high heat and add in the diced onions and mushrooms and lightly brown.
b1c0c4fc-ffa9-4bb0-a5cb-5585ba70150b SPRINKLE the flour on top of the onions and mushrooms and mix in to form a roux and cook for 3 minutes.
b1c0c4fc-ffa9-4bb0-a5cb-5585ba70150b POUR in the milk and whisk over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes until it becomes very thick.
b1c0c4fc-ffa9-4bb0-a5cb-5585ba70150b WHISK in 1 cup of the shredded cheese until all of the lumps are melted in.
b1c0c4fc-ffa9-4bb0-a5cb-5585ba70150b ADD the sauce to a large bowl and mix it together with the drained tuna, frozen peas, cooked egg noodles and salt and pepper until completely combined.
b1c0c4fc-ffa9-4bb0-a5cb-5585ba70150b TRANSFER the mixture into a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan and sprinkle on the remaining 1 cup of shredded cheese followed up by sprinkling the bread crumbs, completely covering the top.
b1c0c4fc-ffa9-4bb0-a5cb-5585ba70150b BAKE in the oven on 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the top begins to brown.
b1c0c4fc-ffa9-4bb0-a5cb-5585ba70150b SERVE hot.
676f0bd4-5fc6-4c74-b44a-bfa68bc93252 COOK the cut potatoes in a large pot of boiling salted water for 20 minutes. Immediately strain the hot water and shock the potatoes with ice to chill them.
676f0bd4-5fc6-4c74-b44a-bfa68bc93252 STRAIN the potatoes and add it to a large bowl along with the diced hard-boiled eggs, celery, onion, mustard, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and mix thoroughly until combined.
676f0bd4-5fc6-4c74-b44a-bfa68bc93252 TRANSFER the tossed potato salad into a Reynolds Kitchens® Pasta & Casserole Pan and chill before serving.
085a38da-7ea7-4a95-8fe3-c8a06486c0fe PREHEAT the oven to 375°
085a38da-7ea7-4a95-8fe3-c8a06486c0fe BOIL the sweet potatoes in a large pot of salted water until they are completely cooked through. Note: They should slide right off from a fork when they are pierced.
085a38da-7ea7-4a95-8fe3-c8a06486c0fe DRAIN the water from the potatoes and add them to a large bowl along with 2 ounces of butter, eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and pepper and mash them together until completely combined.
085a38da-7ea7-4a95-8fe3-c8a06486c0fe ADD the mashed sweet potatoes to a Reynolds Kitchesn® Pasta & Casserole Pan.
085a38da-7ea7-4a95-8fe3-c8a06486c0fe PLACE the pecans, flour, brown sugar and remaining butter into a food processor and pulse until the pecans are chopped and the butter is the size of rice.
085a38da-7ea7-4a95-8fe3-c8a06486c0fe SPREAD the pecan mixture all over the top of the sweet potatoes along with the mini marshmallows.
085a38da-7ea7-4a95-8fe3-c8a06486c0fe BAKE in the oven on 375° for 45 minutes or until the marshmallows are golden brown.
085a38da-7ea7-4a95-8fe3-c8a06486c0fe SERVE hot.
dffd4532-94f3-4c19-af36-5abd288e8db5 PREHEAT the oven to 375°
dffd4532-94f3-4c19-af36-5abd288e8db5 MIX together the breadcrumbs, olive oil, mustard, rosemary, salt and pepper until it is completely combined.
dffd4532-94f3-4c19-af36-5abd288e8db5 RUB the mixture all over the pork loin to form a crust on the outside.
dffd4532-94f3-4c19-af36-5abd288e8db5 PLACE the pork in a Reynolds Kitchens® Roasting Pan.
dffd4532-94f3-4c19-af36-5abd288e8db5 BAKE the pork in the oven on 375° for 80 minutes or until the pork is firm, golden brown and cooked throughout. Note: The meat will be white when completely cooked.
dffd4532-94f3-4c19-af36-5abd288e8db5 SLICE and serve.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 PREHEAT the oven to a temperature of 350°
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 COOK the onions and garlic in a large pot on medium-high heat with 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Once they are browned add in the ground meat and cook until there is no more pink left.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 ADD in the crushed tomatoes and basil and simmer the sauce on low heat.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 WHISK in the tomato paste to thicken the tomato sauce.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 SEASON the sauce with salt and pepper and keep warm.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 BOIL the Mostaccioli pasta noodles in a large pot of boiling water and cook pasta until done.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 STRAIN the pasta noodles and add them to the tomato saucepot and toss.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 POUR the pasta noodles and sauce into a Reynolds Kitchens® Disposable Bakeware Pan.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 SPRINKLE on the Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese over top of the noodles and sauce.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 BAKE in the oven for 30 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and starting to brown.
6baff646-cf4c-43e0-91b6-c75ebb8ff860 GARNISH the dish with any remaining cheese and fresh chopped basil to prepare this authentic food for dinner.
686fa77b-673e-4edd-afe6-7d70a9541956 PREHEAT oven to 375°.
686fa77b-673e-4edd-afe6-7d70a9541956 BOIL the lasagna noodles in a large pot of boiling salted water until the noodles are al dente or slightly crunchy (about 12 minutes).
686fa77b-673e-4edd-afe6-7d70a9541956 ADD the cream, pumpkin, and nutmeg to a large pot and cook on medium high heat until it becomes thick like Alfredo sauce (about 20 minutes). Season with salt and pepper.
686fa77b-673e-4edd-afe6-7d70a9541956 LAYER into a Reynolds Kitchens® Lasagna Pan as follows: Pour a small amount of the pumpkin cream to coat the entire bottom of the pan. Next, evenly spread the lasagna noodles on top of the cream. Spread a thin layer of ricotta cheese on top of the noodles followed up by evenly spreading ½ cups of chopped chicken, 1 cup of spinach leaves, ½ cup of mozzarella cheese, ¼ cup of Parmesan cheese, a small amount of pumpkin cream, salt and pepper.
686fa77b-673e-4edd-afe6-7d70a9541956 REPEAT the process 3 more times by finishing with a layer of noodles, pumpkin cream, mozzarella cheese, and Parmesan cheese.
686fa77b-673e-4edd-afe6-7d70a9541956 BAKE in the oven on 375° for 25 minutes, or until cheese is golden brown.
686fa77b-673e-4edd-afe6-7d70a9541956 GARNISH with chopped sage.
bb192331-06fd-4ae1-8d1b-dcbe6ce29f61 PREHEAT the oven to 375°
bb192331-06fd-4ae1-8d1b-dcbe6ce29f61 CUT the cornbread into 1” inch chunks and add them to a large bowl.
bb192331-06fd-4ae1-8d1b-dcbe6ce29f61 COOK the Italian sausage in a large sauté pan on medium-high heat until golden brown and cooked through.
bb192331-06fd-4ae1-8d1b-dcbe6ce29f61 REMOVE the cooked Italian sausage and set aside, and add to the hot sauté pan the onions, peppers, celery and carrots and cook for 4 to 6 minutes on high heat while continuing to stir.
bb192331-06fd-4ae1-8d1b-dcbe6ce29f61 PLACE the cooked vegetables in the large bowl with corn bread chunks and cooked Italian sausage.
bb192331-06fd-4ae1-8d1b-dcbe6ce29f61 WHISK together the stock and eggs in a separate bowl and add it to the large bowl of vegetables, cornbread and Italian sausage and fold together until combined, and season with salt and pepper.
bb192331-06fd-4ae1-8d1b-dcbe6ce29f61 PLACE the cornbread into a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Pasta & Casserole Pan and bake in the oven on 375° for 30 minutes or until the cornbread on top is lightly browned.
bb192331-06fd-4ae1-8d1b-dcbe6ce29f61 SERVE hot.
1b435b56-0821-43f4-8e22-06570a8c3cb5 PREHEAT the oven to 375°.
1b435b56-0821-43f4-8e22-06570a8c3cb5 ADD the garlic, thyme leaves, olive oil, salt and pepper to a food processor and process until it becomes a thick paste.
1b435b56-0821-43f4-8e22-06570a8c3cb5 PLACE the rib roast in a Reynolds Kitchens® Roasting Pan and place the chopped carrots, celery, and onions around the rib roast.
1b435b56-0821-43f4-8e22-06570a8c3cb5 RUB the garlic and thyme paste all over the rib roast so that it is coated on all sides.
1b435b56-0821-43f4-8e22-06570a8c3cb5 BAKE the rib roast on 375°F for 90 to 100 minutes or until it reaches an internal temperature of at least 125°F or medium-rare. The rib roast should be firm on the outside and browned on all sides.
1b435b56-0821-43f4-8e22-06570a8c3cb5 REST the rib roast for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.
f4dbcd9d-10d3-4b6f-bd5b-2003eda3c00c PREHEAT the oven to 425°.
f4dbcd9d-10d3-4b6f-bd5b-2003eda3c00c MIX together the salt, granulated garlic, onion powder, chili powder and red pepper flakes until combined and set aside
f4dbcd9d-10d3-4b6f-bd5b-2003eda3c00c PLACE the chicken in a large bowl and coat on all sides with the olive oil and spice blend.
f4dbcd9d-10d3-4b6f-bd5b-2003eda3c00c PLACE the seasoned and oiled chicken into a Reynolds Kitchens®Casserole Bakeware Pan and leave a 1” inch gap in between each piece of chicken.
f4dbcd9d-10d3-4b6f-bd5b-2003eda3c00c BAKE in the oven for 25 minutes and then baste with the bbq sauce.
f4dbcd9d-10d3-4b6f-bd5b-2003eda3c00c TURN each piece of chicken over, baste with more bbq sauce and cook in the oven for another 20 minutes, or until the chicken begins to brown and is cooked throughout.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a PREHEAT the oven 350°.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a MELT the butter in a large pot on high heat and add in the onions to sauté, about 4 minutes.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a WHISK in the flour to form a roux.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a POUR in the milk and cook over medium heat until it becomes thick.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a WHISK in 8 ounces of shredded mozzarella cheese until it is completely combined.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a ADD the cooked noodles, chopped cooked chicken, chopped tomatoes and basil to the pot with the sauce and mix until combined. Season with salt and pepper.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a POUR the mixture into a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Lasagna pan with hot pad and carrier and sprinkle on the remaining 1 cup of shredded mozzarella cheese.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a BAKE in the oven for 30 minutes or until the cheese on top is lightly browned.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a GARNISH with chopped tomatoes and basil.
e551f37e-b209-469e-980f-65a1e8bd167a SERVE hot.
480f4d32-5df7-4010-becd-84da6d79b093 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
480f4d32-5df7-4010-becd-84da6d79b093 MELT the butter in a large pot over medium-high heat and add in the diced onions and lightly brown.
480f4d32-5df7-4010-becd-84da6d79b093 SPRINKLE the flour on top of the onions and mix in to form a roux and cook for 3 minutes.
480f4d32-5df7-4010-becd-84da6d79b093 POUR in the milk and whisk over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes until it becomes very thick.
480f4d32-5df7-4010-becd-84da6d79b093 WHISK in the mozzarella and 1 cup of Parmesan cheese until there are no lumps.
480f4d32-5df7-4010-becd-84da6d79b093 ADD the sauce to a large bowl and mix it together with the chopped cooked chicken breasts, cooked fettuccini, salt and pepper until completely combined.
480f4d32-5df7-4010-becd-84da6d79b093 POUR the pasta into a Reynolds Kitchens® ​13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan and evenly sprinkle on 1 cup of parmesan cheese.
480f4d32-5df7-4010-becd-84da6d79b093 BAKE in the oven on 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the top begins to brown.
480f4d32-5df7-4010-becd-84da6d79b093 SERVE hot and garnish with chopped parsley.
7b05fd01-adcc-4c79-8708-2074c2d12d85 PREHEAT the oven to 375°.
7b05fd01-adcc-4c79-8708-2074c2d12d85 MIX together the ground beef, peppers, onions, egg, soaked French bread, hot sauce to taste, and salt and pepper to taste.
7b05fd01-adcc-4c79-8708-2074c2d12d85 DIVIDE the ground meat mixture into 3 Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Non-Stick Mini-Loaf Pans with Parchment Lining and bake them in the oven on 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until the tops become brown and the meatloaf is firm to the touch.
7b05fd01-adcc-4c79-8708-2074c2d12d85 EASILY REMOVE the meatloaves from the pans and top off with the caramelized onions and your favorite BBQ sauce.
7b05fd01-adcc-4c79-8708-2074c2d12d85 SERVE hot.
07dfecd4-6c47-4af0-ae6a-482d4d38ce76 Preheat oven to 400°F. Arrange bacon in a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Bacon Pan.
07dfecd4-6c47-4af0-ae6a-482d4d38ce76 Bake for 8 minutes, until almost crisp. Drizzle the bacon with 1 tablespoon maple syrup and bake 4 to 6 minutes more or until glazed. Cook longer for crispier bacon. Cool and chop.
07dfecd4-6c47-4af0-ae6a-482d4d38ce76 Stir together the cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl. In a small bowl, whisk together milk, eggs, butter and remaining 4 tablespoons maple syrup. Add the milk mixture all at once to the cornmeal mixture. Add the chopped bacon. Stir just until moistened. Pour the batter into a Reynolds Kitchens® 8x8 Bakeware Pan.
07dfecd4-6c47-4af0-ae6a-482d4d38ce76 Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Let cool slightly before serving. Drizzle with additional maple syrup, if desired.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 PREHEAT the oven to 375°F.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 COOK the bacon in a large pot on high heat until crispy and brown.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 REMOVE the bacon from the pot once cooked and browned and set aside, and add in the onions and butter and cook for 4 to 5 minutes on medium heat.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 ADD The flour into the pot with onions and butter and stir together and cook for 2 more minutes.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 WHISK the milk in to the pot until combined and simmer on low heat for 10 minutes or until it begins to become thick.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 FINISH the mixture by whisking in the grated Swiss cheese, salt and pepper.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 FOLD in the bacon and sliced brussel sprouts to the pot and then pour the mixture into a Reynolds Kitchens® 8x8 Bakeware Pan.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 SPRINKLE the breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese to the top of the creamy brussel sprouts.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 BAKE in the oven on 375° for 30 minutes or until the breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese are golden brown.
a8c7d170-cce0-48b0-ac7b-3171e9764ec9 SERVE hot.
4fee0cfc-5b06-43a8-a581-0f4607a835ee COMBINE all dry seasonings and ingredients in a bowl and mix.
4fee0cfc-5b06-43a8-a581-0f4607a835ee RUB the dry seasoning mixture on all sides of the brisket, cover with foil and place in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
4fee0cfc-5b06-43a8-a581-0f4607a835ee PREHEAT the oven to 300°.
4fee0cfc-5b06-43a8-a581-0f4607a835ee COOK the onions in a large sauté pan on medium heat in 1 tablespoon of butter until they are brown (30 to 35 minutes).
4fee0cfc-5b06-43a8-a581-0f4607a835ee PLACE the rubbed Brisket into a Reynolds Kitchens® Roaster pan, cover with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and cook in the oven for about 3 hours.
4fee0cfc-5b06-43a8-a581-0f4607a835ee TURN the oven temperature up to 325°, remove the foil and cook for 1 hour.
4fee0cfc-5b06-43a8-a581-0f4607a835ee POUR 1 1/2 cups of BBQ sauce all over the brisket once they are done cooking and slice thin against the grain of the beef.
4fee0cfc-5b06-43a8-a581-0f4607a835ee SERVE the brisket with the remaining 1/2 cup of BBQ sauce, a tablespoon of caramelized onions on a bun.
4d1cfedc-95a5-41a6-baeb-b450ec529a3b Preheat oven to 350°F.
4d1cfedc-95a5-41a6-baeb-b450ec529a3b Remove the roast from the refrigerator about hour before cooking so it can reach room temperature. Trim all the fat off the meat. Lightly spray meat with olive oil and generously season with salt, pepper, and rosemary. Using a sharp knife pierce the meat and insert slivers of garlic in each hole, pushing all the way in. If using a thermometer place it all the way into the center of the meat now. Place into the Reynolds Kitchens® 10lb Roaster pan.
4d1cfedc-95a5-41a6-baeb-b450ec529a3b Roast until the thermometer reads 130° for rare, 140° for medium rare, 150° for medium, and 155-160° for well done. Remove the roast from the oven when it reaches your desired temperature and let it rest for about minutes before you cut it so that the juices distributed evenly.
45032b36-aaa6-47eb-9cf6-71d58d733d88 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
45032b36-aaa6-47eb-9cf6-71d58d733d88 Rinse and Dry chicken. Rub melted butter all over chicken. Sprinkle rosemary and basil. Place chicken in a Reynolds Kitchens® 10lb Roaster pan.
45032b36-aaa6-47eb-9cf6-71d58d733d88 Roast in the preheated oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until chicken is cooked through and juices run clear. Cooking time will vary a bit depending on the size of the bird.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Preheat the oven to 350°.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Heat the olive oil in a large pot on high heat and add in the onions and sauté for 4 to 6 minutes.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Add in the tomatoes and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Stir in the tomato paste to thicken and add in the dry oregano, dry basil, and adjust the seasonings with salt and pepper. Keep warm.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Pour 1 cup of the tomato sauce in the bottom of 1 Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Lasagna Pan with Hot Pad and Carrier.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Place 3 cooked lasagna noodles on top of the sauce.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Spread 2 ounces of ricotta cheese evenly across the 3 noodles.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Layer on 4 ounces of cooked Italian sausage, shredded mozzarella, shredded parmesan cheese, and asiago cheese followed up by adding on 1 more cup of tomato sauce.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Repeat the process 3 more times finishing with a small amount of shredded parmesan cheese.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Bake in the oven on 350° for 60 minutes or until the cheese has completely melted and is lightly browned on top.
9c691602-4524-4c07-891a-82cef5d920c6 Serve hot.
338c064a-2b11-4e29-9f47-33d0a0aa5623 Preheat the oven to 350°.
338c064a-2b11-4e29-9f47-33d0a0aa5623 Pour 1 cup of the tomato sauce in the bottom of a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Lasagna Pan with Hot Pad and Carrier and sprinkle on 4 ounces of shredded mozzarella cheese.
338c064a-2b11-4e29-9f47-33d0a0aa5623 Place 3 cooked lasagna noodles on top of the sauce.
338c064a-2b11-4e29-9f47-33d0a0aa5623 Layer on evenly squash and zucchini slices followed up by adding on 1 cup of tomato sauce, 4 ounces of shredded mozzarella and 1 ounce of shredded parmesan cheese.
338c064a-2b11-4e29-9f47-33d0a0aa5623 Next evenly layer on all of the slices of eggplant and sliced button mushrooms followed up by adding on 1 cup of tomato sauce, 4 ounces of shredded mozzarella and 1 ounce of shredded parmesan cheese.
338c064a-2b11-4e29-9f47-33d0a0aa5623 Repeat the process of the squash and zucchini layer. Use the remaining shredded parmesan cheese.
338c064a-2b11-4e29-9f47-33d0a0aa5623 Bake in the oven on 350° for 60 minutes or until the cheese has completely melted and is lightly browned on top.
338c064a-2b11-4e29-9f47-33d0a0aa5623 Serve hot.
422a4f77-340e-472d-9cd3-a56ce0b54ffd PREHEAT grill to 400°F. Use a fork to poke drainage holes into 6 sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil. Brush pineapple rings with olive oil, then fully wrap each in foil.
422a4f77-340e-472d-9cd3-a56ce0b54ffd GRILL for 1 to 2 minutes in covered grill over direct heat. Turn pineapple and grill additional 1 to 2 minutes or until pineapple is tender.
422a4f77-340e-472d-9cd3-a56ce0b54ffd REMOVE from foil and transfer each grilled pineapple slice to a bowl. Add a scoop of vanilla ice cream, then drizzle with chocolate syrup, add rainbow sprinkles and top with cherry. Serve immediately.
0687cef4-96a1-49b5-b453-c784f4872721 PREHEAT the oven to 425°
0687cef4-96a1-49b5-b453-c784f4872721 COMBINE all ingredients together in a Reynolds Kitchens® Lasagna Bakeware Pan, season with salt and pepper, and mix
0687cef4-96a1-49b5-b453-c784f4872721 BAKE in the oven on 425° for 45 minutes or until everything is golden brown and the potatoes are cooked through. After 20 minutes of cooking, stir the ingredients to move items from the bottom to the top.
64e89b2f-c4e4-4db9-89cc-c7d58c74a2ed PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
64e89b2f-c4e4-4db9-89cc-c7d58c74a2ed MIX together the apples, lemon juice, sugar and nutmeg in a bowl until combined.
64e89b2f-c4e4-4db9-89cc-c7d58c74a2ed POUR the apple mixture into a Reynolds Kitchens® 8x8 Dessert Pan.
64e89b2f-c4e4-4db9-89cc-c7d58c74a2ed ADD the oats, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and unsalted butter to a food processor and pulse until the butter is the size of rice.
64e89b2f-c4e4-4db9-89cc-c7d58c74a2ed SPREAD the oats and butter mixture all over the apples and make sure the apples are completely covered.
64e89b2f-c4e4-4db9-89cc-c7d58c74a2ed BAKE in the oven for 35 minutes on 350° or until the oatmeal topping is slightly brown.
64e89b2f-c4e4-4db9-89cc-c7d58c74a2ed SERVE hot with vanilla ice cream
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec COMBINE the strawberries, lemon juice, and ½ cup of sugar and add it to a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Dessert Pan and set aside.
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec MIX together the flour, baking powder, salt and ½ cups of sugar until it is combined. Thinly cut in the butter using a pastry knife until and mix in with the dry ingredients until it is the size of rice. Form a well in the middle of the mixture.
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec WHISK together the eggs and milk in a separate bowl and bowl and pour it into the well in the flour and butter mixture bowl.
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec MIX in the liquid slowly using a fork until just combined.
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec PLACE the dough onto a clean dry surface that has been dusted with flour and roll out until it is ½ inch thick.
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec CUT 3 inch circles using a cookie cutter and place each of them lined up on top of the Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Dessert Pan with strawberries.
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec BRUSH the top of each biscuit with melted butter and sprinkle on sugar in the raw.
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec PLACE the pan in the oven and bake for 35 minutes on 350°.
4cb0df0b-7c97-46dd-bd00-50771e1084ec SERVE the strawberry shortcake with whipped cream.
a7fb26a0-1df8-436f-8426-63b455be05c1 PREHEAT oven to 350°.
a7fb26a0-1df8-436f-8426-63b455be05c1 MIX the blackberries in a large bowl along with the lemon juice and ½ cup of sugar until combined and pour it into a Reynolds Kitchens® 8x8 Dessert Pan.
a7fb26a0-1df8-436f-8426-63b455be05c1 WHISK the flour, oats, baking powder, and brown sugar in a large bowl and cut in the butter using a pastry knife. (Alternate: place the flour, oats, baking powder, brown sugar, and butter into a food processer and pulse until the butter is the size of rice.)
a7fb26a0-1df8-436f-8426-63b455be05c1 MIX in the milk until just combined.
a7fb26a0-1df8-436f-8426-63b455be05c1 POUR the batter on top of the blackberries and bake in the oven for 35 minutes.
a7fb26a0-1df8-436f-8426-63b455be05c1 SERVE the cobbler hot.
a9a2af98-dcca-40fd-a2f1-ce770f4ad570 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
a9a2af98-dcca-40fd-a2f1-ce770f4ad570 WHISK together the melted butter and brown sugar until combined.
a9a2af98-dcca-40fd-a2f1-ce770f4ad570 MIX in eggs, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, white chocolate chips, and walnuts until combined.
a9a2af98-dcca-40fd-a2f1-ce770f4ad570 POUR the mixture into a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Dessert Pan and bake in the oven for 30 to 35 minutes on 350°.
a9a2af98-dcca-40fd-a2f1-ce770f4ad570 COOL the brownies on a rack before serving.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 PREHEAT oven to 400°F.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 PULSE together the flour, powdered sugar and butter until combined. Drizzle in the water until combined and place on a dry surface dusted with flour.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 ROLL out the dough until it is 1/8-inch thick and lay over a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware 9-Inch Pie Pan.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 TRIM the excess dough and form the dough around the outside of the pan.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 WHISK together the eggs, sugars, pumpkin, pumpkin pie seasoning and milk until combined.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 POUR the pumpkin batter into the pie dough shell pan.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 BAKE in the oven for 15 minutes on 400°F.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 TURN down the oven after 15 minutes to 350°F and finish baking for 40 minutes or until the pie crust is golden brown.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 COOL the pie completely before serving.
ef424f32-6ff1-44ef-9083-70505c3b9760 SERVE with whipped cream.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba PREHEAT the oven to 350°F.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba CUT the dough in half to make 2 separate balls.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba ROLL out each dough ball until they are 1/8” inches thick.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba LAY one of the rolled out dough’s over a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware 9-inch pie pan.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba TRIM the excess dough and form the dough around the outside of the pan.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba RESERVE the other rolled out dough to lie over the top.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba MIX together the apples, lemon juice, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour in a large bowl until completely combined and pour it into the pie dough shell pan.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba PLACE the other rolled out dough over the top of the apples and form it to the outside pie crust and trim any excess.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba WHISK together the egg and milk and brush the entire top of the pie.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba CUT 4 small slits in the center of the pie.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba BAKE in the oven 350° for 60 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.
4acdae99-1d1f-428a-ae37-2f9895f01eba SERVE warm with vanilla ice cream.
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e PREHEAT the oven to 375°
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e ROLL out the dough until it is 1/8” inches thick and lay over a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware 9 inch pie pan.
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e TRIM the excess dough and form the dough around the outside of the pan.
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e COMBINE the mashed sweet potatoes, brown sugar, butter, cinnamon, nutmeg, eggs and whipping cream into a large bowl until completely mixed together.
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e POUR the mixture into the pie dough shell pan.
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e BAKE in the oven on 375° for 65 minutes or until the crust is golden brown and the pie has set in the center.
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e WHISK the egg whites and sugar in a standing mixer with the whisk attachment until they have formed soft peaks.
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e ADD in the marshmallow crème slowly until completely combined and whip until stiff peaks are formed.
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e REMOVE the pie after it is done cooking and add the marshmallow merengue to the top of the cooked pumpkin pie and return it to the oven and bake for another 10 minutes or until the merengue is lightly browned.
342254d2-c6ea-4a3d-8f71-d8d3bc12ed5e COOL completely before serving.
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 PREHEAT the oven to 350°
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 WHISK together the flour, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and baking soda in a large bowl until combined and set aside.
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 PLACE the milk in a microwave safe bowl and cook in the microwave on high for 90 seconds.
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 WHISK the butter into the bowl with the hot milk until it has melted.
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 ADD in the brown sugar and molasses and mix.
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 STIR in the egg.
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 ADD the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients bowl and mix until it is completely combined.
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 POUR the batter into a Reynolds Kitchens® 8x8 Dessert Pan.
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 BAKE in the oven on 350° for 30 minutes or until it is firm in the center.
38177942-b981-416c-a713-86ac9bab2942 COOL the cake completely. Serve with whipped cream.
ef0003a5-0592-4bd2-b49f-21668af6e960 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
ef0003a5-0592-4bd2-b49f-21668af6e960 MIX together oil and sugar in a standing mixer with the whisk attachment until combined well.
ef0003a5-0592-4bd2-b49f-21668af6e960 ADD 1 egg at a time into the oil and sugar mixture until it is combined and then pour in the vanilla.
ef0003a5-0592-4bd2-b49f-21668af6e960 BEAT in the canned pumpkin.
ef0003a5-0592-4bd2-b49f-21668af6e960 COMBINE the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in a medium size bowl and slowly add it to the oil and sugar mixture making sure to stop the mixer to scrape to combine all of the ingredients.
ef0003a5-0592-4bd2-b49f-21668af6e960 DIVIDE the batter by pouring it into 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Loaf Pans with Parchment Lining.
ef0003a5-0592-4bd2-b49f-21668af6e960 BAKE at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until the top is browned and the center is firm.
a996afaa-09de-4939-832e-3ca1511bbb6c PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
a996afaa-09de-4939-832e-3ca1511bbb6c MIX together the butter and sugar in a standing mixer with the whisk attachment until combined, about 3 to 4 minutes.
a996afaa-09de-4939-832e-3ca1511bbb6c ADD 1 egg at a time into the oil and sugar mixture until it is combined and then pour in the vanilla.
a996afaa-09de-4939-832e-3ca1511bbb6c COMBINE the flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in a medium size bowl and slowly add it to the oil and sugar mixture making sure to stop the mixer to scrape to combine all of the ingredients.
a996afaa-09de-4939-832e-3ca1511bbb6c FOLD in the zucchini and chopped pecans until combined.
a996afaa-09de-4939-832e-3ca1511bbb6c DIVIDE the batter by pouring it into 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Loaf Pans with Parchment Lining.
a996afaa-09de-4939-832e-3ca1511bbb6c BAKE at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until the top is golden brown and the center is firm.
89982040-46d2-43bc-8e32-6811aa0c796a PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
89982040-46d2-43bc-8e32-6811aa0c796a CREAM the butter and sugar together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed until it becomes light and fluffy.
89982040-46d2-43bc-8e32-6811aa0c796a ADD in 1 egg at a time until it is completely mixed in.
89982040-46d2-43bc-8e32-6811aa0c796a POUR in the vanilla and mix until it is combined in.
89982040-46d2-43bc-8e32-6811aa0c796a MIX the mashed bananas into the creamed butter and sugar mixer on low speed until it is combined.
89982040-46d2-43bc-8e32-6811aa0c796a WHISK together the flour, baking soda and baking powder in a large bowl and slowly add it to the mixer on low speed.
89982040-46d2-43bc-8e32-6811aa0c796a FOLD the walnuts into the mixer using a spatula and divide the batter evenly into 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Loaf Pans with Parchment Lining.
89982040-46d2-43bc-8e32-6811aa0c796a BAKE on 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until the top of the bread is golden brown and the center is firm.
89982040-46d2-43bc-8e32-6811aa0c796a COOL before serving.
87d8911a-e018-4865-951d-f3faf83d0e78 PREHEAT the oven to 400°F.
87d8911a-e018-4865-951d-f3faf83d0e78 WHISK together marmalade, orange juice, orange zest, brown sugar, honey and cinnamon in a medium-sized pot until combined.
87d8911a-e018-4865-951d-f3faf83d0e78 BOIL the mixture for 5 to 7 minutes or until it becomes thick and set aside.
87d8911a-e018-4865-951d-f3faf83d0e78 PLACE the ham skin side up on a Reynolds Kitchens® 10lb Roaster Pan.
87d8911a-e018-4865-951d-f3faf83d0e78 SLICE the outside of the ham on all sides to create 1 inch segments.
87d8911a-e018-4865-951d-f3faf83d0e78 PUSH 1 clove into each 1 inch sliced segment all around the ham.
87d8911a-e018-4865-951d-f3faf83d0e78 BRUSH the outside of the ham with the orange glaze.
87d8911a-e018-4865-951d-f3faf83d0e78 BAKE in the oven for 45 minutes while basting with the glaze every 15 minutes. The ham should be well browned on the outside when it is finished.
87d8911a-e018-4865-951d-f3faf83d0e78 GLAZE the ham with the orange glaze before slicing or serving.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b CREAM together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b ADD in the vanilla and then 1 egg at a time until mixed into the butter-sugar mixture.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b MIX the flour, baking powder and salt together in a bowl and add it into the creamed butter-sugar mixture while alternating with the milk but beginning and ending with the dry ingredients. Be sure to stop and scrape the sides of the bowl often.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b POUR the cake batter into the Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Dessert Pan.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b BAKE the cake in the oven on 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown and firm in the center.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b COOL the cake on a cooling rack for 10 to 15 minutes.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b WHIP the butter and cream cheese in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment until light and fluffy.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b ADD in the vanilla and powdered sugar until completely mixed in.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b WHISK in red food coloring drops until a light pink color has been achieved.
85566b08-f722-4d46-a47d-9186f1247c1b FROST the cooled vanilla cake with the pink frosting and sprinkle on sprinkles and use the white icing to make cross diagonal lines.
580bc503-b2d8-4c92-bf16-49400a13cb62 Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Set aside. The sheet will catch spills in the oven later on.
580bc503-b2d8-4c92-bf16-49400a13cb62 Place the potato slices in a large pot and cover with cold water. Season with salt and bring to boil for 5 minutes. Drain in a colander and allow the potatoes to steam for 1 minute.
580bc503-b2d8-4c92-bf16-49400a13cb62 Rub baking dish with the garlic clove and generously butter the dish. Finely chop the garlic. Set aside.
580bc503-b2d8-4c92-bf16-49400a13cb62 With the heat off, transfer the potatoes back to the pot and add heavy cream, thyme, half of the Parmesan cheese, chopped garlic, butter, salt and pepper. Stir all of the ingredients together until the potatoes are well coated.
580bc503-b2d8-4c92-bf16-49400a13cb62 Spread the potatoes evenly in the buttered baking dish. Pour any remaining liquid on top of the potatoes. Place the baking dish on the prepared baking sheet. Cover the baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and bake for 40 minutes. Remove the foil from the baking dish, add the remaining cheese and bake for 15–20 minutes, or until golden brown.
63fd62f6-ea03-4349-8ce7-683d38f64e72 Preheat oven to 400°F. Tear off an 18x18-inch piece of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil; set aside. In a small bowl, combine butter, 2 tablespoons thyme, shallots, and lemon zest.
63fd62f6-ea03-4349-8ce7-683d38f64e72 Place 2 ice cubes in the center of the foil. Add sliced potatoes and leek to center of foil, sprinkle with salt and pepper, and dot with butter mixture. Bring up sides of foil over potatoes; fold down two times. Double-fold both ends of foil to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation. Place packet on a baking sheet with 1-inch sides.
63fd62f6-ea03-4349-8ce7-683d38f64e72 Bake 40 to 45 minutes, or until potatoes are tender. Transfer to a serving plate. Open packet carefully; top with shredded cheese and remaining 1 tablespoon thyme.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d LINE cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with Smart Grid®; set aside. No need to add extra grease or spray your cookie sheets.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d KNEAD flour into sugar cookie dough until well blended.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d ROLL out half of cookie dough at a time to 1/4-inch thickness between lightly floured sheets of Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with Smart Grid®. Using large and small circles, eggs, carrot, bunny and basket-shaped cookie cutters, cut out cookies; place on parchment-lined cookie sheets.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d BEAT powdered sugar, meringue powder, water and extract in a large bowl, with an electric mixer, on high speed until smooth and thick, about 1 minute.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d DIVIDE icing into 7 small bowls. Keep one bowl of frosting white. Stir food coloring in remaining frosting to make purple, blue, orange, yellow, pink and green icing. Cover icing tightly when not in use, icing dries quickly.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d PIPE outlines of cookies with contrasting colors of icing using a decorating bag with tip. Or, place icing in plastic zipper bags. Snip off one corner with scissors and use to pipe icing.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d FOR SUGARED OUTLINES, sprinkle heavily with sugar crystals while icing is wet. Lightly shake off excess crystals. TIP: Sprinkle over Parchment Paper to catch excess for reuse. TO
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d ICE INSIDE OUTLINES, add a little water to thin icing, if necessary. Spoon a small amount of icing onto outlined cookies. Using a brush, small spatula or your finger, spread icing up to outline to fill in spaces.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d FOR BUNNIES, frost the bunny-shaped cookies with white frosting. While frosting is wet, sprinkle with coconut. For tails, use 3 miniature marshmallows. Add mini candy coated chocolate candies for eye and nose. Pipe the inside of the ears with pink frosting. Pipe lines of chocolate for whiskers. If desired, use white frosting to pipe outlines of bunnies legs on top of the coconut.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d FOR BASKETS, pipe chocolate onto unfrosted cookies to outline the handle of the basket and crisscrossed to make the weave of the basket. Use green frosting to pipe the grass on the top of the basket. Tuck flower-shaped sprinkles into the grass at the top of the basket. Tip: Icing colored with brown food coloring can be substituted for chocolate.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d FOR BONNETS, use 2 sizes of cookies. Outline the larger cookies with a scallop edge and the smaller cookies with a round edge. Fill in the outlines with frosting and place the small cookie on top of the larger cookie; let dry. Pipe contrasting color dots in the scallop edging of the larger cookies. Use a third color frosting to pipe a bow between the two cookies.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d FOR CARROTS, follow directions above for outlining and icing the carrot cookies with orange icing. For green tops and details on the carrots, follow directions for sugared outlines.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d FOR EASTER EGGS, pipe dots, dashes, straight and curvy lines on unfrosted cookies with a variety of colors of icing. Have fun with the designs!
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d BAKE 7 to 12 minutes, depending on the size of the cookies or until the edges begin to brown.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d Let stand one minute on cookie sheets.
4d168d1d-883f-4531-9fb2-c86dcd94c63d Slide Parchment Paper with cookies onto a wire racks to cool completely.
500e29cb-80bd-4350-89b5-05024fb43c53 In a large skillet over medium heat, brown ground chicken along with chili powder, cumin, garlic powder and salt. Once cooked remove from heat and set aside.
500e29cb-80bd-4350-89b5-05024fb43c53 Working with one tortilla at a top fill center with cooked rice, prepared chicken, cheddar cheese, beans, Pico de Gallo and sour cream. Fold in sides and tightly roll burrito. Follow by wrapping burrito in a similar manner with a 10 inch piece of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Repeat the above steps with remaining ingredients.
500e29cb-80bd-4350-89b5-05024fb43c53 Preheat oven to 375°F. Arrange aluminum wrapped burritos on a baking sheet and bake on center rack for 20 minutes.
500e29cb-80bd-4350-89b5-05024fb43c53 Serve cut in half along with extra salsa and sour cream.
a126571b-fbf8-4795-9233-cecab19005df Preheat oven to 400°F and line a large baking sheet with nonstick aluminum foil.
a126571b-fbf8-4795-9233-cecab19005df Heat a medium nonstick skillet over medium heat and spray with oil. Add onion, cilantro and garlic and sauté about 2 minutes, until soft.
a126571b-fbf8-4795-9233-cecab19005df Add ground turkey, salt, garlic powder, cumin and cook meat for 4 to 5 minutes until meat is completely cooked through breaking it up with a spoon. Add the tomato paste and water, mix well and simmer on medium for about 2 to 3 minutes, remove from heat.
a126571b-fbf8-4795-9233-cecab19005df Meanwhile, combine cream cheese, cheddar and scallions in a medium bowl. Using a small spoon or a spatula, spoon about 1 teaspoon of the cream cheese filling into the peppers.
a126571b-fbf8-4795-9233-cecab19005df Arrange in a single layer, cut-side up close together. Bake until soft, about 12 to 15 minutes. Top with meat and cheese and bake until melted, about 3 minutes more.
a126571b-fbf8-4795-9233-cecab19005df Remove from oven and top with Pico de Gallo, olives and drizzle with sour cream. Garnish with cilantro and scallions and serve immediately.
cb897725-2c5f-488d-8b95-66ea91ff4ca3 PREHEAT oven to 375°F.
cb897725-2c5f-488d-8b95-66ea91ff4ca3 LINE 4 baking sheets with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil (dull side up). Combine the meat with all other meat ball ingredients and form into bite-size meatballs.
cb897725-2c5f-488d-8b95-66ea91ff4ca3 PLACE 20 meatballs on each pan, and bake for 35 minutes or until browned all the way through.
cb897725-2c5f-488d-8b95-66ea91ff4ca3 While the meatballs are baking, POUR the barbecue sauce and the grape jelly into a sauce pan and heat over medium until they are well combined. If you want your meatballs to have a little extra kick, add some hot sauce to the mix.
cb897725-2c5f-488d-8b95-66ea91ff4ca3 Once the meatballs are finished, SLIDE them right off the pan and into serving dish. Pour sauce on top and serve immediately.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 PREHEAT the oven to 350° F.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 MELT the butter in a large pot on high heat and add in the onions and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 ADD in the mushrooms and cook until they are lightly brown.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 SPRINKLE the flour over top of the mushrooms and onions and stir until they are completely coated.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 POUR in 3 cups of chicken stock and bring to a boil.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 WHISK in the heavy cream.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 ADD the sauce to a large pot with the parboiled green beans and mix together.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 SEASON with salt and pepper and fold in the chopped bacon.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 POUR the mixture into a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan with hot pad and carrier and sprinkle on the 2 cups of bread crumbs and then the 2 cups of French fried onions.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 BAKE in the oven on 350° for 30 minutes or until the French fried onions and bread crumbs turn golden brown.
3dea8a19-1328-4e5a-9b71-fa5273caa4b0 SERVE hot.
cdf474ae-db12-470c-9e86-8fbff5f19c11 PREHEAT the oven to 350° F.
cdf474ae-db12-470c-9e86-8fbff5f19c11 MIX together the flour, cornmeal, baking powder and sugar until combined and set aside.
cdf474ae-db12-470c-9e86-8fbff5f19c11 WHISK together the sour cream, melted butter, milk and egg and pour into the dry ingredient bowl.
cdf474ae-db12-470c-9e86-8fbff5f19c11 MIX in the strained and creamed corn until combined.
cdf474ae-db12-470c-9e86-8fbff5f19c11 POUR the batter into a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan with Hot Pad and Carrier and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until the center is firm.
cdf474ae-db12-470c-9e86-8fbff5f19c11 GARNISH with sliced green onions
cdf474ae-db12-470c-9e86-8fbff5f19c11 SERVE hot.
4aca30b5-8438-48ba-a9dc-e4096110483c COMBINE all ingredients in a large bowl. Using a rubber spatula, fold the mixture until fully combined.
4aca30b5-8438-48ba-a9dc-e4096110483c DIVIDE butter in half, and then transfer each to a sheet of Reynolds Kitchens® Unbleached Parchment Paper. Roll into a tube-like shape and twist each of the ends.
4aca30b5-8438-48ba-a9dc-e4096110483c REFRIGERATE until firm, about one hour.
68a0613c-0ab8-408b-a7ae-2a4afa7eb9fc PREHEAT grill to 450°F. Roll or pat pizza dough into a 14-inch circle on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil. Brush dough with olive oil.
68a0613c-0ab8-408b-a7ae-2a4afa7eb9fc SPRINKLE on oregano and lemon zest. Add green peppers, red onion, cherry tomatoes, olives, feta and mozzarella. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
68a0613c-0ab8-408b-a7ae-2a4afa7eb9fc GRILL 15 to 20 minutes in covered grill over indirect heat.
a9543632-9352-4221-8bd4-56f6406d1bbc PREHEAT the oven to 350°
a9543632-9352-4221-8bd4-56f6406d1bbc WHISK together in a large bowl the eggs, sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and milk until combined.
a9543632-9352-4221-8bd4-56f6406d1bbc SOAK the cubed French bread and raisins in the mixture for 2 to 3 minutes.
a9543632-9352-4221-8bd4-56f6406d1bbc TRANSFER the mixture to a Reynolds Kitchens® Dessert Pan.
a9543632-9352-4221-8bd4-56f6406d1bbc BAKE in the oven on 350° for 35 minutes or until it is golden brown on top.
a9543632-9352-4221-8bd4-56f6406d1bbc SERVE with caramel sauce and vanilla ice cream.
709b9514-1e55-42fc-9972-220a78cc8ebc PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
709b9514-1e55-42fc-9972-220a78cc8ebc CREAM together the butter, vegetable oil and sugar in a mixer with the paddles attachment on high speed for 6 to 8 minutes, or until it becomes light and fluffy.
709b9514-1e55-42fc-9972-220a78cc8ebc ADD 1 egg at a time until it is completely combined.
709b9514-1e55-42fc-9972-220a78cc8ebc MIX together the flour, salt and baking powder in a large bowl and set aside.
709b9514-1e55-42fc-9972-220a78cc8ebc ALTERNATELY ADD the dry ingredients and buttermilk to the mixer on low speed beginning with the dry and ending with the dry.
709b9514-1e55-42fc-9972-220a78cc8ebc DIVIDE the batter into 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Cake Pans with Parchment Lining and bake in the oven on 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the top is lightly browned and the center is firm. Cool to room temperature.
709b9514-1e55-42fc-9972-220a78cc8ebc WHIP the butter in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed for 6 to 8 minutes or until light and fluffy. Slowly add the powdered sugar to the mixer on low speed until it is combined. Add in the vanilla and set the buttercream aside at room temperature until the cakes have finished cooking.
709b9514-1e55-42fc-9972-220a78cc8ebc ICE the cooled cakes with the buttercream and stack them on each other to make a layered funfetti cake.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Preheat the oven to 350°.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Whisk together the flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl and set aside.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Cream the butter and sugar together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed until light and fluffy, about 6 to 8 minutes.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Add 1 egg at a time on low speed until mixed in and then mix in the vanilla.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Alternatively add in the flour mixture and buttermilk on low speed beginning with the dry ingredients and ending with the dry ingredients.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Fold in the melted chocolate.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Pour the batter in 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Cake Pans lined with parchment paper and bake in the oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until the center is firm.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Cool the cakes to room temperature before removing the pan and the parchment paper.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Whisk together the evaporated milk, sugar, butter and egg yolks over medium heat until it reaches 160°, about 12 to 14 minutes.
42c62b21-8114-4377-b52a-ceda10dd9d11 Stir in the coconut and chill to room temperature before icing the chocolate cake.
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 PREHEAT the oven to 375°
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 PULSE together the graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar in a food processor until combined.
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 PRESS the graham cracker crust firmly into the bottom of a Reynolds Kitchens® Sheet Cake Pan with parchment lining making sure to cover the bottom completely.
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 BAKE the crust in the oven for 10 minutes and set aside.
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 ADD the egg yolks to a standing mixer with the whisk attachment and beat the eggs on low speed for 3 to 4 minutes.
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 POUR in the sweetened condensed milk to the eggs and whisk until combined, and scrape the sides.
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 DRIZZLE in the key lime juice to the mixture and finish with the zest, and whisk on low speed until completely combined.
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 POUR the key lime batter on top of the par baked graham cracker crust and bake on 375° for 15 minutes to help settle the mixture.
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 COOL the bars completely for 1 to 2 hours at room temperature and then chill in the refrigerator.
cdda6a54-0cd6-4ee6-894c-635843bd1ea5 GARNISH with whipped cream and sliced limes.
405e4f80-d850-49b6-9974-4608a88e22d4 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place 24 Reynolds Kitchens® Foil Baking Cups in muffin pans or on a cookie sheet; set aside.
405e4f80-d850-49b6-9974-4608a88e22d4 PREPARE cake mix following package directions for 24 cupcakes. Spoon batter into baking cups. Press one chocolate peanut butter candy cup into the center of each cup.
405e4f80-d850-49b6-9974-4608a88e22d4 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes. Cool.
405e4f80-d850-49b6-9974-4608a88e22d4 MIX frosting and peanut butter in a medium bowl until well blended. Frost cupcakes. Top with chocolate shavings, if desired.
9ad6b4ec-6d3b-47c0-bc10-e97a53a58fb1 MIX the peanut butter and butter in a large bowl until it is combined and gradually add in the powdered sugar until it is mixed in.
9ad6b4ec-6d3b-47c0-bc10-e97a53a58fb1 FOLD in the crunched up corn flakes and let the batter sit for 15 to 20 minutes in the refrigerator.
9ad6b4ec-6d3b-47c0-bc10-e97a53a58fb1 FORM small peanut butter balls, about 1" in diameter, and place them on 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Cookie Sheets with Parchment Lining in the refrigerator for 15 minutes to allow them to firm up.
9ad6b4ec-6d3b-47c0-bc10-e97a53a58fb1 MELT the chocolate in a microwave safe bowl, about 1 minute, and dip 1 peanut butter ball at a time with 2 spoons, allowing the excess chocolate to drip off and set them back on the 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Cookie Sheets with Parchment Lining. Line up 4 to a row.
9ad6b4ec-6d3b-47c0-bc10-e97a53a58fb1 REPEAT until all of the peanut butter balls have been dipped in chocolate.
9ad6b4ec-6d3b-47c0-bc10-e97a53a58fb1 COOL and serve.
1db05f1a-e0ce-488f-894b-b38ba163284a PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
1db05f1a-e0ce-488f-894b-b38ba163284a CREAM together the butter and sugar in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment until it becomes light and fluffy, about 6 to 8 minutes.
1db05f1a-e0ce-488f-894b-b38ba163284a ADD 1 egg at a time into the creamed butter mixture until it is combined and then pour in the vanilla.
1db05f1a-e0ce-488f-894b-b38ba163284a COMBINE the flour, cream of tartar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a medium size bowl and slowly add it to the creamed butter mixture making sure to stop the mixer to scrape to combine all of the ingredients.
1db05f1a-e0ce-488f-894b-b38ba163284a MIX together 2 teaspoons of ground cinnamon and ¼ cup of granulated sugar until combined and set aside.
1db05f1a-e0ce-488f-894b-b38ba163284a ROLL the cookie dough into 1” inch balls until there are 36.
1db05f1a-e0ce-488f-894b-b38ba163284a ROLL the cookie dough balls into the cinnamon and sugar topping mixture and place on Reynolds Kitchens® Cookie Sheets with Parchment Lining.
1db05f1a-e0ce-488f-894b-b38ba163284a PRESS the cookies down slightly using the back side of a spoon to help flatten them.
1db05f1a-e0ce-488f-894b-b38ba163284a BAKE the cookies on 350° for 13-15 minutes or until the edges are lightly brown and the centers are still soft.
0c273858-c0b2-4bf0-b71e-e9f32040ac14 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
0c273858-c0b2-4bf0-b71e-e9f32040ac14 MIX together the flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl, set aside
0c273858-c0b2-4bf0-b71e-e9f32040ac14 RUB the zest into sugar with your finger tips in a separate bowl.
0c273858-c0b2-4bf0-b71e-e9f32040ac14 CREAM together the butter and lemon-sugar in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment until it becomes light and fluffy, about 6 to 8 minutes.
0c273858-c0b2-4bf0-b71e-e9f32040ac14 ADD 1 egg at a time until it’s mixed in.
0c273858-c0b2-4bf0-b71e-e9f32040ac14 ADD in lemon juice and vanilla until mixed in.
0c273858-c0b2-4bf0-b71e-e9f32040ac14 CHILL the dough in a refrigerator for 30 to 45 minutes.
0c273858-c0b2-4bf0-b71e-e9f32040ac14 ROLL the dough into little balls, about 2 tablespoons worth, then roll them in the powdered sugar and arrange on 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Cookie Sheets with Parchment Lining to 4 rows of 3, or 12 to a pan, and bake for 10 to 12 minutes on 350°.
0c273858-c0b2-4bf0-b71e-e9f32040ac14 COOL before serving.
53a0bbd1-dad6-4e59-96e6-e3fedefb5208 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
53a0bbd1-dad6-4e59-96e6-e3fedefb5208 MIX together the flour, baking powder and salt in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment.
53a0bbd1-dad6-4e59-96e6-e3fedefb5208 BEAT in eggs, sugar, butter and extracts, and then the almonds on low speed.
53a0bbd1-dad6-4e59-96e6-e3fedefb5208 DIVIDE the dough in half and form a log on 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Cookie Sheets with Parchment Lining and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until dough is firm and gives slightly when pressed.
53a0bbd1-dad6-4e59-96e6-e3fedefb5208 COOL for 20 minutes then using a serrated knife cut ¼ inch pieces and put them back on the baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes flipping them ½ way through to crisp up.
53a0bbd1-dad6-4e59-96e6-e3fedefb5208 COOL before serving.
2a8c2426-c773-4557-9e2f-2ea734a5c6c6 Preheat oven to 350°F.
2a8c2426-c773-4557-9e2f-2ea734a5c6c6 Roll out pie crust dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Use circular cookie cutter or top of glass to cut dough into circles.
2a8c2426-c773-4557-9e2f-2ea734a5c6c6 Top with 1 to 2 spoonfuls of cherry pie filling. Layer with additional, cut pieces of dough to make your favorite design.
2a8c2426-c773-4557-9e2f-2ea734a5c6c6 Place cookies 2 inches apart on cookie sheets lined with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®.
2a8c2426-c773-4557-9e2f-2ea734a5c6c6 Bake at 350°F until lightly browned on bottom and cooked through, about 20–25 minutes.
8540a186-b4e0-48f6-a4c1-f6675293d9f0 PREHEAT the oven to 325oF. PLACE a 9x13-inch Reynolds Kitchens® Dessert Pan on a cookie sheet and set aside.
8540a186-b4e0-48f6-a4c1-f6675293d9f0 STIR cocoa powder, hot chocolate, unsweetened chocolate, vegetable oil, butter, eggs, sugars and flour in a large bowl until everything is fully incorporated.
8540a186-b4e0-48f6-a4c1-f6675293d9f0 ADD chocolate chips. You can also add peanut butter chips or your favorite chocolate candy (optional).
8540a186-b4e0-48f6-a4c1-f6675293d9f0 POUR batter into disposable bakeware; spread into corners of pan.
8540a186-b4e0-48f6-a4c1-f6675293d9f0 BAKE for 40 minutes. When you insert a toothpick in the center, there may be a few moist crumbs.
8540a186-b4e0-48f6-a4c1-f6675293d9f0 COOL for 60 to 90 minutes on wire rack.
8540a186-b4e0-48f6-a4c1-f6675293d9f0 SLICE and serve.
6e9e91d3-70ce-489f-a1ed-8b40d027a89b Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
6e9e91d3-70ce-489f-a1ed-8b40d027a89b Line cookie sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®.
6e9e91d3-70ce-489f-a1ed-8b40d027a89b Place pretzels in a single layer on cookie sheet, then top with chocolate kisses.
6e9e91d3-70ce-489f-a1ed-8b40d027a89b Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 1–2 minutes, until chocolate is soft, but not fully melted.
6e9e91d3-70ce-489f-a1ed-8b40d027a89b Push a pecan or candy-coated chocolate into the center of each chocolate kiss, and chill in the refrigerator until firm.
bfea7a08-4b25-4b64-aa7e-98415dad2b03 Whisk together flour, cocoa powder, cinnamon, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl and set aside.
bfea7a08-4b25-4b64-aa7e-98415dad2b03 Beat butter and brown sugar in an electric mixer on medium-high until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, then vanilla and continue to beat, scraping down bowl as necessary. Reduce speed to stir and slowly add flour mixture, beat until well combined. Form dough into disk, wrap in plastic and chill until firm, at least 2 hours.
bfea7a08-4b25-4b64-aa7e-98415dad2b03 Preheat oven to 350° with racks in top and bottom third. Line two large baking sheets with Reynolds KITCHENS™ Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®. Scoop rounded tablespoons of dough, roll into balls, then in confectioners’ sugar twice to coat heavily. Arrange 2 inches apart on prepared sheets and bake until crackly and puffed but still soft in center, about 10 minutes.
9614a1cb-9c4d-4544-a6f9-6fe232e7415f CREAM butter on high speed for 30 seconds in a large bowl.
9614a1cb-9c4d-4544-a6f9-6fe232e7415f ADD sugar, baking powder, and salt. Beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Beat in egg, half and half, and vanilla until combined.
9614a1cb-9c4d-4544-a6f9-6fe232e7415f ADD flour and cinnamon to the mixer slowly. Make sure dough is evenly mixed.
9614a1cb-9c4d-4544-a6f9-6fe232e7415f WRAP dough in Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper and place in a sealed plastic bag; refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.
9614a1cb-9c4d-4544-a6f9-6fe232e7415f ROLL out dough 1/8-inch thick between 2 lightly floured sheets of Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®.
9614a1cb-9c4d-4544-a6f9-6fe232e7415f CUT dough with 2-inch cookie cutters and place on parchment-lined cookie sheets about 1 inch apart.
9614a1cb-9c4d-4544-a6f9-6fe232e7415f BAKE for 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are very light brown. Slide parchment paper with cookies onto cooling rack; cool.
9614a1cb-9c4d-4544-a6f9-6fe232e7415f DECORATE as desired. Store in an airtight container for up to 5 days.
c835c4c6-dd21-48a1-bb46-4c6d15064f3d Preheat oven following cookie package directions. Line cookie sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
c835c4c6-dd21-48a1-bb46-4c6d15064f3d Portion sugar cookie dough into one-inch balls (a great short cut is to purchase pre-portioned cookie dough)
c835c4c6-dd21-48a1-bb46-4c6d15064f3d Place one caramel between two portions of sugar cookie dough. Mold dough around caramel until caramel is completely covered
c835c4c6-dd21-48a1-bb46-4c6d15064f3d Bake on parchment-lined cookie sheet according to instructions on cookie dough package.
c835c4c6-dd21-48a1-bb46-4c6d15064f3d Enjoy!
8134c093-e914-46c8-9bd5-4da7f7b17e9a In a small bowl, stir together flour and baking soda; set aside.
8134c093-e914-46c8-9bd5-4da7f7b17e9a In a medium saucepan, combine butter, brown sugar, and water. Cook and stir over low heat until butter is melted. Add chocolate pieces; cook and stir until chocolate is melted.
8134c093-e914-46c8-9bd5-4da7f7b17e9a Pour mixture into a large bowl; cool for 10 minutes. Using a wooden spoon, stir egg into chocolate mixture. Stir in flour mixture until combined.
8134c093-e914-46c8-9bd5-4da7f7b17e9a Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours or until dough is easy to handle.
8134c093-e914-46c8-9bd5-4da7f7b17e9a Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
8134c093-e914-46c8-9bd5-4da7f7b17e9a Shape dough into 1-inch balls and using SmartGrid® to measure, place 2 inches apart on parchment-lined cookie sheets.
8134c093-e914-46c8-9bd5-4da7f7b17e9a Bake for 8 minutes.
8134c093-e914-46c8-9bd5-4da7f7b17e9a Immediately place a mint kiss on top of each cookie. Bake about 2 minutes more or until edges are set. If desired, gently swirl the melted mints with a table knife.
8134c093-e914-46c8-9bd5-4da7f7b17e9a Transfer cookies to a wire rack; cool until melted mints are firm.
7693b9c4-a051-4620-a67a-590c363af318 In a large mixing bowl, combine almond flour, chocolate, coconut flour, coconut, baking powder, and salt; set aside.
7693b9c4-a051-4620-a67a-590c363af318 In a medium bowl, beat egg, honey, coconut oil, and vanilla for 2 minutes. Add mixture to the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. Wrap dough with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper and place in a plastic storage bag. Chill for 1 hour or until easy to handle.
7693b9c4-a051-4620-a67a-590c363af318 Preheat oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®. Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls or, for a bumpier top, spoon into 1 1/2-inch portions. Place portions 2 inches apart on baking sheet. Flatten to 1/2 inch thick.
7693b9c4-a051-4620-a67a-590c363af318 Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are firm around edges and light brown on bottoms. Cool on cookie sheets for 1 minute. Remove; cool completely on wire racks.
ff48e1c7-4030-408f-87b5-669dd6e4e081 Preheat oven to 375°. Line a cooke sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
ff48e1c7-4030-408f-87b5-669dd6e4e081 Combine butter and sugar in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed with mixer until fluffy. Beat in egg yolks and lemon peel.
ff48e1c7-4030-408f-87b5-669dd6e4e081 Combine flour, cornstarch, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl. Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture; beat at low speed just until crumbly. Stir in blueberries.
ff48e1c7-4030-408f-87b5-669dd6e4e081 Place dough on a sheet of parchment on countertop. Divide dough in half. Knead each half until dough holds together. Divide each half into 16 pieces. Rol each piece into a ball
ff48e1c7-4030-408f-87b5-669dd6e4e081 Place cooke balls onto parchment-lined cookie sheet. Flatten cooked to 1/4-inch thickness using the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
ff48e1c7-4030-408f-87b5-669dd6e4e081 Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned around edges.
8e0a3d46-f8d1-4ab2-87a9-e381b71bf271 Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
8e0a3d46-f8d1-4ab2-87a9-e381b71bf271 In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
8e0a3d46-f8d1-4ab2-87a9-e381b71bf271 Beat butter and brown sugar in a large bowl on medium speed for about 2 minutes or until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Reduce to low. Gradually add flour mixture, beating after each addition until well blended. Stir in oats and raisins. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto parchment-lined cookie sheet.
8e0a3d46-f8d1-4ab2-87a9-e381b71bf271 Bake for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown. Slide cookies on parchment onto a wire rack to cool.
13c423e9-e1b1-4a5e-8d84-290b3f9dff5b Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Line baking sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper. with SmartGrid®. Mix cinnamon and sugar in a medium bowl; set aside.
