13c423e9-e1b1-4a5e-8d84-290b3f9dff5b Roll out pie crust dough on Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper to 1/4 inch thickness. Brush dough with melted butter. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar evenly over the buttered dough. Starting with a long end, roll the dough over itself to create a log.
13c423e9-e1b1-4a5e-8d84-290b3f9dff5b Cut log into 1/2-inch thick slices.
13c423e9-e1b1-4a5e-8d84-290b3f9dff5b Bake on parchment-lined cookie sheet at 375 degrees F until lightly browned, about 15 minutes. Slide parchment with cookies onto a wire rack. Cool completely.
80094cfc-60ed-4d2b-942d-613de4b85b15 LINE a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil; set aside.
80094cfc-60ed-4d2b-942d-613de4b85b15 MELT the butter in a 2-quart heavy saucepan over medium heat. Stir in sugar, water and corn syrup. Bring to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Avoid splashing side of saucepan. Clip a candy thermometer to side of pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until thermometer registers 290°F or a small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water separates into threads that are hard but not brittle. This will take about 18 minutes. Adjust heat as necessary to maintain a steady boil. Watch carefully the last 5 minutes to prevent overcooking. Remove from heat and remove the thermometer.
80094cfc-60ed-4d2b-942d-613de4b85b15 POUR into the prepared baking pan. Tilt pan to spread mixture evenly. Let stand 2 minutes. In a small bowl combine the cashews, almonds, pumpkin seeds, and sesame seeds. Sprinkle evenly over candy mixture.
80094cfc-60ed-4d2b-942d-613de4b85b15 SET baking pan on a wire rack. Cool completely and break into large pieces to serve.
ae99b1ad-497b-4868-8029-8e555dc835f0 PREHEAT oven to 325oF. Line muffin pan(s) with 12 Reynolds Kitchens® Foil Baking Cups.
ae99b1ad-497b-4868-8029-8e555dc835f0 STIR together cake flour, baking powder and salt, and chocolate in a medium bowl, set aside.
ae99b1ad-497b-4868-8029-8e555dc835f0 WHIP egg whites with an electric mixer on high speed until stiff peaks form, set aside.
ae99b1ad-497b-4868-8029-8e555dc835f0 CREAM together butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl on medium speed until light. Add milk and sour cream. Add flour mixture, mixing until smooth. Fold egg whites into batter.
ae99b1ad-497b-4868-8029-8e555dc835f0 DIVIDE batter evenly among liners.
ae99b1ad-497b-4868-8029-8e555dc835f0 BAKE at 325oF for 20-23 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean.
ae99b1ad-497b-4868-8029-8e555dc835f0 COOL on a wire rack.
ae99b1ad-497b-4868-8029-8e555dc835f0 FROST with your favorite icing.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca WHISK together the 3 eggs, buttermilk, vinegar and food coloring until combined and set aside.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca MIX together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder and baking soda in a standing mixer with the whisk attachment on low speed.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca POUR the wet ingredients slowly into the standing mixer with the dry ingredients on low speed just until combined.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca POUR the batter evenly into 2 separate Reynolds Kitchens® Cake Pans with Parchment Lining.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca BAKE at 350° for 30 minutes or until the top is lightly brown and the center is firm and
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca REMOVE the cake from the pans after they have been cooled to room temperature and then peel off the parchment paper. Set the cakes aside.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca WHIP the cream cheese on high speed in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment until it is light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca ADD in the powdered sugar and heavy cream and mix on low speed until incorporated and then mix on high speed for 2 minutes.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca ICE the double layered cake on the sides and top until the cream cheese frosting is gone.
d6db0f87-a1b4-4f6b-a0de-8b494a5e2eca SERVE at room temperature.
ba443f90-dece-403c-811f-f231234a08fc Line your slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
ba443f90-dece-403c-811f-f231234a08fc Stir together the spice ingredients in a large bowl. Add the wings and toss to fully combine.
ba443f90-dece-403c-811f-f231234a08fc Add the rubbed wings to the slow cooker.
ba443f90-dece-403c-811f-f231234a08fc Using the same bowl, stir together all of the sauce ingredients except the cornstarch. Pour the sauce over the wings and toss.
ba443f90-dece-403c-811f-f231234a08fc Cook on high for 2 hours, or on low for 3 to 4 hours, until the wings reach an internal temperature of 165°F.
ba443f90-dece-403c-811f-f231234a08fc Remove the wings from the slow cooker (leaving the sauce) and place in a large bowl. Stir the cornstarch into 2 tablespoons cold water, and then add to the sauce mixture inside the slow cooker. Stir to combine.
ba443f90-dece-403c-811f-f231234a08fc Cook the sauce on high for 10 more minutes. Pour the thickened sauce over the wings and toss to coat.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a skillet over high heat. Coat the chicken with taco seasoning in a small bowl. Add the chicken to the skillet and sauté both sides until done. Remove from the skillet and set aside.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Add the remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil to a skillet over high heat. Add in the onions and peppers and cook until they are soft. Remove and set aside.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Combine the chicken and pepper mixture in one skillet.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Tear off three 16-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil (dull side facing up). Place on counter surface. Brush softened butter on one side of each tortilla. Center one tortilla on the full sheet.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Then build the quesadillas by laying grated cheese on the bottom tortilla, and then arranging the chicken and peppers mixture.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Top with a little more grated cheese and then top with a second tortilla. Repeat with the remaining tortillas and fillings.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Bring in the long side of each end of the foil, so the ends meet over half of the tortilla. Double fold the two short sides and seal the pocket.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Bake at 350 degrees F for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Remove from oven.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Cut each quesadilla into wedges as small as you’d like.
2d7d00b0-9c6c-400a-aba1-b666ab2637c0 Serve with jalapeños, pico de gallo, sour cream and guacamole.
9cf7d71b-7c3a-4cf8-92eb-8e04a5c0fdc7 Preheat oven to 425 F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil.
9cf7d71b-7c3a-4cf8-92eb-8e04a5c0fdc7 In a medium bowl, stir together water, milk, flour and spices until well-combined.
9cf7d71b-7c3a-4cf8-92eb-8e04a5c0fdc7 Dip florets into the batter, shaking off the excess before adding to the lined baking sheet in a single layer.
9cf7d71b-7c3a-4cf8-92eb-8e04a5c0fdc7 Bake for 20 minutes, flipping halfway through, until crispy and golden brown.
9cf7d71b-7c3a-4cf8-92eb-8e04a5c0fdc7 While the cauliflower is baking, melt butter in a small saucepan over medium heat. Stir in hot sauce and honey. Cook for another 5 minutes until slightly thickened. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
9cf7d71b-7c3a-4cf8-92eb-8e04a5c0fdc7 Add florets to large bowl and toss with ¾ cup of the buffalo sauce. Return to the lined baking sheet in a single layer. Bake for another 15 minutes, then drizzle with remaining sauce.
9cf7d71b-7c3a-4cf8-92eb-8e04a5c0fdc7 Serve immediately with ranch or blue cheese.
5e97ed2a-945a-4672-89bf-f139ab091075 MARINATE salmon by combining all marinade ingredients in a small bowl. Place the salmon fillets in a baking dish or large slider storage bag. Add the marinade to the baking dish and refrigerate for 90 minutes. If you use a bag, seal the bag and gently move the salmon around the marinade before placing it in the refrigerator.
5e97ed2a-945a-4672-89bf-f139ab091075 COOK jasmine rice while the salmon is marinating. In a saucepot, bring the water to a boil, add salt and rice. Cover and lower heat to simmer for 5 minutes. Then remove the rice from the heat and allow the rice to finish cooking without heat and with the lid on. Use a fork to fluff the rice when removing it from the pot. Let the rice cool slightly then add the scallions, red peppers and cilantro. Mix well and set aside til needed.
5e97ed2a-945a-4672-89bf-f139ab091075 PREPARE Mango Bourbon Glaze by placing the ingredients for the glaze in the bowl of a food processor and pulse until smooth. Place the glaze in a small saucepot and bring to a light boil. Remove from heat and divide the glaze into two parts. Set aside till needed. Note: If the glaze gets too thick, add a little water to it. You can also warm it up in the microwave to get the glaze more liquid.
5e97ed2a-945a-4672-89bf-f139ab091075 PREHEAT the oven to 400° F. Remove the salmon from the marinade and place on a plate until needed. Tear off four 16" sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Place one cup of jasmine rice in the center of the foil, perpendicular to the longer sides. Place a salmon filet on top of the rice, then brush the salmon with the mango bourbon glaze. Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet over the food. Double fold the ends, leaving room for heat to circulate inside. Then double fold the two short ends to seal the packet. Repeat this process for all four salmon filets. Place the packets on a sheet pan or baking sheet and place into the oven for 15–20 minutes.
5e97ed2a-945a-4672-89bf-f139ab091075 TOAST sesame seeds in a dry skillet over medium heat for 2–3 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally. Or bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 350 F for 8–10 minutes or until lightly browned. Don’t let them burn!! Place toasted seeds immediately onto a cool plate so they stop cooking.
5e97ed2a-945a-4672-89bf-f139ab091075 REMOVE the salmon from the oven and carefully cut the tops off of each foil packet using kitchen scissors. Open each packet and slide the entire dish onto a plate (The foil will be hot, so use a towel or gloves when handling the packets). Repeat the process with each packet. Garnish the salmon with toasted sesame seeds, scallions and cilantro.
5e97ed2a-945a-4672-89bf-f139ab091075 SERVE with your favorite vegetable and enjoy!
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Heat a grill to medium heat.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Remove steaks from the fridge and rub with olive oil. Season with steak seasoning to taste. Set aside on the counter while you prepare the onions and mushrooms.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Tear off a 16-inch sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil and spray with cooking spray.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Place onion, mushrooms, 2 tablespoons garlic butter and herbs in the center of the foil sheet. Season with salt and pepper.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet and double-fold the ends. Double-fold the two short ends to seal the packet.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Place packet on the preheated grill and grill 10–15 minutes on one side. Flip package over and grill an additional 15 minutes or until onion is tender.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Add the steaks to the grill (after the initial 15 minutes of cooking the foil packets) and cook 5–6 minutes. Flip steaks and cook an additional 6–8 minutes or until it reaches 140 F or desired doneness.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Remove steak from the grill and place on a plate. Loosely tent with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and let rest 5–7 minutes before slicing.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe While steak is resting, butter the ciabatta rolls with garlic butter. Place butter side down on the grill and grill 3–4 minutes or until lightly browned.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Slice steak across the grain into 1/2-inch slices.
01294ef2-c239-4a16-943a-30c61831c3fe Spread each toasted roll with Dijon mustard (if using) and a small handful of arugula. Add sliced steak, mushrooms and onions (and spoon any butter in the packet over the steaks). Serve immediately.
e897e0a7-38ef-41e1-846c-06d9953589eb Hollow out potato using a coring tool. See note for alternative method if you don’t have a coring tool.
e897e0a7-38ef-41e1-846c-06d9953589eb Take the potato that was cored out and dice.
e897e0a7-38ef-41e1-846c-06d9953589eb Fry chopped bacon bits in pan to make fried bacon bits
e897e0a7-38ef-41e1-846c-06d9953589eb Mix all the stuffing ingredients together including the seasoning.
e897e0a7-38ef-41e1-846c-06d9953589eb Stuff the mixture into the potato and wrap securely with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil.
e897e0a7-38ef-41e1-846c-06d9953589eb Place into a 350° F – 400° F grill or oven. After 1 hour, check for tenderness with sharp probe.
e897e0a7-38ef-41e1-846c-06d9953589eb Once potato is completely done, allow to rest for a few minutes. Carefully remove the foil as it will still be very hot and putting off hot steam. Cut potato in half and enjoy!
88dbb93c-09b2-4181-9ebc-5b9b00d66d39 Preheat the oven to 425° F. Line a 13-by-9-inch sheet pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil, dull side facing up toward food.
88dbb93c-09b2-4181-9ebc-5b9b00d66d39 In a medium bowl, toss broccoli with olive oil and season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and spread out on the sheet pan in a single layer on one side.
88dbb93c-09b2-4181-9ebc-5b9b00d66d39 In a medium bowl, combine ground turkey, oatmeal, 1/4 cup ketchup, onion, egg, 3/4 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce and thyme, mix well.
88dbb93c-09b2-4181-9ebc-5b9b00d66d39 Divide mixture into 4 equal portions. Shape each portion into a 4-by-3-inch free-form loaf on the other side of the sheet pan.
88dbb93c-09b2-4181-9ebc-5b9b00d66d39 In a small bowl, mix remaining 2 tablespoons ketchup with remaining teaspoon of Worcestershire sauce and brush onto loaves.
88dbb93c-09b2-4181-9ebc-5b9b00d66d39 Bake 30 minutes in the center of the oven, turning the broccoli halfway, until meat is cooked through in the center and the broccoli is slightly charred.
b81e25cd-9cfc-4fe4-9244-80acbd208067 Preheat grill to medium-high heat or the oven to 425° F.
b81e25cd-9cfc-4fe4-9244-80acbd208067 Cut four large 12 x 18-inch pieces of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil and lay out on a flat surface.
b81e25cd-9cfc-4fe4-9244-80acbd208067 Place 3/4 cup frozen mixed veggies in the center of each piece of foil.
b81e25cd-9cfc-4fe4-9244-80acbd208067 Season chicken with salt, garlic powder and paprika. Brush both sides of the chicken with 1/4 cup BBQ sauce and place 2 pieces (1 drumstick, 1 thigh) in the middle of each foil packet.
b81e25cd-9cfc-4fe4-9244-80acbd208067 Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet over the food. Double fold the ends, leaving room for heat to circulate inside. Double fold the two short ends to seal the packet tight, so no steam escapes.
b81e25cd-9cfc-4fe4-9244-80acbd208067 To grill the Foil Packets: Place foil packets onto a preheated grill over medium-high heat and grill, covered over indirect heat for 50 to 55 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and chicken reaches an internal temp of 160°F when tested with an instant read thermometer. Remove from the grill and carefully open the foil packets. Brush chicken with reserved BBQ sauce and cook uncovered 5 minutes more. Garnish with fresh parsley if desired.
b81e25cd-9cfc-4fe4-9244-80acbd208067 To bake Foil Packets in the Oven: Preheat oven to 425°F. Place foil packets on a baking sheet and bake 50 to 55 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and tender and reaches an internal temp of 160°F with an instant read thermometer. Remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully open foil and brush the chicken with remaining BBQ sauce, bake 5 minutes uncovered and garnish with fresh parsley if desired.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Preheat the oven to 425° F. Tear off six sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil, each 16 inches long, and place on the baking sheet.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Chop veggies and sausage into bite-size pieces, and the corn into quarters.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Divide the sausage and veggies evenly between the six sheets of foil. Place food on the dull side to prevent sticking. Center the food on each foil sheet.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Season each foil packet evenly with the paprika, garlic powder and salt and pepper.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet over the food.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Double fold the ends, leaving room for heat to circulate inside.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Double fold the two short ends to seal the packet.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Fold the foil around the ingredients like a present.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Bake 20–25 minutes.
b62b3763-9d2e-4c8e-a529-1ae8e370570c Gingerly open one of the packets and test for doneness.
ecba91f2-d04d-40b2-a200-e0b02f7fbf75 In a medium-sized saucepan, whisk together orange juice, lemon juice, lime juice, orange marmalade, garlic, soy sauce and brown sugar. In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and water and whisk into the sauce. Heat to medium-high heat and let simmer until it starts to thicken. Remove from heat.
ecba91f2-d04d-40b2-a200-e0b02f7fbf75 Heat grill to medium-high heat. On a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil place the salmon on dull side. Fold up the edges of the aluminum foil. Spread on half of the marinade. Place the foil on the grill and let the salmon cook for 10–12 minutes or until salmon is opaque and cooked throughout. Spread remaining marinade on top and serve.
3c0ab81d-3eb3-4add-9f97-ba952c789e64 Shuck corn and wrap in a single layer of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil to fully enclose the corn then grill corn in foil.
3c0ab81d-3eb3-4add-9f97-ba952c789e64 In a small bowl, combine sour cream, mayo, cilantro, minced garlic, garlic powder, cayenne pepper, cumin, and 2 tablespoons fresh lime juice. Stir to blend and set aside.
3c0ab81d-3eb3-4add-9f97-ba952c789e64 Partially unwrap corn to cool for a few minutes before applying sauce. Keep the foil under the corn to be used for serving the corn.
3c0ab81d-3eb3-4add-9f97-ba952c789e64 Using a basting brush, generously brush on the sauce and sprinkle generously with cotija cheese. Garnish with chili powder and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges.
435491b8-be8e-4770-ace5-4482483590a3 Place a layer of veggies on a large sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil folded in half.
435491b8-be8e-4770-ace5-4482483590a3 Add a couple pats of butter, salt and pepper and any garlic or onions you might like.
435491b8-be8e-4770-ace5-4482483590a3 Top with a filet of fish or handful of shrimp.
435491b8-be8e-4770-ace5-4482483590a3 Season the fish or shrimp with salt and pepper and any other herbs you’d like. Drizzle the top with olive oil. Top the fish or shrimp with a slice of citrus fruit.
435491b8-be8e-4770-ace5-4482483590a3 Close up the foil into packet and place around the edge of 400-600°F fire in the middle of the grill, around a fire pit or next to a campfire.
435491b8-be8e-4770-ace5-4482483590a3 Once the ingredients start to sizzle inside, wait 10 minutes and then rotate the packets 180°F.
435491b8-be8e-4770-ace5-4482483590a3 Use a probe thermometer to check the temp of the fish inside the packet by poking the probe into the packet. Target temperature is 135-145°F.
435491b8-be8e-4770-ace5-4482483590a3 Once the fish comes to temperature, remove the packet from the grill and serve.
6a9d4841-af91-4c01-a270-76dbd0a9fd32 Make the foil packets: Create 6 packets of foil by ripping off four 9-inch-long pieces of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil. In a large bowl, add the melted butter. Toss the fries in the butter and using your hands, make sure they are all coated. Divide the fries evenly into the foil packets, no more than a cup in each packet. Carefully fold one long edge of the foil over the fries. Repeat on the other long edge. On the short edge, fold over twice, creating a bit of bulk, covering an inch of the fries as well. Repeat with the remaining edge. Pinch the corners together to create stability.
6a9d4841-af91-4c01-a270-76dbd0a9fd32 Grill the Fries: Place the foil packs, with the open side up, on the cooler side of the grill. Cover and grill for about 15 minutes. Carefully, using heat resistant gloves, toss the fries in the foil packets. Place back on the grill and cover. Cook an additional 15 minutes, until fries are cooked through, golden brown and crispy. Meanwhile, make the creamy popper topping.
6a9d4841-af91-4c01-a270-76dbd0a9fd32 Make the Creamy Popper Topping: Heat a small cast-iron skillet over the grill. Add the oil and swirl to coat the pan. Add the onion and sauté until softened, 5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook 30 seconds longer. Add the jalapeno, mayo, sour cream, salt, and 2 tablespoons shredded mozzarella. Stir to combine. Transfer to the cooler side of the grill or cover and remove from heat.
6a9d4841-af91-4c01-a270-76dbd0a9fd32 Top the Fries: When the fries are cooked, carefully sprinkle a layer of half of the remaining mozzarella cheese over each. Using a tablespoon, dollop the creamy jalapeno popper topping over the fries. Top each with the remaining mozzarella and the chorizo. Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes longer. The cheese will be thoroughly melted. Using a flat spatula, carefully remove the foil packets from the grill to cool before serving.
6a9d4841-af91-4c01-a270-76dbd0a9fd32 Serve: Serve the cheesy fries directly in the foil packets, on plates as the bottoms will be hot. Garnish with sliced jalapeno, black beans, hot sauce (if you’re feeling bold), and cilantro.
4d17d170-c722-444f-a67b-a06462067b11 Salsa Directions: On a grill heated to medium-high heat, add the oil and swirl to coat pan. Sauté the onion for 5 to 7 minutes until soft. Carefully remove from pan. Meanwhile, char the poblano over the grill until the skin is burnt. Remove from heat and wrap in Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil for 5 minutes. When safe to handle, peel the skin from the poblano and discard. Remove the seeds and add the poblano to a food processor. Add the onion and enchilada sauce. In a food processor, blend the ingredients until smooth.
4d17d170-c722-444f-a67b-a06462067b11 Chilaquiles Directions: Preheat the grill to medium heat, hot enough that you can carefully hold your hand 3 to 4 inches above the grill grates for 3 to 5 seconds. Line the skillet with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil, leaving enough additional length to fold the foil back over to cover, ends meeting in the middle. Place a little bit of sauce to coat the foil. Add a layer of tortilla chips. In a small bowl, toss the chicken with a few tablespoons of sauce. Add a layer of chicken to the skillet. Toss the remaining tortillas chips in the enchilada sauce and top the chicken layer with it. Sprinkle cheese over the chip layer. If you are adding eggs, crack an egg into a small bowl. Drop each egg carefully over the surface. Carefully fold the overhanging foil over the layers, without letting it touch the surface of the food. Pinch the edges together. Place the skillet over the grill and allow to cook until the eggs are set about 15 minutes. When the eggs have set, using heat-resistant gloves, carefully remove the skillet from the oven (It will be hot!) and garnish with the crema and any desired toppings.
4d17d170-c722-444f-a67b-a06462067b11 Chipotle Crema Directions: Using your blender or food processor, pulse the crema, orange juice, and chipotles until smooth. Season with salt if desired. If you want more heat, add 1/2 a chipotle more at a time until you are happy—however, with canned chipotles, it’s best to start small and work your way up.
3fb33066-e11e-465f-a132-ea179bb092f5 Heat your grill to 375° F, with an indirect heat zone.
3fb33066-e11e-465f-a132-ea179bb092f5 Turn a soup bowl upside down. Tear off two 18-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Place one sheet (dull side down) over the bowl and press it down to create a bowl shape. Repeat with the second sheet in the opposite direction.
3fb33066-e11e-465f-a132-ea179bb092f5 Remove the foil and set it right side up. Create four foil bowls.
3fb33066-e11e-465f-a132-ea179bb092f5 In a large bowl, combine the chorizo, rice, wine, chicken broth, tomatoes, turmeric, salt, and pepper. Mix it with your hands to blend really well.
3fb33066-e11e-465f-a132-ea179bb092f5 Place one foil bowl inside the soup bowl you used for the mold. Add 1-1/2 cups of the chorizo rice mixture. Be sure to get an equal amount of liquid in each foil bowl.
3fb33066-e11e-465f-a132-ea179bb092f5 Pull two opposite sides together and fold them over once or twice. Pull the other two sides together and seal the loose openings, folding and pressing, as needed. Repeat with the other three bowls.
3fb33066-e11e-465f-a132-ea179bb092f5 Cook over indirect heat for 30–45 minutes, until the rice is al dente.
3fb33066-e11e-465f-a132-ea179bb092f5 Open the pouch. Add 5 shrimp to each pouch. Fold back up. Cook for 15 more minutes, or until the rice is tender and the shrimp is pink.
3fb33066-e11e-465f-a132-ea179bb092f5 Carefully, open the pouch (it will be hot). Garnish with fresh parsley.
98f8e07a-2f2a-4a18-8ab6-6323404b5f15 Cube the beef, peppers and onions into the size you prefer.
98f8e07a-2f2a-4a18-8ab6-6323404b5f15 Marinate the beef cubes with the marinade ingredients. Cover and let it sit in the fridge for 30 minutes.
98f8e07a-2f2a-4a18-8ab6-6323404b5f15 While the beef marinades, assemble the skewers with the beef cubes and veggies.
98f8e07a-2f2a-4a18-8ab6-6323404b5f15 Tear off a long sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil, about 16–18 inches long and lay it flat on the counter or tray. Place the skewers onto the center of the foil sheet.
98f8e07a-2f2a-4a18-8ab6-6323404b5f15 Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet over the food. Double-fold the ends, leaving room for the heat to circulate inside. Fold to seal both short ends. The skewers end will not seal completely, so don’t worry too much about that. Refer to blog photos.
98f8e07a-2f2a-4a18-8ab6-6323404b5f15 To avoid juices puddling around the food, use a skewer to place holes on the bottom side of the packet.
98f8e07a-2f2a-4a18-8ab6-6323404b5f15 Grill the skewers for about 5 minutes and then turn the skewers over (just the skewers, not the whole pack) to grill on the other side for another 5 minutes. Grilling time varies based on your liking.
98f8e07a-2f2a-4a18-8ab6-6323404b5f15 Remove the skewers from the grill and transfer onto a dish lined with a new sheet of aluminum foil for easy cleanup.
98f8e07a-2f2a-4a18-8ab6-6323404b5f15 Garnish with some parsley and serve with your favorite dip, BBQ seasoning, and side dish.
27bbb14e-6c0d-428c-8dcc-5f29498ec0c5 In a large sealable bag, combine steak, 2 tablespoons oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, ground cumin, chili powder, smoked paprika, cayenne pepper and lime juice. Seal and move everything around with your hands to evenly coat the meat. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, up to 24 hours.
27bbb14e-6c0d-428c-8dcc-5f29498ec0c5 Preheat the grill to medium-high heat when ready to cook.
27bbb14e-6c0d-428c-8dcc-5f29498ec0c5 Add sliced peppers, onion, and remaining 1 tablespoon oil to a medium bowl. Toss to coat the vegetables and season with salt and pepper.
27bbb14e-6c0d-428c-8dcc-5f29498ec0c5 Tear off six large sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil.
27bbb14e-6c0d-428c-8dcc-5f29498ec0c5 Divide the pepper mixture between the sheets evenly, then top with even amounts of sliced steak. Seal the foil tightly around the mixture to form individual packets.
27bbb14e-6c0d-428c-8dcc-5f29498ec0c5 Grill for 6 to 8 minutes on each side. Cooking for 6 minutes per side will get you medium-rare steak. Cook longer for desired doneness.
27bbb14e-6c0d-428c-8dcc-5f29498ec0c5 Serve immediately with your favorite toppings and warmed tortillas.
a5139476-54a3-409d-9ba0-05f7340953c0 PREP the grill. Preheat the grill for indirect heat, around 400 degrees.
a5139476-54a3-409d-9ba0-05f7340953c0 SAUTE the onions. Place a cast-iron skillet on the grill to preheat and add 1 tablespoon butter. Swirl to coat the pan. Add the onions and salt. Allow the onions to sauté, stirring as needed, until they are soft and starting to get lightly golden brown. Remove the onions from the skillet and set aside.
a5139476-54a3-409d-9ba0-05f7340953c0 SCRAMBLE the eggs. In the same skillet, add another tablespoon of butter, if needed to grease the pan. Whisk the eggs in a small bowl and add 1 tablespoon milk. Pour into the hot skillet and, using a wooden spoon, gently fold the eggs, pulling from the bottom, to scramble. Remove the skillet from heat just as they are starting to set and continue to gently stir. Transfer the eggs to a bowl and set aside. Season with salt if desired and sprinkle in chopped scallions.
a5139476-54a3-409d-9ba0-05f7340953c0 REHEAT the leftover burger. In the same skillet, toss in the leftover burger patty and break into tiny chunks. Keep over the heat just long enough to warm. Remove from heat.
a5139476-54a3-409d-9ba0-05f7340953c0 ASSEMBLE the sandwich. Toss the cheese together in a bowl. Coat one side of each slice of bread with a light smear of mayo. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Tear off a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil three times the size of the slice and arrange the slice, mayo side down. Sprinkle 1/8th of the cheese blend onto the bread. Top with 1/4 of the scrambled eggs, 1/4 of the leftover burger, and 1/4 of the sautéed onions. Place another 1/8th of the cheese on top and the remaining slice of bread and sprinkle with a bit of parmesan cheese. Fold the foil around the sandwich, from the top down and bottom overhang up, folding the overhanging edges on the sides securely under the sandwich as well.
a5139476-54a3-409d-9ba0-05f7340953c0 GRILL. Place the sandwiches on the cooler side of the preheated grill and cook about 15 to 20 minutes per side, until golden brown, rotating every 5 to 7 minutes so no side gets too hot.
a5139476-54a3-409d-9ba0-05f7340953c0 SERVE. When the sandwiches are toasted to a golden brown and the cheese has melted through, remove from the grill. Allow to cool 5 minutes, or until the foil can be handled. Carefully peel back the foil and enjoy.
fb5a2c0d-a253-4e74-ac13-d8af744641ec Combine salsa ingredients and refrigerate at least 20 minutes until ready to cook the fish.
fb5a2c0d-a253-4e74-ac13-d8af744641ec Mix the dried spices and seasoning together in a small bowl, squeeze the lime on the fish then rub the seasoning onto fish.
fb5a2c0d-a253-4e74-ac13-d8af744641ec Lay out 4 large 18-by-12-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil. Put the fish in the center of each and drizzle with olive oil.
fb5a2c0d-a253-4e74-ac13-d8af744641ec Bring the short ends of the foil together and fold twice to seal; fold in the sides to seal, leaving room for steam.
fb5a2c0d-a253-4e74-ac13-d8af744641ec Cook the packets.
c6073ffd-f995-41d2-8c91-bad0282797af Score, truss, and season pork with marinade. Cover and place in the fridge for 4+ hours. Ideally overnight.
c6073ffd-f995-41d2-8c91-bad0282797af Heat your grill to 250° F. Pull out pork and discard excess marinade. Smoke until internal temperature is 165° F (about 4 hours).
c6073ffd-f995-41d2-8c91-bad0282797af In your blender, add all ingredients for braising sauce and blend until fine.
c6073ffd-f995-41d2-8c91-bad0282797af Once at 165° F, pull pork off the grill. Heat your grill to 400° F and preheat a skillet with some oil. Place the pork back into the skillet and tightly cover with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Close grill lid and braise until completely tender (about 2+ hours) until about 195° F internal or when it pulls easily with a fork. Check and move pork around as necessary.
c6073ffd-f995-41d2-8c91-bad0282797af Once tender, pull pork off and wrap tightly in the Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil for 10 minutes. Shred pork and heat up tortillas. Top tortillas with pork, onion, cilantro and jalapenos. Wrap in more foil to save for later! Enjoy!
72dbfdc6-8320-483a-8ede-f7d4bbcebf6b Line a 18x13x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
72dbfdc6-8320-483a-8ede-f7d4bbcebf6b Cut stems off strawberries, then hollow out the inside to create a small cavity.
72dbfdc6-8320-483a-8ede-f7d4bbcebf6b Place peanut butter in a quart-sized plastic storage bag. Cut the corner of the bag, then pipe peanut butter inside the strawberries. Transfer strawberries to prepared baking pan.
72dbfdc6-8320-483a-8ede-f7d4bbcebf6b Drizzle strawberries with melted chocolate. Chill until chocolate is set.
6f735c13-edcf-4b40-bcd9-e4db028db57e MAKE THE MARINADE: Pour the orange juice, white vinegar, lime juice and honey into a resealable gallon-size bag. Add the garlic, cumin, paprika, salt, red pepper flakes and black pepper. Seal well and shake to combine.
6f735c13-edcf-4b40-bcd9-e4db028db57e PREP THE PORK: If needed, remove any silverskin from the tenderloin. Cut the pork into 1-inch cubes. Add the cut pork and onion to the marinade, making sure to seal well.
6f735c13-edcf-4b40-bcd9-e4db028db57e MARINATE: Let the pork marinate for 4 to 8 hours in the fridge or in a cooler on ice.
6f735c13-edcf-4b40-bcd9-e4db028db57e PREP THE GRILL: When ready to grill, prep the grill for indirect grilling, around 375° to 400° F. Divide the tenderloin into four Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil packets, folding up the edges to seal in the juices. Pinch the tops shut.
6f735c13-edcf-4b40-bcd9-e4db028db57e GRILL: Place the foil packets over the grill and allow to cook for 10 minutes in the foil packets. Carefully open the packets, rotating if needed based on your heat source, and allow the pork to cook 10 minutes longer.
6f735c13-edcf-4b40-bcd9-e4db028db57e SERVE: Remove the pork bites, in their packets, from the grill once they reach 145° F. Allow the pork to cool in the packets for 5 minutes. Serve with toothpicks as an appetizer or as individual portions with desired sides if using as a main dish.
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Set up your grill or smoker for indirect grilling and preheat to 225° degrees. Brush the grill grate clean and oil it well.
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea In a small bowl, combine the barbecue rub and the smoked paprika. In another bowl, combine the barbecue sauce with the honey and lemon juice. Set aside.
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Place the ribs on a rimmed sheet pan. (For easier cleanup, line the pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil.) If your butcher has not already done so, remove the tough papery membrane on the back of the bones and discard. Using a sharp paring knife, make shallow cuts on either side of and close to each bone on the back of the ribs. This extra step makes deboning the ribs easier once they are cooked.
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Season the ribs on both sides with the barbecue rub; don’t forget the ends.
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Place 3/4 cup of wood chips on each pile of coals or in the smoker box of your gas grill. Lacking a smoker box, place a foil smoking pouch (see Notes below) over one of the burners on your gas grill (under the grill grate).
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Place the ribs directly on the grill grate, meat side up, away from direct heat. Smoke the ribs, lid down, for 2 hours, replenishing the fuel and wood chips as needed.
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Transfer the ribs, meat side up, to the prepared sheet of foil, long sides parallel to each other. Turn the sides and ends of the foil up slightly. Pour the lemon-lime soda around the bottom of the rack. Bring the ends of the foil together and fold twice to make a tight seal. Repeat with the sides. (If using Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty 18” Extra-Wide Foil, bring the long sides over the ribs first, fold, then fold the ends)
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Return the foiled ribs to the grill, seam side up. Replace the lid and cook the ribs for an additional 2 to 2 1/2 hours, replenishing the fuel as needed. (You do not need smoking chips once the ribs are foiled)
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Transfer the ribs to a rimmed sheet pan or cutting board. Carefully open the foil package, avoiding any escaping steam. Discard the foil and any accumulated juices. Brush the ribs on both sides with the reserved barbecue sauce.
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Return the ribs to the grill, meat side up, and continue to cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour, or until the sauce sets and the ribs are very tender. The meat will have shrunk from the ends of the bones by 1/2-inch; a toothpick inserted between the bones near the center of the rack should pierce the meat easily.
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Using a spatula and tongs, carefully transfer the ribs, bone side up, to a cutting board. (Try to keep the rack from flexing and tearing by supporting it in the middle with the spatula.) Carefully remove the bones. They should release easily with minimal help from a paring knife.
8adb13fe-2932-463f-aa24-ac06efd14eea Arrange the now-boneless ribs meat side up on the bottom portion of the bread. Brush the top of the ribs with additional barbecue sauce, if desired. Top with pickle chips and sliced onions. Drizzle lightly with barbecue sauce. To serve, slice the sandwich into 2 or 3 equal portions using a serrated knife.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Slice the garlic cloves into slivers.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Start with the pork shoulder meat-side up/fat-side down.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Using a thin-bladed knife, cut slits in the pork shoulder every 1.5–2 inches.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Leave the knife in the slit, and slide a garlic sliver down the flat side of the knife into the slit and then remove the knife blade.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Cover the meat side of the pork shoulder with slits filled with garlic slivers.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Flip over to the fat side and give the fat a 1/3–1/2-inch crisscross cut.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 In the gaps in the crisscross cut, make more slits on the fat side and insert more garlic.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Flip fat side back over to the bottom and apply a binder (I used duck fat, but mustard or mayo work too), and then season with salt and the barbecue rub.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Prepare the grill and set at 275° F.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Place the pork shoulder fat-side up/rubbed-side down on the smoker, apply the binder and hit with salt and the barbecue rub.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Insert a heat-resistant probe thermometer and close the lid for several hours.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 After the shoulder gets to around 160° F, foil the pork with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil (I foiled at 156° F, which took about 4 hours).
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Leave in the foil until the pork shoulder hits 203° F (This took a total cook time of 5.5 hours).
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Once it hits 203°, remove the probe thermometer and wrap in more Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil to keep liquid from leaking out the hole created by the probe thermometer.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Wrap in a towel and place in an empty cooler or an unlit oven or microwave for at least an hour.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 After an hour of rest (or more), pull back the foil and pull the shoulder blade out. If it comes out clean, it’s perfect.
346acc97-6cb5-44fe-b50b-805624eac490 Pull the pork, put it on buns and top with barbecue sauce and/or coleslaw.
b78e29a3-c273-49c5-bf2e-1adeec612d08 In a bowl, combine 1/2 cup softened butter, 1/4 cup parsley, 1/4 tsp of salt, 1/4 tsp of garlic powder and finely minced garlic. Mash together with a fork. In a separate bowl, combine the parmesan and mozzarella cheese.
b78e29a3-c273-49c5-bf2e-1adeec612d08 Cut your loaf of French bread in half lengthwise and spread the butter mixture on the inside of each half. Place bread buttered side down on a large sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and fold over the foil, creating a pack and sealing the edges. Place foil pack on the grill buttered side down, cover the grill with the lid and cook for 5 minutes.
b78e29a3-c273-49c5-bf2e-1adeec612d08 Carefully open the foil. Flip the halves over with tongs and sprinkle the cheese mixture on top. Do not close the foil pack. Cover the grill and continue to cook for another 4 to 5 minutes to melt the cheese. Remove from the grill, slice bread, garnish with parsley and serve warm.
37135683-2c42-43f3-96c8-99dc96c407de WHISK TOGETHER INGREDIENTS: Heat grill to medium-high heat. In a large bowl, whisk together the dry ranch mix, olive oil, apple cider vinegar and garlic. Add in the chicken, red bell pepper, yellow bell pepper, red onion and zucchini and toss to coat.
37135683-2c42-43f3-96c8-99dc96c407de PREPARE SKEWERS: Lay down a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with the dull side up. Thread the chicken and vegetables onto the wooden skewers. Lay evenly across the foil. Fold up the edges and tightly close around the skewers.
37135683-2c42-43f3-96c8-99dc96c407de GRILL THE CHICKEN SKEWERS: Place the foil pack on the fire or grill. Let the kabobs grill on each side about 5 to 7 minutes, or until chicken is cooked throughout and no longer pink.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Sauté the chopped onion in olive oil (or your choice of oil) until fragrant (2 minutes) over medium-high heat.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Add the farro to the pan and continue cooking for 1–2 minutes over medium heat to bring out the natural nuttiness of the farro.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Lower the heat to simmer and add one-third of the stock at a time to the farro. Repeat this process adding the remainder of the stock in thirds until the farro has absorbed the liquid.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Remove from the heat, cover and set aside until needed (the farro can be cooked ahead of time and refrigerated).
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 While the farro is cooking, sauté the mushrooms in butter until soft. Set aside until needed.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Pat dry the skirt steak with paper towels. Liberally season the steak with sea salt and black pepper. If you’d like to add more flavors to the skirt steak, use your favorite seasonings before cooking.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Heat a sauté pan on high heat until almost smoking. Very carefully add one tablespoon of cooking oil to the pan. Very carefully add the seasoned skirt steak to the pan and sear the steak 2–3 minutes on each side until you get a nice crust on the steak. Make sure to have your kitchen fan on and a window open if possible.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Cut four 16-inch pieces of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Place 1 cup of cooked farro in the center of the foil.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Top the farro with one cup of raw spinach. Add the pan-seared skirt steak on top of the spinach.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Top the skirt steak with the sautéed mushrooms and bleu cheese crumbles.
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 To close the foil pouch: Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet over the food. Double fold the ends, leaving room for heat to circulate inside. Double fold the two short ends to seal the packet. Place the four packets on a sheet pan or baking pan and place into a 350° F preheated oven for 25 minutes (or until the internal temperature has reached 165° F).
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Carefully remove the packets from the oven and cautiously open the packets for serving as steam will escape. The foil will be hot, so use kitchen gloves or towels when touching them. Don’t spoil dinner by getting burned!
f5cd1414-887a-4237-b8fa-26239e51d862 Carefully slide the skirt steak and all the fixings onto a plate, and dinner is served!
a12346f5-9830-41e9-9442-dae0685a3d6e Heat the oven to 400° F. Lightly spray a 9-by-13-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
a12346f5-9830-41e9-9442-dae0685a3d6e Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook lasagna noodles for 5 to 6 minutes, then drain. Place the noodles flat on a couple baking sheets that have been sprayed with nonstick spray. This will keep the noodles from sticking and make it a LOT easier to assemble.
a12346f5-9830-41e9-9442-dae0685a3d6e In a medium skillet, heat oil for the pumpkin layer over medium-high heat. Add sausage and onion, cooking and stirring occasionally, until the sausage is browned, about 5 minutes. Drain out any excess liquid, place in a medium bowl, and let cool for a couple of minutes.
a12346f5-9830-41e9-9442-dae0685a3d6e Add the remaining pumpkin layer ingredients to the bowl with sausage and onion. Set aside.
a12346f5-9830-41e9-9442-dae0685a3d6e Stir together all the ingredients for the ricotta mixture in a medium bowl until combined. Set aside.
a12346f5-9830-41e9-9442-dae0685a3d6e To assemble lasagna, spread 1 1/2 cups of pumpkin mixture on the bottom of the prepared baking pan. Place 4 noodles vertically and 1 at the top horizontally. Spread over half of the ricotta mixture on top of the noodles, then top with 3/4 cup shredded mozzarella.
a12346f5-9830-41e9-9442-dae0685a3d6e Top with 1 1/2 cups of the pumpkin mixture, then sprinkle with 1/2 cup parmesan cheese.
a12346f5-9830-41e9-9442-dae0685a3d6e Repeat layers of noodles, remaining ricotta mixture, and 3/4 cup shredded mozzarella. Top with remaining pumpkin and 1/2 cup parmesan cheese. Sprinkle with remaining 1 1/2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese. If you plan to freeze, stop here and refer to freezer notes below!
a12346f5-9830-41e9-9442-dae0685a3d6e Cover with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Bake for 25 minutes, then remove foil and bake for another 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese is browned lightly on top. Garnish with more grated parmesan cheese and fresh thyme leaves. Cool 15 minutes before cutting and serving.
ca00052b-c9d5-4e6c-aaf7-d6e04d4f1dff Heat oven to 450° F and place an oven rack on the lowest shelf.
ca00052b-c9d5-4e6c-aaf7-d6e04d4f1dff Place a large, nonstick pan over medium-low heat. Once heated, add the buffalo sauce and cream cheese. Continuously stir to help the cream cheese melt and ensure there are no lumps. Pour in the ranch dressing and add the rotisserie chicken to warm. Stir to combine.
ca00052b-c9d5-4e6c-aaf7-d6e04d4f1dff Remove from heat while you finish preparing the dough.
ca00052b-c9d5-4e6c-aaf7-d6e04d4f1dff Next, combine the Greek yogurt and flour in a large mixing bowl or stand mixer. Using a spatula, fold to combine. Once you can no longer fold, use your hands to knead and form a large ball.
ca00052b-c9d5-4e6c-aaf7-d6e04d4f1dff Lightly flour the counter and rolling pin. Roll out the dough and carefully transfer it to a prepared, Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil-lined pizza pan. Press the edges of the dough toward the pan and smooth out any areas that may be thicker than others.
ca00052b-c9d5-4e6c-aaf7-d6e04d4f1dff Brush the top of the dough with the olive oil. Bake for 5 minutes on the lowest rack.
ca00052b-c9d5-4e6c-aaf7-d6e04d4f1dff Carefully remove from the oven and top with the buffalo ranch chicken, mozzarella cheese and cheddar cheese.
ca00052b-c9d5-4e6c-aaf7-d6e04d4f1dff Bake for 5–8 minutes or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.
ca00052b-c9d5-4e6c-aaf7-d6e04d4f1dff Garnish with chopped chives and a drizzle of both buffalo sauce and ranch dressing.
550e5333-7566-4d42-80f7-f37386b238e6 Combine all ingredients for chocolate BBQ sauce in a large saucepan. Heat, stirring often until combined and smooth. Reserve 1 ½ cups for cooked turkey.
550e5333-7566-4d42-80f7-f37386b238e6 Preheat oven to 375°F. Remove neck and giblets from turkey. Rinse, and pat dry.
550e5333-7566-4d42-80f7-f37386b238e6 Tear off a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil 2 1/2 times longer than turkey. Place turkey lengthwise in center of aluminum foil sheet to cook.
550e5333-7566-4d42-80f7-f37386b238e6 Brush with chocolate BBQ sauce.
550e5333-7566-4d42-80f7-f37386b238e6 Close foil loosely by overlapping the ends. Turn up short sides of the foil to hold in juices. Do not seal airtight. Place foil-wrapped turkey in roasting pan at least 2 inches deep. Insert meat thermometer through foil into thickest part of inner thigh, not touching bone.
550e5333-7566-4d42-80f7-f37386b238e6 Roast turkey until meat thermometer reads at least 165°F in the breast and thickest part of the thigh not touching the bone, about 2 hours 45 minutes to 3 hours 15 minutes for a 14 lb unstuffed turkey.
550e5333-7566-4d42-80f7-f37386b238e6 Baste with chocolate BBQ sauce 2-3 times during cooking. To baste, carefully pull back foil to expose turkey skin. Baste with sauce then return foil and continue cooking. Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes. Remove and discard foil.
550e5333-7566-4d42-80f7-f37386b238e6 Transfer to a serving dish and baste with reserved BBQ sauce. Place chocolate chips on top. Dress the dish with fruit and chocolate shavings just before serving.
bf008762-4062-4648-aaed-2a0452688169 Preheat oven to 350°F. Mix together all ingredients for gingerbread rub and set aside. Whisk together molasses and olive oil and set aside.
bf008762-4062-4648-aaed-2a0452688169 Line a roasting pan that is at least 2 inches deep with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil.
bf008762-4062-4648-aaed-2a0452688169 Remove neck and giblets from turkey; rinse and pat turkey dry. Place turkey in foil lined roasting pan. If desired loosely stuff turkey.
bf008762-4062-4648-aaed-2a0452688169 Brush with oil and molasses mixture then fully coat turkey in gingerbread rub.
bf008762-4062-4648-aaed-2a0452688169 Make a foil tent by placing a sheet of foil over the turkey, leaving 1 inch between top of turkey and foil test for heat circulation. Crimp foil onto long sides of pan.
bf008762-4062-4648-aaed-2a0452688169 Roast turkey until meat thermometer reads at least 165°F in the breast and thickest part of the thigh not touching the bone, about 3 to 3 1/2 hours for a 14 lb unstuffed turkey. Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes. Remove and discard foil.
bf008762-4062-4648-aaed-2a0452688169 Transfer turkey to a serving dish. Pipe mashed potato gingerbread man outlines on Turkey. Dress the plate with fresh herbs, gingerbread cookies and candy just before serving.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Preheat the oven to 350° F.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Cream the butter and sugars together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed or using a hand blender on high speed for 5-7 minutes or until light and fluffy.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Pour in the vanilla and add the eggs and mix on medium speed until completely mixed in.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Mix together the baking soda, baking powder, flour and mashed 2/3 cup spicy hot cheese puffs together in a bowl until combined.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Add the dry ingredients to the stand mixer on low speed and mix until just combined.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Place a 3-tablespoon scoop of the cookie dough into your hands and roll it into a ball.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Roll each round cookie dough ball into the extra ½ cup of mashed spicy hot cheese puffs in a bowl to coat on all sides.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Place the cookies on a cookie sheet tray lined with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® and repeat until all of the dough has been used.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Bake at 350°F for 12 mins.
50d2df6a-ee84-43e5-bda9-05c91178457c Cool completely on a rack before serving.
e7d26059-dd52-4dd2-afad-2515c194518b PREHEAT the oven to 400°.
e7d26059-dd52-4dd2-afad-2515c194518b ADD 1 tablespoon of flour to a Reynolds® Oven Bag and shake. Place the bag in a 13x9x2 inch casserole dish.
e7d26059-dd52-4dd2-afad-2515c194518b TOSS together the pineapple, red onions, 1 tablespoon of olive oil, salt and pepper together into a large bowl and pour it into the Reynolds® Oven bag.
e7d26059-dd52-4dd2-afad-2515c194518b MIX together the cumin, chili powder, oregano, red pepper flakes and Kosher salt in a large bowl.
e7d26059-dd52-4dd2-afad-2515c194518b ADD the pork tenderloin and 1 tablespoon of olive oil to the bowl with the spices and herbs and mix thoroughly until the pork tenderloin is completely covered and add it on top of the pineapple salsa in the Reynolds® Oven Bag.
e7d26059-dd52-4dd2-afad-2515c194518b CLOSE the bag and seal it with the provided tie.
e7d26059-dd52-4dd2-afad-2515c194518b CUT 6 half inch slits in the top of the bag and tuck all of the ends into the pan and bake for 30-35 minutes on 400° or until the pork is browned and has reached an internal temperature of 160°.
e7d26059-dd52-4dd2-afad-2515c194518b REMOVE the pork tenderloin from the bag, drain any excess liquid from the bag, and let it rest for 2 to 3 minutes before very thinly slicing it.
e7d26059-dd52-4dd2-afad-2515c194518b SERVE the sliced pork on corn tortillas and top off with pineapple salsa and fresh cilantro leaves.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab CREAM together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab ADD in the vanilla and then 1 egg at a time until mixed into the butter-sugar mixture.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab MIX the flour, baking powder, green tea powder and salt together in a bowl and add it into the creamed butter-sugar mixture while alternating with the milk but beginning and ending with the dry ingredients. Be sure to stop and scrape the sides of the bowl often.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab POUR half of the batter into a bowl and set aside. Dye the remaining batter black with food coloring.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab SPOON each of the batters, creating a large checkerboard-like pattern into two (2) Reynolds® 8-inch Round Bakeware pans. Using a knife, swirl the batters together to create a marbled look. Tap the pans against the counter to evenly distribute and settle the marbled batter.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab BAKE the cakes in the oven on 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and firm in the center.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab COOL the cakes on a cooling rack for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab WHIP the butter and cream cheese in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment until light and fluffy.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab ADD in the vanilla and powdered sugar until completely mixed in.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab PLACE 1 cake layer on a cake plate. Add about 1 cup frosting to the center and spread evenly. Place the second cake layer on top. Frost the cake with the remaining frosting.
07ebebaa-ed78-4dad-86e8-04ce13dd68ab PIPE on melted chocolate to create a spider web design.
8f2e3ad5-69b0-471f-8b1c-586df7625fbf Make the dressing by combining the avocado, yogurt, garlic, lime juice, honey, salt and pepper in a blender. Blend until creamy (the dressing will be thick), then cover and refrigerate the dressing while you make the salad.
8f2e3ad5-69b0-471f-8b1c-586df7625fbf Preheat the grill for 10 minutes on medium heat. Prepare the foil packets by placing two halibut filets each on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Squeeze the lime juice atop the filets, then sprinkle them with the cumin and a pinch of salt and pepper. Fold and crimp together the edges to form sealed foil packets.
8f2e3ad5-69b0-471f-8b1c-586df7625fbf Place the foil packets on the grill, close the lid and grill the fish for 8 to 10 minutes or just until the fish flakes easily and is opaque throughout. Remove the foil packets from the grill and unwrap them.
8f2e3ad5-69b0-471f-8b1c-586df7625fbf Prepare the taco salad by layering the lettuce, beans, cheese, tomatoes and tortilla strips on serving plates. Arrange the grilled fish on top of the salads, drizzle with the avocado dressing and serve.
4dbe914f-9e2f-46f1-9b3a-134e802f11db PREHEAT oven to 350oF. Line muffin pan(s) with 12 Reynolds® StayBrite® Baking Cups.
4dbe914f-9e2f-46f1-9b3a-134e802f11db WHISK together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon in a large bowl. Stir in apples, cranberries, and orange zest.
4dbe914f-9e2f-46f1-9b3a-134e802f11db WHISK together eggs and buttermilk in a medium sized bowl. Stir in melted butter.
4dbe914f-9e2f-46f1-9b3a-134e802f11db FOLD buttermilk mixture gently into flour mixture until combined.
4dbe914f-9e2f-46f1-9b3a-134e802f11db FILL baking cups two-thirds full of batter (approx. ¼ cup of batter).
4dbe914f-9e2f-46f1-9b3a-134e802f11db BAKE for 20 to 23 minutes, until muffins are brown around edges and spring back when touched. Let muffins cool slightly, about 5 minutes, before transferring to a wire rack.
4dbe914f-9e2f-46f1-9b3a-134e802f11db SERVE warm or at room temperature.
b55d8b8a-56f6-40ff-9e77-6b08366fd846 PREHEAT grill to medium-high or oven to 450°F. MIX teriyaki sauce, honey, rice vinegar, minced ginger, sesame oil and red pepper flakes in a small bowl; set aside.
b55d8b8a-56f6-40ff-9e77-6b08366fd846 PLACE a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil, with the non-stick (dull) side facing up on counter with non-stick (dull) side facing up. Place a salmon fillet and 1/4 of the vegetables in center of foil. Spoon 1 tablespoon teriyaki mixture over fillet.
b55d8b8a-56f6-40ff-9e77-6b08366fd846 BRING up sides of foil; fold down two times. DOUBLE FOLD both ends of foil to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. REPEAT to make four packets. Reserve remaining teriyaki mixture to serve with salmon.
b55d8b8a-56f6-40ff-9e77-6b08366fd846 PLACE packets on baking pan with 1-inch sides to transport to grill or bake in oven.
b55d8b8a-56f6-40ff-9e77-6b08366fd846 SLIDE packets onto grill.
b55d8b8a-56f6-40ff-9e77-6b08366fd846 GRILL 8 to 10 minutes in covered grill – OR - BAKE 15 to 20 minutes or until salmon is desired doneness. If grilling, use tongs or oven mitts to SLIDE hot packets back onto pan and transport. OPEN packets carefully by cutting along top folds with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape.
b55d8b8a-56f6-40ff-9e77-6b08366fd846 SERVE with hot cooked rice, drizzled with remaining teriyaki sauce if desired.
4045d735-057b-4d18-b044-d81256a4b03c HEAT oven to 350°F. Line large cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
4045d735-057b-4d18-b044-d81256a4b03c UNROLL pie crusts on work surface. Spread peanut butter chocolate spread over 1 pie crust to within 1/8 inch of edge; sprinkle with bacon. Top with remaining pie crust; press lightly into filling.
4045d735-057b-4d18-b044-d81256a4b03c BEAT egg and 2 teaspoons water until blended in a small bowl. In another small bowl, mix peanuts and 1/2 teaspoon coarse sea salt. Brush egg mixture evenly over pie crust; sprinkle with peanut mixture. With pizza cutter or knife, cut 18 rows by 4 rows. Carefully place fries 1 inch apart on cookie sheets.
4045d735-057b-4d18-b044-d81256a4b03c BAKE 14 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
4045d735-057b-4d18-b044-d81256a4b03c Meanwhile, in small microwavable bowl, microwave caramel topping uncovered on High 30 to 50 seconds or until warm. Serve with fries.
e33377a6-34f4-4b9a-9756-bae697234ee5 Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Slice off the beet leaves close to the tip of the beet. Discard the beet greens. Scrub the beets thoroughly, and then loosely wrap each one in foil.
e33377a6-34f4-4b9a-9756-bae697234ee5 Transfer the wrapped beets to a foil-lined baking sheet. Roast for 50–60 minutes. Check the beets every 20 minutes or so. If they are starting to look dry or are scorching on the bottoms, dribble a tablespoon of water over the beets before rewrapping. Beets are done when a fork or skewer slides easily to the middle of the beet.
e33377a6-34f4-4b9a-9756-bae697234ee5 Cool the beets until they can comfortably be handled. Hold one of the beets in a paper towel and use the edges to rub the skin away. The skin should peel away easily; if it doesn't, the beets likely need to cook for a little longer. Slice the peeled beets into wedges.
e33377a6-34f4-4b9a-9756-bae697234ee5 Combine the beet wedges, mâche, goat cheese, avocado, and shaved fennel on a large serving platter and drizzle with basil vinaigrette. Sprinkle the pepitas on top and serve immediately.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Preheat oven to 350°F.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 In a large mixing bowl beat butter and almond butter with electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Add 1/2 cup granulated sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, cream of tartar, and salt. Beat until combined, scraping bowl occasionally.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Beat in egg, milk, and vanilla until combined.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Beat in whole wheat flour and as much of the all-purpose flour as you can with the mixer. Stir in any remaining flour.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 In a shallow dish combine 3 tablespoons sugar and ground almonds.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Roll balls in sugar mixture to coat.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Place balls 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet lined with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are firm and tops are cracked.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Remove from oven; immediately press a chocolate kiss in the center of each cookie.
b6a78960-c6f3-42f5-9f26-6b8d36dbbe66 Transfer to wire rack. Cool.
50f1b117-627f-444a-957b-fd476e3fe8f2 Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Arrange ribs in prepared pan. In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, cayenne pepper, and black pepper. Sprinkle the spice mixture evenly on both sides of the ribs, rubbing it in with fingers. Pour 1/4 cup water into the bottom of the baking pan and cover the pan tightly with foil.
50f1b117-627f-444a-957b-fd476e3fe8f2 Place the baking pan in oven and bake 1-3/4 to 2 hours, or until a knife can easily pierce the meat.
50f1b117-627f-444a-957b-fd476e3fe8f2 For the Honey-Bourbon Glaze, in a medium saucepan, combine bourbon, honey, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, and onion powder. Bring to a gentle boil and cook, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes, or until the mixture thickens and reduces by about half, watching closely toward the end of cooking (mixture may foam). Or, substitute your favorite barbecue sauce.
50f1b117-627f-444a-957b-fd476e3fe8f2 Remove the ribs from oven and brush with some of the Honey-Bourbon Glaze.
50f1b117-627f-444a-957b-fd476e3fe8f2 Return to oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until just starting to brown. Cut and serve immediately with the remaining Honey-Bourbon Glaze.
b0010d36-50ba-4911-9b67-2711ef70ed08 In a mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, combine flour and salt. Add the cold butter to the flour mixture. On low speed, combine until the mixture looks like coarse sand. Make sure there are no pieces of butter larger than the size of a pea, and do not over-blend.
b0010d36-50ba-4911-9b67-2711ef70ed08 In a small bowl, combine cold water, vinegar and ice. One tablespoon at a time, add the ice water mixture to the flour and butter, mixing between additions. Add the water until the dough comes together into a ball. The dough should be smooth, not sticky or crumbly. Shape into a disk. Wrap the disk in plastic wrap and keep in the fridge for at least 30 minutes or up to three days.
b0010d36-50ba-4911-9b67-2711ef70ed08 Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. In a small skillet over a low heat, add the butter slowly and melt until it is lightly brown and nutty. Take off the heat and add the scraped vanilla to the browned butter.
b0010d36-50ba-4911-9b67-2711ef70ed08 On a lightly floured surface, roll the dough into a 12x12-inch square. Place the crust on a rimmed baking sheet lined with foil.
b0010d36-50ba-4911-9b67-2711ef70ed08 Arrange the apple slices onto the prepared crust in rows, fanning slightly as you go. Make sure to leave a 1-inch border around the edges. Brush with the vanilla-infused browned butter. Sprinkle with the brown sugar. Fold up the edges of the tart over the sides of the apples, pressing down. Brush the sides of the tart with the egg wash. Refrigerate the tart for 30 minutes.
b0010d36-50ba-4911-9b67-2711ef70ed08 Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes at 425 degrees F. Rotate, decrease the oven temperature to 375 degrees F and bake for another 30 minutes or until the pastry is golden brown around the edges. Slice into 4 generous slices and serve.
ce11b240-7a5e-4f89-a127-9ea0c722bccb Preheat oven to 400°F. In a shallow dish, whisk together eggs and buttermilk until frothy. In a separate shallow dish, combine panko, basil, thyme, salt, onion powder, and pepper; set aside. Place flour in a third shallow dish.
ce11b240-7a5e-4f89-a127-9ea0c722bccb Line a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Cut off and discard tips of chicken wings. Cut wings at joints. Working with one piece at a time, dip wing pieces into flour, then egg mixture, and then into the crumb mixture, making sure to shake off excess between each coating.
ce11b240-7a5e-4f89-a127-9ea0c722bccb Arrange wings in a single layer on the prepared pan and sprinkle with any remaining crumb mixture. Drizzle on both sides with melted butter.
ce11b240-7a5e-4f89-a127-9ea0c722bccb Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour, or until chicken is tender, no longer pink, and coating is crisp, turning once halfway through baking time. Serve immediately.
b260d211-a964-4446-af1c-77df30ed31af In small bowl, stir together flour, cocoa and baking soda; set aside. In large bowl, beat 1 cup granulated sugar, the brown sugar and butter with electric mixer on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, until light and fluffy. Beat in vanilla and eggs. On low speed, beat in flour mixture until well blended. Stir in 1/2 cup of the pecans. If necessary, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 30 minutes for easier handling.
b260d211-a964-4446-af1c-77df30ed31af Heat oven to 375°F. In small bowl, mix remaining 1/2 cup pecans and 1 tablespoon sugar. With floured hands, shape about 1 tablespoon dough around each caramel, covering completely. Press 1 side of each ball into pecan mixture. Place nut side up 2 inches apart on cookie sheets lined with parchment paper.
b260d211-a964-4446-af1c-77df30ed31af Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until set and slightly cracked. Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheets to cooling rack. Cool completely, about 15 minutes.
b260d211-a964-4446-af1c-77df30ed31af In 1-quart saucepan, melt candy coating over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth. Drizzle over cookies.
d515709e-5dea-4220-b8c5-315cf98494f5 In a medium bowl, whisk together the butter, sugars and vanilla until smooth. Gently stir in the carrots and applesauce.
d515709e-5dea-4220-b8c5-315cf98494f5 Add the flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon into the wet ingredients. Stir gently with a spatula until combined.
d515709e-5dea-4220-b8c5-315cf98494f5 Fold in the oats and raisins, if desired.
d515709e-5dea-4220-b8c5-315cf98494f5 Form dough into uniform balls (I used about 1 1/2 Tbsp of dough for each cookie) and place on parchment lined baking sheet.
d515709e-5dea-4220-b8c5-315cf98494f5 Bake at 350° F for 10-12 minutes. Let cool for 2 minutes. Then carefully remove parchment and cookies from pan and let cool on counter for 15 minutes.
d515709e-5dea-4220-b8c5-315cf98494f5 While cookies are baking and cooling, prepare the frosting. Use a hand mixer to beat the cream cheese, butter and vanilla together until creamy. Add in powdered sugar 1/2 cup at a time and beat until desired consistency.
d515709e-5dea-4220-b8c5-315cf98494f5 Spread cream cheese frosting between two cooled cookies. Repeat with the rest. Eat and enjoy! Store extra cookies in an airtight container.
9e5da0da-bd24-486d-9856-afea2eca6f24 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag, Large Size in 13x9x2-inch baking pan with opening towards wide side of pan; set aside.
9e5da0da-bd24-486d-9856-afea2eca6f24 BLEND walnuts, cherries, brown sugar, butter, flour and spices in a food processor or blender until well blended.
9e5da0da-bd24-486d-9856-afea2eca6f24 STUFF each apple with walnut mixture until overflowing. Place stuffed apples in oven bag; spoon apple juice over apples.
9e5da0da-bd24-486d-9856-afea2eca6f24 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie. Cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag; tuck ends of bag in pan
9e5da0da-bd24-486d-9856-afea2eca6f24 BAKE 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender. Spoon juices in oven bag over apples.
9e5da0da-bd24-486d-9856-afea2eca6f24 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP: Serve with vanilla ice cream.
7071d9c8-5fcf-498c-9773-b67e682e1721 Heat oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9-inch pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Cut cookie dough in half crosswise. Cut each section in half lengthwise. Press dough evenly in bottom of pan to form crust.
7071d9c8-5fcf-498c-9773-b67e682e1721 Bake 10 minutes. Meanwhile, in medium bowl, mix condensed milk, peanut butter, vanilla and egg yolks until smooth. Spoon milk mixture evenly over partially baked crust; carefully spread.
7071d9c8-5fcf-498c-9773-b67e682e1721 Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until set. Sprinkle with baking chips; let stand 3 minutes to soften. Spread evenly over top. Cool completely, about 1 hour 30 minutes. Refrigerate until set, about 30 minutes. For bars, cut into 6 rows by 6 rows.
ce6eafab-34dc-4db6-be0f-dec1bb52f8ee PREHEAT oven to 425°F. Line two 8x8x2-inch baking pans with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. In large bowl, combine chicken, soup, vegetables and poultry seasoning; mix well. Spoon into baking pans.
ce6eafab-34dc-4db6-be0f-dec1bb52f8ee SOFTEN pie crusts following package directions. Using a small cookie cutter, make cut outs in pie crust or cut slits in top of crust to vent steam. Place one crust on top of each filling. Fold edges of pie crust under slightly to fit pan; flute, if desired.
ce6eafab-34dc-4db6-be0f-dec1bb52f8ee TO SERVE NOW , bake one casserole 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
ce6eafab-34dc-4db6-be0f-dec1bb52f8ee TO FREEZE, cover second casserole with a sheet of foil. Fold edges of bottom and top foil sheet together to make a packet; freeze. When frozen solid, remove baking pan from freezer.
ce6eafab-34dc-4db6-be0f-dec1bb52f8ee PREHEAT oven to 400°F. To bake, return frozen foil packet to original baking pan. Remove top foil sheet from casserole.
ce6eafab-34dc-4db6-be0f-dec1bb52f8ee BAKE 1 1/4 hours or until filling is hot.
38314e46-5894-4f6e-8a86-f09faa10491c PREHEAT oven to 450°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
38314e46-5894-4f6e-8a86-f09faa10491c Place pepper and onion slices evenly in pan.
38314e46-5894-4f6e-8a86-f09faa10491c Top with chicken tenders.
38314e46-5894-4f6e-8a86-f09faa10491c BAKE 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken reaches 170F.
38314e46-5894-4f6e-8a86-f09faa10491c Serve chicken tenders in tortillas. Top with cheese, salsa and sour cream, if desired
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 Line a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper, allowing a 2-inch overhang at each end. Brush the paper with melted butter, which will add flavor to the brownies, and set the pan aside.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 If using a glass dish, preheat the oven to 325°F. If using a metal pan, preheat to 350°F.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 Using an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese with the sour cream, sugars, vanilla, egg and salt until smooth. Set aside.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 Combine both types of flour, baking powder, and salt using a whisk. Sift this mixture into another bowl.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 In a 2 1/2-quart heavy-bottomed saucepan, melt the butter with the two types of chopped chocolate over low heat. Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the espresso powder and vanilla. Whisk the sugar and syrup into the melted chocolate mixture until smooth. Add the eggs, one at a time, whisking well after each addition. Whisk in the egg yolk and, when smooth, add the dry ingredients. Using a batter-whisk, combine the mixtures, until smooth.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 Fold in the chocolate chips, using a large rubber spatula.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 Place the pan into the preheated oven and bake the brownies until a toothpick, inserted into the center, comes out with some chocolate adhering to it without being overly wet. (If you shake the pan, gently, the brownie cake will jiggle, just a bit), about 35 minutes. Avoid over-baking.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 Place the pan on a wire rack and let the brownie cake cool thoroughly. Once cool, cover the pan with aluminum foil and let it sit, for at least 4 hours (preferably overnight) in the refrigerator.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 To cut the brownies, lift the brownie cake out of the pan, using the overhang of foil as a handle, and invert onto another flat tray, lined with wax paper.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 Peel off the foil, then re-invert, right side up, and discard the wax paper.
6d6b6fdb-4236-41a1-870a-7960b2700340 Slice the slab into 2-inch squares, using a sharp knife.
d23f09d8-5aea-42f5-871f-43a4a2c6f2d7 Heat oven to 350°F. In medium bowl, mix powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla until well blended.
d23f09d8-5aea-42f5-871f-43a4a2c6f2d7 Cut cookie dough in half. In an 8- or 9-inch square pan lined with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, break up half of dough. With floured fingers, press dough evenly in bottom of pan. Press peanut butter mixture evenly over dough. Crumble and sprinkle remaining half of cookie dough over peanut butter mixture. Carefully spread as evenly as possible.
d23f09d8-5aea-42f5-871f-43a4a2c6f2d7 Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and firm to the touch. Cool 30 minutes. Refrigerate 1 hour or until chilled. For bars, cut into 4 rows by 3 rows. Serve chilled or at room temperature.
7a5604f9-6320-4423-8333-f509d03ec744 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, set aside.
7a5604f9-6320-4423-8333-f509d03ec744 PLACE flour and melted DOVE® Brand Dark Chocolate and sugar cookie dough in large bowl. Knead until smooth. Divide dough into 12 equal pieces, set aside.
7a5604f9-6320-4423-8333-f509d03ec744 DIVIDE one piece of dough into two pieces. Roll each piece of dough on a lightly floured sheet of parchment paper into 8-inch ropes. Place the two ropes side-by-side, pinching the tops together. Twist the ropes, rolling them into one rope. Shape into a wreath. Transfer to parchment-lined cookie sheets. Repeat to make 12 wreaths.
7a5604f9-6320-4423-8333-f509d03ec744 BAKE until puffed and firm, approximately 10-12 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack to cool.
7a5604f9-6320-4423-8333-f509d03ec744 DECORATE wreaths with M&M'S® Brand Chocolate Candies by attaching them with dots of decorating frosting.
b0db6e30-22bb-4469-b422-5fbf20fc19d2 In a microwave-safe bowl, whisk together 1/4 cup sweet rice flour and 3 tablespoons milk. Microwave on high for 30 seconds, stir and then cook another 20 to 30 seconds longer or until the dough is cooked through, looks opaque and is bouncy, but not so cooked that it is dry. The mixture should still be moist. Set aside to cool slightly.
b0db6e30-22bb-4469-b422-5fbf20fc19d2 In the bowl of a stand mixer with the dough hook attached (you can also do this by hand, but a stand mixer makes it much easier), add the remaining 1 3/4 cups sweet rice flour, 1/2 cup milk, egg, granulated sugar, baking powder, butter and vanilla. Add the cooled, cooked rice flour mixture.
b0db6e30-22bb-4469-b422-5fbf20fc19d2 Knead the dough on low speed until the dough comes together. Increase the speed to medium and knead until the mixture is completely smooth and mixed, about 3 to 5 minutes. The dough will be sticky.
b0db6e30-22bb-4469-b422-5fbf20fc19d2 Line a baking sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
b0db6e30-22bb-4469-b422-5fbf20fc19d2 Sprinkle a clean surface with rice flour and scrape the dough out onto the floured surface. Sprinkle the dough with enough flour to prevent it from sticking. Roll the dough out until is it 1/2 inch thick. Cut out as many doughnuts as you can, using a 3-inch biscuit cutter for the doughnuts and a 1-inch biscuit cutter for the doughnut holes. Place the doughnuts on the prepared baking sheet as you work. Gather any scraps of dough back into a ball and roll the dough out. Cut as many doughnuts as you can and repeat the process, you should get around 10 doughnuts.
b0db6e30-22bb-4469-b422-5fbf20fc19d2 In a heavy-bottomed pot, heat 3 to 4 inches of oil to 330 degrees F. Do not let the oil go over 350 degrees F – or the doughnut will burn before the insides are fully cooked. Fry the doughnuts in batches for 2 to 3 minutes per side. Drain onto a paper towel lined baking tray. Repeat until all the doughnuts have been fried. Allow to cool slightly before glazing.
b0db6e30-22bb-4469-b422-5fbf20fc19d2 If dipping the doughnuts in the vanilla glaze first, do so now and let them dry on a cooling rack for 5 minutes before dipping in the chocolate glaze.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 LINE a 13x9-inch pan (dark pan not recommended) with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 LET cookie dough stand at room temperature 10 minutes to soften.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 BREAK up cookie dough in a large bowl.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 STIR in 3/4 cup of the hazelnut spread until blended.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 PRESS dough evenly in bottom of pan.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 BAKE 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool 30 minutes.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 BEAT cream cheese and egg white with electric mixer in a large bowl on medium speed until smooth. Add condensed milk, 3 cups coconut and vanilla; beat until well blended. Pour over crust.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 BAKE 35 to 40 minutes or until light golden brown and set. Cool completely, about 1 hour.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 HEAT remaining 1/2 cup hazelnut spread and butter in a 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
20f9b9cd-ca45-41d0-8476-7e99b99e5322 SPREAD over cooled bars; sprinkle with toasted coconut. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until topping is set. For bars, cut into 6 rows by 4 rows. Store covered in refrigerator.
e284892c-0735-403a-99ad-de873bd38710 Preheat oven to 350°F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
e284892c-0735-403a-99ad-de873bd38710 In a medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt; set aside.
e284892c-0735-403a-99ad-de873bd38710 In a large bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add granulated sugar and brown sugar and beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Beat in milk, vanilla, and peppermint extract until combined. Gradually beat in as much of the flour mixture as you can with the mixer. Using a wooden spoon, stir in any remaining flour mixture.
