e284892c-0735-403a-99ad-de873bd38710 Using a 1 tablespoon scoop, drop batter 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets. Bake about 15 minutes, or until cookies look dry and edges are set. Transfer cookies on parchment to a wire rack; cool completely.
e284892c-0735-403a-99ad-de873bd38710 In a small microwave-safe bowl, combine semisweet or milk chocolate squares and shortening. Microwave on high for 1 to 1-1/2 minutes, or until melted and smooth, stirring every 30 seconds. Dip one end of each cookie into the chocolate mixture. Let cookies stand on a sheet of parchment paper until the chocolate is set.
ac8a7a5e-dd76-4d4e-a183-461520d27d42 PREHEAT the oven to 400°
ac8a7a5e-dd76-4d4e-a183-461520d27d42 ADD 1 tablespoon of flour to a Reynolds® Oven Bag and shake. Place the bag in a 13x9x2 inch casserole dish
ac8a7a5e-dd76-4d4e-a183-461520d27d42 MIX together the cumin, chili powder, oregano, red pepper flakes and Kosher salt in a large bowl.
ac8a7a5e-dd76-4d4e-a183-461520d27d42 ADD the chicken breasts, melted butter, and lime slices to the bowl with the spices and herbs and mix thoroughly until the chicken breasts are completely covered and add them into the Reynolds® Oven Bag.
ac8a7a5e-dd76-4d4e-a183-461520d27d42 CLOSE the bag and seal it with the provided tie.
ac8a7a5e-dd76-4d4e-a183-461520d27d42 CUT 6 half inch slits in the top of the bag and tuck all of the ends into the pan and bake for 30-35 minutes on 400° or until the chicken is browned and has reached an internal temperature of 160°.
ac8a7a5e-dd76-4d4e-a183-461520d27d42 REMOVE the chicken from the bag, drain any excess liquid from the bag, and garnish with cilantro leaves.
14c82b22-53d4-4786-b27f-b9d09d4818a8 Reserve 20 almonds; set aside. Chop remaining almonds. In medium bowl, stir chopped almonds, coconut and milk until well blended. Refrigerate mixture 25 minutes for easier handling. Let cookie dough stand at room temperature for 10 minutes to soften.
14c82b22-53d4-4786-b27f-b9d09d4818a8 Meanwhile, heat oven to 350°F. In large bowl, knead cookie dough and cocoa with hands until well blended. Cover with plastic wrap; set aside.
14c82b22-53d4-4786-b27f-b9d09d4818a8 For each cookie, press 1 rounded tablespoon dough into 3-inch round. Place 1 tablespoon coconut mixture on center of each round. Wrap dough around filling, pressing edges to seal; shape into a ball. Place balls 3 inches apart on cookie sheets lined with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Press each ball with fingers into 2 1/2-inch round. Press 1 whole almond on each cookie.
14c82b22-53d4-4786-b27f-b9d09d4818a8 Bake 9 to 12 minutes or until puffed and edges are set. Immediately remove from cookie sheet to cooling rack. Cool completely, about 30 minutes.
14c82b22-53d4-4786-b27f-b9d09d4818a8 In small microwavable bowl, microwave chocolate chips uncovered on High 10 to 20 seconds, stirring every 10 seconds, until smooth. Place in resealable food-storage plastic bag; cut small tip from corner of bag. Drizzle chocolate over cookies. Before storing, let cookies stand at room temperature until chocolate is set. Store in airtight container.
d5f1d18b-125a-44ae-8e91-c75efe42ef34 Rinse shrimp in cold water and pat dry with paper towels.
d5f1d18b-125a-44ae-8e91-c75efe42ef34 Set up 3 shallow bowls. In the first, stir together 1/4 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt. In the second, add eggs and lightly beat with a fork. In the third, combine 1 1/2 cups coconut flakes and 1/2 cup panko bread crumbs.
d5f1d18b-125a-44ae-8e91-c75efe42ef34 Dredge shrimp in flour, dip in beaten egg and then finally dip in coconut crumb mixture using your hands to press the mixture onto the shrimp. Transfer to a Reynolds® Parchment Paper lined baking sheet and repeat with remaining shrimp. Once all of the shrimp are breaded, sauté right away.
d5f1d18b-125a-44ae-8e91-c75efe42ef34 Place a large non-stick pan over medium heat and add enough oil to generously cover the bottom. Once oil is hot, add shrimp and sauté 2 to 3 minutes, flip and sauté another 2 minutes until golden brown on both sides and shrimp is firm and pink. Cook in batches and don’t overcrowd the pan.
d5f1d18b-125a-44ae-8e91-c75efe42ef34 Stir together the sweet chili sauce and apricot preserves and serve with coconut shrimp.
7072bc64-005a-41c6-96ba-53bbcd7df037 PREHEAT oven to 400ºF. Place Reynolds Ktichens™ Oven Bag, Large Size in a 13x9x2-inch pan. Add flour, salt and pepper to bag. Gently squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
7072bc64-005a-41c6-96ba-53bbcd7df037 ADD onion, mushrooms, rice and butter to oven bag. Turn bag several time to mix ingredients. Arrange ingredients in even layer in bag. Fold down bag opening two times to hold it open; set aside.
7072bc64-005a-41c6-96ba-53bbcd7df037 MICROWAVE water and chicken broth in a medium microwave-safe bowl or measuring cup for about 3 minutes on high power until liquid is very hot. Carefully pour or ladle liquid over ingredients in bag. Carefully unfold bag opening.
7072bc64-005a-41c6-96ba-53bbcd7df037 CLOSE bag at gathers with nylon tie. Cut six ½ inch slits in top near tie.
7072bc64-005a-41c6-96ba-53bbcd7df037 BAKE 25 to 30 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed. Let stand 5 minutes. Carefully cut top of bag open. Spoon rice mixture into a large serving bowl. Stir in remaining tablespoon of butter and shredded cheese. Stir in up to cup additional hot water, if needed to make mixture creamy. Add additional salt and pepper and garnish with parsley, if desired.
acf39b8d-ba68-45de-86e3-997b6d899ea4 PLACE steak in a large resealable plastic bag. Add lime juice, vegetable oil, chili powder, salt, and cayenne pepper to the steak in bag. Seal bag; turn to coat steak.
acf39b8d-ba68-45de-86e3-997b6d899ea4 MARINATE in the refrigerator 30 minutes to 1 hour.
acf39b8d-ba68-45de-86e3-997b6d899ea4 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Drain meat; discard marinade. Center meat on a sheet (12x18 inches) of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Center sweet peppers, onion, and garlic on another sheet (12x18 inches) of heavy duty aluminum foil. Repeat steps above to make another foil packet.
acf39b8d-ba68-45de-86e3-997b6d899ea4 WRAP tortillas tightly in heavy duty aluminum foil.
acf39b8d-ba68-45de-86e3-997b6d899ea4 BAKE meat and vegetable foil packets 30 to 35 minutes or until meat is desired doneness (145°F for medium rare) and vegetables are tender, adding tortillas to the oven for the last 10 minutes of baking or until heated through.
acf39b8d-ba68-45de-86e3-997b6d899ea4 OPEN packets carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape; then open top of foil packet. Thinly slice the meat.
acf39b8d-ba68-45de-86e3-997b6d899ea4 FILL warm tortillas with meat and pepper mixture to serve. If desired, top with guacamole, salsa, and/or sour cream.
a447091b-5a49-4c71-9566-621612482478 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 2-quart square baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Pan Lining Paper, parchment side up.
a447091b-5a49-4c71-9566-621612482478 MELT cream cheese over medium heat in a large skillet. Add garlic and whisk until smooth. Whisk in the milk slowly; then add the 1 cup Parmesan cheese. Continue to cook and stir about 5 minutes or until sauce thickens slightly.
a447091b-5a49-4c71-9566-621612482478 ADD frozen vegetables, thyme, and black pepper to the skillet. Cook and stir just until boiling. Stir in chicken; heat through. Transfer mixture to the prepared baking dish.
a447091b-5a49-4c71-9566-621612482478 DIP biscuit dough rounds in cornmeal to coat.
a447091b-5a49-4c71-9566-621612482478 PLACE biscuit dough rounds on top of hot mixture in baking dish, cutting rounds as needed to cover mixture. Sprinkle the 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese on top.
a447091b-5a49-4c71-9566-621612482478 BAKE, uncovered, 25 to 28 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and crust is golden.
a447091b-5a49-4c71-9566-621612482478 LET stand 15 minutes before serving.
a601e5d9-e662-4901-a80c-9024f5cd1bf6 DICE peaches into 1/2-inch pieces
a601e5d9-e662-4901-a80c-9024f5cd1bf6 PREHEAT oven to 400F.
a601e5d9-e662-4901-a80c-9024f5cd1bf6 COMBINE the peaches, brown sugar, granulated sugar and all-purpose flour together untll the peaches are well-coated
a601e5d9-e662-4901-a80c-9024f5cd1bf6 ADD lemon juice, lemon zest and basil. Gently stir.
a601e5d9-e662-4901-a80c-9024f5cd1bf6 SPOON filling into a 9-inch x 13-inch Reynolds® Bakeware Non-Stick Pan
a601e5d9-e662-4901-a80c-9024f5cd1bf6 ROLL out refrigerated pie crust dough onto a large cutting board. Using a sharp knife or a pastry cutter, cut 1/2-inch to 3/4-inch strips on one round. Place half of the strips 1 1/2 to 2-inches apart. Weave remaining strips over and under the first strips to make a lattice. Stretch the dough slightly for lengthwise strips making any necessary repairs with leftover pastry pieces. Repeat until the cobbler is covered with the lattice pattern.
a601e5d9-e662-4901-a80c-9024f5cd1bf6 BRUSH beaten egg onto the lattice with a pastry brush.
a601e5d9-e662-4901-a80c-9024f5cd1bf6 BAKE for 30 to 35 minutes or until the lattice is golden brown.
6252778a-40f4-4e70-bd67-cf2c5605c7dd PREHEAT oven to 375°F (or to 350°F if using dark or nonstick cookie sheet). Place 12 Reynolds® Extra Large Foil Baking Cups on cookie sheet.
6252778a-40f4-4e70-bd67-cf2c5605c7dd COMBINE topping ingredients in small bowl until crumbly; set aside.
6252778a-40f4-4e70-bd67-cf2c5605c7dd COMBINE flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl. Combine eggs, milk, butter and vanilla in medium bowl; stir into flour mixture just until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in blueberries. Spoon 1/3 cup batter into each baking cup; sprinkle topping evenly over batter.
6252778a-40f4-4e70-bd67-cf2c5605c7dd BAKE to minutes until lightly browned and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
2c808840-4927-4efb-ad89-794ff2a123a9 Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
2c808840-4927-4efb-ad89-794ff2a123a9 Combine flour, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl. In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Beat in egg and pumpkin until combined. Beat in as much of the flour mixture as you can with the mixer. Using a wooden spoon, stir in any remaining flour mixture.
2c808840-4927-4efb-ad89-794ff2a123a9 Drop dough by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets.
2c808840-4927-4efb-ad89-794ff2a123a9 Bake 12−15 minutes or until bottoms are light brown. Transfer the cookies on the parchment paper to a wire rack; cool completely.
2c808840-4927-4efb-ad89-794ff2a123a9 Make the filling: Beat cream cheese and butter in a large mixing bowl until smooth. Add marshmallow cream, vanilla extract and pumpkin pie spice. Beat until well combined. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until smooth.
2c808840-4927-4efb-ad89-794ff2a123a9 Spread the bottoms of half of the cookies with the filing, using about 1 tablespoon on each. Top each with one of the remaining cookies, bottom side down, to make sandwich cookies.
ba55092a-5d87-44d7-bcb3-44b195d5103e GRILL to minutes or until fish is done.
c14a0cac-646b-48a6-a912-705081937acd Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Set aside.
c14a0cac-646b-48a6-a912-705081937acd Beat butter using an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds in a large bowl. Add 1/2 cup granulated sugar, brown sugar, ginger, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and cloves. Mix until combined, scraping bowl occasionally. Beat in molasses and egg. Beat in as much of the flour as you can with the mixer. Using a wooden spoon, stir in any remaining flour.
c14a0cac-646b-48a6-a912-705081937acd Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours or until dough is easy to handle.
c14a0cac-646b-48a6-a912-705081937acd Place coarse sugar in a small bowl. Shape 1/4 cup dough into a ball and roll ball in sugar, if desired. Place balls 3 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets.
c14a0cac-646b-48a6-a912-705081937acd Bake one sheet at a time for 15 to 18 minutes or until tops are crackled and edges are firm. Cool 2 minutes on the cookie sheets. Transfer the cookies on the parchment paper to a wire rack; cool completely.
7a5976f7-31e3-4de5-a4b1-6d3b6c1de8e1 PREHEAT oven to 400F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch pan.
7a5976f7-31e3-4de5-a4b1-6d3b6c1de8e1 ADD tomatoes to oven bag; squeeze bag to break open tomatoes
7a5976f7-31e3-4de5-a4b1-6d3b6c1de8e1 ADD chicken, artichokes, feta, olives, flour and Greek seasoning to bag. Turn bag several times to mix ingredients; arrange ingredients in an even layer in bag.
7a5976f7-31e3-4de5-a4b1-6d3b6c1de8e1 CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag into pan.
7a5976f7-31e3-4de5-a4b1-6d3b6c1de8e1 BAKE 18 to 20 minutes, until chicken reads 170F on meat thermometer. Carefully cut open bag; stir. Add Basil Chiffonade to garnish servings.
28f04945-df47-4c1d-9930-55ceec836b63 Whisk together all sauce ingredients in a medium sauce pan. Bring to a boil, reduce to simmer and cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from heat and allow to cool to room temperature. Reserve 1/2 cup of sauce and pour remaining sauce in a large sealable bag. Add chicken breasts to bag. Seal and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
28f04945-df47-4c1d-9930-55ceec836b63 Preheat grill to medium heat and arrange four 12x12-inch pieces of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil on the grill. Use tongs to transfer one chicken breast to each foil square. Discard marinade.
28f04945-df47-4c1d-9930-55ceec836b63 Brush each chicken breast with some of the remaining BBQ sauce. Top with sliced mushrooms and onions. Fold foil around each chicken breast to enclose the chicken and veggies. Allow to cook over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear or meat thermometer reads 170 degrees F.
28f04945-df47-4c1d-9930-55ceec836b63 Unwrap foil packets and place two slices of provolone cheese over the top of each chicken breast so that the cheese is lying on top of the mushrooms and onions. Allow to cook uncovered 2 to 3 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Garnish with fresh parsley or cilantro and serve.
8fdf3dc9-5a75-40d1-a269-8e20c4a13efe PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
8fdf3dc9-5a75-40d1-a269-8e20c4a13efe ADD the butter and chocolate chips to a medium sized metal bowl and put it over a pot of simmering water to create a double boiler. Continually stir with a rubber spatula.
8fdf3dc9-5a75-40d1-a269-8e20c4a13efe WHISK together in a separate large bowl the eggs, brown sugar, sugar, flour, cocoa powder, vanilla and baking powder.
8fdf3dc9-5a75-40d1-a269-8e20c4a13efe COOL the chocolate at room temperature for 10 minutes and then fold it into the eggs and sugar mixture until completely combined.
8fdf3dc9-5a75-40d1-a269-8e20c4a13efe POUR the batter into a Reynolds® Bakeware 8x8 Pan and bake in the oven on 350° for 35 minutes or until the brownies begin to pull away from the outside of the pan.
8fdf3dc9-5a75-40d1-a269-8e20c4a13efe ADD the chopped candy canes to the top of the brownies with 10 minutes left in the cooking process.
8fdf3dc9-5a75-40d1-a269-8e20c4a13efe COOL before forming.
8fdf3dc9-5a75-40d1-a269-8e20c4a13efe REMOVE the brownies from the pan and cut holiday shapes using holiday shaped cookie cutters.
8fdf3dc9-5a75-40d1-a269-8e20c4a13efe DECORATE with icings and assorted colored chocolate candies.
36d2a07b-bf82-4675-9a9f-0dcf9e4c8290 COMBINE flour, ginger, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in large bowl. In another large bowl, with an electric mixer at low speed, beat margarine, brown sugar and molasses until light and fluffy. Add in egg and vanilla; beat until well mixed. Gradually stir in flour mixture until well blended.
36d2a07b-bf82-4675-9a9f-0dcf9e4c8290 DIVIDE dough in half; wrap in Reynolds® Plastic Wrap. Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
36d2a07b-bf82-4675-9a9f-0dcf9e4c8290 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside. Working with one-fourth of dough at a time, roll out dough –inch thick between two sheets of parchment paper. Using a 5-inch gingerbread man cookie cutter cut out cookies; place on parchment-lined cookie sheet. Bake until edges begin to brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
36d2a07b-bf82-4675-9a9f-0dcf9e4c8290 CUT fruit roll-up candy into fashionable outfits. Attach outfits to gingerbread men with decorators icing. Attach mini candies with decorators icing for eyes, nose, mouth and buttons.
36d2a07b-bf82-4675-9a9f-0dcf9e4c8290 WRAP cookies individually in color plastic wrap and tie with a ribbon at the top of each cookie. Place cookies in a basket lined with color plastic wrap. Add a holiday mug to the basket, if desired.
f5350b87-49b6-42d4-8158-a0621e878f8e Preheat oven to 400°F. In a small bowl, combine garlic, paprika, cumin, brown sugar, salt, and pepper. Sprinkle over the ribs.
f5350b87-49b6-42d4-8158-a0621e878f8e Line a roasting pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Add 1/3 cup water to the pan. Place ribs in the pan and cover tightly with foil. Cover and bake in the preheated oven for 2 to 2-1/2 hours for flanken-cut ribs or 2-1/2 to 3 hours for English-cut ribs, or until tender and the meat is falling off the bone.
f5350b87-49b6-42d4-8158-a0621e878f8e For the Honey-Sriracha Sauce, In a small bowl combine honey, Sriracha sauce, and lime juice. Or, substitute your favorite barbecue sauce.
f5350b87-49b6-42d4-8158-a0621e878f8e Remove ribs from oven and increase oven temperature to 425°F. Transfer ribs to two foil-lined 15x10x1-inch baking pans, arranging ribs in a single layer. Brush 1 cup of the Honey-Sriracha Sauce over ribs. Return to oven for 12 to 15 minutes, or until just starting to brown.
f5350b87-49b6-42d4-8158-a0621e878f8e If desired, sprinkle with green onion to serve. Pass remaining Honey-Sriracha Sauce.
2d79585f-75d7-4124-b41f-96fd300d880d Heat oven to 350°F. Let cookie dough stand at room temperature 10 minutes to soften. Line 2 large cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
2d79585f-75d7-4124-b41f-96fd300d880d In large bowl, break up cookie dough. Add hazelnut spread, cocoa, chili powder and cinnamon. Beat with electric mixer on low speed about 2 minutes or until well blended.
2d79585f-75d7-4124-b41f-96fd300d880d Shape dough into 12 (2-inch) balls. Flatten each ball into 3-inch round. Shape 1 cookie dough round around 1 marshmallow half, covering completely. Repeat with remaining dough rounds and marshmallows. Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
2d79585f-75d7-4124-b41f-96fd300d880d Bake 10 to 13 minutes or until surface of cookie appears cracked and marshmallow shows through. Cool 5 minutes; remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks. Cool an additional 5 minutes. Serve warm. Store tightly covered.
a1609118-2c74-4915-84a4-48ae08805918 LINE a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
a1609118-2c74-4915-84a4-48ae08805918 COMBINE flour, baking powder and salt on a sheet of parchment aper; set aside. Beat sugar and butter until fluffy in large bowl, with an electric mixer. Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended. Gradually beat flour mixture into butter mixture until smooth. Divide dough in half; shape into 2 flat disks. Wrap dough in parchment paper; refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm enough to roll.
a1609118-2c74-4915-84a4-48ae08805918 TO BAKE, preheat oven to 375°F.
a1609118-2c74-4915-84a4-48ae08805918 ROLL OUT dough 1/8-inch thick between 2 lightly floured sheets of parchment paper. Cut dough with 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter. Cut centers out of half of cookies with a 1-inch diameter cookie cutter. Place cookies 1-inch apart on parchment-lined cookie sheet.
a1609118-2c74-4915-84a4-48ae08805918 BAKE 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are just beginning to brown on edges. Cool. Spread 1/2 to 1 teaspoon of jam over whole cookies. Top with remaining cut-out cookies, sandwich style.
d26febad-a215-4da1-af40-65fe6fc90b28 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
d26febad-a215-4da1-af40-65fe6fc90b28 Beat together butter and sugar with an electric mixer until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes, stopping once or twice to scrape down the sides of bowl with a rubber spatula. Beat in egg yolks and vanilla extract. Reduce mixer speed and add flour and salt and mix until just incorporated.
d26febad-a215-4da1-af40-65fe6fc90b28 Form dough into 1-inch balls and arrange on prepared baking sheet. Using your thumb, flatten balls slightly to make an indentation in the center of each cookie. Bake cookies for 8–10 minutes or until bottoms are just golden.
d26febad-a215-4da1-af40-65fe6fc90b28 Remove baking sheet from oven. Fill each indentation with a heaping 1/2 teaspoon of jam. Bake for an additional 5 to 6 minutes, or until the edges of cookies are lightly golden. Transfer cookies to wire racks to cool.
5fedf0b2-5a05-4cd6-8434-d9a89132bb1b Preheat the grill to medium.
5fedf0b2-5a05-4cd6-8434-d9a89132bb1b Form two 2-foot pieces of Reynolds® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil into a large bowl-like shape with the sides about 2 inches tall and add it to the grill on medium heat.
5fedf0b2-5a05-4cd6-8434-d9a89132bb1b Add the cutup point from the brisket to the foil bowl along with the beef broth and BBQ sauce and mix until combined.
5fedf0b2-5a05-4cd6-8434-d9a89132bb1b Cook the brisket for 30 minutes on medium heat with the grill door closed or until it appears to be caramelizing and deeply browned, almost as if it were burnt.
5fedf0b2-5a05-4cd6-8434-d9a89132bb1b Serve the BBQ burnt ends on hamburger buns.
c6a873f2-002f-4f18-97d8-8e24e2e43238 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place 24 Reynolds® Pastels Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
c6a873f2-002f-4f18-97d8-8e24e2e43238 PREPARE cake mix following package directions, for 24 cupcakes, adding lemon extract to the batter. Spoon cake batter into baking cups.
c6a873f2-002f-4f18-97d8-8e24e2e43238 BAKE 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.
c6a873f2-002f-4f18-97d8-8e24e2e43238 BEAT cream cheese, lime juice and lime peel with an electric mixer on medium speed. Gradually blend in sugar until mixture is smooth. Frost cupcakes and top with a jelly bean. Serve immediately or store in the refrigerator.
9aa326a4-549e-4076-9fed-6aac4cef5a6c PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag, Large Size in 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
9aa326a4-549e-4076-9fed-6aac4cef5a6c ADD flour, chicken broth, Worcestershire sauce and mustard to oven bag; squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
9aa326a4-549e-4076-9fed-6aac4cef5a6c ADD meatballs, onion, and mushrooms. Turn bag several times to mix. Arrange ingredients in an even layer in pan.
9aa326a4-549e-4076-9fed-6aac4cef5a6c CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six half-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
9aa326a4-549e-4076-9fed-6aac4cef5a6c BAKE 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through and sauce has thickened. Carefully cut open bag.
9aa326a4-549e-4076-9fed-6aac4cef5a6c SPOON meatballs and sauce into large serving bowl. Slowly stir in sour cream, dill, salt and pepper. Serve over cooked egg noodles. Garnish if desired.
226efa8b-56e3-4cc7-a539-028802b2b229 PREHEAT oven to 425°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
226efa8b-56e3-4cc7-a539-028802b2b229 MIX ground beef, 1 cup salsa, tortilla chips, onion, egg and spices together in a large bowl until well blended.
226efa8b-56e3-4cc7-a539-028802b2b229 SPOON mixture in center of foil-lined pan; shape into a 12x6-inch loaf.
226efa8b-56e3-4cc7-a539-028802b2b229 BAKE 50 to 55 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 160°F. Top with remaining salsa; serve immediately.
92029a45-e118-452a-bdf4-c0889006836e In a food processor, process 3/4 cup of the toasted walnuts until very finely ground but still dry. Set ground walnuts and remaining 3/4 cup finely chopped walnuts aside.
92029a45-e118-452a-bdf4-c0889006836e In a large bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add granulated sugar and beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Beat in milk, vanilla, 1 1/2 teaspoons of the cinnamon, lemon zest, and salt until combined. Beat in as much of the flour with the mixer as you can. Stir in any remaining flour, the ground walnuts, and the finely chopped walnuts. Wrap in Reynolds® Parchment Paper and place in a resealable bag. Chill for 1 to 2 hours, or until dough is easy to handle.
92029a45-e118-452a-bdf4-c0889006836e Preheat oven to 325°F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Shape dough into 2-teaspoon-size balls. Place 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets. Bake about 18 minutes, or until bottoms are light brown. Cool on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
92029a45-e118-452a-bdf4-c0889006836e In a small bowl, combine powdered sugar and remaining 3/4 teaspoon of cinnamon. Toss cookies in the powdered sugar mixture, then cool completely on a wire rack.
9fefb690-fe3c-4b3d-a52c-1164b4902060 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Place 24 Reynolds® StayBrite® or Foil Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
9fefb690-fe3c-4b3d-a52c-1164b4902060 MIX ground beef, tortilla chips, salsa, onion, eggs, chili powder and garlic salt together in a large bowl until well blended.
9fefb690-fe3c-4b3d-a52c-1164b4902060 Spoon about 1/3 meat mixture into each baking cup.
9fefb690-fe3c-4b3d-a52c-1164b4902060 BAKE 25 to 30 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 160°F. Top each with shredded cheese. Serve immediately, with additional salsa, sour cream and chips, if desired.
35238bb7-9e0f-4b38-ad38-ab4fc4cf0228 PREHEAT oven to 425?F. Place 12 Reynolds® StayBrite™ Baking Cups in a muffin pan. Lightly spray each baking cup with cooking spray; set aside.
35238bb7-9e0f-4b38-ad38-ab4fc4cf0228 COMBINE potatoes, 1/3 cup cheese, onion and 1 tablespoon melted butter in medium bowl. Spoon a heaping tablespoon of mixture into each baking cup.
35238bb7-9e0f-4b38-ad38-ab4fc4cf0228 BAKE 15 minutes.
35238bb7-9e0f-4b38-ad38-ab4fc4cf0228 MIX remaining cheese, butter, sausage, eggs, milk, bell pepper and garlic salt in bowl. Spoon about 2 tablespoons mixture into each baking cup over potatoes.
35238bb7-9e0f-4b38-ad38-ab4fc4cf0228 BAKE an additional 15 minutes or until a inserted knife comes out clean.
e0d78a84-e227-4f54-abf6-b6fea917b8c5 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
e0d78a84-e227-4f54-abf6-b6fea917b8c5 ADD the butter and semi-sweet chocolate chips to a medium sized metal bowl and put it over a pot of simmering water to create a double boiler. Continually stir with a rubber spatula.
e0d78a84-e227-4f54-abf6-b6fea917b8c5 WHISK together in a separate large bowl the eggs, brown sugar, sugar, flour, cocoa powder, vanilla and baking powder.
e0d78a84-e227-4f54-abf6-b6fea917b8c5 COOL the chocolate at room temperature for 10 minutes and then fold it into the eggs and sugar mixture until completely combined. Fold in the mint chocolate chips.
e0d78a84-e227-4f54-abf6-b6fea917b8c5 POUR the batter into a Reynolds® Bakeware 8x8 Pan and bake in the oven on 350° for 35 minutes or until the brownies begin to pull away from the outside of the pan.
e0d78a84-e227-4f54-abf6-b6fea917b8c5 REMOVE the pan from the oven and garnish with chopped Andes Mints and Green Mint M&M’s.
e0d78a84-e227-4f54-abf6-b6fea917b8c5 COOL before serving.
38cc9c7d-2b10-41c2-9256-1815e921e764 Heat oven to 375°F. Line a 13x9-inch pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. In bottom of pan, spread nuts. Cut cookie dough into 1/2-inch slices; place over nuts in pan. With floured fingers, press dough evenly to form crust. Sprinkle toffee bits over crust; press in lightly.
38cc9c7d-2b10-41c2-9256-1815e921e764 Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 30 minutes.
38cc9c7d-2b10-41c2-9256-1815e921e764 In large microwavable bowl, place chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Microwave on High 1 minute 30 seconds to 2 minutes or until melted, stirring every 30 seconds until smooth. Stir in peanut butter until well blended. Fold in pretzels. Spread mixture evenly over baked crust.
38cc9c7d-2b10-41c2-9256-1815e921e764 In small microwavable bowl, place candy coating. Microwave on High 30 to 60 seconds or until melted, stirring every 15 seconds until smooth. Drizzle over bars. Refrigerate until chocolate is set, about 30 minutes. For bars, cut into 6 rows by 6 rows.
4e05cb7a-c134-46b9-99de-f0208111dc4b PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
4e05cb7a-c134-46b9-99de-f0208111dc4b BEAT the butter and sugar in a large bowl using an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until light and fluffy. Add the egg, orange peel, lemon peel, and vanilla and beat until well blended.
4e05cb7a-c134-46b9-99de-f0208111dc4b COMBINE the flour, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl. Add half of flour mixture to the butter mixture, beating until just combined. Add the milk. Beat about 10 seconds. Beat in the remaining flour mixture until just combined.
4e05cb7a-c134-46b9-99de-f0208111dc4b DROP tablespoon-size mounds of dough on prepared cookie sheets.
4e05cb7a-c134-46b9-99de-f0208111dc4b BAKE 8 to 10 minutes or until set and the bottoms are browned. Transfer the cookies on the parchment paper to a wire rack; cool completely.
4e05cb7a-c134-46b9-99de-f0208111dc4b DRIZZLE with Citrus Glaze to serve.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba PREHEAT the oven to 300°.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba CREAM together the butter and sugar and add 1 egg yolk at a time until combined.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba ADD in the sour cream, orange zest, and orange juice until combined.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba STOP the mixer and scrape the bowl.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba MIX together the flour, baking soda, and salt until combined and mix it into the creamed butter mixture until combined.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba POUR the batter into a large bowl and set aside.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba WHIP the egg whites until stiff peaks are formed and fold into the bowl with the batter until combined.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba POUR the mixture into a Reynolds® Bakeware 8x8 pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes on 300°.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba COOL on a cooling rack and then cut into 1” inch squares.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba SKEWER the pound cake squares along with fresh berries and marshmallows.
bf3a0242-2f94-4b81-84fa-8482550287ba DRIZZLE the melted chocolate over the pound cake and fruit skewers.
983bb949-b6c3-40c8-abf6-1dfeb652065a Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Toss the brussels sprouts with pancetta, olive oil, salt and 1 tablespoon of the brown sugar. Place in a casserole pan and cover the pan with a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
983bb949-b6c3-40c8-abf6-1dfeb652065a Roast for 30 minutes, then remove the foil and continue roasting until the brussels sprouts are lightly browned around the edges, about 10 to 15 minutes more. Remove from oven and set aside.
983bb949-b6c3-40c8-abf6-1dfeb652065a Melt the butter and remaining tablespoon brown sugar in a medium-sized frying pan over medium heat, stirring every few minutes. Once the sugar has melted, add the pecans and stir to coat. Let them sit for a few minutes until they smell toasty, then stir. Continue to stir every few minutes until most of the pecans are lightly browned and very aromatic.
983bb949-b6c3-40c8-abf6-1dfeb652065a Remove the pan from the heat and empty the mixture onto a large baking sheet lined with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Smooth the pecans so they are in one layer, then sprinkle with salt. Place the pan in the freezer for 10 minutes to allow the nuts to harden, then remove the pan and separate the pecans by hand.
983bb949-b6c3-40c8-abf6-1dfeb652065a Toss the roasted brussels sprouts with caramelized pecans before serving.
941b3d52-6eaf-4f42-9c0f-05425745c4f7 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
941b3d52-6eaf-4f42-9c0f-05425745c4f7 ADD the butter and chocolate chips to a medium sized metal bowl and put it over a pot of simmering water to create a double boiler. Continually stir with a rubber spatula.
941b3d52-6eaf-4f42-9c0f-05425745c4f7 WHISK together in a separate large bowl the eggs, brown sugar, sugar, flour, cocoa powder, vanilla and baking powder.
941b3d52-6eaf-4f42-9c0f-05425745c4f7 COOL the chocolate at room temperature for 10 minutes and then fold it into the eggs and sugar mixture until completely combined.
941b3d52-6eaf-4f42-9c0f-05425745c4f7 POUR the batter into a Reynolds® Bakeware 8x8 Pan and bake in the oven on 350° for 35 minutes or until the brownies begin to pull away from the outside of the pan.
941b3d52-6eaf-4f42-9c0f-05425745c4f7 ADD the chopped candy canes to the top of the brownies with 10 minutes left in the cooking process.
941b3d52-6eaf-4f42-9c0f-05425745c4f7 COOL before serving.
624636b4-086e-4a86-a5a8-cb65d2e524a7 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Spread the pecans on the foil-lined sheet and toast in the oven for 7–10 minutes. Remove and allow to cool completely. When cooled, give the pecans a rough chop and return to the foil-lined baking sheet.
624636b4-086e-4a86-a5a8-cb65d2e524a7 In a stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, mix the cream cheese, garlic, pickle, cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack, pimentos, black pepper, hot sauce and pinch of cayenne pepper. Turn the mixer to medium speed and mix for about a minute. Transfer to a small bowl, cover with plastic wrap and chill for at least 2 hours or up to 3 days.
624636b4-086e-4a86-a5a8-cb65d2e524a7 Form chilled mixture into a ball, and smooth out by hand. Roll the ball in the toasted chopped pecans. Keep in the fridge until you’re ready to serve.
624636b4-086e-4a86-a5a8-cb65d2e524a7 Serve on a plate or board with an array of crackers or veggies like carrots, celery or radishes.
d09342e9-e9d6-4730-b45a-ffb3ee487650 Place pork tenderloin on the center of piece of aluminum foil and season with salt and pepper.
d09342e9-e9d6-4730-b45a-ffb3ee487650 Top with vegetables, garlic salt, cumin and drizzle of olive oil.
d09342e9-e9d6-4730-b45a-ffb3ee487650 Bring the two sides of the foil up to meet at the center, folding down twice. Then fold the two open ends twice to completely enclose food; creating a foil packet.
d09342e9-e9d6-4730-b45a-ffb3ee487650 With long tongs, place packet on the grill set at high and close the lid.
d09342e9-e9d6-4730-b45a-ffb3ee487650 Cook for 30-35 minutes, or until pork is cooked through and juices run clear.
0765183c-47c7-437c-b231-f2be30a0ae99 Preheat oven to 375°F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. In a large bowl, combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat pastry flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, the baking soda, ginger, salt, and nutmeg. Set aside.
0765183c-47c7-437c-b231-f2be30a0ae99 In a very large bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds, or until light and fluffy. Add brown sugar and molasses. Beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Add the egg and beat until combined. Using a wooden spoon, stir in flour mixture. Divide dough in half.
0765183c-47c7-437c-b231-f2be30a0ae99 Line a workspace with parchment paper and sprinkle with flour. Using a floured rolling pin, roll each portion of dough to 1/4-inch thickness on the parchment paper. Cut out shapes with a lightly floured 2- to 3-inch pumpkin-shape cutter, rerolling scraps as needed. Place cutouts 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets.
0765183c-47c7-437c-b231-f2be30a0ae99 Bake 7 to 8 minutes, or until edges are just firm. Cool on cookie sheets set on wire racks for 1 minute. Transfer cookies on parchment to wire racks and cool completely.
0765183c-47c7-437c-b231-f2be30a0ae99 Frost cookies with Pumpkin Frosting. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
ff8dd295-18c5-4bde-bf27-2fdbf9ac2b01 PREHEAT oven to 400° F.
ff8dd295-18c5-4bde-bf27-2fdbf9ac2b01 PLACE flatbread on a cookie sheet lined with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
ff8dd295-18c5-4bde-bf27-2fdbf9ac2b01 DRIZZLE olive oil over the flatbread.
ff8dd295-18c5-4bde-bf27-2fdbf9ac2b01 ADD a few slices of tomatoes to each flatbread.
ff8dd295-18c5-4bde-bf27-2fdbf9ac2b01 SPRINKLE equal amounts of mozzarella on top of the tomatoes.
ff8dd295-18c5-4bde-bf27-2fdbf9ac2b01 PLACE the basil leaves on top of the mozzarella.
ff8dd295-18c5-4bde-bf27-2fdbf9ac2b01 SPRINKLE about a tablespoon of Parmesan cheese over the top of each flatbread. Don’t worry about getting the cheese on the cookie sheet as it’s lined with the foil. The cheese will make a mess but to clean up all you need to do is throw away the foil.
ff8dd295-18c5-4bde-bf27-2fdbf9ac2b01 PLACE the cookie sheet into the oven. Bake for 10-12 minutes. When done the cheese should be melted and is beginning to brown.
ff8dd295-18c5-4bde-bf27-2fdbf9ac2b01 REMOVE the pizzas from the pan and transfer to a plate. Serve with additional basil.
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 Line baking tin with <a href="/products/baking-cups/staybrite/" title="stay brite baking cups reynolds">Reynolds StayBrite® baking cups</a>
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 Prepare red velvet cake batter as directed on back of box and add red food coloring.
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 Pour red velvet cake batter ¼ full in the <a href="/products/baking-cups/staybrite/" title="stay brite baking cups reynolds">baking cups</a> and set aside.
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 To make the cream cheese mixture - in a bowl use a hand mixer on medium to blend the cream cheese, granulated sugar, vanilla extract and eggs until smooth.
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 Place about 2 tbsp. of the cream cheese mixture in the center of the red velvet cake batter in the baking cups.
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 With a toothpick, gently swirl the cream cheese mixture into the red velvet batter.
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 Place cupcakes in the oven and cook for 18-22 minutes. When done, remove from oven and allow to completely cool inside baking tin
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 While the cupcakes are baking, make the blueberry topping by adding the drained blueberries, granulated sugar and unsalted butter to a medium saucepan. Over high heat, stir and allow to come to a boil, once at a boil turn heat to low and allow to simmer for 5 minutes. Then remove from heat and set aside to cool.
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 Once cupcakes and blueberry topping are cooled, add blueberry topping to the cupcakes and refrigerate for 30 minutes
0e82e503-c277-4d17-aab3-9a9ca1fe83e2 ENJOY and share the Red Velvet, Cream Cheese and Blueberry love!
6c3acdf3-30e1-4f4b-8fcb-ae311d9fd7a3 Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. Create a foil ring to support the chicken while it roasts. Cut a 4-foot piece of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Starting with a long end of your foil sheet, fold a 1.5-inch section over itself repeatedly to create a thick strip. Take the strip and form a ring that is slightly smaller than the size of the chicken. Line a roasting pan with foil. Place the ring inside the roasting pan. Set aside.
6c3acdf3-30e1-4f4b-8fcb-ae311d9fd7a3 Mix butter with garlic, lemon zest and thyme. By hand, carefully loosen the skin all the way around the chicken. Spread the butter between the meat and the skin. Cut lemon in half and put in cavity of chicken. Truss the chicken.
6c3acdf3-30e1-4f4b-8fcb-ae311d9fd7a3 Spread remaining butter on the outside skin of the chicken. Salt skin well with Kosher salt.
6c3acdf3-30e1-4f4b-8fcb-ae311d9fd7a3 Place the chicken breast side down on the ring in the lined roasting pan. Roast for 45–50 minutes or until cooked through.
9be05372-cc7a-4a82-92d9-fae128dcf7ab PREHEAT the oven to 350°F.
9be05372-cc7a-4a82-92d9-fae128dcf7ab LINE a 15x10-inch rimmed cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
9be05372-cc7a-4a82-92d9-fae128dcf7ab MIX the oatmeal, walnuts, and coconut in large bowl. Spread mixture onto a parchment-lined cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
9be05372-cc7a-4a82-92d9-fae128dcf7ab LIFT mixture from pan using ends of parchment; transfer it to a large mixing bowl and sprinkle with flour. Add cranberries. Set parchment lined baking sheet aside.
9be05372-cc7a-4a82-92d9-fae128dcf7ab PLACE the butter, honey, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and vanilla in a small saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook and stir for one minute, then pour over oatmeal mixture.
9be05372-cc7a-4a82-92d9-fae128dcf7ab POUR the mixture into the parchment-lined baking sheet. Lightly press the mixture with a spatula to even it out.
9be05372-cc7a-4a82-92d9-fae128dcf7ab BAKE for 20 minutes, until light golden brown. Let cool to room temperature on cooling rack. Slide mixture from pan, using ends of parchment, onto cutting board. Cut into bars. Serve at room temperature.
0e6ba2e4-c9ab-41ab-a818-daf798483ef9 PREHEAT oven to 450°F.
0e6ba2e4-c9ab-41ab-a818-daf798483ef9 CENTER one-fourth of asparagus on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Top with salmon fillet; sprinkle with thyme and salt. Top with sun-dried tomatoes; drizzle with vinaigrette.
0e6ba2e4-c9ab-41ab-a818-daf798483ef9 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets. Place packets on a cookie sheet.
0e6ba2e4-c9ab-41ab-a818-daf798483ef9 BAKE 18 to 20 minutes or until salmon is opaque in center. If desired, sprinkle with feta cheese before serving.
023e11b2-d8a5-4c58-8fc5-44c09d3fa4d8 OPEN slow cooker liner and place it in a 5- to 6 1/2 -qt slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of the bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
023e11b2-d8a5-4c58-8fc5-44c09d3fa4d8 COOK ground beef, celery, and bell pepper in large skillet over medium-high heat until meat is evenly browned; drain off grease.
023e11b2-d8a5-4c58-8fc5-44c09d3fa4d8 PLACE cooked beef mixture and remaining ingredients in slow cooker liner. Place lid on slow cooker.
023e11b2-d8a5-4c58-8fc5-44c09d3fa4d8 COOK on LOW for 6 to 7 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours until chili is hot and bubbling.
023e11b2-d8a5-4c58-8fc5-44c09d3fa4d8 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
023e11b2-d8a5-4c58-8fc5-44c09d3fa4d8 REYNOLDS KITCHENS TIP:This recipe was developed for 5- to 6 1/2 -quart slow cookers, but it may be adjusted for smaller or larger cookers.
ff178ad6-a451-4d64-9b34-06b6b862ddaf PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds KITCHENS™ Parchment Paper; set aside.
ff178ad6-a451-4d64-9b34-06b6b862ddaf BEAT butter and sugar until fluffy in a large bowl with an electric mixer. Mix in egg and lemon extract until well blended.
ff178ad6-a451-4d64-9b34-06b6b862ddaf COMBINE flour, baking powder and salt in a separate bowl. Gradually beat flour mixture into butter mixture until smooth. Divide dough in half; shape into 2 flat disks. Wrap dough in parchment paper; refrigerate 1 hour or until firm enough to roll.
ff178ad6-a451-4d64-9b34-06b6b862ddaf ROLL out the dough 1/8-inch thick between two sheets of lightly floured parchment paper. Tear off two long sheets (at least 24 inches in length) of parchment paper and place the dough in between the two sheets. Next, bring one side of the excess paper down past the edge of your countertop and lean into it so you’re holding it all in place. Roll out the dough while it’s still between the parchment paper.
ff178ad6-a451-4d64-9b34-06b6b862ddaf CUT dough with 2-to-6-inch snowflake cookie cutters. Place cookies 1 inch apart on parchment-lined cookie sheet. The SmartGrid lines make spacing your cookies easy! Decorate with colored sprinkles.
ff178ad6-a451-4d64-9b34-06b6b862ddaf BAKE 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are just beginning to brown on edges. Cool.
ff178ad6-a451-4d64-9b34-06b6b862ddaf MIX powdered sugar and milk together in a small bowl, adding milk slowly until desired consistency is reached. Drizzle over cooled cookies.
ff178ad6-a451-4d64-9b34-06b6b862ddaf PORTION cookies into Reynolds KITCHENS™ Wax Paper Sandwich Bags to share with neighbors, take to a bake sale or as a party goodie bag.
8fa2a7a0-4ef6-4966-900a-1214957e47a1 Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Line a large baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil. Grease or spray foil to prevent sticking.
8fa2a7a0-4ef6-4966-900a-1214957e47a1 Combine cilantro, sour cream, jalapeño, mayonnaise, garlic and lime juice in the bowl of a food processor; season with salt and pepper to taste. Set aside.
8fa2a7a0-4ef6-4966-900a-1214957e47a1 Mash avocados using a potato masher. Add black beans, corn, tomato, lime juice, chili powder, cumin and salt and pepper and gently toss to combine.
8fa2a7a0-4ef6-4966-900a-1214957e47a1 Place avocado mixture in the center of each wrapper. Bring the bottom edge of the wrapper tightly over the filling, folding in the sides. Continue rolling until the top of the wrapper is reached. Using your finger, rub the edges of the wrapper with water, pressing to seal. Repeat with remaining wrappers and avocado mixture.
8fa2a7a0-4ef6-4966-900a-1214957e47a1 Place egg rolls on the prepared baking dish. Lightly coat with nonstick spray.
8fa2a7a0-4ef6-4966-900a-1214957e47a1 Place into oven and bake until golden brown and crisp, about 18 to 20 minutes.
8fa2a7a0-4ef6-4966-900a-1214957e47a1 Serve immediately with cilantro dipping sauce.
e3576e0b-29e4-402a-ac4d-4ac4fa9f0e15 PREHEAT oven to 400F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch pan. Add flour and Mexican seasoning to bag; squeeze bag to blend seasonings.
e3576e0b-29e4-402a-ac4d-4ac4fa9f0e15 ADD chicken, black beans, tomatoes, and rice to oven bag. Gently squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Arrange ingredients in even layer. Fold down bag opening two times to hold bag open.
e3576e0b-29e4-402a-ac4d-4ac4fa9f0e15 MICROWAVE chicken broth in microwave-safe bowl or measuring cup for about 2 minutes until it is very hot. Carefully pour broth over other ingredients in bag. Carefully unfold bag opening.
e3576e0b-29e4-402a-ac4d-4ac4fa9f0e15 CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
e3576e0b-29e4-402a-ac4d-4ac4fa9f0e15 BAKE 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken reads 170F on a meat thermometer and rice is done. Let stand 5 minutes. Carefully cut bag open.
e3576e0b-29e4-402a-ac4d-4ac4fa9f0e15 SPOON chicken and rice mixture onto heated tortillas. Add toppers, if desired. Turn tortilla ends in and roll around filling to eat.
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 PREHEAToven to 350F. Place Reynolds Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch pan.
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 ADD olive oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, flour, seafood seasoning and minced garlic to oven bag. Gently squeeze several times to blend.
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 ADD shrimp to oven bag; turn bag several times to coat shrimp with sauce. Arrange shrimp in an even layer.
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 MAKE Bang Bang Sauce while shrimp is marinating:
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 MIX mayonnaise, sweet chili sauce and hot chili sauce in a small bowl; set aside.
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 REMOVE shrimp from refrigerator.
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 CUT six -inch slits in top of bag. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 BAKE minutes or until shrimp turns pink and is done. Place lettuce on appetizer plates. Carefully cut bag open; spoon shrimp over lettuce. Top with crushed potato chips; drizzle with Bang Bang Sauce. Garnish with green onions, if desired.
bef3527f-06cd-4ee6-8000-6ad063eaafc4 REYNOLDS OVEN BAGS TIPS: To crush potato chips, place chips in a small resealable plastic bag; use a rolling pin or can to crush chips. We tested with Old Bay seafood seasoning, Maggi Taste of Asia Sweet Chili Sauce and Tuong Ot Sriracha Hot Chili Sauce.
21fc8854-9e9d-41d8-9b4c-d01f55b4897d PREHEAT oven to 400F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch pan. Add flour, peanut sauce and water to bag.
21fc8854-9e9d-41d8-9b4c-d01f55b4897d Gently squeeze bag to blend ingredients; set aside.
21fc8854-9e9d-41d8-9b4c-d01f55b4897d SLICE pork tenderloin 1-inch thick; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add to oven bag. Turn bag several times to coat pork with sauce. Arrange pork in even layer in oven bag. Top with snap peas and bell pepper.
21fc8854-9e9d-41d8-9b4c-d01f55b4897d CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
21fc8854-9e9d-41d8-9b4c-d01f55b4897d BAKE 12 to 14 minutes or until pork reads 145F on meat thermometer. While pork is baking, break up noodles and COOK according to package directions.
21fc8854-9e9d-41d8-9b4c-d01f55b4897d Drain cooked noodles and place in medium bowl with 1 seasoning packet, sesame oil and green onions; stir to mix well.
21fc8854-9e9d-41d8-9b4c-d01f55b4897d Carefully cut bag open. PLACE of noodles on each plate and top with pork, vegetables, and sauce. Sprinkle with peanuts and green onions. Drizzle with additional peanut sauce, if desired.
69f57730-69f5-489d-a204-598c8a2c879e Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Clean mushrooms; remove and set aside stems. Place mushroom caps, stem sides down, on the prepared baking sheet. Lightly coat the rounded side of each mushroom cap with nonstick cooking spray. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until nearly tender. Place mushrooms, stem sides down, on paper towels to drain.
69f57730-69f5-489d-a204-598c8a2c879e Increase oven temperature to 425°F. Chop enough of the reserved stems to measure 1 cup.
69f57730-69f5-489d-a204-598c8a2c879e In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Cook the chopped mushroom stems, green onion, jalapeño, and garlic in butter for 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in cornbread or polenta and 1/2 cup cheese. Spoon mixture into mushroom caps, packing tightly. Return stuffed mushrooms to the baking pan.
69f57730-69f5-489d-a204-598c8a2c879e Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until heated through and browned. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Return to the oven for 1 to 2 minutes, or until cheese is melted. Serve warm.
dc7a2a3d-7371-4522-8f31-aa113e5486d7 Heat oven to 350°F. Line a 9- or 8-inch square pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Cut cookie dough in half crosswise. With floured fingers, press half of dough evenly in bottom of pan to form crust. Bake 6 to 12 minutes or until edges are light golden brown. Cool 10 minutes.
dc7a2a3d-7371-4522-8f31-aa113e5486d7 In medium microwavable bowl, place butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Microwave on Medium 1 minute to 1 minute 30 seconds or until mixture is melted, stirring every 30 seconds until smooth. Add shoestring potatoes and peanuts; stir gently to coat.
dc7a2a3d-7371-4522-8f31-aa113e5486d7 Spoon and carefully spread mixture over crust. Crumble remaining half of dough over top. Sprinkle with coconut.
dc7a2a3d-7371-4522-8f31-aa113e5486d7 Bake 12 to 22 minutes or until set and golden brown. Cool 30 minutes. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm. For bars, cut into 5 rows by 4 rows.
0e9b3fae-0087-4e44-a182-8e6c9b32884e Directions:
0e9b3fae-0087-4e44-a182-8e6c9b32884e <span style="textdecoration: underline;">Sweet Potato Chips </span>
0e9b3fae-0087-4e44-a182-8e6c9b32884e <span style="textdecoration: underline;">Garlic Aioli Dipping Love: </span>
0e9b3fae-0087-4e44-a182-8e6c9b32884e Make funnels with parchment paper to serve the chips in. To make the funnels more festive, get your children involved and ask them to color the parchment paper on the side that will end up on the outside of the cone (make sure you allow the paper to dry if markers are used).
50e8398c-c81f-4fe0-85a1-f6ec1f9fc807 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Place 2 large sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil onto a clean surface.
50e8398c-c81f-4fe0-85a1-f6ec1f9fc807 Divide ingredients. In the center of each piece of foil, place an even, single layer of onion and lemon slices. Top the onion and lemon with lobster tails, cut-side up (2 per foil sheet), and corn. In a small mixing bowl, whisk together butter, wine, garlic and tarragon.
50e8398c-c81f-4fe0-85a1-f6ec1f9fc807 Gently fold up the edges of the foil around the food to create a shallow bowl. Pour butter mixture over the tails and corn and top with thyme sprigs. Season with salt and pepper. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
50e8398c-c81f-4fe0-85a1-f6ec1f9fc807 Bake for 20–25 minutes or until tails just cook through. Open packets carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape; then open top of foil packet. Serve with drawn butter and lemon wedges.
c8151297-bc92-48dd-a8e3-4055686ccd98 PREHEAT oven to 400F.
c8151297-bc92-48dd-a8e3-4055686ccd98 Place Reynolds® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch pan. Add flour, 2 teaspoons Italian seasoning, lemon zest and teaspoon salt to bag; gently squeeze bag to blend seasonings.
c8151297-bc92-48dd-a8e3-4055686ccd98 ADD tomatoes to oven bag; gently squeeze bag to crush tomatoes. Add beans, garlic and wine to bag. Turn bag several times to mix ingredients. Arrange ingredients in even layer in bag. Roll down open end of bag three times to hold it open.
c8151297-bc92-48dd-a8e3-4055686ccd98 BRUSH tilapia with olive oil and lemon juice. Sprinkle fish with remaining Italian seasoning; season with salt and pepper, if desired. Place fish in even layer on bean mixture in bag. Unroll bag.
c8151297-bc92-48dd-a8e3-4055686ccd98 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
c8151297-bc92-48dd-a8e3-4055686ccd98 BAKE 15 minutes or until fish flakes and beans are hot. Carefully cut top of bag open. Spoon sauce over fish; garnish with lemon slices, if desired.
0f00b0aa-e155-458d-b37f-4b9590b9e767 In a blender, combine all the dipping sauce ingredients except the basil and cilantro. Blend until smooth, add the basil and cilantro and pulse until chopped. Pour into a bowl, cover and place in the fridge until serving.
0f00b0aa-e155-458d-b37f-4b9590b9e767 Squeeze a little lime juice over the sliced avocado. Create an assembly line of vegetables and herbs, so that they are all ready to go.
0f00b0aa-e155-458d-b37f-4b9590b9e767 Fill a shallow dish with warm water. Add a rice paper sheet, one at a time for 5 to 10 seconds. Remove and place on a flat surface. Toward one end of the rice wrapper, begin layering with 1 to 2 slices of avocado, small handfuls of fresh cilantro and mint, and a handful of veggies. Sprinkle the veggies with salt and pepper. Fold both ends to the center and roll the sheet as tightly as you can without ripping. Place each prepared spring roll on a serving platter and cover with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil to keep the spring rolls from drying out.
0f00b0aa-e155-458d-b37f-4b9590b9e767 Continue with remaining ingredients, adding them to the platter as you work. Keep the spring rolls covered with foil at all times.
0f00b0aa-e155-458d-b37f-4b9590b9e767 Serve the spring rolls with the mango dipping sauce and chopped peanuts (if desired).
d66f1eb8-c562-4165-9ec8-b0efd046b079 Let cookie dough stand at room temperature minutes to soften. Meanwhile, heat oven to °F. Line cookie sheets with parchment paper.
d66f1eb8-c562-4165-9ec8-b0efd046b079 In food processor, place pecans, apricots, preserves, cinnamon and cloves. Cover; process, using quick on and off motions, to seconds or until pecans and apricots are finely chopped and mixture holds together.
d66f1eb8-c562-4165-9ec8-b0efd046b079 In large bowl, mix pecan mixture and sour cream. Crumble cookie dough into pecan mixture; stir with wooden spoon until well blended. Stir in flour until well blended.
d66f1eb8-c562-4165-9ec8-b0efd046b079 Onto cookie sheets, drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls inches apart. Bake to minutes or until light golden brown. Cool minutes; remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks. Cool completely, about minutes.
d66f1eb8-c562-4165-9ec8-b0efd046b079 Place waxed paper under cooling racks. In medium bowl, stir powdered sugar and milk until smooth. Dip tops of cookies into glaze; place on racks and let stand minutes. Dip cookies again; let stand minutes longer or until glaze is set.
cbf3f243-eaf7-4bc9-9fd4-0e328f0c940e Heat oven to °F. In small bowl, mix chopped peanuts, granulated sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
cbf3f243-eaf7-4bc9-9fd4-0e328f0c940e In another small bowl, stir peanut butter and powdered sugar until completely blended. Shape mixture into inch balls.
cbf3f243-eaf7-4bc9-9fd4-0e328f0c940e Cut roll of cookie dough into slices. Cut each slice in half crosswise to make pieces; flatten slightly. Shape cookie dough piece around peanut butter ball, covering completely. Repeat with remaining dough and balls.
cbf3f243-eaf7-4bc9-9fd4-0e328f0c940e Roll each covered ball in peanut mixture; gently pat mixture completely onto balls. Line a cookie sheet with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Place balls inches apart on cookie sheet. Press bottom of drinking glass into remaining peanut mixture. Flatten each ball to /inch thickness with bottom of glass. Sprinkle any remaining peanut mixture evenly on tops of cookies; gently press into dough.
cbf3f243-eaf7-4bc9-9fd4-0e328f0c940e Bake to minutes or until edges are golden brown. Cool minute; remove from cookie sheets to cooling rack. Store tightly covered.
d69958d4-61af-4287-81a2-e05e53f4b70d PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
d69958d4-61af-4287-81a2-e05e53f4b70d PLACE tilapia in parchment-lined pan.
d69958d4-61af-4287-81a2-e05e53f4b70d MIX lime juice, olive oil, seafood seasoning, garlic, salt and red pepper flakes in a medium bowl until well blended. Pour over fish.
d69958d4-61af-4287-81a2-e05e53f4b70d BAKE to minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Serve / fillet in each tortilla with lettuce, salsa and avocado.
933f0c11-ccc2-4319-b7f4-6438f41cb23c Heat oven to °F (°F for dark or nonstick pan). Line bottom of xinch pan with Reynolds<span>® Parchment Paper</span>.
933f0c11-ccc2-4319-b7f4-6438f41cb23c In medium bowl, stir / cup melted butter, / cups of the cracker crumbs and / cup of the toffee bits. Press mixture evenly in bottom of pan. Refrigerate about minutes or until firm.
933f0c11-ccc2-4319-b7f4-6438f41cb23c Meanwhile, let cookie dough stand at room temperature minutes to soften. In quart saucepan, heat chocolate chips, milk and tablespoon butter over medium heat, stirring frequently, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Spread mixture over cracker crust.
933f0c11-ccc2-4319-b7f4-6438f41cb23c In medium bowl, break up cookie dough. Mix in remaining / cup cracker crumbs with wooden spoon until well blended. Crumble mixture evenly over chocolate layer. Sprinkle with remaining / cup toffee bits.
933f0c11-ccc2-4319-b7f4-6438f41cb23c Bake to minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely, about hours. For a firmer bar, refrigerate minutes longer. For bars, cut into rows by rows.
60de1255-91a6-4b1a-9bbb-3cf9b8b7b415 Preheat grill to medium heat and place a 12x12-inch piece of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil on the grill.
60de1255-91a6-4b1a-9bbb-3cf9b8b7b415 Brush corn with olive oil, then sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning. Place corn on foil and cook for 10 to 12 minutes, turning occasionally until kernels begin to char. Remove from heat and slice kernels off of the cob.
60de1255-91a6-4b1a-9bbb-3cf9b8b7b415 Toss together corn, tomatoes, onions and basil in a medium bowl.
60de1255-91a6-4b1a-9bbb-3cf9b8b7b415 Whisk together all dressing ingredients. Add to salad and toss to coat. Serve immediately.
78db0c97-bda9-4f3e-b244-fa95ca82189f Cut a large piece of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and firmly fit it over the grill grate. Heat the grill to medium heat.
78db0c97-bda9-4f3e-b244-fa95ca82189f While the grill is heating, make the dressing. To a shallow bowl, add the shallot, vinegar, maple syrup, and a couple pinches of salt and pepper to taste. Let the mixture sit until the shallots are tender, about 10 minutes. Add 4 tablespoons of the oil and whisk until the dressing is mixed and blended. Set aside.
78db0c97-bda9-4f3e-b244-fa95ca82189f Cut the garlic clove in half. Using the cut side of the garlic, gently rub each side of bread. Using 1 tablespoon of oil, lightly brush each side of bread.
78db0c97-bda9-4f3e-b244-fa95ca82189f Place the bread on the hot grill and cook until toasted and firm, about 7 to 10 minutes. Remove the bread and let cool.
78db0c97-bda9-4f3e-b244-fa95ca82189f Brush the peaches with the remaining tablespoon of oil and sprinkle with a couple pinches of salt. Place the peaches on the foil-covered grill and cook until lightly browned but firm, about 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.
78db0c97-bda9-4f3e-b244-fa95ca82189f In a large serving bowl, toss together the arugula and basil. Tear the bread into large chunks and add to the bowl. Add the peaches and fennel, mix in the dressing and give everything a thorough toss.
8ec6391b-a232-456b-9652-9acf11787742 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
8ec6391b-a232-456b-9652-9acf11787742 SHAKE flour in Reynolds® Oven Bag large size.
8ec6391b-a232-456b-9652-9acf11787742 PLACE in 13x9x2-inch baking pan with opening towards wide side of pan.
8ec6391b-a232-456b-9652-9acf11787742 ADD all ingredients except sweet potatoes to oven bag; squeeze bag to blend in flour.
8ec6391b-a232-456b-9652-9acf11787742 ADD sweet potatoes; turn to coat evenly. Arrange ingredients in an even layer.
8ec6391b-a232-456b-9652-9acf11787742 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
8ec6391b-a232-456b-9652-9acf11787742 BAKE 45 to 50 minutes or until sweet potatoes are tender.
8ec6391b-a232-456b-9652-9acf11787742 Spoon sauce over sweet potatoes before serving.
309731d1-e248-4f6f-96fb-f789f6c3115c Line a small baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Set aside.
309731d1-e248-4f6f-96fb-f789f6c3115c In a food processor, combine the shallots, vinegar, lemon juice, maple syrup, olive oil, salt and pepper and blend until smooth. Set aside.
309731d1-e248-4f6f-96fb-f789f6c3115c In a non-stick pan over medium heat, combine the hazelnuts, sugar and cayenne. Stir with a silicone spatula until the sugar has melted and sticks to the nuts, about 5 minutes; turn down the heat to prevent burning if needed. Spread the sticky nuts out on the foil-lined sheet to cool. When the nuts are cool enough to handle, break them up by hand.
309731d1-e248-4f6f-96fb-f789f6c3115c Stem the kale and chop well. Using a mandolin, shred the Brussels sprouts, discarding the tough ends. Combine both in a large salad bowl. Add the hazelnuts, quinoa, pomegranate seeds, green onions and cheese. Dress to your liking and serve immediately.
a387d81c-3500-48e0-a687-2a03d2da7a2d Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
a387d81c-3500-48e0-a687-2a03d2da7a2d Slice woody ends from garlic cloves, leaving papery skin intact. Lay out a 10-inch square of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil, set garlic cloves sliced-side down in the center and drizzle with 1 tablespoon olive oil and a pinch of sea salt. Carefully pull up corners and crimp the top to secure foil tightly around garlic. Place in a small ovenproof dish and bake 15 minutes, or until garlic is translucent and very soft. (Use caution when opening foil packet – steam can be very hot.) Set foil packet aside until garlic is cool enough to handle.
a387d81c-3500-48e0-a687-2a03d2da7a2d Squeeze garlic from papery skins and mash with a fork in a small mixing bowl. With the same fork, whisk in lime juice, grated ginger, honey and 1/2 teaspoon sea salt. Whisking vigorously, slowly drizzle in 1/4 cup olive oil.
a387d81c-3500-48e0-a687-2a03d2da7a2d Toss cabbage, bell peppers and chilies with dressing in a large mixing bowl. Fold in mango slices and cilantro. Taste and add a pinch more salt or a squeeze of lime if needed.
5edf93ac-15f2-4557-8905-bafde90cdb29 PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line a muffin pan with twelve Reynolds® Foil Baking Cups; set aside. In a large bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Make a well in the center of flour mixture; set aside.
5edf93ac-15f2-4557-8905-bafde90cdb29 WHISK together buttermilk, eggs, butter, and dill in a 2-cup measure. Add all at once to flour mixture. Gently stir just until moistened (batter should be lumpy). Chop 2 ounces of the smoked salmon. Gently fold in salmon.
5edf93ac-15f2-4557-8905-bafde90cdb29 SPOON batter into prepared muffin cups, filling each three-fourths full.
5edf93ac-15f2-4557-8905-bafde90cdb29 BAKE for 15 minutes or until golden. Cool in cups on a wire rack for 5 minutes.
5edf93ac-15f2-4557-8905-bafde90cdb29 SPLIT the muffins and spread split sides with cream cheese. Sandwich some of the remaining 2 ounces smoked salmon in between muffin halves. Garnish with additional fresh dill.
8ccf1e02-bc00-4161-b300-bc30ef59b307 Preheat oven to 475°F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil.
8ccf1e02-bc00-4161-b300-bc30ef59b307 Cut potatoes into thick wedges. Place potato wedges in a medium bowl and cover with cold water; soak for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain wedges and thoroughly pat dry with paper towels. Place wedges on prepared baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil; sprinkle with salt. Toss to thoroughly coat wedges. Arrange wedges in a single layer.
8ccf1e02-bc00-4161-b300-bc30ef59b307 Bake about 15 minutes, or until potatoes are golden brown, cooked through, and starting to become crispy, turning every 5 minutes.
8ccf1e02-bc00-4161-b300-bc30ef59b307 To serve, drizzle sweet potato wedges with Marshmallow Sauce. Sprinkle potatoes and sauce with cinnamon, if desired.
10cd9f6e-e0cd-4630-b50c-815dda8a9089 PREHEAT oven to 450°F. Place Reynolds® Baking Cups in muffin pans; set aside.
10cd9f6e-e0cd-4630-b50c-815dda8a9089 PLACE cauliflower florets in center of foil. SPOON cheese sauce evenly over cauliflowerettes; TOP with bell pepper and ice cubes. SPRINKLE with salt and pepper, if desired. PLACE packet on baking sheet with 1-inch sides.
10cd9f6e-e0cd-4630-b50c-815dda8a9089 BRING up sides of foil; fold down two times. DOUBLE FOLD both ends of foil to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
10cd9f6e-e0cd-4630-b50c-815dda8a9089 BAKE 20 to 25 minutes or until cauliflowerettes are at desired texture.
10cd9f6e-e0cd-4630-b50c-815dda8a9089 OPEN packet carefully by cutting along top folds with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape.
10cd9f6e-e0cd-4630-b50c-815dda8a9089 STIR to coat evenly.
2fa97979-b1e7-4a2a-9622-ad3a8110f67a PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
2fa97979-b1e7-4a2a-9622-ad3a8110f67a PLACE tilapia in parchment-lined pan.
2fa97979-b1e7-4a2a-9622-ad3a8110f67a MIX lime juice, olive oil, seafood seasoning, garlic, salt and red pepper flakes in a medium bowl until well blended. Pour over fish.
2fa97979-b1e7-4a2a-9622-ad3a8110f67a BAKE to minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Serve / fillet in each tortilla with lettuce, salsa and avocado.
54104038-b809-4230-a66c-f82707040177 Preheat oven to 350 degree F.
54104038-b809-4230-a66c-f82707040177 In a large mixing bowl combine flour, sugar, baking soda, and salt. Cut in butter and the 1/2 cup peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Beat in honey and milk until well combined.
54104038-b809-4230-a66c-f82707040177 Pat 1 tablespoon of the dough into a 2-inch circle. Place 1 piece of candy in the center of the circle.
54104038-b809-4230-a66c-f82707040177 Shape the dough around candy to form a 1-1/2-inch ball. Place on a cookie sheet lined with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Repeat with remaining cookie dough and candy bars.
54104038-b809-4230-a66c-f82707040177 Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Cool on wire rack.
11d9e9e2-b77f-4272-924b-f003022d0621 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
11d9e9e2-b77f-4272-924b-f003022d0621 PREPARE one of the pound cake mixes as instructed on the box instructions. Add the cocoa powder to the batter then mix to fully combine. Transfer to Reynolds® Bakeware Loaf Pan, then bake as instructed on the box instructions. Transfer to a wire rack to cool for 15 minutes, remove from pan, then transfer to the freezer to cool completely.
11d9e9e2-b77f-4272-924b-f003022d0621 CUT the entire loaf into thick, 1 1/2-inch slices. Using a witch hat-shaped cookie cutter, cut shapes out of the center of each of the slices.
11d9e9e2-b77f-4272-924b-f003022d0621 PREPARE the second pound cake mix as instructed on the box instructions. Pour a thin layer of batter on to the bottom of a Reynolds® Bakeware Loaf Pan.
11d9e9e2-b77f-4272-924b-f003022d0621 STACK the witch hats upright, inside the pan, in a straight line on top of the batter. Carefully pour the remaining batter on the sides and then on top of the witch hats. Make sure the witch hats are fully covered.
11d9e9e2-b77f-4272-924b-f003022d0621 BAKE the pound cake as instructed on the box instructions. Transfer to a wire rack to cool for 15 minutes, remove from pan and cool completely.
11d9e9e2-b77f-4272-924b-f003022d0621 WHISK the powdered sugar and orange juice in a large bowel until fully combined and smooth. Pour the icing over the top of the pound cake. Use a spatula to smooth. Sprinkle on pepitas and/or pistachios.
11d9e9e2-b77f-4272-924b-f003022d0621 SLICE the cake into 3/4 –inch pieces before serving. The sliced cake will showcase the surprise witch hat inside.
039e7b1a-6935-4838-ad9f-93390d4853b8 In a medium bowl, combine the beef, chipotle pepper, adobo sauce, and 1/4 cup of the blue cheese. Form into 8 patties.
039e7b1a-6935-4838-ad9f-93390d4853b8 In a large skillet, brown the patties on each side over medium heat until no longer pink.
039e7b1a-6935-4838-ad9f-93390d4853b8 Keep patties in the skillet and top with remaining 1/4 cup blue cheese crumbles. Cover skillet and cook for 1-2 minutes or until blue cheese melts.
039e7b1a-6935-4838-ad9f-93390d4853b8 Serve sliders on buns with bacon and green onions on top.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Chop the candies in a food processor to a fine powder.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Mix the butter and granulated sugar in the bowl of a stand
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 mixer fitted with the paddle attachment on medium-high speed, about 3 minutes.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Add the vanilla and unbeaten egg and beat to incorporate.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Reduce the speed to low and add the flour in 2 additions, beating
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 to incorporate each until the dough just comes together.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Add the peppermint powder and mix until a dough ball forms.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Turn the dough out onto a 20-inch-long sheet of Reynolds® Parchment Paper and roll it out into a 16-by-12-inch rectangle just under 1/4 inch thick.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Place the dough in the refrigerator for 10 minutes to chill, then brush it with the beaten egg and sprinkle with the sanding sugar.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Roll the dough into a tight log, with the short end facing you. Rotate and center the dough on the parchment and roll it up tightly; twist the ends and tuck them under. (It should look like a giant piece of wrapped candy.)
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Roll and chill in the refrigerator, about 25 minutes.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Line 2 baking sheets with Reynolds Parchment Paper.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Slice the dough into 24 1/4-inch-thick cookies and place them 1 inch apart on the prepared baking sheets.
bd3ba905-b8ff-47a0-adf4-60ff8ea73a86 Bake until golden brown, about 10 minutes. Transfer the cookies to a wire rack to cool.
0b2de15b-1229-4893-abf1-e05a98ddcd74 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
0b2de15b-1229-4893-abf1-e05a98ddcd74 GREASE a 10-inch Bundt pan with non-stick cooking spray. Thoroughly combine the cinnamon and sugar. Transfer to a shallow bowl and set aside.
0b2de15b-1229-4893-abf1-e05a98ddcd74 CUT each biscuit into quarters, then roll into balls. Transfer each of the dough balls into the cinnamon sugar. Toss until fully coated.
0b2de15b-1229-4893-abf1-e05a98ddcd74 WHISK together the melted butter, brown sugar and pumpkin puree.
0b2de15b-1229-4893-abf1-e05a98ddcd74 TRANSFER half of the cinnamon-sugared dough balls into the prepared Bundt cake pan. Pour half of the pumpkin mixture on top. Add the remaining dough balls, then pour the remaining pumpkin mixture on top. Cover with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
0b2de15b-1229-4893-abf1-e05a98ddcd74 BAKE for 40 to 45 minutes or the center is fully cooked. Transfer to a wire rack to cool for 15 minutes, then flip Monkey Bread out of the pan and cool completely.
0b2de15b-1229-4893-abf1-e05a98ddcd74 WHISK together the powdered sugar and milk in a large bowl until fully combined and smooth. Pour the icing over the top of the monkey bread. Use a spatula to smooth. Sprinkle pepitas or pumpkin seeds on top.
7ea45310-df64-46f6-88d2-eab7b4efbc57 Preheat the oven to 450°.
7ea45310-df64-46f6-88d2-eab7b4efbc57 Toss together the potatoes, olive oil, salt and pepper until combined.
7ea45310-df64-46f6-88d2-eab7b4efbc57 Transfer the mixture to a Reynolds® 13x9 Bakeware pan and bake in the oven at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the potatoes are lightly browned and tender.
7ea45310-df64-46f6-88d2-eab7b4efbc57 Remove the pan from the oven and evenly sprinkle the cheese over top. Return the pan to the oven and cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
7ea45310-df64-46f6-88d2-eab7b4efbc57 Drizzle the ranch dressing over the top of the potatoes and sprinkle on the chopped, crispy bacon and sliced green onions.
7ea45310-df64-46f6-88d2-eab7b4efbc57 Serve hot.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 STIR together flour, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl; set aside.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 BEAT butter and sugar together with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Scrape the sides of the bowl and continue beating on medium speed for 2 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Beat in vanilla.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 ADD the flour mixture and champagne to the beaten mixture, alternating them and beating on low speed just until combined after each addition. Beat on high speed for 20 seconds more.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 POUR the cake batter into a Reynolds® 13x9 Bakeware pan.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 BAKE the cake in the oven on 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown and firm in the center.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 COOL the cake on a cooling rack for 10 minutes.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 Champagne Frosting: BEAT the butter and cream cheese with an electric mixer on high speed until light and fluffy.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 Champagne Frosting: ADD in the powdered sugar and champagne and mix on low speed until incorporated and then mix on high speed for 2 minutes.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 Cake Bite Assembly: CRUMBLE cake. Transfer to a large bowl and add prepared icing. Mix together until fully combined.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 ROLL into 1-inch balls and freeze at least 1 hour or overnight.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 MELT white chocolate.
cbd6c74e-37a8-493b-8f96-95a81bdb53b0 DIP each of the cake bites into melted chocolate. Transfer to Reynolds® Parchment Paper. Add decoration if desired. Refrigerate until chocolate has hardened.
c0cf341c-b6f1-4c8c-b691-5e64768b902b Line a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner; set aside.
c0cf341c-b6f1-4c8c-b691-5e64768b902b In a large bowl, combine chili powder, cumin, oregano, and salt; set aside.
c0cf341c-b6f1-4c8c-b691-5e64768b902b Trim fat from meat; cut into 2-inch pieces, add to spice mixture, and toss gently to coat.
c0cf341c-b6f1-4c8c-b691-5e64768b902b In a Dutch oven or large pot, cook meat, half at a time, in hot oil over medium-high heat, stirring to brown evenly. With a slotted spoon, transfer meat to the prepared slow cooker. Add onion and garlic; cook until just tender. Transfer to the slow cooker.
c0cf341c-b6f1-4c8c-b691-5e64768b902b Pour orange juice and water over meat and vegetables. Add bay leaves. Cover slow cooker and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
c0cf341c-b6f1-4c8c-b691-5e64768b902b Using a slotted spoon, remove meat from lined slow cooker. (Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.) Using two forks, coarsely shred meat; discard any fat. Skim fat from cooking liquid. Drizzle meat with 1 to 2 cups of the cooking liquid.
c0cf341c-b6f1-4c8c-b691-5e64768b902b Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
c0cf341c-b6f1-4c8c-b691-5e64768b902b To warm the tortillas, preheat oven to 350°F. Wrap tortillas in foil and bake about 10 minutes or until heated through.
c0cf341c-b6f1-4c8c-b691-5e64768b902b Serve with warmed corn tortillas, fresh salsa, radishes, and lime wedges. If desired, garnish with Mexican crema or sour cream.
67996064-4575-4a4b-955e-b3332ffb1b10 LINE a 18x13x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
67996064-4575-4a4b-955e-b3332ffb1b10 CUT 10, 4-inch circular disks out of the pre-packaged pie dough
67996064-4575-4a4b-955e-b3332ffb1b10 SPOON Bananas onto one side of each dough disk. Drizzle about a teaspoon of caramel on top. Brush the inner edges with heavy cream, and then fold the dough over into half moon shape. Crimp and flute edges together to seal. Repeat with remaining dough.
67996064-4575-4a4b-955e-b3332ffb1b10 TRANSFER to parchment lined pan.
67996064-4575-4a4b-955e-b3332ffb1b10 DIVIDE remaining heavy cream into 7 small prep bowls. Place 1 to 2 tablespoons of cream into each bowl. Use food coloring to dye each of the creams into red, orange, yellow, green, blue and purple.
67996064-4575-4a4b-955e-b3332ffb1b10 USE a small paintbrush to paint the colored cream wash onto each of the empanadas in a rainbow pattern. Repeat with a second coat if necessary. Transfer to freezer for 15 minutes.
67996064-4575-4a4b-955e-b3332ffb1b10 PREHEAT the oven to 350° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is golden.
67996064-4575-4a4b-955e-b3332ffb1b10 COOL on a wire rack for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
287ea70c-befb-470b-8bfa-022ee8a6f2aa PREHEAT the oven to 375°. Line a 18x13x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
287ea70c-befb-470b-8bfa-022ee8a6f2aa COMBINE strawberries, sugar, cornstarch, balsamic vinegar, black pepper and cayenne pepper in a large bowl. Stir the mixture together and set aside
287ea70c-befb-470b-8bfa-022ee8a6f2aa WHISK together egg and 1 tablespoon of water to make an egg wash.
287ea70c-befb-470b-8bfa-022ee8a6f2aa CUT 16, 3-inch circular disks out of the pre-packaged pie dough.
287ea70c-befb-470b-8bfa-022ee8a6f2aa SPOON strawberry mixture into the center of the pie dough disk. Brush the inner edges with egg wash then place a second circular disk on top. Press edges together to seal, then use a fork to make a decorative imprint around the edge of the dough. Repeat with remaining dough pieces.
287ea70c-befb-470b-8bfa-022ee8a6f2aa TRANSFER to parchment lined pan. Brush each empanada with egg wash and sprinkle with sugar.
287ea70c-befb-470b-8bfa-022ee8a6f2aa BAKE for 25 to 30 minutes or until juices in the center are bubbling and crust is golden.
287ea70c-befb-470b-8bfa-022ee8a6f2aa COOL on a wire rack for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
9585220d-b1f3-452c-9e9f-e4e25cec4613 PREHEAT the oven to 375°.
9585220d-b1f3-452c-9e9f-e4e25cec4613 ADD 1 tablespoon of flour to a Reynolds® Oven Bag and shake. Place the bag in a 13x9x2 inch casserole dish.
