9585220d-b1f3-452c-9e9f-e4e25cec4613 PLACE all ingredients except the parsley and lemon inside the oven bag and mix thoroughly to coat.
9585220d-b1f3-452c-9e9f-e4e25cec4613 CLOSE the bag and seal it with the provided tie.
9585220d-b1f3-452c-9e9f-e4e25cec4613 CUT 6 half-inch slits in the top of the bag and bake for 30-35 minutes or until shrimp are opaque and potatoes are tender.
9585220d-b1f3-452c-9e9f-e4e25cec4613 REMOVE seafood from bag and drain any excess liquid. Spread seafood boil out on a long sheet of Reynolds® Parchment Paper for serving.
9585220d-b1f3-452c-9e9f-e4e25cec4613 Garnish with parsley and serve with lemon wedges.
c23c2eb7-2aea-4d53-b9fb-5858f8ea345f Preheat oven to 350°F.
c23c2eb7-2aea-4d53-b9fb-5858f8ea345f Place butter and oil in a 12-inch cast-iron skillet or a Reynolds® Bakeware 13x9 Non-Stick Pan. Heat in the oven until melted and fragrant, 5 to 7 minutes.
c23c2eb7-2aea-4d53-b9fb-5858f8ea345f Meanwhile, combine flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Add milk, sugar and vanilla; stir to combine.
c23c2eb7-2aea-4d53-b9fb-5858f8ea345f Add the melted butter mixture to the batter and stir to combine. Pour the batter into the hot pan. Spoon peaches and blueberries evenly over the batter.
c23c2eb7-2aea-4d53-b9fb-5858f8ea345f Return the pan to the oven and bake until the top of the cobbler is browned and the batter around the fruit is completely set, 50 minutes to 1 hour. Remove to a wire rack to cool for at least 15 minutes. Serve warm.
b2f67132-b81c-48a2-9e89-dc427efb4a5a COMBINE flour, baking soda, ginger, allspice and salt in medium bowl; set aside.
b2f67132-b81c-48a2-9e89-dc427efb4a5a BEAT butter and brown sugar in a large bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy. Add in molasses, egg and vanilla; beat until well mixed. Set mixer to low speed and gradually add in flour mixture until completely blended. Divide dough into three equal portions; wrap each in a sheet of Reynolds KITCHENS™ Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®. Refrigerate 1 hour or until chilled and firm enough to handle easily.
b2f67132-b81c-48a2-9e89-dc427efb4a5a PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with parchment paper; set aside.
b2f67132-b81c-48a2-9e89-dc427efb4a5a ROLL one portion of dough between to two sheets of lightly floured parchment paper.
b2f67132-b81c-48a2-9e89-dc427efb4a5a CUT dough into shapes using 3- to 4-inch gingerbread cookie cutters. Place shapes 2 inches apart on parchment-lined cookie sheets.
b2f67132-b81c-48a2-9e89-dc427efb4a5a BAKE 8 to 10 minutes until bottoms are very lightly browned. Cool 3 minutes on wire rack. Carefully slide parchment paper with cookies onto cooling rack; cool completely on parchment paper. Decorate as desired.
b2f67132-b81c-48a2-9e89-dc427efb4a5a FOR ICING: MIX confectioners’ sugar, water, meringue power and clear vanilla extract in a medium bowl on low speed until just mixed. Stir 1 to 2 tablespoons more water if needed. Continue mixing on high speed for 5 to 7 minutes until mixture is glossy and forms stiff peaks. Spoon some icing in parchment paper piping bag to decorate cookies. STORE unused icing in airtight container and refrigerate up to one week. Stir in more water if needed.
35cf91ca-45ed-4464-a0e0-e4ddfe3e9901 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
35cf91ca-45ed-4464-a0e0-e4ddfe3e9901 COMBINE sugar and molasses in a large saucepan. Over medium-high heat, bring sugar and molasses to a boil.
35cf91ca-45ed-4464-a0e0-e4ddfe3e9901 REMOVE from heat and stir in baking soda. Add shortening to mixture, stirring until melted. Stir in egg. Mix in flour, spice and salt until crumbly dough forms.
35cf91ca-45ed-4464-a0e0-e4ddfe3e9901 TRANSFER the other half of the dough to a work surface lined with a sheet of parchment paper. Knead the dough until smooth. Cover dough with another sheet of parchment paper and roll to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut out the cookie shape using a paring knife. Remove the scraps, leaving the cookie on the parchment paper.
35cf91ca-45ed-4464-a0e0-e4ddfe3e9901 SLIDE the parchment paper with cookie onto a cookie sheet. Trim so that no parchment hangs over edges of cookie sheet.
35cf91ca-45ed-4464-a0e0-e4ddfe3e9901 BAKE 14 to 18 minutes or until just starting to brown around the edges. Slide parchment with cookie onto a wire rack and cool completely.
35cf91ca-45ed-4464-a0e0-e4ddfe3e9901 REPEAT rolling, cutting and baking with the remaining dough and scraps. Cool cookies completely before decorating.
35cf91ca-45ed-4464-a0e0-e4ddfe3e9901 SPOON white frosting into a pastry bag made of parchment paper. Snip tip of bag if needed to pipe a thin outline on each cookie. Add food coloring to remaining frosting, if desired and spoon into another pastry bag made of parchment paper. Decorate with frosting or and candies as desired.
9a1f2b95-70fb-49d3-a5e3-7b5d756d89e3 COMBINE flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl; set aside.
9a1f2b95-70fb-49d3-a5e3-7b5d756d89e3 BEAT butter and sugar in large bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add egg yolks and vanilla until mixed well. Gradually add flour mixture and combine.
9a1f2b95-70fb-49d3-a5e3-7b5d756d89e3 WRAP dough in parchment paper and place in plastic slider top bag. Refrigerate at least one hour until chilled and firm enough to handle easily.
9a1f2b95-70fb-49d3-a5e3-7b5d756d89e3 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds KITCHENS™ Parchment Paper; set aside.
9a1f2b95-70fb-49d3-a5e3-7b5d756d89e3 ROLL out dough 1/4-inch thick between 2 sheets of lightly floured parchment paper. CUT dough with 2 inch cookie cutters. PLACE dough 1-inch apart on parchment-lined cookie sheets.
9a1f2b95-70fb-49d3-a5e3-7b5d756d89e3 BAKE 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned on edges. COOL 3 minutes on cooling rack. Slide parchment paper with cookies onto cooling rack; cool.
9a1f2b95-70fb-49d3-a5e3-7b5d756d89e3 FOR DECORATIVE ICING: MIX confectioners’ sugar, water, meringue power and clear vanilla extract in a medium bowl on low speed until just mixed. Stir 1 to 2 tablespoons more water if needed. Continue mixing on high speed for 5 to 7 minutes until mixture is glossy and forms stiff peaks. DIVIDE icing into small bowls and cover bowls as you work to prevent drying. STIR 2 teaspoons water into 1 cup icing. Add more water if needed to thin icing enough to spread easily.
9a1f2b95-70fb-49d3-a5e3-7b5d756d89e3 TO DECORATE: ARRANGE cookies in single layer on a sheet of parchment paper. SPOON about 1 tablespoon thinned frosting in center of each cookie. Top with a marshmallow. ADD food coloring, one drop at a time to icing in remaining bowls. SPOON some icing in parchment paper piping bag to decorate to create snowmen. Stir in more water, 1 teaspoon at a time, if icing is too thick to spoon or pipe. Let cookies set till icing hardens. STORE unused icing in airtight container and refrigerate up to one week. Stir in more water if needed.
9a1f2b95-70fb-49d3-a5e3-7b5d756d89e3 Store finished cookies in airtight containers for up to 5 days.
2d01779c-e23f-4d14-a412-36720057eb73 LINE a 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner. Place popcorn, pretzel twists, rice cereal, salted peanuts, and white chocolate chips inside. Toss and stir to combine.
2d01779c-e23f-4d14-a412-36720057eb73 PLACE brown sugar and butter in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until just boiling. Pour butter mixture over popcorn mixture in slow cooker. Stir to fully combine.
2d01779c-e23f-4d14-a412-36720057eb73 COOK on low-heat setting, uncovered for 1 hour, stirring often.
2d01779c-e23f-4d14-a412-36720057eb73 TRANSFER mixture to a Reynolds® Bakeware Pans. Drizzle melted red and green confectionary coating on top.
2d01779c-e23f-4d14-a412-36720057eb73 COOL mixture completely before serving or sharing.
0947e102-b43a-4c76-8999-81be6a74ba6d PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds KITCHENS® Parchment Paper.
0947e102-b43a-4c76-8999-81be6a74ba6d BEAT butter in a large bowl with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add sugar, baking powder, and salt. Beat until combined, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally. Beat in the egg, milk, and vanilla until combined. Beat in as much of the flour as you can with the mixer. Using a wooden spoon, stir in any remaining flour. Divide dough in half. If necessary, cover and chill dough about 30 minutes or until easy to handle.
0947e102-b43a-4c76-8999-81be6a74ba6d ROLL half the dough at a time between two sheets of parchment paper to 1/8- to 1/4-inch thickness. Using a 2 1/2-inch heart-shape cookie cutter, cut out cookie shapes, rerolling dough as needed until all the dough is cut out. Place shapes 1 inch apart on prepared cookie sheets.
0947e102-b43a-4c76-8999-81be6a74ba6d BAKE 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are firm and bottoms are very light brown. Transfer the parchment paper with baked cookies to wire racks and let cool. Once cooled, slide the parchment paper onto a work surface.
0947e102-b43a-4c76-8999-81be6a74ba6d Tint frosting as desired with food coloring. Frost cookies with one color and use another color to pipe a message over the frosted cookies.
8c390769-c587-4930-bfb2-3afc33ddf086 Preheat oven to 425°F.
8c390769-c587-4930-bfb2-3afc33ddf086 Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add leeks, garlic, 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper and cook, stirring, until soft and beginning to brown, about 6 minutes. Add wine and cook, stirring, 1 minute more. Transfer the mixture to a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
8c390769-c587-4930-bfb2-3afc33ddf086 Layer tomatoes, summer squash (or zucchini) and eggplant slices in an alternating shingle pattern over the leek mixture (they will overlap quite a bit). If you have extra vegetable slices, save them for another use. Sprinkle the vegetables with the remaining 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper and drizzle with the remaining 2 tablespoons oil.
8c390769-c587-4930-bfb2-3afc33ddf086 Bake the vegetables for 1-1/4 hours. Sprinkle cheese and marjoram over the top. Continue baking until the edges are browned and the vegetables are very tender, about 15 minutes more. Let cool for about 5 minutes before serving.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 PREHEAT oven to 350°F.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 LINE cookie sheets with Reynolds KITCHENS™ Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside. No need to add extra grease or spray your cookie sheets.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 KNEAD flour into sugar cookie dough until well blended.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 ROLL out half of cookie dough at a time to 1/4-inch thickness between lightly floured sheets of Reynolds KITCHENS™ Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®. Using circles, shamrocks and leprechaun hat shaped cookie cutters, cut out cookies; place on parchment-lined cookie sheets 1" apart.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 BAKE 7 to 12 minutes, depending on the size of the cookies or until the edges begin to brown. Let stand one minute on cookie sheets. Slide Parchment Paper with cookies onto a wire racks to cool completely.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 DECORATING SUGAR COOKIES:
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 BEAT powdered sugar, meringue powder, water and extract in a large bowl, with an electric mixer, on high speed until smooth and thick, about 1 minute. DIVIDE icing into 8 small bowls. Keep one bowl of frosting white. Stir food coloring in remaining frosting to make green, neon green, black, yellow, blue, orange, and red icing. Cover icing tightly when not in use, icing dries quickly. PIPE outlines of cookies with contrasting colors of icing using a decorating bag with tip. Or, place icing in plastic zipper bags. Snip off one corner with scissors and use to pipe icing.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 FOR SUGARED OUTLINES:
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 SPRINKLE heavily with sugar crystals while icing is wet. Lightly shake off excess crystals.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 TO ICE INSIDE OUTLINES: ADD a little water to thin icing, if necessary. Spoon a small amount of icing onto outlined cookies. Using a brush, small spatula or your finger, spread icing up to outline to fill in spaces.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 FOR POTS OF GOLD: PIPE black icing onto unfrosted round cookies to outline the handle and the shape of the pot. For the "gold", use yellow icing as the glue to attach yellow mini candy-coated candies. Tip: Dots of frosting can be substituted if yellow candies are not available in the quantities that you need.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 FOR RAINBOWS: PIPE curved lines of colors of the rainbow around the top edge of round cookies. To make the clouds, use scissors to cut miniature marshmallows in half. Press the cut edge down on the ends of the rainbows.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 FOR LEPRECHAN HATS: FOLLOW directions above for outlining and icing the hats with green frosting. Pipe chocolate frosting across cookies for a hat band. Pipe a square of yellow frosting for a buckle on the hat band. When icing is dry, pipe details of hat with green frosting.
7eeb6d31-06ae-40bf-9ce5-49b332edf088 FOR MESSAGE COOKIES: FOLLOW directions above for icing the cookies. While the icing is still wet, add a border of coordinating mini candy-coated chocolate candies; let dry. Pipe messages with either contrasting color icing or chocolate frosting.
8e606501-6670-4d49-ae61-1f8e9b471cfe PREHEAT Oven to 375°F. Line a baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil.
8e606501-6670-4d49-ae61-1f8e9b471cfe MOLD 4-6 foil block molds to hold and shape taco shells. Molds should be approx. 4” tall x 5”wide. Place foil molds on top pf baking sheet and set aside.
8e606501-6670-4d49-ae61-1f8e9b471cfe BRUSH hot sauce on corn tortilla. Press crushed chips on top to fully coat the taco shell.
8e606501-6670-4d49-ae61-1f8e9b471cfe DRAPE prepared shells over foil molds and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until shells are crisp. Cool for 10 minutes before removing shells from foil mold.
8e606501-6670-4d49-ae61-1f8e9b471cfe FILL with favorite taco fillings and serve immediately.
98c9a49d-904b-4bb2-a9b4-d7380f8b275b PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Use grid lines to tear or cut sheets of Reynolds KITCHENS™ Parchment Paper to fit your cookie sheet(s). Line cookie sheet(s) and set aside.
98c9a49d-904b-4bb2-a9b4-d7380f8b275b COMBINE flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl; set aside.
98c9a49d-904b-4bb2-a9b4-d7380f8b275b BEAT butter and sugar in large bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add eggs, vanilla extract and lemon extract; beat until mixed well. Reduce speed to low and gradually add flour mixture until mixed well.
98c9a49d-904b-4bb2-a9b4-d7380f8b275b SHAPE tablespoons of dough into 1 inch balls. (If dough is too soft to shape into balls, cover tightly and refrigerate dough for up to one hour until it is firm enough to shape.) Place balls of dough 2 inches apart of parchment lined cookie sheets. Make a small indention about half way through thickness in the center of each ball using your thumb or the bottom of a round shaped measuring teaspoon. Fill each indention with 1 teaspoon of lemon curd.
98c9a49d-904b-4bb2-a9b4-d7380f8b275b BAKE 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are very lightly browned on bottom edges. COOL 3 minutes on wire rack. Slide parchment paper with cookies onto rack; cool completely.
98c9a49d-904b-4bb2-a9b4-d7380f8b275b PLACE confectioners’ sugar in a small bowl. ADD lemon juice one teaspoon at a time, whisking until the consistency is smooth and thin enough to drizzle. Add water, ½ teaspoon at a time if glaze is too thick to drizzle. DRIZZLE glaze over each cookie, making designs as desired. Let cookies set until glaze hardens.
98c9a49d-904b-4bb2-a9b4-d7380f8b275b STORE cookies refrigerated in an airtight container separated by sheets of parchment for up to one week.
73fecbfc-50b3-4a95-b473-2762f78d3eb2 LINE a 5-8 quart slow cooker bowl with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens Slow Cooker Liner.
73fecbfc-50b3-4a95-b473-2762f78d3eb2 PLACE water and three-fourths of the vegetables in the lined-slow cooker. Reserve 1 tablespoon onion soup mix. Sprinkle remaining onion soup mix over vegetables; stir gently to coat evenly. Sprinkle and rub salt, pepper and thyme over the pot roast. Place pot roast on top of vegetables. Place remaining vegetables around pot roast; sprinkle vegetables with remaining onion soup mix.
73fecbfc-50b3-4a95-b473-2762f78d3eb2 COVER and COOK for 8-9 hours on LOW OR 5 hours on HIGH, until pot roast is tender.
73fecbfc-50b3-4a95-b473-2762f78d3eb2 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve food directly from slow cooker using a wooden or plastic spoon. REMOVE all food and cool slow cooker completely before lifting liner from slow cooker.
b6edf5ea-588e-410e-89af-f0e53125ec78 COMBINE balsamic vinegar, ¼ cup olive oil, honey, minced garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper in a gallon size slider-top plastic storage bag; gently squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Place bag in a rectangular dish and add pork tenderloins to bag. Close bag and turn to coat the pork.
b6edf5ea-588e-410e-89af-f0e53125ec78 REFRIGERATE pork at least 2 hours to marinade.
b6edf5ea-588e-410e-89af-f0e53125ec78 ABOUT 15 minutes before removing pork from refrigerator, PREHEAT the oven to 400°F. **LINE a large baking pan, at least 15x10x1-inches, with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil; set pan aside.
b6edf5ea-588e-410e-89af-f0e53125ec78 TOSS vegetables with the remaining olive oil, salt and pepper in a large bowl until vegetables are well coated. ARRANGE vegetables evenly in the pan, spacing the vegetables so heat can circulate between them.
b6edf5ea-588e-410e-89af-f0e53125ec78 Bake 20 mins. Carefully remove pan from oven. Push vegetables to sides of pan.
b6edf5ea-588e-410e-89af-f0e53125ec78 REMOVE the tenderloins from the marinade, draining as much marinade as possible, and place tenderloins in center of vegetables in pan. SPRINKLE pork with paprika. ARRANGE vegetables evenly around pork tenderloins. If desired, lightly brush additional marinade on pork and vegetables. Discard unused marinade.
b6edf5ea-588e-410e-89af-f0e53125ec78 RETURN pans to oven; BAKE 25 to 30 minutes until meat thermometer in center of both tenderloins reads 145°F. Cook longer if you prefer no pink color in center of the pork roasts. Cover meat with a clean sheet of foil and let rest for 10 minutes before serving.
c4a7b098-906f-4351-ab9f-2a97174e38d9 LINE a 9x5x3-inch loaf pan with Reynolds KITCHENS™ Quick Cut™ Plastic Wrap and set aside.
c4a7b098-906f-4351-ab9f-2a97174e38d9 COMBINE all ingredients for layer 1 in a bowl. Mix thoroughly to fully combine.
c4a7b098-906f-4351-ab9f-2a97174e38d9 TRANSFER mixture to plastic wrap lined loaf pan. Using a second piece of plastic wrap, press mixture into the bottom and up the sides of the pan to create a smooth and even layer. Cover in plastic wrap and transfer to freezer for 15 minutes.
c4a7b098-906f-4351-ab9f-2a97174e38d9 COMBINE all ingredients for layer 2 in a bowl. Mix thoroughly to fully combine.
c4a7b098-906f-4351-ab9f-2a97174e38d9 TRANSFER mixture to plastic wrap lined pan, on top of layer 1. Using a second piece of plastic wrap, press mixture into the bottom and up the sides of layer 1 to create a smooth and even second layer. Cover in plastic wrap and transfer to freezer for 15 minutes.
c4a7b098-906f-4351-ab9f-2a97174e38d9 COMBINE all ingredients for layer 3 in a bowl. Mix thoroughly to fully combine.
c4a7b098-906f-4351-ab9f-2a97174e38d9 TRANSFER mixture into the cavity on top of layer 2. Using a second piece of plastic wrap to press and smooth top. Cover in plastic wrap and chill until firm, about 2 hours.
c4a7b098-906f-4351-ab9f-2a97174e38d9 REMOVE plastic wrap from base of chilled cheese log. Invert on to a plate. Remove loaf pan, then remove plastic wrap from cheese log. Cover with chopped pecans before serving. Serve layer 1 with Pinot Grigio, layer 2 with Chardonnay and layer 3 with Riesling.
203e1159-be37-409a-ab2d-2632e9ff2c12 LINE a medium sized mixing bowl with Reynolds KITCHENS® Quick Cut™ Plastic Wrap and set aside.
203e1159-be37-409a-ab2d-2632e9ff2c12 COMBINE all ingredients for layer 1 in a bowl. Mix thoroughly to fully combine.
203e1159-be37-409a-ab2d-2632e9ff2c12 TRANSFER mixture to plastic wrap lined bowl. Using a second piece of plastic wrap, press mixture into the bottom and up the sides of the bowl to create a smooth and even layer. Cover in plastic wrap and transfer to freezer for 15 minutes.
203e1159-be37-409a-ab2d-2632e9ff2c12 COMBINE all ingredients for layer 2 in a bowl. Mix thoroughly to fully combine.
203e1159-be37-409a-ab2d-2632e9ff2c12 TRANSFER mixture to plastic wrap lined bowl, on top of layer 1. Using a second piece of plastic wrap, press mixture into the bottom and up the sides of layer 1 to create a smooth and even second layer. Cover in plastic wrap and transfer to freezer for 15 minutes.
203e1159-be37-409a-ab2d-2632e9ff2c12 COMBINE all ingredients for layer 3 in a bowl. Mix thoroughly to fully combine.
203e1159-be37-409a-ab2d-2632e9ff2c12 TRANSFER mixture into the cavity on top of layer 2. Using a second piece of plastic wrap to press and smooth top. Cover in plastic wrap and chill until firm, about 2 hours.
203e1159-be37-409a-ab2d-2632e9ff2c12 REMOVE plastic wrap from base of chilled cheese ball. Invert on to a plate. Remove loaf pan, then remove plastic wrap from cheese ball. Cover with chopped almonds before serving. Serve layer 1 with Merlot, layer 2 with Malbec and layer 3 with Pinot Noir.
8f4274e8-10e6-48a5-ae7a-fd9472e9a28b In a food processor, mini food processor, or blender, combine all of the dressing ingredients except salt and pepper and blend until very smooth and bright green. Season to taste and set aside.
8f4274e8-10e6-48a5-ae7a-fd9472e9a28b Heat a grill to medium high. Remove a 36-inch length of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil from the roll, and fold in half. Roll the edges over a few times to create sides, and crimp the corners. Poke a holes in it using a metal skewer or the tip of a sharp knife. Place the foil “pan” on a baking sheet, and place the asparagus and onions on it. Toss with the oil, coarse salt and pepper, coating well.
8f4274e8-10e6-48a5-ae7a-fd9472e9a28b Using tongs, slide the foil “pan” to the grill while holding the baking sheet right next to the grill. Grill for 5-7 minutes, tossing once or twice, until lightly charred and tender. (time will vary depending on heat of grill and thickness of asparagus).
8f4274e8-10e6-48a5-ae7a-fd9472e9a28b Using tongs, pull the foil “pan” onto the baking sheet.
8f4274e8-10e6-48a5-ae7a-fd9472e9a28b Spread some of the green goddess dressing on the bottom of a serving platter, and top with the asparagus and onions. Sprinkle with flaky sea salt and snipped chives. Pass extra dressing on the side.
2b4eef0a-3d05-4027-8068-5ea6271bc67b Remove the membrane from the back of each rack--grip the corner with a paper towel and peel off.
2b4eef0a-3d05-4027-8068-5ea6271bc67b In a small bowl, combine salt, paprika, chili powder, brown sugar, oregano, garlic and pepper. Spread evenly on both sides of the racks and rub in. Place on two foil-lined baking sheets.
2b4eef0a-3d05-4027-8068-5ea6271bc67b Cook for 2½ to 3 hours at 275°F, or until soft and yielding to pressure. At this point, the ribs can be cooled and refrigerated for later grilling. Take out 1 hour before ready to serve.
2b4eef0a-3d05-4027-8068-5ea6271bc67b When ready to serve, brush with BBQ sauce on both sides and wrap well in heavy duty foil. Heat grill to med-low. Grill for 5 minutes per side, or until heated through and very tender.
a3039694-1e7e-4eec-bbf0-54ad370ef242 Prepare the hard veggies for grilling. In a wide and shallow, microwaveable dish -- preferably with a lid -- add ½ inch of water and one kind of vegetable at a time. Microwave covered for the prescribed time, stirring once during cooking. Let steam, covered, for 2 minutes longer. For sweet potatoes, cook 3 minutes. For beets, cook 4 minutes. For radishes, cook 2 ½ minutes. For shallots, cook 1½ minutes. For broccoli, cook 45 seconds (do not let steam after cooking.)
a3039694-1e7e-4eec-bbf0-54ad370ef242 Skewer the vegetables with broccoli, radishes, shallots and beets on some skewers, and zucchini, peppers, sweet potatoes, radishes, and string beans on others. Brush with the oil, and wrap skewers in Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil, taking care to keep the foil flat against the vegetables so they make good contact with the grill. Store until ready to cook.
a3039694-1e7e-4eec-bbf0-54ad370ef242 Whisk together all of the sauce ingredients, and thin as needed with water (about ¼ cup, or more).
a3039694-1e7e-4eec-bbf0-54ad370ef242 Heat a gas or charcoal grill to medium high. Lay the skewer packages on the grill, and cook for about 3 minutes per side. Drizzle with sauce and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
a8840a76-c211-4411-9bc8-d5d15a3b64ed Trim fat from roast. Cut roast to fit in crockery cooker, if necessary. Rub Cajun seasoning all over meat.
a8840a76-c211-4411-9bc8-d5d15a3b64ed In a large skillet brown meat on all sides in hot oil.
a8840a76-c211-4411-9bc8-d5d15a3b64ed In a 3-1/2- to 4-quart crockery cooker lined with a Reynolds KITCHENS® Slow Cooker Liner combine undrained tomatoes, onion, celery, tapioca, and garlic. Place meat on top of vegetable mixture.
a8840a76-c211-4411-9bc8-d5d15a3b64ed Cover and cook on low-heat setting for 10 to 12 hours or on high-heat setting for 5 to 6 hours.
a8840a76-c211-4411-9bc8-d5d15a3b64ed Slice meat; serve with sauce over rice.
7fdc2763-e27c-4878-b02d-c6ccd23b2b5a PULSE the bacon in a food processor until finely chopped. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-low. Cook bacon, stirring often, until browned and fat renders, about 4 minutes.
7fdc2763-e27c-4878-b02d-c6ccd23b2b5a ADD breadcrumbs and cook, stirring often, until brown and crisp, about 5 minutes. Transfer mixture to paper towels to drain and let cool slightly. Toss in a bowl with thyme, lemon zest, and chile; set aside.
7fdc2763-e27c-4878-b02d-c6ccd23b2b5a HEAT oven to 425°F. Line an 11- by 18-inch sheet pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Trim and cut the Brussels sprouts in half, separating and reserving loose leaves that fall away. Toss the sprouts on the baking sheet with 2 Tbsp oil, and season with salt and pepper. Roast until golden brown and tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
7fdc2763-e27c-4878-b02d-c6ccd23b2b5a ADD the reserved loose leaves in the last 5 minutes of cooking, tossing them to lightly coat with oil. Transfer to a serving bowl, squeeze the lemon half over, and top with the breadcrumb mixture.
6f38129f-a36f-4f20-8d4e-1ef4c6bce5b6 CUT the top and hollow out the center of the Italian loaf.
6f38129f-a36f-4f20-8d4e-1ef4c6bce5b6 SPRINKLE 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese into the loaf, then pour 1/2 cup marinara sauce on top. Place 1 lasagna noodle on top of sauce. Combine ricotta and mozzarella cheese and spread over lasagna noodle.
6f38129f-a36f-4f20-8d4e-1ef4c6bce5b6 PLACE red peppers on top of ricotta mixture. Place remaining lasagna noodle on top. Top with remaining 1/2 cup of marinara sauce, then add remaining 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese.
6f38129f-a36f-4f20-8d4e-1ef4c6bce5b6 WRAP loaf in Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil and bake at 350°F for 30 to 35 minutes or until fully heated throughout.
6f38129f-a36f-4f20-8d4e-1ef4c6bce5b6 COOL slightly and cut into slices for serving.
72b7d3cf-1212-4095-bdbc-292b863f1107 Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Line two large baking sheets with Reynolds KITCHENS® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®.
72b7d3cf-1212-4095-bdbc-292b863f1107 In medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa, and baking soda. In large bowl, with mixer on high speed, beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add egg and vanilla, and beat to combine. Alternate adding flour mixture and buttermilk in small batches, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
72b7d3cf-1212-4095-bdbc-292b863f1107 Mix until smooth, occasionally scraping sides of bowl. With a tablespoon, spoon mounds of batter 2 inches apart onto baking sheets and form into football shapes. SmartGrid® lines represent 1 inch squares to help you with precise spacing.
72b7d3cf-1212-4095-bdbc-292b863f1107 Bake 15 minutes or until tops are puffed and cakes spring back when touched. Transfer to a rack and cool completely.
72b7d3cf-1212-4095-bdbc-292b863f1107 In medium bowl, with mixer on high speed, beat together butter, powdered sugar, marshmallow cream, and vanilla until smooth, about 3 minutes.
72b7d3cf-1212-4095-bdbc-292b863f1107 Makes about 1-1/2 cups of filling. Spread a rounded tablespoon of filling on flat sides of half the cakes. Top with other cakes.
72b7d3cf-1212-4095-bdbc-292b863f1107 To decorate your whoopie pies to look like footballs, cut two pieces of Reynolds KITCHENS® Plastic Wrap about 15 inches wide and criss-cross them over each other to form a large X with the two pieces. In the center of the X, scoop all of your remaining filling and then gather the sides to push the filling down into a ball. Very carefully poke a small hole into the bottom of this ball so that you can pipe the football laces onto your whoopie pies. The thickness of your laces will depend on how big of a hole you poke into the plastic wrap.
cfc71118-364c-4d5c-bf23-a3eb4b483591 Preheat oven to 400°F.
cfc71118-364c-4d5c-bf23-a3eb4b483591 Cook bacon in a small frying pan until crispy. Remove from pan to drain on paper towels. Reserve bacon grease.
cfc71118-364c-4d5c-bf23-a3eb4b483591 Place green beans and onions in a large bowl. Add about 2 tablespoons of the reserved bacon grease. Sprinkle with salt and pepper, toss to coat.
cfc71118-364c-4d5c-bf23-a3eb4b483591 Cover a cookie sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Spread green beans in single layer on cookie sheet.
cfc71118-364c-4d5c-bf23-a3eb4b483591 Roast for 20-30 minutes, or until green beans are browned and cooked. Toss with bacon and serve hot.
54755f4a-a7f4-4e71-9e36-70782a2053d2 Fire up the grill to about 350°F in temperature.
54755f4a-a7f4-4e71-9e36-70782a2053d2 Tear off a long sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil – about twice the length of the salmon – and fold it in half.
54755f4a-a7f4-4e71-9e36-70782a2053d2 Place the salmon on top and season with garlic, lime zest and pepper. Fold in the sides of the foil and then the top and bottom in order to seal it closed. Place on the grill for 6 to 8 minutes.
54755f4a-a7f4-4e71-9e36-70782a2053d2 Mix together the ingredients for the sauce. Season to taste with lime zest, pepper and sea salt.
54755f4a-a7f4-4e71-9e36-70782a2053d2 Take the salmon off the grill and open up the foil. Reduce the heat of the grill to low) around 180°F) and set it to “smoke,” or add some soaked wood chips to the coals so it begins to smoke.
54755f4a-a7f4-4e71-9e36-70782a2053d2 Drizzle the sauce on the salmon, then brush it all over the salmon. Leave it open and place it back on the grill. If desired, slice open ripe avocados, remove the pit, then place the avocados face down on the grill. Smoke for 10 to 15 minutes and baste with a brush every 5 to 6 minutes. Remove the avocado halves after about 5 minutes or after they have grill marks on the flesh.
54755f4a-a7f4-4e71-9e36-70782a2053d2 Remove the salmon from the grill once it is cooked to your desired readiness and garnish with cilantro and lime.
54755f4a-a7f4-4e71-9e36-70782a2053d2 Flake the salmon with a fork then stuff it inside the grilled avocados. Top it off with salsa. Add sea salt and pepper to taste.
5b15ca49-3411-4cd5-ab59-06f3cfa40f8d PREHEAT oven to 325°F.
5b15ca49-3411-4cd5-ab59-06f3cfa40f8d SHAKE flour in Reynolds Oven Bag; place in 13x9x2-inch or larger baking pan with sides at least 2 inches deep. Combine oregano, pepper and salt; rub onto surface of roast.
5b15ca49-3411-4cd5-ab59-06f3cfa40f8d ADD roast, fat-side up, to oven bag. Arrange potatoes, carrots and onions around roast in an even layer in bag; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cut 1 inch off top of unpeeled garlic bulb, cutting through tips of cloves; discard top portion. Place in bag.
5b15ca49-3411-4cd5-ab59-06f3cfa40f8d CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
5b15ca49-3411-4cd5-ab59-06f3cfa40f8d BAKE 1-1/2 to 1-3/4 hours or until meat thermometer reads 145°F. Remove vegetables from oven bag to serving bowl. Squeeze softened garlic cloves into a small bowl; combine with butter. Add to vegetables; toss to coat. Season with additional salt and pepper, if desired. Serve roast with vegetables.
eeadde1f-5282-4399-a882-f0a39b4cf19e Keep clams cool until ready to cook. Place shrimp in bowl. Mix lemongrass, ginger, garlic, sugar and pepper. Add half to shrimp along with 1 teaspoon fish sauce and toss well. Refrigerate until ready to cook, up to 8 hours. To remaining lemongrass mixture, add scallion whites, remaining fish sauce, soy sauce, wine and water.
eeadde1f-5282-4399-a882-f0a39b4cf19e Preheat oven or grill to 450°F. For oven, place large sheet pan on middle rack. Using 2 sheets of foil on top of each other, lift the shorter sides and press together lightly to form a loose packet with wings, open at the top. Do not press tightly yet. Make a 2nd packet in the same manner. Divide clams between the packets. Pour half the lemongrass mixture over the clams in each packet. Distribute into a single layer. Spread shrimp over the top of clams. For each packet, bring together long edges of foil over the top of clams and seal tightly. Open the pressed edges and seal tightly with the top edge. Place both packets onto hot sheet pan in oven, or directly on grill rack. Cook 20-25 minutes in oven or 15-20 minutes on grill, until clams are fully open.
eeadde1f-5282-4399-a882-f0a39b4cf19e While clams roast, cook pancetta in medium skillet until crisp. Open bags carefully and transfer clams and shrimp to serving bowls, along with the cooking juices. Top with crispy pancetta and sliced scallions. Serve warm with rustic bread for dipping in sauce.
490316c0-bd04-4031-9f79-f16ac8e2cc89 Preheat the oven to 425°F.
490316c0-bd04-4031-9f79-f16ac8e2cc89 Mix together the gochujang, soy sauce, water, sesame oil and sugar in a large bowl until combined.
490316c0-bd04-4031-9f79-f16ac8e2cc89 Place the sliced chicken, green onions, cabbage, mushrooms, zucchini and cooked ramen noodles into the large bowl with the gochujang mixture and toss until coated.
490316c0-bd04-4031-9f79-f16ac8e2cc89 Place a 1 1/2 to 2 feet long sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil on a table and place 1/4 of the ramen noodle mixture into the center of the foil. Fold up the ends and then the outside to create a foil packet.
490316c0-bd04-4031-9f79-f16ac8e2cc89 Repeat the process 3 more times and place the foil packets on a cookie sheet tray.
490316c0-bd04-4031-9f79-f16ac8e2cc89 Bake in the oven for 25 minutes or until chicken is cooked throughout.
5544a979-5576-4116-ad7d-59a9e7cbe2fb Preheat the grill to medium heat.
5544a979-5576-4116-ad7d-59a9e7cbe2fb Fold the Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil for the Grill in half, making a rectangle that is about 8"x11", and place it onto the grill in the center.
5544a979-5576-4116-ad7d-59a9e7cbe2fb Place the graham crackers onto the foil and place the chocolate squares on top.
5544a979-5576-4116-ad7d-59a9e7cbe2fb Close the grill and cook for about 3 to 5 minutes until the chocolate has melted. Using a spatula, transfer the crackers to a plate.
5544a979-5576-4116-ad7d-59a9e7cbe2fb Scoop some ice cream over top of one of the crackers with chocolate, and then top with the other cracker and chocolate. You can also serve these open faced by just using one graham cracker and melted chocolate with one scoop of ice cream. Serve immediately.
f4c644f8-dd95-4263-b133-29259d727682 Make the pesto by combining the avocado, basil leaves, Parmesan, garlic, pistachios, salt and pepper in a blender. Pulse until the mixture is roughly chopped and then with the blender running, slowly stream in the olive oil. Continue blending until the pesto is a thick paste, scraping down the sides of the blender as needed. Set the pesto aside.
f4c644f8-dd95-4263-b133-29259d727682 Preheat the grill for 10 minutes on medium heat. Spread the butter on the corn, then wrap each ear of corn in Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Place the corn on the grill, close the lid and grill the corn, turning it frequently until it is tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Unwrap the corn and when cool enough to handle, slice the kernels off the cob.
f4c644f8-dd95-4263-b133-29259d727682 Brush both sides of the flatbreads with olive oil and grill them for 1 to 2 minutes on each side to warm them. Remove the flatbreads from the grill and top with the avocado pesto, Gruyère, mozzarella, red onions and corn. Return the flatbreads to the grill, close the lid and grill until the cheese is melted.
f4c644f8-dd95-4263-b133-29259d727682 Remove the flatbreads from the grill and transfer them to serving plates. Top the flatbreads with arugula and crushed red pepper flakes (optional) and then slice and serve immediately.
70ce04c3-826a-4fd7-8e17-0f9879724f01 PREHEAT grill to 450°F. Brush corn with 2 tablespoons olive oil. Transfer to the grill and char on all sides. Let cool, then remove charred corn from cob.
70ce04c3-826a-4fd7-8e17-0f9879724f01 CENTER each pizza crust on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Brush crusts with remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil.
70ce04c3-826a-4fd7-8e17-0f9879724f01 TOP each crust evenly with lime zest. Mix together parmesan cheese and chili powder then divide mixture evenly and sprinkle over each crust. Top each crust evenly with charred corn, garlic and cotija cheese.
70ce04c3-826a-4fd7-8e17-0f9879724f01 GRILL 8 to 10 minutes in covered grill over indirect heat.
70ce04c3-826a-4fd7-8e17-0f9879724f01 COMBINE mayonnaise, lime juice and chipotle chili pepper powder. Mix thoroughly to combine. Drizzle over cooked pizzas. Garnish with cilantro and serve immediately.
d26b178e-14d5-4bf3-987f-715d3384fb0c BEAT goat cheese, yogurt, honey and mint with an electric mixer until combined and smooth, about one minute. Set aside.
d26b178e-14d5-4bf3-987f-715d3384fb0c PREHEAT grill to 400°F. Brush both sides of watermelon with olive oil, then fully wrap each wedge in a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil.
d26b178e-14d5-4bf3-987f-715d3384fb0c GRILL for 5 minutes in covered grill over direct heat. Turn watermelon and grill additional 5 minutes or until watermelon is tender.
d26b178e-14d5-4bf3-987f-715d3384fb0c REMOVE from foil and serve immediately with a dollop of goat cheese mixture.
cf8138eb-94fa-44f6-b96f-b54a103d2546 COMBINE peanut butter, soy sauce, lime juice, brown sugar and ginger in a small saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently for 1 minute or until peanut butter is melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat and set aside.
cf8138eb-94fa-44f6-b96f-b54a103d2546 PREHEAT grill to 450°F. Roll or pat pizza dough into a 14-inch circle on a sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Brush dough with olive oil.
cf8138eb-94fa-44f6-b96f-b54a103d2546 SPREAD peanut sauce over the dough then sprinkle on red pepper flakes. Add garlic, chicken, carrots, snap peas, green onion, red cabbage, peanuts and mozzarella cheese.
cf8138eb-94fa-44f6-b96f-b54a103d2546 GRILL 15 to 20 minutes in covered grill over indirect heat. Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve immediately.
a129c6fa-4eac-4aae-bf10-8f2f1a5075ab MAKE the Carolina-Style Barbecue Sauce: Combine vinegar, brown sugar, ketchup, mustard, garlic, onion powder and salt in medium saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring often. Reduce heat and simmer until mixture has reduced by about 1/3, about 45 minutes.
a129c6fa-4eac-4aae-bf10-8f2f1a5075ab PREHEAT grill to 400°F. Place four 12-by-10-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil on your work surface with non-stick (dull) side toward food. Pour 1 cup of prepared barbecue sauce in a large bowl. Transfer the chicken leg quarters to bowl and completely cover with sauce.
a129c6fa-4eac-4aae-bf10-8f2f1a5075ab CENTER one chicken leg quarter on each sheet of foil. Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
a129c6fa-4eac-4aae-bf10-8f2f1a5075ab TRANSFER to the grill and cook for 20 minutes. Open each packet and baste with additional barbecue sauce. Close foil packets and continue cooking on the grill for 20 more minutes, or until a meat thermometer reaches 165°F and the juices run clear.
a129c6fa-4eac-4aae-bf10-8f2f1a5075ab REMOVE from grill and let rest for 10 minutes. Garnish with fresh parsley and serve with additional barbecue sauce.
a2d82b99-c8f0-44fd-9f5a-2fa1313a1676 Preheat a grill to medium high. Lay out four 12-by-18-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil on a work surface. Combine the tomatoes, beans, olive oil, wine, garlic, red pepper flakes, oregano, ¾ teaspoon salt and a few grinds of pepper in a large bowl. Stir well.
a2d82b99-c8f0-44fd-9f5a-2fa1313a1676 Drizzle the foil with olive oil. Evenly mound the kale in the center of each sheet. Season the halibut with salt and pepper and place on top of the kale. Add the mussels to the sheets, then spoon the tomato mixture on top. Bring the two short ends of the foil together and fold twice; fold in the sides to seal.
a2d82b99-c8f0-44fd-9f5a-2fa1313a1676 Grill the foil packets until the fish is cooked through and the mussels open, about 10 minutes. Carefully remove to a baking sheet. Grill the bread until lightly charred, 1 to 2 minutes per side. Drizzle the cut sides with olive oil and season with salt. Carefully open the foil packets; discard any unopened mussels. Sprinkle with the parsley and serve with the bread.
8211d9a6-d5f2-4e4e-b357-23e7ad33a7c1 Line a 4-quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds KITCHENS™ Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
8211d9a6-d5f2-4e4e-b357-23e7ad33a7c1 Stir together onion, ketchup, water, sugar, mustard, Worcestershire, vinegar, and pepper in slow cooker until blended. Stir in ham. Cover and cook on LOW until onions are tender, about 4 hours. Stir gently using a wooden or plastic utensil. Serve directly from lined slow cooker.
8211d9a6-d5f2-4e4e-b357-23e7ad33a7c1 Place 1/2 cup chipped ham on bottom half of each hamburger bun. Top each sandwich with 1 tablespoon relish and top half of bun.
fd1dd66d-742b-4892-ac34-76bd1dde7f38 Preheat your grill to medium-high heat (400–450 degrees F).
fd1dd66d-742b-4892-ac34-76bd1dde7f38 In a large bowl, combine all ingredients for the coconut sauce.
fd1dd66d-742b-4892-ac34-76bd1dde7f38 Tear off four large sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil. Place 9 shrimp in the center of each piece of foil, not overlapping. Fold up the edges of the foil to create a dish. Pour equal amounts of the coconut sauce into each foil pouch. Tightly crimp the edges of the foil pouch together. If there are any gaps in the foil, wrap in a second sheet to create a tight seal. Set aside.
fd1dd66d-742b-4892-ac34-76bd1dde7f38 Tear off one more sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil and fold up the edges to create a flat surface with rimmed edges (like a baking sheet) about 6 inches square. Spread the coconut out across the foil in a single layer.
fd1dd66d-742b-4892-ac34-76bd1dde7f38 Place the shrimp packets, the coconut tray, and the pineapple on the grill. Cook the pineapple for 2–3 minutes per side. Toast the coconut until golden brown, stirring as needed.
fd1dd66d-742b-4892-ac34-76bd1dde7f38 Grill the shrimp for 6–8 minutes, flipping once, or until the shrimp is opaque throughout and reads 145 degrees F with an internal thermometer (you can slightly open a pouch to check the temperature).
fd1dd66d-742b-4892-ac34-76bd1dde7f38 Open the pouches and sprinkle with the toasted coconut and cilantro (optional). Serve with the grilled pineapple straight out of the foil pouch. Delicious on its own or with cooked rice. Enjoy!
50a8e39a-d20e-4c91-947d-afaac90b5127 In a small mixing bowl, stir together brown sugar, lime juice, lime zest, butter and cayenne pepper.
50a8e39a-d20e-4c91-947d-afaac90b5127 Place salmon fillets in a dish. Spoon and spread lime mixture over tops and sides of salmon if using skin-on salmon. If using skinless, spread mixture over top and bottom of salmon (use up all of the mixture). Let marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.
50a8e39a-d20e-4c91-947d-afaac90b5127 Line a 13 by 9-inch baking dish with Reynolds Kitchens® Unbleached Parchment Paper.
50a8e39a-d20e-4c91-947d-afaac90b5127 Place salmon on parchment, leaving space between fillets. Season with salt and pepper.
50a8e39a-d20e-4c91-947d-afaac90b5127 Bake in preheated oven until salmon flakes easily with a fork, about 12–15 minutes (cook time will vary based on thickness of fillets).
50a8e39a-d20e-4c91-947d-afaac90b5127 Sprinkle with cilantro and serve warm with lime wedges for spritzing over salmon. Serve over coconut rice if desired.
60900d5b-0253-451a-b19f-96a659b355a3 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high.
60900d5b-0253-451a-b19f-96a659b355a3 TEAR off 4 12"x18" sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil.
60900d5b-0253-451a-b19f-96a659b355a3 For each packet, PLACE one halved chicken breast in center of each foil sheet and arrange broccoli around it. SPREAD one teaspoon garlic over each chicken breast, then top with 1 tablespoon of Parmesan cheese, 1/2 tablespoon of capers (optional) and top with two lemon slices. Add one tablespoon of butter on top of lemon slices.
60900d5b-0253-451a-b19f-96a659b355a3 BRING UP foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make 4 packets.
60900d5b-0253-451a-b19f-96a659b355a3 PLACE packets onto rimmed baking sheet.
60900d5b-0253-451a-b19f-96a659b355a3 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes in the oven or grill 12 to 14 minutes in covered grill.
60900d5b-0253-451a-b19f-96a659b355a3 REMOVE pan from oven or use tongs to slide hot packets from grill onto pan or plate. Open packets carefully by cutting along top folds with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape. Then open top of foil.
60900d5b-0253-451a-b19f-96a659b355a3 GARNISH with freshly chopped parsley before serving. (Optional).
e0aa0e78-b704-40a6-834c-7a972bd34721 Prepare and pre-bake the pastry according to package directions in an 11-inch tart pan with a removable bottom. Allow to cool slightly before filling.
e0aa0e78-b704-40a6-834c-7a972bd34721 Preheat oven to 375 degrees
e0aa0e78-b704-40a6-834c-7a972bd34721 Wash and slice the tomatoes and place on a paper towel lined plate to drain.
e0aa0e78-b704-40a6-834c-7a972bd34721 Cook onions in a skillet with a touch of olive oil until soft.
e0aa0e78-b704-40a6-834c-7a972bd34721 In a medium mixing bowl combine the eggs, milk, flour and chopped basil. Whisk until well blended.
e0aa0e78-b704-40a6-834c-7a972bd34721 Sprinkle the shredded cheese in the bottom of the baked crust. Layer half the tomatoes over the cheese. Pour the egg mixture over the tomatoes and cheese. Top with the remaining tomatoes and onions.
e0aa0e78-b704-40a6-834c-7a972bd34721 Bake for 30 minutes or until the egg mixture is set in the center. Tent the quiche with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil during baking if the crust browns too quickly.
e0aa0e78-b704-40a6-834c-7a972bd34721 Remove from the oven and allow the quiche to cool for 10-15 minutes before serving.
90324f29-dbab-4beb-913c-64447aca342c PREHEAT oven to 400°F. Add flour to a Reynolds Kitchens® Large Oven Bag. Shake. This helps prevent bag from bursting. Place bag in a 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
90324f29-dbab-4beb-913c-64447aca342c ADD rice, sweet potato, onion, 1 tablespoon butter, thyme, garlic, and pepper to oven bag. Turn bag several times to mix ingredients. Arrange ingredients in even layer in bag. Fold down bag opening two times to hold it open; set aside.
90324f29-dbab-4beb-913c-64447aca342c MICROWAVE chicken broth and wine in a medium microwave-safe bowl or measuring cup for 3 minutes on high power until liquid is hot (140°F). Carefully pour or ladle liquid over ingredients in bag. Carefully unfold bag opening.
90324f29-dbab-4beb-913c-64447aca342c CLOSE bag with tie (found inside package). Cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag to allow steam to escape. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
90324f29-dbab-4beb-913c-64447aca342c PLACE pan in oven, allowing room for bag to expand during cooking without touching heating elements, wall, or racks. Bag should not hang over pan.
90324f29-dbab-4beb-913c-64447aca342c BAKE 25 to 30 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed. Let stand 5 minutes.
90324f29-dbab-4beb-913c-64447aca342c CUT open top of oven bag carefully. Remember: Always support bag with pan.
90324f29-dbab-4beb-913c-64447aca342c SPOON rice mixture into a large serving bowl. Stir in remaining 1 tablespoon butter and 1/4 cup cheese. Sprinkle with additional cheese, if desired.
114d5400-26ed-4c1a-b18b-a2769132a86b Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Heat olive oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat. When hot, add the shallot and cook until slightly softened, about 3 minutes. Mix in the chopped garlic and cook for an additional minute, until fragrant. Add squash and water. Cover the pan and cook for about 15 to 20 minutes until squash has softened. Set aside.
114d5400-26ed-4c1a-b18b-a2769132a86b Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add flour and stir, cooking flour for about 1 minute. In a steady stream, pour in the milk and whisk vigorously until the sauce has thickened and is very smooth, about 5 to 7 minutes.
114d5400-26ed-4c1a-b18b-a2769132a86b Ladle about 1 cup of the béchamel sauce into a blender. Add the squash in batches, and blend until very smooth, adding more béchamel sauce if more liquid is needed. Be sure to allow steam to escape as you process. This can also be done with an immersion blender.
114d5400-26ed-4c1a-b18b-a2769132a86b Pour the butternut squash béchamel sauce mixture back into the pot holding the remaining béchamel sauce; stir until combined. In a small skillet, cook the chorizo over medium heat, breaking it up into crumbles as it cooks. Set aside.
114d5400-26ed-4c1a-b18b-a2769132a86b To assemble the lasagna, ladle about 1/4 cup of butternut squash béchamel sauce into the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish. Spread the sauce around evenly and top with 3 lasagna sheets, laying them side by side. Top with about 1/2 cup of the sauce, spreading it into one even layer. Then add a few spoonfuls of chorizo crumbles and a handful of Monterey Jack. Repeat the layering process a few more times until all but three lasagna sheets are used — about 3 layers. Finally, top the lasagna with the last 3 lasagna sheets a handful of Monterey Jack and all of the Parmesan cheese.
114d5400-26ed-4c1a-b18b-a2769132a86b Cover the baking dish with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil and bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees F. Uncover and transfer the lasagna to the broiler, cooking about 5 minutes until the top is golden brown. Slice and serve. Lasagna stays good in the refrigerator (and heats up nicely!) for up to 3 days.
76da9bb7-c177-4538-9fc3-c5aa529d16e4 Preheat the oven to 400°.
76da9bb7-c177-4538-9fc3-c5aa529d16e4 Place the butternut squash on a cookie sheet tray lined with parchment paper and drizzle on olive oil and bake in the oven for 45-60 minutes at 400° or until it is lightly browned and tender. Mash the squash using a hand masher until it is smooth and free of lumps. Set aside.
76da9bb7-c177-4538-9fc3-c5aa529d16e4 Melt the butter in a large pot over medium high heat and add in the onions and cook for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
76da9bb7-c177-4538-9fc3-c5aa529d16e4 Sprinkle the flour over the onions and stir until combined.
76da9bb7-c177-4538-9fc3-c5aa529d16e4 Pour in the milk and whisk over medium heat until it becomes thick.
76da9bb7-c177-4538-9fc3-c5aa529d16e4 Whisk 6 ounces of the cheese into the milk mixture until combined. Season with salt and pepper.
76da9bb7-c177-4538-9fc3-c5aa529d16e4 Transfer the mixture to a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Bakeware pan and mix together with the noodles until combined. Sprinkle the remaining cheese and bread crumbs over top of the mixture.
76da9bb7-c177-4538-9fc3-c5aa529d16e4 Bake in the oven at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until the top is lightly browned and the mac n cheese is firm. Garnish with fresh chopped sage.
0d82ebca-d3a5-440a-9642-46eb8f9c7f60 PREHEAT oven to 400 degrees F. Place Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
0d82ebca-d3a5-440a-9642-46eb8f9c7f60 ADD corn starch, honey, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to oven bag. Squeeze bag to mix ingredients.
0d82ebca-d3a5-440a-9642-46eb8f9c7f60 SLICE pork tenderloin 1-inch thick. Place pork and asparagus in bag. Turn bag several times to coat pork and asparagus with sauce. Place ingredients in an even layer.
0d82ebca-d3a5-440a-9642-46eb8f9c7f60 CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
0d82ebca-d3a5-440a-9642-46eb8f9c7f60 BAKE 12 to 14 minutes or until pork reads 145 degrees F on thermometer. Let stand 5 minutes. Carefully cut bag open and serve. Garnish if desired.
e309a18b-46fd-4be9-a7d0-0bae385e2fd2 Line your slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens®​ Slow Cooker Liner. Place the pork, soda, garlic, chili powder, oregano, and Worcestershire sauce in the crockpot. Cover and cook on high for 4-5 hours or low for 6-8 hours.
e309a18b-46fd-4be9-a7d0-0bae385e2fd2 When the meat falls apart easily, remove the meat from the slow cooker liner and transfer to a cutting board. Shred it with two forks. Place meat back in the lined slow cooker and add the balsamic dressing and stir with the liquid in the crockpot. The meat should be saucy and moist.
e309a18b-46fd-4be9-a7d0-0bae385e2fd2 Preheat the oven to 400°F (or use the broil setting if available) and transfer the mixture to a baking sheet lined with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Spread it in an even, thin layer and cook in the preheated oven until the juices are bubbling and the edges are crispy, 10-15 minutes (5-7 minutes if you have a broil setting).
e309a18b-46fd-4be9-a7d0-0bae385e2fd2 Transfer to a serving platter and enjoy on sandwiches or with a baked potato.
a43e5c61-ce64-438e-b3f1-ce0dcefbeb4f PREHEAT oven to 400F. Place Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag in 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Add flour, thyme, salt and pepper to bag; squeeze bag to blend seasonings.
a43e5c61-ce64-438e-b3f1-ce0dcefbeb4f ADD Brussels sprouts and butter to oven bag. Turn bag several times to mix. Arrange Brussels sprouts in an even layer.
a43e5c61-ce64-438e-b3f1-ce0dcefbeb4f CLOSE bag with nylon tie. Cut six -inch slits in top. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
a43e5c61-ce64-438e-b3f1-ce0dcefbeb4f BAKE 15 to 20 minutes or until Brussels sprouts are tender. Carefully cut bag open.
a43e5c61-ce64-438e-b3f1-ce0dcefbeb4f SPOON Brussels sprouts into medium serving bowl immediately; sprinkle Brussels sprouts with blue cheese and bacon. Cover with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil and let sit 5 minutes. Stir and serve.
ce75a3fd-0ab2-4032-a25f-16a1fde3fab5 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line two baking sheets with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil; set aside.
ce75a3fd-0ab2-4032-a25f-16a1fde3fab5 SCRUB sweet potatoes and pierce all over with a fork. Wrap each potato in a piece of aluminum foil and place on prepared pan.
ce75a3fd-0ab2-4032-a25f-16a1fde3fab5 BAKE potatoes for 1 hour or until tender. Set aside to cool slightly.
ce75a3fd-0ab2-4032-a25f-16a1fde3fab5 PLACE the walnuts on one of the prepared baking sheets. Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until walnuts are lightly toasted.
ce75a3fd-0ab2-4032-a25f-16a1fde3fab5 CUT each potato in half lengthwise. Using a spoon, scoop pulp from each potato half, leaving 1/4-inch shells. In a medium bowl combine the pulp, goat cheese, butter, and ¼ teaspoon salt. Using a potato masher or fork, mash until smooth. Spoon potato mixture into the potato shells.
ce75a3fd-0ab2-4032-a25f-16a1fde3fab5 BAKE, uncovered, on a foil-lined baking sheet 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
ce75a3fd-0ab2-4032-a25f-16a1fde3fab5 SPRINKLE toasted walnuts, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and sage over the tops of the sweet potatoes. Drizzle with olive oil. Serve immediately.
d6af95cb-aade-48b8-8eab-22c9da51d8dd PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line an 11 by 18-inch sheet pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Build separate foil trays by folding a large piece of foil in half, and folding up the edges to create three trays; one taking up about ½ of the tray to hold the turkey and stuffing, and two smaller equal trays to each hold the string beans and sweet potatoes. Fit the largest one into the left half of the baking sheet. Set aside.
d6af95cb-aade-48b8-8eab-22c9da51d8dd PREPARE the stuffing: In a large bowl, mix the stuffing ingredients until well incorporated. Let soak for 15 minutes, and spread an even layer into the largest foil pan, making a well in the center for the turkey.
d6af95cb-aade-48b8-8eab-22c9da51d8dd PREPARE the turkey: In a small bowl, mix together the melted butter with the sage, thyme and garlic. Season the turkey breast well with salt and pepper, and rub the turkey with the butter mixture. Nestle turkey breast in the center of the stuffing. Place in oven, and cook for 30 minutes.
d6af95cb-aade-48b8-8eab-22c9da51d8dd PREPARE the sweet potatoes: In a medium bowl, toss all of the sweet potato ingredients together to coat. Spread the sweet potatoes out in one of the small foil pans, letting them overlap to show the layers.
d6af95cb-aade-48b8-8eab-22c9da51d8dd PREPARE the green beans: In a medium bowl, toss together all the green beans ingredients and spread out in the remaining foil pan.
d6af95cb-aade-48b8-8eab-22c9da51d8dd REMOVE sheet pan from oven, and add the two smaller foil pans with the sweet potatoes and green beans. Continue cooking until the sweet potatoes and green beans are tender and the turkey reads 165°F on an instant-read thermometer when inserted, another 30-40 minutes. If the green beans are finished sooner, simply remove the foil tray and set aside until turkey is done.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc PREHEAT oven to 375F.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc WASH and scrub sweet potatoes. Poke deep holes into each sweet potato. Brush with olive oil, then wrap each in Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Transfer to one half of a sheet pan.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc STUFF the cavity of each Cornish hen with lemon and rosemary. Brush the skins with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Transfer both hens into a large Reynolds Kitchens® Oven Bag, then place on the same sheet pan as the sweet potatoes on the opposite side of the pan. Transfer to bottom rack of the oven. We recommend placing the Oven Bag in a pan with at least a 2” lip, such as a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Pan.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc START the stuffing. Line a baking sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper. Melt the butter in a skillet; add the onion, celery, garlic, pumpkin seeds, sage and rosemary. Cook over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes. Add stock and continue cooking until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in salt and pepper. Toss the bread in the beaten egg, the place bread pieces in the bottom of a greased 6-cavity muffin tin. Pour the vegetable/stock mixture on top.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc PLACE the stuffing cups on one-side of a parchment lined baking sheet. Transfer to the top rack of the oven and set the timer for 30 minutes.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc START brussel sprouts. While the above items are cooking, wash, then chop brussel sprouts in half. Toss in olive oil and season with salt and salt and pepper. Set aside.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc REMOVE stuffing cups from the oven with the 30 minute time is up. Cover the stuffing cups with foil, then add the brussel sprouts to the opposite side of the pan. Return to the oven on the lower rack, and move the Cornish hen and sweet potatoes to the top rack and continue cooking for an additional 30 minutes.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc START the mashed potatoes. While the above items are cooking, peel and chop russet potatoes. Boil potatoes and cook until tender. Drain water and transfer to a medium bowl. Add butter, milk, garlic, and salt and pepper to taste. Mash until thick and fluffy. Cover with foil and set aside.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc REMOVE both sheet pans from the oven when the 30-minute timer is up. Check the Cornish hen to ensure chicken is tender and juices run clear or meat thermometer reads 170°F for breasts, 180°F for other pieces. Remove from sheet pan and let rest for 10 min. (*note return Cornish hen to oven if longer baking time is needed).
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc PEEL back the foil on the sweet potatoes. Using a knife cut down the center of each potato and push the ends together. Add brown sugar, pecans and marshmallow. Pull the foil back over and return to the oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc TRANSFER roasted brussel sprouts to a serving dish. Top each of the stuffing cups with mashed potatoes. Transfer the cooked Cornish hens to dinner plates.
2d30fee1-19e6-47bd-a6ec-482a3ca7bddc REMOVE sweet potatoes from oven and serve with the rest of the prepared meal.
fb4ac8cc-4352-483f-bba9-02a03901044c PREHEAT oven to 350°F. SHAKE flour in a Reynolds Kitchens® Turkey Oven Bag and place in large roasting pan at least 2 inches deep. Spray inside of bag with nonstick spray to reduce sticking, if desired.
fb4ac8cc-4352-483f-bba9-02a03901044c MIX chicken broth, basil, thyme and pepper; set aside. Remove neck and giblets from turkey. Rinse turkey; pat dry. Brush turkey with oil. Place turkey in oven bag. Pour broth mixture over turkey.
fb4ac8cc-4352-483f-bba9-02a03901044c CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Insert meat thermometer through slit in bag into thickest part of inner thigh. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
fb4ac8cc-4352-483f-bba9-02a03901044c BAKE until meat thermometer reads 180°F, 2 to 2 1/2 hours for a 12 to 16 lb. turkey; 2 1/2 to 3 hours for a 16 to 20 lb. turkey; and 3 to 3 1/2 hours for a 20 to 24 lb. turkey. Add 1/2 hour for stuffed turkey.Let stand in oven bag 15 minutes. If turkey sticks to bag, gently loosen bag from turkey.
2c4a08b4-04a7-454a-a6c1-17e565d49c06 PREHEAT oven to 375°F.
2c4a08b4-04a7-454a-a6c1-17e565d49c06 PLACE a 24-inch long piece Reynolds Kitchens® Unbleached Parchment Paper on to your work surface. Place the biscuit dough on top and sprinkle with flour. Using a rolling pin, roll the dough into an 18-inch by 8-inch rectangle.
2c4a08b4-04a7-454a-a6c1-17e565d49c06 SPREAD preserves onto the prepared dough. Sprinkle on walnuts, then top with Brie cheese.
2c4a08b4-04a7-454a-a6c1-17e565d49c06 STARTING at the 18-inch side, roll up the dough and pinch edges together to seal. Cut into 12, 1 1/2-inch slices. Transfer to 8x8-inch Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Pan.
2c4a08b4-04a7-454a-a6c1-17e565d49c06 BAKE 30 to 35 minutes or until rolls are golden. Cool on a wire rack for 15 minutes before serving.
0de4b614-333e-4505-8b5d-e2aca0db3e44 In a large bowl, toss the potatoes with olive oil, garlic powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and black pepper to taste. Toss evenly to coat.
0de4b614-333e-4505-8b5d-e2aca0db3e44 Transfer to a large sheet, 18 x 18 inches, of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil on a flat surface.
0de4b614-333e-4505-8b5d-e2aca0db3e44 Place the ingredients in the center of the Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil. Form a packet by bringing two ends of the foil together and fold twice to seal, leaving room for steam.
0de4b614-333e-4505-8b5d-e2aca0db3e44 TO GRILL: Grill covered over medium heat for 30 minutes, shaking the bag every 10 minutes so the bottom of the potatoes don’t burn. Open carefully and top with 1/8 teaspoon salt, lemon zest and parsley.
0de4b614-333e-4505-8b5d-e2aca0db3e44 IN THE OVEN: Bake in a preheated 400° F oven for 35 to 40 minutes, shaking the bag halfway through. Open carefully and top with 1/8 teaspoon salt, lemon zest and parsley.
38cc2dd3-960d-4865-abe3-0a312a5ae07d FOR SPAGHETTI SQUASH: Pierce the squashes down the middle of one side with the tines of a fork. Place on a plate (one at a time) and microwave for 5 minutes. Remove, let cool until able to handle. Cut off the stem and base. Then cut the squash in half, lengthwise, with a sharp knife. Scoop out the seeds and discard. Drizzle each side of squash with oil (I use about 1 tablespoon per half of squash) and sprinkle to taste with salt and pepper. Place on a parchment paper-lined sheet pan cut side down. Roast at 400 F for 35–45 minutes on the bottom rack of the oven or until fork tender (easily pierced with a fork).
38cc2dd3-960d-4865-abe3-0a312a5ae07d FOR MEATBALLS: Preheat the oven to 400 F. Using the large holes on a cheese grater, grate an onion until you have 2/3 a cup. Add to a very large bowl. Finely mince OR grate the garlic on a microplane and add to the bowl. Add the salt, paprika, oregano, basil, pepper, finely chopped parsley (measured AFTER being chopped), finely grated Parmesan cheese (I like to use a microplane here to grate the Parmesan), Panko, egg, and Worcestershire sauce. Stir until all the ingredients are well combined. Add in the ground turkey straight from the fridge (keep the turkey as cold as possible as it's easier to work with). Gently knead the ingredients until combined, being careful to not overwork the meat. This will yield tough/rubbery meatballs.
38cc2dd3-960d-4865-abe3-0a312a5ae07d MEATBALLS CONTINUED: Shape the meat mixture into meatballs. I use a 1/8th measuring cup (2 tablespoons) to ensure meatballs all end up the same size. Place measured balls on a large plate and refrigerate the first half while working on forming the last half of the meat into meatballs.
38cc2dd3-960d-4865-abe3-0a312a5ae07d BAKING: Line a large sheet pan with parchment paper (don't skip or cleanup is a lot harder!). Add a wire cooling rack right on top and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange meatballs on the rack. Brush the meatballs with oil (about 2-3 teaspoons total). Bake until browned, on the top rack of the oven, about 15 to 20 minutes. A thermometer should read 160 F. (Carry-over heat will increase it to 165 F).
38cc2dd3-960d-4865-abe3-0a312a5ae07d SERVE: Using a fork, pull the strands from the cooled spaghetti squash and transfer to a plate OR serve right in the squash. Prepare homemade marinara or use store bought (you’ll need about 3 cups); toss meatballs with marinara and top squash with the meatballs. If desired, garnish with fresh parsley and freshly grated Parmesan cheese. Add additional cracked pepper and a drizzle of olive oil to plates if desired.
bf153eb4-6f33-4ff7-bbf5-7f8787cfeb0c PREP: Line a slow cooker (5 quarts or larger) with one Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Set aside.
bf153eb4-6f33-4ff7-bbf5-7f8787cfeb0c COOK MEAT: Heat a large cast iron skillet over medium-high heat. Add the sausage. Let cook without touching for 30 seconds to a minute to get a nice browning and then use a wooden spoon to break it up and continue to cook until nicely browned through. Transfer the sausage to the slow cooker OR to a paper towel lined plate to slightly drain off grease if desired. To the same pot, add in the diced onions. If needed add a drizzle of olive oil (if there wasn't a lot of grease left from the sausage). Cook, over medium-high heat, stirring until softened and tender, about 4–5 minutes. Add the garlic and stir until fragrant, about 30 seconds to a minute. Add right on top of the sausage.
bf153eb4-6f33-4ff7-bbf5-7f8787cfeb0c POTATOES: Peel and dice potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces and then add in an even layer right on top of the sausage, onion and garlic. Press all the ingredients into an even layer and then cover with chicken stock. If all ingredients aren't completely covered, add water until they are (up to 1 cup total).
bf153eb4-6f33-4ff7-bbf5-7f8787cfeb0c COOK: Cover and cook on LOW for 5-6 hours or HIGH for 3-4 hours or until potatoes are fork tender. Before the soup is finished, wash the kale and remove it from the stem. Dice it and pack into a measuring cups to get 2 cups total. Stir into the soup along with the heavy cream, red pepper flakes, thyme, and seasonings to taste (I add 1/2 teaspoon salt and heaping 1/4 teaspoon pepper, add to preference, remembering that bacon and Parmesan add a good amount of saltiness). Let cook for 15 more minutes and then taste and adjust any seasonings. While it’s finishing cooking, cook the bacon in a skillet until it’s reached desired crispiness. Drain onto a paper towel-lined plate and serve alongside the soup.
bf153eb4-6f33-4ff7-bbf5-7f8787cfeb0c SERVE: Serve with desired toppings: freshly grated Parmesan cheese (grate on a microplane for the best texture!) and a crusty toasted baguette or bread. Sprinkle bacon on top of the soup and enjoy.
8ca21530-240c-417f-8f31-b380e7be0bea Heat broiler on high, with rack in the second position about 6 inches from the flame. Line a half-sheet pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil.
8ca21530-240c-417f-8f31-b380e7be0bea In a medium bowl combine the turkey with celery, mayonnaise, cranberries and red onion, and stir until combined.
8ca21530-240c-417f-8f31-b380e7be0bea Arrange the toasted bread on a baking sheet and divide the turkey salad evenly among slices, then top each with 1 ounce of cheese.
8ca21530-240c-417f-8f31-b380e7be0bea Broil about 6 inches from the flame until the cheese is golden and bubbling, about 2 to 3 minutes, keeping a close eye on it to avoid burning.
68ff75db-c1fd-43a5-a0cc-aaa02261bd8b Knead dough/crust ingredients together, wrap in Reynolds Kitchens® Quick Cut® Plastic Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
68ff75db-c1fd-43a5-a0cc-aaa02261bd8b Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
68ff75db-c1fd-43a5-a0cc-aaa02261bd8b Divide the dough into 2 even sections. Roll dough/crust out on a flat surface sprinkled with powdered sugar (not flour) to 1/4-inch thickness in a circle.
68ff75db-c1fd-43a5-a0cc-aaa02261bd8b Place filling ingredients in medium saucepan and cook on low heat until chocolate is melted.
68ff75db-c1fd-43a5-a0cc-aaa02261bd8b Spread chocolate filling evenly over the top of the dough circles.
68ff75db-c1fd-43a5-a0cc-aaa02261bd8b Roll up and put each log on an ungreased cookie sheet.
68ff75db-c1fd-43a5-a0cc-aaa02261bd8b Bake 20 minutes.
68ff75db-c1fd-43a5-a0cc-aaa02261bd8b Allow to cool 30 minutes and slice into even cookies.
5537da88-805f-4a53-bc39-a624121e82d1 Turn your slow cooker on to warm. Line your slow cooker with one Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
5537da88-805f-4a53-bc39-a624121e82d1 With the slow cooker lined, add all of the ingredients into the slow cooker except the kale and the lime. Stir to combine.
5537da88-805f-4a53-bc39-a624121e82d1 Set the slow cooker on high for 3 hours or on low for 6 hours (for high, monitor the last 30 minutes and for low, monitor the last hour).
5537da88-805f-4a53-bc39-a624121e82d1 At the end, stir in the kale and lime juice and let it cook for about 5 more minutes.
4a9ec5d4-f7c7-4645-9404-3a6c12e136fb Preheat the oven to 350˚F. In a large skillet on medium heat, brown your beef. When there is no pink, add 4 tablespoons taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water, and cook for an additional 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
4a9ec5d4-f7c7-4645-9404-3a6c12e136fb Tear off four 16-inch-long pieces of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Place a handful of tortilla chips in the center of the sheet, top with a heaping 1/4 cup Mexican cheese, then cover with 1/4 of the ground beef mixture followed by another 1/4 cup of cheese. Bring up and double-fold the long ends, leaving room for air to circulate. Bring up and double-fold the short ends to close your foil packet.
4a9ec5d4-f7c7-4645-9404-3a6c12e136fb Just before serving, place on a baking sheet and bake at 350˚F for 10 minutes. Prep all of your toppings so they are ready to serve over hot nachos. Open the foil packs, add desired toppings and serve immediately.
00fb12d0-3812-45dc-8956-41f21dd94de7 Line your slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
00fb12d0-3812-45dc-8956-41f21dd94de7 Stir together the spice ingredients in a large bowl. Add the wings and toss to fully combine.
00fb12d0-3812-45dc-8956-41f21dd94de7 Add the rubbed wings to the slow cooker.
00fb12d0-3812-45dc-8956-41f21dd94de7 Using the same bowl, stir together all of the sauce ingredients except the cornstarch. Pour the sauce over the wings and toss.
00fb12d0-3812-45dc-8956-41f21dd94de7 Cook on high for 2 hours, or on low for 3 to 4 hours, until the wings reach an internal temperature of 165°F.
00fb12d0-3812-45dc-8956-41f21dd94de7 Remove the wings from the slow cooker (leaving the sauce) and place in a large bowl. Stir the cornstarch into 2 tablespoons cold water, and then add to the sauce mixture inside the slow cooker. Stir to combine.
00fb12d0-3812-45dc-8956-41f21dd94de7 Cook the sauce on high for 10 more minutes. Pour the thickened sauce over the wings and toss to coat.
11792bb3-4eeb-4588-a619-6f6eee610ec8 LINE a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of the bowl; pull to of liner over rim of bowl.
11792bb3-4eeb-4588-a619-6f6eee610ec8
11792bb3-4eeb-4588-a619-6f6eee610ec8 COMBINE chicken, beans, corn, onion, garlic, cumin, salt, and pepper in the slow cooker. Pour broth and salsa Verde over mixture.
11792bb3-4eeb-4588-a619-6f6eee610ec8
11792bb3-4eeb-4588-a619-6f6eee610ec8 COVER and cook 8 to 10 hours on LOW OR 4 to 5 hours on HIGH.
11792bb3-4eeb-4588-a619-6f6eee610ec8
11792bb3-4eeb-4588-a619-6f6eee610ec8 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Stir in sour cream and cheese. Sprinkle with jalapeño, if desired. Serve chili directly from lined slow cooker, topped with additional shredded cheese, if desired. Remove all food and cool slow cooker completely before removing liner from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561 LINE a 5-to 6-quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561 TRIM any large pieces of fat from chicken thighs. Add chicken to lined slow cooker; sprinkle with half the salt and pepper. Add onion, garlic, jalapeño, orange juice, lime juice, soy sauce, cumin, and the remaining salt and pepper evenly over chicken.
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561 COVER and cook 2 to 3 hours on HIGH OR 4 to 5 hours on LOW, until chicken at least 165°F and the chicken shreds easily with a fork.
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561 CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Change slow cooker setting to Warm. Use a slotted spoon to transfer chicken from the slow cooker liner to a large bowl or cutting board. Shred into bite-size chunks. Ladle some juices onto to shredded chicken, if desired. Discard the remaining juices.
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561 Spoon shredded chicken back into lined slow cooker. Season with additional salt, pepper, and cumin, if desired.
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561
56e65442-7799-4838-8ae6-11caa0ede561 Serve directly from slow cooker liner using a wooden or plastic utensil to spoon chicken onto warm tortillas. Top with diced red onion, chopped cilantro, and a squeeze of fresh lime juice. Remove all food and cool slow cooker completely before removing liner from slow cooker. Do no lift or transport liner with food inside.
914a8aab-af75-40b5-803b-414f5b66aa8b Line a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Place onions and sweet peppers on the bottom of cooker. Place beef on top of the vegetables, trimming to fit as needed.
914a8aab-af75-40b5-803b-414f5b66aa8b LINE a 5 to 6 quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of the bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
914a8aab-af75-40b5-803b-414f5b66aa8b PLACE onions and sweet peppers on the bottom of cooker. Place beef on top of the vegetables, trimming to fit as needed. In a medium bowl, combine tomato paste, brown sugar, water, vinegar, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, and dry mustard. Pour sauce over meat in cooker.
914a8aab-af75-40b5-803b-414f5b66aa8b COVER and cook 9 to 10 hours on LOW OR 5 to 6 hours on HIGH until beef is fork tender.
914a8aab-af75-40b5-803b-414f5b66aa8b CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Transfer meat to a platter or a shallow dish. Skim fat from vegetable mixture. Serve beef with vegetables and mashed potatoes. Remove all food and cool slow cooker completely before removing liner. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.
f4f85f71-9b81-468f-a5ae-6246827ff751 LINE a 5 to 6 quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim.
f4f85f71-9b81-468f-a5ae-6246827ff751
f4f85f71-9b81-468f-a5ae-6246827ff751 PLACE chicken and sausage in the lined slow cooker. Sprinkle with seasonings. Pour in diced tomatoes. Top with vegetables.
f4f85f71-9b81-468f-a5ae-6246827ff751
f4f85f71-9b81-468f-a5ae-6246827ff751 COVER and COOK 7 to 8 hours on LOW OR 3 to 4 hours on HIGH, until chicken is done. Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Add cooked shrimp; stir with wooden or plastic spoon to mix. Cook 10 minutes longer on LOW.
f4f85f71-9b81-468f-a5ae-6246827ff751
f4f85f71-9b81-468f-a5ae-6246827ff751 SPOON Jambalaya directly from lined-slow cooker into bowls of cooked rice. Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Remove all food and cool slow cooker completely before removing liner from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.
f4f85f71-9b81-468f-a5ae-6246827ff751
17fce277-44d4-47d7-8214-b7ccf132cf95 Line a 5-to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
17fce277-44d4-47d7-8214-b7ccf132cf95 Cover and cook for about 6-8 hours on low, or 3-4 hours on high, or until the squash is completely tender and mashes easily with a fork.
17fce277-44d4-47d7-8214-b7ccf132cf95 Remove bay leaf and discard. Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Transfer contents from slow cooker liner to a blender using a wooden or plastic utensil. Blend until smooth.
17fce277-44d4-47d7-8214-b7ccf132cf95 When smooth, pour contents back into the slow cooker liner and add in salt, pepper, sage and coconut milk. Stir with a wooden or plastic utensil. Taste and then add more salt and pepper as needed.
17fce277-44d4-47d7-8214-b7ccf132cf95 Serve directly from slow cooker liner using a wooden or plastic utensil. Enjoy with croutons or crusty bread.
17fce277-44d4-47d7-8214-b7ccf132cf95 Cool slow cooker completely; remove empty liner and toss. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.
7f206cd9-51af-4b05-a16e-0e03a62943ae Line a 5-to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
7f206cd9-51af-4b05-a16e-0e03a62943ae Add beer, onions, maple syrup, vinegar, caraway seeds, thyme, and Worcestershire sauce to the lined slow cooker. Stir gently with a rubber spatula to combine. Place bratwurst on top of the mixture in cooker.
7f206cd9-51af-4b05-a16e-0e03a62943ae Cover and cook for 4 hours on high or for 8 hours on low.
