7f206cd9-51af-4b05-a16e-0e03a62943ae Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Serve directly from slow cooker liner using a wooden or plastic utensil. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss.
7f206cd9-51af-4b05-a16e-0e03a62943ae Serve bratwursts and onions in toasted buns topped with cheese and lettuce, if desired.
64ed7726-54ae-4700-8d08-632d576c298c Open Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner and place it inside a 3- to 4-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
64ed7726-54ae-4700-8d08-632d576c298c Place cubed cheese product, chicken, tomatoes and green chilies, and cumin (if desired) into slow cooker liner. Place lid on slow cooker.
64ed7726-54ae-4700-8d08-632d576c298c Cook on low for 2 hours or until cheese is melted. Set slow cooker control to warm setting.
64ed7726-54ae-4700-8d08-632d576c298c Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Add green onions; stir gently to mix all ingredients. Serve dip directly from slow cooker liner using a wooden or plastic utensil. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss. Estimate 2 tablespoons per serving.
bf86b917-1ad8-4ace-9d1b-94b6504af60f LINE a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
bf86b917-1ad8-4ace-9d1b-94b6504af60f ADD squash, broth, pears, cider, carrots, onion, and garlic to the prepared slow cooker. Stir gently with a rubber spatula to combine.
bf86b917-1ad8-4ace-9d1b-94b6504af60f COVER and cook for 4 hours on high or for 8 hours on low.
bf86b917-1ad8-4ace-9d1b-94b6504af60f STIR in cream and pepper. Let soup cool slightly. When cool enough, ladle soup into a blender or food processor bowl, working in batches if necessary. Puree to desired consistency.
bf86b917-1ad8-4ace-9d1b-94b6504af60f TOP with Polenta Croutons to serve, if desired
37f1a193-b645-481f-8685-6274ed721d18 Place Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner in slow cooker as directed on package. Place squash in slow cooker; top with tomatoes, onions and peppers. Pour dressing over ingredients in slow cooker; top with chicken. Cover with lid.
37f1a193-b645-481f-8685-6274ed721d18 Cook on LOW 8 to 9 hours (or on HIGH 4 to 6 hours).
37f1a193-b645-481f-8685-6274ed721d18 Remove chicken from slow cooker; cool slightly. Pull into shreds with 2 forks. Return to slow cooker; mix well. Serve over rice topped with sour cream and cilantro.
fd04f890-bf5f-4072-9fca-a6030a5651c0 LINE a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
fd04f890-bf5f-4072-9fca-a6030a5651c0 COMBINE ground turkey, bread crumbs, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 1/4 cup of the onion, and the egg in a large bowl. Mix well. Shape mixture into 1-inch meatballs.
fd04f890-bf5f-4072-9fca-a6030a5651c0 ADD broth, undrained tomatoes, celery, carrots, and remaining 1/4 cup onion to the prepared slow cooker. Stir gently with a rubber spatula to combine. Place meatballs on top of the mixture in cooker.
fd04f890-bf5f-4072-9fca-a6030a5651c0 COVER and cook for 4 hours on high or for 8 hours on low.
fd04f890-bf5f-4072-9fca-a6030a5651c0 ADD the noodles; stir gently and cook for 10 more minutes.
fd04f890-bf5f-4072-9fca-a6030a5651c0 SERVE with additional Parmesan cheese and parsley, if desired.
65ae2751-f2aa-40bd-bf0d-22168d2e8479 LINE a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
65ae2751-f2aa-40bd-bf0d-22168d2e8479 ADD broth, chicken, cauliflower, carrots, onion, curry powder, ginger, and garlic to the prepared slow cooker. Stir gently with a rubber spatula to combine.
65ae2751-f2aa-40bd-bf0d-22168d2e8479 COVER and cook for 4 hours on high or for 8 hours on low.
65ae2751-f2aa-40bd-bf0d-22168d2e8479 STIR in coconut milk and peas. Cover and cook about 10 minutes more or until heated through.
65ae2751-f2aa-40bd-bf0d-22168d2e8479 TOP with cilantro to serve. If desired, serve with hot cooked rice.
fa7af95a-baf3-4178-8a67-0b585c4793be LINE a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner; set aside.
fa7af95a-baf3-4178-8a67-0b585c4793be ADD the roasted peppers, broth, beans, tomatoes, artichoke hearts, celery, onions, olive oil, and garlic to the lined-slow cooker. Stir gently with a wooden spoon or rubber scrapper to combine.
fa7af95a-baf3-4178-8a67-0b585c4793be COVER and cook on high for 5 hours.
fa7af95a-baf3-4178-8a67-0b585c4793be STIR in Swiss chard and tortellini gently with a rubber spatula and cook 7 to 9 minutes more or until pasta is just al dente. Serve with Parmesan cheese and Parmesan Crisps, if desired.
2648635f-b343-41e7-9496-a999a17ab1cf LINE a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner.
2648635f-b343-41e7-9496-a999a17ab1cf ADD beans, sweet potatoes, orange juice, sweet pepper, carrots, onion, jalapeño pepper, chili powder, cumin, and garlic to the prepared slow cooker. Stir gently with a rubber spatula to combine.
2648635f-b343-41e7-9496-a999a17ab1cf COVER and cook for 4 hours on high or for 8 hours on low.
2648635f-b343-41e7-9496-a999a17ab1cf SERVE with cheese, if desired.
6c32f961-7051-430a-bbd6-71fe2acd20e4 Line a 5-to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
6c32f961-7051-430a-bbd6-71fe2acd20e4 Whisk together eggs, milk, cream, sugar, pecans, cranberries, cocoa powder, vanilla, and cinnamon in a large bowl.
6c32f961-7051-430a-bbd6-71fe2acd20e4 Stir in chocolate and bread and let it sit for five minutes.
6c32f961-7051-430a-bbd6-71fe2acd20e4 Pour mixture into a lined slow cooker and cover. Cook for 2 to 3 hours on high or 4 to 6 hours on low, until center temperature reaches 160°F and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
6c32f961-7051-430a-bbd6-71fe2acd20e4 Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Let sit with lid off for 10 minutes before serving.
6c32f961-7051-430a-bbd6-71fe2acd20e4 Serve directly from slow cooker liner using a wooden or plastic utensil. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove empty liner and toss.
6c32f961-7051-430a-bbd6-71fe2acd20e4 Serve warm with whipped topping.
cda8efb3-23a6-4b0a-8677-4b35585fe98d LINE a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker with a Regular size Reynolds Kitchens® Slow Cooker Liner. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.
cda8efb3-23a6-4b0a-8677-4b35585fe98d COAT the beef with flour. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until beef is browned; set aside. Add the beans, carrots, onion, garlic and browned beef to the lined slow cooker. Gently stir in tomatoes, broth, chili powder, cumin, salt, and pepper with a wooden or plastic spoon.
cda8efb3-23a6-4b0a-8677-4b35585fe98d
cda8efb3-23a6-4b0a-8677-4b35585fe98d COVER and cook 3 to 4 hours on HIGH OR 6 to 7 hours on LOW, until the beef is fork-tender.
cda8efb3-23a6-4b0a-8677-4b35585fe98d CAREFULLY remove lid to allow steam to escape. Gently stir in the corn. Cover and cook 10 minutes longer or until corn is heated through.
cda8efb3-23a6-4b0a-8677-4b35585fe98d
cda8efb3-23a6-4b0a-8677-4b35585fe98d SERVE stew directly from lined slow cooker. Top with avocado, cilantro, and/or crushed red pepper, if desired. Remove all food and cool slow cooker completely before removing liner from slow cooker. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside.
45738c7a-2136-4dbf-a2f9-212aba66c351 Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Line two 18x13x1-inch baking pans with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
45738c7a-2136-4dbf-a2f9-212aba66c351 Place a sheet of Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper on your work surface. Thaw puff pasty dough as indicated on the package instructions. Transfer to parchment paper and cut each sheet of pastry into 6 4x3-inch rectangles.
45738c7a-2136-4dbf-a2f9-212aba66c351 Melt the butter in a large pot. Add the mushrooms, onions and garlic and cook 3 to 4 minutes. Add the spinach and continue cooking, stirring often until wilted, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and drain any liquid from the pan. Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
45738c7a-2136-4dbf-a2f9-212aba66c351 Brush each piece of puff pastry with egg. Spoon mixture into the center of each of the puff pastry pieces. Pull the short ends of each piece together. Pinch to create seam, then pinch together both sides to fully enclose. Crimp or roll the edges. Transfer to prepared baking sheet and brush with egg.
45738c7a-2136-4dbf-a2f9-212aba66c351 Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
c45a5423-3896-423c-ad75-c76ef22e3da5 Cook the pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water for 10 to 12 minutes or until pasta is soft and cooked through. Drain and cool immediately.
c45a5423-3896-423c-ad75-c76ef22e3da5 Place the cooled noodles into the Non-Stick Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Lasagna Pan with Carrier and Hot Pad along with the tomatoes, cucumbers, salami, olives, mozzarella balls, basil, red onion and Italian dressing and mix until combined.
c45a5423-3896-423c-ad75-c76ef22e3da5 Chill before serving.
5913ee32-b366-496c-8ea4-78db2f045a13 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line three cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper Roll with SmartGrid®. Set aside.
5913ee32-b366-496c-8ea4-78db2f045a13 PREPARE and bake the sugar cookies as instructed. Remove from oven. Using a small circular cutter, or a knife. Carefully cut holes in the center of 12 of the cookies. Discard the scraps. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
5913ee32-b366-496c-8ea4-78db2f045a13 WHISK together powdered sugar, milk and lemon juice in a medium bowl. Whisk to to make an icing of spreading consistency. Transfer to a pastry bag. Set aside.
5913ee32-b366-496c-8ea4-78db2f045a13 PLACE 12 solid cookies on a sheet of Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®. Pipe a single line of icing around the edge of each cookie, then place a cookie with the center cut out on top. Gently press to secure into the icing. Fill each of the centers with Pop Rocks candy. Pipe a single line of icing around the edge of the filled cookie, then press another solid cookie on top. Use the remaining icing to decorate the finished cookies as desired.
95ae627a-8f26-4469-ab56-6f4a7884f790 Set grill to medium heat.
95ae627a-8f26-4469-ab56-6f4a7884f790 Clean and remove skin from shrimp (leaving tail on).
95ae627a-8f26-4469-ab56-6f4a7884f790 In plastic container or bag add shrimp, cilantro, lime juice, ground black pepper and sea salt, place in refrigerator and allow to marinate for minimum of 30 minutes (overnight will give the best flavor).
95ae627a-8f26-4469-ab56-6f4a7884f790 Place marinated shrimp on sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil, pour BBQ sauce over shrimp, fold aluminum foil up and fold over twice, fold each end. Leave enough room for air to circulate in packet.
95ae627a-8f26-4469-ab56-6f4a7884f790 Place packet on grill and allow to cook 6-8 minutes.
579218f7-a3dd-43ec-8920-f94c94dabeda Preheat oven or toaster oven to 400 degrees F. On a small sheet pan lined with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil, toss the tomatoes and garlic with 1 tablespoon of the olive oil.
579218f7-a3dd-43ec-8920-f94c94dabeda Add salt and pepper and toss to coat. Roast in oven for 15 minutes.
579218f7-a3dd-43ec-8920-f94c94dabeda Transfer the warm tomatoes to a serving platter.
579218f7-a3dd-43ec-8920-f94c94dabeda Drain the water from the burrata or mozzarella balls and add to the warm tomatoes.
579218f7-a3dd-43ec-8920-f94c94dabeda Drizzle with the olive oil and balsamic vinegar then season with the kosher salt and freshly ground pepper. Toss gently to coat if desired.
579218f7-a3dd-43ec-8920-f94c94dabeda Gently tear the basil leaves into smaller pieces and scatter over the salad and serve.
492710e6-61e2-4123-b291-91369a5a4797 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
492710e6-61e2-4123-b291-91369a5a4797 MELT the butter in a large pot over medium-high heat and add in the diced onions and lightly brown.
492710e6-61e2-4123-b291-91369a5a4797 SPRINKLE the flour on top of the onions and mix in to form a roux and cook for 3 minutes.
492710e6-61e2-4123-b291-91369a5a4797 POUR in the chicken stock and whisk over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes until it becomes very thick.
492710e6-61e2-4123-b291-91369a5a4797 ADD the sauce to a large bowl and mix it together with the 2 cups of shredded cheese, chopped cooked chicken breasts, broccoli florettes, cooked rice, sour cream, and salt and pepper until completely combined.
492710e6-61e2-4123-b291-91369a5a4797 TRANSFER the mixture into a Reynolds Kitchens® 13x9 Pasta & Casserole Pan and sprinkle on the remaining 1 cup of shredded cheese followed up by sprinkling the crushed corn flakes, completely covering the top.
492710e6-61e2-4123-b291-91369a5a4797 BAKE in the oven on 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the top begins to brown.
492710e6-61e2-4123-b291-91369a5a4797 SERVE hot.
b4941cdd-dfea-4061-ace3-b5d42b55b153 PREHEAT the oven to 375°.
b4941cdd-dfea-4061-ace3-b5d42b55b153 MIX together the ground beef, peppers, onions, egg, button mushrooms, soaked and squeezed French bread, and salt and pepper to taste.
b4941cdd-dfea-4061-ace3-b5d42b55b153 LINE each Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Non-Stick Mini-Loaf Pans with Parchment Lining with 5 strips of bacon.
b4941cdd-dfea-4061-ace3-b5d42b55b153 DIVIDE the ground meat mixture into 3 Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Non-Stick Mini-Loaf Pans with Parchment Lining.
b4941cdd-dfea-4061-ace3-b5d42b55b153 FOLD over the bacon so that it covers the meatloaves.
b4941cdd-dfea-4061-ace3-b5d42b55b153 BAKE them in the oven on 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until the tops become brown and the meatloaf is firm to the touch.
b4941cdd-dfea-4061-ace3-b5d42b55b153 WHISK together the ketchup, soy sauce and brown sugar until it’s combined and set aside.
b4941cdd-dfea-4061-ace3-b5d42b55b153 EASILY REMOVE the meatloaves from the pans and top off the tangy ketchup sauce.
b4941cdd-dfea-4061-ace3-b5d42b55b153 SERVE hot.
b3050b77-54b1-4aaa-a0fa-8fa84c87927d Preheat the oven to 400°.
b3050b77-54b1-4aaa-a0fa-8fa84c87927d Whisk together the butter, dill, capers, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a large bowl and set aside.
b3050b77-54b1-4aaa-a0fa-8fa84c87927d Season the swordfish in both sides with salt and pepper.
b3050b77-54b1-4aaa-a0fa-8fa84c87927d Place the swordfish on a Reynolds Kitchens® Bakeware Non-Stick fish pan.
b3050b77-54b1-4aaa-a0fa-8fa84c87927d Place 2 tablespoons of the herb butter on top of each swordfish fillet.
b3050b77-54b1-4aaa-a0fa-8fa84c87927d Bake in the oven at 400° for 16 to 18 minutes or until the swordfish is lightly browned on top and cooked throughout.
d4ab1bbe-2582-42e5-a748-ef13f0318012 PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
d4ab1bbe-2582-42e5-a748-ef13f0318012 WHISK together in a bowl the hoison sauce, ketchup, honey and soy sauce until combined and set aside.
d4ab1bbe-2582-42e5-a748-ef13f0318012 ADD the ribs to a large bowl and season by rubbing them with the Chinese 5-spice and salt and pepper.
d4ab1bbe-2582-42e5-a748-ef13f0318012 PLACE the ribs side by side in a Reynolds Kitchens® 10lb Roaster Pan, baste them with a small amount of the honey-hoison sauce and bake in the oven on 350° for 2 1/2 hours. They will become dark in color and the meat will easily pull away from the bone when they’re finished.
d4ab1bbe-2582-42e5-a748-ef13f0318012 BASTE the ribs every 20-25 minutes or until the sauce is gone.
d6ec7609-a390-4913-9c72-45ccf06405e1 CUT chicken breasts in half, lengthwise, to create 4 even portions.
d6ec7609-a390-4913-9c72-45ccf06405e1 PLACE chicken in a large bowl and marinate in milk for about 20 minutes.
d6ec7609-a390-4913-9c72-45ccf06405e1 MIX together flour, paprika, all-purpose spice, salt, and pepper in a medium sized bowl. Set aside.
d6ec7609-a390-4913-9c72-45ccf06405e1 PREHEAT oven to 400ºF.
d6ec7609-a390-4913-9c72-45ccf06405e1 MELT butter and pour into a Reynolds Kitchens® 10lb Roaster Pan, coating the bottom of the pan.
d6ec7609-a390-4913-9c72-45ccf06405e1 DIP each chicken breast, one at a time, in the flour mixture. COAT both sides liberally. PLACE in pan.
d6ec7609-a390-4913-9c72-45ccf06405e1 REPEAT with all four chicken breasts, making sure there is a small amount of room between each breast in the pan. This will allow them to crisp while baking.
d6ec7609-a390-4913-9c72-45ccf06405e1 BAKE at 400ºF for 35-40 minutes (or until the breading is golden brown and the juices run clear), flipping each breast after 20 minutes.
d6ec7609-a390-4913-9c72-45ccf06405e1 Remove from oven and transfer to a serving dish or serve directly from your Reynolds Kitchens® Roaster Pan! Garnish with parsley if desired. Enjoy!
9bae8be0-e3c5-456b-95f9-0cb4cffe9e69 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
9bae8be0-e3c5-456b-95f9-0cb4cffe9e69 Generously season tenderloin with salt and pepper. Set aside. In a small mixing bowl, whisk together mustard, brown sugar and thyme.
9bae8be0-e3c5-456b-95f9-0cb4cffe9e69 Place a large sheet of Reynolds Wrap®Aluminum Foil onto a baking sheet. Place onion slices in the center of the foil, in a single layer. Place pork over the onions and brush with 1/2 of the mustard mixture.
9bae8be0-e3c5-456b-95f9-0cb4cffe9e69 Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Bake for 40–45 minutes or until the internal temperature reads 130 degrees F.
9bae8be0-e3c5-456b-95f9-0cb4cffe9e69 Remove from oven. Open packet carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape. When uncovered, brush with remaining mustard mixture. Leaving the packet open, broil for about 1 minute or until a nice crust forms on top. Remove from the oven and allow tenderloin to rest for 10–15 minutes before slicing and serving
e999e251-b989-427f-9320-d751c307107f PRE-HEAT oven to 450F.
e999e251-b989-427f-9320-d751c307107f LINE two 10x15-inch baking sheets with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
e999e251-b989-427f-9320-d751c307107f DIVIDE sliced sweet potatoes among baking sheets ensuring potatoes are not stacked.
e999e251-b989-427f-9320-d751c307107f BRUSH both sides of sliced sweet potatoes with olive oil.
e999e251-b989-427f-9320-d751c307107f BAKE 13-14 minutes until edges are brown. Remove chips with crispy brown edges and continue baking other chips, checking constantly and removing as edges brown.
e999e251-b989-427f-9320-d751c307107f SPRINKLE with salt and serve in basket. Add fun flavorings your family loves, like BBQ spice rub or Parmesan cheese.
4e26923a-e7d6-4cac-986e-b57f172999a0 PREHEAT oven to 450°F or grill to medium-high. Cut chicken into bite–sized pieces. Combine chicken with remaining ingredients except tortilla chips.
4e26923a-e7d6-4cac-986e-b57f172999a0 CENTER one-fourth of chicken mixture on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil with non-stick (dull) side toward facing up.
4e26923a-e7d6-4cac-986e-b57f172999a0 BRING up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets.
4e26923a-e7d6-4cac-986e-b57f172999a0 BAKE 18 to 22 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven
4e26923a-e7d6-4cac-986e-b57f172999a0 OR GRILL 10 to 12 minutes in covered grill. Serve over tortilla chips.
19454200-1eae-4d10-80bd-5d4e858709b7 Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Set aside.
19454200-1eae-4d10-80bd-5d4e858709b7 Wrap each sweet potato cube with a bacon slice, holding in place with a toothpick. Place on the prepared baking sheet, toothpicks facing up.
19454200-1eae-4d10-80bd-5d4e858709b7 Combine the olive oil, melted butter, cinnamon and pepper, stirring until well mixed. Drizzle the mixture over the sweet potato bites. Sprinkle with sea salt. Loosely tent the toothpicks with damp paper towels and wrap the baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil, being careful not to pierce the foil. Bake until the potatoes are just tender, about 20 minutes.
19454200-1eae-4d10-80bd-5d4e858709b7 Remove the foil and paper towels and return to the oven; bake until the bacon is crispy and the fat starts to render, 15–20 more minutes. Blot the excess fat with the paper towels and then serve.
df13bedc-685c-4d9a-95b7-c4bc8343be37 Preheat your oven to 425 degrees F.
df13bedc-685c-4d9a-95b7-c4bc8343be37 In a large bowl, toss together the halved potatoes, olive oil, butter, garlic salt and freshly cracked black pepper.
df13bedc-685c-4d9a-95b7-c4bc8343be37 Tear 4 large sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil, each about 16 inches long. Divide the potato mixture evenly between the sheets of foil. Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Place the packets on a baking sheet and transfer to the oven. Cook for 25 minutes.
df13bedc-685c-4d9a-95b7-c4bc8343be37 Remove one packet from the oven. Open packet carefully by cutting along top fold with a sharp knife, allowing steam to escape; then open top of foil packet. Check to see if the potatoes are fully cooked and fork tender; if not, return to the oven for 5 more minutes.
df13bedc-685c-4d9a-95b7-c4bc8343be37 Once cooked, open up the packets and top each portion of potatoes with cheese and herbs. Let the cheese melt before serving. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
c5a61c6f-27f3-40f4-8bc0-35f8f9b06fec Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Line two 18x13x1-inch baking pans with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil.
c5a61c6f-27f3-40f4-8bc0-35f8f9b06fec Combine sea salt and paprika.
c5a61c6f-27f3-40f4-8bc0-35f8f9b06fec Cut the beets into very thin slices using a sharp knife or mandoline. Divide beets between each of the prepared pans. Drizzle each with oil then shake in the pan. Sprinkle with salt mixture and toss again.
c5a61c6f-27f3-40f4-8bc0-35f8f9b06fec Bake for 15 minutes, then flip and bake for another 15 minutes or until chips are crispy.
2d9721e6-ef47-451c-9e67-c25349ae8146 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Line an 18x13x1-inch baking pan with Reynolds Wrap® Aluminum Foil. Toss the oats, quinoa and flaxseed in the pan. Bake for 10 minutes. Turn the mixture and bake additional 10 minutes. Remove from oven and transfer oat mixture to a large bowl.
2d9721e6-ef47-451c-9e67-c25349ae8146 Line an 8x8x2-inch pan with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper.
2d9721e6-ef47-451c-9e67-c25349ae8146 Combine the peanut butter, honey and butter in saucepan. Cook on medium-low heat, stirring frequently for 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture starts to bubble. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips.
2d9721e6-ef47-451c-9e67-c25349ae8146 Pour the peanut butter mixture over the oat mixture. Fold to incorporate. Add the cherries and continue folding until fully incorporated.
2d9721e6-ef47-451c-9e67-c25349ae8146 Press the mixture firmly and evenly into prepared pan. Chill for 2 hours.
2d9721e6-ef47-451c-9e67-c25349ae8146 Cut into bars and store in an airtight container.
8f86e275-7ae6-4682-8975-ccb21cc241d1 HEAT oven to 350°F. Line 3 large cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper. In small bowl, mix cinnamon and sugar.
8f86e275-7ae6-4682-8975-ccb21cc241d1 SHAPE dough by 1/4 teaspoonfuls into balls. Roll balls in cinnamon-sugar mixture; place 1 inch apart on cookie sheets.
8f86e275-7ae6-4682-8975-ccb21cc241d1 BAKE 8 to 12 minutes or until cookies are golden brown and set. Cool 2 minutes; carefully slide parchment to cooling rack. Cool completely, about 10 minutes.
8f86e275-7ae6-4682-8975-ccb21cc241d1 MIX remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Add cooled cookies; stir gently to mix. Store in airtight container.
40731d4e-11b8-4305-9817-e7b45f9a0a86 COMBINE all ingredients in a large bowl. Using a rubber spatula, fold the mixture until fully combined.
40731d4e-11b8-4305-9817-e7b45f9a0a86 DIVIDE butter in half, and then transfer each to a sheet of Reynolds Kitchens® Unbleached Parchment Paper. Roll into a tube-like shape and twist each of the ends.
40731d4e-11b8-4305-9817-e7b45f9a0a86 REFRIGERATE until firm, about one hour.
81b9e4ca-518c-4910-954f-1c2076ca0d58 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper; set aside.
81b9e4ca-518c-4910-954f-1c2076ca0d58 STIR together banana, peanut butter, honey, milk, egg, and vanilla in a large bowl. In a small bowl combine oats, whole wheat flour, cinnamon, salt, and baking soda. Add oat mixture to banana mixture, stirring until combined. Stir in dried cherries and chocolate.
81b9e4ca-518c-4910-954f-1c2076ca0d58 DROP mounds of dough about 3 inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets using a 1/4-cup measure or scoop. Flatten and spread each mound of dough with damp hands until about 1/2-inch thick.
81b9e4ca-518c-4910-954f-1c2076ca0d58 BAKE 14 to 16 minutes or until light brown. Transfer the cookies on the parchment paper to a wire rack; cool completely.
aad7e7e6-feb2-4e35-87ea-9b1891cb188b PREHEAT the oven to 200°. Line an 18x13x1-inch rimmed baking pan with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid.
aad7e7e6-feb2-4e35-87ea-9b1891cb188b PLACE all ingredients in a blender. Blend until smooth. Pour mango mixture into the prepared pan. Tilt the pan or use a spatula to form a thin, even layer throughout the pan.
aad7e7e6-feb2-4e35-87ea-9b1891cb188b BAKE for 4 1/2 to 5 hours or until mixture is almost dehydrated with a leather-like texture and can be torn.
aad7e7e6-feb2-4e35-87ea-9b1891cb188b COOL completely. Cut fruit leather and the parchment paper into 2-inch strips and roll. Store in an airtight container.
e9078786-223b-4e48-9220-eca88a0c8675 PREHEAT the oven to 200°. Line an 18x13x1-inch rimmed baking pan with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid.
e9078786-223b-4e48-9220-eca88a0c8675 PLACE all ingredients in a blender. Blend until smooth. Pour blackberry mixture into the prepared pan. Tilt the pan or use a spatula to form a thin, even layer throughout the pan.
e9078786-223b-4e48-9220-eca88a0c8675 BAKE for 4 to 4 1/2 hours or until mixture is almost dehydrated with a leather-like texture and can be torn.
e9078786-223b-4e48-9220-eca88a0c8675 COOL completely. Cut fruit leather and the parchment paper into 2-inch strips and roll. Store in an airtight container.
834b7fff-70ad-4c33-8dfc-9a1400272ab6 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon salt; set aside.
834b7fff-70ad-4c33-8dfc-9a1400272ab6 BEAT butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds in a large mixing bowl. Gradually add sugar, about 1/4 cup at a time, beating on medium speed until well combined (3 to 4 minutes). Scrape the sides of the bowl; continue beating on medium speed for 2 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition (about 1 minute total). Beat in vanilla.
834b7fff-70ad-4c33-8dfc-9a1400272ab6 ADD the flour mixture and milk to the beaten mixture, alternating them and beating on low speed just until combined after each addition. Beat on medium to high speed for 20 seconds more. Spread batter evenly into a 9x13 Reynolds Kitchens® Dessert Pan.
834b7fff-70ad-4c33-8dfc-9a1400272ab6 BAKE 45 to 50 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool cake completely in the disposable bakeware pan on a wire rack. Top with Caramel Frosting and sprinkle with sea salt.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff PREHEAT the oven to 350°.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff CREAM the butter and sugar together in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed until it becomes light and fluffy.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff ADD in 1 egg at a time until it is completely mixed in.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff ADD the lemon juice, lemon zest and poppy seeds to the mixer and combine on low speed until mixed in.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff WHISK together the flour, baking soda and baking powder in a large bowl and set aside
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff WHISK together the sour cream and milk in a separate bowl and set aside.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff ALTERNATELY ADD the dry ingredients and wet ingredients to the mixer on low speed beginning with the dry and ending with the dry.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff DIVIDE the batter evenly into 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Loaf Pans with Parchment Lining.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff BAKE on 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until the top of the bread is golden brown and the center is firm.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff COOL before serving.
7d262df2-5a46-4901-afbf-65b2e18c06ff WHISK together the lemon juice and powdered sugar and drizzle over the cooled lemon poppy seed bread.
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Preheat the oven to 375°.
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Mix together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and cocoa powder in a bowl until combined and set aside
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Whip together the butter and peanut butter in a standing mixer with the paddle attachment on high speed until light and fluffy, about 3 to 4 minutes.
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Mix in the sugar and brown sugar on low speed until combined.
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Add in the egg and milk until they are mixed in.
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Pour the dry ingredients slowly into the bowl on low speed until it is completely mixed in.
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Form 24 balls from the cookie dough and place on 2 Reynolds Kitchens® Cookie Sheets with Parchment Lining.
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until the center of the cookies are slightly soft.
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Press 24 chocolate kisses into the center of each cookie as soon as it’s removed from the oven.
2b07fd67-750d-4151-aade-7866ff2c5352 Cool before serving.
d36dc22a-5962-4007-9f95-42914c4680e7 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line muffin pans with Reynolds Kitchens® Foil Baking Cups.
d36dc22a-5962-4007-9f95-42914c4680e7 STIR together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl. In a large mixing bowl, beat the butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Gradually add sugar, about 1/4 cup at a time, beating on medium speed until combined. Scrape sides of bowl; beat about 2 minutes more or until light and fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the vanilla. Alternately add the flour mixture and milk to the butter mixture, beating on low speed after each addition just until combined. Beat on medium to high speed for 20 seconds more.
d36dc22a-5962-4007-9f95-42914c4680e7 SPOON batter into prepared baking cups, filling each one-half to two-thirds full. Use the back of a spoon to smooth out batter in cups.
d36dc22a-5962-4007-9f95-42914c4680e7 BAKE about 18 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in centers comes out clean. Cool cupcakes in muffin pans on wire racks for 5 minutes. Remove cupcakes from muffin pans. Cool completely on wire racks.
d36dc22a-5962-4007-9f95-42914c4680e7 USE a small paring knife to remove a cone-shape piece of cupcake, going down only about one-third to one-half of the way into the cupcake. Fill each with 1 teaspoon preserves. Top with the removed portion of the cupcake, then with Raspberry Frosting and fresh raspberries.
3f4115c2-ac3c-4100-b949-2ebca6b54404 COMBINE flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl; set aside.
3f4115c2-ac3c-4100-b949-2ebca6b54404 BEAT butter and sugar with electric mixer until fluffy, about 3 minutes. Beat in egg yolks and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture and combine.
3f4115c2-ac3c-4100-b949-2ebca6b54404 WRAP dough in Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® and place in plastic slider bag; refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.
3f4115c2-ac3c-4100-b949-2ebca6b54404 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
3f4115c2-ac3c-4100-b949-2ebca6b54404 ROLL out dough 1/8-inch thick between 2 lightly floured sheets of parchment paper. CUT dough with 2 inch cookie cutters. PLACE dough on parchment-lined cookie sheets.
3f4115c2-ac3c-4100-b949-2ebca6b54404 BAKE 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned on edges. Slide Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® with cookies onto cooling rack; cool.
3f4115c2-ac3c-4100-b949-2ebca6b54404 DECORATE as desired. Store in airtight containers for up to 5 days.
0d51a6aa-adac-4f4b-abd7-4815fc130c96 PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
0d51a6aa-adac-4f4b-abd7-4815fc130c96 COMBINE flour, salt and baking soda in a medium bowl; set aside.
0d51a6aa-adac-4f4b-abd7-4815fc130c96 BEAT peanut butter, shortening and brown sugar in a large bowl on medium speed until well blended. Beat in milk, vanilla and egg just until blended.
0d51a6aa-adac-4f4b-abd7-4815fc130c96 REDUCE speed to low. Gradually add flour mixture, beating after each addition until well blended. Stir in chocolate chunks, peanuts and oats.
0d51a6aa-adac-4f4b-abd7-4815fc130c96 DROP by heaping tablespoons onto parchment-lined cookie sheets. Flatten each cookie slightly with the back of a spoon.
0d51a6aa-adac-4f4b-abd7-4815fc130c96 BAKE 9 to 11 minutes or until cookies are set and edges start to brown. Slide parchment with cookies onto a wire rack to cool.
89da8f1e-c4d3-45d9-9738-f0a8769dfd5d PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
89da8f1e-c4d3-45d9-9738-f0a8769dfd5d COMBINE flour, baking soda, and salt in a medium bowl; set aside.
89da8f1e-c4d3-45d9-9738-f0a8769dfd5d BEAT brown sugar, butter and sugar together in a large bowl on medium speed for about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Reduce speed to low. Gradually add flour mixture, beating after each addition until well blended. Stir in oats, chocolate chunks, nuts and cherries until well blended. Using SmartGrid® to measure, drop by rounded tablespoons 2 inches apart onto parchment-lined cookie sheets.
89da8f1e-c4d3-45d9-9738-f0a8769dfd5d BAKE 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Slide parchment paper with cookies onto a wire rack to cool.
89da8f1e-c4d3-45d9-9738-f0a8769dfd5d STIR together powdered sugar and water in a small bowl. Drizzle over cooled cookies on parchment paper.
8f975e07-7eea-42d9-a0c0-9bf10892c7ae Preheat oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
8f975e07-7eea-42d9-a0c0-9bf10892c7ae Combine flour, ground oats and baking soda in a medium bowl. Set aside. Beat butter with an electric mixer on medium speed for 45 to 60 seconds in an extra large mixing bowl. Add the sugar and brown sugar and beat mixture until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Beat in egg and vanilla extract until combined. Slowly fold in flour mixture in several batches. Stir in chocolate chips and white chocolate chips with a wooden spoon.
8f975e07-7eea-42d9-a0c0-9bf10892c7ae Place dough by rounded tablespoons, 2 inches apart, onto parchment lined cookie sheets. (About 15 cookies per baking sheet.)
8f975e07-7eea-42d9-a0c0-9bf10892c7ae Bake in center of oven for 10–12 minutes or until the edges are set. Place cookie sheet on cooling rack for 2 minutes to cool. Slide the parchment sheets with baked cookies onto wire racks and cool completely.
81d76f6d-6e8c-4e9f-ba0e-28dd01fd94e6 LINE two cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
81d76f6d-6e8c-4e9f-ba0e-28dd01fd94e6 STIR together flour, cocoa powder, and salt in a medium bowl; set aside. In a large bowl beat butter using an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add powdered sugar and hazelnut extract. Beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Beat in egg until combined. Beat in as much of the flour mixture as you can with the mixer. Using a wooden spoon, stir in any remaining flour mixture and the chocolate chips.
81d76f6d-6e8c-4e9f-ba0e-28dd01fd94e6 COVER and chill about 1 hour or until dough is easy to handle.
81d76f6d-6e8c-4e9f-ba0e-28dd01fd94e6 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place balls 2 inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets. Place a sheet of parchment paper over the dough balls. Using the bottom of a flat object like a drinking glass, measuring cup or mug, flatten balls into circles, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter. Remove top sheet of parchment paper; set aside.
81d76f6d-6e8c-4e9f-ba0e-28dd01fd94e6 BAKE 8 to 10 minutes or just until tops are firm. Transfer the cookies on the parchment paper to a wire rack; cool completely.
81d76f6d-6e8c-4e9f-ba0e-28dd01fd94e6 SPREAD a rounded teaspoon of the chocolate hazelnut spread onto flat side of half of the cookies. Top with the remaining cookies.
e4fc09b4-2bd9-473e-898b-b918be547646 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper, extending parchment paper about 1 inch above rim of pan; set aside.
e4fc09b4-2bd9-473e-898b-b918be547646 BEAT crust ingredients in a large bowl on low speed until mixture is crumbly; press mixture evenly in bottom parchment-lined pan.
e4fc09b4-2bd9-473e-898b-b918be547646 BAKE 20 minutes or until light brown; remove pan from oven.
e4fc09b4-2bd9-473e-898b-b918be547646 COMBINE filling ingredientsin a medium bowl until well blended; pour mixture evenly over warm baked crust.
e4fc09b4-2bd9-473e-898b-b918be547646 BAKE 15 to 20 minutes longer or until filling is set and bars are brown around the edges. Cool completely on a wire rack. Use edges of parchment lining to lift bars from pan onto a cutting board. Pull back edges of parchment; sprinkle with additional powdered sugar. Cut into bars.
17631781-cb72-4707-ac07-4f66706de3aa Heat oven to 350°F. Line cookie sheets with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®; set aside.
17631781-cb72-4707-ac07-4f66706de3aa Combine flour and baking soda. Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with mixer until light and fluffy. Add dry pudding mix; beat until blended. Add eggs and food coloring; mix well. Gradually add flour mixture, mixing well after each addition. Stir in chopped chocolate.
17631781-cb72-4707-ac07-4f66706de3aa Drop tablespoonsful of dough, 2 inches apart, onto parchment-covered baking sheets.
17631781-cb72-4707-ac07-4f66706de3aa Bake 10 to 12 min. or until edges of cookies are lightly browned. Cool on baking sheet 1 min. Remove to wire racks; cool completely.
cd129b64-4bfc-417c-9bad-a6e7a0c8c030 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line an 8x8x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid®. Set pan aside.
cd129b64-4bfc-417c-9bad-a6e7a0c8c030 STIR the butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and salt together in a medium bowl until thoroughly combined. Add eggs, egg yolk and vanilla. Whisk or beat rapidly together until ingredients are mixed and become a lighter color.
cd129b64-4bfc-417c-9bad-a6e7a0c8c030 ADD flour, cocoa powder, half of the chocolate chips, and half of the peanut butter chips. Stir gently until the dry ingredients are just combined, being careful not to over mix. Spread the batter in the parchment-lined pan. Sprinkle additional chocolate chips and peanut butter chips evenly over batter, if desired.
cd129b64-4bfc-417c-9bad-a6e7a0c8c030 BAKE 25 to 28 minutes or until the center of the brownies is set and the edges are firm. Cool brownies in pan for 10 minutes on a wire rack. Use a knife to loosen brownies from sides of pan not covered by parchment paper. Use ends of parchment paper to lift brownies from pan and transfer to a wire rack to cool completely. Cut into 12 squares.
c56a0a38-121d-4865-9e87-6c5d9c7cc173 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with Reynolds Kitchens® Parchment Paper with SmartGrid® and set aside.
c56a0a38-121d-4865-9e87-6c5d9c7cc173 Whisk together flour, kosher salt, baking powder and baking soda in a large bowl; set aside. Mix butter, light brown sugar and granulated sugar together with an electric mixer until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
c56a0a38-121d-4865-9e87-6c5d9c7cc173 Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing well between each egg. Add vanilla and beat until incorporated. Slowly add flour mixture, mixing gently until ingredients are just incorporated. Fold in caramel-filled chocolate candies and chocolate chips.
c56a0a38-121d-4865-9e87-6c5d9c7cc173 Roll 2 tablespoons of dough into a ball, covering any candies with dough so they are not exposed.
c56a0a38-121d-4865-9e87-6c5d9c7cc173 Place dough balls on Reynolds Kitchens® Cookie Sheet with parchment lining. Bake cookies for 10–12 minutes. Cool cookies for 5 minutes on baking sheet and then transfer parchment paper with cookies onto wire racks to cool completely.
c56a0a38-121d-4865-9e87-6c5d9c7cc173 Drizzle cooled cookies with melted chocolate and sprinkle with sea salt. Chill cookies until chocolate is set.
7121be88-a16f-42e1-8698-91649e7edb0b Preheat the oven to 350˚F. In a large skillet on medium heat, brown your beef. When there is no pink, add 4 tablespoons taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water, and cook for an additional 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
7121be88-a16f-42e1-8698-91649e7edb0b Tear off four 16-inch-long pieces of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Place a handful of tortilla chips in the center of the sheet, top with a heaping 1/4 cup Mexican cheese, then cover with 1/4 of the ground beef mixture followed by another 1/4 cup of cheese. Bring up and double-fold the long ends, leaving room for air to circulate. Bring up and double-fold the short ends to close your foil packet.
7121be88-a16f-42e1-8698-91649e7edb0b Just before serving, place on a baking sheet and bake at 350˚F for 10 minutes. Prep all of your toppings so they are ready to serve over hot nachos. Open the foil packs, add desired toppings and serve immediately.
54f6d5bb-8da6-42d5-861d-59fcc5b8bda4 In a large bowl, combine oats, dark chocolate chips, chocolate chips, coconut flakes, almonds, cranberries, peanut butter and honey until incorporated.
54f6d5bb-8da6-42d5-861d-59fcc5b8bda4 Line a 9-by-13-inch pan with Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Spread the mixture evenly in the pan and press down firmly. Freeze for 30 minutes until the bars are firm and cut into rectangles.
bbd61152-4cb8-4e93-80cb-c5f31a124714 Mix together ingredients for the marinade, and in a food-safe bowl mix the marinade with the chicken wings. Set in the fridge to marinate for at least 5 hours, but ideally overnight.
bbd61152-4cb8-4e93-80cb-c5f31a124714 Take chicken wings out of the fridge and discard extra marinade. Taking a large sheet of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil, wrap 5–8 chicken wings inside.
bbd61152-4cb8-4e93-80cb-c5f31a124714 Preheat your smoker to 300° F on two-zone indirect cooking. Set the foil-wrapped chicken on the cool side of the grill to cook for 30 minutes or until 165° F internal.
bbd61152-4cb8-4e93-80cb-c5f31a124714 While the chicken is cooking, preheat a skillet for the chili lime sauce. Add oil to skillet and garlic paste. Let garlic brown (about 1–2 minutes). Add the rest of the ingredients for the sauce to the skillet and let simmer over the heat for 7–8 minutes or until thickened.
bbd61152-4cb8-4e93-80cb-c5f31a124714 Pull chicken out of foil and place in a food-safe bowl. Add chili lime sauce on top of the chicken and toss. Take tossed chicken and place on the hot side of the grill to cook for 1 minute per side.
bbd61152-4cb8-4e93-80cb-c5f31a124714 Once done, pull off, top with chopped cilantro and enjoy!
6bb04813-4495-439f-b097-346161cf64bb Juice and zest two lemons, removing seeds. Whisk in a small bowl with the butter, olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper.
6bb04813-4495-439f-b097-346161cf64bb Place the shrimp in a large bowl. Pour in 2/3 of the lemon garlic butter sauce. Stir gently to coat.
6bb04813-4495-439f-b097-346161cf64bb Trim about one inch from the woody ends of the asparagus and discard. Cut the remaining asparagus spears into 2-inch pieces. Place in another large bowl. Add the remaining sauce and toss gently.
6bb04813-4495-439f-b097-346161cf64bb Heat the grill to medium-high. Add two large sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum foil on top of the grill grates.
6bb04813-4495-439f-b097-346161cf64bb Pour the shrimp and asparagus onto the foil. Spread into a single layer. Save the asparagus bowl.
6bb04813-4495-439f-b097-346161cf64bb Grill, turning occasionally for 6–8 minutes or until the shrimp are pink and the asparagus is slightly tender.
6bb04813-4495-439f-b097-346161cf64bb Place in the asparagus bowl. Toss to combine. Serve with cooked rice.
c5f5f5b2-0c41-4d9b-8832-fdfca0d6e70a Set up your grill (charcoal or gas) for direct grilling and heat to medium-high (400° F), leaving 1/3 fire-free as a safety zone.
c5f5f5b2-0c41-4d9b-8832-fdfca0d6e70a Put half the steak in a single layer in the center of a 16-inch-long piece of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Aluminum Foil. Top with half the peppers, mushrooms and onions. Season with salt and pepper. Place 1 tablespoon of butter on top of the meat and vegetables. Repeat for the remaining package.
c5f5f5b2-0c41-4d9b-8832-fdfca0d6e70a Bring the long edges of the foil together and fold twice. Fold the short edges to completely enclose the meat and vegetables. Repeat for the remaining package. Transfer each foil packet to a rimmed baking sheet. Lightly butter the cut sides of the baguette or rolls with the remaining butter. Set aside.
c5f5f5b2-0c41-4d9b-8832-fdfca0d6e70a Arrange the foil packets, seam-side up, on the grill grate over direct heat. Grill for 6 minutes. Protect your hands with grill gloves, then using tongs, turn the packets over and grill for 2 minutes more. Move the packets to the safety zone, seam side up. Carefully open the packets to reveal the meat and vegetables. (The emerging steam will be very hot.)
c5f5f5b2-0c41-4d9b-8832-fdfca0d6e70a Top each with half the provolone, overlapping the slices. (There is no need to reseal the packets.) Cover the grill with the lid for 1 to 2 minutes to melt the cheese. Remove the lid, then grill the bread, cut sides down, 30 seconds to 1 minute. (The bread will toast quickly, so watch carefully.) Transfer the foil packets and the grilled bread to a rimmed baking sheet.
c5f5f5b2-0c41-4d9b-8832-fdfca0d6e70a Using a wide spatula, carefully transfer the meat, vegetables, and cheese from each foil packet to the bottom side of a baguette. Serve immediately.
9ffd97a1-1fcb-491f-8086-7a89346640a4 Set up your grill for direct grilling and preheat to medium-high (400° F).
9ffd97a1-1fcb-491f-8086-7a89346640a4 Arrange a 16-inch piece of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil Extra Wide on a flat surface. Place a corn tortilla in the center. Put a 1/2 cup mound of refried beans in the center of the tortilla and spread to within 1/2 inch of the edge of the tortilla with the back of a spoon, building up the sides slightly. Make a shallow depression in the center to hold the egg. Carefully break the egg into the depression. Season with salt and pepper.
9ffd97a1-1fcb-491f-8086-7a89346640a4 Bring the long edges of the foil together. Fold twice, making sure the foil doesn’t touch the top of the egg. Fold the short edges to completely enclose the egg and tortilla. Repeat for the remaining package. Carefully transfer each foil packet to a rimmed baking sheet. (Do not tilt, as you want the egg to remain contained in the depression you made in the beans).
9ffd97a1-1fcb-491f-8086-7a89346640a4 Transfer the foil packets to the grill grate — again, keeping them level. Grill for 13 to 15 minutes, or until the whites of the eggs are set and the yolks are still runny. Carefully open the packets to check on the eggs’ doneness, avoiding any escaping steam. When the eggs are cooked to your liking, remove the packets from the grill. Sprinkle each egg with half of the cheese, scallions, and bacon. (The residual heat will melt the cheese). Add a spoonful of pico de gallo and a dollop of sour cream. Garnish each egg with a sprig of fresh cilantro if desired.
383f6d47-92c8-48f7-a4a1-3761f1be1b8c Place the wings in a large bowl and sprinkle all over with sea salt and pepper. In a large measuring cup, whisk together the oil, lemon juice, zest, garlic, salt and pepper.
383f6d47-92c8-48f7-a4a1-3761f1be1b8c Pour about 3/4 of this mixture over the wings and toss to coat. Save the remaining marinade for after grilling. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and marinate for 1–2 hours.
383f6d47-92c8-48f7-a4a1-3761f1be1b8c Divide the wings between two 16-inch sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil to create foil packets. Discarding excess marinade, place with wings in the center of each foil sheet. Wrap and seal the foil packets tightly on the long and short ends.
383f6d47-92c8-48f7-a4a1-3761f1be1b8c Heat your grill to high heat, place both foil packets on the grill, and grill for a total of 20–25 minutes, turning once midway. Before serving, stir the parsley into the remaining lemon-garlic mixture and drizzle over the wings to serve. Enjoy!
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Preheat grill to medium-high heat to approximately 450° F.
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 In a medium mixing bowl, combine olive oil, lime juice and taco seasoning. Mix well. Add the chicken breasts, tossing to fully coat each breast. Set aside to marinate while you prep the vegetables.
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Combine the cauliflower rice with the salsa, diced green chiles and garlic powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. (I used 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of black pepper. Season to your taste/dietary preference.)
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Lay each piece of Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil side by side on the counter. Spray each with nonstick cooking spray.
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Divide the cauliflower rice, black beans, corn and bell pepper slices to the center of each piece of foil. Place a chicken breast on top of each.
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Bring the ends of each foil packet up, lengthwise, and fold them down together 2 times. Leave room for the food to steam and ventilate. Do the same with the ends.
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Place the packets on the grill, vegetable side down, to cook for 10 minutes. Carefully flip and cook for an additional 10–15 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through.
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Check doneness by inserting a meat thermometer into the thickest part of the chicken. Temperature should read 165° F.
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Carefully remove the foil packets from the grill and place them onto a small sheet pan. Give them 1–2 minutes to cool to safely touch.
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Open each foil packet and sprinkle with shredded Mexican cheese. Leaving the packets open, place the sheet pan onto the grill. Cook for 2–3 additional minutes, or until the cheese has melted.
c4610283-97cc-4c00-b510-e2d167152338 Serve garnished with Greek yogurt (or sour cream), freshly chopped cilantro, avocado, jalapeno slices and a lime wedge.
0b39f9d3-719e-40cb-952e-8f0b66470edf
0b39f9d3-719e-40cb-952e-8f0b66470edf
0b39f9d3-719e-40cb-952e-8f0b66470edf In a medium mixing bowl, whisk together all sauce ingredients. Place cubed chicken in a bowl and then pour half of the Hawaiian-style sauce over top and toss to evenly coat.
0b39f9d3-719e-40cb-952e-8f0b66470edf Tear off four sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil, each 16 inches long. Place foil on a baking sheet. Place food in the center of the dull side of each foil sheet to prevent sticking.
0b39f9d3-719e-40cb-952e-8f0b66470edf Place pineapple, red and green bell peppers, and chicken with sauce divided evenly between the four sheets of foil. Season each foil packet evenly with additional garlic pepper, salt and seasoning of your choice.
0b39f9d3-719e-40cb-952e-8f0b66470edf Now evenly pour the remaining Hawaiian-style sauce over top of each foil packet. Bring up the long sides of the foil, so the ends meet over the food. Double-fold the ends, leaving room for heat to circulate inside.
0b39f9d3-719e-40cb-952e-8f0b66470edf Double-fold the two short ends to seal the packet. Fold the foil around the ingredients like a present.
0b39f9d3-719e-40cb-952e-8f0b66470edf Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is done. Carefully open one of the packets and test for doneness. Serve hot with rice if desired. Enjoy!
982c0d6c-215d-4361-ad2d-673b084660a0 Heat the grill to medium heat, about 350° F degrees.
982c0d6c-215d-4361-ad2d-673b084660a0 Tear off two sheets of Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil. They should be about 1 inch larger than your fillet on all sides. Making sure the dull (non-stick) side is up, fold the edges up to form a rim all the way around.
982c0d6c-215d-4361-ad2d-673b084660a0 Place a salmon fillet on each piece of foil.
982c0d6c-215d-4361-ad2d-673b084660a0 Drizzle olive oil on each fillet. Cut the lemon and tangerine in half. Using just one half, squeeze juice over each fillet. Sprinkle it with salt and pepper.
982c0d6c-215d-4361-ad2d-673b084660a0 Cut the rest of the citrus into slices. Layer along the salmon.
982c0d6c-215d-4361-ad2d-673b084660a0 Roughly chop the fresh herbs and add alongside the citrus. Sprinkle the nuts next to those.
982c0d6c-215d-4361-ad2d-673b084660a0 Place the salmon-topped foil onto the grill. Cook for 10 minutes, or until the internal temperature in the thickest part reaches 145° F degrees.
982c0d6c-215d-4361-ad2d-673b084660a0 Remove from the grill. For added flavor, you can drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with a pinch of cayenne and flake sea salt.
58fe2901-9707-45e7-9161-b5d39f947663 Preheat the oven to 400ºF.
58fe2901-9707-45e7-9161-b5d39f947663 Take the tofu out of the package and drain well. Gently wrap the tofu in paper towel and place on a plate. Leave for 15 minutes.
58fe2901-9707-45e7-9161-b5d39f947663 Slice the tofu into bite size cubes and place them in a bowl. Drizzle with 1 tablespoon oil, and gently fold using a spatula. Season with salt and pepper and sprinkle 1 tablespoon cornstarch on top. Gently fold again to ensure all the pieces are coated.
58fe2901-9707-45e7-9161-b5d39f947663 Cover a baking sheet with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil, including the edges.
58fe2901-9707-45e7-9161-b5d39f947663 Place the tofu cubes on the Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil and bake in the oven in the middle rack for 15 minutes.
58fe2901-9707-45e7-9161-b5d39f947663 Take the tray out and flip the tofu. Return in the oven for an additional 15 minutes.
58fe2901-9707-45e7-9161-b5d39f947663 Meanwhile, whisk the water, soy sauce, salt, sugar, cornstarch mix, and peppercorns, and set aside.
58fe2901-9707-45e7-9161-b5d39f947663 In a small pan, add 1 tablespoon oil, garlic, and shallots. Cook on medium low for 3-4 minutes, until shallots are tender. Whisk the bowl with the sauce ingredients and slowly pour the mixture in the pan, while stirring constantly. The sauce is ready when it bubbles and thickens. Turn the heat off and set aside.
58fe2901-9707-45e7-9161-b5d39f947663 Take the tofu out of the oven and transfer the tofu cubes to a serving bowl. Pour the black pepper sauce on top and top with chopped scallions.
6b844f9e-e947-491c-a3dc-7ac727fe7f4a Preheat oven to 325°F. Line a roasting pan that is at least 2 inches deep with Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil.
6b844f9e-e947-491c-a3dc-7ac727fe7f4a Remove neck and giblets from turkey; rinse and pat turkey dry. Place turkey in foil lined roasting pan. If desired loosely stuff turkey. Brush turkey with oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
6b844f9e-e947-491c-a3dc-7ac727fe7f4a Make a foil tent by placing a sheet of foil over the turkey, leaving 1 inch between top of turkey and foil test for heat circulation. Crimp foil onto long sides of pan.
6b844f9e-e947-491c-a3dc-7ac727fe7f4a Roast turkey for one hour. Meanwhile, place butter, brown sugar and corn syrup in a saucepan. Cook, stirring often until combined and smooth. Reserve 3 tablespoons of glaze for later use. Carefully remove foil tent and baste the turkey in the glaze. Return foil tent and continue roasting, basting every 30 minutes or until meat thermometer reads at least 165°F in the breast and thickest part of the thigh not touching the bone, about 3 to 3 1/2 hours for a 14 lb. unstuffed turkey.
6b844f9e-e947-491c-a3dc-7ac727fe7f4a Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes. Remove and discard foil.
6b844f9e-e947-491c-a3dc-7ac727fe7f4a Toss reserved glaze with pecans. Transfer to a foil-lined baking sheet. Cook at 325F for 8-10 minutes or until fragrant and crisp. Let pecans cool completely.
6b844f9e-e947-491c-a3dc-7ac727fe7f4a Transfer turkey to a serving dish. Affix candied pecans to the breast section of the turkey. Chop remaining candied pecans and sprinkle over legs and wings. Dress the plate with fresh herbs and mashed sweet potatoes just before serving.
33d90267-3892-4f6c-8c4d-ab88daa9d927 PREHEAT oven to 350°F. Line an 8x8x2-inch square baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper. To line pan: turn pan upside down and press a sheet of parchment paper around it. Remove parchment paper, flip pan over and drop parchment paper inside. Crimp the edges and you're ready to cook!
33d90267-3892-4f6c-8c4d-ab88daa9d927 WHISK together all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, and allspice in a medium bowl. Set aside.
33d90267-3892-4f6c-8c4d-ab88daa9d927 CREAM the sugar and butter with an electric mixer on medium speed in a medium bowl about 2 minutes or until light and fluffy. Add egg; beat to combine. Beat in applesauce and vanilla. Reduce speed to low and gradually add in the flour mixture. Stir in apple and the peanut butter pieces. Spread into prepared pan.
33d90267-3892-4f6c-8c4d-ab88daa9d927 BAKE 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
33d90267-3892-4f6c-8c4d-ab88daa9d927 REMOVE from oven and cool 5 minutes in the pan. Lift the cake out of the pan using the parchment paper. Place on a wire rack to cool completely. Using the parchment paper, transfer thecaketo a cutting board.
33d90267-3892-4f6c-8c4d-ab88daa9d927 DRIZZLE with Peanut Butter Glaze. Allow cake to stand until glaze is set before slicing.
aea12b28-9460-498e-abd2-2d5d4f7259c1 PREHEAT oven to 325°F. Do not exceed 400°F. Add flour to a Reynolds® Large Oven Bag. Shake. Place bag in a roasting pan at least 2 inches deep.
aea12b28-9460-498e-abd2-2d5d4f7259c1 PLACE carrots, broth, shallots, soy sauce, ginger, honey, and garlic in bag. Gently squeeze to blend. Add meat to bag.
aea12b28-9460-498e-abd2-2d5d4f7259c1 CLOSE bag with tie (found inside package). Holding the bag upright, cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag to allow steam to escape. Tuck ends of bag in pan.
aea12b28-9460-498e-abd2-2d5d4f7259c1 PLACE pan in oven, allowing room for bag to expand during cooking without touching heating elements, wall, or racks. Bag should not hang over pan.
aea12b28-9460-498e-abd2-2d5d4f7259c1 BAKE about 2 1/2 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
aea12b28-9460-498e-abd2-2d5d4f7259c1 CUT open top of oven bag carefully. Remember: Always support bag with pan.
aea12b28-9460-498e-abd2-2d5d4f7259c1 SERVE roast, vegetables, and cooking liquid over hot cooked rice. Garnish with green onions and/or sesame seeds, if desired.
d0ee8b35-e031-4c26-bca3-3c898d8eb5a7 PREHEAT oven to 375°F. Place Reynolds® Oven Bag, Large Size in 13x9x2-inch baking dish with opening towards wide side of dish; set aside.
d0ee8b35-e031-4c26-bca3-3c898d8eb5a7 BLEND all ingredients except mushrooms in a food processor or blender. Pour mixture into oven bag.
d0ee8b35-e031-4c26-bca3-3c898d8eb5a7 PLACE mushrooms in oven bag.
d0ee8b35-e031-4c26-bca3-3c898d8eb5a7 CLOSE oven bag with nylon tie. Turn bag to coat mushrooms in sauce. Arrange mushrooms evenly with top sides facing up. Cut six 1/2-inch slits in bag; tuck ends of bag in dish.
d0ee8b35-e031-4c26-bca3-3c898d8eb5a7 BAKE to minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
